var P_HTM = [];
P_HTM[1]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa* **";
P_HTM[2]="*Majjhimanikāyo* **";
P_HTM[3]="*Majjhimapaṇṇāsapāḷi* **";
P_HTM[4]="*5. Brāhmaṇavaggo* **";
P_HTM[5]="*51. Kandarakasutta**With Kandaraka*";
P_HTM[6]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Campā on the banks of the Gaggarā Lotus Pond together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[8]="*Atha kho pesso ca hatthārohaputto kandarako ca paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā pesso hatthārohaputto bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Then Pessa the elephant driver’s son and Kandaraka the wanderer went to see the Buddha. When they had approached, Pessa bowed and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[9]="*Kandarako pana paribbājako bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**But the wanderer Kandaraka exchanged greetings with the Buddha and stood to one side.*";
P_HTM[10]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho kandarako paribbājako tuṇhībhūtaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ anuviloketvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**He looked around the mendicant Saṅgha, who were so very silent, and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[11]="*“acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama.**“It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[12]="*Yāvañcidaṃ bhotā gotamena sammā bhikkhusaṃgho paṭipādito.**How the mendicant Saṅgha has been led to practice properly by Master Gotama!*";
P_HTM[13]="*Yepi te, bho gotama, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā tepi bhagavanto etaparamaṃyeva sammā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paṭipādesuṃ—**All the perfected ones, the fully awakened Buddhas in the past or the future who lead the mendicant Saṅgha to practice properly will at best do so*";
P_HTM[14]="*seyyathāpi etarahi bhotā gotamena sammā bhikkhusaṃgho paṭipādito.**like Master Gotama does in the present.”*";
P_HTM[15]="*Yepi te, bho gotama, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā tepi bhagavanto etaparamaṃyeva sammā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paṭipādessanti—* **";
P_HTM[16]="*seyyathāpi etarahi bhotā gotamena sammā bhikkhusaṃgho paṭipādito”ti.* **";
P_HTM[17]="*“Evametaṃ, kandaraka, evametaṃ, kandaraka.**“That’s so true, Kandaraka! That’s so true!*";
P_HTM[18]="*Yepi te, kandaraka, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā tepi bhagavanto etaparamaṃyeva sammā bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṭipādesuṃ—**All the perfected ones, the fully awakened Buddhas in the past or the future who lead the mendicant Saṅgha to practice properly will at best do so*";
P_HTM[19]="*seyyathāpi etarahi mayā sammā bhikkhusaṅgho paṭipādito.**like I do in the present.*";
P_HTM[20]="*Yepi te, kandaraka, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā tepi bhagavanto etaparamaṃyeva sammā bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṭipādessanti—* **";
P_HTM[21]="*seyyathāpi etarahi mayā sammā bhikkhusaṅgho paṭipādito.* **";
P_HTM[22]="*Santi hi, kandaraka, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṃghe arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā.**For in this mendicant Saṅgha there are perfected mendicants, who have ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment.*";
P_HTM[23]="*Santi hi, kandaraka, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṃghe sekkhā santatasīlā santatavuttino nipakā nipakavuttino;**And in this mendicant Saṅgha there are trainee mendicants who are consistently ethical, living consistently, alert, living alertly.*";
P_HTM[24]="*te catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittā viharanti.**They meditate with their minds firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[25]="*Katamesu catūsu?**What four?*";
P_HTM[26]="*Idha, kandaraka, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[27]="*vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**They meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[28]="*citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**They meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[29]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassan”ti.**They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.”*";
P_HTM[30]="*Evaṃ vutte, pesso hatthārohaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Pessa said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[31]="*“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[32]="*Yāva supaññattā cime, bhante, bhagavatā cattāro satipaṭṭhānā sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya.**how much the Buddha has clearly described the four kinds of mindfulness meditation! They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[33]="*Mayampi hi, bhante, gihī odātavasanā kālena kālaṃ imesu catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittā viharāma.**For we white-clothed laypeople also from time to time meditate with our minds well established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[34]="*Idha mayaṃ, bhante, kāye kāyānupassino viharāma ātāpino sampajānā satimanto, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**We meditate observing an aspect of the body …*";
P_HTM[35]="*vedanāsu vedanānupassino viharāma ātāpino sampajānā satimanto, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**feelings …*";
P_HTM[36]="*citte cittānupassino viharāma ātāpino sampajānā satimanto, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**mind …*";
P_HTM[37]="*dhammesu dhammānupassino viharāma ātāpino sampajānā satimanto, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[38]="*Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[39]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bhante, bhagavā evaṃ manussagahane evaṃ manussakasaṭe evaṃ manussasāṭheyye vattamāne sattānaṃ hitāhitaṃ jānāti.**How the Buddha knows what’s best for sentient beings, even though people continue to be so shady, rotten, and tricky.*";
P_HTM[40]="*Gahanañhetaṃ, bhante, yadidaṃ manussā;**For human beings are shady, sir,*";
P_HTM[41]="*uttānakañhetaṃ, bhante, yadidaṃ pasavo.**while the animal is obvious.*";
P_HTM[42]="*Ahañhi, bhante, pahomi hatthidammaṃ sāretuṃ.**For I can drive an elephant in training,*";
P_HTM[43]="*Yāvatakena antarena campaṃ gatāgataṃ karissati sabbāni tāni sāṭheyyāni kūṭeyyāni vaṅkeyyāni jimheyyāni pātukarissati.**and while going back and forth in Campā it’ll try all the tricks, bluffs, ruses, and feints that it can.*";
P_HTM[44]="*Amhākaṃ pana, bhante, dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā aññathāva kāyena samudācaranti aññathāva vācāya aññathāva nesaṃ cittaṃ hoti.**But my bondservants, employees, and workers behave one way by body, another by speech, and their minds another.*";
P_HTM[45]="*Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[46]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bhante, bhagavā evaṃ manussagahane evaṃ manussakasaṭe evaṃ manussasāṭheyye vattamāne sattānaṃ hitāhitaṃ jānāti.**How the Buddha knows what’s best for sentient beings, even though people continue to be so shady, rotten, and tricky.*";
P_HTM[47]="*Gahanañhetaṃ, bhante, yadidaṃ manussā;**For human beings are shady, sir,*";
P_HTM[48]="*uttānakañhetaṃ, bhante, yadidaṃ pasavo”ti.**while the animal is obvious.”*";
P_HTM[49]="*“Evametaṃ, pessa, evametaṃ, pessa.**“That’s so true, Pessa! That’s so true!*";
P_HTM[50]="*Gahanañhetaṃ, pessa, yadidaṃ manussā;**For human beings are shady,*";
P_HTM[51]="*uttānakañhetaṃ, pessa, yadidaṃ pasavo.**while the animal is obvious.*";
P_HTM[52]="*Cattārome, pessa, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**Pessa, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[53]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[54]="*Idha, pessa, ekacco puggalo attantapo hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;**One person mortifies themselves, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves.*";
P_HTM[55]="*idha pana, pessa, ekacco puggalo parantapo hoti paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;**One person mortifies others, committed to the practice of mortifying others.*";
P_HTM[56]="*idha pana, pessa, ekacco puggalo attantapo ca hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;**One person mortifies themselves and others, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[57]="*idha pana, pessa, ekacco puggalo nevattantapo hoti nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person doesn’t mortify either themselves or others, committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others.*";
P_HTM[58]="*So anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati.**They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.*";
P_HTM[59]="*Imesaṃ, pessa, catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ katamo te puggalo cittaṃ ārādhetī”ti?**Which one of these four people do you like the sound of?”*";
P_HTM[60]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, ayaṃ me puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.**“Sir, I don’t like the sound of the first three people.*";
P_HTM[61]="*Yopāyaṃ, bhante, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, ayampi me puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[62]="*Yopāyaṃ, bhante, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, ayampi me puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.* **";
P_HTM[63]="*Yo ca kho ayaṃ, bhante, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati—* **";
P_HTM[64]="*ayameva me puggalo cittaṃ ārādhetī”ti.**I only like the sound of the last person, who doesn’t mortify either themselves or others.”*";
P_HTM[65]="*“Kasmā pana te, pessa, ime tayo puggalā cittaṃ nārādhentī”ti?**“But why don’t you like the sound of those three people?”*";
P_HTM[66]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so attānaṃ sukhakāmaṃ dukkhapaṭikkūlaṃ ātāpeti paritāpeti—**“Sir, the person who mortifies themselves does so even though they want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[67]="*iminā me ayaṃ puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.**That’s why I don’t like the sound of that person.*";
P_HTM[68]="*Yopāyaṃ, bhante, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so paraṃ sukhakāmaṃ dukkhapaṭikkūlaṃ ātāpeti paritāpeti—**The person who mortifies others does so even though others want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[69]="*iminā me ayaṃ puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.**That’s why I don’t like the sound of that person.*";
P_HTM[70]="*Yopāyaṃ, bhante, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so attānañca parañca sukhakāmaṃ dukkhapaṭikkūlaṃ ātāpeti paritāpeti—**The person who mortifies themselves and others does so even though both themselves and others want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[71]="*iminā me ayaṃ puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.**That’s why I don’t like the sound of that person.*";
P_HTM[72]="*Yo ca kho ayaṃ, bhante, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati;**The person who doesn’t mortify either themselves or others—living without wishes, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves—does not torment themselves or others, both of whom want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[73]="*so attānañca parañca sukhakāmaṃ dukkhapaṭikkūlaṃ neva ātāpeti na paritāpeti—* **";
P_HTM[74]="*iminā me ayaṃ puggalo cittaṃ ārādheti.**That’s why I like the sound of that person.*";
P_HTM[75]="*Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante, gacchāma;**Well, now, sir, I must go.*";
P_HTM[76]="*bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[77]="*“Yassadāni tvaṃ, pessa, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, Pessa, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[78]="*Atha kho pesso hatthārohaputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**And then Pessa the elephant driver’s son approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[79]="*Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkante pesse hatthārohaputte bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then, not long after he had left, the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[80]="*“paṇḍito, bhikkhave, pesso hatthārohaputto;**“Mendicants, Pessa the elephant driver’s son is astute.*";
P_HTM[81]="*mahāpañño, bhikkhave, pesso hatthārohaputto.**He has great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[82]="*Sace, bhikkhave, pesso hatthārohaputto muhuttaṃ nisīdeyya yāvassāhaṃ ime cattāro puggale vitthārena vibhajissāmi, mahatā atthena saṃyutto abhavissa.**If he had sat here a little longer so that I could have analyzed these four people in detail, he would have greatly benefited.*";
P_HTM[83]="*Api ca, bhikkhave, ettāvatāpi pesso hatthārohaputto mahatā atthena saṃyutto”ti.**Still, even with this much he has already greatly benefited.”*";
P_HTM[84]="*“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo, etassa, sugata, kālo,**“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One!*";
P_HTM[85]="*yaṃ bhagavā ime cattāro puggale vitthārena vibhajeyya. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**May the Buddha analyze these four people in detail. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[86]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[87]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[88]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[89]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto? Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo acelako hoti muttācāro hatthāpalekhano naehibhaddantiko natiṭṭhabhaddantiko; nābhihaṭaṃ na uddissakataṃ na nimantanaṃ sādiyati;**“And what person mortifies themselves, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves? It’s when someone goes naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food prepared for them, or an invitation for a meal.*";
P_HTM[90]="*so na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti na eḷakamantaraṃ na daṇḍamantaraṃ na musalamantaraṃ na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ na gabbhiniyā na pāyamānāya na purisantaragatāya na saṅkittīsu na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī; na macchaṃ na maṃsaṃ na suraṃ na merayaṃ na thusodakaṃ pivati.**They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer.*";
P_HTM[91]="*So ekāgāriko vā hoti ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā hoti dvālopiko … pe … sattāgāriko vā hoti sattālopiko;**They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls.*";
P_HTM[92]="*ekissāpi dattiyā yāpeti, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpeti … pe … sattahipi dattīhi yāpeti;**They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day.*";
P_HTM[93]="*ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti … pe … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti—iti evarūpaṃ aḍḍhamāsikaṃ pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even up to once a fortnight. They live committed to the practice of eating food at set intervals.*";
P_HTM[94]="*So sākabhakkho vā hoti, sāmākabhakkho vā hoti, nīvārabhakkho vā hoti, daddulabhakkho vā hoti, haṭabhakkho vā hoti, kaṇabhakkho vā hoti, ācāmabhakkho vā hoti, piññākabhakkho vā hoti, tiṇabhakkho vā hoti, gomayabhakkho vā hoti; vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī.**They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit.*";
P_HTM[95]="*So sāṇānipi dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti, chavadussānipi dhāreti, paṃsukūlānipi dhāreti, tirīṭānipi dhāreti, ajinampi dhāreti, ajinakkhipampi dhāreti, kusacīrampi dhāreti, vākacīrampi dhāreti, phalakacīrampi dhāreti, kesakambalampi dhāreti, vāḷakambalampi dhāreti, ulūkapakkhampi dhāreti;**They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings.*";
P_HTM[96]="*kesamassulocakopi hoti, kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto,**They tear out their hair and beard, committed to this practice.*";
P_HTM[97]="*ubbhaṭṭhakopi hoti āsanapaṭikkhitto,**They constantly stand, refusing seats.*";
P_HTM[98]="*ukkuṭikopi hoti ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto,**They squat, committed to the endeavor of squatting.*";
P_HTM[99]="*kaṇṭakāpassayikopi hoti kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappeti;**They lie on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns their bed.*";
P_HTM[100]="*sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati—**They’re committed to the practice of immersion in water three times a day, including the evening.*";
P_HTM[101]="*iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**And so they live committed to practicing these various ways of mortifying and tormenting the body.*";
P_HTM[102]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies themselves, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves.*";
P_HTM[103]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And what person mortifies others, committed to the practice of mortifying others?*";
P_HTM[104]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo orabbhiko hoti sūkariko sākuṇiko māgaviko luddo macchaghātako coro coraghātako goghātako bandhanāgāriko, ye vā panaññepi keci kurūrakammantā.**It’s when a person is a slaughterer of sheep, pigs, or poultry, a hunter or trapper, a fisher, a bandit, an executioner, a butcher, a jailer, or someone with some other kind of cruel livelihood.*";
P_HTM[105]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies others, being committed to the practice of mortifying others.*";
P_HTM[106]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And what person mortifies themselves and others, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others?*";
P_HTM[107]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo rājā vā hoti khattiyo muddhāvasitto brāhmaṇo vā mahāsālo.**It’s when a person is an anointed king or a well-to-do brahmin.*";
P_HTM[108]="*So puratthimena nagarassa navaṃ santhāgāraṃ kārāpetvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kharājinaṃ nivāsetvā sappitelena kāyaṃ abbhañjitvā magavisāṇena piṭṭhiṃ kaṇḍuvamāno navaṃ santhāgāraṃ pavisati saddhiṃ mahesiyā brāhmaṇena ca purohitena.**He has a new temple built to the east of the city. He shaves off his hair and beard, dresses in a rough antelope hide, and smears his body with ghee and oil. Scratching his back with antlers, he enters the temple with his chief queen and the brahmin high priest.*";
P_HTM[109]="*So tattha anantarahitāya bhūmiyā haritupalittāya seyyaṃ kappeti.**There he lies on the bare ground strewn with grass.*";
P_HTM[110]="*Ekissāya gāviyā sarūpavacchāya yaṃ ekasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena rājā yāpeti, yaṃ dutiyasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena mahesī yāpeti, yaṃ tatiyasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena brāhmaṇo purohito yāpeti, yaṃ catutthasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena aggiṃ juhati, avasesena vacchako yāpeti.**The king feeds on the milk from one teat of a cow that has a calf of the same color. The chief queen feeds on the milk from the second teat. The brahmin high priest feeds on the milk from the third teat. The milk from the fourth teat is offered to the flames. The calf feeds on the remainder.*";
P_HTM[111]="*So evamāha:**He says:*";
P_HTM[112]="*‘ettakā usabhā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā vacchatarā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā vacchatariyo haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā ajā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā urabbhā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā assā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā rukkhā chijjantu yūpatthāya, ettakā dabbhā lūyantu barihisatthāyā’ti.**‘Slaughter this many bulls, bullocks, heifers, goats, rams, and horses for the sacrifice! Fell this many trees and reap this much grass for the sacrificial equipment!’*";
P_HTM[113]="*Yepissa te honti dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā tepi daṇḍatajjitā bhayatajjitā assumukhā rudamānā parikammāni karonti.**His bondservants, employees, and workers do their jobs under threat of punishment and danger, weeping with tearful faces.*";
P_HTM[114]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies themselves and others, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[115]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati?**And what person doesn’t mortify either themselves or others, but lives without wishes, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves?*";
P_HTM[116]="*Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā.**It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.*";
P_HTM[117]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[118]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[119]="*Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule paccājāto.**A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some clan.*";
P_HTM[120]="*So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati.**They gain faith in the Realized One,*";
P_HTM[121]="*So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati:**and reflect:*";
P_HTM[122]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[123]="*Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[124]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[125]="*So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, mahantaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, mahantaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā, kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[126]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāsājīvasamāpanno pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho, lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.**Once they’ve gone forth, they take up the training and livelihood of the mendicants. They give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[127]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī, athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharati.**They give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. They keep themselves clean by not thieving.*";
P_HTM[128]="*Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī hoti ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.**They give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.*";
P_HTM[129]="*Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa.**They give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words.*";
P_HTM[130]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya—iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[131]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[132]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ.**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[133]="*So bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid injuring plants and seeds.*";
P_HTM[134]="*ekabhattiko hoti rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā;**They eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[135]="*naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti;**They avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows.*";
P_HTM[136]="*mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti;**They avoid beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, perfumes, and makeup.*";
P_HTM[137]="*uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato hoti;**They avoid high and luxurious beds.*";
P_HTM[138]="*jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**They avoid receiving gold and money,*";
P_HTM[139]="*āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**raw grains,*";
P_HTM[140]="*āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**raw meat,*";
P_HTM[141]="*itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**women and girls,*";
P_HTM[142]="*dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**male and female bondservants,*";
P_HTM[143]="*ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**goats and sheep,*";
P_HTM[144]="*kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**chickens and pigs,*";
P_HTM[145]="*hatthigavassavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**elephants, cows, horses, and mares,*";
P_HTM[146]="*khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti;**and fields and land.*";
P_HTM[147]="*dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti;**They avoid running errands and messages;*";
P_HTM[148]="*kayavikkayā paṭivirato hoti;**buying and selling;*";
P_HTM[149]="*tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato hoti;**falsifying weights, metals, or measures;*";
P_HTM[150]="*ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato hoti;**bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity;*";
P_HTM[151]="*chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato hoti.**mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence.*";
P_HTM[152]="*So santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati, samādāyeva pakkamati.**They’re content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[153]="*Seyyathāpi nāma pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti, sapattabhārova ḍeti;**They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden.*";
P_HTM[154]="*evameva bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati, samādāyeva pakkamati.**In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[155]="*So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a blameless happiness inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[156]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they see a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[157]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[158]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[159]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[160]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[161]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[162]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[163]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[164]="*So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied bliss inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[165]="*So abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti.**They act with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent.*";
P_HTM[166]="*So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato**When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble contentment, this noble sense restraint, and this noble mindfulness and situational awareness,*";
P_HTM[167]="*vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[168]="*So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down cross-legged with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[169]="*So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ parisodheti,**Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, cleansing the mind of desire.*";
P_HTM[170]="*byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up ill will, they meditate with a mind rid of ill will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill will and malevolence.*";
P_HTM[171]="*thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[172]="*uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse.*";
P_HTM[173]="*vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṃkathī kusalesu dhammesu, vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt.*";
P_HTM[174]="*So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe,**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[175]="*vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[176]="*vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[177]="*pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[178]="*sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[179]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[180]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect many kinds of past lives, that is, one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. They remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[181]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[182]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti: ‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā; ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti. Iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds: ‘These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[183]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[184]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. ‘Ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. ‘Ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. ‘Ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[185]="*‘Ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. ‘Ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. ‘Ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. ‘Ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[186]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati.**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[187]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[188]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[189]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who neither mortifies themselves or others, being committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others.*";
P_HTM[190]="*So attantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharatī”ti.**They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.”*";
P_HTM[191]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[192]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[193]="*Kandarakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[194]="*52. Aṭṭhakanāgarasutta**The Man From the City of Aṭṭhaka*";
P_HTM[195]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[196]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando vesāliyaṃ viharati beluvagāmake.**At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Vesālī in the little village of Beluva.*";
P_HTM[197]="*Tena kho pana samayena dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro pāṭaliputtaṃ anuppatto hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time the householder Dasama from the city of Aṭṭhaka had arrived at Pāṭaliputta on some business.*";
P_HTM[198]="*Atha kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro yena kukkuṭārāmo yena aññataro bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:**He went to the Chicken Monastery, approached a certain mendicant, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[199]="*“kahaṃ nu kho, bhante, āyasmā ānando etarahi viharati?**“Sir, where is Venerable Ānanda now staying?*";
P_HTM[200]="*Dassanakāmā hi mayaṃ taṃ āyasmantaṃ ānandan”ti.**For I want to see him.”*";
P_HTM[201]="*“Eso, gahapati, āyasmā ānando vesāliyaṃ viharati beluvagāmake”ti.**“Householder, Venerable Ānanda is staying near Vesālī in the little village of Beluva.”*";
P_HTM[202]="*Atha kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro pāṭaliputte taṃ karaṇīyaṃ tīretvā yena vesālī yena beluvagāmako yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Dasama, having concluded his business there, went to the little village of Beluva in Vesālī to see Ānanda. He bowed, sat down to one side, and said to Ānanda:*";
P_HTM[203]="*“atthi nu kho, bhante ānanda, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ekadhammo akkhāto yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇātī”ti?**“Sir, Ānanda, is there one thing that has been rightly explained by the Blessed One—who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha—practicing which a diligent, keen, and resolute mendicant’s mind is freed, their defilements are ended, and they arrive at the supreme sanctuary?”*";
P_HTM[204]="*“Atthi kho, gahapati, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ekadhammo akkhāto, yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇātī”ti.**“There is, householder.”*";
P_HTM[205]="*“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ekadhammo akkhāto, yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇātī”ti?**“And what is that one thing?”*";
P_HTM[206]="*“Idha, gahapati, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**“Householder, it’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[207]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Then they reflect:*";
P_HTM[208]="*‘idampi kho paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ.**‘Even this first absorption is produced by choices and intentions.’*";
P_HTM[209]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is impermanent and liable to cessation.’*";
P_HTM[210]="*So tattha ṭhito āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti.**Abiding in that they attain the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[211]="*No ce āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti, teneva dhammarāgena tāya dhammanandiyā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, with the ending of the five lower fetters they’re reborn spontaneously, because of their passion and love for that meditation. They are extinguished there, and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[212]="*Ayampi kho, gahapati, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ekadhammo akkhāto, yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (1)**This is one thing that has been rightly explained by the Blessed One—who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha—practicing which a diligent, keen, and resolute mendicant’s mind is freed, their defilements are ended, and they arrive at the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[213]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[214]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[215]="*‘idampi kho dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[216]="*anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (2)* **";
P_HTM[217]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[218]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[219]="*‘idampi kho tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[220]="*anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (3)* **";
P_HTM[221]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[222]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[223]="*‘idampi kho catutthaṃ jhānaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[224]="*anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (4)* **";
P_HTM[225]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[226]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Then they reflect:*";
P_HTM[227]="*‘ayampi kho mettācetovimutti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā.**‘Even this heart’s release by love is produced by choices and intentions.’*";
P_HTM[228]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is impermanent and liable to cessation.’ …*";
P_HTM[229]="*So tattha ṭhito … pe …* **";
P_HTM[230]="*anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (5)* **";
P_HTM[231]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[232]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[233]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**equanimity …*";
P_HTM[234]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[235]="*‘ayampi kho upekkhācetovimutti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā.* **";
P_HTM[236]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’ti pajānāti.* **";
P_HTM[237]="*So tattha ṭhito … pe …* **";
P_HTM[238]="*anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (6–8.)* **";
P_HTM[239]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, householder, a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[240]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Then they reflect:*";
P_HTM[241]="*‘ayampi kho ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpatti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā.**‘Even this attainment of the dimension of infinite space is produced by choices and intentions.’*";
P_HTM[242]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is impermanent and liable to cessation.’ …*";
P_HTM[243]="*So tattha ṭhito … pe …* **";
P_HTM[244]="*anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (9)* **";
P_HTM[245]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness. …*";
P_HTM[246]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[247]="*‘ayampi kho viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpatti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā.* **";
P_HTM[248]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’ti pajānāti.* **";
P_HTM[249]="*So tattha ṭhito … pe …* **";
P_HTM[250]="*anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇāti. (10)* **";
P_HTM[251]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[252]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Then they reflect:*";
P_HTM[253]="*‘ayampi kho ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpatti abhisaṅkhatā abhisañcetayitā.**‘Even this attainment of the dimension of nothingness is produced by choices and intentions.’*";
P_HTM[254]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is impermanent and liable to cessation.’*";
P_HTM[255]="*So tattha ṭhito āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti.**Abiding in that they attain the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[256]="*No ce āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti, teneva dhammarāgena tāya dhammanandiyā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, with the ending of the five lower fetters they’re reborn spontaneously because of their passion and love for that meditation. They are extinguished there, and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[257]="*Ayampi kho, gahapati, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena ekadhammo akkhāto yattha bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato avimuttañceva cittaṃ vimuccati, aparikkhīṇā ca āsavā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, ananuppattañca anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ anupāpuṇātī”ti. (11)**This too is one thing that has been rightly explained by the Blessed One—who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha—practicing which a diligent, keen, and resolute mendicant’s mind is freed, their defilements are ended, and they arrive at the supreme sanctuary.”*";
P_HTM[258]="*Evaṃ vutte, dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the householder Dasama said to Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[259]="*“seyyathāpi, bhante ānanda, puriso ekaṃva nidhimukhaṃ gavesanto sakideva ekādasa nidhimukhāni adhigaccheyya;**“Sir, suppose a person was looking for an entrance to a hidden treasure. And all at once they’d come across eleven entrances!*";
P_HTM[260]="*evameva kho ahaṃ, bhante, ekaṃ amatadvāraṃ gavesanto sakideva ekādasa amatadvārāni alatthaṃ bhāvanāya.**In the same way, I was searching for the door to the deathless. And all at once I got to hear of eleven doors to the deathless.*";
P_HTM[261]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, purisassa agāraṃ ekādasadvāraṃ, so tasmiṃ agāre āditte ekamekenapi dvārena sakkuṇeyya attānaṃ sotthiṃ kātuṃ;**Suppose a person had a house with eleven doors. If the house caught fire they’d be able to flee to safety through any one of those doors.*";
P_HTM[262]="*evameva kho ahaṃ, bhante, imesaṃ ekādasannaṃ amatadvārānaṃ ekamekenapi amatadvārena sakkuṇissāmi attānaṃ sotthiṃ kātuṃ.**In the same way, I’m able to flee to safety through any one of these eleven doors to the deathless.*";
P_HTM[263]="*Imehi nāma, bhante, aññatitthiyā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesissanti, kimaṅgaṃ panāhaṃ āyasmato ānandassa pūjaṃ na karissāmī”ti.**Sir, those who follow other paths seek a fee for the teacher. Why shouldn’t I make an offering to Venerable Ānanda?”*";
P_HTM[264]="*Atha kho dasamo gahapati aṭṭhakanāgaro pāṭaliputtakañca vesālikañca bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātetvā paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi,**Then the householder Dasama, having assembled the Saṅgha from Vesālī and Pāṭaliputta, served and satisfied them with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[265]="*ekamekañca bhikkhuṃ paccekaṃ dussayugena acchādesi, āyasmantañca ānandaṃ ticīvarena acchādesi, āyasmato ca ānandassa pañcasatavihāraṃ kārāpesīti.**He clothed each and every mendicant in a pair of garments, with a set of three robes for Ānanda. And he had a dwelling worth five hundred built for Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[266]="*Aṭṭhakanāgarasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[267]="*53. Sekhasutta**A Trainee*";
P_HTM[268]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[269]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery.*";
P_HTM[270]="*Tena kho pana samayena kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ navaṃ santhāgāraṃ acirakāritaṃ hoti anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā manussabhūtena.**Now at that time a new town hall had recently been constructed for the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu. It had not yet been occupied by an ascetic or brahmin or any person at all.*";
P_HTM[271]="*Atha kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[272]="*“idha, bhante, kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ navaṃ santhāgāraṃ acirakāritaṃ anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā manussabhūtena.**“Sir, a new town hall has recently been constructed for the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu. It has not yet been occupied by an ascetic or brahmin or any person at all.*";
P_HTM[273]="*Taṃ, bhante, bhagavā paṭhamaṃ paribhuñjatu. Bhagavatā paṭhamaṃ paribhuttaṃ pacchā kāpilavatthavā sakyā paribhuñjissanti.**May the Buddha be the first to use it, and only then will the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu use it.*";
P_HTM[274]="*Tadassa kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**That would be for the lasting welfare and happiness of the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu.”*";
P_HTM[275]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[276]="*Atha kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena navaṃ santhāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā sabbasanthariṃ santhāgāraṃ santharitvā āsanāni paññapetvā udakamaṇikaṃ upaṭṭhapetvā telappadīpaṃ āropetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, the Sakyans got up from their seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their right. Then they went to the new town hall, where they spread carpets all over, prepared seats, set up a water jar, and placed a lamp. Then they went back to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[277]="*upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu.**bowed, stood to one side,*";
P_HTM[278]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**and told him of their preparations, saying,*";
P_HTM[279]="*“sabbasanthariṃ santhataṃ, bhante, santhāgāraṃ, āsanāni paññattāni, udakamaṇiko upaṭṭhāpito, telappadīpo āropito.* **";
P_HTM[280]="*Yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ maññatī”ti.**“Please, sir, come at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[281]="*Atha kho bhagavā nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena yena santhāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ pavisitvā majjhimaṃ thambhaṃ nissāya puratthābhimukho nisīdi.**Then the Buddha robed up and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the new town hall together with the Saṅgha of mendicants. Having washed his feet he entered the town hall and sat against the central column facing east.*";
P_HTM[282]="*Bhikkhusaṃghopi kho pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ pavisitvā pacchimaṃ bhittiṃ nissāya puratthābhimukho nisīdi, bhagavantaṃyeva purakkhatvā.**The Saṅgha of mendicants also washed their feet, entered the town hall, and sat against the west wall facing east, with the Buddha right in front of them.*";
P_HTM[283]="*Kāpilavatthavāpi kho sakyā pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ pavisitvā puratthimaṃ bhittiṃ nissāya pacchimābhimukhā nisīdiṃsu, bhagavantaṃyeva purakkhatvā.**The Sakyans of Kapilavatthu also washed their feet, entered the town hall, and sat against the east wall facing west, with the Buddha right in front of them.*";
P_HTM[284]="*Atha kho bhagavā kāpilavatthave sakye bahudeva rattiṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**The Buddha spent most of the night educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the Sakyans with a Dhamma talk. Then he addressed Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[285]="*“paṭibhātu taṃ, ānanda, kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ sekho pāṭipado.**“Ānanda, speak about the practicing trainee to the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu as you feel inspired.*";
P_HTM[286]="*Piṭṭhi me āgilāyati;**My back is sore,*";
P_HTM[287]="*tamahaṃ āyamissāmī”ti.**I’ll stretch it.”*";
P_HTM[288]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied.*";
P_HTM[289]="*Atha kho bhagavā catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññāpetvā dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappesi, pāde pādaṃ accādhāya, sato sampajāno, uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā.**And then the Buddha spread out his outer robe folded in four and laid down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up.*";
P_HTM[290]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ āmantesi:**Then Ānanda addressed Mahānāma the Sakyan:*";
P_HTM[291]="*“idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlasampanno hoti, indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, bhojane mattaññū hoti, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti, sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti, catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī.**“Mahānāma, a noble disciple is accomplished in ethics, guards the sense doors, eats in moderation, and is dedicated to wakefulness. They have seven good qualities, and they get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[292]="*Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlasampanno hoti?**And how is a noble disciple accomplished in ethics?*";
P_HTM[293]="*Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**It’s when a noble disciple is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[294]="*Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlasampanno hoti. (1)**That’s how a noble disciple is ethical.*";
P_HTM[295]="*Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?**And how does a noble disciple guard the sense doors?*";
P_HTM[296]="*Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When a noble disciple sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[297]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[298]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[299]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[300]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[301]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[302]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[303]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[304]="*Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako indriyesu guttadvāro hoti. (2)**That’s how a noble disciple guards the sense doors.*";
P_HTM[305]="*Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako bhojane mattaññū hoti?**And how does a noble disciple eat in moderation?*";
P_HTM[306]="*Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:**It’s when a noble disciple reflects properly on the food that they eat:*";
P_HTM[307]="*‘neva davāya na madāya na maṇḍanāya na vibhūsanāya; yāvadeva imassa kāyassa ṭhitiyā yāpanāya vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya. Iti purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me bhavissati anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti.**‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to sustain this body, to avoid harm, and to support spiritual practice. In this way, I shall put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and I will live blamelessly and at ease.’*";
P_HTM[308]="*Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako bhojane mattaññū hoti. (3)**That’s how a noble disciple eats in moderation.*";
P_HTM[309]="*Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti?**And how is a noble disciple dedicated to wakefulness?*";
P_HTM[310]="*Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako divasaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodheti,**It’s when a noble disciple practices walking and sitting meditation by day, purifying their mind from obstacles.*";
P_HTM[311]="*rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodheti,**In the evening, they continue to practice walking and sitting meditation.*";
P_HTM[312]="*rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappeti, pāde pādaṃ accādhāya, sato sampajāno, uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā,**In the middle of the night, they lie down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up.*";
P_HTM[313]="*rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ paccuṭṭhāya caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodheti.**In the last part of the night, they get up and continue to practice walking and sitting meditation, purifying their mind from obstacles.*";
P_HTM[314]="*Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti. (4)**That’s how a noble disciple is dedicated to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[315]="*Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti?**And how does a noble disciple have seven good qualities?*";
P_HTM[316]="*Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:**It’s when a noble disciple has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:*";
P_HTM[317]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[318]="*Hirimā hoti, hirīyati kāyaduccaritena vacīduccaritena manoduccaritena, hirīyati pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā.**They have a conscience. They’re conscientious about bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and conscientious about having any bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[319]="*Ottappī hoti, ottappati kāyaduccaritena vacīduccaritena manoduccaritena, ottappati pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā.**They exercise prudence. They’re prudent when it comes to bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and prudent when it comes to acquiring any bad, unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[320]="*Bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo. Ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthā sabyañjanā kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[321]="*Āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu.**They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[322]="*Satimā hoti, paramena satinepakkena samannāgato, cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi saritā anussaritā.**They’re mindful. They have utmost mindfulness and alertness, and can remember and recall what was said and done long ago.*";
P_HTM[323]="*Paññavā hoti, udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato, ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā.**They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[324]="*Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti. (5–11)**That’s how a noble disciple has seven good qualities.*";
P_HTM[325]="*Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī?**And how does a noble disciple get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty?*";
P_HTM[326]="*Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**It’s when a noble disciple, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[327]="*vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**second absorption …*";
P_HTM[328]="*pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[329]="*sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[330]="*Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī. (12–15.)**That’s how a noble disciple gets the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[331]="*Yato kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako evaṃ sīlasampanno hoti, evaṃ indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, evaṃ bhojane mattaññū hoti, evaṃ jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti, evaṃ sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti, evaṃ catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, ayaṃ vuccati, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sekho pāṭipado apuccaṇḍatāya samāpanno, bhabbo abhinibbhidāya, bhabbo sambodhāya, bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**When a noble disciple is accomplished in ethics, guards the sense doors, eats in moderation, and is dedicated to wakefulness; and they have seven good qualities, and they get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty, they are called a noble disciple who is a practicing trainee. Their eggs are unspoiled, and they are capable of breaking out of their shell, becoming awakened, and achieving the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[332]="*Seyyathāpi, mahānāma, kukkuṭiyā aṇḍāni aṭṭha vā dasa vā dvādasa vā tānāssu kukkuṭiyā sammā adhisayitāni sammā pariseditāni sammā paribhāvitāni, kiñcāpi tassā kukkuṭiyā na evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:**Suppose there was a chicken with eight or ten or twelve eggs. And she properly sat on them to keep them warm and incubated. Even if that chicken doesn’t wish,*";
P_HTM[333]="*‘aho vatime kukkuṭapotakā pādanakhasikhāya vā mukhatuṇḍakena vā aṇḍakosaṃ padāletvā sotthinā abhinibbhijjeyyun’ti,**‘If only my chicks could break out of the eggshell with their claws and beak and hatch safely!’*";
P_HTM[334]="*atha kho bhabbāva te kukkuṭapotakā pādanakhasikhāya vā mukhatuṇḍakena vā aṇḍakosaṃ padāletvā sotthinā abhinibbhijjituṃ.**Still they can break out and hatch safely.*";
P_HTM[335]="*Evameva kho, mahānāma, yato ariyasāvako evaṃ sīlasampanno hoti, evaṃ indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, evaṃ bhojane mattaññū hoti, evaṃ jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti, evaṃ sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti, evaṃ catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, ayaṃ vuccati, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sekho pāṭipado apuccaṇḍatāya samāpanno, bhabbo abhinibbhidāya, bhabbo sambodhāya, bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**In the same way, when a noble disciple is practicing all these things they are called a noble disciple who is a practicing trainee. Their eggs are unspoiled, and they are capable of breaking out of their shell, becoming awakened, and achieving the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[336]="*Sa kho so, mahānāma, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ āgamma anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati,**Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble disciple recollects their many kinds of past lives.*";
P_HTM[337]="*seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati,**That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. … And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[338]="*ayamassa paṭhamābhinibbhidā hoti kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā. (1)**This is their first breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell.*";
P_HTM[339]="*Sa kho so, mahānāma, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ āgamma dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti,**Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble disciple, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, sees sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. … They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[340]="*ayamassa dutiyābhinibbhidā hoti kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā. (2)**This is their second breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell.*";
P_HTM[341]="*Sa kho so, mahānāma, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ āgamma āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati,**Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble disciple realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[342]="*ayamassa tatiyābhinibbhidā hoti kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā. (3)**This is their third breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell.*";
P_HTM[343]="*Yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlasampanno hoti, idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ;**A noble disciple’s conduct includes the following: being accomplished in ethics,*";
P_HTM[344]="*yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ;**guarding the sense doors,*";
P_HTM[345]="*yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako bhojane mattaññū hoti, idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ;**moderation in eating,*";
P_HTM[346]="*yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti, idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ;**being dedicated to wakefulness,*";
P_HTM[347]="*yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti, idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ;**having seven good qualities,*";
P_HTM[348]="*yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ.**and getting the four absorptions when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[349]="*Yañca kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, idampissa hoti vijjāya;**A noble disciple’s knowledge includes the following: recollecting their past lives,*";
P_HTM[350]="*yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti, idampissa hoti vijjāya.**clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman,*";
P_HTM[351]="*Yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati, idampissa hoti vijjāya.**and realizing the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[352]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, mahānāma, ariyasāvako vijjāsampanno itipi caraṇasampanno itipi vijjācaraṇasampanno itipi.**This noble disciple is said to be ‘accomplished in knowledge’, and also ‘accomplished in conduct’, and also ‘accomplished in knowledge and conduct’.*";
P_HTM[353]="*Brahmunāpesā, mahānāma, sanaṅkumārena gāthā bhāsitā:**And Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra also spoke this verse:*";
P_HTM[354]="*‘Khattiyo seṭṭho janetasmiṃ,**‘The aristocrat is best of those people*";
P_HTM[355]="*ye gottapaṭisārino;**who take clan as the standard.*";
P_HTM[356]="*Vijjācaraṇasampanno,**But one accomplished in knowledge and conduct*";
P_HTM[357]="*so seṭṭho devamānuse’ti.**is best of gods and humans.’*";
P_HTM[358]="*Sā kho panesā, mahānāma, brahmunā sanaṅkumārena gāthā sugītā no duggītā, subhāsitā no dubbhāsitā, atthasaṃhitā no anatthasaṃhitā, anumatā bhagavatā”ti.**And that verse was well sung by Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra, not poorly sung; well spoken, not poorly spoken, beneficial, not harmful, and it was approved by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[359]="*Atha kho bhagavā uṭṭhahitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha got up and said to Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[360]="*“sādhu sādhu, ānanda,**“Good, good, Ānanda!*";
P_HTM[361]="*sādhu kho tvaṃ, ānanda, kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ sekhaṃ pāṭipadaṃ abhāsī”ti.**It’s good that you spoke to the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu about the practicing trainee.”*";
P_HTM[362]="*Idamavocāyasmā ānando.**This is what Venerable Ānanda said,*";
P_HTM[363]="*Samanuñño satthā ahosi.**and the teacher approved.*";
P_HTM[364]="*Attamanā kāpilavatthavā sakyā āyasmato ānandassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu were happy with what Venerable Ānanda said.*";
P_HTM[365]="*Sekhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[366]="*54. Potaliyasutta**With Potaliya the Wanderer*";
P_HTM[367]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[368]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅguttarāpesu viharati āpaṇaṃ nāma aṅguttarāpānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Northern Āpaṇas, near the town of theirs named Āpaṇa.*";
P_HTM[369]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āpaṇaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Āpaṇa for alms.*";
P_HTM[370]="*Āpaṇe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yenaññataro vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**He wandered for alms in Āpaṇa. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to a certain forest grove for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[371]="*Taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**Having plunged deep into it, he sat at the root of a certain tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[372]="*Potaliyopi kho gahapati sampannanivāsanapāvuraṇo chattupāhanāhi jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena so vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Potaliya the householder also approached that forest grove while going for a walk. He was well dressed in a cloak and sarong, with parasol and sandals. Having plunged deep into it, he went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[373]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho potaliyaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side, and the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[374]="*“saṃvijjanti kho, gahapati, āsanāni; sace ākaṅkhasi nisīdā”ti.**“There are seats, householder. Please sit if you wish.”*";
P_HTM[375]="*Evaṃ vutte, potaliyo gahapati “gahapativādena maṃ samaṇo gotamo samudācaratī”ti kupito anattamano tuṇhī ahosi.**When he said this, Potaliya was angry and upset. Thinking, “The ascetic Gotama addresses me as ‘householder’!” he stayed silent.*";
P_HTM[376]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[377]="*tatiyampi kho bhagavā potaliyaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**and a third time the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[378]="*“saṃvijjanti kho, gahapati, āsanāni; sace ākaṅkhasi nisīdā”ti.**“There are seats, householder. Please sit if you wish.”*";
P_HTM[379]="*Evaṃ vutte, potaliyo gahapati “gahapativādena maṃ samaṇo gotamo samudācaratī”ti kupito anattamano bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Potaliya was angry and upset. Thinking, “The ascetic Gotama addresses me as ‘householder’!” he said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[380]="*“tayidaṃ, bho gotama, nacchannaṃ, tayidaṃ nappatirūpaṃ, yaṃ maṃ tvaṃ gahapativādena samudācarasī”ti.**“Master Gotama, it is neither proper nor appropriate for you to address me as ‘householder’.”*";
P_HTM[381]="*“Te hi te, gahapati, ākārā, te liṅgā, te nimittā yathā taṃ gahapatissā”ti.**“Well, householder, you have the features, attributes, and signs of a householder.”*";
P_HTM[382]="*“Tathā hi pana me, bho gotama, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā samucchinnā”ti.**“Master Gotama, it’s because I have refused all work and cut off all judgments.”*";
P_HTM[383]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana te, gahapati, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā samucchinnā”ti?**“Householder, in what way have you refused all work and cut off all judgments?”*";
P_HTM[384]="*“Idha me, bho gotama, yaṃ ahosi dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā sabbaṃ taṃ puttānaṃ dāyajjaṃ niyyātaṃ, tatthāhaṃ anovādī anupavādī ghāsacchādanaparamo viharāmi.**“Master Gotama, all the money, grain, gold, and silver I used to have has been handed over to my children as their inheritance. And in this matter I do not advise or reprimand them, but live with nothing more than food and clothes.*";
P_HTM[385]="*Evaṃ kho me, bho gotama, sabbe kammantā paṭikkhittā, sabbe vohārā samucchinnā”ti.**That’s how I have refused all work and cut off all judgments.”*";
P_HTM[386]="*“Aññathā kho tvaṃ, gahapati, vohārasamucchedaṃ vadasi, aññathā ca pana ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti.**“The cutting off of judgments as you describe it is one thing, householder, but the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training is quite different.”*";
P_HTM[387]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedo hoti?**“But what, sir, is cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training?*";
P_HTM[388]="*Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti.**Sir, please teach me this.”*";
P_HTM[389]="*“Tena hi, gahapati, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, householder, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[390]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho potaliyo gahapati bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” said Potaliya.*";
P_HTM[391]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[392]="*“aṭṭha kho ime, gahapati, dhammā ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattanti.**“Householder, these eight things lead to the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training.*";
P_HTM[393]="*Katame aṭṭha?**What eight?*";
P_HTM[394]="*Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo;**Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[395]="*dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabbaṃ;**Stealing should be given up, relying on not stealing.*";
P_HTM[396]="*saccavācaṃ nissāya musāvādo pahātabbo;**Lying should be given up, relying on speaking the truth.*";
P_HTM[397]="*apisuṇaṃ vācaṃ nissāya pisuṇā vācā pahātabbā;**Divisive speech should be given up, relying on speech that isn’t divisive.*";
P_HTM[398]="*agiddhilobhaṃ nissāya giddhilobho pahātabbo;**Greed and lust should be given up, relying on not being greedy and lustful.*";
P_HTM[399]="*anindārosaṃ nissāya nindāroso pahātabbo;**Blaming and insulting should be given up, relying on not blaming and not insulting.*";
P_HTM[400]="*akkodhūpāyāsaṃ nissāya kodhūpāyāso pahātabbo;**Anger and distress should be given up, relying on not being angry and distressed.*";
P_HTM[401]="*anatimānaṃ nissāya atimāno pahātabbo.**Arrogance should be given up, relying on not being arrogant.*";
P_HTM[402]="*Ime kho, gahapati, aṭṭha dhammā saṃkhittena vuttā, vitthārena avibhattā, ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These are the eight things—stated in brief without being analyzed in detail—that lead to the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training.”*";
P_HTM[403]="*“Ye me, bhante, bhagavatā aṭṭha dhammā saṃkhittena vuttā, vitthārena avibhattā, ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattanti, sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā ime aṭṭha dhamme vitthārena vibhajatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti.**“Sir, please teach me these eight things in detail out of compassion.”*";
P_HTM[404]="*“Tena hi, gahapati, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, householder, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[405]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho potaliyo gahapati bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” said Potaliya.*";
P_HTM[406]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[407]="*“‘Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**“‘Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living creatures.’ That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[408]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[409]="*‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu pāṇātipātī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno.**‘I am practicing to give up and cut off the fetters that might cause me to kill living creatures.*";
P_HTM[410]="*Ahañceva kho pana pāṇātipātī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya pāṇātipātapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ pāṇātipātapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā pāṇātipātapaccayā.**But if I were to kill living creatures, because of that I would reprimand myself; sensible people, after examination, would criticize me; and when my body breaks up, after death, I could expect to be reborn in a bad place.*";
P_HTM[411]="*Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ pāṇātipāto.**And killing living creatures is itself a fetter and a hindrance.*";
P_HTM[412]="*Ye ca pāṇātipātapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, pāṇātipātā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’.**The distressing and feverish defilements that might arise because of killing living creatures do not occur in someone who does not kill living creatures.’*";
P_HTM[413]="*‘Apāṇātipātaṃ nissāya pāṇātipāto pahātabbo’ti—**‘Killing living creatures should be given up, relying on not killing living creatures.’*";
P_HTM[414]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[415]="*‘Dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabban’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**‘Stealing …*";
P_HTM[416]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[417]="*‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu adinnādāyī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno.* **";
P_HTM[418]="*Ahañceva kho pana adinnādāyī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya adinnādānapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ adinnādānapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā adinnādānapaccayā.* **";
P_HTM[419]="*Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ adinnādānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[420]="*Ye ca adinnādānapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā adinnādānā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’.* **";
P_HTM[421]="*‘Dinnādānaṃ nissāya adinnādānaṃ pahātabban’ti—* **";
P_HTM[422]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[423]="*‘Saccavācaṃ nissāya musāvādo pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**lying …*";
P_HTM[424]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[425]="*‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu musāvādī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno.* **";
P_HTM[426]="*Ahañceva kho pana musāvādī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya musāvādapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ musāvādapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā musāvādapaccayā.* **";
P_HTM[427]="*Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ musāvādo.* **";
P_HTM[428]="*Ye ca musāvādapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, musāvādā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’.* **";
P_HTM[429]="*‘Saccavācaṃ nissāya musāvādo pahātabbo’ti—* **";
P_HTM[430]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[431]="*‘Apisuṇaṃ vācaṃ nissāya pisuṇā vācā pahātabbā’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**divisive speech …*";
P_HTM[432]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[433]="*‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu pisuṇavāco assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno.* **";
P_HTM[434]="*Ahañceva kho pana pisuṇavāco assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya pisuṇavācāpaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ pisuṇavācāpaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā pisuṇavācāpaccayā.* **";
P_HTM[435]="*Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ pisuṇā vācā.* **";
P_HTM[436]="*Ye ca pisuṇavācāpaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’.* **";
P_HTM[437]="*‘Apisuṇaṃ vācaṃ nissāya pisuṇā vācā pahātabbā’ti—* **";
P_HTM[438]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[439]="*‘Agiddhilobhaṃ nissāya giddhilobho pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**greed and lust …*";
P_HTM[440]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[441]="*‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu giddhilobhī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno.* **";
P_HTM[442]="*Ahañceva kho pana giddhilobhī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya giddhilobhapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ giddhilobhapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā giddhilobhapaccayā.* **";
P_HTM[443]="*Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ giddhilobho.* **";
P_HTM[444]="*Ye ca giddhilobhapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, giddhilobhā paṭiviratassa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’.* **";
P_HTM[445]="*‘Agiddhilobhaṃ nissāya giddhilobho pahātabbo’ti—* **";
P_HTM[446]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[447]="*‘Anindārosaṃ nissāya nindāroso pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**blaming and insulting …*";
P_HTM[448]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[449]="*‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu nindārosī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno.* **";
P_HTM[450]="*Ahañceva kho pana nindārosī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya nindārosapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ nindārosapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā nindārosapaccayā.* **";
P_HTM[451]="*Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ nindāroso.* **";
P_HTM[452]="*Ye ca nindārosapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, anindārosissa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’.* **";
P_HTM[453]="*‘Anindārosaṃ nissāya nindāroso pahātabbo’ti—* **";
P_HTM[454]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[455]="*‘Akkodhūpāyāsaṃ nissāya kodhūpāyāso pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**anger and distress …*";
P_HTM[456]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[457]="*‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu kodhūpāyāsī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno.* **";
P_HTM[458]="*Ahañceva kho pana kodhūpāyāsī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya kodhūpāyāsapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ kodhūpāyāsapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā kodhūpāyāsapaccayā.* **";
P_HTM[459]="*Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ kodhūpāyāso.* **";
P_HTM[460]="*Ye ca kodhūpāyāsapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, akkodhūpāyāsissa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’.* **";
P_HTM[461]="*‘Akkodhūpāyāsaṃ nissāya kodhūpāyāso pahātabbo’ti—* **";
P_HTM[462]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[463]="*‘Anatimānaṃ nissāya atimāno pahātabbo’ti iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**Arrogance should be given up, relying on not being arrogant.’ That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[464]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[465]="*‘yesaṃ kho ahaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ hetu atimānī assaṃ, tesāhaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya paṭipanno.**‘I am practicing to give up and cut off the fetters that might cause me to be arrogant.*";
P_HTM[466]="*Ahañceva kho pana atimānī assaṃ, attāpi maṃ upavadeyya atimānapaccayā, anuviccāpi maṃ viññū garaheyyuṃ atimānapaccayā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā atimānapaccayā.**But if I were to be arrogant, because of that I would reprimand myself; sensible people, after examination, would criticize me; and when my body breaks up, after death, I could expect to be reborn in a bad place.*";
P_HTM[467]="*Etadeva kho pana saṃyojanaṃ etaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ atimāno.**And arrogance is itself a fetter and a hindrance.*";
P_HTM[468]="*Ye ca atimānapaccayā uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, anatimānissa evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti’.**The distressing and feverish defilements that might arise because of arrogance do not occur in someone who is not arrogant.’*";
P_HTM[469]="*‘Anatimānaṃ nissāya atimāno pahātabbo’ti—**‘Arrogance should be given up by not being arrogant.’*";
P_HTM[470]="*iti yantaṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[471]="*Ime kho, gahapati, aṭṭha dhammā saṃkhittena vuttā, vitthārena vibhattā, ye ariyassa vinaye vohārasamucchedāya saṃvattanti;**These are the eight things—stated in brief and analyzed in detail—that lead to the cutting off of judgments in the noble one’s training.*";
P_HTM[472]="*na tveva tāva ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti.**But just this much does not constitute the cutting off of judgments in each and every respect in the noble one’s training.”*";
P_HTM[473]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedo hoti?**“But, sir, how is there the cutting off of judgments in each and every respect in the noble one’s training?*";
P_HTM[474]="*Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedo hotī”ti.**Sir, please teach me this.”*";
P_HTM[475]="*“Tena hi, gahapati, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, householder, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[476]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho potaliyo gahapati bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” said Potaliya.*";
P_HTM[477]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[478]="*1. Kāmādīnavakathā**1. The Dangers of Sensual Pleasures*";
P_HTM[479]="*“Seyyathāpi, gahapati, kukkuro jighacchādubbalyapareto goghātakasūnaṃ paccupaṭṭhito assa.**“Householder, suppose a dog weak with hunger was hanging around a butcher’s shop.*";
P_HTM[480]="*Tamenaṃ dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā aṭṭhikaṅkalaṃ sunikkantaṃ nikkantaṃ nimmaṃsaṃ lohitamakkhitaṃ upasumbheyya.**Then a deft butcher or their apprentice would toss them a skeleton scraped clean of flesh and smeared in blood.*";
P_HTM[481]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[482]="*api nu kho so kukkuro amuṃ aṭṭhikaṅkalaṃ sunikkantaṃ nikkantaṃ nimmaṃsaṃ lohitamakkhitaṃ palehanto jighacchādubbalyaṃ paṭivineyyā”ti?**Gnawing on such a fleshless skeleton, would that dog still get rid of its hunger?”*";
P_HTM[483]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[484]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why not?*";
P_HTM[485]="*“Aduñhi, bhante, aṭṭhikaṅkalaṃ sunikkantaṃ nikkantaṃ nimmaṃsaṃ lohitamakkhitaṃ.**Because that skeleton is scraped clean of flesh and smeared in blood.*";
P_HTM[486]="*Yāvadeva pana so kukkuro kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That dog will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[487]="*“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**“In the same way, a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[488]="*‘aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti.**‘With the simile of a skeleton the Buddha said that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.’*";
P_HTM[489]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā yāyaṃ upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā taṃ abhinivajjetvā, yāyaṃ upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā yattha sabbaso lokāmisūpādānā aparisesā nirujjhanti tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti.**Having truly seen this with right understanding, they reject equanimity based on diversity and develop only the equanimity based on unity, where all kinds of grasping to the world’s material delights cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[490]="*Seyyathāpi, gahapati, gijjho vā kaṅko vā kulalo vā maṃsapesiṃ ādāya uḍḍīyeyya.**Suppose a vulture or a crow or a hawk was to grab a lump of meat and fly away.*";
P_HTM[491]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kaṅkāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitaccheyyuṃ vissajjeyyuṃ.**Other vultures, crows, and hawks would keep chasing it, pecking and clawing.*";
P_HTM[492]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[493]="*sace so gijjho vā kaṅko vā kulalo vā taṃ maṃsapesiṃ na khippameva paṭinissajjeyya, so tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan”ti?**If that vulture, crow, or hawk doesn’t quickly let go of that lump of meat, wouldn’t that result in death or deadly suffering for them?”*";
P_HTM[494]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[495]="*“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[496]="*‘maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[497]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā yāyaṃ upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā taṃ abhinivajjetvā yāyaṃ upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā yattha sabbaso lokāmisūpādānā aparisesā nirujjhanti tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti.* **";
P_HTM[498]="*Seyyathāpi, gahapati, puriso ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ ādāya paṭivātaṃ gaccheyya.**“Suppose a person carrying a blazing grass torch was to walk against the wind.*";
P_HTM[499]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[500]="*sace so puriso taṃ ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ na khippameva paṭinissajjeyya tassa sā ādittā tiṇukkā hatthaṃ vā daheyya bāhuṃ vā daheyya aññataraṃ vā aññataraṃ vā aṅgapaccaṅgaṃ daheyya, so tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan”ti?**If that person doesn’t quickly let go of that blazing grass torch, wouldn’t they burn their hands or arm or other limb, resulting in death or deadly suffering for them?”*";
P_HTM[501]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[502]="*“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[503]="*‘tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[504]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā … pe … tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti.* **";
P_HTM[505]="*Seyyathāpi, gahapati, aṅgārakāsu sādhikaporisā, pūrā aṅgārānaṃ vītaccikānaṃ vītadhūmānaṃ.**“Suppose there was a pit of glowing coals deeper than a man’s height, full of glowing coals that neither flamed nor smoked.*";
P_HTM[506]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhapaṭikkūlo.**Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, who wants to be happy and recoils from pain.*";
P_HTM[507]="*Tamenaṃ dve balavanto purisā nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuṃ upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**Then two strong men would grab them by the arms and drag them towards the pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[508]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[509]="*api nu so puriso iticiticeva kāyaṃ sannāmeyyā”ti?**Wouldn’t that person writhe and struggle to and fro?”*";
P_HTM[510]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.*";
P_HTM[511]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[512]="*“Viditañhi, bhante, tassa purisassa imañcāhaṃ aṅgārakāsuṃ papatissāmi, tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchissāmi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan”ti.**For that person knows: ‘If I fall in that pit of glowing coals, that’d result in my death or deadly pain.’” …*";
P_HTM[513]="*“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[514]="*‘aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[515]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā … pe … tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti.* **";
P_HTM[516]="*Seyyathāpi, gahapati, puriso supinakaṃ passeyya ārāmarāmaṇeyyakaṃ vanarāmaṇeyyakaṃ bhūmirāmaṇeyyakaṃ pokkharaṇirāmaṇeyyakaṃ.**“Suppose a person was to see delightful parks, woods, meadows, and lotus ponds in a dream.*";
P_HTM[517]="*So paṭibuddho na kiñci paṭipasseyya.**But when they woke they couldn’t see them at all. …*";
P_HTM[518]="*Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[519]="*‘supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti … pe …* **";
P_HTM[520]="*tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti.* **";
P_HTM[521]="*Seyyathāpi, gahapati, puriso yācitakaṃ bhogaṃ yācitvā yānaṃ vā poriseyyaṃ pavaramaṇikuṇḍalaṃ.**Suppose a man had borrowed some goods—a gentleman’s carriage and fine jewelled earrings—*";
P_HTM[522]="*So tehi yācitakehi bhogehi purakkhato parivuto antarāpaṇaṃ paṭipajjeyya.**and preceded and surrounded by these he proceeded through the middle of Āpaṇa.*";
P_HTM[523]="*Tamenaṃ jano disvā evaṃ vadeyya:**When people saw him they’d say:*";
P_HTM[524]="*‘bhogī vata bho puriso, evaṃ kira bhogino bhogāni bhuñjantī’ti.**‘This must be a wealthy man! For that’s how the wealthy enjoy their wealth.’*";
P_HTM[525]="*Tamenaṃ sāmikā yattha yattheva passeyyuṃ tattha tattheva sāni hareyyuṃ.**But when the owners saw him, they’d take back what was theirs.*";
P_HTM[526]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, alaṃ nu kho tassa purisassa aññathattāyā”ti?**What do you think? Would that be enough for that man to get upset?”*";
P_HTM[527]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.*";
P_HTM[528]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[529]="*“Sāmino hi, bhante, sāni harantī”ti.**Because the owners took back what was theirs.” …*";
P_HTM[530]="*“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:* **";
P_HTM[531]="*‘yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti … pe …* **";
P_HTM[532]="*tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti.* **";
P_HTM[533]="*Seyyathāpi, gahapati, gāmassa vā nigamassa vā avidūre tibbo vanasaṇḍo.**“Suppose there was a dark forest grove not far from a town or village.*";
P_HTM[534]="*Tatrassa rukkho sampannaphalo ca upapannaphalo ca, na cassu kānici phalāni bhūmiyaṃ patitāni.**And there was a tree laden with fruit, yet none of the fruit had fallen to the ground.*";
P_HTM[535]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya phalatthiko phalagavesī phalapariyesanaṃ caramāno.**And along came a person in need of fruit, wandering in search of fruit.*";
P_HTM[536]="*So taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā taṃ rukkhaṃ passeyya sampannaphalañca upapannaphalañca.**Having plunged deep into that forest grove, they’d see that tree laden with fruit.*";
P_HTM[537]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[538]="*‘ayaṃ kho rukkho sampannaphalo ca upapannaphalo ca, natthi ca kānici phalāni bhūmiyaṃ patitāni.**‘That tree is laden with fruit, yet none of the fruit has fallen to the ground.*";
P_HTM[539]="*Jānāmi kho panāhaṃ rukkhaṃ ārohituṃ.**But I know how to climb a tree.*";
P_HTM[540]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ rukkhaṃ ārohitvā yāvadatthañca khādeyyaṃ ucchaṅgañca pūreyyan’ti.**Why don’t I climb the tree, eat as much as I like, then fill my pouch?’*";
P_HTM[541]="*So taṃ rukkhaṃ ārohitvā yāvadatthañca khādeyya ucchaṅgañca pūreyya.**And that’s what they’d do.*";
P_HTM[542]="*Atha dutiyo puriso āgaccheyya phalatthiko phalagavesī phalapariyesanaṃ caramāno tiṇhaṃ kuṭhāriṃ ādāya.**And along would come a second person in need of fruit, wandering in search of fruit, carrying a sharp axe.*";
P_HTM[543]="*So taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā taṃ rukkhaṃ passeyya sampannaphalañca upapannaphalañca.**Having plunged deep into that forest grove, they’d see that tree laden with fruit.*";
P_HTM[544]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[545]="*‘ayaṃ kho rukkho sampannaphalo ca upapannaphalo ca, natthi ca kānici phalāni bhūmiyaṃ patitāni.**‘That tree is laden with fruit, yet none of the fruit has fallen to the ground.*";
P_HTM[546]="*Na kho panāhaṃ jānāmi rukkhaṃ ārohituṃ.**But I don’t know how to climb a tree.*";
P_HTM[547]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ rukkhaṃ mūlato chetvā yāvadatthañca khādeyyaṃ ucchaṅgañca pūreyyan’ti.**Why don’t I chop this tree down at the root, eat as much as I like, then fill my pouch?’*";
P_HTM[548]="*So taṃ rukkhaṃ mūlatova chindeyya.**And so they’d chop the tree down at the root.*";
P_HTM[549]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[550]="*amuko yo so puriso paṭhamaṃ rukkhaṃ ārūḷho sace so na khippameva oroheyya tassa so rukkho papatanto hatthaṃ vā bhañjeyya pādaṃ vā bhañjeyya aññataraṃ vā aññataraṃ vā aṅgapaccaṅgaṃ bhañjeyya, so tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhan”ti?**If the first person, who climbed the tree, doesn’t quickly come down, when that tree fell wouldn’t they break their hand or arm or other limb, resulting in death or deadly suffering for them?”*";
P_HTM[551]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[552]="*“Evameva kho, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**“In the same way, a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[553]="*‘rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo’ti.**‘With the simile of the fruit tree the Buddha said that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.’*";
P_HTM[554]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā yāyaṃ upekkhā nānattā nānattasitā taṃ abhinivajjetvā yāyaṃ upekkhā ekattā ekattasitā yattha sabbaso lokāmisūpādānā aparisesā nirujjhanti tamevūpekkhaṃ bhāveti.**Having truly seen this with right understanding, they reject equanimity based on diversity and develop only the equanimity based on unity, where all kinds of grasping to the world’s material delights cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[555]="*Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ āgamma anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati,**Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble disciple recollects their many kinds of past lives.*";
P_HTM[556]="*seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. … They recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[557]="*Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ āgamma dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble disciple, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, sees sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. … They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[558]="*Sa kho so, gahapati, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ āgamma āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble disciple realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[559]="*Ettāvatā kho, gahapati, ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedo hoti.**That’s how there is the cutting off of judgments in each and every respect in the noble one’s training.*";
P_HTM[560]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[561]="*yathā ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedo hoti, api nu tvaṃ evarūpaṃ vohārasamucchedaṃ attani samanupassasī”ti?**Do you regard yourself as having cut off judgments in a way comparable to the cutting off of judgments in each and every respect in the noble one’s training?”*";
P_HTM[562]="*“Ko cāhaṃ, bhante, ko ca ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedo.**“Who am I compared to one who has cut off judgments in each and every respect in the noble one’s training?*";
P_HTM[563]="*Ārakā ahaṃ, bhante, ariyassa vinaye sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ vohārasamucchedā.**I am far from that.*";
P_HTM[564]="*Mayañhi, bhante, pubbe aññatitthiye paribbājake anājānīyeva samāne ājānīyāti amaññimha, anājānīyeva samāne ājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojimha, anājānīyeva samāne ājānīyaṭhāne ṭhapimha;**Sir, I used to think that the wanderers following other paths were thoroughbreds, and I fed them and treated them accordingly, but they were not actually thoroughbreds.*";
P_HTM[565]="*bhikkhū pana mayaṃ, bhante, ājānīyeva samāne anājānīyāti amaññimha, ājānīyeva samāne anājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojimha, ājānīyeva samāne anājānīyaṭhāne ṭhapimha;**I thought that the mendicants were not thoroughbreds, and I fed them and treated them accordingly, but they actually were thoroughbreds.*";
P_HTM[566]="*idāni pana mayaṃ, bhante, aññatitthiye paribbājake anājānīyeva samāne anājānīyāti jānissāma, anājānīyeva samāne anājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojessāma, anājānīyeva samāne anājānīyaṭhāne ṭhapessāma.**But now I shall understand that the wanderers following other paths are not actually thoroughbreds, and I will feed them and treat them accordingly.*";
P_HTM[567]="*Bhikkhū pana mayaṃ, bhante, ājānīyeva samāne ājānīyāti jānissāma, ājānīyeva samāne ājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojessāma, ājānīyeva samāne ājānīyaṭhāne ṭhapessāma.**And I shall understand that the mendicants actually are thoroughbreds, and I will feed them and treat them accordingly.*";
P_HTM[568]="*Ajanesi vata me, bhante, bhagavā samaṇesu samaṇappemaṃ, samaṇesu samaṇappasādaṃ, samaṇesu samaṇagāravaṃ.**The Buddha has inspired me to have love, confidence, and respect for ascetics!*";
P_HTM[569]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**Excellent, sir! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[570]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya, ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[571]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[572]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[573]="*Potaliyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[574]="*55. Jīvakasutta**With Jīvaka*";
P_HTM[575]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[576]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati jīvakassa komārabhaccassa ambavane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha in the Mango Grove of Jīvaka Komārabhacca.*";
P_HTM[577]="*Atha kho jīvako komārabhacco yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho jīvako komārabhacco bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Jīvaka went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[578]="*“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:**“Sir, I have heard this:*";
P_HTM[579]="*‘samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ uddissa pāṇaṃ ārabhanti, taṃ samaṇo gotamo jānaṃ uddissakataṃ maṃsaṃ paribhuñjati paṭiccakamman’ti.**‘They slaughter living creatures specially for the ascetic Gotama. The ascetic Gotama knowingly eats meat prepared on purpose for him: this is a deed he caused.’*";
P_HTM[580]="*Ye te, bhante, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ uddissa pāṇaṃ ārabhanti, taṃ samaṇo gotamo jānaṃ uddissakataṃ maṃsaṃ paribhuñjati paṭiccakamman’ti, kacci te, bhante, bhagavato vuttavādino, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti?**I trust that those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and do not misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”*";
P_HTM[581]="*“Ye te, jīvaka, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ uddissa pāṇaṃ ārabhanti, taṃ samaṇo gotamo jānaṃ uddissakataṃ maṃsaṃ paribhuñjati paṭiccakamman’ti na me te vuttavādino, abbhācikkhanti ca maṃ te asatā abhūtena.**“Jīvaka, those who say this do not repeat what I have said. They misrepresent me with what is false and untrue.*";
P_HTM[582]="*Tīhi kho ahaṃ, jīvaka, ṭhānehi maṃsaṃ aparibhoganti vadāmi.**In three cases I say that meat may not be eaten:*";
P_HTM[583]="*Diṭṭhaṃ, sutaṃ, parisaṅkitaṃ—**it’s seen, heard, or suspected.*";
P_HTM[584]="*imehi kho ahaṃ, jīvaka, tīhi ṭhānehi maṃsaṃ aparibhoganti vadāmi.**These are three cases in which meat may not be eaten.*";
P_HTM[585]="*Tīhi kho ahaṃ, jīvaka, ṭhānehi maṃsaṃ paribhoganti vadāmi.**In three cases I say that meat may be eaten:*";
P_HTM[586]="*Adiṭṭhaṃ, asutaṃ, aparisaṅkitaṃ—**it’s not seen, heard, or suspected.*";
P_HTM[587]="*imehi kho ahaṃ, jīvaka, tīhi ṭhānehi maṃsaṃ paribhoganti vadāmi.**These are three cases in which meat may be eaten.*";
P_HTM[588]="*Idha, jīvaka, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati.**Take the case of a mendicant living supported by a town or village.*";
P_HTM[589]="*So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**They meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[590]="*Tamenaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā upasaṅkamitvā svātanāya bhattena nimanteti.**A householder or their child approaches and invites them for the next day’s meal.*";
P_HTM[591]="*Ākaṅkhamānova, jīvaka, bhikkhu adhivāseti.**The mendicant accepts if they want.*";
P_HTM[592]="*So tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena tassa gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamati; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdati.**When the night has passed, they robe up in the morning, take their bowl and robe, and approach that householder’s home, where they sit on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[593]="*Tamenaṃ so gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena piṇḍapātena parivisati.**That householder or their child serves them with delicious alms-food.*";
P_HTM[594]="*Tassa na evaṃ hoti:**It never occurs to them,*";
P_HTM[595]="*‘sādhu vata māyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena piṇḍapātena pariviseyyāti.**‘It’s so good that this householder serves me with delicious alms-food!*";
P_HTM[596]="*Aho vata māyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā āyatimpi evarūpena paṇītena piṇḍapātena pariviseyyā’ti—**I hope they serve me with such delicious alms-food in the future!’*";
P_HTM[597]="*evampissa na hoti.**They don’t think that.*";
P_HTM[598]="*So taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ agathito amucchito anajjhopanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati.**They eat that alms-food untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawback, and understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[599]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, jīvaka,**What do you think, Jīvaka?*";
P_HTM[600]="*api nu so bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye attabyābādhāya vā ceteti, parabyābādhāya vā ceteti, ubhayabyābādhāya vā cetetī”ti?**At that time is that mendicant intending to hurt themselves, hurt others, or hurt both?”*";
P_HTM[601]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[602]="*“Nanu so, jīvaka, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye anavajjaṃyeva āhāraṃ āhāretī”ti?**“Aren’t they eating blameless food at that time?”*";
P_HTM[603]="*“Evaṃ, bhante.**“Yes, sir.*";
P_HTM[604]="*Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:**Sir, I have heard that*";
P_HTM[605]="*‘brahmā mettāvihārī’ti.**Brahmā abides in love.*";
P_HTM[606]="*Taṃ me idaṃ, bhante, bhagavā sakkhidiṭṭho;**Now, I’ve seen the Buddha with my own eyes,*";
P_HTM[607]="*bhagavā hi, bhante, mettāvihārī”ti.**and it is the Buddha who truly abides in love.”*";
P_HTM[608]="*“Yena kho, jīvaka, rāgena yena dosena yena mohena byāpādavā assa so rāgo so doso so moho tathāgatassa pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo.**“Any greed, hate, or delusion that might give rise to ill will has been given up by the Realized One, cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and is unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[609]="*Sace kho te, jīvaka, idaṃ sandhāya bhāsitaṃ anujānāmi te etan”ti.**If that’s what you were referring to, I acknowledge it.”*";
P_HTM[610]="*“Etadeva kho pana me, bhante, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ”.**“That’s exactly what I was referring to.”*";
P_HTM[611]="*“Idha, jīvaka, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati.**“Take the case, Jīvaka, of a mendicant living supported by a town or village.*";
P_HTM[612]="*So karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[613]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[614]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ.**They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth.*";
P_HTM[615]="*Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[616]="*Tamenaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā upasaṅkamitvā svātanāya bhattena nimanteti.**A householder or their child approaches and invites them for the next day’s meal.*";
P_HTM[617]="*Ākaṅkhamānova, jīvaka, bhikkhu adhivāseti.**The mendicant accepts if they want.*";
P_HTM[618]="*So tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamati; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdati.**When the night has passed, they robe up in the morning, take their bowl and robe, and approach that householder’s home, where they sit on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[619]="*Tamenaṃ so gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena piṇḍapātena parivisati.**That householder or their child serves them with delicious alms-food.*";
P_HTM[620]="*Tassa na evaṃ hoti:**It never occurs to them,*";
P_HTM[621]="*‘sādhu vata māyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena piṇḍapātena pariviseyyāti.**‘It’s so good that this householder serves me with delicious alms-food!*";
P_HTM[622]="*Aho vata māyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā āyatimpi evarūpena paṇītena piṇḍapātena pariviseyyā’ti—**I hope they serve me with such delicious alms-food in the future!’*";
P_HTM[623]="*evampissa na hoti.**They don’t think that.*";
P_HTM[624]="*So taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ agathito amucchito anajjhopanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati.**They eat that alms-food untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawback, and understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[625]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, jīvaka,**What do you think, Jīvaka?*";
P_HTM[626]="*api nu so bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye attabyābādhāya vā ceteti, parabyābādhāya vā ceteti, ubhayabyābādhāya vā cetetī”ti?**At that time is that mendicant intending to hurt themselves, hurt others, or hurt both?”*";
P_HTM[627]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[628]="*“Nanu so, jīvaka, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye anavajjaṃyeva āhāraṃ āhāretī”ti?**“Aren’t they eating blameless food at that time?”*";
P_HTM[629]="*“Evaṃ, bhante.**“Yes, sir.*";
P_HTM[630]="*Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:**Sir, I have heard that*";
P_HTM[631]="*‘brahmā upekkhāvihārī’ti.**Brahmā abides in equanimity.*";
P_HTM[632]="*Taṃ me idaṃ, bhante, bhagavā sakkhidiṭṭho;**Now, I’ve seen the Buddha with my own eyes,*";
P_HTM[633]="*bhagavā hi, bhante, upekkhāvihārī”ti.**and it is the Buddha who truly abides in equanimity.”*";
P_HTM[634]="*“Yena kho, jīvaka, rāgena yena dosena yena mohena vihesavā assa arativā assa paṭighavā assa so rāgo so doso so moho tathāgatassa pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo.**“Any greed, hate, or delusion that might give rise to cruelty, negativity, or repulsion has been given up by the Realized One, cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and is unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[635]="*Sace kho te, jīvaka, idaṃ sandhāya bhāsitaṃ, anujānāmi te etan”ti.**If that’s what you were referring to, I acknowledge it.”*";
P_HTM[636]="*“Etadeva kho pana me, bhante, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ”.**“That’s exactly what I was referring to.”*";
P_HTM[637]="*“Yo kho, jīvaka, tathāgataṃ vā tathāgatasāvakaṃ vā uddissa pāṇaṃ ārabhati so pañcahi ṭhānehi bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati.**“Jīvaka, anyone who slaughters a living creature specially for the Realized One or the Realized One’s disciple makes much bad karma for five reasons.*";
P_HTM[638]="*Yampi so, gahapati, evamāha:**When they say:*";
P_HTM[639]="*‘gacchatha, amukaṃ nāma pāṇaṃ ānethā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati.**‘Go, fetch that living creature,’ this is the first reason.*";
P_HTM[640]="*Yampi so pāṇo galappaveṭhakena ānīyamāno dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, iminā dutiyena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati.**When that living creature experiences pain and sadness as it’s led along by a collar, this is the second reason.*";
P_HTM[641]="*Yampi so evamāha:**When they say:*";
P_HTM[642]="*‘gacchatha imaṃ pāṇaṃ ārabhathā’ti, iminā tatiyena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati.**‘Go, slaughter that living creature,’ this is the third reason.*";
P_HTM[643]="*Yampi so pāṇo ārabhiyamāno dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, iminā catutthena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati.**When that living creature experiences pain and sadness as it’s being slaughtered, this is the fourth reason.*";
P_HTM[644]="*Yampi so tathāgataṃ vā tathāgatasāvakaṃ vā akappiyena āsādeti, iminā pañcamena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati.**When they provide the Realized One or the Realized One’s disciple with unallowable food, this is the fifth reason.*";
P_HTM[645]="*Yo kho, jīvaka, tathāgataṃ vā tathāgatasāvakaṃ vā uddissa pāṇaṃ ārabhati so imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**Anyone who slaughters a living creature specially for the Realized One or the Realized One’s disciple makes much bad karma for five reasons.”*";
P_HTM[646]="*Evaṃ vutte, jīvako komārabhacco bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Jīvaka said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[647]="*“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[648]="*Kappiyaṃ vata, bhante, bhikkhū āhāraṃ āhārenti;**The mendicants indeed eat allowable food.*";
P_HTM[649]="*anavajjaṃ vata, bhante, bhikkhū āhāraṃ āhārenti.**The mendicants indeed eat blameless food.*";
P_HTM[650]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe …**Excellent, sir! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[651]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[652]="*Jīvakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[653]="*56. Upālisutta**With Upāli*";
P_HTM[654]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[655]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ viharati pāvārikambavane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Nālandā in Pāvārika’s mango grove.*";
P_HTM[656]="*Tena kho pana samayena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto nāḷandāyaṃ paṭivasati mahatiyā nigaṇṭhaparisāya saddhiṃ.**At that time Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta was residing at Nāḷandā together with a large assembly of Jain ascetics.*";
P_HTM[657]="*Atha kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho nāḷandāyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena pāvārikambavanaṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the Jain ascetic Dīgha Tapassī wandered for alms in Nāḷandā. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to Pāvārika’s mango grove. There he approached the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[658]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho dīghatapassiṃ nigaṇṭhaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[659]="*“saṃvijjanti kho, tapassi, āsanāni; sace ākaṅkhasi nisīdā”ti.**“There are seats, Tapassī. Please sit if you wish.”*";
P_HTM[660]="*Evaṃ vutte, dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When he said this, Dīgha Tapassī took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[661]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho dīghatapassiṃ nigaṇṭhaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[662]="*“kati pana, tapassi, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto kammāni paññapeti pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā”ti?**“Tapassī, how many kinds of deed does Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta describe for performing bad deeds?”*";
P_HTM[663]="*“Na kho, āvuso gotama, āciṇṇaṃ nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa ‘kammaṃ, kamman’ti paññapetuṃ;**“Reverend Gotama, Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta doesn’t usually speak in terms of ‘deeds’.*";
P_HTM[664]="*‘daṇḍaṃ, daṇḍan’ti kho, āvuso gotama, āciṇṇaṃ nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa paññapetun”ti.**He usually speaks in terms of ‘rods’.”*";
P_HTM[665]="*“Kati pana, tapassi, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto daṇḍāni paññapeti pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā”ti?**“Then how many kinds of rod does Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta describe for performing bad deeds?”*";
P_HTM[666]="*“Tīṇi kho, āvuso gotama, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto daṇḍāni paññapeti pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyāti, seyyathidaṃ—**“Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta describes three kinds of rod for performing bad deeds:*";
P_HTM[667]="*kāyadaṇḍaṃ, vacīdaṇḍaṃ, manodaṇḍan”ti.**the physical rod, the verbal rod, and the mental rod.”*";
P_HTM[668]="*“Kiṃ pana, tapassi, aññadeva kāyadaṇḍaṃ, aññaṃ vacīdaṇḍaṃ, aññaṃ manodaṇḍan”ti?**“But are these kinds of rod all distinct from each other?”*";
P_HTM[669]="*“Aññadeva, āvuso gotama, kāyadaṇḍaṃ, aññaṃ vacīdaṇḍaṃ, aññaṃ manodaṇḍan”ti.**“Yes, each is quite distinct.”*";
P_HTM[670]="*“Imesaṃ pana, tapassi, tiṇṇaṃ daṇḍānaṃ evaṃ paṭivibhattānaṃ evaṃ paṭivisiṭṭhānaṃ katamaṃ daṇḍaṃ nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto mahāsāvajjataraṃ paññapeti pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, yadi vā kāyadaṇḍaṃ, yadi vā vacīdaṇḍaṃ, yadi vā manodaṇḍan”ti?**“Of the three rods thus analyzed and differentiated, which rod does Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta describe as being the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds: the physical rod, the verbal rod, or the mental rod?”*";
P_HTM[671]="*“Imesaṃ kho, āvuso gotama, tiṇṇaṃ daṇḍānaṃ evaṃ paṭivibhattānaṃ evaṃ paṭivisiṭṭhānaṃ kāyadaṇḍaṃ nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto mahāsāvajjataraṃ paññapeti pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, no tathā vacīdaṇḍaṃ, no tathā manodaṇḍan”ti.**“Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta describes the physical rod as being the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds, not so much the verbal rod or the mental rod.”*";
P_HTM[672]="*“Kāyadaṇḍanti, tapassi, vadesi”?**“Do you say the physical rod, Tapassī?”*";
P_HTM[673]="*“Kāyadaṇḍanti, āvuso gotama, vadāmi”.**“I say the physical rod, Reverend Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[674]="*“Kāyadaṇḍanti, tapassi, vadesi”?**“Do you say the physical rod, Tapassī?”*";
P_HTM[675]="*“Kāyadaṇḍanti, āvuso gotama, vadāmi”.**“I say the physical rod, Reverend Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[676]="*“Kāyadaṇḍanti, tapassi, vadesi”?**“Do you say the physical rod, Tapassī?”*";
P_HTM[677]="*“Kāyadaṇḍanti, āvuso gotama, vadāmī”ti.**“I say the physical rod, Reverend Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[678]="*Itiha bhagavā dīghatapassiṃ nigaṇṭhaṃ imasmiṃ kathāvatthusmiṃ yāvatatiyakaṃ patiṭṭhāpesi.**Thus the Buddha made Dīgha Tapassī stand by this point up to the third time.*";
P_HTM[679]="*Evaṃ vutte, dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When this was said, Dīgha Tapassī said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[680]="*“tvaṃ panāvuso gotama, kati daṇḍāni paññapesi pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā”ti?**“But Reverend Gotama, how many kinds of rod do you describe for performing bad deeds?”*";
P_HTM[681]="*“Na kho, tapassi, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatassa ‘daṇḍaṃ, daṇḍan’ti paññapetuṃ;**“Tapassī, the Realized One doesn’t usually speak in terms of ‘rods’.*";
P_HTM[682]="*‘kammaṃ, kamman’ti kho, tapassi, āciṇṇaṃ tathāgatassa paññapetun”ti?**He usually speaks in terms of ‘deeds’.”*";
P_HTM[683]="*“Tvaṃ panāvuso gotama, kati kammāni paññapesi pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā”ti?**“Then how many kinds of deed do you describe for performing bad deeds?”*";
P_HTM[684]="*“Tīṇi kho ahaṃ, tapassi, kammāni paññapemi pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, seyyathidaṃ—**“I describe three kinds of deed for performing bad deeds:*";
P_HTM[685]="*kāyakammaṃ, vacīkammaṃ, manokamman”ti.**physical deeds, verbal deeds, and mental deeds.”*";
P_HTM[686]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso gotama, aññadeva kāyakammaṃ, aññaṃ vacīkammaṃ, aññaṃ manokamman”ti?**“But are these kinds of deed all distinct from each other?”*";
P_HTM[687]="*“Aññadeva, tapassi, kāyakammaṃ, aññaṃ vacīkammaṃ, aññaṃ manokamman”ti.**“Yes, each is quite distinct.”*";
P_HTM[688]="*“Imesaṃ panāvuso gotama, tiṇṇaṃ kammānaṃ evaṃ paṭivibhattānaṃ evaṃ paṭivisiṭṭhānaṃ katamaṃ kammaṃ mahāsāvajjataraṃ paññapesi pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, yadi vā kāyakammaṃ, yadi vā vacīkammaṃ, yadi vā manokamman”ti?**“Of the three deeds thus analyzed and differentiated, which deed do you describe as being the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds: physical deeds, verbal deeds, or mental deeds?”*";
P_HTM[689]="*“Imesaṃ kho ahaṃ, tapassi, tiṇṇaṃ kammānaṃ evaṃ paṭivibhattānaṃ evaṃ paṭivisiṭṭhānaṃ manokammaṃ mahāsāvajjataraṃ paññapemi pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, no tathā kāyakammaṃ, no tathā vacīkamman”ti.**“I describe mental deeds as being the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds, not so much physical deeds or verbal deeds.”*";
P_HTM[690]="*“Manokammanti, āvuso gotama, vadesi”?**“Do you say mental deeds, Reverend Gotama?”*";
P_HTM[691]="*“Manokammanti, tapassi, vadāmi”.**“I say mental deeds, Tapassī.”*";
P_HTM[692]="*“Manokammanti, āvuso gotama, vadesi”?**“Do you say mental deeds, Reverend Gotama?”*";
P_HTM[693]="*“Manokammanti, tapassi, vadāmi”.**“I say mental deeds, Tapassī.”*";
P_HTM[694]="*“Manokammanti, āvuso gotama, vadesi”?**“Do you say mental deeds, Reverend Gotama?”*";
P_HTM[695]="*“Manokammanti, tapassi, vadāmī”ti.**“I say mental deeds, Tapassī.”*";
P_HTM[696]="*Itiha dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho bhagavantaṃ imasmiṃ kathāvatthusmiṃ yāvatatiyakaṃ patiṭṭhāpetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkami.**Thus the Jain ascetic Dīgha Tapassī made the Buddha stand by this point up to the third time, after which he got up from his seat and went to see Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta.*";
P_HTM[697]="*Tena kho pana samayena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto mahatiyā gihiparisāya saddhiṃ nisinno hoti bālakiniyā parisāya upālipamukhāya.**Now at that time Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta was sitting together with a large assembly of laypeople of Bālaka headed by Upāli.*";
P_HTM[698]="*Addasā kho nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto dīghatapassiṃ nigaṇṭhaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ;**Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta saw Dīgha Tapassī coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[699]="*disvāna dīghatapassiṃ nigaṇṭhaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[700]="*“handa kuto nu tvaṃ, tapassi, āgacchasi divā divassā”ti?**“So, Tapassī, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?”*";
P_HTM[701]="*“Ito hi kho ahaṃ, bhante, āgacchāmi samaṇassa gotamassa santikā”ti.**“Just now, sir, I’ve come from the presence of the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[702]="*“Ahu pana te, tapassi, samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti?**“But did you have some discussion with him?”*";
P_HTM[703]="*“Ahu kho me, bhante, samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti.**“I did.”*";
P_HTM[704]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana te, tapassi, ahu samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti?**“And what kind of discussion did you have with him?”*";
P_HTM[705]="*Atha kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho yāvatako ahosi bhagavatā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa ārocesi.**Then Dīgha Tapassī informed Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta of all they had discussed.*";
P_HTM[706]="*Evaṃ vutte, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto dīghatapassiṃ nigaṇṭhaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Nigaṇṭha said to him,*";
P_HTM[707]="*“sādhu sādhu, tapassi.**“Good, good, Tapassī!*";
P_HTM[708]="*Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena evameva dīghatapassinā nigaṇṭhena samaṇassa gotamassa byākataṃ.**Dīgha Tapassī has answered the ascetic Gotama like an educated disciple who rightly understands their teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[709]="*Kiñhi sobhati chavo manodaṇḍo imassa evaṃ oḷārikassa kāyadaṇḍassa upanidhāya.**For how impressive is the measly mental rod when compared with the substantial physical rod?*";
P_HTM[710]="*Atha kho kāyadaṇḍova mahāsāvajjataro pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, no tathā vacīdaṇḍo, no tathā manodaṇḍo”ti.**Rather, the physical rod is the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds, not so much the verbal rod or the mental rod.”*";
P_HTM[711]="*Evaṃ vutte, upāli gahapati nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the householder Upāli said to him,*";
P_HTM[712]="*“sādhu sādhu, bhante dīghatapassī.**“Good, sir! Well done, Dīgha Tapassī!*";
P_HTM[713]="*Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena evamevaṃ bhadantena tapassinā samaṇassa gotamassa byākataṃ.**The honorable Tapassī has answered the ascetic Gotama like an educated disciple who rightly understands their teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[714]="*Kiñhi sobhati chavo manodaṇḍo imassa evaṃ oḷārikassa kāyadaṇḍassa upanidhāya.**For how impressive is the measly mental rod when compared with the substantial physical rod?*";
P_HTM[715]="*Atha kho kāyadaṇḍova mahāsāvajjataro pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, no tathā vacīdaṇḍo, no tathā manodaṇḍo.**Rather, the physical rod is the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds, not so much the verbal rod or the mental rod.*";
P_HTM[716]="*Handa cāhaṃ, bhante, gacchāmi samaṇassa gotamassa imasmiṃ kathāvatthusmiṃ vādaṃ āropessāmi.**I’d better go and refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine regarding this point.*";
P_HTM[717]="*Sace me samaṇo gotamo tathā patiṭṭhahissati yathā bhadantena tapassinā patiṭṭhāpitaṃ; seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso dīghalomikaṃ eḷakaṃ lomesu gahetvā ākaḍḍheyya parikaḍḍheyya samparikaḍḍheyya; evamevāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ vādena vādaṃ ākaḍḍhissāmi parikaḍḍhissāmi samparikaḍḍhissāmi.**If he stands by the position that he stated to Dīgha Tapassī, I’ll take him on in debate and drag him to and fro and round about, like a strong man would drag a fleecy sheep to and fro and round about!*";
P_HTM[718]="*Seyyathāpi nāma balavā soṇḍikākammakāro mahantaṃ soṇḍikākilañjaṃ gambhīre udakarahade pakkhipitvā kaṇṇe gahetvā ākaḍḍheyya parikaḍḍheyya samparikaḍḍheyya; evamevāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ vādena vādaṃ ākaḍḍhissāmi parikaḍḍhissāmi samparikaḍḍhissāmi.**Taking him on in debate, I’ll drag him to and fro and round about, like a strong brewer’s worker would toss a large brewer’s sieve into a deep lake, grab it by the corners, and drag it to and fro and round about!*";
P_HTM[719]="*Seyyathāpi nāma balavā soṇḍikādhutto vālaṃ kaṇṇe gahetvā odhuneyya niddhuneyya nipphoṭeyya; evamevāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ vādena vādaṃ odhunissāmi niddhunissāmi nipphoṭessāmi.**Taking him on in debate, I’ll shake him down and about and give him a beating, like a strong brewer’s mixer would grab a strainer by the corners and shake it down and about, and give it a beating!*";
P_HTM[720]="*Seyyathāpi nāma kuñjaro saṭṭhihāyano gambhīraṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā sāṇadhovikaṃ nāma kīḷitajātaṃ kīḷati; evamevāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ sāṇadhovikaṃ maññe kīḷitajātaṃ kīḷissāmi.**I’ll play a game of ear-washing with the ascetic Gotama, like a sixty-year-old elephant would plunge into a deep lotus pond and play a game of ear-washing!*";
P_HTM[721]="*Handa cāhaṃ, bhante, gacchāmi samaṇassa gotamassa imasmiṃ kathāvatthusmiṃ vādaṃ āropessāmī”ti.**Sir, I’d better go and refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine on this point.”*";
P_HTM[722]="*“Gaccha tvaṃ, gahapati, samaṇassa gotamassa imasmiṃ kathāvatthusmiṃ vādaṃ āropehi.**“Go, householder, refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine on this point.*";
P_HTM[723]="*Ahaṃ vā hi, gahapati, samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropeyyaṃ, dīghatapassī vā nigaṇṭho, tvaṃ vā”ti.**For either I should do so, or Dīgha Tapassī, or you.”*";
P_HTM[724]="*Evaṃ vutte, dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Dīgha Tapassī said to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta,*";
P_HTM[725]="*“na kho metaṃ, bhante, ruccati yaṃ upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropeyya.**“Sir, I don’t believe it’s a good idea for the householder Upāli to rebut the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine.*";
P_HTM[726]="*Samaṇo hi, bhante, gotamo māyāvī āvaṭṭaniṃ māyaṃ jānāti yāya aññatitthiyānaṃ sāvake āvaṭṭetī”ti.**For the ascetic Gotama is a magician. He knows a conversion magic, and uses it to convert the disciples of those who follow other paths.”*";
P_HTM[727]="*“Aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, tapassi, anavakāso yaṃ upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyya.**“It is impossible, Tapassī, it cannot happen that Upāli could become Gotama’s disciple.*";
P_HTM[728]="*Ṭhānañca kho etaṃ vijjati yaṃ samaṇo gotamo upālissa gahapatissa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyya.**But it is possible that Gotama could become Upāli’s disciple.*";
P_HTM[729]="*Gaccha tvaṃ, gahapati, samaṇassa gotamassa imasmiṃ kathāvatthusmiṃ vādaṃ āropehi.**Go, householder, refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine on this point.*";
P_HTM[730]="*Ahaṃ vā hi, gahapati, samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropeyyaṃ, dīghatapassī vā nigaṇṭho, tvaṃ vā”ti.**For either I should do so, or Dīgha Tapassī, or you.”*";
P_HTM[731]="*Dutiyampi kho dīghatapassī … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[732]="*tatiyampi kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time, Dīgha Tapassī said to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta,*";
P_HTM[733]="*“na kho metaṃ, bhante, ruccati yaṃ upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropeyya.**“Sir, I don’t believe it’s a good idea for the householder Upāli to rebut the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine.*";
P_HTM[734]="*Samaṇo hi, bhante, gotamo māyāvī āvaṭṭaniṃ māyaṃ jānāti yāya aññatitthiyānaṃ sāvake āvaṭṭetī”ti.**For the ascetic Gotama is a magician. He knows a conversion magic, and uses it to convert the disciples of those who follow other paths.”*";
P_HTM[735]="*“Aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, tapassi, anavakāso yaṃ upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyya.**“It is impossible, Tapassī, it cannot happen that Upāli could become Gotama’s disciple.*";
P_HTM[736]="*Ṭhānañca kho etaṃ vijjati yaṃ samaṇo gotamo upālissa gahapatissa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyya.**But it is possible that Gotama could become Upāli’s disciple.*";
P_HTM[737]="*Gaccha tvaṃ, gahapati, samaṇassa gotamassa imasmiṃ kathāvatthusmiṃ vādaṃ āropehi.**Go, householder, refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine on this point.*";
P_HTM[738]="*Ahaṃ vā hi, gahapati, samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropeyyaṃ, dīghatapassī vā nigaṇṭho, tvaṃ vā”ti.**For either I should do so, or Dīgha Tapassī, or you.”*";
P_HTM[739]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho upāli gahapati nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena pāvārikambavanaṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho upāli gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” replied the householder Upāli to Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled him, keeping him on his right. Then he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[740]="*“āgamā nu khvidha, bhante, dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho”ti?**“Sir, did the Jain ascetic Dīgha Tapassī come here?”*";
P_HTM[741]="*“Āgamā khvidha, gahapati, dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho”ti.**“He did, householder.”*";
P_HTM[742]="*“Ahu kho pana te, bhante, dīghatapassinā nigaṇṭhena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti?**“But did you have some discussion with him?”*";
P_HTM[743]="*“Ahu kho me, gahapati, dīghatapassinā nigaṇṭhena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti.**“I did.”*";
P_HTM[744]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana te, bhante, ahu dīghatapassinā nigaṇṭhena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti?**“And what kind of discussion did you have with him?”*";
P_HTM[745]="*Atha kho bhagavā yāvatako ahosi dīghatapassinā nigaṇṭhena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ upālissa gahapatissa ārocesi.**Then the Buddha informed Upāli of all they had discussed.*";
P_HTM[746]="*Evaṃ vutte, upāli gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the householder Upāli said to him,*";
P_HTM[747]="*“sādhu sādhu, bhante tapassī.**“Good, sir, well done by Tapassī!*";
P_HTM[748]="*Yathā taṃ sutavatā sāvakena sammadeva satthusāsanaṃ ājānantena evamevaṃ dīghatapassinā nigaṇṭhena bhagavato byākataṃ.**The honorable Tapassī has answered the ascetic Gotama like an educated disciple who rightly understands their teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[749]="*Kiñhi sobhati chavo manodaṇḍo imassa evaṃ oḷārikassa kāyadaṇḍassa upanidhāya?**For how impressive is the measly mental rod when compared with the substantial physical rod?*";
P_HTM[750]="*Atha kho kāyadaṇḍova mahāsāvajjataro pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, no tathā vacīdaṇḍo, no tathā manodaṇḍo”ti.**Rather, the physical rod is the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds, not so much the verbal rod or the mental rod.”*";
P_HTM[751]="*“Sace kho tvaṃ, gahapati, sacce patiṭṭhāya manteyyāsi siyā no ettha kathāsallāpo”ti.**“Householder, so long as you debate on the basis of truth, we can have some discussion about this.”*";
P_HTM[752]="*“Sacce ahaṃ, bhante, patiṭṭhāya mantessāmi;**“I will debate on the basis of truth, sir.*";
P_HTM[753]="*hotu no ettha kathāsallāpo”ti.**Let us have some discussion about this.”*";
P_HTM[754]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**“What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[755]="*idhassa nigaṇṭho ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno sītodakapaṭikkhitto uṇhodakapaṭisevī.**Take a Jain ascetic who is sick, suffering, gravely ill. They reject cold water and use only hot water.*";
P_HTM[756]="*So sītodakaṃ alabhamāno kālaṃ kareyya.**Not getting cold water, they might die.*";
P_HTM[757]="*Imassa pana, gahapati, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto katthūpapattiṃ paññapetī”ti?**Now, where does Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta say they would be reborn?”*";
P_HTM[758]="*“Atthi, bhante, manosattā nāma devā tattha so upapajjati”.**“Sir, there are gods called ‘mind-bound’. They would be reborn there.*";
P_HTM[759]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[760]="*“Asu hi, bhante, manopaṭibaddho kālaṃ karotī”ti.**Because they died with mental attachment.”*";
P_HTM[761]="*“Manasi karohi, gahapati, manasi karitvā kho, gahapati, byākarohi.**“Think about it, householder! You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[762]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ, pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[763]="*Bhāsitā kho pana te, gahapati, esā vācā:**But you said that you would debate on the basis of truth.”*";
P_HTM[764]="*‘sacce ahaṃ, bhante, patiṭṭhāya mantessāmi,* **";
P_HTM[765]="*hotu no ettha kathāsallāpo’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[766]="*“Kiñcāpi, bhante, bhagavā evamāha, atha kho kāyadaṇḍova mahāsāvajjataro pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, no tathā vacīdaṇḍo, no tathā manodaṇḍo”ti.**“Even though the Buddha says this, still the physical rod is the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds, not so much the verbal rod or the mental rod.”*";
P_HTM[767]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**“What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[768]="*idhassa nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto cātuyāmasaṃvarasaṃvuto sabbavārivārito sabbavāriyutto sabbavāridhuto sabbavāriphuṭo.**Take a Jain ascetic who is restrained in the fourfold restraint: obstructed by all water, devoted to all water, shaking off all water, pervaded by all water.*";
P_HTM[769]="*So abhikkamanto paṭikkamanto bahū khuddake pāṇe saṅghātaṃ āpādeti.**When going out and coming back they accidentally injure many little creatures.*";
P_HTM[770]="*Imassa pana, gahapati, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto kaṃ vipākaṃ paññapetī”ti?**Now, what result does Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta say they would incur?”*";
P_HTM[771]="*“Asañcetanikaṃ, bhante, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto no mahāsāvajjaṃ paññapetī”ti.**“Sir, Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta says that unintentional acts are not very blameworthy.”*";
P_HTM[772]="*“Sace pana, gahapati, cetetī”ti?**“But if they are intentional?”*";
P_HTM[773]="*“Mahāsāvajjaṃ, bhante, hotī”ti.**“Then they are very blameworthy.”*";
P_HTM[774]="*“Cetanaṃ pana, gahapati, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto kismiṃ paññapetī”ti?**“But where does Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta say that intention is classified?”*";
P_HTM[775]="*“Manodaṇḍasmiṃ, bhante”ti.**“In the mental rod, sir.”*";
P_HTM[776]="*“Manasi karohi, gahapati, manasi karitvā kho, gahapati, byākarohi.**“Think about it, householder! You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[777]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ, pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[778]="*Bhāsitā kho pana te, gahapati, esā vācā:**But you said that you would debate on the basis of truth.”*";
P_HTM[779]="*‘sacce ahaṃ, bhante, patiṭṭhāya mantessāmi;* **";
P_HTM[780]="*hotu no ettha kathāsallāpo’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[781]="*“Kiñcāpi, bhante, bhagavā evamāha, atha kho kāyadaṇḍova mahāsāvajjataro pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, no tathā vacīdaṇḍo, no tathā manodaṇḍo”ti.**“Even though the Buddha says this, still the physical rod is the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds, not so much the verbal rod or the mental rod.”*";
P_HTM[782]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**“What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[783]="*ayaṃ nāḷandā iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ākiṇṇamanussā”ti?**Is this Nāḷandā successful and prosperous and full of people?”*";
P_HTM[784]="*“Evaṃ, bhante, ayaṃ nāḷandā iddhā ceva phītā ca bahujanā ākiṇṇamanussā”ti.**“Indeed it is, sir.”*";
P_HTM[785]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**“What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[786]="*idha puriso āgaccheyya ukkhittāsiko.**Suppose a man were to come along with a drawn sword*";
P_HTM[787]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**and say:*";
P_HTM[788]="*‘ahaṃ yāvatikā imissā nāḷandāya pāṇā te ekena khaṇena ekena muhuttena ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ karissāmī’ti.**‘In one moment I will reduce all the living creatures within the bounds of Nāḷandā to one heap and mass of flesh!’*";
P_HTM[789]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[790]="*pahoti nu kho so puriso yāvatikā imissā nāḷandāya pāṇā te ekena khaṇena ekena muhuttena ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ kātun”ti?**Could he do that?”*";
P_HTM[791]="*“Dasapi, bhante, purisā, vīsampi, bhante, purisā, tiṃsampi, bhante, purisā, cattārīsampi, bhante, purisā, paññāsampi, bhante, purisā nappahonti yāvatikā imissā nāḷandāya pāṇā te ekena khaṇena ekena muhuttena ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ kātuṃ.**“Sir, even ten, twenty, thirty, forty, or fifty men couldn’t do that.*";
P_HTM[792]="*Kiñhi sobhati eko chavo puriso”ti.**How impressive is one measly man?”*";
P_HTM[793]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**“What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[794]="*idha āgaccheyya samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā iddhimā cetovasippatto.**Suppose an ascetic or brahmin with psychic power, who has achieved mastery of the mind, were to come along*";
P_HTM[795]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**and say:*";
P_HTM[796]="*‘ahaṃ imaṃ nāḷandaṃ ekena manopadosena bhasmaṃ karissāmī’ti.**‘I will reduce Nāḷandā to ashes with a single malevolent act of will!’*";
P_HTM[797]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[798]="*pahoti nu kho so samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā iddhimā cetovasippatto imaṃ nāḷandaṃ ekena manopadosena bhasmaṃ kātun”ti?**Could he do that?”*";
P_HTM[799]="*“Dasapi, bhante, nāḷandā, vīsampi nāḷandā, tiṃsampi nāḷandā, cattārīsampi nāḷandā, paññāsampi nāḷandā pahoti so samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā iddhimā cetovasippatto ekena manopadosena bhasmaṃ kātuṃ.**“Sir, an ascetic or brahmin with psychic power, who has achieved mastery of the mind, could reduce ten, twenty, thirty, forty, or fifty Nāḷandās to ashes with a single malevolent act of will.*";
P_HTM[800]="*Kiñhi sobhati ekā chavā nāḷandā”ti.**How impressive is one measly Nāḷandā?”*";
P_HTM[801]="*“Manasi karohi, gahapati, manasi karitvā kho, gahapati, byākarohi.**“Think about it, householder! You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[802]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ, pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[803]="*Bhāsitā kho pana te, gahapati, esā vācā:**But you said that you would debate on the basis of truth.”*";
P_HTM[804]="*‘sacce ahaṃ, bhante, patiṭṭhāya mantessāmi;* **";
P_HTM[805]="*hotu no ettha kathāsallāpo’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[806]="*“Kiñcāpi, bhante, bhagavā evamāha, atha kho kāyadaṇḍova mahāsāvajjataro pāpassa kammassa kiriyāya pāpassa kammassa pavattiyā, no tathā vacīdaṇḍo, no tathā manodaṇḍo”ti.**“Even though the Buddha says this, still the physical rod is the most blameworthy for performing bad deeds, not so much the verbal rod or the mental rod.”*";
P_HTM[807]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati,**“What do you think, householder?*";
P_HTM[808]="*sutaṃ te daṇḍakīraññaṃ kāliṅgāraññaṃ majjhāraññaṃ mātaṅgāraññaṃ araññaṃ araññabhūtan”ti?**Have you heard how the wildernesses of Daṇḍaka, Kāliṅga, Mejjha, and Mātaṅga came to be that way?”*";
P_HTM[809]="*“Evaṃ, bhante, sutaṃ me daṇḍakīraññaṃ kāliṅgāraññaṃ majjhāraññaṃ mātaṅgāraññaṃ araññaṃ araññabhūtan”ti.**“I have, sir.”*";
P_HTM[810]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, kinti te sutaṃ kena taṃ daṇḍakīraññaṃ kāliṅgāraññaṃ majjhāraññaṃ mātaṅgāraññaṃ araññaṃ araññabhūtan”ti?**“What have you heard?”*";
P_HTM[811]="*“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, isīnaṃ manopadosena taṃ daṇḍakīraññaṃ kāliṅgāraññaṃ majjhāraññaṃ mātaṅgāraññaṃ araññaṃ araññabhūtan”ti.**“I heard that it was because of a malevolent act of will by hermits that the wildernesses of Daṇḍaka, Kāliṅga, Mejjha, and Mātaṅga came to be that way.”*";
P_HTM[812]="*“Manasi karohi, gahapati, manasi karitvā kho, gahapati, byākarohi.**“Think about it, householder! You should think before answering.*";
P_HTM[813]="*Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ, pacchimena vā purimaṃ.**What you said before and what you said after don’t match up.*";
P_HTM[814]="*Bhāsitā kho pana te, gahapati, esā vācā:**But you said that you would debate on the basis of truth.”*";
P_HTM[815]="*‘sacce ahaṃ, bhante, patiṭṭhāya mantessāmi;* **";
P_HTM[816]="*hotu no ettha kathāsallāpo’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[817]="*“Purimenevāhaṃ, bhante, opammena bhagavato attamano abhiraddho.**“Sir, I was already delighted and satisfied by the Buddha’s very first simile.*";
P_HTM[818]="*Api cāhaṃ imāni bhagavato vicitrāni pañhapaṭibhānāni sotukāmo, evāhaṃ bhagavantaṃ paccanīkaṃ kātabbaṃ amaññissaṃ.**Nevertheless, I wanted to hear the Buddha’s various solutions to the problem, so I thought I’d oppose you in this way.*";
P_HTM[819]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**Excellent, sir! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[820]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[821]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[822]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[823]="*“Anuviccakāraṃ kho, gahapati, karohi, anuviccakāro tumhādisānaṃ ñātamanussānaṃ sādhu hotī”ti.**“Householder, you should act after careful consideration. It’s good for well-known people such as yourself to act after careful consideration.”*";
P_HTM[824]="*“Imināpāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato bhiyyoso mattāya attamano abhiraddho yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evamāha: ‘anuviccakāraṃ kho, gahapati, karohi, anuviccakāro tumhādisānaṃ ñātamanussānaṃ sādhu hotī’ti.**“Now I’m even more delighted and satisfied with the Buddha, since he tells me to act after careful consideration.*";
P_HTM[825]="*Mañhi, bhante, aññatitthiyā sāvakaṃ labhitvā kevalakappaṃ nāḷandaṃ paṭākaṃ parihareyyuṃ:**For if the followers of other paths were to gain me as a disciple, they’d carry a banner all over Nāḷandā, saying:*";
P_HTM[826]="*‘upāli amhākaṃ gahapati sāvakattaṃ upagato’ti.**‘The householder Upāli has become our disciple!’*";
P_HTM[827]="*Atha ca pana maṃ bhagavā evamāha:**And yet the Buddha says:*";
P_HTM[828]="*‘anuviccakāraṃ kho, gahapati, karohi, anuviccakāro tumhādisānaṃ ñātamanussānaṃ sādhu hotī’ti.**‘Householder, you should act after careful consideration. It’s good for well-known people such as yourself to act after careful consideration.’*";
P_HTM[829]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, dutiyampi bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**For a second time, I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[830]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[831]="*“Dīgharattaṃ kho te, gahapati, nigaṇṭhānaṃ opānabhūtaṃ kulaṃ yena nesaṃ upagatānaṃ piṇḍakaṃ dātabbaṃ maññeyyāsī”ti.**“For a long time now, householder, your family has been a well-spring of support for the Jain ascetics. You should consider giving to them when they come.”*";
P_HTM[832]="*“Imināpāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato bhiyyoso mattāya attamano abhiraddho yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evamāha: ‘dīgharattaṃ kho te, gahapati, nigaṇṭhānaṃ opānabhūtaṃ kulaṃ yena nesaṃ upagatānaṃ piṇḍakaṃ dātabbaṃ maññeyyāsī’ti.**“Now I’m even more delighted and satisfied with the Buddha, since he tells me to consider giving to the Jain ascetics when they come.*";
P_HTM[833]="*Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, samaṇo gotamo evamāha:**I have heard, sir, that the ascetic Gotama says this:*";
P_HTM[834]="*‘mayhameva dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ;**‘Gifts should only be given to me, not to others.*";
P_HTM[835]="*mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dānaṃ dātabbaṃ;**Gifts should only be given to my disciples, not to the disciples of others.*";
P_HTM[836]="*mayhameva dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ;**Only what is given to me is very fruitful, not what is given to others.*";
P_HTM[837]="*mayhameva sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, nāññesaṃ sāvakānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalan’ti.**Only what is given to my disciples is very fruitful, not what is given to the disciples of others.’*";
P_HTM[838]="*Atha ca pana maṃ bhagavā nigaṇṭhesupi dāne samādapeti.**Yet the Buddha encourages me to give to the Jain ascetics.*";
P_HTM[839]="*Api ca, bhante, mayamettha kālaṃ jānissāma.**Well, sir, we’ll know the proper time for that.*";
P_HTM[840]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, tatiyampi bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**For a third time, I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[841]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[842]="*Atha kho bhagavā upālissa gahapatissa anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, seyyathidaṃ—**Then the Buddha taught the householder Upāli step by step, with*";
P_HTM[843]="*dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ, kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṃkilesaṃ, nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi.**a talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven. He explained the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[844]="*Yadā bhagavā aññāsi upāliṃ gahapatiṃ kallacittaṃ muducittaṃ vinīvaraṇacittaṃ udaggacittaṃ pasannacittaṃ, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā taṃ pakāsesi—**And when he knew that Upāli’s mind was ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas:*";
P_HTM[845]="*dukkhaṃ, samudayaṃ, nirodhaṃ, maggaṃ.**suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path.*";
P_HTM[846]="*Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya;**Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye,*";
P_HTM[847]="*evameva upālissa gahapatissa tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:**in that very seat the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in Upāli:*";
P_HTM[848]="*“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti.**“Everything that has a beginning has an end.”*";
P_HTM[849]="*Atha kho upāli gahapati diṭṭhadhammo pattadhammo viditadhammo pariyogāḷhadhammo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṃkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Upāli saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. He went beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[850]="*“handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante, gacchāma, bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**He said to the Buddha, “Well, now, sir, I must go. I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[851]="*“Yassadāni tvaṃ, gahapati, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, householder, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[852]="*Atha kho upāli gahapati bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena sakaṃ nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā dovārikaṃ āmantesi:**And then the householder Upāli approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. Then he went back to his own home, where he addressed the gatekeeper,*";
P_HTM[853]="*“ajjatagge, samma dovārika, āvarāmi dvāraṃ nigaṇṭhānaṃ nigaṇṭhīnaṃ, anāvaṭaṃ dvāraṃ bhagavato bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ.**“My good gatekeeper, from this day forth close the gate to Jain monks and nuns, and open it for the Buddha’s monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen.*";
P_HTM[854]="*Sace koci nigaṇṭho āgacchati tamenaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:**If any Jain ascetics come, say this to them:*";
P_HTM[855]="*‘tiṭṭha, bhante, mā pāvisi.**‘Wait, sir, do not enter.*";
P_HTM[856]="*Ajjatagge upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato.**From now on the householder Upāli has become a disciple of the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[857]="*Āvaṭaṃ dvāraṃ nigaṇṭhānaṃ nigaṇṭhīnaṃ, anāvaṭaṃ dvāraṃ bhagavato bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ.**His gate is closed to Jain monks and nuns, and opened for the Buddha’s monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen.*";
P_HTM[858]="*Sace te, bhante, piṇḍakena attho, ettheva tiṭṭha, ettheva te āharissantī’”ti.**If you require alms-food, wait here, they will bring it to you.’”*";
P_HTM[859]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho dovāriko upālissa gahapatissa paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied the gatekeeper.*";
P_HTM[860]="*Assosi kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho:**Dīgha Tapassī heard that*";
P_HTM[861]="*“upāli kira gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato”ti.**Upāli had become a disciple of the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[862]="*Atha kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**He went to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta and said to him,*";
P_HTM[863]="*“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, upāli kira gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato”ti.**“Sir, they say that the householder Upāli has become a disciple of the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[864]="*“Aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, tapassi, anavakāso yaṃ upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyya.**“It is impossible, Tapassī, it cannot happen that Upāli could become Gotama’s disciple.*";
P_HTM[865]="*Ṭhānañca kho etaṃ vijjati yaṃ samaṇo gotamo upālissa gahapatissa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyyā”ti.**But it is possible that Gotama could become Upāli’s disciple.”*";
P_HTM[866]="*Dutiyampi kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[867]="*tatiyampi kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time, Dīgha Tapassī said to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta,*";
P_HTM[868]="*“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante …**“Sir, they say that the householder Upāli has become a disciple of the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[869]="*pe …**“It is impossible, Tapassī, it cannot happen that Upāli could become Gotama’s disciple.*";
P_HTM[870]="*upālissa gahapatissa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyyā”ti.**But it is possible that Gotama could become Upāli’s disciple.”*";
P_HTM[871]="*“Handāhaṃ, bhante, gacchāmi yāva jānāmi yadi vā upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato yadi vā no”ti.**“Well, sir, I’d better go and find out whether or not Upāli has become Gotama’s disciple.”*";
P_HTM[872]="*“Gaccha tvaṃ, tapassi, jānāhi yadi vā upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato yadi vā no”ti.**“Go, Tapassī, and find out whether or not Upāli has become Gotama’s disciple.”*";
P_HTM[873]="*Atha kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho yena upālissa gahapatissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Then Dīgha Tapassī went to Upāli’s home.*";
P_HTM[874]="*Addasā kho dovāriko dīghatapassiṃ nigaṇṭhaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The gatekeeper saw him coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[875]="*Disvāna dīghatapassiṃ nigaṇṭhaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[876]="*“tiṭṭha, bhante, mā pāvisi.**“Wait, sir, do not enter.*";
P_HTM[877]="*Ajjatagge upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato.**From now on the householder Upāli has become a disciple of the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[878]="*Āvaṭaṃ dvāraṃ nigaṇṭhānaṃ nigaṇṭhīnaṃ, anāvaṭaṃ dvāraṃ bhagavato bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ.**His gate is closed to Jain monks and nuns, and opened for the Buddha’s monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen.*";
P_HTM[879]="*Sace te, bhante, piṇḍakena attho, ettheva tiṭṭha, ettheva te āharissantī”ti.**If you require alms-food, wait here, they will bring it to you.”*";
P_HTM[880]="*“Na me, āvuso, piṇḍakena attho”ti vatvā tato paṭinivattitvā yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**Saying, “No, mister, I do not require alms-food,” he turned back and went to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta and said to him,*";
P_HTM[881]="*“saccaṃyeva kho, bhante, yaṃ upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato.**“Sir, it’s really true that Upāli has become Gotama’s disciple.*";
P_HTM[882]="*Etaṃ kho te ahaṃ, bhante, nālatthaṃ, na kho me, bhante, ruccati yaṃ upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropeyya.**Sir, I couldn’t get you to accept that it wasn’t a good idea for the householder Upāli to rebut the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine.*";
P_HTM[883]="*Samaṇo hi, bhante, gotamo māyāvī āvaṭṭaniṃ māyaṃ jānāti yāya aññatitthiyānaṃ sāvake āvaṭṭetīti.**For the ascetic Gotama is a magician. He knows a conversion magic, and uses it to convert the disciples of those who follow other paths.*";
P_HTM[884]="*Āvaṭṭo kho te, bhante, upāli gahapati samaṇena gotamena āvaṭṭaniyā māyāyā”ti.**The householder Upāli has been converted by the ascetic Gotama’s conversion magic!”*";
P_HTM[885]="*“Aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, tapassi, anavakāso yaṃ upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyya.**“It is impossible, Tapassī, it cannot happen that Upāli could become Gotama’s disciple.*";
P_HTM[886]="*Ṭhānañca kho etaṃ vijjati yaṃ samaṇo gotamo upālissa gahapatissa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyyā”ti.**But it is possible that Gotama could become Upāli’s disciple.”*";
P_HTM[887]="*Dutiyampi kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[888]="*“saccaṃyeva, bhante … pe …* **";
P_HTM[889]="*upālissa gahapatissa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[890]="*Tatiyampi kho dīghatapassī nigaṇṭho nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time, Dīgha Tapassī told Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta*";
P_HTM[891]="*“saccaṃyeva kho, bhante …**that it was really true.*";
P_HTM[892]="*pe …**“It is impossible …*";
P_HTM[893]="*upālissa gahapatissa sāvakattaṃ upagaccheyyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[894]="*“Handa cāhaṃ, tapassi, gacchāmi yāva cāhaṃ sāmaṃyeva jānāmi yadi vā upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato yadi vā no”ti.**Well, Tapassī, I’d better go and find out for myself whether or not Upāli has become Gotama’s disciple.”*";
P_HTM[895]="*Atha kho nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto mahatiyā nigaṇṭhaparisāya saddhiṃ yena upālissa gahapatissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Then Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta went to Upāli’s home together with a large following of Jain ascetics.*";
P_HTM[896]="*Addasā kho dovāriko nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The gatekeeper saw him coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[897]="*Disvāna nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him:*";
P_HTM[898]="*“tiṭṭha, bhante, mā pāvisi.**‘Wait, sir, do not enter.*";
P_HTM[899]="*Ajjatagge upāli gahapati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakattaṃ upagato.**From now on the householder Upāli has become a disciple of the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[900]="*Āvaṭaṃ dvāraṃ nigaṇṭhānaṃ nigaṇṭhīnaṃ, anāvaṭaṃ dvāraṃ bhagavato bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ.**His gate is closed to Jain monks and nuns, and opened for the Buddha’s monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen.*";
P_HTM[901]="*Sace te, bhante, piṇḍakena attho, ettheva tiṭṭha, ettheva te āharissantī”ti.**If you require alms-food, wait here, they will bring it to you.”*";
P_HTM[902]="*“Tena hi, samma dovārika, yena upāli gahapati tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā upāliṃ gahapatiṃ evaṃ vadehi:**“Well then, my good gatekeeper, go to Upāli and say:*";
P_HTM[903]="*‘nigaṇṭho, bhante, nāṭaputto mahatiyā nigaṇṭhaparisāya saddhiṃ bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhito;**‘Sir, Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta is waiting outside the gates together with a large following of Jain ascetics.*";
P_HTM[904]="*so te dassanakāmo’”ti.**He wishes to see you.’”*";
P_HTM[905]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho dovāriko nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa paṭissutvā yena upāli gahapati tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā upāliṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” replied the gatekeeper. He went to Upāli and relayed what was said.*";
P_HTM[906]="*“nigaṇṭho, bhante, nāṭaputto mahatiyā nigaṇṭhaparisāya saddhiṃ bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhito;* **";
P_HTM[907]="*so te dassanakāmo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[908]="*“Tena hi, samma dovārika, majjhimāya dvārasālāya āsanāni paññapehī”ti.**Upāli said to him, “Well, then, my good gatekeeper, prepare seats in the hall of the middle gate.”*";
P_HTM[909]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho dovāriko upālissa gahapatissa paṭissutvā majjhimāya dvārasālāya āsanāni paññapetvā yena upāli gahapati tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā upāliṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” replied the gatekeeper. He did as he was asked, then returned to Upāli and said,*";
P_HTM[910]="*“paññattāni kho, bhante, majjhimāya dvārasālāya āsanāni.**“Sir, seats have been prepared in the hall of the middle gate.*";
P_HTM[911]="*Yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**Please go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[912]="*Atha kho upāli gahapati yena majjhimā dvārasālā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā yaṃ tattha āsanaṃ aggañca seṭṭhañca uttamañca paṇītañca tattha sāmaṃ nisīditvā dovārikaṃ āmantesi:**Then Upāli went to the hall of the middle gate, where he sat on the highest and finest seat. He addressed the gatekeeper,*";
P_HTM[913]="*“tena hi, samma dovārika, yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ evaṃ vadehi:**“Well then, my good gatekeeper, go to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta and say to him:*";
P_HTM[914]="*‘upāli, bhante, gahapati evamāha—**‘Sir, Upāli says*";
P_HTM[915]="*pavisa kira, bhante, sace ākaṅkhasī’”ti.**you may enter if you wish.’”*";
P_HTM[916]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho dovāriko upālissa gahapatissa paṭissutvā yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” replied the gatekeeper. He went to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta and relayed what was said.*";
P_HTM[917]="*“upāli, bhante, gahapati evamāha:* **";
P_HTM[918]="*‘pavisa kira, bhante, sace ākaṅkhasī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[919]="*Atha kho nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto mahatiyā nigaṇṭhaparisāya saddhiṃ yena majjhimā dvārasālā tenupasaṅkami.**Then Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta went to the hall of the middle gate together with a large following of Jain ascetics.*";
P_HTM[920]="*Atha kho upāli gahapati—* **";
P_HTM[921]="*yaṃ sudaṃ pubbe yato passati nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ disvāna tato paccuggantvā yaṃ tattha āsanaṃ aggañca seṭṭhañca uttamañca paṇītañca taṃ uttarāsaṅgena sammajjitvā pariggahetvā nisīdāpeti so—**Previously, when Upāli saw Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta coming, he would go out to greet him and, having wiped off the highest and finest seat with his upper robe, he would put his arms around him and sit him down.*";
P_HTM[922]="*dāni yaṃ tattha āsanaṃ aggañca seṭṭhañca uttamañca paṇītañca tattha sāmaṃ nisīditvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**But today, having seated himself on the highest and finest seat, he said to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta,*";
P_HTM[923]="*“saṃvijjanti kho, bhante, āsanāni;**“There are seats, sir.*";
P_HTM[924]="*sace ākaṅkhasi, nisīdā”ti.**Please sit if you wish.”*";
P_HTM[925]="*Evaṃ vutte, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto upāliṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta said to him:*";
P_HTM[926]="*“ummattosi tvaṃ, gahapati, dattosi tvaṃ, gahapati.**“You’re mad, householder! You’re a moron!*";
P_HTM[927]="*‘Gacchāmahaṃ, bhante, samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropessāmī’ti gantvā mahatāsi vādasaṅghāṭena paṭimukko āgato.**You said: ‘I’ll go and refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine.’ But you come back caught in the vast net of his doctrine.*";
P_HTM[928]="*Seyyathāpi, gahapati, puriso aṇḍahārako gantvā ubbhatehi aṇḍehi āgaccheyya, seyyathā vā pana gahapati puriso akkhikahārako gantvā ubbhatehi akkhīhi āgaccheyya;**Suppose a man went to deliver a pair of balls, but came back castrated. Or they went to deliver eyes, but came back blinded.*";
P_HTM[929]="*evameva kho tvaṃ, gahapati, ‘gacchāmahaṃ, bhante, samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropessāmī’ti gantvā mahatāsi vādasaṅghāṭena paṭimukko āgato.**In the same way, you said: ‘I’ll go and refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine.’ But you come back caught in the vast net of his doctrine.*";
P_HTM[930]="*Āvaṭṭosi kho tvaṃ, gahapati, samaṇena gotamena āvaṭṭaniyā māyāyā”ti.**You’ve been converted by the ascetic Gotama’s conversion magic!”*";
P_HTM[931]="*“Bhaddikā, bhante, āvaṭṭanī māyā;**“Sir, this conversion magic is excellent.*";
P_HTM[932]="*kalyāṇī, bhante, āvaṭṭanī māyā;**This conversion magic is lovely!*";
P_HTM[933]="*piyā me, bhante, ñātisālohitā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ; piyānampi me assa ñātisālohitānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya;**If my loved ones—relatives and kin—were to be converted by this, it would be for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[934]="*sabbe cepi, bhante, khattiyā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ; sabbesānampissa khattiyānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya; sabbe cepi, bhante, brāhmaṇā … pe … vessā … pe … suddā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ; sabbesānampissa suddānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya;**If all the aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers were to be converted by this, it would be for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[935]="*sadevako cepi, bhante, loko samārako sabrahmako sassamaṇabrāhmaṇī pajā sadevamanussā imāya āvaṭṭaniyā āvaṭṭeyyuṃ; sadevakassapissa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyāti.**If the whole world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—were to be converted by this, it would be for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[936]="*Tena hi, bhante, upamaṃ te karissāmi.**Well then, sir, I shall give you a simile.*";
P_HTM[937]="*Upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti.**For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said.*";
P_HTM[938]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhante, aññatarassa brāhmaṇassa jiṇṇassa vuḍḍhassa mahallakassa daharā māṇavikā pajāpatī ahosi gabbhinī upavijaññā.**Once upon a time there was an old brahmin, elderly and senior. His wife was a young brahmin lady who was pregnant and approaching the time for giving birth.*";
P_HTM[939]="*Atha kho, bhante, sā māṇavikā taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca,**Then she said to the brahmin,*";
P_HTM[940]="*‘gaccha tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, āpaṇā makkaṭacchāpakaṃ kiṇitvā ānehi, yo me kumārakassa kīḷāpanako bhavissatī’ti.**‘Go, brahmin, buy a baby monkey from the market and bring it back so it can be a playmate for my child.’*";
P_HTM[941]="*Evaṃ vutte, so brāhmaṇo taṃ māṇavikaṃ etadavoca:**When she said this, the brahmin said to her,*";
P_HTM[942]="*‘āgamehi tāva, bhoti, yāva vijāyati.**‘Wait, my dear, until you give birth.*";
P_HTM[943]="*Sace tvaṃ, bhoti, kumārakaṃ vijāyissasi, tassā te ahaṃ āpaṇā makkaṭacchāpakaṃ kiṇitvā ānessāmi, yo te kumārakassa kīḷāpanako bhavissati.**If your child is a boy, I’ll buy you a male monkey,*";
P_HTM[944]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, bhoti, kumārikaṃ vijāyissasi, tassā te ahaṃ āpaṇā makkaṭacchāpikaṃ kiṇitvā ānessāmi, yā te kumārikāya kīḷāpanikā bhavissatī’ti.**but if it’s a girl, I’ll buy a female monkey.’*";
P_HTM[945]="*Dutiyampi kho, bhante, sā māṇavikā … pe …**For a second time,*";
P_HTM[946]="*tatiyampi kho, bhante, sā māṇavikā taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time she said to the brahmin,*";
P_HTM[947]="*‘gaccha tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, āpaṇā makkaṭacchāpakaṃ kiṇitvā ānehi, yo me kumārakassa kīḷāpanako bhavissatī’ti.**‘Go, brahmin, buy a baby monkey from the market and bring it back so it can be a playmate for my child.’*";
P_HTM[948]="*Atha kho, bhante, so brāhmaṇo tassā māṇavikāya sāratto paṭibaddhacitto āpaṇā makkaṭacchāpakaṃ kiṇitvā ānetvā taṃ māṇavikaṃ etadavoca:**Then that brahmin, because of his love for the brahmin lady, bought a male baby monkey at the market, brought it to her, and said,*";
P_HTM[949]="*‘ayaṃ te, bhoti, āpaṇā makkaṭacchāpako kiṇitvā ānīto, yo te kumārakassa kīḷāpanako bhavissatī’ti.**‘I’ve bought this male baby monkey for you so it can be a playmate for your child.’*";
P_HTM[950]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, sā māṇavikā taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, she said to him,*";
P_HTM[951]="*‘gaccha tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imaṃ makkaṭacchāpakaṃ ādāya yena rattapāṇi rajakaputto tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā rattapāṇiṃ rajakaputtaṃ evaṃ vadehi—**‘Go, brahmin, take this monkey to Rattapāṇi the dyer and say,*";
P_HTM[952]="*icchāmahaṃ, samma rattapāṇi, imaṃ makkaṭacchāpakaṃ pītāvalepanaṃ nāma raṅgajātaṃ rajitaṃ ākoṭitapaccākoṭitaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhan’ti.**“Mister Rattapāṇi, I wish to have this monkey dyed the color of yellow greasepaint, pounded and re-pounded, and pressed on both sides.”’*";
P_HTM[953]="*Atha kho, bhante, so brāhmaṇo tassā māṇavikāya sāratto paṭibaddhacitto taṃ makkaṭacchāpakaṃ ādāya yena rattapāṇi rajakaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rattapāṇiṃ rajakaputtaṃ etadavoca:**Then that brahmin, because of his love for the brahmin lady, took the monkey to Rattapāṇi the dyer and said,*";
P_HTM[954]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, samma rattapāṇi, imaṃ makkaṭacchāpakaṃ pītāvalepanaṃ nāma raṅgajātaṃ rajitaṃ ākoṭitapaccākoṭitaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhan’ti.**‘Mister Rattapāṇi, I wish to have this monkey dyed the color of yellow greasepaint, pounded and re-pounded, and pressed on both sides.’*";
P_HTM[955]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, rattapāṇi rajakaputto taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Rattapāṇi said to him,*";
P_HTM[956]="*‘ayaṃ kho te, bhante, makkaṭacchāpako raṅgakkhamo hi kho, no ākoṭanakkhamo, no vimajjanakkhamo’ti.**‘Sir, this monkey can withstand a dying, but not a pounding or a pressing.’*";
P_HTM[957]="*Evameva kho, bhante, bālānaṃ nigaṇṭhānaṃ vādo raṅgakkhamo hi kho bālānaṃ no paṇḍitānaṃ, no anuyogakkhamo, no vimajjanakkhamo.**In the same way, the doctrine of the foolish Jains looks fine initially—for fools, not for the astute—but can’t withstand being scrutinized or pressed.*";
P_HTM[958]="*Atha kho, bhante, so brāhmaṇo aparena samayena navaṃ dussayugaṃ ādāya yena rattapāṇi rajakaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rattapāṇiṃ rajakaputtaṃ etadavoca:**Then some time later that brahmin took a new pair of garments to Rattapāṇi the dyer and said,*";
P_HTM[959]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, samma rattapāṇi, imaṃ navaṃ dussayugaṃ pītāvalepanaṃ nāma raṅgajātaṃ rajitaṃ ākoṭitapaccākoṭitaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhan’ti.**‘Mister Rattapāṇi, I wish to have this new pair of garments dyed the color of yellow greasepaint, pounded and re-pounded, and pressed on both sides.’*";
P_HTM[960]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, rattapāṇi rajakaputto taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Rattapāṇi said to him,*";
P_HTM[961]="*‘idaṃ kho te, bhante, navaṃ dussayugaṃ raṅgakkhamañceva ākoṭanakkhamañca vimajjanakkhamañcā’ti.**‘Sir, this pair of garments can withstand a dying, a pounding, and a pressing.’*";
P_HTM[962]="*Evameva kho, bhante, tassa bhagavato vādo arahato sammāsambuddhassa raṅgakkhamo ceva paṇḍitānaṃ no bālānaṃ, anuyogakkhamo ca vimajjanakkhamo cā”ti.**In the same way, the doctrine of the Buddha looks fine initially—for the astute, not for fools—and it can withstand being scrutinized and pressed.”*";
P_HTM[963]="*“Sarājikā kho, gahapati, parisā evaṃ jānāti:**“Householder, the king and his retinue know you as*";
P_HTM[964]="*‘upāli gahapati nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa sāvako’ti.**a disciple of Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta.*";
P_HTM[965]="*Kassa taṃ, gahapati, sāvakaṃ dhāremā”ti?**Whose disciple should we remember you as?”*";
P_HTM[966]="*Evaṃ vutte, upāli gahapati uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, the householder Upāli got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms in the direction of the Buddha, and said to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta,*";
P_HTM[967]="*“tena hi, bhante, suṇohi yassāhaṃ sāvako”ti:**“Well then, sir, hear whose disciple I am:*";
P_HTM[968]="*“Dhīrassa vigatamohassa,**The wise one, free of delusion,*";
P_HTM[969]="*Pabhinnakhīlassa vijitavijayassa;**rid of barrenness, victor in battle;*";
P_HTM[970]="*Anīghassa susamacittassa,**he’s untroubled and so even-minded,*";
P_HTM[971]="*Vuddhasīlassa sādhupaññassa;**with the virtue of an elder and the wisdom of a saint,*";
P_HTM[972]="*Vesamantarassa vimalassa,**immaculate in the midst of it all:*";
P_HTM[973]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[974]="*Akathaṅkathissa tusitassa,**He has no indecision, he’s content,*";
P_HTM[975]="*Vantalokāmisassa muditassa;**joyful, he has spat out the world’s bait;*";
P_HTM[976]="*Katasamaṇassa manujassa,**he has completed the ascetic’s task as a human,*";
P_HTM[977]="*Antimasārīrassa narassa;**a man who bears his final body;*";
P_HTM[978]="*Anopamassa virajassa,**he’s beyond compare, he’s stainless:*";
P_HTM[979]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[980]="*Asaṃsayassa kusalassa,**He’s free of doubt, he’s skillful,*";
P_HTM[981]="*Venayikassa sārathivarassa;**he’s a trainer, an excellent charioteer;*";
P_HTM[982]="*Anuttarassa ruciradhammassa,**supreme, with brilliant qualities,*";
P_HTM[983]="*Nikkaṅkhassa pabhāsakassa;**confident, his light shines forth;*";
P_HTM[984]="*Mānacchidassa vīrassa,**he has cut off conceit, he’s a hero:*";
P_HTM[985]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[986]="*Nisabhassa appameyyassa,**The chief bull, immeasurable,*";
P_HTM[987]="*Gambhīrassa monapattassa;**profound, sagacious;*";
P_HTM[988]="*Khemaṅkarassa vedassa,**he is the builder of sanctuary, knowledgeable,*";
P_HTM[989]="*Dhammaṭṭhassa saṃvutattassa;**firm in principle and restrained;*";
P_HTM[990]="*Saṅgātigassa muttassa,**he has got over clinging and is liberated:*";
P_HTM[991]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[992]="*Nāgassa pantasenassa,**He’s a giant, living remotely,*";
P_HTM[993]="*Khīṇasaṃyojanassa muttassa;**he’s ended the fetters and is liberated;*";
P_HTM[994]="*Paṭimantakassa dhonassa,**he’s skilled in dialogue and cleansed,*";
P_HTM[995]="*Pannadhajassa vītarāgassa;**with banner put down, desireless;*";
P_HTM[996]="*Dantassa nippapañcassa,**he’s tamed, and doesn’t proliferate:*";
P_HTM[997]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[998]="*Isisattamassa akuhassa,**He is the seventh sage, free of deceit,*";
P_HTM[999]="*Tevijjassa brahmapattassa;**with three knowledges, he has attained to holiness,*";
P_HTM[1000]="*Nhātakassa padakassa,**he has bathed, he knows philology,*";
P_HTM[1001]="*Passaddhassa viditavedassa;**he’s tranquil, he understands what is known;*";
P_HTM[1002]="*Purindadassa sakkassa,**he crushes resistance, he is the lord:*";
P_HTM[1003]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[1004]="*Ariyassa bhāvitattassa,**The noble one, self-developed,*";
P_HTM[1005]="*Pattipattassa veyyākaraṇassa;**he has attained the goal and explains it;*";
P_HTM[1006]="*Satimato vipassissa,**he is mindful, discerning,*";
P_HTM[1007]="*Anabhinatassa no apanatassa;**neither leaning forward nor pulling back,*";
P_HTM[1008]="*Anejassa vasippattassa,**he’s unstirred, attained to mastery:*";
P_HTM[1009]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[1010]="*Samuggatassa jhāyissa,**He has risen up, he practices absorption,*";
P_HTM[1011]="*Ananugatantarassa suddhassa;**not following inner thoughts, he is pure,*";
P_HTM[1012]="*Asitassa hitassa,**independent, and fearless;*";
P_HTM[1013]="*Pavivittassa aggappattassa;**secluded, he has reached the peak,*";
P_HTM[1014]="*Tiṇṇassa tārayantassa,**crossed over, he helps others across:*";
P_HTM[1015]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[1016]="*Santassa bhūripaññassa,**He’s peaceful, his wisdom is vast,*";
P_HTM[1017]="*Mahāpaññassa vītalobhassa;**with great wisdom, he’s free of greed;*";
P_HTM[1018]="*Tathāgatassa sugatassa,**he is the Realized One, the Holy One,*";
P_HTM[1019]="*Appaṭipuggalassa asamassa;**unrivaled, unequaled,*";
P_HTM[1020]="*Visāradassa nipuṇassa,**assured, and subtle:*";
P_HTM[1021]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmi.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[1022]="*Taṇhacchidassa buddhassa,**He has cut off craving and is awakened,*";
P_HTM[1023]="*Vītadhūmassa anupalittassa;**free of fuming, unsullied;*";
P_HTM[1024]="*Āhuneyyassa yakkhassa,**a mighty spirit worthy of offerings,*";
P_HTM[1025]="*Uttamapuggalassa atulassa;**best of men, inestimable,*";
P_HTM[1026]="*Mahato yasaggapattassa,**grand, he has reached the peak of glory:*";
P_HTM[1027]="*Bhagavato tassa sāvakohamasmī”ti.**he is the Buddha, and I am his disciple.”*";
P_HTM[1028]="*“Kadā saññūḷhā pana te, gahapati, ime samaṇassa gotamassa vaṇṇā”ti?**“But when did you compose these praises of the ascetic Gotama’s beautiful qualities, householder?”*";
P_HTM[1029]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhante, nānāpupphānaṃ mahāpuppharāsi, tamenaṃ dakkho mālākāro vā mālākārantevāsī vā vicittaṃ mālaṃ gantheyya;**“Sir, suppose there was a large heap of many different flowers. A deft garland-maker or their apprentice could tie them into a colorful garland.*";
P_HTM[1030]="*evameva kho, bhante, so bhagavā anekavaṇṇo anekasatavaṇṇo.**In the same way, the Buddha has many beautiful qualities to praise, many hundreds of such qualities.*";
P_HTM[1031]="*Ko hi, bhante, vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ na karissatī”ti?**Who, sir, would not praise the praiseworthy?”*";
P_HTM[1032]="*Atha kho nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa bhagavato sakkāraṃ asahamānassa tattheva uṇhaṃ lohitaṃ mukhato uggacchīti.**Unable to bear this honor paid to the Buddha, Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta spewed hot blood from his mouth there and then.*";
P_HTM[1033]="*Upālisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1034]="*57. Kukkuravatikasutta**The Ascetic Who Behaved Like a Dog*";
P_HTM[1035]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[1036]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā koliyesu viharati haliddavasanaṃ nāma koliyānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Koliyans, where they have a town named Haliddavasana.*";
P_HTM[1037]="*Atha kho puṇṇo ca koliyaputto govatiko acelo ca seniyo kukkuravatiko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Acelo pana seniyo kukkuravatiko bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā kukkurova palikujjitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Then Puṇṇa Koliyaputta, who had taken a vow to behave like a cow, and Seniya, a naked ascetic who had taken a vow to behave like a dog, went to see the Buddha. Puṇṇa bowed to the Buddha and sat down to one side, while Seniya exchanged greetings and polite conversation with him before sitting down to one side curled up like a dog.*";
P_HTM[1038]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Puṇṇa said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1039]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, acelo seniyo kukkuravatiko dukkarakārako chamānikkhittaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjati.**“Sir, this naked dog ascetic Seniya does a hard thing: he eats food placed on the ground.*";
P_HTM[1040]="*Tassa taṃ kukkuravataṃ dīgharattaṃ samattaṃ samādinnaṃ.**For a long time he has undertaken that observance to behave like a dog.*";
P_HTM[1041]="*Tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where will he be reborn in his next life?”*";
P_HTM[1042]="*“Alaṃ, puṇṇa, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī”ti.**“Enough, Puṇṇa, let it be. Don’t ask me that.”*";
P_HTM[1043]="*Dutiyampi kho puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[1044]="*tatiyampi kho puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time, Puṇṇa said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1045]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, acelo seniyo kukkuravatiko dukkarakārako chamānikkhittaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjati.**“Sir, this naked dog ascetic Seniya does a hard thing: he eats food placed on the ground.*";
P_HTM[1046]="*Tassa taṃ kukkuravataṃ dīgharattaṃ samattaṃ samādinnaṃ.**For a long time he has undertaken that observance to behave like a dog.*";
P_HTM[1047]="*Tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where will he be reborn in his next life?”*";
P_HTM[1048]="*“Addhā kho te ahaṃ, puṇṇa, na labhāmi.**“Clearly, Puṇṇa, I’m not getting through to you when I say:*";
P_HTM[1049]="*Alaṃ, puṇṇa, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchīti;**‘Enough, Puṇṇa, let it be. Don’t ask me that.’*";
P_HTM[1050]="*api ca tyāhaṃ byākarissāmi.**Nevertheless, I will answer you.*";
P_HTM[1051]="*Idha, puṇṇa, ekacco kukkuravataṃ bhāveti paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, kukkurasīlaṃ bhāveti paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, kukkuracittaṃ bhāveti paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, kukkurākappaṃ bhāveti paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ.**Take someone who develops the dog observance fully and uninterruptedly. They develop a dog’s ethics, a dog’s mentality, and a dog’s behavior fully and uninterruptedly.*";
P_HTM[1052]="*So kukkuravataṃ bhāvetvā paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, kukkurasīlaṃ bhāvetvā paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, kukkuracittaṃ bhāvetvā paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, kukkurākappaṃ bhāvetvā paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā kukkurānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of dogs.*";
P_HTM[1053]="*Sace kho panassa evaṃdiṭṭhi hoti: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti, sāssa hoti micchādiṭṭhi.**But if they have such a view: ‘By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life, may I become one of the gods!’ This is their wrong view.*";
P_HTM[1054]="*Micchādiṭṭhissa kho ahaṃ, puṇṇa, dvinnaṃ gatīnaṃ aññataraṃ gatiṃ vadāmi—nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā.**An individual with wrong view is reborn in one of two places, I say: hell or the animal realm.*";
P_HTM[1055]="*Iti kho, puṇṇa, sampajjamānaṃ kukkuravataṃ kukkurānaṃ sahabyataṃ upaneti, vipajjamānaṃ nirayan”ti.**So if the dog observance succeeds it leads to rebirth in the company of dogs, but if it fails it leads to hell.”*";
P_HTM[1056]="*Evaṃ vutte, acelo seniyo kukkuravatiko parodi, assūni pavattesi.**When he said this, Seniya cried and burst out in tears.*";
P_HTM[1057]="*Atha kho bhagavā puṇṇaṃ koliyaputtaṃ govatikaṃ etadavoca:**The Buddha said to Puṇṇa,*";
P_HTM[1058]="*“etaṃ kho te ahaṃ, puṇṇa, nālatthaṃ.**“This is what I didn’t get through to you when I said:*";
P_HTM[1059]="*Alaṃ, puṇṇa, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī”ti.**‘Enough, Puṇṇa, let it be. Don’t ask me that.’”*";
P_HTM[1060]="*“Nāhaṃ, bhante, etaṃ rodāmi yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evamāha;**“Sir, I’m not crying because of what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[1061]="*api ca me idaṃ, bhante, kukkuravataṃ dīgharattaṃ samattaṃ samādinnaṃ.**But, sir, for a long time I have undertaken this observance to behave like a dog.*";
P_HTM[1062]="*Ayaṃ, bhante, puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko.**Sir, this Puṇṇa has taken a vow to behave like a cow.*";
P_HTM[1063]="*Tassa taṃ govataṃ dīgharattaṃ samattaṃ samādinnaṃ.**For a long time he has undertaken that observance to behave like a cow.*";
P_HTM[1064]="*Tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where will he be reborn in his next life?”*";
P_HTM[1065]="*“Alaṃ, seniya, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī”ti.**“Enough, Seniya, let it be. Don’t ask me that.”*";
P_HTM[1066]="*Dutiyampi kho acelo seniyo … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[1067]="*tatiyampi kho acelo seniyo kukkuravatiko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time Seniya said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1068]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko.**“Sir, this Puṇṇa has taken a vow to behave like a cow.*";
P_HTM[1069]="*Tassa taṃ govataṃ dīgharattaṃ samattaṃ samādinnaṃ.**For a long time he has undertaken that observance to behave like a cow.*";
P_HTM[1070]="*Tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where will he be reborn in his next life?”*";
P_HTM[1071]="*“Addhā kho te ahaṃ, seniya, na labhāmi.**“Clearly, Seniya, I’m not getting through to you when I say:*";
P_HTM[1072]="*Alaṃ, seniya, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchīti;**‘Enough, Seniya, let it be. Don’t ask me that.’*";
P_HTM[1073]="*api ca tyāhaṃ byākarissāmi.**Nevertheless, I will answer you.*";
P_HTM[1074]="*Idha, seniya, ekacco govataṃ bhāveti paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, gosīlaṃ bhāveti paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, gocittaṃ bhāveti paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, gavākappaṃ bhāveti paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ.**Take someone who develops the cow observance fully and uninterruptedly. They develop a cow’s ethics, a cow’s mentality, and a cow’s behavior fully and uninterruptedly.*";
P_HTM[1075]="*So govataṃ bhāvetvā paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, gosīlaṃ bhāvetvā paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, gocittaṃ bhāvetvā paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ, gavākappaṃ bhāvetvā paripuṇṇaṃ abbokiṇṇaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā gunnaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of cows.*";
P_HTM[1076]="*Sace kho panassa evaṃdiṭṭhi hoti: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti, sāssa hoti micchādiṭṭhi.**But if they have such a view: ‘By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life, may I become one of the gods!’ This is their wrong view.*";
P_HTM[1077]="*Micchādiṭṭhissa kho ahaṃ, seniya, dvinnaṃ gatīnaṃ aññataraṃ gatiṃ vadāmi—nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā.**An individual with wrong view is reborn in one of two places, I say: hell or the animal realm.*";
P_HTM[1078]="*Iti kho, seniya, sampajjamānaṃ govataṃ gunnaṃ sahabyataṃ upaneti, vipajjamānaṃ nirayan”ti.**So if the cow observance succeeds it leads to rebirth in the company of cows, but if it fails it leads to hell.”*";
P_HTM[1079]="*Evaṃ vutte, puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko parodi, assūni pavattesi.**When he said this, Puṇṇa cried and burst out in tears.*";
P_HTM[1080]="*Atha kho bhagavā acelaṃ seniyaṃ kukkuravatikaṃ etadavoca:**The Buddha said to Seniya,*";
P_HTM[1081]="*“etaṃ kho te ahaṃ, seniya, nālatthaṃ.**“This is what I didn’t get through to you when I said:*";
P_HTM[1082]="*Alaṃ, seniya, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī”ti.**‘Enough, Seniya, let it be. Don’t ask me that.’”*";
P_HTM[1083]="*“Nāhaṃ, bhante, etaṃ rodāmi yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evamāha;**“Sir, I’m not crying because of what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[1084]="*api ca me idaṃ, bhante, govataṃ dīgharattaṃ samattaṃ samādinnaṃ.**But, sir, for a long time I have undertaken this observance to behave like a cow.*";
P_HTM[1085]="*Evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati;**I am quite confident that the Buddha*";
P_HTM[1086]="*pahoti bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetuṃ yathā ahaṃ cevimaṃ govataṃ pajaheyyaṃ, ayañceva acelo seniyo kukkuravatiko taṃ kukkuravataṃ pajaheyyā”ti.**is capable of teaching me so that I can give up this cow observance, and the naked ascetic Seniya can give up that dog observance.”*";
P_HTM[1087]="*“Tena hi, puṇṇa, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, Puṇṇa, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[1088]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” he replied.*";
P_HTM[1089]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[1090]="*“Cattārimāni, puṇṇa, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni.**“Puṇṇa, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with my own insight.*";
P_HTM[1091]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1092]="*Atthi, puṇṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ;**There are dark deeds with dark results;*";
P_HTM[1093]="*atthi, puṇṇa, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ;**bright deeds with bright results;*";
P_HTM[1094]="*atthi, puṇṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ;**dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results; and*";
P_HTM[1095]="*atthi, puṇṇa, kammaṃ akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ, kammakkhayāya saṃvattati.**neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[1096]="*Katamañca, puṇṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ?**And what are dark deeds with dark results?*";
P_HTM[1097]="*Idha, puṇṇa, ekacco sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes hurtful choices by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1098]="*So sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**Having made these choices, they’re reborn in a hurtful world,*";
P_HTM[1099]="*Tamenaṃ sabyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ sabyābajjhā phassā phusanti.**where hurtful contacts touch them.*";
P_HTM[1100]="*So sabyābajjhehi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno sabyābajjhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti ekantadukkhaṃ, seyyathāpi sattā nerayikā.**Touched by hurtful contacts, they experience hurtful feelings that are exclusively painful—like the beings in hell.*";
P_HTM[1101]="*Iti kho, puṇṇa, bhūtā bhūtassa upapatti hoti;**This is how a being is born from a being.*";
P_HTM[1102]="*yaṃ karoti tena upapajjati,**For your deeds determine your rebirth,*";
P_HTM[1103]="*upapannamenaṃ phassā phusanti.**and when you’re reborn contacts affect you.*";
P_HTM[1104]="*Evampāhaṃ, puṇṇa, ‘kammadāyādā sattā’ti vadāmi.**This is why I say that sentient beings are heirs to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[1105]="*Idaṃ vuccati, puṇṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ. (1)**These are called dark deeds with dark results.*";
P_HTM[1106]="*Katamañca, puṇṇa, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?**And what are bright deeds with bright results?*";
P_HTM[1107]="*Idha, puṇṇa, ekacco abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, abyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, abyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1108]="*So abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, abyābajjhaṃ vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, abyābajjhaṃ manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā abyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**Having made these choices, they are reborn in a pleasing world,*";
P_HTM[1109]="*Tamenaṃ abyābajjhaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ abyābajjhā phassā phusanti.**where pleasing contacts touch them.*";
P_HTM[1110]="*So abyābajjhehi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno abyābajjhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti ekantasukhaṃ, seyyathāpi devā subhakiṇhā.**Touched by pleasing contacts, they experience pleasing feelings that are exclusively happy—like the gods replete with glory.*";
P_HTM[1111]="*Iti kho, puṇṇa, bhūtā bhūtassa upapatti hoti;**This is how a being is born from a being.*";
P_HTM[1112]="*yaṃ karoti tena upapajjati,**For your deeds determine your rebirth,*";
P_HTM[1113]="*upapannamenaṃ phassā phusanti.**and when you’re reborn contacts affect you.*";
P_HTM[1114]="*Evampāhaṃ, puṇṇa, ‘kammadāyādā sattā’ti vadāmi.**This is why I say that sentient beings are heirs to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[1115]="*Idaṃ vuccati, puṇṇa, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ. (2)**These are called bright deeds with bright results.*";
P_HTM[1116]="*Katamañca, puṇṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?**And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?*";
P_HTM[1117]="*Idha, puṇṇa, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti.**It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1118]="*So sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā, sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharitvā sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi lokaṃ upapajjati.**Having made these choices, they are reborn in a world that is both hurtful and pleasing,*";
P_HTM[1119]="*Tamenaṃ sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi lokaṃ upapannaṃ samānaṃ sabyābajjhāpi abyābajjhāpi phassā phusanti.**where hurtful and pleasing contacts touch them.*";
P_HTM[1120]="*So sabyābajjhehipi abyābajjhehipi phassehi phuṭṭho samāno sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi vedanaṃ vedeti vokiṇṇasukhadukkhaṃ, seyyathāpi manussā ekacce ca devā ekacce ca vinipātikā.**Touched by both hurtful and pleasing contacts, they experience both hurtful and pleasing feelings that are a mixture of pleasure and pain—like humans, some gods, and some beings in the underworld.*";
P_HTM[1121]="*Iti kho, puṇṇa, bhūtā bhūtassa upapatti hoti;**This is how a being is born from a being.*";
P_HTM[1122]="*yaṃ karoti tena upapajjati.**For what you do brings about your rebirth,*";
P_HTM[1123]="*Upapannamenaṃ phassā phusanti.**and when you’re reborn contacts affect you.*";
P_HTM[1124]="*Evampāhaṃ, puṇṇa, ‘kammadāyādā sattā’ti vadāmi.**This is why I say that sentient beings are heirs to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[1125]="*Idaṃ vuccati, puṇṇa, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ. (3)**These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[1126]="*Katamañca, puṇṇa, kammaṃ akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ, kammakkhayāya saṃvattati?**And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds?*";
P_HTM[1127]="*Tatra, puṇṇa, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā, yamidaṃ kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ tassa pahānāya yā cetanā—**It’s the intention to give up dark deeds with dark results, bright deeds with bright results, and both dark and bright deeds with both dark and bright results.*";
P_HTM[1128]="*idaṃ vuccati, puṇṇa, kammaṃ akaṇhaṃ asukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ, kammakkhayāya saṃvattatīti.**These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds.*";
P_HTM[1129]="*Imāni kho, puṇṇa, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditānī”ti. (4)**These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with my own insight.”*";
P_HTM[1130]="*Evaṃ vutte, puṇṇo koliyaputto govatiko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Puṇṇa Koliyaputta the observer of cow behavior said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1131]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**“Excellent, sir! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[1132]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1133]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[1134]="*Acelo pana seniyo kukkuravatiko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**And Seniya the naked dog ascetic said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1135]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**“Excellent, sir! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[1136]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante … pe … pakāsito.* **";
P_HTM[1137]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[1138]="*Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti.**Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”*";
P_HTM[1139]="*“Yo kho, seniya, aññatitthiyapubbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhati pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhati upasampadaṃ so cattāro māse parivasati. Catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti, upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya.**“Seniya, if someone formerly ordained in another sect wishes to take the going forth, the ordination in this teaching and training, they must spend four months on probation. When four months have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, they’ll give the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.*";
P_HTM[1140]="*Api ca mettha puggalavemattatā viditā”ti.**However, I have recognized individual differences in this matter.”*";
P_HTM[1141]="*“Sace, bhante, aññatitthiyapubbā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhantā pabbajjaṃ ākaṅkhantā upasampadaṃ te cattāro māse parivasanti catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya, ahaṃ cattāri vassāni parivasissāmi catunnaṃ vassānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājentu, upasampādentu bhikkhubhāvāyā”ti.**“Sir, if four months probation are required in such a case, I’ll spend four years on probation. When four years have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, let them give me the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.”*";
P_HTM[1142]="*Alattha kho acelo seniyo kukkuravatiko bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ.**And the naked dog ascetic Seniya received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence.*";
P_HTM[1143]="*Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā seniyo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, Tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**Not long after his ordination, Venerable Seniya, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[1144]="*“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi.**He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[1145]="*Aññataro kho panāyasmā seniyo arahataṃ ahosīti.**And Venerable Seniya became one of the perfected.*";
P_HTM[1146]="*Kukkuravatikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1147]="*58. Abhayarājakumārasutta**With Prince Abhaya*";
P_HTM[1148]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[1149]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[1150]="*Atha kho abhayo rājakumāro yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho abhayaṃ rājakumāraṃ nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto etadavoca:**Then Prince Abhaya went up to Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta, bowed, and sat down to one side. Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta said to him,*";
P_HTM[1151]="*“ehi tvaṃ, rājakumāra, samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropehi.**“Come, prince, refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine.*";
P_HTM[1152]="*Evaṃ te kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchissati:**Then you will get a good reputation:*";
P_HTM[1153]="*‘abhayena rājakumārena samaṇassa gotamassa evaṃ mahiddhikassa evaṃ mahānubhāvassa vādo āropito’”ti.**‘Prince Abhaya refuted the doctrine of the ascetic Gotama, so mighty and powerful!’”*";
P_HTM[1154]="*“Yathā kathaṃ panāhaṃ, bhante, samaṇassa gotamassa evaṃ mahiddhikassa evaṃ mahānubhāvassa vādaṃ āropessāmī”ti?**“But sir, how am I to do this?”*";
P_HTM[1155]="*“Ehi tvaṃ, rājakumāra, yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ vadehi:**“Here, prince, go to the ascetic Gotama and say to him:*";
P_HTM[1156]="*‘bhāseyya nu kho, bhante, tathāgato taṃ vācaṃ yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā’ti?**‘Sir, might the Realized One utter speech that is disliked by others?’*";
P_HTM[1157]="*Sace te samaṇo gotamo evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākaroti:**When he’s asked this, if he answers:*";
P_HTM[1158]="*‘bhāseyya, rājakumāra, tathāgato taṃ vācaṃ yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā’ti, tamenaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:**‘He might, prince,’ say this to him,*";
P_HTM[1159]="*‘atha kiñcarahi te, bhante, puthujjanena nānākaraṇaṃ?**‘Then, sir, what exactly is the difference between you and an ordinary person?*";
P_HTM[1160]="*Puthujjanopi hi taṃ vācaṃ bhāseyya yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā’ti.**For even an ordinary person might utter speech that is disliked by others.’*";
P_HTM[1161]="*Sace pana te samaṇo gotamo evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākaroti:**But if he answers,*";
P_HTM[1162]="*‘na, rājakumāra, tathāgato taṃ vācaṃ bhāseyya yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā’ti, tamenaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:**‘He would not, prince,’ say this to him:*";
P_HTM[1163]="*‘atha kiñcarahi te, bhante, devadatto byākato:**‘Then, sir, why exactly did you declare of Devadatta:*";
P_HTM[1164]="*“āpāyiko devadatto, nerayiko devadatto, kappaṭṭho devadatto, atekiccho devadatto”ti?**“Devadatta is going to a place of loss, to hell, there to remain for an eon, irredeemable”?*";
P_HTM[1165]="*Tāya ca pana te vācāya devadatto kupito ahosi anattamano’ti.**Devadatta was angry and upset with what you said.’*";
P_HTM[1166]="*Imaṃ kho te, rājakumāra, samaṇo gotamo ubhatokoṭikaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno neva sakkhiti uggilituṃ na sakkhiti ogilituṃ.**When you put this dilemma to him, the Buddha won’t be able to either spit it out or swallow it down.*";
P_HTM[1167]="*Seyyathāpi nāma purisassa ayosiṅghāṭakaṃ kaṇṭhe vilaggaṃ, so neva sakkuṇeyya uggilituṃ na sakkuṇeyya ogilituṃ;**He’ll be like a man with an iron cross stuck in his throat, unable to either spit it out or swallow it down.”*";
P_HTM[1168]="*evameva kho te, rājakumāra, samaṇo gotamo imaṃ ubhatokoṭikaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno neva sakkhiti uggilituṃ na sakkhiti ogilitun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1169]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho abhayo rājakumāro nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Abhaya. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta, keeping him on his right. Then he went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[1170]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnassa kho abhayassa rājakumārassa sūriyaṃ ulloketvā etadahosi:**Then he looked up at the sun and thought,*";
P_HTM[1171]="*“akālo kho ajja bhagavato vādaṃ āropetuṃ.**“It’s too late to refute the Buddha’s doctrine today.*";
P_HTM[1172]="*Sve dānāhaṃ sake nivesane bhagavato vādaṃ āropessāmī”ti bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**I shall refute his doctrine in my own home tomorrow.” He said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1173]="*“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya attacatuttho bhattan”ti.**“Sir, may the Buddha please accept tomorrow’s meal from me, together with three other monks.”*";
P_HTM[1174]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[1175]="*Atha kho abhayo rājakumāro bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, Abhaya got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[1176]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena abhayassa rājakumārassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then when the night had passed, the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Abhaya’s home, and sat down on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[1177]="*Atha kho abhayo rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Then Abhaya served and satisfied the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[1178]="*Atha kho abhayo rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Abhaya took a low seat, sat to one side,*";
P_HTM[1179]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho abhayo rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[1180]="*“bhāseyya nu kho, bhante, tathāgato taṃ vācaṃ yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā”ti?**“Sir, might the Realized One utter speech that is disliked by others?”*";
P_HTM[1181]="*“Na khvettha, rājakumāra, ekaṃsenā”ti.**“This is no simple matter, prince.”*";
P_HTM[1182]="*“Ettha, bhante, anassuṃ nigaṇṭhā”ti.**“Then the Jains have lost in this, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1183]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, rājakumāra, evaṃ vadesi:**“But prince, why do you say that*";
P_HTM[1184]="*‘ettha, bhante, anassuṃ nigaṇṭhā’”ti?**the Jains have lost in this?”*";
P_HTM[1185]="*“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho maṃ, bhante, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto etadavoca:**Then Abhaya told the Buddha all that had happened.*";
P_HTM[1186]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, rājakumāra, samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropehi.* **";
P_HTM[1187]="*Evaṃ te kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchissati—* **";
P_HTM[1188]="*abhayena rājakumārena samaṇassa gotamassa evaṃ mahiddhikassa evaṃ mahānubhāvassa vādo āropito’ti.* **";
P_HTM[1189]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[1190]="*‘yathā kathaṃ panāhaṃ, bhante, samaṇassa gotamassa evaṃ mahiddhikassa evaṃ mahānubhāvassa vādaṃ āropessāmī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[1191]="*‘Ehi tvaṃ, rājakumāra, yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ vadehi:* **";
P_HTM[1192]="*“bhāseyya nu kho, bhante, tathāgato taṃ vācaṃ yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[1193]="*Sace te samaṇo gotamo evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākaroti:* **";
P_HTM[1194]="*“bhāseyya, rājakumāra, tathāgato taṃ vācaṃ yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā”ti, tamenaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1195]="*“atha kiñcarahi te, bhante, puthujjanena nānākaraṇaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[1196]="*Puthujjanopi hi taṃ vācaṃ bhāseyya yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1197]="*Sace pana te samaṇo gotamo evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākaroti:* **";
P_HTM[1198]="*“na, rājakumāra, tathāgato taṃ vācaṃ bhāseyya yā sā vācā paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā”ti, tamenaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi—* **";
P_HTM[1199]="*atha kiñcarahi te, bhante, devadatto byākato:* **";
P_HTM[1200]="*“āpāyiko devadatto, nerayiko devadatto, kappaṭṭho devadatto, atekiccho devadatto”ti?* **";
P_HTM[1201]="*Tāya ca pana te vācāya devadatto kupito ahosi anattamano’ti.* **";
P_HTM[1202]="*Imaṃ kho te, rājakumāra, samaṇo gotamo ubhatokoṭikaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno neva sakkhiti uggilituṃ na sakkhiti ogilituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1203]="*Seyyathāpi nāma purisassa ayosiṅghāṭakaṃ kaṇṭhe vilaggaṃ, so neva sakkuṇeyya uggilituṃ na sakkuṇeyya ogilituṃ;* **";
P_HTM[1204]="*evameva kho te, rājakumāra, samaṇo gotamo imaṃ ubhatokoṭikaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno neva sakkhiti uggilituṃ na sakkhiti ogilitun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1205]="*Tena kho pana samayena daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako abhayassa rājakumārassa aṅke nisinno hoti.**Now at that time a little baby boy was sitting in Prince Abhaya’s lap.*";
P_HTM[1206]="*Atha kho bhagavā abhayaṃ rājakumāraṃ etadavoca:**Then the Buddha said to Abhaya,*";
P_HTM[1207]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**“What do you think, prince?*";
P_HTM[1208]="*sacāyaṃ kumāro tuyhaṃ vā pamādamanvāya dhātiyā vā pamādamanvāya kaṭṭhaṃ vā kaṭhalaṃ vā mukhe āhareyya, kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti?**If—because of your negligence or his nurse’s negligence—your boy was to put a stick or stone in his mouth, what would you do to him?”*";
P_HTM[1209]="*“Āhareyyassāhaṃ, bhante.**“I’d try to take it out, sir.*";
P_HTM[1210]="*Sace, bhante, na sakkuṇeyyaṃ ādikeneva āhattuṃ, vāmena hatthena sīsaṃ pariggahetvā dakkhiṇena hatthena vaṅkaṅguliṃ karitvā salohitampi āhareyyaṃ.**If that didn’t work, I’d hold his head with my left hand, and take it out using a hooked finger of my right hand, even if it drew blood.*";
P_HTM[1211]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1212]="*Atthi me, bhante, kumāre anukampā”ti.**Because I have compassion for the boy, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1213]="*“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, yaṃ tathāgato vācaṃ jānāti abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ sā ca paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā, na taṃ tathāgato vācaṃ bhāsati.**“In the same way, prince, the Realized One does not utter speech that he knows to be untrue, false, and harmful, and which is disliked by others.*";
P_HTM[1214]="*Yampi tathāgato vācaṃ jānāti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ sā ca paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā, tampi tathāgato vācaṃ na bhāsati.**The Realized One does not utter speech that he knows to be true and substantive, but which is harmful and disliked by others.*";
P_HTM[1215]="*Yañca kho tathāgato vācaṃ jānāti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ sā ca paresaṃ appiyā amanāpā, tatra kālaññū tathāgato hoti tassā vācāya veyyākaraṇāya.**The Realized One knows the right time to speak so as to explain what he knows to be true, substantive, and beneficial, but which is disliked by others.*";
P_HTM[1216]="*Yaṃ tathāgato vācaṃ jānāti abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ sā ca paresaṃ piyā manāpā, na taṃ tathāgato vācaṃ bhāsati.**The Realized One does not utter speech that he knows to be untrue, false, and harmful, but which is liked by others.*";
P_HTM[1217]="*Yampi tathāgato vācaṃ jānāti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ sā ca paresaṃ piyā manāpā tampi tathāgato vācaṃ na bhāsati.**The Realized One does not utter speech that he knows to be true and substantive, but which is harmful, even if it is liked by others.*";
P_HTM[1218]="*Yañca tathāgato vācaṃ jānāti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ sā ca paresaṃ piyā manāpā, tatra kālaññū tathāgato hoti tassā vācāya veyyākaraṇāya.**The Realized One knows the right time to speak so as to explain what he knows to be true, substantive, and beneficial, and which is liked by others.*";
P_HTM[1219]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1220]="*Atthi, rājakumāra, tathāgatassa sattesu anukampā”ti.**Because the Realized One has compassion for sentient beings.”*";
P_HTM[1221]="*“Yeme, bhante, khattiyapaṇḍitāpi brāhmaṇapaṇḍitāpi gahapatipaṇḍitāpi samaṇapaṇḍitāpi pañhaṃ abhisaṅkharitvā tathāgataṃ upasaṅkamitvā pucchanti,**“Sir, there are clever aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics who come to see you with a question already planned.*";
P_HTM[1222]="*pubbeva nu kho, etaṃ, bhante, bhagavato cetaso parivitakkitaṃ hoti ‘ye maṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ pucchissanti tesāhaṃ evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissāmī’ti, udāhu ṭhānasovetaṃ tathāgataṃ paṭibhātī”ti?**Do you think beforehand that if they ask you like this, you’ll answer like that, or does the answer just appear to you on the spot?”*";
P_HTM[1223]="*“Tena hi, rājakumāra, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi, yathā te khameyya tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi.**“Well then, prince, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as you like.*";
P_HTM[1224]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**What do you think, prince?*";
P_HTM[1225]="*kusalo tvaṃ rathassa aṅgapaccaṅgānan”ti?**Are you skilled in the various parts of a chariot?”*";
P_HTM[1226]="*“Evaṃ, bhante, kusalo ahaṃ rathassa aṅgapaccaṅgānan”ti.**“I am, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1227]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**“What do you think, prince?*";
P_HTM[1228]="*ye taṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**When they come to you and ask:*";
P_HTM[1229]="*‘kiṃ nāmidaṃ rathassa aṅgapaccaṅgan’ti?**‘What’s the name of this chariot part?’*";
P_HTM[1230]="*Pubbeva nu kho te etaṃ cetaso parivitakkitaṃ assa ‘ye maṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ pucchissanti tesāhaṃ evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissāmī’ti, udāhu ṭhānasovetaṃ paṭibhāseyyā”ti?**Do you think beforehand that if they ask you like this, you’ll answer like that, or does the answer appear to you on the spot?”*";
P_HTM[1231]="*“Ahañhi, bhante, rathiko saññāto kusalo rathassa aṅgapaccaṅgānaṃ.**“Sir, I’m well-known as a charioteer skilled in a chariot’s parts.*";
P_HTM[1232]="*Sabbāni me rathassa aṅgapaccaṅgāni suviditāni.**All the parts are well-known to me.*";
P_HTM[1233]="*Ṭhānasovetaṃ maṃ paṭibhāseyyā”ti.**The answer just appears to me on the spot.”*";
P_HTM[1234]="*“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, ye te khattiyapaṇḍitāpi brāhmaṇapaṇḍitāpi gahapatipaṇḍitāpi samaṇapaṇḍitāpi pañhaṃ abhisaṅkharitvā tathāgataṃ upasaṅkamitvā pucchanti, ṭhānasovetaṃ tathāgataṃ paṭibhāti.**“In the same way, when clever aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics come to see me with a question already planned, the answer just appears to me on the spot.*";
P_HTM[1235]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1236]="*Sā hi, rājakumāra, tathāgatassa dhammadhātu suppaṭividdhā yassā dhammadhātuyā suppaṭividdhattā ṭhānasovetaṃ tathāgataṃ paṭibhātī”ti.**Because the Realized One has clearly comprehended the principle of the teachings, so that the answer just appears to him on the spot.”*";
P_HTM[1237]="*Evaṃ vutte, abhayo rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Prince Abhaya said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1238]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe …**“Excellent, sir! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[1239]="*ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[1240]="*Abhayarājakumārasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1241]="*59. Bahuvedanīyasutta**The Many Kinds of Feeling*";
P_HTM[1242]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[1243]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[1244]="*Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**Then the master builder Pañcakaṅga went up to Venerable Udāyī, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[1245]="*“kati nu kho, bhante udāyi, vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti?**“Sir, how many feelings has the Buddha spoken of?”*";
P_HTM[1246]="*“Tisso kho, thapati, vedanā vuttā bhagavatā.**“Master builder, the Buddha has spoken of three feelings:*";
P_HTM[1247]="*Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—**pleasant, painful, and neutral.*";
P_HTM[1248]="*imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti.**The Buddha has spoken of these three feelings.”*";
P_HTM[1249]="*Evaṃ vutte, pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī,*";
P_HTM[1250]="*“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā;**“Sir, Udāyī, the Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings.*";
P_HTM[1251]="*dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—**He’s spoken of two feelings:*";
P_HTM[1252]="*sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā.**pleasant and painful.*";
P_HTM[1253]="*Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā bhagavatā”ti.**The Buddha said that neutral feeling is included as a peaceful and subtle kind of pleasure.”*";
P_HTM[1254]="*Dutiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca:**For a second time, Udāyī said to Pañcakaṅga,*";
P_HTM[1255]="*“na kho, gahapati, dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā;**“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of two feelings,*";
P_HTM[1256]="*tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā.**he’s spoken of three.”*";
P_HTM[1257]="*Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—* **";
P_HTM[1258]="*imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1259]="*Dutiyampi kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**For a second time, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī,*";
P_HTM[1260]="*“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā;**“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings,*";
P_HTM[1261]="*dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—**he’s spoken of two.”*";
P_HTM[1262]="*sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā.* **";
P_HTM[1263]="*Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā bhagavatā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1264]="*Tatiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca:**And for a third time, Udāyī said to Pañcakaṅga,*";
P_HTM[1265]="*“na kho, thapati, dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā;**“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of two feelings,*";
P_HTM[1266]="*tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā.**he’s spoken of three.”*";
P_HTM[1267]="*Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—* **";
P_HTM[1268]="*imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1269]="*Tatiyampi kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**And for a third time, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī,*";
P_HTM[1270]="*“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā,**“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings,*";
P_HTM[1271]="*dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—**he’s spoken of two.”*";
P_HTM[1272]="*sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā.* **";
P_HTM[1273]="*Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā bhagavatā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1274]="*Neva kho sakkhi āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ saññāpetuṃ, na panāsakkhi pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ saññāpetuṃ.**But neither was able to persuade the other.*";
P_HTM[1275]="*Assosi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ.**Venerable Ānanda heard this discussion between Udāyī and Pañcakaṅga.*";
P_HTM[1276]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Then he went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[1277]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako ahosi āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi.**and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed.*";
P_HTM[1278]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[1279]="*“santaññeva kho, ānanda, pariyāyaṃ pañcakaṅgo thapati udāyissa nābbhanumodi, santaññeva ca pana pariyāyaṃ udāyī pañcakaṅgassa thapatissa nābbhanumodi.**“Ānanda, the explanation by the mendicant Udāyī, which the master builder Pañcakaṅga didn’t agree with, was quite correct. But the explanation by Pañcakaṅga, which Udāyī didn’t agree with, was also quite correct.*";
P_HTM[1280]="*Dvepānanda, vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, tissopi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, pañcapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, chapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, aṭṭhārasapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, chattiṃsapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, aṭṭhasatampi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena.**In one explanation I’ve spoken of two feelings. In another explanation I’ve spoken of three feelings, or five, six, eighteen, thirty-six, or a hundred and eight feelings.*";
P_HTM[1281]="*Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo.**I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways.*";
P_HTM[1282]="*Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ sulapitaṃ na samanujānissanti na samanumaññissanti na samanumodissanti tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharissanti.**This being so, you can expect that those who don’t concede, approve, or agree with what has been well spoken will argue, quarrel, and fight, continually wounding each other with barbed words.*";
P_HTM[1283]="*Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo.**I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways.*";
P_HTM[1284]="*Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ sulapitaṃ samanujānissanti samanumaññissanti samanumodissanti tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharissanti.**This being so, you can expect that those who do concede, approve, or agree with what has been well spoken will live in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each other with kindly eyes.*";
P_HTM[1285]="*Pañca kho ime, ānanda, kāmaguṇā.**There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[1286]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[1287]="*Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[1288]="*sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[1289]="*ghānaviññeyyā gandhā … pe …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[1290]="*jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[1291]="*kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[1292]="*ime kho, ānanda, pañca kāmaguṇā.**These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[1293]="*Yaṃ kho, ānanda, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati kāmasukhaṃ.**The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual stimulation is called sensual pleasure.*";
P_HTM[1294]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya: ‘etaparamaṃ sattā sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti, idamassa nānujānāmi.**There are those who would say that this is the highest pleasure and happiness that sentient beings experience. But I don’t grant them that.*";
P_HTM[1295]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1296]="*Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.**Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1297]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1298]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[1299]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.**This is a pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1300]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya: ‘etaparamaṃ sattā sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti, idamassa nānujānāmi.**There are those who would say that this is the highest pleasure and happiness that sentient beings experience. But I don’t grant them that.*";
P_HTM[1301]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1302]="*Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.**Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1303]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1304]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. …*";
P_HTM[1305]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.* **";
P_HTM[1306]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …* **";
P_HTM[1307]="*pe ….**There is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1308]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1309]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’ …*";
P_HTM[1310]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.* **";
P_HTM[1311]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …* **";
P_HTM[1312]="*pe ….**There is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1313]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1314]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. …*";
P_HTM[1315]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.* **";
P_HTM[1316]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …* **";
P_HTM[1317]="*pe ….**There is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1318]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1319]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā, paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā, nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space. …*";
P_HTM[1320]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.* **";
P_HTM[1321]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …* **";
P_HTM[1322]="*pe ….**There is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1323]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1324]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness. …*";
P_HTM[1325]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.* **";
P_HTM[1326]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …* **";
P_HTM[1327]="*pe ….**There is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1328]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1329]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness. …*";
P_HTM[1330]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.* **";
P_HTM[1331]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya …* **";
P_HTM[1332]="*pe ….**There is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1333]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1334]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, enters and remains in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[1335]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.**This is a pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1336]="*Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya: ‘etaparamaṃ sattā sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti, idamassa nānujānāmi.**There are those who would say that this is the highest pleasure and happiness that sentient beings experience. But I don’t grant them that.*";
P_HTM[1337]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1338]="*Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.**Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1339]="*Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?**And what is that pleasure?*";
P_HTM[1340]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[1341]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca.**This is a pleasure that is finer than that.*";
P_HTM[1342]="*Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say,*";
P_HTM[1343]="*‘saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samaṇo gotamo āha; tañca sukhasmiṃ paññapeti.**‘The ascetic Gotama spoke of the cessation of perception and feeling, and he includes it in happiness.*";
P_HTM[1344]="*Tayidaṃ kiṃsu, tayidaṃ kathaṃsū’ti?**What’s up with that?’*";
P_HTM[1345]="*Evaṃvādino, ānanda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:**When wanderers who follow other paths say this, you should say to them,*";
P_HTM[1346]="*‘na kho, āvuso, bhagavā sukhaṃyeva vedanaṃ sandhāya sukhasmiṃ paññapeti;**‘Reverends, when the Buddha describes what’s included in happiness, he’s not just referring to pleasant feeling.*";
P_HTM[1347]="*api ca, āvuso, yattha yattha sukhaṃ upalabbhati yahiṃ yahiṃ taṃ taṃ tathāgato sukhasmiṃ paññapetī’”ti.**The Realized One describes pleasure as included in happiness wherever it’s found, and in whatever context.’”*";
P_HTM[1348]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[1349]="*Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[1350]="*Bahuvedanīyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1351]="*60. Apaṇṇakasutta**Guaranteed*";
P_HTM[1352]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[1353]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena sālā nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇagāmo tadavasari.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Kosalan brahmins named Sālā.*";
P_HTM[1354]="*Assosuṃ kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:**The brahmins and householders of Sālā heard:*";
P_HTM[1355]="*“samaṇo khalu bho gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ sālaṃ anuppatto.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—wandering in the land of the Kosalans has arrived at Sālā, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[1356]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[1357]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[1358]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[1359]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[1360]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[1361]="*Atha kho sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu; sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho sāleyyake brāhmaṇagahapatike bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the brahmins and householders of Sālā went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. The Buddha said to them:*";
P_HTM[1362]="*“atthi pana vo, gahapatayo, koci manāpo satthā yasmiṃ vo ākāravatī saddhā paṭiladdhā”ti?**“So, householders, is there some other teacher you’re happy with, in whom you have acquired grounded faith?”*";
P_HTM[1363]="*“Natthi kho no, bhante, koci manāpo satthā yasmiṃ no ākāravatī saddhā paṭiladdhā”ti.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1364]="*“Manāpaṃ vo, gahapatayo, satthāraṃ alabhantehi ayaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo samādāya vattitabbo.**“Since you haven’t found a teacher you’re happy with, you should undertake and implement this guaranteed teaching.*";
P_HTM[1365]="*Apaṇṇako hi, gahapatayo, dhammo samatto samādinno, so vo bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**For when the guaranteed teaching is undertaken, it will be for your lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[1366]="*Katamo ca, gahapatayo, apaṇṇako dhammo?**And what is the guaranteed teaching?*";
P_HTM[1367]="*Santi, gahapatayo, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[1368]="*‘natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ, natthi hutaṃ; natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko, natthi paro loko; natthi mātā, natthi pitā; natthi sattā opapātikā; natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammā paṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.**‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no obligation to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’*";
P_HTM[1369]="*Tesaṃyeva kho, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā ujuvipaccanīkavādā.**And there are some ascetics and brahmins whose doctrine directly contradicts this.*";
P_HTM[1370]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say:*";
P_HTM[1371]="*‘atthi dinnaṃ, atthi yiṭṭhaṃ, atthi hutaṃ; atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko; atthi ayaṃ loko, atthi paro loko; atthi mātā, atthi pitā; atthi sattā opapātikā; atthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammā paṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.**‘There is meaning in giving, sacrifice, and offerings. There are fruits and results of good and bad deeds. There is an afterlife. There is obligation to mother and father. There are beings reborn spontaneously. And there are ascetics and brahmins who are well attained and practiced, and who describe the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’*";
P_HTM[1372]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, gahapatayo:**What do you think, householders?*";
P_HTM[1373]="*‘nanume samaṇabrāhmaṇā aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā’”ti?**Don’t these doctrines directly contradict each other?”*";
P_HTM[1374]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1375]="*“Tatra, gahapatayo, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**“Since this is so, consider those ascetics and brahmins whose view is that*";
P_HTM[1376]="*‘natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ … pe … ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti**there’s no meaning in giving, etc.*";
P_HTM[1377]="*tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—yamidaṃ kāyasucaritaṃ, vacīsucaritaṃ, manosucaritaṃ—ime tayo kusale dhamme abhinivajjetvā yamidaṃ kāyaduccaritaṃ, vacīduccaritaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ—ime tayo akusale dhamme samādāya vattissanti.**You can expect that they will reject good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and undertake and implement bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1378]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1379]="*Na hi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā passanti akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṃkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ.**Because those ascetics and brahmins don’t see that unskillful qualities are full of drawbacks, sordidness, and corruption, or that skillful qualities have the benefit and cleansing power of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[1380]="*Santaṃyeva pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘natthi paro loko’ tissa diṭṭhi hoti; sāssa hoti micchādiṭṭhi.**Moreover, since there actually is another world, their view that there is no other world is wrong view.*";
P_HTM[1381]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘natthi paro loko’ti saṅkappeti; svāssa hoti micchāsaṅkappo.**Since there actually is another world, their thought that there is no other world is wrong thought.*";
P_HTM[1382]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘natthi paro loko’ti vācaṃ bhāsati; sāssa hoti micchāvācā.**Since there actually is another world, their speech that there is no other world is wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[1383]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘natthi paro loko’ti āha; ye te arahanto paralokaviduno tesamayaṃ paccanīkaṃ karoti.**Since there actually is another world, in saying that there is no other world they contradict those perfected ones who know the other world.*";
P_HTM[1384]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘natthi paro loko’ti paraṃ saññāpeti; sāssa hoti asaddhammasaññatti.**Since there actually is another world, in convincing another that there is no other world they are convincing them to accept an untrue teaching.*";
P_HTM[1385]="*Tāya ca pana asaddhammasaññattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti.**And on account of that they glorify themselves and put others down.*";
P_HTM[1386]="*Iti pubbeva kho panassa susīlyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, dussīlyaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ—**So they give up their former ethical conduct and are established in unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[1387]="*ayañca micchādiṭṭhi micchāsaṅkappo micchāvācā ariyānaṃ paccanīkatā asaddhammasaññatti attukkaṃsanā paravambhanā. Evamassime aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti micchādiṭṭhipaccayā.**And that is how wrong view gives rise to these many bad, unskillful qualities—wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, contradicting the noble ones, convincing others to accept untrue teachings, and glorifying oneself and putting others down.*";
P_HTM[1388]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[1389]="*‘sace kho natthi paro loko evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā sotthimattānaṃ karissati;**‘If there is no other world, when this individual’s body breaks up they will keep themselves safe.*";
P_HTM[1390]="*sace kho atthi paro loko, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissati.**And if there is another world, when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[1391]="*Kāmaṃ kho pana māhu paro loko, hotu nesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ;**But let’s assume that those who say that there is no other world are correct.*";
P_HTM[1392]="*atha ca panāyaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ gārayho—dussīlo purisapuggalo micchādiṭṭhi natthikavādo’ti.**Regardless, that individual is still criticized by sensible people in the present life as being an immoral individual of wrong view, a nihilist.’*";
P_HTM[1393]="*Sace kho attheva paro loko, evaṃ imassa bhoto purisapuggalassa ubhayattha kaliggaho—**But if there really is another world, they lose on both counts.*";
P_HTM[1394]="*yañca diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ gārayho, yañca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissati.**For they are criticized by sensible people in the present life, and when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[1395]="*Evamassāyaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo dussamatto samādinno, ekaṃsaṃ pharitvā tiṭṭhati, riñcati kusalaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**They have wrongly undertaken this guaranteed teaching in such a way that it encompasses the positive outcomes of one side only, leaving out the skillful premise.*";
P_HTM[1396]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**Since this is so, consider those ascetics and brahmins whose view is that*";
P_HTM[1397]="*‘atthi dinnaṃ … pe … ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti**there is meaning in giving, etc.*";
P_HTM[1398]="*tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—yamidaṃ kāyaduccaritaṃ, vacīduccaritaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ—ime tayo akusale dhamme abhinivajjetvā yamidaṃ kāyasucaritaṃ, vacīsucaritaṃ, manosucaritaṃ—ime tayo kusale dhamme samādāya vattissanti.**You can expect that they will reject bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and undertake and implement good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1399]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1400]="*Passanti hi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ.**Because those ascetics and brahmins see that unskillful qualities are full of drawbacks, sordidness, and corruption, and that skillful qualities have the benefit and cleansing power of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[1401]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘atthi paro loko’ tissa diṭṭhi hoti; sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi.**Moreover, since there actually is another world, their view that there is another world is right view.*";
P_HTM[1402]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘atthi paro loko’ti saṅkappeti; svāssa hoti sammāsaṅkappo.**Since there actually is another world, their thought that there is another world is right thought.*";
P_HTM[1403]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘atthi paro loko’ti vācaṃ bhāsati; sāssa hoti sammāvācā.**Since there actually is another world, their speech that there is another world is right speech.*";
P_HTM[1404]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘atthi paro loko’ti āha; ye te arahanto paralokaviduno tesamayaṃ na paccanīkaṃ karoti.**Since there actually is another world, in saying that there is another world they don’t contradict those perfected ones who know the other world.*";
P_HTM[1405]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana paraṃ lokaṃ ‘atthi paro loko’ti paraṃ saññāpeti; sāssa hoti saddhammasaññatti.**Since there actually is another world, in convincing another that there is another world they are convincing them to accept a true teaching.*";
P_HTM[1406]="*Tāya ca pana saddhammasaññattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**And on account of that they don’t glorify themselves or put others down.*";
P_HTM[1407]="*Iti pubbeva kho panassa dussīlyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, susīlyaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ—**So they give up their former unethical conduct and are established in ethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[1408]="*ayañca sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā ariyānaṃ apaccanīkatā saddhammasaññatti anattukkaṃsanā aparavambhanā. Evamassime aneke kusalā dhammā sambhavanti sammādiṭṭhipaccayā.**And that is how right view gives rise to these many skillful qualities—right view, right thought, right speech, not contradicting the noble ones, convincing others to accept true teachings, and not glorifying oneself or putting others down.*";
P_HTM[1409]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[1410]="*‘sace kho atthi paro loko, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissati.**‘If there is another world, when this individual’s body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[1411]="*Kāmaṃ kho pana māhu paro loko, hotu nesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ;**But let’s assume that those who say that there is no other world are correct.*";
P_HTM[1412]="*atha ca panāyaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ pāsaṃso—sīlavā purisapuggalo sammādiṭṭhi atthikavādo’ti.**Regardless, that individual is still praised by sensible people in the present life as being a moral individual of right view, who affirms a positive teaching.’*";
P_HTM[1413]="*Sace kho attheva paro loko, evaṃ imassa bhoto purisapuggalassa ubhayattha kaṭaggaho—**So if there really is another world, they win on both counts.*";
P_HTM[1414]="*yañca diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ pāsaṃso, yañca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissati.**For they are praised by sensible people in the present life, and when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[1415]="*Evamassāyaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo susamatto samādinno ubhayaṃsaṃ pharitvā tiṭṭhati, riñcati akusalaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**They have rightly undertaken this guaranteed teaching in such a way that it encompasses the positive outcomes of both sides, leaving out the unskillful premise.*";
P_HTM[1416]="*Santi, gahapatayo, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[1417]="*‘karoto kārayato, chindato chedāpayato, pacato pācāpayato, socayato socāpayato, kilamato kilamāpayato, phandato phandāpayato, pāṇamatipātayato, adinnaṃ ādiyato, sandhiṃ chindato, nillopaṃ harato, ekāgārikaṃ karoto, paripanthe tiṭṭhato, paradāraṃ gacchato, musā bhaṇato; karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ.**‘The one who acts does nothing wrong when they punish, mutilate, torture, aggrieve, oppress, intimidate, or when they encourage others to do the same. They do nothing wrong when they kill, steal, break into houses, plunder wealth, steal from isolated buildings, commit highway robbery, commit adultery, and lie.*";
P_HTM[1418]="*Khurapariyantena cepi cakkena yo imissā pathaviyā pāṇe ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ kareyya, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo.**If you were to reduce all the living creatures of this earth to one heap and mass of flesh with a razor-edged chakram, no evil comes of that, and no outcome of evil.*";
P_HTM[1419]="*Dakkhiṇañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya hananto ghātento, chindanto chedāpento, pacanto pācento; natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo.**If you were to go along the south bank of the Ganges killing, mutilating, and torturing, and encouraging others to do the same, no evil comes of that, and no outcome of evil.*";
P_HTM[1420]="*Uttarañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya dadanto dāpento, yajanto yajāpento; natthi tatonidānaṃ puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo.**If you were to go along the north bank of the Ganges giving and sacrificing and encouraging others to do the same, no merit comes of that, and no outcome of merit.*";
P_HTM[1421]="*Dānena damena saṃyamena saccavajjena natthi puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo’ti.**In giving, self-control, restraint, and truthfulness there is no merit or outcome of merit.’*";
P_HTM[1422]="*Tesaṃyeva kho, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā ujuvipaccanīkavādā te evamāhaṃsu:**And there are some ascetics and brahmins whose doctrine directly contradicts this. They say:*";
P_HTM[1423]="*‘karoto kārayato, chindato chedāpayato, pacato pācāpayato, socayato socāpayato, kilamato kilamāpayato, phandato phandāpayato, pāṇamatipātayato, adinnaṃ ādiyato, sandhiṃ chindato, nillopaṃ harato, ekāgārikaṃ karoto, paripanthe tiṭṭhato, paradāraṃ gacchato, musā bhaṇato; karoto karīyati pāpaṃ.**‘The one who acts does a bad deed when they punish, mutilate, torture, aggrieve, oppress, intimidate, or when they encourage others to do the same. They do a bad deed when they kill, steal, break into houses, plunder wealth, steal from isolated buildings, commit highway robbery, commit adultery, and lie.*";
P_HTM[1424]="*Khurapariyantena cepi cakkena yo imissā pathaviyā pāṇe ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ kareyya, atthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, atthi pāpassa āgamo.**If you were to reduce all the living creatures of this earth to one heap and mass of flesh with a razor-edged chakram, evil comes of that, and an outcome of evil.*";
P_HTM[1425]="*Dakkhiṇañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya hananto ghātento, chindanto chedāpento, pacanto pācento; atthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, atthi pāpassa āgamo.**If you were to go along the south bank of the Ganges killing, mutilating, and torturing, and encouraging others to do the same, evil comes of that, and an outcome of evil.*";
P_HTM[1426]="*Uttarañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya dadanto dāpento, yajanto yajāpento; atthi tatonidānaṃ puññaṃ, atthi puññassa āgamo.**If you were to go along the north bank of the Ganges giving and sacrificing and encouraging others to do the same, merit comes of that, and an outcome of merit.*";
P_HTM[1427]="*Dānena damena saṃyamena saccavajjena atthi puññaṃ, atthi puññassa āgamo’ti.**In giving, self-control, restraint, and truthfulness there is merit and outcome of merit.’*";
P_HTM[1428]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, gahapatayo,**What do you think, householders?*";
P_HTM[1429]="*nanume samaṇabrāhmaṇā aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā”ti?**Don’t these doctrines directly contradict each other?”*";
P_HTM[1430]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1431]="*“Tatra, gahapatayo, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**“Since this is so, consider those ascetics and brahmins whose view is that*";
P_HTM[1432]="*‘karoto kārayato, chindato chedāpayato, pacato pācāpayato, socayato socāpayato, kilamato kilamāpayato, phandato phandāpayato, pāṇamatipātayato, adinnaṃ ādiyato, sandhiṃ chindato, nillopaṃ harato, ekāgārikaṃ karoto, paripanthe tiṭṭhato, paradāraṃ gacchato, musā bhaṇato; karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ.**the one who acts does nothing wrong when they punish, etc.*";
P_HTM[1433]="*Khurapariyantena cepi cakkena yo imissā pathaviyā pāṇe ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ kareyya, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo.* **";
P_HTM[1434]="*Dakkhiṇañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya hananto ghātento … pe … dānena damena saṃyamena saccavajjena natthi puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo’ti* **";
P_HTM[1435]="*tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—yamidaṃ kāyasucaritaṃ, vacīsucaritaṃ, manosucaritaṃ—ime tayo kusale dhamme abhinivajjetvā yamidaṃ kāyaduccaritaṃ, vacīduccaritaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ—ime tayo akusale dhamme samādāya vattissanti.**You can expect that they will reject good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and undertake and implement bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1436]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1437]="*Na hi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā passanti akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ.**Because those ascetics and brahmins don’t see that unskillful qualities are full of drawbacks, sordidness, and corruption, or that skillful qualities have the benefit and cleansing power of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[1438]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘natthi kiriyā’ tissa diṭṭhi hoti; sāssa hoti micchādiṭṭhi.**Moreover, since action actually does have an effect, their view that action is ineffective is wrong view.*";
P_HTM[1439]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘natthi kiriyā’ti saṅkappeti; svāssa hoti micchāsaṅkappo.**Since action actually does have an effect, their thought that action is ineffective is wrong thought.*";
P_HTM[1440]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘natthi kiriyā’ti vācaṃ bhāsati; sāssa hoti micchāvācā.**Since action actually does have an effect, their speech that action is ineffective is wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[1441]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘natthi kiriyā’ti āha, ye te arahanto kiriyavādā tesamayaṃ paccanīkaṃ karoti.**Since action actually does have an effect, in saying that action is ineffective they contradict those perfected ones who teach that action is effective.*";
P_HTM[1442]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘natthi kiriyā’ti paraṃ saññāpeti; sāssa hoti asaddhammasaññatti.**Since action actually does have an effect, in convincing another that action is ineffective they are convincing them to accept an untrue teaching.*";
P_HTM[1443]="*Tāya ca pana asaddhammasaññattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti.**And on account of that they glorify themselves and put others down.*";
P_HTM[1444]="*Iti pubbeva kho panassa susīlyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, dussīlyaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ—**So they give up their former ethical conduct and are established in unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[1445]="*ayañca micchādiṭṭhi micchāsaṅkappo micchāvācā ariyānaṃ paccanīkatā asaddhammasaññatti attukkaṃsanā paravambhanā. Evamassime aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti micchādiṭṭhipaccayā.**And that is how wrong view gives rise to these many bad, unskillful qualities—wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, contradicting the noble ones, convincing others to accept untrue teachings, and glorifying oneself and putting others down.*";
P_HTM[1446]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[1447]="*‘sace kho natthi kiriyā, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā sotthimattānaṃ karissati;**‘If there is no effective action, when this individual’s body breaks up they will keep themselves safe.*";
P_HTM[1448]="*sace kho atthi kiriyā evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissati.**And if there is effective action, when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[1449]="*Kāmaṃ kho pana māhu kiriyā, hotu nesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ;**But let’s assume that those who say that there is no effective action are correct.*";
P_HTM[1450]="*atha ca panāyaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ gārayho—dussīlo purisapuggalo micchādiṭṭhi akiriyavādo’ti.**Regardless, that individual is still criticized by sensible people in the present life as being an immoral individual of wrong view, one who denies the efficacy of action.’*";
P_HTM[1451]="*Sace kho attheva kiriyā, evaṃ imassa bhoto purisapuggalassa ubhayattha kaliggaho—**But if there really is effective action, they lose on both counts.*";
P_HTM[1452]="*yañca diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ gārayho, yañca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissati.**For they are criticized by sensible people in the present life, and when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[1453]="*Evamassāyaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo dussamatto samādinno, ekaṃsaṃ pharitvā tiṭṭhati, riñcati kusalaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**They have wrongly undertaken this guaranteed teaching in such a way that it encompasses the positive outcomes of one side only, leaving out the skillful premise.*";
P_HTM[1454]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**Since this is so, consider those ascetics and brahmins whose view is that*";
P_HTM[1455]="*‘karoto kārayato, chindato chedāpayato, pacato pācāpayato, socayato socāpayato, kilamato kilamāpayato, phandato phandāpayato, pāṇamatipātayato, adinnaṃ ādiyato, sandhiṃ chindato, nillopaṃ harato, ekāgārikaṃ karoto, paripanthe tiṭṭhato, paradāraṃ gacchato, musā bhaṇato; karoto karīyati pāpaṃ.**the one who acts does a bad deed when they punish, etc.*";
P_HTM[1456]="*Khurapariyantena cepi cakkena yo imissā pathaviyā pāṇe ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ kareyya, atthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, atthi pāpassa āgamo.* **";
P_HTM[1457]="*Dakkhiṇañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya hananto ghātento, chindanto chedāpento, pacanto pācento, atthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, atthi pāpassa āgamo.* **";
P_HTM[1458]="*Uttarañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya dadanto dāpento, yajanto yajāpento, atthi tatonidānaṃ puññaṃ, atthi puññassa āgamo. Dānena damena saṃyamena saccavajjena atthi puññaṃ, atthi puññassa āgamo’ti* **";
P_HTM[1459]="*tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ yamidaṃ kāyaduccaritaṃ, vacīduccaritaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ—ime tayo akusale dhamme abhinivajjetvā yamidaṃ kāyasucaritaṃ, vacīsucaritaṃ, manosucaritaṃ—ime tayo kusale dhamme samādāya vattissanti.**You can expect that they will reject bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and undertake and implement good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1460]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1461]="*Passanti hi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ.**Because those ascetics and brahmins see that unskillful qualities are full of drawbacks, sordidness, and corruption, and that skillful qualities have the benefit and cleansing power of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[1462]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘atthi kiriyā’ tissa diṭṭhi hoti; sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi.**Moreover, since action actually does have an effect, their view that action is effective is right view.*";
P_HTM[1463]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘atthi kiriyā’ti saṅkappeti; svāssa hoti sammāsaṅkappo.**Since action actually does have an effect, their thought that action is effective is right thought.*";
P_HTM[1464]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘atthi kiriyā’ti vācaṃ bhāsati; sāssa hoti sammāvācā.**Since action actually does have an effect, their speech that action is effective is right speech.*";
P_HTM[1465]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘atthi kiriyā’ti āha; ye te arahanto kiriyavādā tesamayaṃ na paccanīkaṃ karoti.**Since action actually does have an effect, in saying that action is effective they don’t contradict those perfected ones who teach that action is effective.*";
P_HTM[1466]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana kiriyaṃ ‘atthi kiriyā’ti paraṃ saññāpeti; sāssa hoti saddhammasaññatti.**Since action actually does have an effect, in convincing another that action is effective they are convincing them to accept a true teaching.*";
P_HTM[1467]="*Tāya ca pana saddhammasaññattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**And on account of that they don’t glorify themselves or put others down.*";
P_HTM[1468]="*Iti pubbeva kho panassa dussīlyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, susīlyaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ—**So they give up their former unethical conduct and are established in ethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[1469]="*ayañca sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā ariyānaṃ apaccanīkatā saddhammasaññatti anattukkaṃsanā aparavambhanā. Evamassime aneke kusalā dhammā sambhavanti sammādiṭṭhipaccayā.**And that is how right view gives rise to these many skillful qualities—right view, right thought, right speech, not contradicting the noble ones, convincing others to accept true teachings, and not glorifying oneself or putting others down.*";
P_HTM[1470]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[1471]="*‘sace kho atthi kiriyā, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissati.**‘If there is effective action, when this individual’s body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[1472]="*Kāmaṃ kho pana māhu kiriyā, hotu nesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ;**But let’s assume that those who say that there is no effective action are correct.*";
P_HTM[1473]="*atha ca panāyaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ pāsaṃso—sīlavā purisapuggalo sammādiṭṭhi kiriyavādo’ti.**Regardless, that individual is still praised by sensible people in the present life as being a moral individual of right view, who affirms the efficacy of action.’*";
P_HTM[1474]="*Sace kho attheva kiriyā, evaṃ imassa bhoto purisapuggalassa ubhayattha kaṭaggaho—**So if there really is effective action, they win on both counts.*";
P_HTM[1475]="*yañca diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ pāsaṃso, yañca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissati.**For they are praised by sensible people in the present life, and when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[1476]="*Evamassāyaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo susamatto samādinno, ubhayaṃsaṃ pharitvā tiṭṭhati, riñcati akusalaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**They have rightly undertaken this guaranteed teaching in such a way that it encompasses the positive outcomes of both sides, leaving out the unskillful premise.*";
P_HTM[1477]="*Santi, gahapatayo, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[1478]="*‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṃkilesāya;**‘There is no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[1479]="*ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti.**Sentient beings are corrupted without cause or reason.*";
P_HTM[1480]="*Natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;**There’s no cause or condition for the purification of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[1481]="*ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhanti.**Sentient beings are purified without cause or reason.*";
P_HTM[1482]="*Natthi balaṃ, natthi vīriyaṃ, natthi purisathāmo, natthi purisaparakkamo;**There is no power, no energy, no manly strength or vigor.*";
P_HTM[1483]="*sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā niyatisaṃgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti.**All sentient beings, all living creatures, all beings, all souls lack control, power, and energy. Molded by destiny, circumstance, and nature, they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth.’*";
P_HTM[1484]="*Tesaṃyeva kho, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā ujuvipaccanīkavādā.**And there are some ascetics and brahmins whose doctrine directly contradicts this.*";
P_HTM[1485]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say:*";
P_HTM[1486]="*‘atthi hetu, atthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṃkilesāya;**‘There is a cause and condition for the corruption of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[1487]="*sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti.**Sentient beings are corrupted with cause and reason.*";
P_HTM[1488]="*Atthi hetu, atthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;**There is a cause and condition for the purification of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[1489]="*sahetū sappaccayā sattā visujjhanti.**Sentient beings are purified with cause and reason.*";
P_HTM[1490]="*Atthi balaṃ, atthi vīriyaṃ, atthi purisathāmo, atthi purisaparakkamo;**There is power, energy, manly strength and vigor.*";
P_HTM[1491]="*na sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā niyatisaṃgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti.**It is not the case that all sentient beings, all living creatures, all beings, all souls lack control, power, and energy, or that, molded by destiny, circumstance, and nature, they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth.’*";
P_HTM[1492]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, gahapatayo,**What do you think, householders?*";
P_HTM[1493]="*nanume samaṇabrāhmaṇā aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā”ti?**Don’t these doctrines directly contradict each other?”*";
P_HTM[1494]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1495]="*“Tatra, gahapatayo, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**“Since this is so, consider those ascetics and brahmins whose view is that*";
P_HTM[1496]="*‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya;**there’s no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient beings, etc.*";
P_HTM[1497]="*ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti.* **";
P_HTM[1498]="*Natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;* **";
P_HTM[1499]="*ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhanti.* **";
P_HTM[1500]="*Natthi balaṃ, natthi vīriyaṃ, natthi purisathāmo, natthi purisaparakkamo; sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā niyatisaṅgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti* **";
P_HTM[1501]="*tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—yamidaṃ kāyasucaritaṃ, vacīsucaritaṃ, manosucaritaṃ—ime tayo kusale dhamme abhinivajjetvā yamidaṃ kāyaduccaritaṃ, vacīduccaritaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ—ime tayo akusale dhamme samādāya vattissanti.**You can expect that they will reject good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and undertake and implement bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1502]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1503]="*Na hi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā passanti akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ.**Because those ascetics and brahmins don’t see that unskillful qualities are full of drawbacks, sordidness, and corruption, or that skillful qualities have the benefit and cleansing power of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[1504]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ tissa diṭṭhi hoti; sāssa hoti micchādiṭṭhi.**Moreover, since there actually is causality, their view that there is no causality is wrong view.*";
P_HTM[1505]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ti saṅkappeti; svāssa hoti micchāsaṅkappo.**Since there actually is causality, their thought that there is no causality is wrong thought.*";
P_HTM[1506]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ti vācaṃ bhāsati; sāssa hoti micchāvācā.**Since there actually is causality, their speech that there is no causality is wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[1507]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ti āha; ye te arahanto hetuvādā tesamayaṃ paccanīkaṃ karoti.**Since there actually is causality, in saying that there is no causality they contradict those perfected ones who teach that there is causality.*";
P_HTM[1508]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ti paraṃ saññāpeti; sāssa hoti asaddhammasaññatti.**Since there actually is causality, in convincing another that there is no causality they are convincing them to accept an untrue teaching.*";
P_HTM[1509]="*Tāya ca pana asaddhammasaññattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti.**And on account of that they glorify themselves and put others down.*";
P_HTM[1510]="*Iti pubbeva kho panassa susīlyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, dussīlyaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ—**So they give up their former ethical conduct and are established in unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[1511]="*ayañca micchādiṭṭhi micchāsaṅkappo micchāvācā ariyānaṃ paccanīkatā asaddhammasaññatti attānukkaṃsanā paravambhanā. Evamassime aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti micchādiṭṭhipaccayā.**And that is how wrong view gives rise to these many bad, unskillful qualities—wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, contradicting the noble ones, convincing others to accept untrue teachings, and glorifying oneself and putting others down.*";
P_HTM[1512]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[1513]="*‘sace kho natthi hetu, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sotthimattānaṃ karissati;**‘If there is no causality, when this individual’s body breaks up they will keep themselves safe.*";
P_HTM[1514]="*sace kho atthi hetu, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissati.**And if there is causality, when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[1515]="*Kāmaṃ kho pana māhu hetu, hotu nesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ;**But let’s assume that those who say that there is no causality are correct.*";
P_HTM[1516]="*atha ca panāyaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ gārayho—dussīlo purisapuggalo micchādiṭṭhi ahetukavādo’ti.**Regardless, that individual is still criticized by sensible people in the present life as being an immoral individual of wrong view, one who denies causality.’*";
P_HTM[1517]="*Sace kho attheva hetu, evaṃ imassa bhoto purisapuggalassa ubhayattha kaliggaho—**But if there really is causality, they lose on both counts.*";
P_HTM[1518]="*yañca diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ gārayho, yañca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissati.**For they are criticized by sensible people in the present life, and when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[1519]="*Evamassāyaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo dussamatto samādinno, ekaṃsaṃ pharitvā tiṭṭhati, riñcati kusalaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**They have wrongly undertaken this guaranteed teaching in such a way that it encompasses the positive outcomes of one side only, leaving out the skillful premise.*";
P_HTM[1520]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**Since this is so, consider those ascetics and brahmins whose view is that*";
P_HTM[1521]="*‘atthi hetu, atthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya;**there is a cause and condition for the corruption of sentient beings, etc.*";
P_HTM[1522]="*sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti.* **";
P_HTM[1523]="*Atthi hetu, atthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;* **";
P_HTM[1524]="*sahetū sappaccayā sattā visujjhanti.* **";
P_HTM[1525]="*Atthi balaṃ, atthi vīriyaṃ, atthi purisathāmo, atthi purisaparakkamo; na sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā niyatisaṅgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti* **";
P_HTM[1526]="*tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—yamidaṃ kāyaduccaritaṃ, vacīduccaritaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ—ime tayo akusale dhamme abhinivajjetvā yamidaṃ kāyasucaritaṃ, vacīsucaritaṃ, manosucaritaṃ—ime tayo kusale dhamme samādāya vattissanti.**You can expect that they will reject bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and undertake and implement good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[1527]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[1528]="*Passanti hi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ.**Because those ascetics and brahmins see that unskillful qualities are full of drawbacks, sordidness, and corruption, and that skillful qualities have the benefit and cleansing power of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[1529]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘atthi hetū’ tissa diṭṭhi hoti; sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi.**Moreover, since there actually is causality, their view that there is causality is right view.*";
P_HTM[1530]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘atthi hetū’ti saṅkappeti; svāssa hoti sammāsaṅkappo.**Since there actually is causality, their thought that there is causality is right thought.*";
P_HTM[1531]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘atthi hetū’ti vācaṃ bhāsati; sāssa hoti sammāvācā.**Since there actually is causality, their speech that there is causality is right speech.*";
P_HTM[1532]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘atthi hetū’ti āha, ye te arahanto hetuvādā tesamayaṃ na paccanīkaṃ karoti.**Since there actually is causality, in saying that there is causality they don’t contradict those perfected ones who teach that there is causality.*";
P_HTM[1533]="*Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘atthi hetū’ti paraṃ saññāpeti; sāssa hoti saddhammasaññatti.**Since there actually is causality, in convincing another that there is causality they are convincing them to accept a true teaching.*";
P_HTM[1534]="*Tāya ca pana saddhammasaññattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti.**And on account of that they don’t glorify themselves or put others down.*";
P_HTM[1535]="*Iti pubbeva kho panassa dussīlyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, susīlyaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ—**So they give up their former unethical conduct and are established in ethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[1536]="*ayañca sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā ariyānaṃ apaccanīkatā saddhammasaññatti anattukkaṃsanā aparavambhanā. Evamassime aneke kusalā dhammā sambhavanti sammādiṭṭhipaccayā.**And that is how right view gives rise to these many skillful qualities—right view, right thought, right speech, not contradicting the noble ones, convincing others to accept true teachings, and not glorifying oneself or putting others down.*";
P_HTM[1537]="*Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati: ‘sace kho atthi hetu, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissati.**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way: ‘If there is causality, when this individual’s body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[1538]="*Kāmaṃ kho pana māhu hetu, hotu nesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ;**But let’s assume that those who say that there is no causality are correct.*";
P_HTM[1539]="*atha ca panāyaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ pāsaṃso—sīlavā purisapuggalo sammādiṭṭhi hetuvādo’ti.**Regardless, that individual is still praised by sensible people in the present life as being a moral individual of right view, who affirms causality.’*";
P_HTM[1540]="*Sace kho atthi hetu, evaṃ imassa bhoto purisapuggalassa ubhayattha kaṭaggaho—**So if there really is causality, they win on both counts.*";
P_HTM[1541]="*yañca diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ pāsaṃso, yañca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissati.**For they are praised by sensible people in the present life, and when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[1542]="*Evamassāyaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo susamatto samādinno, ubhayaṃsaṃ pharitvā tiṭṭhati, riñcati akusalaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**They have rightly undertaken this guaranteed teaching in such a way that it encompasses the positive outcomes of both sides, leaving out the unskillful premise.*";
P_HTM[1543]="*Santi, gahapatayo, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[1544]="*‘natthi sabbaso āruppā’ti.**‘There are no totally formless states of meditation.’*";
P_HTM[1545]="*Tesaṃyeva kho, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā ujuvipaccanīkavādā.**And there are some ascetics and brahmins whose doctrine directly contradicts this.*";
P_HTM[1546]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say:*";
P_HTM[1547]="*‘atthi sabbaso āruppā’ti.**‘There are totally formless states of meditation.’*";
P_HTM[1548]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, gahapatayo,**What do you think, householders?*";
P_HTM[1549]="*nanume samaṇabrāhmaṇā aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā”ti?**Don’t these doctrines directly contradict each other?”*";
P_HTM[1550]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1551]="*“Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati—**“A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[1552]="*ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**‘Some ascetics and brahmins say that*";
P_HTM[1553]="*‘natthi sabbaso āruppā’ti, idaṃ me adiṭṭhaṃ;**there are no totally formless meditations, but I have not seen that.*";
P_HTM[1554]="*yepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**Some ascetics and brahmins say that*";
P_HTM[1555]="*‘atthi sabbaso āruppā’ti, idaṃ me aviditaṃ.**there are totally formless meditations, but I have not known that.*";
P_HTM[1556]="*Ahañceva kho pana ajānanto apassanto ekaṃsena ādāya vohareyyaṃ—**Without knowing or seeing, it would not be appropriate for me to take one side and declare,*";
P_HTM[1557]="*idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññanti, na metaṃ assa patirūpaṃ.**‘This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’*";
P_HTM[1558]="*Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**If those ascetics and brahmins who say that*";
P_HTM[1559]="*‘natthi sabbaso āruppā’ti, sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati—**there are no totally formless meditations are correct, it is possible*";
P_HTM[1560]="*ye te devā rūpino manomayā, apaṇṇakaṃ me tatrūpapatti bhavissati.**that I will be guaranteed rebirth among the gods who possess form and made of mind.*";
P_HTM[1561]="*Ye pana te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**If those ascetics and brahmins who say that*";
P_HTM[1562]="*‘atthi sabbaso āruppā’ti, sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati—**there are totally formless meditations are correct, it is possible*";
P_HTM[1563]="*ye te devā arūpino saññāmayā, apaṇṇakaṃ me tatrūpapatti bhavissati.**that I will be guaranteed rebirth among the gods who are formless and made of perception.*";
P_HTM[1564]="*Dissanti kho pana rūpādhikaraṇaṃ daṇḍādānasatthādānakalahaviggahavivādatuvaṃtuvaṃpesuññamusāvādā.**Now, owing to form, bad things are seen: taking up the rod and the sword, quarrels, arguments, and fights, accusations, divisive speech, and lies.*";
P_HTM[1565]="*‘Natthi kho panetaṃ sabbaso arūpe’ti.**But those things don’t exist where it is totally formless.’*";
P_HTM[1566]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya rūpānaṃyeva nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti.**Reflecting like this, they simply practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding forms.*";
P_HTM[1567]="*Santi, gahapatayo, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[1568]="*‘natthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti.**‘There is no such thing as the total cessation of future lives.’*";
P_HTM[1569]="*Tesaṃyeva kho, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā ujuvipaccanīkavādā.**And there are some ascetics and brahmins whose doctrine directly contradicts this.*";
P_HTM[1570]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say:*";
P_HTM[1571]="*‘atthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti.**‘There is such a thing as the total cessation of future lives.’*";
P_HTM[1572]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, gahapatayo,**What do you think, householders?*";
P_HTM[1573]="*nanume samaṇabrāhmaṇā aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā”ti?**Don’t these doctrines directly contradict each other?”*";
P_HTM[1574]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1575]="*“Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati—**“A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[1576]="*ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**‘Some ascetics and brahmins say that*";
P_HTM[1577]="*‘natthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, idaṃ me adiṭṭhaṃ;**there is no such thing as the total cessation of future lives, but I have not seen that.*";
P_HTM[1578]="*yepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**Some ascetics and brahmins say that*";
P_HTM[1579]="*‘atthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, idaṃ me aviditaṃ.**there is such a thing as the total cessation of future lives, but I have not known that.*";
P_HTM[1580]="*Ahañceva kho pana ajānanto apassanto ekaṃsena ādāya vohareyyaṃ—**Without knowing or seeing, it would not be appropriate for me to take one side and declare,*";
P_HTM[1581]="*idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññanti, na metaṃ assa patirūpaṃ.**‚This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’*";
P_HTM[1582]="*Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**If those ascetics and brahmins who say that*";
P_HTM[1583]="*‘natthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati—**there is no such thing as the total cessation of future lives are correct, it is possible*";
P_HTM[1584]="*ye te devā arūpino saññāmayā apaṇṇakaṃ me tatrūpapatti bhavissati.**that I will be guaranteed rebirth among the gods who are formless and made of perception.*";
P_HTM[1585]="*Ye pana te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**If those ascetics and brahmins who say that*";
P_HTM[1586]="*‘atthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ vacanaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati—**there is such a thing as the total cessation of future lives are correct, it is possible*";
P_HTM[1587]="*yaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyissāmi.**that I will be extinguished in the present life.*";
P_HTM[1588]="*Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**The view of those ascetics and brahmins who say that*";
P_HTM[1589]="*‘natthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, tesamayaṃ diṭṭhi sārāgāya santike, saṃyogāya santike, abhinandanāya santike, ajjhosānāya santike, upādānāya santike.**there is no such thing as the total cessation of future lives is close to greed, approving, attachment, and grasping.*";
P_HTM[1590]="*Ye pana te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**The view of those ascetics and brahmins who say that*";
P_HTM[1591]="*‘atthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, tesamayaṃ diṭṭhi asārāgāya santike, asaṃyogāya santike, anabhinandanāya santike, anajjhosānāya santike, anupādānāya santiketi.**there is such a thing as the total cessation of future lives is close to non-greed, non-approving, non-attachment, and non-grasping.’*";
P_HTM[1592]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya bhavānaṃyeva nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti.**Reflecting like this, they simply practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding future lives.*";
P_HTM[1593]="*Cattārome, gahapatayo, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**Householders, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[1594]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[1595]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo attantapo hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies themselves, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves.*";
P_HTM[1596]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo parantapo hoti paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies others, committed to the practice of mortifying others.*";
P_HTM[1597]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo attantapo ca hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies themselves and others, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[1598]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo nevattantapo hoti nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;**One person doesn’t mortify either themselves or others, committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others.*";
P_HTM[1599]="*so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati.**They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.*";
P_HTM[1600]="*Katamo ca, gahapatayo, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And what person mortifies themselves, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves?*";
P_HTM[1601]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo acelako hoti muttācāro hatthāpalekhano … pe …**It’s when someone goes naked, ignoring conventions. …*";
P_HTM[1602]="*iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**And so they live committed to practicing these various ways of mortifying and tormenting the body.*";
P_HTM[1603]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapatayo, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies themselves, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves.*";
P_HTM[1604]="*Katamo ca, gahapatayo, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And what person mortifies others, committed to the practice of mortifying others?*";
P_HTM[1605]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo orabbhiko hoti sūkariko … pe … ye vā panaññepi keci kurūrakammantā.**It’s when a person is a butcher of sheep, pigs, poultry, or deer, a hunter or fisher, a bandit, an executioner, a butcher of cattle, a jailer, or has some other cruel livelihood.*";
P_HTM[1606]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapatayo, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies others, being committed to the practice of mortifying others.*";
P_HTM[1607]="*Katamo ca, gahapatayo, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And what person mortifies themselves and others, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others?*";
P_HTM[1608]="*Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo rājā vā hoti khattiyo muddhāvasitto … pe …**It’s when a person is an anointed king or a well-to-do brahmin. …*";
P_HTM[1609]="*tepi daṇḍatajjitā bhayatajjitā assumukhā rudamānā parikammāni karonti.**His bondservants, servants, and workers do their jobs under threat of punishment and danger, weeping, with tearful faces.*";
P_HTM[1610]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapatayo, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies themselves and others, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[1611]="*Katamo ca, gahapatayo, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;**And what person doesn’t mortify either themselves or others, committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others,*";
P_HTM[1612]="*so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati?**living without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves?*";
P_HTM[1613]="*Idha, gahapatayo, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho …**It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha …*";
P_HTM[1614]="*pe …**A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some good family. …*";
P_HTM[1615]="*so ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[1616]="*vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[1617]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …**second absorption …*";
P_HTM[1618]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[1619]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[1620]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives. …*";
P_HTM[1621]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[1622]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[1623]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. … They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[1624]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[1625]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe …**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[1626]="*‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[1627]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati.**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[1628]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[1629]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[1630]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapatayo, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;**This is called a person who neither mortifies themselves or others, being committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others.*";
P_HTM[1631]="*so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharatī”ti.**They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.”*";
P_HTM[1632]="*Evaṃ vutte, sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Sālā said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[1633]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[1634]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[1635]="*Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[1636]="*Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gate”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[1637]="*Apaṇṇakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1638]="*Gahapativaggo niṭṭhito paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[1639]="*Kandaranāgarasekhavato ca,* **";
P_HTM[1640]="*Potaliyo puna jīvakabhacco;* **";
P_HTM[1641]="*Upālidamatho kukkuraabhayo,* **";
P_HTM[1642]="*Bahuvedanīyāpaṇṇakato dasamo.* **";
P_HTM[1643]="*61. Ambalaṭṭhikarāhulovādasutta**Advice to Rāhula at Ambalaṭṭhika*";
P_HTM[1644]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[1645]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[1646]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā rāhulo ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ viharati.**Now at that time Venerable Rāhula was staying at Ambalaṭṭhikā.*";
P_HTM[1647]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena ambalaṭṭhikā yenāyasmā rāhulo tenupasaṅkami.**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to Ambalaṭṭhika to see Venerable Rāhula.*";
P_HTM[1648]="*Addasā kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Rāhula saw the Buddha coming off in the distance.*";
P_HTM[1649]="*Disvāna āsanaṃ paññāpesi, udakañca pādānaṃ.**He spread out a seat and placed water for washing the feet.*";
P_HTM[1650]="*Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane.**The Buddha sat on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[1651]="*Nisajja pāde pakkhālesi.**and washed his feet.*";
P_HTM[1652]="*Āyasmāpi kho rāhulo bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Rāhula bowed to the Buddha and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[1653]="*Atha kho bhagavā parittaṃ udakāvasesaṃ udakādhāne ṭhapetvā āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha, leaving a little water in the pot, addressed Rāhula,*";
P_HTM[1654]="*“passasi no tvaṃ, rāhula, imaṃ parittaṃ udakāvasesaṃ udakādhāne ṭhapitan”ti?**“Rāhula, do you see this little bit of water left in the pot?”*";
P_HTM[1655]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1656]="*“Evaṃ parittakaṃ kho, rāhula, tesaṃ sāmaññaṃ yesaṃ natthi sampajānamusāvāde lajjā”ti.**“That’s how little of the ascetic’s nature is left in those who are not ashamed to tell a deliberate lie.”*";
P_HTM[1657]="*Atha kho bhagavā parittaṃ udakāvasesaṃ chaḍḍetvā āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha, tossing away what little water was left in the pot, said to Rāhula,*";
P_HTM[1658]="*“passasi no tvaṃ, rāhula, parittaṃ udakāvasesaṃ chaḍḍitan”ti?**“Do you see this little bit of water that was tossed away?”*";
P_HTM[1659]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1660]="*“Evaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ kho, rāhula, tesaṃ sāmaññaṃ yesaṃ natthi sampajānamusāvāde lajjā”ti.**“That’s how the ascetic’s nature is tossed away in those who are not ashamed to tell a deliberate lie.”*";
P_HTM[1661]="*Atha kho bhagavā taṃ udakādhānaṃ nikkujjitvā āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha, turning the pot upside down, said to Rāhula,*";
P_HTM[1662]="*“passasi no tvaṃ, rāhula, imaṃ udakādhānaṃ nikkujjitan”ti?**“Do you see how this pot is turned upside down?”*";
P_HTM[1663]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1664]="*“Evaṃ nikkujjitaṃ kho, rāhula, tesaṃ sāmaññaṃ yesaṃ natthi sampajānamusāvāde lajjā”ti.**“That’s how the ascetic’s nature is turned upside down in those who are not ashamed to tell a deliberate lie.”*";
P_HTM[1665]="*Atha kho bhagavā taṃ udakādhānaṃ ukkujjitvā āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha, turning the pot right side up, said to Rāhula,*";
P_HTM[1666]="*“passasi no tvaṃ, rāhula, imaṃ udakādhānaṃ rittaṃ tucchan”ti?**“Do you see how this pot is vacant and hollow?”*";
P_HTM[1667]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1668]="*“Evaṃ rittaṃ tucchaṃ kho, rāhula, tesaṃ sāmaññaṃ yesaṃ natthi sampajānamusāvāde lajjāti.**“That’s how vacant and hollow the ascetic’s nature is in those who are not ashamed to tell a deliberate lie.*";
P_HTM[1669]="*Seyyathāpi, rāhula, rañño nāgo īsādanto urūḷhavā abhijāto saṅgāmāvacaro saṅgāmagato purimehipi pādehi kammaṃ karoti, pacchimehipi pādehi kammaṃ karoti, purimenapi kāyena kammaṃ karoti, pacchimenapi kāyena kammaṃ karoti, sīsenapi kammaṃ karoti, kaṇṇehipi kammaṃ karoti, dantehipi kammaṃ karoti, naṅguṭṭhenapi kammaṃ karoti; rakkhateva soṇḍaṃ.**Suppose there was a royal bull elephant with tusks like plows, able to draw a heavy load, pedigree and battle-hardened. In battle it uses its fore-feet and hind-feet, its fore-quarters and hind-quarters, its head, ears, tusks, and tail, but it still protects its trunk.*";
P_HTM[1670]="*Tattha hatthārohassa evaṃ hoti:**So its rider thinks:*";
P_HTM[1671]="*‘ayaṃ kho rañño nāgo īsādanto urūḷhavā abhijāto saṅgāmāvacaro saṅgāmagato purimehipi pādehi kammaṃ karoti, pacchimehipi pādehi kammaṃ karoti … pe … naṅguṭṭhenapi kammaṃ karoti; rakkhateva soṇḍaṃ.**‘This royal bull elephant still protects its trunk.*";
P_HTM[1672]="*Apariccattaṃ kho rañño nāgassa jīvitan’ti.**It has not fully dedicated its life.’*";
P_HTM[1673]="*Yato kho, rāhula, rañño nāgo īsādanto urūḷhavā abhijāto saṅgāmāvacaro saṅgāmagato purimehipi pādehi kammaṃ karoti, pacchimehipi pādehi kammaṃ karoti … pe … naṅguṭṭhenapi kammaṃ karoti, soṇḍāyapi kammaṃ karoti, tattha hatthārohassa evaṃ hoti:**But when that royal bull elephant … in battle uses its fore-feet and hind-feet, its fore-quarters and hind-quarters, its head, ears, tusks, and tail, and its trunk, its rider thinks:*";
P_HTM[1674]="*‘ayaṃ kho rañño nāgo īsādanto urūḷhavā abhijāto saṅgāmāvacaro saṅgāmagato purimehipi pādehi kammaṃ karoti, pacchimehipi pādehi kammaṃ karoti, purimenapi kāyena kammaṃ karoti, pacchimenapi kāyena kammaṃ karoti, sīsenapi kammaṃ karoti, kaṇṇehipi kammaṃ karoti, dantehipi kammaṃ karoti, naṅguṭṭhenapi kammaṃ karoti, soṇḍāyapi kammaṃ karoti.**‘This royal bull elephant … in battle uses its fore-feet and hind-feet, its fore-quarters and hind-quarters, its head, ears, tusks, and tail, and its trunk.*";
P_HTM[1675]="*Pariccattaṃ kho rañño nāgassa jīvitaṃ.**It has fully dedicated its life.*";
P_HTM[1676]="*Natthi dāni kiñci rañño nāgassa akaraṇīyan’ti.**Now there is nothing that royal bull elephant would not do.’*";
P_HTM[1677]="*Evameva kho, rāhula, yassa kassaci sampajānamusāvāde natthi lajjā, nāhaṃ tassa kiñci pāpaṃ akaraṇīyanti vadāmi.**In the same way, when someone is not ashamed to tell a deliberate lie, there is no bad deed they would not do, I say.*";
P_HTM[1678]="*Tasmātiha te, rāhula, ‘hassāpi na musā bhaṇissāmī’ti—**So you should train like this: ‘I will not tell a lie, even for a joke.’*";
P_HTM[1679]="*evañhi te, rāhula, sikkhitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1680]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[1681]="*kimatthiyo ādāso”ti?**What is the purpose of a mirror?”*";
P_HTM[1682]="*“Paccavekkhaṇattho, bhante”ti.**“It’s for checking your reflection, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1683]="*“Evameva kho, rāhula, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā kāyena kammaṃ kattabbaṃ, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā vācāya kammaṃ kattabbaṃ, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā manasā kammaṃ kattabbaṃ.**“In the same way, deeds of body, speech, and mind should be done only after repeated checking.*";
P_HTM[1684]="*Yadeva tvaṃ, rāhula, kāyena kammaṃ kattukāmo ahosi, tadeva te kāyakammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:**When you want to act with the body, you should check on that same deed:*";
P_HTM[1685]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—**‘Does this act with the body that I want to do lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both?*";
P_HTM[1686]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?**Is it unskillful, with suffering as its outcome and result?’*";
P_HTM[1687]="*Sace tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**If, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1688]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—**‘This act with the body that I want to do leads to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1689]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ te, rāhula, kāyena kammaṃ sasakkaṃ na karaṇīyaṃ.**It’s unskillful, with suffering as its outcome and result.’ To the best of your ability, Rāhula, you should not do such a deed.*";
P_HTM[1690]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**But if, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1691]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—**‘This act with the body that I want to do doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1692]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ te, rāhula, kāyena kammaṃ karaṇīyaṃ.**It’s skillful, with happiness as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should do such a deed.*";
P_HTM[1693]="*Karontenapi te, rāhula, kāyena kammaṃ tadeva te kāyakammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:**While you are acting with the body, you should check on that same act:*";
P_HTM[1694]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘Does this act with the body that I am doing lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both?*";
P_HTM[1695]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?**Is it unskillful, with suffering as its outcome and result?’*";
P_HTM[1696]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**If, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1697]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘This act with the body that I am doing leads to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1698]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, paṭisaṃhareyyāsi tvaṃ, rāhula, evarūpaṃ kāyakammaṃ.**It’s unskillful, with suffering as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should desist from such a deed.*";
P_HTM[1699]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**But if, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1700]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘This act with the body that I am doing doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1701]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, anupadajjeyyāsi tvaṃ, rāhula, evarūpaṃ kāyakammaṃ.**It’s skillful, with happiness as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should continue doing such a deed.*";
P_HTM[1702]="*Katvāpi te, rāhula, kāyena kammaṃ tadeva te kāyakammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:**After you have acted with the body, you should check on that same act:*";
P_HTM[1703]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ akāsiṃ idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘Does this act with the body that I have done lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both?*";
P_HTM[1704]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?**Is it unskillful, with suffering as its outcome and result?’*";
P_HTM[1705]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**If, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1706]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ akāsiṃ, idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘This act with the body that I have done leads to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1707]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ te, rāhula, kāyakammaṃ satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu desetabbaṃ, vivaritabbaṃ, uttānīkātabbaṃ;**It’s unskillful, with suffering as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should confess, reveal, and clarify such a deed to the Teacher or a sensible spiritual companion.*";
P_HTM[1708]="*desetvā vivaritvā uttānīkatvā āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjitabbaṃ.**And having revealed it you should restrain yourself in future.*";
P_HTM[1709]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**But if, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1710]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ kāyena kammaṃ akāsiṃ idaṃ me kāyakammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘This act with the body that I have done doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1711]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ kāyakammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, teneva tvaṃ, rāhula, pītipāmojjena vihareyyāsi ahorattānusikkhī kusalesu dhammesu.**It’s skillful, with happiness as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should live in rapture and joy because of this, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[1712]="*“Yadeva tvaṃ, rāhula, vācāya kammaṃ kattukāmo ahosi, tadeva te vacīkammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:**When you want to act with speech, you should check on that same deed:*";
P_HTM[1713]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—**‘Does this act of speech that I want to do lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both?’ …*";
P_HTM[1714]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?* **";
P_HTM[1715]="*Sace tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1716]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—* **";
P_HTM[1717]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ te, rāhula, vācāya kammaṃ sasakkaṃ na karaṇīyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1718]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1719]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—* **";
P_HTM[1720]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ te, rāhula, vācāya kammaṃ karaṇīyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1721]="*Karontenapi te, rāhula, vācāya kammaṃ tadeva te vacīkammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[1722]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—* **";
P_HTM[1723]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?* **";
P_HTM[1724]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1725]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—* **";
P_HTM[1726]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, paṭisaṃhareyyāsi tvaṃ, rāhula, evarūpaṃ vacīkammaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1727]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1728]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—* **";
P_HTM[1729]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, anupadajjeyyāsi tvaṃ, rāhula, evarūpaṃ vacīkammaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1730]="*Katvāpi te, rāhula, vācāya kammaṃ tadeva te vacīkammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[1731]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ akāsiṃ idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—* **";
P_HTM[1732]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?* **";
P_HTM[1733]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**If, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1734]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ akāsiṃ idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘This act of speech that I have done leads to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1735]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ te, rāhula, vacīkammaṃ satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu desetabbaṃ, vivaritabbaṃ, uttānīkattabbaṃ;**It’s unskillful, with suffering as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should confess, reveal, and clarify such a deed to the Teacher or a sensible spiritual companion.*";
P_HTM[1736]="*desetvā vivaritvā uttānīkatvā āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjitabbaṃ.**And having revealed it you should restrain yourself in future.*";
P_HTM[1737]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**But if, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1738]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ vācāya kammaṃ akāsiṃ idaṃ me vacīkammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘This act of speech that I have done doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1739]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ vacīkammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, teneva tvaṃ, rāhula, pītipāmojjena vihareyyāsi ahorattānusikkhī kusalesu dhammesu.**It’s skillful, with happiness as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should live in rapture and joy because of this, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[1740]="*Yadeva tvaṃ, rāhula, manasā kammaṃ kattukāmo ahosi, tadeva te manokammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:**When you want to act with the mind, you should check on that same deed:*";
P_HTM[1741]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me manokammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—**‘Does this act of mind that I want to do lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both?’ …*";
P_HTM[1742]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?* **";
P_HTM[1743]="*Sace tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1744]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me manokammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—* **";
P_HTM[1745]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ te, rāhula, manasā kammaṃ sasakkaṃ na karaṇīyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1746]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1747]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ kattukāmo idaṃ me manokammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvatteyya—* **";
P_HTM[1748]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ te, rāhula, manasā kammaṃ karaṇīyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1749]="*Karontenapi te, rāhula, manasā kammaṃ tadeva te manokammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[1750]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me manokammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—* **";
P_HTM[1751]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?* **";
P_HTM[1752]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1753]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me manokammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—* **";
P_HTM[1754]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, paṭisaṃhareyyāsi tvaṃ, rāhula, evarūpaṃ manokammaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1755]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:* **";
P_HTM[1756]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ karomi idaṃ me manokammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—* **";
P_HTM[1757]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, anupadajjeyyāsi tvaṃ, rāhula, evarūpaṃ manokammaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1758]="*Katvāpi te, rāhula, manasā kammaṃ tadeva te manokammaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[1759]="*‘yannu kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ akāsiṃ idaṃ me manokammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—* **";
P_HTM[1760]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti?* **";
P_HTM[1761]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**If, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1762]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ akāsiṃ idaṃ me manokammaṃ attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘This act of mind that I have done leads to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1763]="*akusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākan’ti, evarūpaṃ pana te, rāhula, manokammaṃ aṭṭīyitabbaṃ harāyitabbaṃ jigucchitabbaṃ;**It’s unskillful, with suffering as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should be horrified, repelled, and disgusted by that deed.*";
P_HTM[1764]="*aṭṭīyitvā harāyitvā jigucchitvā āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjitabbaṃ.**And being repelled, you should restrain yourself in future.*";
P_HTM[1765]="*Sace pana tvaṃ, rāhula, paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jāneyyāsi:**But if, while checking in this way, you know:*";
P_HTM[1766]="*‘yaṃ kho ahaṃ idaṃ manasā kammaṃ akāsiṃ idaṃ me manokammaṃ nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati—**‘This act with the mind that I have done doesn’t lead to hurting myself, hurting others, or hurting both.*";
P_HTM[1767]="*kusalaṃ idaṃ manokammaṃ sukhudrayaṃ sukhavipākan’ti, teneva tvaṃ, rāhula, pītipāmojjena vihareyyāsi ahorattānusikkhī kusalesu dhammesu.**It’s skillful, with happiness as its outcome and result.’ Then, Rāhula, you should live in rapture and joy because of this, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[1768]="*Ye hi keci, rāhula, atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyakammaṃ parisodhesuṃ, vacīkammaṃ parisodhesuṃ, manokammaṃ parisodhesuṃ, sabbe te evamevaṃ paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā kāyakammaṃ parisodhesuṃ, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā vacīkammaṃ parisodhesuṃ, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā manokammaṃ parisodhesuṃ.**All the ascetics and brahmins of the past, future, and present who purify their physical, verbal, and mental actions do so after repeatedly checking.*";
P_HTM[1769]="*Yepi hi keci, rāhula, anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyakammaṃ parisodhessanti, vacīkammaṃ parisodhessanti, manokammaṃ parisodhessanti, sabbe te evamevaṃ paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā kāyakammaṃ parisodhessanti, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā vacīkammaṃ parisodhessanti, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā manokammaṃ parisodhessan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1770]="*Yepi hi keci, rāhula, etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyakammaṃ parisodhenti, vacīkammaṃ parisodhenti, manokammaṃ parisodhenti, sabbe te evamevaṃ paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā kāyakammaṃ parisodhenti, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā vacīkammaṃ parisodhenti, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā manokammaṃ parisodhenti.* **";
P_HTM[1771]="*Tasmātiha, rāhula, ‘paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā kāyakammaṃ parisodhessāmi, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā vacīkammaṃ parisodhessāmi, paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā manokammaṃ parisodhessāmī’ti—**So Rāhula, you should train yourself like this: ‘I will purify my physical, verbal, and mental actions after repeatedly checking.’”*";
P_HTM[1772]="*evañhi te, rāhula, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1773]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[1774]="*Attamano āyasmā rāhulo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Rāhula was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[1775]="*Ambalaṭṭhikarāhulovādasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1776]="*62. Mahārāhulovādasutta**The Longer Advice to Rāhula*";
P_HTM[1777]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[1778]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[1779]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[1780]="*Āyasmāpi kho rāhulo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi.**And Venerable Rāhula also robed up and followed behind the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[1781]="*Atha kho bhagavā apaloketvā āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha looked back at Rāhula and said,*";
P_HTM[1782]="*“yaṃ kiñci, rāhula, rūpaṃ—atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā—sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabban”ti.**“Rāhula, you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’”*";
P_HTM[1783]="*“Rūpameva nu kho, bhagavā, rūpameva nu kho, sugatā”ti?**“Only form, Blessed One? Only form, Holy One?”*";
P_HTM[1784]="*“Rūpampi, rāhula, vedanāpi, rāhula, saññāpi, rāhula, saṅkhārāpi, rāhula, viññāṇampi, rāhulā”ti.**“Form, Rāhula, as well as feeling and perception and choices and consciousness.”*";
P_HTM[1785]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo “ko najja bhagavatā sammukhā ovādena ovadito gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissatī”ti tato paṭinivattitvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdi pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**Then Rāhula thought, “Who would go to the village for alms today after being advised directly by the Buddha?” Turning back, he sat down at the root of a certain tree cross-legged, with his body straight, and established mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[1786]="*Addasā kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisinnaṃ pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**Venerable Sāriputta saw him sitting there,*";
P_HTM[1787]="*Disvāna āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:**and addressed him,*";
P_HTM[1788]="*“ānāpānassatiṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**“Rāhula, develop mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[1789]="*Ānāpānassati, rāhula, bhāvanā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā”ti.**When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial.”*";
P_HTM[1790]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, Rāhula came out of retreat, went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[1791]="*“kathaṃ bhāvitā nu kho, bhante, ānāpānassati, kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā”ti?**“Sir, how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very fruitful and beneficial?”*";
P_HTM[1792]="*“Yaṃ kiñci, rāhula, ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ kakkhaḷaṃ kharigataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**“Rāhula, the interior earth element is said to be anything hard, solid, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[1793]="*kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco maṃsaṃ nhāru aṭṭhi aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ antaṃ antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ kakkhaḷaṃ kharigataṃ upādinnaṃ—**head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, sinews, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, diaphragm, spleen, lungs, intestines, mesentery, undigested food, feces, or anything else hard, solid, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual.*";
P_HTM[1794]="*ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu.**This is called the interior earth element.*";
P_HTM[1795]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā pathavīdhātu yā ca bāhirā pathavīdhātu, pathavīdhāturevesā.**The interior earth element and the exterior earth element are just the earth element.*";
P_HTM[1796]="*Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[1797]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindati, pathavīdhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the earth element, detaching the mind from the earth element.*";
P_HTM[1798]="*Katamā ca, rāhula, āpodhātu?**And what is the water element?*";
P_HTM[1799]="*Āpodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā.**The water element may be interior or exterior.*";
P_HTM[1800]="*Katamā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā āpodhātu?**And what is the interior water element?*";
P_HTM[1801]="*Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ āpo āpogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**Anything that’s water, watery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[1802]="*pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā muttaṃ, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ āpo āpogataṃ upādinnaṃ—**bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears, grease, saliva, snot, synovial fluid, urine, or anything else that’s water, watery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual.*";
P_HTM[1803]="*ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā āpodhātu.**This is called the interior water element.*";
P_HTM[1804]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā āpodhātu yā ca bāhirā āpodhātu āpodhāturevesā.**The interior water element and the exterior water element are just the water element.*";
P_HTM[1805]="*Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[1806]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā āpodhātuyā nibbindati, āpodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the water element, detaching the mind from the water element.*";
P_HTM[1807]="*Katamā ca, rāhula, tejodhātu?**And what is the fire element?*";
P_HTM[1808]="*Tejodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā.**The fire element may be interior or exterior.*";
P_HTM[1809]="*Katamā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā tejodhātu?**And what is the interior fire element?*";
P_HTM[1810]="*Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ tejo tejogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**Anything that’s fire, fiery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[1811]="*yena ca santappati yena ca jīrīyati yena ca pariḍayhati yena ca asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ sammā pariṇāmaṃ gacchati, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ tejo tejogataṃ upādinnaṃ—**that which warms, that which ages, that which heats you up when feverish, that which properly digests food and drink, or anything else that’s fire, fiery, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual.*";
P_HTM[1812]="*ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā tejodhātu.**This is called the interior fire element.*";
P_HTM[1813]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā tejodhātu yā ca bāhirā tejodhātu tejodhāturevesā.**The interior fire element and the exterior fire element are just the fire element.*";
P_HTM[1814]="*Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[1815]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā tejodhātuyā nibbindati, tejodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the fire element, detaching the mind from the fire element.*";
P_HTM[1816]="*Katamā ca, rāhula, vāyodhātu?**And what is the air element?*";
P_HTM[1817]="*Vāyodhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā.**The air element may be interior or exterior.*";
P_HTM[1818]="*Katamā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu?**And what is the interior air element?*";
P_HTM[1819]="*Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ vāyo vāyogataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**Anything that’s wind, windy, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[1820]="*uddhaṅgamā vātā, adhogamā vātā, kucchisayā vātā, koṭṭhāsayā vātā, aṅgamaṅgānusārino vātā, assāso passāso iti, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ vāyo vāyogataṃ upādinnaṃ—**winds that go up or down, winds in the belly or the bowels, winds that flow through the limbs, in-breaths and out-breaths, or anything else that’s air, airy, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual.*";
P_HTM[1821]="*ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā vāyodhātu.**This is called the interior air element.*";
P_HTM[1822]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā vāyodhātu yā ca bāhirā vāyodhātu vāyodhāturevesā.**The interior air element and the exterior air element are just the air element.*";
P_HTM[1823]="*Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[1824]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā vāyodhātuyā nibbindati, vāyodhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the air element, detaching the mind from the air element.*";
P_HTM[1825]="*Katamā ca, rāhula, ākāsadhātu?**And what is the space element?*";
P_HTM[1826]="*Ākāsadhātu siyā ajjhattikā, siyā bāhirā.**The space element may be interior or exterior.*";
P_HTM[1827]="*Katamā ca, rāhula, ajjhattikā ākāsadhātu?**And what is the interior space element?*";
P_HTM[1828]="*Yaṃ ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ ākāsaṃ ākāsagataṃ upādinnaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—**Anything that’s space, spacious, and organic that’s internal, pertaining to an individual. This includes:*";
P_HTM[1829]="*kaṇṇacchiddaṃ nāsacchiddaṃ mukhadvāraṃ, yena ca asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ ajjhoharati, yattha ca asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ santiṭṭhati, yena ca asitapītakhāyitasāyitaṃ adhobhāgaṃ nikkhamati, yaṃ vā panaññampi kiñci ajjhattaṃ paccattaṃ ākāsaṃ ākāsagataṃ, aghaṃ aghagataṃ, vivaraṃ vivaragataṃ, asamphuṭṭhaṃ, maṃsalohitehi upādinnaṃ—**the ear canals, nostrils, and mouth; and the space for swallowing what is eaten and drunk, the space where it stays, and the space for excreting it from the nether regions.*";
P_HTM[1830]="*ayaṃ vuccati, rāhula, ajjhattikā ākāsadhātu.**This is called the interior space element.*";
P_HTM[1831]="*Yā ceva kho pana ajjhattikā ākāsadhātu yā ca bāhirā ākāsadhātu ākāsadhāturevesā.**The interior space element and the exterior space element are just the space element.*";
P_HTM[1832]="*Taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**This should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[1833]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā ākāsadhātuyā cittaṃ nibbindati, ākāsadhātuyā cittaṃ virājeti.**When you truly see with right understanding, you reject the space element, detaching the mind from the space element.*";
P_HTM[1834]="*Pathavīsamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Rāhula, meditate like the earth.*";
P_HTM[1835]="*Pathavīsamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like the earth, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1836]="*Seyyathāpi, rāhula, pathaviyā sucimpi nikkhipanti, asucimpi nikkhipanti, gūthagatampi nikkhipanti, muttagatampi nikkhipanti, kheḷagatampi nikkhipanti, pubbagatampi nikkhipanti, lohitagatampi nikkhipanti, na ca tena pathavī aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;**Suppose they were to toss both clean and unclean things on the earth, like feces, urine, spit, pus, and blood. The earth isn’t horrified, repelled, and disgusted because of this.*";
P_HTM[1837]="*evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, pathavīsamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**In the same way, meditate like the earth.*";
P_HTM[1838]="*Pathavīsamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like the earth, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1839]="*Āposamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate like water.*";
P_HTM[1840]="*Āposamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like water, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1841]="*Seyyathāpi, rāhula, āpasmiṃ sucimpi dhovanti, asucimpi dhovanti, gūthagatampi dhovanti, muttagatampi dhovanti, kheḷagatampi dhovanti, pubbagatampi dhovanti, lohitagatampi dhovanti, na ca tena āpo aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;**Suppose they were to wash both clean and unclean things in the water, like feces, urine, spit, pus, and blood. The water isn’t horrified, repelled, and disgusted because of this.*";
P_HTM[1842]="*evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, āposamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**In the same way, meditate like water.*";
P_HTM[1843]="*Āposamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like water, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1844]="*Tejosamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate like fire.*";
P_HTM[1845]="*Tejosamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like fire, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1846]="*Seyyathāpi, rāhula, tejo sucimpi dahati, asucimpi dahati, gūthagatampi dahati, muttagatampi dahati, kheḷagatampi dahati, pubbagatampi dahati, lohitagatampi dahati, na ca tena tejo aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;**Suppose a fire were to burn both clean and unclean things, like feces, urine, spit, pus, and blood. The fire isn’t horrified, repelled, and disgusted because of this.*";
P_HTM[1847]="*evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, tejosamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**In the same way, meditate like fire.*";
P_HTM[1848]="*Tejosamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like fire, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1849]="*Vāyosamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate like wind.*";
P_HTM[1850]="*Vāyosamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like wind, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1851]="*Seyyathāpi, rāhula, vāyo sucimpi upavāyati, asucimpi upavāyati, gūthagatampi upavāyati, muttagatampi upavāyati, kheḷagatampi upavāyati, pubbagatampi upavāyati, lohitagatampi upavāyati, na ca tena vāyo aṭṭīyati vā harāyati vā jigucchati vā;**Suppose the wind were to blow on both clean and unclean things, like feces, urine, spit, pus, and blood. The wind isn’t horrified, repelled, and disgusted because of this.*";
P_HTM[1852]="*evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, vāyosamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**In the same way, meditate like the wind.*";
P_HTM[1853]="*Vāyosamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like wind, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1854]="*Ākāsasamaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate like space.*";
P_HTM[1855]="*Ākāsasamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like space, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1856]="*Seyyathāpi, rāhula, ākāso na katthaci patiṭṭhito;**Just as space is not established anywhere,*";
P_HTM[1857]="*evameva kho tvaṃ, rāhula, ākāsasamaṃ bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**in the same way, meditate like space.*";
P_HTM[1858]="*Ākāsasamañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato uppannā manāpāmanāpā phassā cittaṃ na pariyādāya ṭhassanti.**For when you meditate like space, pleasant and unpleasant contacts will not occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[1859]="*Mettaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate on love.*";
P_HTM[1860]="*Mettañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yo byāpādo so pahīyissati.**For when you meditate on love any ill will will be given up.*";
P_HTM[1861]="*Karuṇaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate on compassion.*";
P_HTM[1862]="*Karuṇañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yā vihesā sā pahīyissati.**For when you meditate on compassion any cruelty will be given up.*";
P_HTM[1863]="*Muditaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate on rejoicing.*";
P_HTM[1864]="*Muditañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yā arati sā pahīyissati.**For when you meditate on rejoicing any negativity will be given up.*";
P_HTM[1865]="*Upekkhaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate on equanimity.*";
P_HTM[1866]="*Upekkhañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yo paṭigho so pahīyissati.**For when you meditate on equanimity any repulsion will be given up.*";
P_HTM[1867]="*Asubhaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate on ugliness.*";
P_HTM[1868]="*Asubhañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yo rāgo so pahīyissati.**For when you meditate on ugliness any lust will be given up.*";
P_HTM[1869]="*Aniccasaññaṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Meditate on impermanence.*";
P_HTM[1870]="*Aniccasaññañhi te, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvayato yo asmimāno so pahīyissati.**For when you meditate on impermanence any conceit ‘I am’ will be given up.*";
P_HTM[1871]="*Ānāpānassatiṃ, rāhula, bhāvanaṃ bhāvehi.**Develop mindfulness of breathing.*";
P_HTM[1872]="*Ānāpānassati hi te, rāhula, bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā.**When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated it’s very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[1873]="*Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, rāhula, ānāpānassati, kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā?**And how is mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated to be very fruitful and beneficial?*";
P_HTM[1874]="*Idha, rāhula, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establishes mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[1875]="*So satova assasati satova passasati.**Just mindful, they breath in. Mindful, they breath out.*";
P_HTM[1876]="*Dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti;**When breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’*";
P_HTM[1877]="*rassaṃ vā assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā passasanto ‘rassaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti.**When breathing in lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing in lightly.’ When breathing out lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing out lightly.’*";
P_HTM[1878]="*‘Sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘sabbakāyappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in experiencing the whole body. They practice breathing out experiencing the whole body.*";
P_HTM[1879]="*‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice breathing in stilling the body’s motion. They practice breathing out stilling the body’s motion.*";
P_HTM[1880]="*‘Pītippaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘pītippaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in experiencing rapture. They practice breathing out experiencing rapture.*";
P_HTM[1881]="*‘sukhappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘sukhappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in experiencing bliss. They practice breathing out experiencing bliss.*";
P_HTM[1882]="*‘cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘cittasaṅkhārappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in experiencing these emotions. They practice breathing out experiencing these emotions.*";
P_HTM[1883]="*‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice breathing in stilling these emotions. They practice breathing out stilling these emotions.*";
P_HTM[1884]="*‘Cittappaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘cittappaṭisaṃvedī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in experiencing the mind. They practice breathing out experiencing the mind.*";
P_HTM[1885]="*‘abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in gladdening the mind. They practice breathing out gladdening the mind.*";
P_HTM[1886]="*‘samādahaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘samādahaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in immersing the mind. They practice breathing out immersing the mind.*";
P_HTM[1887]="*‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘vimocayaṃ cittaṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice breathing in freeing the mind. They practice breathing out freeing the mind.*";
P_HTM[1888]="*‘Aniccānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘aniccānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in observing impermanence. They practice breathing out observing impermanence.*";
P_HTM[1889]="*‘virāgānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘virāgānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in observing fading away. They practice breathing out observing fading away.*";
P_HTM[1890]="*‘nirodhānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘nirodhānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;**They practice breathing in observing cessation. They practice breathing out observing cessation.*";
P_HTM[1891]="*‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati; ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati.**They practice breathing in observing letting go. They practice breathing out observing letting go.*";
P_HTM[1892]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, rāhula, ānāpānassati, evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā.**Mindfulness of breathing, when developed and cultivated in this way, is very fruitful and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[1893]="*Evaṃ bhāvitāya, rāhula, ānāpānassatiyā, evaṃ bahulīkatāya yepi te carimakā assāsā tepi viditāva nirujjhanti no aviditā”ti.**When mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated in this way, even when the final breaths in and out cease, they are known, not unknown.”*";
P_HTM[1894]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[1895]="*Attamano āyasmā rāhulo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Rāhula was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[1896]="*Mahārāhulovādasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1897]="*63. Cūḷamālukyasutta**The Shorter Discourse With Māluṅkya*";
P_HTM[1898]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[1899]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[1900]="*Atha kho āyasmato mālukyaputtassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:**Then as Venerable Māluṅkya was in private retreat this thought came to his mind:*";
P_HTM[1901]="*“yānimāni diṭṭhigatāni bhagavatā abyākatāni ṭhapitāni paṭikkhittāni:**“There are several convictions that the Buddha has left undeclared; he has set them aside and refused to comment on them.*";
P_HTM[1902]="*‘sassato loko’tipi, ‘asassato loko’tipi, ‘antavā loko’tipi, ‘anantavā loko’tipi, ‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’tipi, ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’tipi, ‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’tipi, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’tipi, ‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’tipi, ‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’tipi—**For example: the world is eternal, or not eternal, or finite, or infinite; the soul and the body are the same thing, or they are different things; after death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist.*";
P_HTM[1903]="*tāni me bhagavā na byākaroti.**The Buddha does not give me a straight answer on these points.*";
P_HTM[1904]="*Yāni me bhagavā na byākaroti taṃ me na ruccati, taṃ me nakkhamati.**I don’t like that, and do not accept it.*";
P_HTM[1905]="*Sohaṃ bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ pucchissāmi.**I’ll go to him and ask him about this.*";
P_HTM[1906]="*Sace me bhagavā byākarissati:**If he gives me a straight answer on any of these points,*";
P_HTM[1907]="*‘sassato loko’ti vā ‘asassato loko’ti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1908]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā—* **";
P_HTM[1909]="*evāhaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi;**I will live the spiritual life under him.*";
P_HTM[1910]="*no ce me bhagavā byākarissati:**If he does not give me a straight answer on any of these points,*";
P_HTM[1911]="*‘sassato loko’ti vā ‘asassato loko’ti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1912]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā—* **";
P_HTM[1913]="*evāhaṃ sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī”ti.**I will reject the training and return to a lesser life.”*";
P_HTM[1914]="*Atha kho āyasmā mālukyaputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mālukyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, Māluṅkya came out of retreat and went to the Buddha. He bowed, sat down to one side, and told the Buddha of his thoughts. He then continued:*";
P_HTM[1915]="*“Idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi—* **";
P_HTM[1916]="*yānimāni diṭṭhigatāni bhagavatā abyākatāni ṭhapitāni paṭikkhittāni:* **";
P_HTM[1917]="*‘sassato loko’tipi, ‘asassato loko’tipi … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1918]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’tipi—* **";
P_HTM[1919]="*tāni me bhagavā na byākaroti.* **";
P_HTM[1920]="*Yāni me bhagavā na byākaroti taṃ me na ruccati, taṃ me nakkhamati.* **";
P_HTM[1921]="*Sohaṃ bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ pucchissāmi.* **";
P_HTM[1922]="*Sace me bhagavā byākarissati:* **";
P_HTM[1923]="*‘sassato loko’ti vā, ‘asassato loko’ti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1924]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā—* **";
P_HTM[1925]="*evāhaṃ bhagavati, brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi.* **";
P_HTM[1926]="*No ce me bhagavā byākarissati:* **";
P_HTM[1927]="*‘sassato loko’ti vā, ‘asassato loko’ti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1928]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā—* **";
P_HTM[1929]="*evāhaṃ sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmīti.* **";
P_HTM[1930]="*Sace bhagavā jānāti:**“If the Buddha knows*";
P_HTM[1931]="*‘sassato loko’ti, ‘sassato loko’ti me bhagavā byākarotu;**that the world is eternal, please tell me.*";
P_HTM[1932]="*sace bhagavā jānāti:**If you know*";
P_HTM[1933]="*‘asassato loko’ti, ‘asassato loko’ti me bhagavā byākarotu.**that the world is not eternal, tell me.*";
P_HTM[1934]="*No ce bhagavā jānāti:**If you don’t know*";
P_HTM[1935]="*‘sassato loko’ti vā, ‘asassato loko’ti vā, ajānato kho pana apassato etadeva ujukaṃ hoti yadidaṃ:**whether the world is eternal or not, then it is straightforward to simply say:*";
P_HTM[1936]="*‘na jānāmi, na passāmī’ti.**‘I neither know nor see.’*";
P_HTM[1937]="*Sace bhagavā jānāti:**If you know*";
P_HTM[1938]="*‘antavā loko’ti, ‘anantavā loko’ti me bhagavā byākarotu;**that the world is finite, or infinite; that the soul and the body are the same thing, or they are different things; that after death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist, please tell me.*";
P_HTM[1939]="*sace bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1940]="*‘anantavā loko’ti, ‘anantavā loko’ti me bhagavā byākarotu.* **";
P_HTM[1941]="*No ce bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1942]="*‘antavā loko’ti vā, ‘anantavā loko’ti vā, ajānato kho pana apassato etadeva ujukaṃ hoti yadidaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[1943]="*‘na jānāmi, na passāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[1944]="*Sace bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1945]="*‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti, ‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti me bhagavā byākarotu;* **";
P_HTM[1946]="*sace bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1947]="*‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti, ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti me bhagavā byākarotu.* **";
P_HTM[1948]="*No ce bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1949]="*‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā, ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā, ajānato kho pana apassato etadeva ujukaṃ hoti yadidaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[1950]="*‘na jānāmi, na passāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[1951]="*Sace bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1952]="*‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, ‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti me bhagavā byākarotu;* **";
P_HTM[1953]="*sace bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1954]="*‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti me bhagavā byākarotu.* **";
P_HTM[1955]="*No ce bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1956]="*‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ajānato kho pana apassato etadeva ujukaṃ hoti yadidaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[1957]="*‘na jānāmi na passāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[1958]="*Sace bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1959]="*‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, ‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti me bhagavā byākarotu;* **";
P_HTM[1960]="*sace bhagavā jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[1961]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, ‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti me bhagavā byākarotu.* **";
P_HTM[1962]="*No ce bhagavā jānāti:**If you don’t know*";
P_HTM[1963]="*‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ajānato kho pana apassato etadeva ujukaṃ hoti yadidaṃ:**any of these things, then it is straightforward to simply say:*";
P_HTM[1964]="*‘na jānāmi, na passāmī’”ti.**‘I neither know nor see.’”*";
P_HTM[1965]="*“Kiṃ nu tāhaṃ, mālukyaputta, evaṃ avacaṃ:**“What, Māluṅkyaputta, did I ever say to you:*";
P_HTM[1966]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, mayi brahmacariyaṃ cara, ahaṃ te byākarissāmi:**‘Come, Māluṅkyaputta, live the spiritual life under me, and I will declare these things to you’?”*";
P_HTM[1967]="*“sassato loko”ti vā, “asassato loko”ti vā, “antavā loko”ti vā, “anantavā loko”ti vā, “taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran”ti vā, “aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran”ti vā, “hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[1968]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1969]="*“Tvaṃ vā pana maṃ evaṃ avaca:**“Or did you ever say to me:*";
P_HTM[1970]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi, bhagavā me byākarissati:**‘Sir, I will live the spiritual life under the Buddha, and the Buddha will declare these things to me’?”*";
P_HTM[1971]="*“sassato loko”ti vā, “asassato loko”ti vā, “antavā loko”ti vā, “anantavā loko”ti vā, “taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran”ti vā, “aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran”ti vā, “hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā, “neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[1972]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[1973]="*“Iti kira, mālukyaputta, nevāhaṃ taṃ vadāmi:**“So it seems that I did not say to you:*";
P_HTM[1974]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, mayi brahmacariyaṃ cara, ahaṃ te byākarissāmi:**‘Come, Māluṅkyaputta, live the spiritual life under me, and I will declare these things to you.’*";
P_HTM[1975]="*“sassato loko”ti vā, “asassato loko”ti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1976]="*“neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā”’ti;* **";
P_HTM[1977]="*napi kira maṃ tvaṃ vadesi:**And you never said to me:*";
P_HTM[1978]="*‘ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi, bhagavā me byākarissati:**‘Sir, I will live the spiritual life under the Buddha, and the Buddha will declare these things to me.’*";
P_HTM[1979]="*“sassato loko”ti vā “asassato loko”ti vā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[1980]="*“neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[1981]="*Evaṃ sante, moghapurisa, ko santo kaṃ paccācikkhasi?**In that case, you silly man, are you really in a position to be abandoning anything?*";
P_HTM[1982]="*Yo kho, mālukyaputta, evaṃ vadeyya:**Suppose someone were to say this:*";
P_HTM[1983]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi yāva me bhagavā na byākarissati:**‘I will not live the spiritual life under the Buddha until the Buddha declares to me*";
P_HTM[1984]="*“sassato loko”ti vā, “asassato loko”ti vā … pe …**that the world is eternal, or that the world is not eternal …*";
P_HTM[1985]="*“neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā’ti,**or that after death a Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist.’*";
P_HTM[1986]="*abyākatameva taṃ, mālukyaputta, tathāgatena assa, atha so puggalo kālaṃ kareyya.**That would still remain undeclared by the Realized One, and meanwhile that person would die.*";
P_HTM[1987]="*Seyyathāpi, mālukyaputta, puriso sallena viddho assa savisena gāḷhapalepanena.**Suppose a man was struck by an arrow thickly smeared with poison.*";
P_HTM[1988]="*Tassa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā bhisakkaṃ sallakattaṃ upaṭṭhapeyyuṃ.**His friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would get a field surgeon to treat him.*";
P_HTM[1989]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**But the man would say:*";
P_HTM[1990]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ purisaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, khattiyo vā brāhmaṇo vā vesso vā suddo vā’ti;**‘I won’t pull out this arrow as long as I don’t know whether the man who wounded me was an aristocrat, a brahmin, a merchant, or a worker.’*";
P_HTM[1991]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:**He’d say:*";
P_HTM[1992]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ purisaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, evaṃnāmo evaṃgotto iti vā’ti;**‘I won’t pull out this arrow as long as I don’t know the following things about the man who wounded me: his name and clan;*";
P_HTM[1993]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[1994]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ purisaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, dīgho vā rasso vā majjhimo vā’ti;**whether he’s tall, short, or medium;*";
P_HTM[1995]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[1996]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ purisaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, kāḷo vā sāmo vā maṅguracchavī vā’ti;**whether his skin is black, brown, or tawny;*";
P_HTM[1997]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[1998]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ purisaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, amukasmiṃ gāme vā nigame vā nagare vā’ti;**and what village, town, or city he comes from.*";
P_HTM[1999]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[2000]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ dhanuṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, yadi vā cāpo yadi vā kodaṇḍo’ti;**I won’t pull out this arrow as long as I don’t know whether the bow that wounded me is made of wood or cane;*";
P_HTM[2001]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[2002]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ jiyaṃ jānāmi yāyamhi viddho, yadi vā akkassa yadi vā saṇhassa yadi vā nhārussa yadi vā maruvāya yadi vā khīrapaṇṇino’ti;**whether the bow-string is made of swallow-wort fibre, sunn hemp fibre, sinew, sanseveria fibre, or spurge fibre;*";
P_HTM[2003]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[2004]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ kaṇḍaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, yadi vā gacchaṃ yadi vā ropiman’ti;**whether the shaft is made from a bush or a plantation tree;*";
P_HTM[2005]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[2006]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ kaṇḍaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, yassa pattehi vājitaṃ yadi vā gijjhassa yadi vā kaṅkassa yadi vā kulalassa yadi vā morassa yadi vā sithilahanuno’ti;**whether the shaft was fitted with feathers from a vulture, a heron, a hawk, a peacock, or a stork;*";
P_HTM[2007]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[2008]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ kaṇḍaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, yassa nhārunā parikkhittaṃ yadi vā gavassa yadi vā mahiṃsassa yadi vā bheravassa yadi vā semhārassā’ti;**whether the shaft was bound with sinews of a cow, a buffalo, a swamp deer, or a gibbon;*";
P_HTM[2009]="*so evaṃ vadeyya:* **";
P_HTM[2010]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ imaṃ sallaṃ āharissāmi yāva na taṃ sallaṃ jānāmi yenamhi viddho, yadi vā sallaṃ yadi vā khurappaṃ yadi vā vekaṇḍaṃ yadi vā nārācaṃ yadi vā vacchadantaṃ yadi vā karavīrapattan’ti—**and whether the arrowhead was spiked, razor-tipped, barbed, made of iron or a calf’s tooth, or lancet-shaped.’*";
P_HTM[2011]="*aññātameva taṃ, mālukyaputta, tena purisena assa, atha so puriso kālaṃ kareyya.**That man would still not have learned these things, and meanwhile they’d die.*";
P_HTM[2012]="*Evameva kho, mālukyaputta, yo evaṃ vadeyya:**In the same way, suppose someone was to say:*";
P_HTM[2013]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi yāva me bhagavā na byākarissati:**‘I will not live the spiritual life under the Buddha until the Buddha declares to me*";
P_HTM[2014]="*“sassato loko”ti vā “asassato loko”ti vā … pe …**that the world is eternal, or that the world is not eternal …*";
P_HTM[2015]="*“neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti vā’ti—**or that after death a Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist.’*";
P_HTM[2016]="*abyākatameva taṃ, mālukyaputta, tathāgatena assa, atha so puggalo kālaṃ kareyya.**That would still remain undeclared by the Realized One, and meanwhile that person would die.*";
P_HTM[2017]="*‘Sassato loko’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evaṃ no.**It’s not true that if there were the view ‘the world is eternal’ there would be the living of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[2018]="*‘Asassato loko’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evampi no.**It’s not true that if there were the view ‘the world is not eternal’ there would be the living of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[2019]="*‘Sassato loko’ti vā, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati, ‘asassato loko’ti vā diṭṭhiyā sati attheva jāti, atthi jarā, atthi maraṇaṃ, santi sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā;**When there is the view that the world is eternal or that the world is not eternal, there is rebirth, there is old age, there is death, and there is sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[2020]="*yesāhaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme nighātaṃ paññapemi.**And it is the defeat of these things in this very life that I advocate.*";
P_HTM[2021]="*‘Antavā loko’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evaṃ no.**It’s not true that if there were the view ‘the world is finite’ …*";
P_HTM[2022]="*‘Anantavā loko’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evampi no.**‘the world is infinite’ …*";
P_HTM[2023]="*‘Antavā loko’ti vā, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati, ‘anantavā loko’ti vā diṭṭhiyā sati attheva jāti, atthi jarā, atthi maraṇaṃ, santi sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā;* **";
P_HTM[2024]="*yesāhaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme nighātaṃ paññapemi.* **";
P_HTM[2025]="*‘Taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evaṃ no.**‘the soul and the body are the same thing’ …*";
P_HTM[2026]="*‘Aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evampi no.**‘the soul and the body are different things’ …*";
P_HTM[2027]="*‘Taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati, ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā diṭṭhiyā sati attheva jāti … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2028]="*nighātaṃ paññapemi.* **";
P_HTM[2029]="*‘Hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evaṃ no.**‘a Realized One exists after death’ …*";
P_HTM[2030]="*‘Na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evampi no.**‘a Realized One doesn’t exist after death’ …*";
P_HTM[2031]="*‘Hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā diṭṭhiyā sati attheva jāti … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2032]="*yesāhaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme nighātaṃ paññapemi.* **";
P_HTM[2033]="*‘Hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evaṃ no.**‘a Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death’ …*";
P_HTM[2034]="*‘Neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati brahmacariyavāso abhavissāti, evampi no.**‘a Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death’ there would be the living of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[2035]="*‘Hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, mālukyaputta, diṭṭhiyā sati, ‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā diṭṭhiyā sati attheva jāti … pe …**When there are any of these views there is rebirth, there is old age, there is death, and there is sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[2036]="*yesāhaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme nighātaṃ paññapemi.**And it is the defeat of these things in this very life that I advocate.*";
P_HTM[2037]="*Tasmātiha, mālukyaputta, abyākatañca me abyākatato dhāretha;**So, Māluṅkyaputta, you should remember what I have not declared as undeclared,*";
P_HTM[2038]="*byākatañca me byākatato dhāretha.**and what I have declared as declared.*";
P_HTM[2039]="*Kiñca, mālukyaputta, mayā abyākataṃ?**And what have I not declared?*";
P_HTM[2040]="*‘Sassato loko’ti mālukyaputta, mayā abyākataṃ;**I have not declared the following: ‘the world is eternal,’*";
P_HTM[2041]="*‘asassato loko’ti—**‘the world is not eternal,’*";
P_HTM[2042]="*mayā abyākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2043]="*‘antavā loko’ti—**‘the world is finite,’*";
P_HTM[2044]="*mayā abyākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2045]="*‘anantavā loko’ti—**‘the world is infinite,’*";
P_HTM[2046]="*mayā abyākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2047]="*‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti—**‘the soul and the body are the same thing,’*";
P_HTM[2048]="*mayā abyākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2049]="*‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti—**‘the soul and the body are different things,’*";
P_HTM[2050]="*mayā abyākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2051]="*‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti—**‘a Realized One exists after death,’*";
P_HTM[2052]="*mayā abyākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2053]="*‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti—**‘a Realized One doesn’t exist after death,’*";
P_HTM[2054]="*mayā abyākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2055]="*‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti—**‘a Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death,’*";
P_HTM[2056]="*mayā abyākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2057]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti—**‘a Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death.’*";
P_HTM[2058]="*mayā abyākataṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2059]="*Kasmā cetaṃ, mālukyaputta, mayā abyākataṃ?**And why haven’t I declared these things?*";
P_HTM[2060]="*Na hetaṃ, mālukyaputta, atthasaṃhitaṃ na ādibrahmacariyakaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati.**Because they aren’t beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual life. They don’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[2061]="*Tasmā taṃ mayā abyākataṃ.**That’s why I haven’t declared them.*";
P_HTM[2062]="*Kiñca, mālukyaputta, mayā byākataṃ?**And what have I declared?*";
P_HTM[2063]="*‘Idaṃ dukkhan’ti, mālukyaputta, mayā byākataṃ;**I have declared the following: ‘this is suffering,’*";
P_HTM[2064]="*‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti—**‘this is the origin of suffering,’*";
P_HTM[2065]="*mayā byākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2066]="*‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti—**‘this is the cessation of suffering,’*";
P_HTM[2067]="*mayā byākataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2068]="*‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti—**‘this is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2069]="*mayā byākataṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2070]="*Kasmā cetaṃ, mālukyaputta, mayā byākataṃ?**And why have I declared these things?*";
P_HTM[2071]="*Etañhi, mālukyaputta, atthasaṃhitaṃ etaṃ ādibrahmacariyakaṃ nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati.**Because they are beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual life. They lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[2072]="*Tasmā taṃ mayā byākataṃ.**That’s why I have declared them.*";
P_HTM[2073]="*Tasmātiha, mālukyaputta, abyākatañca me abyākatato dhāretha;**So, Māluṅkyaputta, you should remember what I have not declared as undeclared,*";
P_HTM[2074]="*byākatañca me byākatato dhārethā”ti.**and what I have declared as declared.”*";
P_HTM[2075]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2076]="*Attamano āyasmā mālukyaputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Māluṅkyaputta was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2077]="*Cūḷamālukyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2078]="*64. Mahāmālukyasutta**The Longer Discourse With Māluṅkya*";
P_HTM[2079]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2080]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2081]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[2082]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2083]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2084]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2085]="*“dhāretha no tumhe, bhikkhave, mayā desitāni pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanānī”ti?**“Mendicants, do you remember the five lower fetters that I taught?”*";
P_HTM[2086]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā mālukyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Māluṅkyaputta said to him,*";
P_HTM[2087]="*“ahaṃ kho, bhante, dhāremi bhagavatā desitāni pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanānī”ti.**“Sir, I remember them.”*";
P_HTM[2088]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, dhāresi mayā desitāni pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanānī”ti?**“But how do you remember them?”*";
P_HTM[2089]="*“Sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ dhāremi;**“I remember the lower fetters taught by the Buddha as follows: identity view,*";
P_HTM[2090]="*vicikicchaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ dhāremi;**doubt,*";
P_HTM[2091]="*sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ dhāremi;**misapprehension of precepts and observances,*";
P_HTM[2092]="*kāmacchandaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ dhāremi;**sensual desire,*";
P_HTM[2093]="*byāpādaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ dhāremi.**and ill will.*";
P_HTM[2094]="*Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, dhāremi bhagavatā desitāni pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanānī”ti.**That’s how I remember the five lower fetters taught by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[2095]="*“Kassa kho nāma tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, imāni evaṃ pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni desitāni dhāresi?**“Who on earth do you remember being taught the five lower fetters in that way?*";
P_HTM[2096]="*Nanu, mālukyaputta, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā iminā taruṇūpamena upārambhena upārambhissanti?**Wouldn’t the wanderers who follow other paths fault you using the simile of the infant?*";
P_HTM[2097]="*Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa sakkāyotipi na hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati sakkāyadiṭṭhi?**For a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘identity’, so how could identity view possibly arise in them?*";
P_HTM[2098]="*Anusetvevassa sakkāyadiṭṭhānusayo.**Yet the underlying tendency to identity view still lies within them.*";
P_HTM[2099]="*Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa dhammātipi na hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati dhammesu vicikicchā?**A little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘teachings’, so how could doubt about the teachings possibly arise in them?*";
P_HTM[2100]="*Anusetvevassa vicikicchānusayo.**Yet the underlying tendency to doubt still lies within them.*";
P_HTM[2101]="*Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa sīlātipi na hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati sīlesu sīlabbataparāmāso?**A little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘precepts’, so how could misapprehension of precepts and observances possibly arise in them?*";
P_HTM[2102]="*Anusetvevassa sīlabbataparāmāsānusayo.**Yet the underlying tendency to misapprehension of precepts and observances still lies within them.*";
P_HTM[2103]="*Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa kāmātipi na hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati kāmesu kāmacchando?**A little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘sensual pleasures’, so how could desire for sensual pleasures possibly arise in them?*";
P_HTM[2104]="*Anusetvevassa kāmarāgānusayo.**Yet the underlying tendency to sensual desire still lies within them.*";
P_HTM[2105]="*Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa sattātipi na hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati sattesu byāpādo?**A little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘sentient beings’, so how could ill will for sentient beings possibly arise in them?*";
P_HTM[2106]="*Anusetvevassa byāpādānusayo.**Yet the underlying tendency to ill will still lies within them.*";
P_HTM[2107]="*Nanu, mālukyaputta, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā iminā taruṇūpamena upārambhena upārambhissantī”ti?**Wouldn’t the wanderers who follow other paths fault you using the simile of the infant?”*";
P_HTM[2108]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[2109]="*“etassa, bhagavā, kālo, etassa, sugata, kālo**“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One!*";
P_HTM[2110]="*yaṃ bhagavā pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni deseyya. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**May the Buddha teach the five lower fetters. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[2111]="*“Tena hānanda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[2112]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied.*";
P_HTM[2113]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2114]="*“Idhānanda, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto**“Ānanda, take an uneducated ordinary person who has not seen the noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the good persons.*";
P_HTM[2115]="*sakkāyadiṭṭhipariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati sakkāyadiṭṭhiparetena;**Their heart is overcome and mired in identity view,*";
P_HTM[2116]="*uppannāya ca sakkāyadiṭṭhiyā nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**and they don’t truly understand the escape from identity view that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2117]="*Tassa sā sakkāyadiṭṭhi thāmagatā appaṭivinītā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ.**That identity view is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower fetter.*";
P_HTM[2118]="*Vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati vicikicchāparetena;**Their heart is overcome and mired in doubt,*";
P_HTM[2119]="*uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**and they don’t truly understand the escape from doubt that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2120]="*Tassa sā vicikicchā thāmagatā appaṭivinītā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ.**That doubt is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower fetter.*";
P_HTM[2121]="*Sīlabbataparāmāsapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati sīlabbataparāmāsaparetena;**Their heart is overcome and mired in misapprehension of precepts and observances,*";
P_HTM[2122]="*uppannassa ca sīlabbataparāmāsassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**and they don’t truly understand the escape from misapprehension of precepts and observances that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2123]="*Tassa so sīlabbataparāmāso thāmagato appaṭivinīto orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ.**That misapprehension of precepts and observances is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower fetter.*";
P_HTM[2124]="*Kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati kāmarāgaparetena;**Their heart is overcome and mired in sensual desire,*";
P_HTM[2125]="*uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**and they don’t truly understand the escape from sensual desire that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2126]="*Tassa so kāmarāgo thāmagato appaṭivinīto orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ.**That sensual desire is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower fetter.*";
P_HTM[2127]="*Byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati byāpādaparetena;**Their heart is overcome and mired in ill will,*";
P_HTM[2128]="*uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**and they don’t truly understand the escape from ill will that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2129]="*Tassa so byāpādo thāmagato appaṭivinīto orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ.**That ill will is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower fetter.*";
P_HTM[2130]="*Sutavā ca kho, ānanda, ariyasāvako ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido sappurisadhamme suvinīto na sakkāyadiṭṭhipariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na sakkāyadiṭṭhiparetena;**But an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good persons, and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons. Their heart is not overcome and mired in identity view,*";
P_HTM[2131]="*uppannāya ca sakkāyadiṭṭhiyā nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**and they truly understand the escape from identity view that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2132]="*Tassa sā sakkāyadiṭṭhi sānusayā pahīyati.**That identity view, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up in them.*";
P_HTM[2133]="*Na vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na vicikicchāparetena;**Their heart is not overcome and mired in doubt,*";
P_HTM[2134]="*uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**and they truly understand the escape from doubt that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2135]="*Tassa sā vicikicchā sānusayā pahīyati.**That doubt, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up in them.*";
P_HTM[2136]="*Na sīlabbataparāmāsapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na sīlabbataparāmāsaparetena;**Their heart is not overcome and mired in misapprehension of precepts and observances,*";
P_HTM[2137]="*uppannassa ca sīlabbataparāmāsassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**and they truly understand the escape from misapprehension of precepts and observances that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2138]="*Tassa so sīlabbataparāmāso sānusayo pahīyati.**That misapprehension of precepts and observances, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up in them.*";
P_HTM[2139]="*Na kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na kāmarāgaparetena;**Their heart is not overcome and mired in sensual desire,*";
P_HTM[2140]="*uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**and they truly understand the escape from sensual desire that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2141]="*Tassa so kāmarāgo sānusayo pahīyati.**That sensual desire, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up in them.*";
P_HTM[2142]="*Na byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na byāpādaparetena;**Their heart is not overcome and mired in ill will,*";
P_HTM[2143]="*uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**and they truly understand the escape from ill will that has arisen.*";
P_HTM[2144]="*Tassa so byāpādo sānusayo pahīyati.**That ill will, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up in them.*";
P_HTM[2145]="*Yo, ānanda, maggo yā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya taṃ maggaṃ taṃ paṭipadaṃ anāgamma pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni ñassati vā dakkhati vā pajahissati vāti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**There is a path and a practice for giving up the five lower fetters. It’s not possible to know or see or give up the five lower fetters without relying on that path and that practice.*";
P_HTM[2146]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato tacaṃ acchetvā phegguṃ acchetvā sāracchedo bhavissatīti—**Suppose there was a large tree standing with heartwood. It’s not possible to cut out the heartwood without having cut through the bark and the softwood.*";
P_HTM[2147]="*netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati;* **";
P_HTM[2148]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yo maggo yā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya taṃ maggaṃ taṃ paṭipadaṃ anāgamma pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni ñassati vā dakkhati vā pajahissati vāti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**In the same way, there is a path and a practice for giving up the five lower fetters. It’s not possible to know or see or give up the five lower fetters without relying on that path and that practice.*";
P_HTM[2149]="*Yo ca kho, ānanda, maggo yā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya taṃ maggaṃ taṃ paṭipadaṃ āgamma pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni ñassati vā dakkhati vā pajahissati vāti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**There is a path and a practice for giving up the five lower fetters. It is possible to know and see and give up the five lower fetters by relying on that path and that practice.*";
P_HTM[2150]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato tacaṃ chetvā phegguṃ chetvā sāracchedo bhavissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**Suppose there was a large tree standing with heartwood. It is possible to cut out the heartwood after having cut through the bark and the softwood.*";
P_HTM[2151]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yo maggo yā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya taṃ maggaṃ taṃ paṭipadaṃ āgamma pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni ñassati vā dakkhati vā pajahissati vāti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**In the same way, there is a path and a practice for giving up the five lower fetters. It is possible to know and see and give up the five lower fetters by relying on that path and that practice.*";
P_HTM[2152]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, gaṅgā nadī pūrā udakassa samatittikā kākapeyyā.**Suppose the river Ganges was full to the brim so a crow could drink from it.*";
P_HTM[2153]="*Atha dubbalako puriso āgaccheyya:**Then along comes a feeble person, who thinks:*";
P_HTM[2154]="*‘ahaṃ imissā gaṅgāya nadiyā tiriyaṃ bāhāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gacchissāmī’ti;**‘By swimming with my arms I’ll safely cross over to the far shore of the Ganges.’*";
P_HTM[2155]="*so na sakkuṇeyya gaṅgāya nadiyā tiriyaṃ bāhāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gantuṃ.**But they’re not able to do so.*";
P_HTM[2156]="*Evameva kho, ānanda, yesaṃ kesañci sakkāyanirodhāya dhamme desiyamāne cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati;**In the same way, when the Dhamma is being taught for the cessation of identity view, someone whose mind isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided*";
P_HTM[2157]="*seyyathāpi so dubbalako puriso evamete daṭṭhabbā.**should be regarded as being like that feeble person.*";
P_HTM[2158]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, gaṅgā nadī pūrā udakassa samatittikā kākapeyyā.**Suppose the river Ganges was full to the brim so a crow could drink from it.*";
P_HTM[2159]="*Atha balavā puriso āgaccheyya:**Then along comes a strong person, who thinks:*";
P_HTM[2160]="*‘ahaṃ imissā gaṅgāya nadiyā tiriyaṃ bāhāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gacchissāmī’ti;**‘By swimming with my arms I’ll safely cross over to the far shore of the Ganges.’*";
P_HTM[2161]="*so sakkuṇeyya gaṅgāya nadiyā tiriyaṃ bāhāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ gantuṃ.**And they are able to do so.*";
P_HTM[2162]="*Evameva kho, ānanda, yesaṃ kesañci sakkāyanirodhāya dhamme desiyamāne cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati;**In the same way, when the Dhamma is being taught for the cessation of identity view, someone whose mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided*";
P_HTM[2163]="*seyyathāpi so balavā puriso evamete daṭṭhabbā.**should be regarded as being like that strong person.*";
P_HTM[2164]="*Katamo cānanda, maggo, katamā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya?**And what, Ānanda, is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters?*";
P_HTM[2165]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhu upadhivivekā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānā sabbaso kāyaduṭṭhullānaṃ paṭippassaddhiyā vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant—due to the seclusion from attachments, the giving up of unskillful qualities, and the complete settling of physical discomfort—quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[2166]="*So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati.**They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as not-self.*";
P_HTM[2167]="*So tehi dhammehi cittaṃ paṭivāpeti.**They turn their mind away from those things,*";
P_HTM[2168]="*So tehi dhammehi cittaṃ paṭivāpetvā amatāya dhātuyā cittaṃ upasaṃharati:**and apply it to the deathless element:*";
P_HTM[2169]="*‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānan’ti.**‘This is peaceful; this is sublime—that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, cessation, extinguishment.’*";
P_HTM[2170]="*So tattha ṭhito āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti;**Abiding in that they attain the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2171]="*no ce āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti teneva dhammarāgena tāya dhammanandiyā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti, tattha parinibbāyī, anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, with the ending of the five lower fetters they’re reborn spontaneously, because of their passion and love for that meditation. They are extinguished there, and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[2172]="*Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya.**This is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters.*";
P_HTM[2173]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe …**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[2174]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[2175]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[2176]="*So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ …**They contemplate the phenomena there as impermanent …*";
P_HTM[2177]="*pe …**They turn their mind away from those things …*";
P_HTM[2178]="*anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, they’re reborn spontaneously … and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[2179]="*Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya.**This too is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters.*";
P_HTM[2180]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[2181]="*So yadeva tattha hoti vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ …**They contemplate the phenomena there as impermanent …*";
P_HTM[2182]="*pe …**They turn their mind away from those things …*";
P_HTM[2183]="*anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, they’re reborn spontaneously … and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[2184]="*Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya.**This too is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters.*";
P_HTM[2185]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[2186]="*So yadeva tattha hoti vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ …**They contemplate the phenomena there as impermanent …*";
P_HTM[2187]="*pe …**They turn their mind away from those things …*";
P_HTM[2188]="*anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, they’re reborn spontaneously … and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[2189]="*Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya.**This too is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters.*";
P_HTM[2190]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[2191]="*So yadeva tattha hoti vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ …**They contemplate the phenomena there as impermanent …*";
P_HTM[2192]="*pe …**They turn their mind away from those things …*";
P_HTM[2193]="*anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, they’re reborn spontaneously … and are not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[2194]="*Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāyā”ti.**This too is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters.”*";
P_HTM[2195]="*“Eso ce, bhante, maggo esā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya, atha kiñcarahi idhekacce bhikkhū cetovimuttino ekacce bhikkhū paññāvimuttino”ti?**“Sir, if this is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters, how come some mendicants here are released in heart while others are released by wisdom?”*";
P_HTM[2196]="*“Ettha kho panesāhaṃ, ānanda, indriyavemattataṃ vadāmī”ti.**“In that case, I say it is the diversity of their faculties.”*";
P_HTM[2197]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2198]="*Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2199]="*Mahāmālukyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2200]="*65. Bhaddālisutta**With Bhaddāli*";
P_HTM[2201]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2202]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2203]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[2204]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2205]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2206]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2207]="*“Ahaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ekāsanabhojanaṃ bhuñjāmi;**“Mendicants, I eat my food in one sitting per day.*";
P_HTM[2208]="*ekāsanabhojanaṃ kho, ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhuñjamāno appābādhatañca sañjānāmi appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.**Doing so, I find that I’m healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[2209]="*Etha, tumhepi, bhikkhave, ekāsanabhojanaṃ bhuñjatha;**You too should eat your food in one sitting per day.*";
P_HTM[2210]="*ekāsanabhojanaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tumhepi bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānissatha appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañcā”ti.**Doing so, you’ll find that you’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.”*";
P_HTM[2211]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā bhaddāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Bhaddāli said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[2212]="*“ahaṃ kho, bhante, na ussahāmi ekāsanabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ;**“Sir, I’m not going to try to eat my food in one sitting per day.*";
P_HTM[2213]="*ekāsanabhojanañhi me, bhante, bhuñjato siyā kukkuccaṃ, siyā vippaṭisāro”ti.**For when eating once a day I might feel remorse and regret.”*";
P_HTM[2214]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, bhaddāli, yattha nimantito assasi tattha ekadesaṃ bhuñjitvā ekadesaṃ nīharitvāpi bhuñjeyyāsi.**“Well then, Bhaddāli, eat one part of the meal in the place where you’re invited, and bring the rest back to eat.*";
P_HTM[2215]="*Evampi kho tvaṃ, bhaddāli, bhuñjamāno ekāsano yāpessasī”ti.**Eating this way, too, you will sustain yourself.”*";
P_HTM[2216]="*“Evampi kho ahaṃ, bhante, na ussahāmi bhuñjituṃ;**“Sir, I’m not going to try to eat that way, either.*";
P_HTM[2217]="*evampi hi me, bhante, bhuñjato siyā kukkuccaṃ, siyā vippaṭisāro”ti.**For when eating that way I might also feel remorse and regret.”*";
P_HTM[2218]="*Atha kho āyasmā bhaddāli bhagavatā sikkhāpade paññāpiyamāne bhikkhusaṃghe sikkhaṃ samādiyamāne anussāhaṃ pavedesi.**Then, as this rule was being laid down by the Buddha and the Saṅgha was undertaking it, Bhaddāli announced he would not try to keep it.*";
P_HTM[2219]="*Atha kho āyasmā bhaddāli sabbaṃ taṃ temāsaṃ na bhagavato sammukhībhāvaṃ adāsi, yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī.**Then for the whole of that three months Bhaddāli did not present himself in the presence of the Buddha, as happens when someone doesn’t fulfill the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2220]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karonti—**At that time several mendicants were making a robe for the Buddha, thinking that*";
P_HTM[2221]="*niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissatīti.**when his robe was finished and the three months of the rains residence had passed the Buddha would set out wandering.*";
P_HTM[2222]="*Atha kho āyasmā bhaddāli yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Bhaddāli went up to those mendicants, and exchanged greetings with them.*";
P_HTM[2223]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ bhaddāliṃ te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. The mendicants said to Bhaddāli,*";
P_HTM[2224]="*“idaṃ kho, āvuso bhaddāli, bhagavato cīvarakammaṃ karīyati.**“Reverend Bhaddāli, this robe is being made for the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2225]="*Niṭṭhitacīvaro bhagavā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamissati.**When it’s finished and the three months of the rains residence have passed the Buddha will set out wandering.*";
P_HTM[2226]="*Iṅghāvuso bhaddāli, etaṃ dosakaṃ sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, mā te pacchā dukkarataraṃ ahosī”ti.**Come on, Bhaddāli, learn your lesson. Don’t make it hard for yourself later on.”*";
P_HTM[2227]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā bhaddāli tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā bhaddāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, reverends,” Bhaddāli replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[2228]="*“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yohaṃ bhagavatā sikkhāpade paññāpiyamāne bhikkhusaṃghe sikkhaṃ samādiyamāne anussāhaṃ pavedesiṃ.**“I have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of me that, as this rule was being laid down by the Buddha and the Saṅgha was undertaking it, I announced I would not try to keep it.*";
P_HTM[2229]="*Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti.**Please, sir, accept my mistake for what it is, so I will restrain myself in future.”*";
P_HTM[2230]="*“Taggha tvaṃ, bhaddāli, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ mayā sikkhāpade paññāpiyamāne bhikkhusaṅghe sikkhaṃ samādiyamāne anussāhaṃ pavedesi.**“Indeed, Bhaddāli, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of you that, as this rule was being laid down by the Buddha and the Saṅgha was undertaking it, you announced you would not try to keep it.*";
P_HTM[2231]="*Samayopi kho te, bhaddāli, appaṭividdho ahosi:**And you didn’t realize this situation:*";
P_HTM[2232]="*‘bhagavā kho sāvatthiyaṃ viharati, bhagavāpi maṃ jānissati—**‘The Buddha is staying in Sāvatthī, and he’ll know me*";
P_HTM[2233]="*bhaddāli nāma bhikkhu satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī’ti.**as the mendicant named Bhaddāli who doesn’t fulfill the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.’*";
P_HTM[2234]="*Ayampi kho te, bhaddāli, samayo appaṭividdho ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[2235]="*Samayopi kho te, bhaddāli, appaṭividdho ahosi:**And you didn’t realize this situation:*";
P_HTM[2236]="*‘sambahulā kho bhikkhū sāvatthiyaṃ vassaṃ upagatā, tepi maṃ jānissanti—**‘Several monks have commenced the rains retreat in Sāvatthī …*";
P_HTM[2237]="*bhaddāli nāma bhikkhu satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2238]="*Ayampi kho te, bhaddāli, samayo appaṭividdho ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[2239]="*Samayopi kho te, bhaddāli, appaṭividdho ahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2240]="*‘sambahulā kho bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiyaṃ vassaṃ upagatā, tāpi maṃ jānissanti—**several nuns have commenced the rains retreat in Sāvatthī …*";
P_HTM[2241]="*bhaddāli nāma bhikkhu satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2242]="*Ayampi kho te, bhaddāli, samayo appaṭividdho ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[2243]="*Samayopi kho te, bhaddāli, appaṭividdho ahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2244]="*‘sambahulā kho upāsakā sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasanti, tepi maṃ jānissanti—**several laymen reside in Sāvatthī …*";
P_HTM[2245]="*bhaddāli nāma bhikkhu satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2246]="*Ayampi kho te, bhaddāli, samayo appaṭividdho ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[2247]="*Samayopi kho te, bhaddāli, appaṭividdho ahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2248]="*‘sambahulā kho upāsikā sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasanti, tāpi maṃ jānissanti—**several laywomen reside in Sāvatthī, and they’ll know me*";
P_HTM[2249]="*bhaddāli nāma bhikkhu satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī’ti.**as the mendicant named Bhaddāli who doesn’t fulfill the training according to the Teacher’s instructions. …*";
P_HTM[2250]="*Ayampi kho te, bhaddāli, samayo appaṭividdho ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[2251]="*Samayopi kho te, bhaddāli, appaṭividdho ahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2252]="*‘sambahulā kho nānātitthiyā samaṇabrāhmaṇā sāvatthiyaṃ vassaṃ upagatā, tepi maṃ jānissanti—**Several ascetics and brahmins who follow various other paths have commenced the rains retreat in Sāvatthī, and they’ll know me*";
P_HTM[2253]="*bhaddāli nāma bhikkhu samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako theraññataro bhikkhu sāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī’ti.**as the mendicant named Bhaddāli, one of the senior disciples of Gotama, who doesn’t fulfill the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.’*";
P_HTM[2254]="*Ayampi kho te, bhaddāli, samayo appaṭividdho ahosī”ti.**You also didn’t realize this situation.”*";
P_HTM[2255]="*“Accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yohaṃ bhagavatā sikkhāpade paññāpiyamāne bhikkhusaṅghe sikkhaṃ samādiyamāne anussāhaṃ pavedesiṃ.**“I made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of me that, as this rule was being laid down by the Buddha and the Saṅgha was undertaking it, I announced I would not try to keep it.*";
P_HTM[2256]="*Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti.**Please, sir, accept my mistake for what it is, so I will restrain myself in future.”*";
P_HTM[2257]="*“Taggha tvaṃ, bhaddāli, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ mayā sikkhāpade paññāpiyamāne bhikkhusaṅghe sikkhaṃ samādiyamāne anussāhaṃ pavedesi.**“Indeed, Bhaddāli, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of you that, as this rule was being laid down by the Buddha and the Saṅgha was undertaking it, you announced you would not try to keep it.*";
P_HTM[2258]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhaddāli,**What do you think, Bhaddāli?*";
P_HTM[2259]="*idhassa bhikkhu ubhatobhāgavimutto, tamahaṃ evaṃ vadeyyaṃ:**Suppose I was to say this to a mendicant who is freed both ways:*";
P_HTM[2260]="*‘ehi me tvaṃ, bhikkhu, paṅke saṅkamo hohī’ti, api nu kho so saṅkameyya vā aññena vā kāyaṃ sannāmeyya, ‘no’ti vā vadeyyā”ti?**‘Please, mendicant, be a bridge for me to cross over the mud.’ Would they cross over themselves, or struggle to get out of it, or just say no?”*";
P_HTM[2261]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2262]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhaddāli,**“What do you think, Bhaddāli?*";
P_HTM[2263]="*idhassa bhikkhu paññāvimutto …**Suppose I was to say the same thing to a mendicant who is freed by wisdom,*";
P_HTM[2264]="*kāyasakkhi …**or a personal witness,*";
P_HTM[2265]="*diṭṭhippatto …**or attained to view,*";
P_HTM[2266]="*saddhāvimutto …**or freed by faith,*";
P_HTM[2267]="*dhammānusārī …**or a follower of the teachings,*";
P_HTM[2268]="*saddhānusārī, tamahaṃ evaṃ vadeyyaṃ:**or a follower by faith:*";
P_HTM[2269]="*‘ehi me tvaṃ, bhikkhu, paṅke saṅkamo hohī’ti, api nu kho so saṅkameyya vā aññena vā kāyaṃ sannāmeyya, ‘no’ti vā vadeyyā”ti?**‘Please, mendicant, be a bridge for me to cross over the mud.’ Would they cross over themselves, or struggle to get out of it, or just say no?”*";
P_HTM[2270]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2271]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhaddāli,**“What do you think, Bhaddāli?*";
P_HTM[2272]="*api nu tvaṃ, bhaddāli, tasmiṃ samaye ubhatobhāgavimutto vā hosi paññāvimutto vā kāyasakkhi vā diṭṭhippatto vā saddhāvimutto vā dhammānusārī vā saddhānusārī vā”ti?**At that time were you freed both ways, freed by wisdom, a personal witness, attained to view, freed by faith, a follower of the teachings, or a follower by faith?”*";
P_HTM[2273]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2274]="*“Nanu tvaṃ, bhaddāli, tasmiṃ samaye ritto tuccho aparaddho”ti?**“Weren’t you void, hollow, and mistaken?”*";
P_HTM[2275]="*“Evaṃ, bhante.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2276]="*Accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yohaṃ bhagavatā sikkhāpade paññāpiyamāne bhikkhusaṅghe sikkhaṃ samādiyamāne anussāhaṃ pavedesiṃ.**“I made a mistake, sir. …*";
P_HTM[2277]="*Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti.**Please, sir, accept my mistake for what it is, so I will restrain myself in future.”*";
P_HTM[2278]="*“Taggha tvaṃ, bhaddāli, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ mayā sikkhāpade paññāpiyamāne bhikkhusaṅghe sikkhaṃ samādiyamāne anussāhaṃ pavedesi.**“Indeed, Bhaddāli, you made a mistake. …*";
P_HTM[2279]="*Yato ca kho tvaṃ, bhaddāli, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma.**But since you have recognized your mistake for what it is, and have dealt with it properly, I accept it.*";
P_HTM[2280]="*Vuddhihesā, bhaddāli, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti, āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**For it is growth in the training of the noble one to recognize a mistake for what it is, deal with it properly, and commit to restraint in the future.*";
P_HTM[2281]="*Idha, bhaddāli, ekacco bhikkhu satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī hoti.**Bhaddāli, take a mendicant who doesn’t fulfill the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2282]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think,*";
P_HTM[2283]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajeyyaṃ araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**‘Why don’t I frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[2284]="*Appeva nāmāhaṃ uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ sacchikareyyan’ti.**Hopefully I’ll realize a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.’*";
P_HTM[2285]="*So vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**So they frequent a secluded lodging.*";
P_HTM[2286]="*Tassa tathāvūpakaṭṭhassa viharato satthāpi upavadati, anuviccapi viññū sabrahmacārī upavadanti, devatāpi upavadanti, attāpi attānaṃ upavadati.**While they’re living withdrawn, they’re reprimanded by the Teacher, by sensible spiritual companions after examination, by deities, and by themselves.*";
P_HTM[2287]="*So satthārāpi upavadito, anuviccapi viññūhi sabrahmacārīhi upavadito, devatāhipi upavadito, attanāpi attānaṃ upavadito na uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ sacchikaroti.**Being reprimanded in this way, they don’t realize any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[2288]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2289]="*Evañhi taṃ, bhaddāli, hoti yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārissa.**Because that’s how it is when someone doesn’t fulfill the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2290]="*Idha pana, bhaddāli, ekacco bhikkhu satthusāsane sikkhāya paripūrakārī hoti.**But take a mendicant who does fulfill the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2291]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think,*";
P_HTM[2292]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajeyyaṃ araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**‘Why don’t I frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[2293]="*Appeva nāmāhaṃ uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ sacchikareyyan’ti.**Hopefully I’ll realize a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.’*";
P_HTM[2294]="*So vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**They frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[2295]="*Tassa tathāvūpakaṭṭhassa viharato satthāpi na upavadati, anuviccapi viññū sabrahmacārī na upavadanti, devatāpi na upavadanti, attāpi attānaṃ na upavadati.**While they’re living withdrawn, they’re not reprimanded by the Teacher, by sensible spiritual companions after examination, by deities, or by themselves.*";
P_HTM[2296]="*So satthārāpi anupavadito, anuviccapi viññūhi sabrahmacārīhi anupavadito, devatāhipi anupavadito, attanāpi attānaṃ anupavadito uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ sacchikaroti.**Not being reprimanded in this way, they realize a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[2297]="*So vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[2298]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2299]="*Evañhi taṃ, bhaddāli, hoti yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya paripūrakārissa.**Because that’s what happens when someone fulfills the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2300]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhaddāli, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[2301]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2302]="*Evañhi taṃ, bhaddāli, hoti yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya paripūrakārissa.**Because that’s what happens when someone fulfills the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2303]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhaddāli, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati, sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[2304]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2305]="*Evañhi taṃ, bhaddāli, hoti yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya paripūrakārissa.**Because that’s what happens when someone fulfills the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2306]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhaddāli, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[2307]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2308]="*Evañhi taṃ, bhaddāli, hoti yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya paripūrakārissa.**Because that’s what happens when someone fulfills the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2309]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[2310]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect many kinds of past lives, that is, one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. … They recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[2311]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2312]="*Evañhi taṃ, bhaddāli, hoti yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya paripūrakārissa.**Because that’s what happens when someone fulfills the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2313]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[2314]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti: ‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā … pe … vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā; ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā … pe … sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds: ‘These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. … They’re reborn in the underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. … they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman … they understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[2315]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2316]="*Evañhi taṃ, bhaddāli, hoti yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya paripūrakārissa.**Because that’s what happens when someone fulfills the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.*";
P_HTM[2317]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2318]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti;**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[2319]="*‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[2320]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati.**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[2321]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[2322]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[2323]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2324]="*Evañhi taṃ, bhaddāli, hoti yathā taṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya paripūrakārissā”ti.**Because that’s what happens when someone fulfills the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.”*";
P_HTM[2325]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā bhaddāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Bhaddāli said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[2326]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena midhekaccaṃ bhikkhuṃ pasayha pasayha kāraṇaṃ karonti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why they punish some monk, repeatedly pressuring him?*";
P_HTM[2327]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena midhekaccaṃ bhikkhuṃ no tathā pasayha pasayha kāraṇaṃ karontī”ti?**And what is the cause, what is the reason why they don’t similarly punish another monk, repeatedly pressuring him?”*";
P_HTM[2328]="*“Idha, bhaddāli, ekacco bhikkhu abhiṇhāpattiko hoti āpattibahulo.**“Take a monk who is a frequent offender with many offenses.*";
P_HTM[2329]="*So bhikkhūhi vuccamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, na sammā vattati, na lomaṃ pāteti, na netthāraṃ vattati, ‘yena saṃgho attamano hoti taṃ karomī’ti nāha.**When admonished by the monks, he dodges the issue, distracting the discussion with irrelevant points. He displays annoyance, hate, and bitterness. He doesn’t proceed properly, he doesn’t fall in line, he doesn’t proceed to get past it, and he doesn’t say: ‘I’ll do what pleases the Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[2330]="*Tatra, bhaddāli, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti:**In such a case, the monks say:*";
P_HTM[2331]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu abhiṇhāpattiko āpattibahulo.**‘Reverends, this monk is a frequent offender, with many offenses.*";
P_HTM[2332]="*So bhikkhūhi vuccamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, na sammā vattati, na lomaṃ pāteti, na netthāraṃ vattati, “yena saṃgho attamano hoti taṃ karomī”ti nāha.**When admonished by the monks, he dodges the issue, distracting the discussion with irrelevant points. He displays annoyance, hate, and bitterness. He doesn’t proceed properly, he doesn’t fall in line, he doesn’t proceed to get past it, and he doesn’t say: “I’ll do what pleases the Saṅgha.”*";
P_HTM[2333]="*Sādhu vatāyasmanto imassa bhikkhuno tathā tathā upaparikkhatha yathāssidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ na khippameva vūpasameyyā’ti.**It’d be good for the venerables to examine this monk in such a way that this disciplinary issue is not quickly settled.’*";
P_HTM[2334]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhaddāli, bhikkhuno bhikkhū tathā tathā upaparikkhanti yathāssidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ na khippameva vūpasammati.**And that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[2335]="*Idha pana, bhaddāli, ekacco bhikkhu abhiṇhāpattiko hoti āpattibahulo.**Take some other monk who is a frequent offender with many offenses.*";
P_HTM[2336]="*So bhikkhūhi vuccamāno nāññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ na apanāmeti, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, ‘yena saṅgho attamano hoti taṃ karomī’ti āha.**When admonished by the monks, he doesn’t dodge the issue, distracting the discussion with irrelevant points. He doesn’t display annoyance, hate, and bitterness. He proceeds properly, he falls in line, he proceeds to get past it, and he says: ‘I’ll do what pleases the Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[2337]="*Tatra, bhaddāli, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti:**In such a case, the monks say:*";
P_HTM[2338]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu abhiṇhāpattiko āpattibahulo.**‘Reverends, this monk is a frequent offender, with many offenses.*";
P_HTM[2339]="*So bhikkhūhi vuccamāno nāññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ na apanāmeti, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, “yena saṅgho attamano hoti taṃ karomī”ti āha.**When admonished by the monks, he doesn’t dodge the issue, distracting the discussion with irrelevant points. He doesn’t display annoyance, hate, and bitterness. He proceeds properly, he falls in line, he proceeds to get past it, and he says: ‘I’ll do what pleases the Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[2340]="*Sādhu vatāyasmanto, imassa bhikkhuno tathā tathā upaparikkhatha yathāssidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ khippameva vūpasameyyā’ti.**It’d be good for the venerables to examine this monk in such a way that this disciplinary issue is quickly settled.’*";
P_HTM[2341]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhaddāli, bhikkhuno bhikkhū tathā tathā upaparikkhanti yathāssidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ khippameva vūpasammati.**And that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[2342]="*Idha, bhaddāli, ekacco bhikkhu adhiccāpattiko hoti anāpattibahulo.**Take some other monk who is an occasional offender without many offenses.*";
P_HTM[2343]="*So bhikkhūhi vuccamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, na sammā vattati, na lomaṃ pāteti, na netthāraṃ vattati, ‘yena saṅgho attamano hoti taṃ karomī’ti nāha.**When admonished by the monks, he dodges the issue …*";
P_HTM[2344]="*Tatra, bhaddāli, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti:**In such a case, the monks say:*";
P_HTM[2345]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu adhiccāpattiko anāpattibahulo.**‘Reverends, this monk is an occasional offender without many offenses.*";
P_HTM[2346]="*So bhikkhūhi vuccamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, na sammā vattati, na lomaṃ pāteti, na netthāraṃ vattati, “yena saṅgho attamano hoti taṃ karomī”ti nāha.**When admonished by the monks, he dodges the issue …*";
P_HTM[2347]="*Sādhu vatāyasmanto, imassa bhikkhuno tathā tathā upaparikkhatha yathāssidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ na khippameva vūpasameyyā’ti.**It’d be good for the venerables to examine this monk in such a way that this disciplinary issue is not quickly settled.’*";
P_HTM[2348]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhaddāli, bhikkhuno bhikkhū tathā tathā upaparikkhanti yathāssidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ na khippameva vūpasammati.**And that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[2349]="*Idha pana, bhaddāli, ekacco bhikkhu adhiccāpattiko hoti anāpattibahulo.**Take some other monk who is an occasional offender without many offenses.*";
P_HTM[2350]="*So bhikkhūhi vuccamāno nāññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, na bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, ‘yena saṅgho attamano hoti taṃ karomī’ti āha.**When admonished by the monks, he doesn’t dodge the issue …*";
P_HTM[2351]="*Tatra, bhaddāli, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti:**In such a case, the monks say:*";
P_HTM[2352]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu adhiccāpattiko anāpattibahulo.**‘Reverends, this monk is an occasional offender without many offenses.*";
P_HTM[2353]="*So bhikkhūhi vuccamāno nāññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, na bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, sammā vattati, lomaṃ pāteti, netthāraṃ vattati, “yena saṅgho attamano hoti taṃ karomī”ti āha.**When admonished by the monks, he doesn’t dodge the issue …*";
P_HTM[2354]="*Sādhu vatāyasmanto, imassa bhikkhuno tathā tathā upaparikkhatha yathāssidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ khippameva vūpasameyyā’ti.**It’d be good for the venerables to examine this monk in such a way that this disciplinary issue is quickly settled.’*";
P_HTM[2355]="*Tassa kho evaṃ, bhaddāli, bhikkhuno bhikkhū tathā tathā upaparikkhanti yathāssidaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ khippameva vūpasammati.**And that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[2356]="*Idha, bhaddāli, ekacco bhikkhu saddhāmattakena vahati pemamattakena.**Take some other monk who gets by with mere faith and love.*";
P_HTM[2357]="*Tatra, bhaddāli, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti:**In such a case, the monks say:*";
P_HTM[2358]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu saddhāmattakena vahati pemamattakena.**‘Reverends, this monk gets by with mere faith and love.*";
P_HTM[2359]="*Sace mayaṃ imaṃ bhikkhuṃ pasayha pasayha kāraṇaṃ karissāma—**If we punish him, repeatedly pressuring him—*";
P_HTM[2360]="*mā yampissa taṃ saddhāmattakaṃ pemamattakaṃ tamhāpi parihāyī’ti.**no, let him not lose what little faith and love he has!’*";
P_HTM[2361]="*Seyyathāpi, bhaddāli, purisassa ekaṃ cakkhuṃ, tassa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā taṃ ekaṃ cakkhuṃ rakkheyyuṃ:**Suppose there was a person with one eye. Their friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would protect that one eye:*";
P_HTM[2362]="*‘mā yampissa taṃ ekaṃ cakkhuṃ tamhāpi parihāyī’ti;**‘Let them not lose the one eye that they have!’*";
P_HTM[2363]="*evameva kho, bhaddāli, idhekacco bhikkhu saddhāmattakena vahati pemamattakena.**In the same way, some monk gets by with mere faith and love.*";
P_HTM[2364]="*Tatra, bhaddāli, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti:**In such a case, the monks say:*";
P_HTM[2365]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu saddhāmattakena vahati pemamattakena.**‘Reverends, this monk gets by with mere faith and love.*";
P_HTM[2366]="*Sace mayaṃ imaṃ bhikkhuṃ pasayha pasayha kāraṇaṃ karissāma—**If we punish him, repeatedly pressuring him—*";
P_HTM[2367]="*mā yampissa taṃ saddhāmattakaṃ pemamattakaṃ tamhāpi parihāyī’ti.**no, let him not lose what little faith and love he has!’*";
P_HTM[2368]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhaddāli, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena midhekaccaṃ bhikkhuṃ pasayha pasayha kāraṇaṃ karonti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why they punish some monk, repeatedly pressuring him.*";
P_HTM[2369]="*Ayaṃ pana, bhaddāli, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekaccaṃ bhikkhuṃ no tathā pasayha pasayha kāraṇaṃ karontī”ti.**And this is the cause, this is the reason why they don’t similarly punish another monk, repeatedly pressuring him.”*";
P_HTM[2370]="*“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena pubbe appatarāni ceva sikkhāpadāni ahesuṃ bahutarā ca bhikkhū aññāya saṇṭhahiṃsu?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why there used to be fewer training rules but more enlightened mendicants?*";
P_HTM[2371]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena etarahi bahutarāni ceva sikkhāpadāni honti appatarā ca bhikkhū aññāya saṇṭhahantī”ti?**And what is the cause, what is the reason why these days there are more training rules and fewer enlightened mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[2372]="*“Evametaṃ, bhaddāli, hoti sattesu hāyamānesu, saddhamme antaradhāyamāne, bahutarāni ceva sikkhāpadāni honti appatarā ca bhikkhū aññāya saṇṭhahantīti.**“That’s how it is, Bhaddāli. When sentient beings are in decline and the true teaching is disappearing there are more training rules and fewer enlightened mendicants.*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Na tāva, bhaddāli, satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññāpeti yāva na idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṅghe pātubhavanti.**The Teacher doesn’t lay down training rules for disciples as long as certain defiling influences have not appeared in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[2374]="*Yato ca kho, bhaddāli, idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṅghe pātubhavanti, atha satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññāpeti tesaṃyeva āsavaṭṭhānīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭighātāya.**But when such defiling influences appear in the Saṅgha, the Teacher lays down training rules for disciples to protect against them.*";
P_HTM[2375]="*Na tāva, bhaddāli, idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṅghe pātubhavanti yāva na saṅgho mahattaṃ patto hoti.**And they don’t appear until the Saṅgha has attained a great size,*";
P_HTM[2376]="*Yato ca kho, bhaddāli, saṅgho mahattaṃ patto hoti, atha idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṅghe pātubhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[2377]="*Atha satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññāpeti tesaṃyeva āsavaṭṭhānīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭighātāya.* **";
P_HTM[2378]="*Na tāva, bhaddāli, idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṅghe pātubhavanti yāva na saṅgho lābhaggaṃ patto hoti, yasaggaṃ patto hoti, bāhusaccaṃ patto hoti, rattaññutaṃ patto hoti.**an abundance of material support and fame, learning, and seniority.*";
P_HTM[2379]="*Yato ca kho, bhaddāli, saṅgho rattaññutaṃ patto hoti, atha idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṅghe pātubhavanti, atha satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññāpeti tesaṃyeva āsavaṭṭhānīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭighātāya.**But when the Saṅgha has attained these things, then such defiling influences appear in the Saṅgha, and the Teacher lays down training rules for disciples to protect against them.*";
P_HTM[2380]="*Appakā kho tumhe, bhaddāli, tena samayena ahuvattha yadā vo ahaṃ ājānīyasusūpamaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ desesiṃ.**There were only of few of you there at the time when I taught the exposition of the teaching on the simile of the thoroughbred colt.*";
P_HTM[2381]="*Taṃ sarasi bhaddālī”ti?**Do you remember that, Bhaddāli?”*";
P_HTM[2382]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2383]="*“Tatra, bhaddāli, kaṃ hetuṃ paccesī”ti?**“What do you believe the reason for that is?”*";
P_HTM[2384]="*“So hi nūnāhaṃ, bhante, dīgharattaṃ satthusāsane sikkhāya aparipūrakārī ahosin”ti.**“Sir, it’s surely because for a long time now I haven’t fulfilled the training according to the Teacher’s instructions.”*";
P_HTM[2385]="*“Na kho, bhaddāli, eseva hetu, esa paccayo.**“That’s not the only reason, Bhaddāli.*";
P_HTM[2386]="*Api ca me tvaṃ, bhaddāli, dīgharattaṃ cetasā cetoparicca vidito:**Rather, for a long time I have comprehended your mind and known:*";
P_HTM[2387]="*‘na cāyaṃ moghapuriso mayā dhamme desiyamāne aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetaso samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇātī’ti.**‘While I’m teaching, this silly man doesn’t pay heed, pay attention, engage wholeheartedly, or lend an ear.’*";
P_HTM[2388]="*Api ca te ahaṃ, bhaddāli, ājānīyasusūpamaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi.**Still, Bhaddāli, I shall teach the exposition of the teaching on the simile of the thoroughbred colt.*";
P_HTM[2389]="*Taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[2390]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā bhaddāli bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Bhaddāli replied.*";
P_HTM[2391]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2392]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhaddāli, dakkho assadamako bhadraṃ assājānīyaṃ labhitvā paṭhameneva mukhādhāne kāraṇaṃ kāreti.**“Suppose a deft horse trainer were to obtain a fine thoroughbred. First of all he’d make it get used to wearing the bit.*";
P_HTM[2393]="*Tassa mukhādhāne kāraṇaṃ kāriyamānassa hontiyeva visūkāyitāni visevitāni vipphanditāni kānici kānici, yathā taṃ akāritapubbaṃ kāraṇaṃ kāriyamānassa.**Because it has not done this before, it still resorts to some tricks, dodges, and evasions.*";
P_HTM[2394]="*So abhiṇhakāraṇā anupubbakāraṇā tasmiṃ ṭhāne parinibbāyati.**But with regular and gradual practice it quells that bad habit.*";
P_HTM[2395]="*Yato kho, bhaddāli, bhadro assājānīyo abhiṇhakāraṇā anupubbakāraṇā tasmiṃ ṭhāne parinibbuto hoti, tamenaṃ assadamako uttari kāraṇaṃ kāreti yugādhāne.**When it has done this, the horse trainer next makes it get used to wearing the harness.*";
P_HTM[2396]="*Tassa yugādhāne kāraṇaṃ kāriyamānassa hontiyeva visūkāyitāni visevitāni vipphanditāni kānici kānici, yathā taṃ akāritapubbaṃ kāraṇaṃ kāriyamānassa.**Because it has not done this before, it still resorts to some tricks, dodges, and evasions.*";
P_HTM[2397]="*So abhiṇhakāraṇā anupubbakāraṇā tasmiṃ ṭhāne parinibbāyati.**But with regular and gradual practice it quells that bad habit.*";
P_HTM[2398]="*Yato kho, bhaddāli, bhadro assājānīyo abhiṇhakāraṇā anupubbakāraṇā tasmiṃ ṭhāne parinibbuto hoti, tamenaṃ assadamako uttari kāraṇaṃ kāreti anukkame maṇḍale khurakāse dhāve davatte rājaguṇe rājavaṃse uttame jave uttame haye uttame sākhalye.**When it has done this, the horse trainer next makes it get used to walking in procession, circling, prancing, galloping, charging, the protocols and traditions of court, and in the very best speed, fleetness, and friendliness.*";
P_HTM[2399]="*Tassa uttame jave uttame haye uttame sākhalye kāraṇaṃ kāriyamānassa hontiyeva visūkāyitāni visevitāni vipphanditāni kānici kānici, yathā taṃ akāritapubbaṃ kāraṇaṃ kāriyamānassa.**Because it has not done this before, it still resorts to some tricks, dodges, and evasions.*";
P_HTM[2400]="*So abhiṇhakāraṇā anupubbakāraṇā tasmiṃ ṭhāne parinibbāyati.**But with regular and gradual practice it quells that bad habit.*";
P_HTM[2401]="*Yato kho, bhaddāli, bhadro assājānīyo abhiṇhakāraṇā anupubbakāraṇā tasmiṃ ṭhāne parinibbuto hoti, tamenaṃ assadamako uttari vaṇṇiyañca pāṇiyañca anuppavecchati.**When it has done this, the horse trainer next rewards it with a grooming and a rub down.*";
P_HTM[2402]="*Imehi kho, bhaddāli, dasahaṅgehi samannāgato bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo rañño aṅganteva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**A fine royal thoroughbred with these ten factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and reckoned as a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[2403]="*Evameva kho, bhaddāli, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with ten qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[2404]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2405]="*Idha, bhaddāli, bhikkhu asekhāya sammādiṭṭhiyā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāsaṅkappena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāvācāya samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammākammantena samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāājīvena samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāvāyāmena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāsatiyā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāsamādhinā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāñāṇena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāvimuttiyā samannāgato hoti—**It’s when a mendicant has an adept’s right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[2406]="*imehi kho, bhaddāli, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these ten factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[2407]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2408]="*Attamano āyasmā bhaddāli bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Bhaddāli was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2409]="*Bhaddālisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2410]="*66. Laṭukikopamasutta**The Simile of the Quail*";
P_HTM[2411]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2412]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅguttarāpesu viharati āpaṇaṃ nāma aṅguttarāpānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Northern Āpaṇas, near the town of theirs named Āpaṇa.*";
P_HTM[2413]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āpaṇaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Āpaṇa for alms.*";
P_HTM[2414]="*Āpaṇe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yenaññataro vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**He wandered for alms in Āpaṇa. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to a certain forest grove for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[2415]="*Taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**Having plunged deep into it, he sat at the root of a certain tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[2416]="*Āyasmāpi kho udāyī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āpaṇaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Venerable Udāyī also robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Āpaṇa for alms.*";
P_HTM[2417]="*Āpaṇe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena so vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**He wandered for alms in Āpaṇa. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to a certain forest grove for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[2418]="*Taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**Having plunged deep into it, he sat at the root of a certain tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[2419]="*Atha kho āyasmato udāyissa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:**Then as Venerable Udāyī was in private retreat this thought came to his mind:*";
P_HTM[2420]="*“bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā dukkhadhammānaṃ apahattā, bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā sukhadhammānaṃ upahattā;**“The Buddha has rid us of so many things that bring suffering and gifted us so many things that bring happiness!*";
P_HTM[2421]="*bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ apahattā, bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upahattā”ti.**He has rid us of so many unskillful things and gifted us so many skillful things!”*";
P_HTM[2422]="*Atha kho āyasmā udāyī sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā udāyī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, Udāyī came out of retreat and went to the Buddha. He bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2423]="*“idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:**“Just now, sir, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind:*";
P_HTM[2424]="*‘bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā dukkhadhammānaṃ apahattā, bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā sukhadhammānaṃ upahattā;**‘The Buddha has rid us of so many things that bring suffering and gifted us so many things that bring happiness!*";
P_HTM[2425]="*bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ apahattā, bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upahattā’ti.**He has rid us of so many unskillful things and gifted us so many skillful things!’*";
P_HTM[2426]="*Mayañhi, bhante, pubbe sāyañceva bhuñjāma pāto ca divā ca vikāle.**For we used to eat in the evening, the morning, and at the wrong time of day.*";
P_HTM[2427]="*Ahu kho so, bhante, samayo yaṃ bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**But then there came a time when the Buddha addressed the mendicants, saying,*";
P_HTM[2428]="*‘iṅgha tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ divāvikālabhojanaṃ pajahathā’ti.**‘Please, mendicants, give up that meal at the wrong time of day.’*";
P_HTM[2429]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, ahudeva aññathattaṃ, ahudeva domanassaṃ:**At that, sir, we became sad and upset,*";
P_HTM[2430]="*‘yampi no saddhā gahapatikā divā vikāle paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ denti tassapi no bhagavā pahānamāha, tassapi no sugato paṭinissaggamāhā’ti.**‘But these faithful householders give us a variety of delicious foods at the wrong time of day. And the Blessed One tells us to give it up! The Holy One tells us to let it go!’*";
P_HTM[2431]="*Te mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavati pemañca gāravañca hiriñca ottappañca sampassamānā evaṃ taṃ divāvikālabhojanaṃ pajahimhā.**But when we considered our love and respect for the Buddha, and our sense of conscience and prudence, we gave up that meal at the wrong time of day.*";
P_HTM[2432]="*Te mayaṃ, bhante, sāyañceva bhuñjāma pāto ca.**Then we ate in the evening and the morning.*";
P_HTM[2433]="*Ahu kho so, bhante, samayo yaṃ bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**But then there came a time when the Buddha addressed the mendicants, saying,*";
P_HTM[2434]="*‘iṅgha tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ rattiṃvikālabhojanaṃ pajahathā’ti.**‘Please, mendicants, give up that meal at the wrong time of night.’*";
P_HTM[2435]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, ahudeva aññathattaṃ ahudeva domanassaṃ:**At that, sir, we became sad and upset,*";
P_HTM[2436]="*‘yampi no imesaṃ dvinnaṃ bhattānaṃ paṇītasaṅkhātataraṃ tassapi no bhagavā pahānamāha, tassapi no sugato paṭinissaggamāhā’ti.**‘But that’s considered the more delicious of the two meals. And the Blessed One tells us to give it up! The Holy One tells us to let it go!’*";
P_HTM[2437]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhante, aññataro puriso divā sūpeyyaṃ labhitvā evamāha:**Once it so happened that a certain person got some soup during the day. He said,*";
P_HTM[2438]="*‘handa ca imaṃ nikkhipatha, sāyaṃ sabbeva samaggā bhuñjissāmā’ti.**‘Come, let’s set this aside; we’ll enjoy it together this evening.’*";
P_HTM[2439]="*Yā kāci, bhante, saṅkhatiyo sabbā tā rattiṃ, appā divā.**Nearly all meals are prepared at night, only a few in the day.*";
P_HTM[2440]="*Te mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavati pemañca gāravañca hiriñca ottappañca sampassamānā evaṃ taṃ rattiṃvikālabhojanaṃ pajahimhā.**But when we considered our love and respect for the Buddha, and our sense of conscience and prudence, we gave up that meal at the wrong time of night.*";
P_HTM[2441]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhante, bhikkhū rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ piṇḍāya carantā candanikampi pavisanti, oligallepi papatanti, kaṇṭakāvāṭampi ārohanti, suttampi gāviṃ ārohanti, māṇavehipi samāgacchanti katakammehipi akatakammehipi, mātugāmopi te asaddhammena nimanteti.**In the past, mendicants went wandering for alms in the dark of the night. They walked into a swamp, or fell into a sewer, or collided with a thorn bush, or collided with a sleeping cow, or encountered youths escaping a crime or on their way to commit one, or were invited by a female to commit a lewd act.*";
P_HTM[2442]="*Bhūtapubbāhaṃ, bhante, rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ piṇḍāya carāmi.**Once it so happened that I wandered for alms in the dark of the night.*";
P_HTM[2443]="*Addasā kho maṃ, bhante, aññatarā itthī vijjantarikāya bhājanaṃ dhovantī.**A woman washing a pot saw me by a flash of lightning.*";
P_HTM[2444]="*Disvā maṃ bhītā vissaramakāsi:**Startled, she cried out,*";
P_HTM[2445]="*‘abhumme pisāco vata man’ti.**‘Bloody hell! A goblin’s upon me!’*";
P_HTM[2446]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, taṃ itthiṃ etadavocaṃ:**When she said this, I said to her,*";
P_HTM[2447]="*‘nāhaṃ, bhagini, pisāco;**‘Sister, I am no goblin.*";
P_HTM[2448]="*bhikkhu piṇḍāya ṭhito’ti.**I’m a mendicant waiting for alms.’*";
P_HTM[2449]="*‘Bhikkhussa ātumārī, bhikkhussa mātumārī.**‘Then it’s a mendicant whose ma died and pa died!*";
P_HTM[2450]="*Varaṃ te, bhikkhu, tiṇhena govikantanena kucchi parikanto, na tveva varaṃ yaṃ rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ kucchihetu piṇḍāya carasī’ti.**You’d be better off having your belly sliced open with a meat cleaver than to wander for alms in the dark of night for the sake of your belly.’*";
P_HTM[2451]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, tadanussarato evaṃ hoti:**Recollecting that, I thought,*";
P_HTM[2452]="*‘bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā dukkhadhammānaṃ apahattā, bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā sukhadhammānaṃ upahattā;**‘The Buddha has rid us of so many things that bring suffering and gifted us so many things that bring happiness!*";
P_HTM[2453]="*bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ apahattā, bahūnaṃ vata no bhagavā kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upahattā’”ti.**He has rid us of so many unskillful things and gifted us so many skillful things!’”*";
P_HTM[2454]="*“Evameva panudāyi, idhekacce moghapurisā ‘idaṃ pajahathā’ti mayā vuccamānā te evamāhaṃsu:**“This is exactly what happens when some foolish people are told by me to give something up. They say,*";
P_HTM[2455]="*‘kiṃ panimassa appamattakassa oramattakassa adhisallikhatevāyaṃ samaṇo’ti.**‘What, such a trivial, insignificant thing as this? This ascetic is much too strict!’*";
P_HTM[2456]="*Te tañceva nappajahanti, mayi ca appaccayaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti.**They don’t give it up, and they nurse bitterness towards me;*";
P_HTM[2457]="*Ye ca bhikkhū sikkhākāmā tesaṃ taṃ, udāyi, hoti balavaṃ bandhanaṃ, daḷhaṃ bandhanaṃ, thiraṃ bandhanaṃ, apūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, thūlo, kaliṅgaro—**and for the mendicants who want to train, that becomes a strong, firm, stout bond, a tie that has not rotted, and a heavy yoke.*";
P_HTM[2458]="*seyyathāpi, udāyi, laṭukikā sakuṇikā pūtilatāya bandhanena baddhā tattheva vadhaṃ vā bandhaṃ vā maraṇaṃ vā āgameti.**Suppose a quail was tied with a rotten creeper, and was waiting there to be injured, caged, or killed.*";
P_HTM[2459]="*Yo nu kho, udāyi, evaṃ vadeyya:**Would it be right to say that,*";
P_HTM[2460]="*‘yena sā laṭukikā sakuṇikā pūtilatāya bandhanena baddhā tattheva vadhaṃ vā bandhaṃ vā maraṇaṃ vā āgameti, tañhi tassā abalaṃ bandhanaṃ, dubbalaṃ bandhanaṃ, pūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, asārakaṃ bandhanan’ti;**for that quail, that rotten creeper is weak, feeble, rotten, and insubstantial?”*";
P_HTM[2461]="*sammā nu kho so, udāyi, vadamāno vadeyyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2462]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[2463]="*Yena sā, bhante, laṭukikā sakuṇikā pūtilatāya bandhanena baddhā tattheva vadhaṃ vā bandhaṃ vā maraṇaṃ vā āgameti, tañhi tassā balavaṃ bandhanaṃ, daḷhaṃ bandhanaṃ, thiraṃ bandhanaṃ apūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, thūlo, kaliṅgaro”ti.**For that quail, that rotten creeper is a strong, firm, stout bond, a tie that has not rotted, and a heavy yoke.”*";
P_HTM[2464]="*“Evameva kho, udāyi, idhekacce moghapurisā ‘idaṃ pajahathā’ti mayā vuccamānā te evamāhaṃsu:**“In the same way, when some foolish people are told by me to give something up, they say,*";
P_HTM[2465]="*‘kiṃ panimassa appamattakassa oramattakassa adhisallikhatevāyaṃ samaṇo’ti?**‘What, such a trivial, insignificant thing as this? This ascetic is much too strict!’*";
P_HTM[2466]="*Te tañceva nappajahanti, mayi ca appaccayaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti.**They don’t give it up, and they nurse bitterness towards me;*";
P_HTM[2467]="*Ye ca bhikkhū sikkhākāmā tesaṃ taṃ, udāyi, hoti balavaṃ bandhanaṃ, daḷhaṃ bandhanaṃ, thiraṃ bandhanaṃ, apūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, thūlo, kaliṅgaro.**and for the mendicants who want to train, that becomes a strong, firm, stout bond, a tie that has not rotted, and a heavy yoke.*";
P_HTM[2468]="*Idha panudāyi, ekacce kulaputtā ‘idaṃ pajahathā’ti mayā vuccamānā te evamāhaṃsu:**But when some gentlemen are told by me to give something up, they say,*";
P_HTM[2469]="*‘kiṃ panimassa appamattakassa oramattakassa pahātabbassa yassa no bhagavā pahānamāha, yassa no sugato paṭinissaggamāhā’ti?**‘What, we just have to give up such a trivial, insignificant thing as this, when the Blessed One tells us to give it up, the Holy One tells us to let it go?’*";
P_HTM[2470]="*Te tañceva pajahanti, mayi ca na appaccayaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti.**They give it up, and they don’t nurse bitterness towards me;*";
P_HTM[2471]="*Ye ca bhikkhū sikkhākāmā te taṃ pahāya appossukkā pannalomā paradattavuttā migabhūtena cetasā viharanti.**and when the mendicants who want to train have given that up, they live relaxed, unruffled, surviving on charity, their hearts free as a wild deer.*";
P_HTM[2472]="*Tesaṃ taṃ, udāyi, hoti abalaṃ bandhanaṃ, dubbalaṃ bandhanaṃ, pūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, asārakaṃ bandhanaṃ—**For them, that bond is weak, feeble, rotten, and insubstantial.*";
P_HTM[2473]="*seyyathāpi, udāyi, rañño nāgo īsādanto urūḷhavā abhijāto saṅgāmāvacaro daḷhehi varattehi bandhanehi baddho īsakaṃyeva kāyaṃ sannāmetvā tāni bandhanāni saṃchinditvā sampadāletvā yena kāmaṃ pakkamati.**Suppose there was a royal bull elephant with tusks like plows, able to draw a heavy load, pedigree and battle-hardened. And it was bound with a strong harness. But just by twisting its body a little, it would break apart its bonds and go wherever it wants.*";
P_HTM[2474]="*Yo nu kho, udāyi, evaṃ vadeyya:**Would it be right to say that,*";
P_HTM[2475]="*‘yehi so rañño nāgo īsādanto urūḷhavā abhijāto saṅgāmāvacaro daḷhehi varattehi bandhanehi baddho īsakaṃyeva kāyaṃ sannāmetvā tāni bandhanāni saṃchinditvā sampadāletvā yena kāmaṃ pakkamati, tañhi tassa balavaṃ bandhanaṃ, daḷhaṃ bandhanaṃ, thiraṃ bandhanaṃ, apūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, thūlo, kaliṅgaro’ti;**for that bull elephant, that strong harness is a strong, firm, stout bond, a tie that has not rotted, and a heavy yoke?”*";
P_HTM[2476]="*sammā nu kho so, udāyi, vadamāno vadeyyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2477]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[2478]="*Yehi so, bhante, rañño nāgo īsādanto urūḷhavā abhijāto saṅgāmāvacaro daḷhehi varattehi bandhanehi baddho īsakaṃyeva kāyaṃ sannāmetvā tāni bandhanāni saṃchinditvā sampadāletvā yena kāmaṃ pakkamati, tañhi tassa abalaṃ bandhanaṃ … pe … asārakaṃ bandhanan”ti.**For that bull elephant, that strong harness is weak, feeble, rotten, and insubstantial.”*";
P_HTM[2479]="*“Evameva kho, udāyi, idhekacce kulaputtā ‘idaṃ pajahathā’ti mayā vuccamānā te evamāhaṃsu:**“In the same way, when some gentlemen are told by me to give something up, they say,*";
P_HTM[2480]="*‘kiṃ panimassa appamattakassa oramattakassa pahātabbassa yassa no bhagavā pahānamāha, yassa no sugato paṭinissaggamāhā’ti?**‘What, we just have to give up such a trivial, insignificant thing as this, when the Blessed One tells us to give it up, the Holy One tells us to let it go?’*";
P_HTM[2481]="*Te tañceva pajahanti, mayi ca na appaccayaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti.**They give it up, and they don’t nurse bitterness towards me;*";
P_HTM[2482]="*Ye ca bhikkhū sikkhākāmā te taṃ pahāya appossukkā pannalomā paradattavuttā migabhūtena cetasā viharanti.**and when the mendicants who want to train have given that up, they live relaxed, unruffled, surviving on charity, their hearts free as a wild deer.*";
P_HTM[2483]="*Tesaṃ taṃ, udāyi, hoti abalaṃ bandhanaṃ, dubbalaṃ bandhanaṃ, pūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, asārakaṃ bandhanaṃ.**For them, that bond is weak, feeble, rotten, and insubstantial.*";
P_HTM[2484]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, puriso daliddo assako anāḷhiyo;**Suppose there was a poor man, with few possessions and little wealth.*";
P_HTM[2485]="*tassassa ekaṃ agārakaṃ oluggaviluggaṃ kākātidāyiṃ naparamarūpaṃ, ekā khaṭopikā oluggaviluggā naparamarūpā, ekissā kumbhiyā dhaññasamavāpakaṃ naparamarūpaṃ, ekā jāyikā naparamarūpā.**He had a single broken-down hovel open to the crows, not the best sort; a single broken-down couch, not the best sort; a single pot for storing grain, not the best sort; and a single wifey, not the best sort.*";
P_HTM[2486]="*So ārāmagataṃ bhikkhuṃ passeyya sudhotahatthapādaṃ manuññaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuttāviṃ sītāya chāyāya nisinnaṃ adhicitte yuttaṃ.**He’d see a mendicant sitting in meditation in the cool shade, their hands and feet well washed after eating a delectable meal.*";
P_HTM[2487]="*Tassa evamassa:**He’d think,*";
P_HTM[2488]="*‘sukhaṃ vata bho sāmaññaṃ, ārogyaṃ vata bho sāmaññaṃ.**‘The ascetic life is so very pleasant! The ascetic life is so very skillful!*";
P_HTM[2489]="*So vatassaṃ yohaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**If only I could shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[2490]="*So na sakkuṇeyya ekaṃ agārakaṃ oluggaviluggaṃ kākātidāyiṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekaṃ khaṭopikaṃ oluggaviluggaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekissā kumbhiyā dhaññasamavāpakaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekaṃ jāyikaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ.**But he’s not able to give up his broken-down hovel, his broken-down couch, his pot for storing grain, or his wifey—none of which are the best sort—in order to go forth.*";
P_HTM[2491]="*Yo nu kho, udāyi, evaṃ vadeyya:**Would it be right to say that,*";
P_HTM[2492]="*‘yehi so puriso bandhanehi baddho na sakkoti ekaṃ agārakaṃ oluggaviluggaṃ kākātidāyiṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekaṃ khaṭopikaṃ oluggaviluggaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekissā kumbhiyā dhaññasamavāpakaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekaṃ jāyikaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ;**for that man,*";
P_HTM[2493]="*tañhi tassa abalaṃ bandhanaṃ, dubbalaṃ bandhanaṃ, pūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, asārakaṃ bandhanan’ti;**those bonds are weak, feeble, rotten, and insubstantial?”*";
P_HTM[2494]="*sammā nu kho so, udāyi, vadamāno vadeyyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2495]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[2496]="*Yehi so, bhante, puriso bandhanehi baddho, na sakkoti ekaṃ agārakaṃ oluggaviluggaṃ kākātidāyiṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekaṃ khaṭopikaṃ oluggaviluggaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekissā kumbhiyā dhaññasamavāpakaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya, ekaṃ jāyikaṃ naparamarūpaṃ pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ;**For that man,*";
P_HTM[2497]="*tañhi tassa balavaṃ bandhanaṃ, daḷhaṃ bandhanaṃ, thiraṃ bandhanaṃ, apūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, thūlo, kaliṅgaro”ti.**they are a strong, firm, stout bond, a tie that has not rotted, and a heavy yoke.”*";
P_HTM[2498]="*“Evameva kho, udāyi, idhekacce moghapurisā ‘idaṃ pajahathā’ti mayā vuccamānā te evamāhaṃsu:**“In the same way, when some foolish people are told by me to give something up, they say,*";
P_HTM[2499]="*‘kiṃ panimassa appamattakassa oramattakassa adhisallikhatevāyaṃ samaṇo’ti?**‘What, such a trivial, insignificant thing as this? This ascetic is much too strict!’*";
P_HTM[2500]="*Te tañceva nappajahanti, mayi ca appaccayaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti.**They don’t give it up, and they nurse bitterness towards me;*";
P_HTM[2501]="*Ye ca bhikkhū sikkhākāmā tesaṃ taṃ, udāyi, hoti balavaṃ bandhanaṃ, daḷhaṃ bandhanaṃ, thiraṃ bandhanaṃ, apūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, thūlo, kaliṅgaro.**and for the mendicants who want to train, that becomes a strong, firm, stout bond, a tie that has not rotted, and a heavy yoke.*";
P_HTM[2502]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo, nekānaṃ nikkhagaṇānaṃ cayo, nekānaṃ dhaññagaṇānaṃ cayo, nekānaṃ khettagaṇānaṃ cayo, nekānaṃ vatthugaṇānaṃ cayo, nekānaṃ bhariyagaṇānaṃ cayo, nekānaṃ dāsagaṇānaṃ cayo, nekānaṃ dāsigaṇānaṃ cayo;**Suppose there was a rich man, affluent, and wealthy. He had a vast amount of gold coin, grain, fields, lands, wives, and male and female bondservants.*";
P_HTM[2503]="*so ārāmagataṃ bhikkhuṃ passeyya sudhotahatthapādaṃ manuññaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuttāviṃ sītāya chāyāya nisinnaṃ adhicitte yuttaṃ.**He’d see a mendicant sitting in meditation in the cool shade, their hands and feet well washed after eating a delectable meal.*";
P_HTM[2504]="*Tassa evamassa:**He’d think,*";
P_HTM[2505]="*‘sukhaṃ vata bho sāmaññaṃ, ārogyaṃ vata bho sāmaññaṃ.**‘The ascetic life is so very pleasant! The ascetic life is so very skillful!*";
P_HTM[2506]="*So vatassaṃ yohaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**If only I could shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[2507]="*So sakkuṇeyya nekāni nikkhagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dhaññagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni khettagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni vatthugaṇāni pahāya, nekāni bhariyagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dāsagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dāsigaṇāni pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ.**And he is able to give up his vast amount of gold coin, grain, fields, lands, wives, and male and female bondservants in order to go forth.*";
P_HTM[2508]="*Yo nu kho, udāyi, evaṃ vadeyya:**Would it be right to say that,*";
P_HTM[2509]="*‘yehi so gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā bandhanehi baddho, sakkoti nekāni nikkhagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dhaññagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni khettagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni vatthugaṇāni pahāya, nekāni bhariyagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dāsagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dāsigaṇāni pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ, tañhi tassa balavaṃ bandhanaṃ, daḷhaṃ bandhanaṃ, thiraṃ bandhanaṃ, apūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, thūlo, kaliṅgaro’ti;**for that man, they are a strong, firm, stout bond, a tie that has not rotted, and a heavy yoke?”*";
P_HTM[2510]="*sammā nu kho so, udāyi, vadamāno vadeyyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2511]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[2512]="*Yehi so, bhante, gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā bandhanehi baddho, sakkoti nekāni nikkhagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dhaññagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni khettagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni vatthugaṇāni pahāya, nekāni bhariyagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dāsagaṇāni pahāya, nekāni dāsigaṇāni pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ;**For that man,*";
P_HTM[2513]="*tañhi tassa abalaṃ bandhanaṃ, dubbalaṃ bandhanaṃ, pūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, asārakaṃ bandhanan”ti.**those bonds are weak, feeble, rotten, and insubstantial.”*";
P_HTM[2514]="*“Evameva kho, udāyi, idhekacce kulaputtā ‘idaṃ pajahathā’ti mayā vuccamānā te evamāhaṃsu:**“In the same way, when some gentlemen are told by me to give something up, they say,*";
P_HTM[2515]="*‘kiṃ panimassa appamattakassa oramattakassa pahātabbassa yassa no bhagavā pahānamāha, yassa no sugato paṭinissaggamāhā’ti?**‘What, we just have to give up such a trivial, insignificant thing as this, when the Blessed One tells us to give it up, the Holy One tells us to let it go?’*";
P_HTM[2516]="*Te tañceva pajahanti, mayi ca na appaccayaṃ upaṭṭhāpenti.**They give it up, and they don’t nurse bitterness towards me;*";
P_HTM[2517]="*Ye ca bhikkhū sikkhākāmā te taṃ pahāya appossukkā pannalomā paradattavuttā migabhūtena cetasā viharanti.**and when the mendicants who want to train have given that up, they live relaxed, unruffled, surviving on charity, their hearts free as a wild deer.*";
P_HTM[2518]="*Tesaṃ taṃ, udāyi, hoti abalaṃ bandhanaṃ, dubbalaṃ bandhanaṃ, pūtikaṃ bandhanaṃ, asārakaṃ bandhanaṃ.**For them, that bond is weak, feeble, rotten, and insubstantial.*";
P_HTM[2519]="*Cattārome, udāyi, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**Udāyī, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2520]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2521]="*Idhudāyi, ekacco puggalo upadhipahānāya paṭipanno hoti upadhipaṭinissaggāya.**Take a certain person practicing to give up and let go of attachments.*";
P_HTM[2522]="*Tamenaṃ upadhipahānāya paṭipannaṃ upadhipaṭinissaggāya upadhipaṭisaṃyuttā sarasaṅkappā samudācaranti.**As they do so, memories and thoughts connected with attachments beset them.*";
P_HTM[2523]="*So te adhivāseti, nappajahati, na vinodeti, na byantīkaroti, na anabhāvaṃ gameti.**They tolerate them and don’t give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them.*";
P_HTM[2524]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, udāyi, puggalaṃ ‘saṃyutto’ti vadāmi no ‘visaṃyutto’.**I call this person ‘fettered’, not ‘detached’.*";
P_HTM[2525]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2526]="*Indriyavemattatā hi me, udāyi, imasmiṃ puggale viditā.**Because I understand the diversity of faculties as it applies to this person.*";
P_HTM[2527]="*Idha panudāyi, ekacco puggalo upadhipahānāya paṭipanno hoti upadhipaṭinissaggāya.**Take another person practicing to give up and let go of attachments.*";
P_HTM[2528]="*Tamenaṃ upadhipahānāya paṭipannaṃ upadhipaṭinissaggāya upadhipaṭisaṃyuttā sarasaṅkappā samudācaranti.**As they do so, memories and thoughts connected with attachments beset them.*";
P_HTM[2529]="*So te nādhivāseti, pajahati, vinodeti, byantīkaroti, anabhāvaṃ gameti.**They don’t tolerate them, but give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them.*";
P_HTM[2530]="*Imampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, puggalaṃ ‘saṃyutto’ti vadāmi no ‘visaṃyutto’.**I call this person ‘fettered’, not ‘detached’.*";
P_HTM[2531]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2532]="*Indriyavemattatā hi me, udāyi, imasmiṃ puggale viditā.**Because I understand the diversity of faculties as it applies to this person.*";
P_HTM[2533]="*Idha panudāyi, ekacco puggalo upadhipahānāya paṭipanno hoti upadhipaṭinissaggāya.**Take another person practicing to give up and let go of attachments.*";
P_HTM[2534]="*Tamenaṃ upadhipahānāya paṭipannaṃ upadhipaṭinissaggāya kadāci karahaci satisammosā upadhipaṭisaṃyuttā sarasaṅkappā samudācaranti;**As they do so, every so often they lose mindfulness, and memories and thoughts connected with attachments beset them.*";
P_HTM[2535]="*dandho, udāyi, satuppādo.**Their mindfulness is slow to come up,*";
P_HTM[2536]="*Atha kho naṃ khippameva pajahati, vinodeti, byantīkaroti, anabhāvaṃ gameti.**but they quickly give up, get rid of, eliminate, and obliterate those thoughts.*";
P_HTM[2537]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, puriso divasaṃsantatte ayokaṭāhe dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni nipāteyya;**Suppose there was an iron cauldron that had been heated all day, and a person let two or three drops of water fall onto it.*";
P_HTM[2538]="*dandho, udāyi, udakaphusitānaṃ nipāto. Atha kho naṃ khippameva parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya.**The drops would be slow to fall, but they’d quickly dry up and evaporate.*";
P_HTM[2539]="*Evameva kho, udāyi, idhekacco puggalo upadhipahānāya paṭipanno hoti upadhipaṭinissaggāya.**In the same way, take a person practicing to give up and let go of attachments.*";
P_HTM[2540]="*Tamenaṃ upadhipahānāya paṭipannaṃ upadhipaṭinissaggāya kadāci karahaci satisammosā upadhipaṭisaṃyuttā sarasaṅkappā samudācaranti;**As they do so, every so often they lose mindfulness, and memories and thoughts connected with attachments beset them.*";
P_HTM[2541]="*dandho, udāyi, satuppādo.**Their mindfulness is slow to come up,*";
P_HTM[2542]="*Atha kho naṃ khippameva pajahati, vinodeti, byantīkaroti, anabhāvaṃ gameti.**but they quickly give them up, get rid of, eliminate, and obliterate those thoughts.*";
P_HTM[2543]="*Imampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, puggalaṃ ‘saṃyutto’ti vadāmi no ‘visaṃyutto’.**I also call this person ‘fettered’, not ‘detached’.*";
P_HTM[2544]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2545]="*Indriyavemattatā hi me, udāyi, imasmiṃ puggale viditā.**Because I understand the diversity of faculties as it applies to this person.*";
P_HTM[2546]="*Idha panudāyi, ekacco puggalo ‘upadhi dukkhassa mūlan’ti—**Take another person who, understanding that attachment is the root of suffering,*";
P_HTM[2547]="*iti viditvā nirupadhi hoti, upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto.**is freed with the ending of attachments.*";
P_HTM[2548]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, udāyi, puggalaṃ ‘visaṃyutto’ti vadāmi no ‘saṃyutto’ti.**I call this person ‘detached’, not ‘fettered’.*";
P_HTM[2549]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2550]="*Indriyavemattatā hi me, udāyi, imasmiṃ puggale viditā.**Because I understand the diversity of faculties as it applies to this person.*";
P_HTM[2551]="*Ime kho, udāyi, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**These are the four people found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2552]="*Pañca kho ime, udāyi, kāmaguṇā.**Udāyī, these are the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2553]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2554]="*Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2555]="*sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[2556]="*ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[2557]="*jivhāviññeyyā rasā …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[2558]="*kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2559]="*Ime kho, udāyi, pañca kāmaguṇā.**These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2560]="*Yaṃ kho, udāyi, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati kāmasukhaṃ miḷhasukhaṃ puthujjanasukhaṃ anariyasukhaṃ, na sevitabbaṃ, na bhāvetabbaṃ, na bahulīkātabbaṃ; ‘bhāyitabbaṃ etassa sukhassā’ti vadāmi.**The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual stimulation is called sensual pleasure—a filthy, ordinary, ignoble pleasure. Such pleasure should not be cultivated or developed, but should be feared, I say.*";
P_HTM[2561]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati**Take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[2562]="*vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,**second absorption …*";
P_HTM[2563]="*pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati,**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[2564]="*sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[2565]="*Idaṃ vuccati nekkhammasukhaṃ pavivekasukhaṃ upasamasukhaṃ sambodhasukhaṃ, āsevitabbaṃ, bhāvetabbaṃ, bahulīkātabbaṃ; ‘na bhāyitabbaṃ etassa sukhassā’ti vadāmi.**This is called the pleasure of renunciation, the pleasure of seclusion, the pleasure of peace, the pleasure of awakening. Such pleasure should be cultivated and developed, and should not be feared, I say.*";
P_HTM[2566]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**Take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[2567]="*idaṃ kho ahaṃ, udāyi, iñjitasmiṃ vadāmi.**This belongs to the perturbable, I say.*";
P_HTM[2568]="*Kiñca tattha iñjitasmiṃ?**And what there belongs to the perturbable?*";
P_HTM[2569]="*Yadeva tattha vitakkavicārā aniruddhā honti idaṃ tattha iñjitasmiṃ.**Whatever placing of the mind and keeping it connected has not ceased there is what belongs to the perturbable.*";
P_HTM[2570]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**Take a mendicant who, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, enters and remains in the second absorption.*";
P_HTM[2571]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, iñjitasmiṃ vadāmi.**This belongs to the perturbable, I say.*";
P_HTM[2572]="*Kiñca tattha iñjitasmiṃ?**And what there belongs to the perturbable?*";
P_HTM[2573]="*Yadeva tattha pītisukhaṃ aniruddhaṃ hoti idaṃ tattha iñjitasmiṃ.**Whatever rapture and bliss has not ceased there is what belongs to the perturbable.*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**Take a mendicant who, with the fading away of rapture, enters and remains in the third absorption.*";
P_HTM[2575]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, iñjitasmiṃ vadāmi.**This belongs to the perturbable.*";
P_HTM[2576]="*Kiñca tattha iñjitasmiṃ?**And what there belongs to the perturbable?*";
P_HTM[2577]="*Yadeva tattha upekkhāsukhaṃ aniruddhaṃ hoti idaṃ tattha iñjitasmiṃ.**Whatever equanimous bliss has not ceased there is what belongs to the perturbable.*";
P_HTM[2578]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**Take a mendicant who, giving up pleasure and pain, enters and remains in the fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[2579]="*idaṃ kho ahaṃ, udāyi, aniñjitasmiṃ vadāmi.**This belongs to the imperturbable.*";
P_HTM[2580]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**Take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[2581]="*idaṃ kho ahaṃ, udāyi, ‘analan’ti vadāmi, ‘pajahathā’ti vadāmi, ‘samatikkamathā’ti vadāmi.**But this is not enough, I say: give it up, go beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2582]="*Ko ca tassa samatikkamo?**And what goes beyond it?*";
P_HTM[2583]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ tassa samatikkamo;**Take a mendicant who, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, enters and remains in the second absorption. That goes beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2584]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, ‘analan’ti vadāmi, ‘pajahathā’ti vadāmi, ‘samatikkamathā’ti vadāmi.**But this too is not enough, I say: give it up, go beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2585]="*Ko ca tassa samatikkamo?**And what goes beyond it?*";
P_HTM[2586]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ tassa samatikkamo;**Take a mendicant who, with the fading away of rapture, enters and remains in the third absorption. That goes beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2587]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, ‘analan’ti vadāmi, ‘pajahathā’ti vadāmi, ‘samatikkamathā’ti vadāmi.**But this too is not enough, I say: give it up, go beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2588]="*Ko ca tassa samatikkamo?**And what goes beyond it?*";
P_HTM[2589]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ tassa samatikkamo;**Take a mendicant who, giving up pleasure and pain, enters and remains in the fourth absorption. That goes beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2590]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, ‘analan’ti vadāmi, ‘pajahathā’ti vadāmi, ‘samatikkamathā’ti vadāmi.**But this too is not enough, I say: give it up, go beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2591]="*Ko ca tassa samatikkamo?**And what goes beyond it?*";
P_HTM[2592]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ tassa samatikkamo;**Take a mendicant who, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space. That goes beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2593]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, ‘analan’ti vadāmi, ‘pajahathā’ti vadāmi, ‘samatikkamathā’ti vadāmi.**But this too is not enough, I say: give it up, go beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2594]="*Ko ca tassa samatikkamo?**And what goes beyond it?*";
P_HTM[2595]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ tassa samatikkamo;**Take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness. That goes beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2596]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, ‘analan’ti vadāmi, ‘pajahathā’ti vadāmi, ‘samatikkamathā’ti vadāmi.**But this too is not enough, I say: give it up, go beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2597]="*Ko ca tassa samatikkamo?**And what goes beyond it?*";
P_HTM[2598]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ tassa samatikkamo;**Take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness. That goes beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2599]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, ‘analan’ti vadāmi, ‘pajahathā’ti vadāmi, ‘samatikkamathā’ti vadāmi.**But this too is not enough, I say: give it up, go beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2600]="*Ko ca tassa samatikkamo?**And what goes beyond it?*";
P_HTM[2601]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ tassa samatikkamo;**Take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, enters and remains in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. That goes beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2602]="*idampi kho ahaṃ, udāyi, ‘analan’ti vadāmi, ‘pajahathā’ti vadāmi, ‘samatikkamathā’ti vadāmi.**But this too is not enough, I say: give it up, go beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2603]="*Ko ca tassa samatikkamo?**And what goes beyond it?*";
P_HTM[2604]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ tassa samatikkamo;**Take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of perception and feeling. That goes beyond it.*";
P_HTM[2605]="*iti kho ahaṃ, udāyi, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanassapi pahānaṃ vadāmi.**So, Udāyī, I even recommend giving up the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[2606]="*Passasi no tvaṃ, udāyi, taṃ saṃyojanaṃ aṇuṃ vā thūlaṃ vā yassāhaṃ no pahānaṃ vadāmī”ti?**Do you see any fetter, large or small, that I don’t recommend giving up?”*";
P_HTM[2607]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”ti.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2608]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2609]="*Attamano āyasmā udāyī bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Udāyī was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2610]="*Laṭukikopamasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2611]="*67. Cātumasutta**At Cātumā*";
P_HTM[2612]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2613]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā cātumāyaṃ viharati āmalakīvane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Cātumā in a myrobalan grove.*";
P_HTM[2614]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāriputtamoggallānappamukhāni pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni cātumaṃ anuppattāni honti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**Now at that time around five hundred mendicants headed by Sāriputta and Moggallāna arrived at Cātumā to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2615]="*Te ca āgantukā bhikkhū nevāsikehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodamānā senāsanāni paññāpayamānā pattacīvarāni paṭisāmayamānā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā ahesuṃ.**And the visiting mendicants, while exchanging pleasantries with the resident mendicants, preparing their lodgings, and putting away their bowls and robes, made a dreadful racket.*";
P_HTM[2616]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[2617]="*“ke panete, ānanda, uccāsaddā mahāsaddā, kevaṭṭā maññe macchavilope”ti?**“Ānanda, who’s making that dreadful racket? You’d think it was fishermen hauling in a catch!”*";
P_HTM[2618]="*“Etāni, bhante, sāriputtamoggallānappamukhāni pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni cātumaṃ anuppattāni bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**And Ānanda told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2619]="*Te āgantukā bhikkhū nevāsikehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodamānā senāsanāni paññāpayamānā pattacīvarāni paṭisāmayamānā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2620]="*“Tenahānanda, mama vacanena te bhikkhū āmantehi:**“Well then, Ānanda, in my name tell those mendicants that*";
P_HTM[2621]="*‘satthā āyasmante āmantetī’”ti.**the teacher summons them.”*";
P_HTM[2622]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied. He went to those mendicants and said,*";
P_HTM[2623]="*“satthā āyasmante āmantetī”ti.**“Venerables, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[2624]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” replied those mendicants. Then they rose from their seats and went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them:*";
P_HTM[2625]="*“kiṃ nu tumhe, bhikkhave, uccāsaddā mahāsaddā, kevaṭṭā maññe macchavilope”ti?**“Mendicants, what’s with that dreadful racket? You’d think it was fishermen hauling in a catch!”*";
P_HTM[2626]="*“Imāni, bhante, sāriputtamoggallānappamukhāni pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni cātumaṃ anuppattāni bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**And they told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2627]="*Teme āgantukā bhikkhū nevāsikehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodamānā senāsanāni paññāpayamānā pattacīvarāni paṭisāmayamānā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2628]="*“Gacchatha, bhikkhave, paṇāmemi vo, na vo mama santike vatthabban”ti.**“Go away, mendicants, I dismiss you. You are not to stay in my presence.”*";
P_HTM[2629]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya pakkamiṃsu.**“Yes, sir,” replied those mendicants. They got up from their seats, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their right. They set their lodgings in order and left, taking their bowls and robes.*";
P_HTM[2630]="*Tena kho pana samayena cātumeyyakā sakyā santhāgāre sannipatitā honti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time the Sakyans of Cātumā were sitting together at the meeting hall on some business.*";
P_HTM[2631]="*Addasaṃsu kho cātumeyyakā sakyā te bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante;**Seeing those mendicants coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[2632]="*disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ:**they went up to them and said,*";
P_HTM[2633]="*“handa kahaṃ pana tumhe āyasmanto gacchathā”ti?**“Hello venerables, where are you going?”*";
P_HTM[2634]="*“Bhagavatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhusaṃgho paṇāmito”ti.**“Sirs, the mendicant Saṅgha has been dismissed by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[2635]="*“Tenahāyasmanto muhuttaṃ nisīdatha, appeva nāma mayaṃ sakkuṇeyyāma bhagavantaṃ pasādetun”ti.**“Well then, venerables, sit here for a minute. Hopefully we’ll be able to restore the Buddha’s confidence.”*";
P_HTM[2636]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū cātumeyyakānaṃ sakyānaṃ paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sirs,” replied the mendicants.*";
P_HTM[2637]="*Atha kho cātumeyyakā sakyā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho cātumeyyakā sakyā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then the Sakyans of Cātumā went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2638]="*“abhinandatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ;**“May the Buddha approve of the mendicant Saṅgha!*";
P_HTM[2639]="*abhivadatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ.**May the Buddha welcome the mendicant Saṅgha!*";
P_HTM[2640]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, bhagavatā pubbe bhikkhusaṃgho anuggahito; evameva bhagavā etarahi anuggaṇhātu bhikkhusaṃghaṃ.**May the Buddha support the mendicant Saṅgha now as he did in the past!*";
P_HTM[2641]="*Santettha, bhante, bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ.**There are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2642]="*Tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo.**If they don’t get to see the Buddha they may change and fall apart.*";
P_HTM[2643]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, bījānaṃ taruṇānaṃ udakaṃ alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo;**If young seedlings don’t get water they may change and fall apart.*";
P_HTM[2644]="*evameva kho, bhante, santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo.**In the same way, there are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. If they don’t get to see the Buddha they may change and fall apart.*";
P_HTM[2645]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, vacchassa taruṇassa mātaraṃ apassantassa siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo;**If a young calf doesn’t see its mother it may change and fall apart.*";
P_HTM[2646]="*evameva kho, bhante, santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ apassantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo.**In the same way, there are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. If they don’t get to see the Buddha they may change and fall apart.*";
P_HTM[2647]="*Abhinandatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ;**May the Buddha approve of the mendicant Saṅgha!*";
P_HTM[2648]="*abhivadatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ.**May the Buddha welcome the mendicant Saṅgha!*";
P_HTM[2649]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, bhagavatā pubbe bhikkhusaṃgho anuggahito; evameva bhagavā etarahi anuggaṇhātu bhikkhusaṃghan”ti.**May the Buddha support the mendicant Saṅgha now as he did in the past!”*";
P_HTM[2650]="*Atha kho brahmā sahampati bhagavato cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito bhagavato purato pāturahosi.**Then Brahmā Sahampati knew what the Buddha was thinking. As easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2651]="*Atha kho brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**He arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said:*";
P_HTM[2652]="*“abhinandatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ;**“May the Buddha approve of the mendicant Saṅgha!*";
P_HTM[2653]="*abhivadatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ.**May the Buddha welcome the mendicant Saṅgha!*";
P_HTM[2654]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, bhagavatā pubbe bhikkhusaṃgho anuggahito; evameva bhagavā etarahi anuggaṇhātu bhikkhusaṃghaṃ.**May the Buddha support the mendicant Saṅgha now as he did in the past!*";
P_HTM[2655]="*Santettha, bhante, bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo.**There are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. If they don’t get to see the Buddha they may change and fall apart.*";
P_HTM[2656]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, bījānaṃ taruṇānaṃ udakaṃ alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo;**If young seedlings don’t get water they may change and fall apart. …*";
P_HTM[2657]="*evameva kho, bhante, santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo.* **";
P_HTM[2658]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, vacchassa taruṇassa mātaraṃ apassantassa siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo;**If a young calf doesn’t see its mother it may change and fall apart.*";
P_HTM[2659]="*evameva kho, bhante, santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ apassantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo.**In the same way, there are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. If they don’t get to see the Buddha they may change and fall apart.*";
P_HTM[2660]="*Abhinandatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ;**May the Buddha approve of the mendicant Saṅgha!*";
P_HTM[2661]="*abhivadatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ.**May the Buddha welcome the mendicant Saṅgha!*";
P_HTM[2662]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, bhagavatā pubbe bhikkhusaṃgho anuggahito; evameva bhagavā etarahi anuggaṇhātu bhikkhusaṃghan”ti.**May the Buddha support the mendicant Saṅgha now as he did in the past!”*";
P_HTM[2663]="*Asakkhiṃsu kho cātumeyyakā ca sakyā brahmā ca sahampati bhagavantaṃ pasādetuṃ bījūpamena ca taruṇūpamena ca.**The Sakyans of Cātumā and Brahmā Sahampati were able to restore the Buddha’s confidence with the similes of the seedlings and the calf.*";
P_HTM[2664]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[2665]="*“uṭṭhethāvuso, gaṇhatha pattacīvaraṃ.**“Get up, reverends, and pick up your bowls and robes.*";
P_HTM[2666]="*Pasādito bhagavā cātumeyyakehi ca sakyehi brahmunā ca sahampatinā bījūpamena ca taruṇūpamena cā”ti.**The Buddha’s confidence has been restored.”*";
P_HTM[2667]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pattacīvaramādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” replied those mendicants. Then they rose from their seats and, taking their bowls and robes, went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to Venerable Sāriputta,*";
P_HTM[2668]="*“kinti te, sāriputta, ahosi mayā bhikkhusaṃghe paṇāmite”ti?**“Sāriputta, what did you think when the mendicant Saṅgha was dismissed by me?”*";
P_HTM[2669]="*“Evaṃ kho me, bhante, ahosi:**“Sir, I thought this:*";
P_HTM[2670]="*‘bhagavatā bhikkhusaṃgho paṇāmito.**‘The Buddha has dismissed the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[2671]="*Appossukko dāni bhagavā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāraṃ anuyutto viharissati, mayampi dāni appossukkā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāramanuyuttā viharissāmā’”ti.**Now he will remain passive, dwelling in blissful meditation in the present life, and so will we.’”*";
P_HTM[2672]="*“Āgamehi tvaṃ, sāriputta, āgamehi tvaṃ, sāriputta, diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāran”ti.**“Hold on, Sāriputta, hold on! Don’t you ever think such a thing again!”*";
P_HTM[2673]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha addressed Venerable Mahāmoggallāna,*";
P_HTM[2674]="*“kinti te, moggallāna, ahosi mayā bhikkhusaṃghe paṇāmite”ti?**“Moggallāna, what did you think when the mendicant Saṅgha was dismissed by me?”*";
P_HTM[2675]="*“Evaṃ kho me, bhante, ahosi:**“Sir, I thought this:*";
P_HTM[2676]="*‘bhagavatā bhikkhusaṃgho paṇāmito.**‘The Buddha has dismissed the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[2677]="*Appossukko dāni bhagavā diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāraṃ anuyutto viharissati, ahañca dāni āyasmā ca sāriputto bhikkhusaṃghaṃ pariharissāmā’”ti.**Now he will remain passive, dwelling in blissful meditation in the present life. Meanwhile, Venerable Sāriputta and I will lead the mendicant Saṅgha.’”*";
P_HTM[2678]="*“Sādhu sādhu, moggallāna.**“Good, good, Moggallāna!*";
P_HTM[2679]="*Ahaṃ vā hi, moggallāna, bhikkhusaṃghaṃ parihareyyaṃ sāriputtamoggallānā vā”ti.**For either I should lead the mendicant Saṅgha, or else Sāriputta and Moggallāna.”*";
P_HTM[2680]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2681]="*“cattārimāni, bhikkhave, bhayāni udakorohante pāṭikaṅkhitabbāni.**“Mendicants, when you go into the water you should anticipate four dangers.*";
P_HTM[2682]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2683]="*Ūmibhayaṃ, kumbhīlabhayaṃ, āvaṭṭabhayaṃ, susukābhayaṃ—**The dangers of waves, crocodiles, whirlpools, and sharks.*";
P_HTM[2684]="*imāni, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayāni udakorohante pāṭikaṅkhitabbāni.**These are the four dangers that anyone who enters the water should anticipate.*";
P_HTM[2685]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, cattārimāni bhayāni idhekacce puggale imasmiṃ dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajite pāṭikaṅkhitabbāni.**In the same way, a gentleman who goes forth from the lay life to homelessness in this teaching and training should anticipate four dangers.*";
P_HTM[2686]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[2687]="*Ūmibhayaṃ, kumbhīlabhayaṃ, āvaṭṭabhayaṃ, susukābhayaṃ.**The dangers of waves, crocodiles, whirlpools, and sharks.*";
P_HTM[2688]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, ūmibhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the danger of waves?*";
P_HTM[2689]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**It’s when a gentleman has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2690]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[2691]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2692]="*Tamenaṃ tathā pabbajitaṃ samānaṃ sabrahmacārī ovadanti, anusāsanti:**When they’ve gone forth, their spiritual companions advise and instruct them:*";
P_HTM[2693]="*‘evaṃ te abhikkamitabbaṃ, evaṃ te paṭikkamitabbaṃ, evaṃ te ālokitabbaṃ, evaṃ te vilokitabbaṃ, evaṃ te samiñjitabbaṃ, evaṃ te pasāritabbaṃ, evaṃ te saṅghāṭipattacīvaraṃ dhāretabban’ti.**‘You should go out like this, and come back like that. You should look to the front like this, and to the side like that. You should contract your limbs like this, and extend them like that. This is how you should bear your outer robe, bowl, and robes.’*";
P_HTM[2694]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[2695]="*‘mayaṃ kho pubbe agāriyabhūtā samānā aññe ovadāma, anusāsāma.**‘Formerly, as laypeople, we advised and instructed others.*";
P_HTM[2696]="*Ime panamhākaṃ puttamattā maññe, nattamattā maññe, amhe ovaditabbaṃ anusāsitabbaṃ maññantī’ti.**And now these mendicants—who you’d think were our children or grandchildren—imagine they can advise and instruct us!’*";
P_HTM[2697]="*So sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**They reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[2698]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ūmibhayassa bhīto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto.**This is called one who rejects the training and returns to a lesser life because they’re afraid of the danger of waves.*";
P_HTM[2699]="*‘Ūmibhayan’ti kho, bhikkhave, kodhupāyāsassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Danger of waves’ is a term for anger and distress.*";
P_HTM[2700]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kumbhīlabhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the danger of crocodiles?*";
P_HTM[2701]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**It’s when a gentleman has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2702]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[2703]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2704]="*Tamenaṃ tathā pabbajitaṃ samānaṃ sabrahmacārī ovadanti anusāsanti:**When they’ve gone forth, their spiritual companions advise and instruct them:*";
P_HTM[2705]="*‘idaṃ te khāditabbaṃ, idaṃ te na khāditabbaṃ; idaṃ te bhuñjitabbaṃ, idaṃ te na bhuñjitabbaṃ; idaṃ te sāyitabbaṃ, idaṃ te na sāyitabbaṃ; idaṃ te pātabbaṃ, idaṃ te na pātabbaṃ; kappiyaṃ te khāditabbaṃ, akappiyaṃ te na khāditabbaṃ; kappiyaṃ te bhuñjitabbaṃ, akappiyaṃ te na bhuñjitabbaṃ; kappiyaṃ te sāyitabbaṃ, akappiyaṃ te na sāyitabbaṃ; kappiyaṃ te pātabbaṃ, akappiyaṃ te na pātabbaṃ; kāle te khāditabbaṃ, vikāle te na khāditabbaṃ; kāle te bhuñjitabbaṃ, vikāle te na bhuñjitabbaṃ; kāle te sāyitabbaṃ, vikāle te na sāyitabbaṃ; kāle te pātabbaṃ, vikāle te na pātabban’ti.**‘You may eat, consume, taste, and drink these things, but not those. You may eat what’s allowable, but not what’s unallowable. You may eat at the right time, but not at the wrong time.’*";
P_HTM[2706]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti: ‘mayaṃ kho pubbe agāriyabhūtā samānā yaṃ icchāma taṃ khādāma, yaṃ na icchāma na taṃ khādāma; yaṃ icchāma taṃ bhuñjāma, yaṃ na icchāma na taṃ bhuñjāma; yaṃ icchāma taṃ sāyāma, yaṃ na icchāma na taṃ sāyāma; yaṃ icchāma taṃ pivāma, yaṃ na icchāma na taṃ pivāma;**They think: ‘When we were laypeople, we used to eat, consume, taste, and drink what we wanted, not what we didn’t want.*";
P_HTM[2707]="*kappiyampi khādāma, akappiyampi khādāma; kappiyampi bhuñjāma, akappiyampi bhuñjāma; kappiyampi sāyāma, akappiyampi sāyāma; kappiyampi pivāma, akappiyampi pivāma; kālepi khādāma, vikālepi khādāma; kālepi bhuñjāma vikālepi bhuñjāma; kālepi sāyāma, vikālepi sāyāma; kālepi pivāma, vikālepi pivāma.**We ate and drank both allowable and unallowable things, at the right time and the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[2708]="*Yampi no saddhā gahapatikā divā vikāle paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ denti tatthapime mukhāvaraṇaṃ maññe karontī’ti.**And these faithful householders give us a variety of delicious foods at the wrong time of day. But these mendicants imagine they can gag our mouths!’*";
P_HTM[2709]="*So sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**They reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[2710]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kumbhīlabhayassa bhīto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto.**This is called one who rejects the training and returns to a lesser life because they’re afraid of the danger of crocodiles.*";
P_HTM[2711]="*‘Kumbhīlabhayan’ti kho, bhikkhave, odarikattassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Danger of crocodiles’ is a term for gluttony.*";
P_HTM[2712]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, āvaṭṭabhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the danger of whirlpools?*";
P_HTM[2713]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**It’s when a gentleman has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2714]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[2715]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2716]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati.**When they’ve gone forth, they robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter a village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties.*";
P_HTM[2717]="*Arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi so tattha passati gahapatiṃ vā gahapatiputtaṃ vā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitaṃ samaṅgībhūtaṃ paricārayamānaṃ.**There they see a householder or their child amusing themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2718]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[2719]="*‘mayaṃ kho pubbe agāriyabhūtā samānā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā paricārimhā.**‘Formerly, as laypeople, we amused ourselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2720]="*Saṃvijjanti kho pana me kule bhogā.**And it’s true that my family is wealthy.*";
P_HTM[2721]="*Sakkā bhoge ca bhuñjituṃ puññāni ca kātun’ti.**I can both enjoy my wealth and make merit.’*";
P_HTM[2722]="*So sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**They reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[2723]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, āvaṭṭabhayassa bhīto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto.**This is called one who rejects the training and returns to a lesser life because they’re afraid of the danger of whirlpools.*";
P_HTM[2724]="*‘Āvaṭṭabhayan’ti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Danger of whirlpools’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[2725]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, susukābhayaṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the danger of sharks?*";
P_HTM[2726]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco kulaputto saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti:**It’s when a gentleman has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2727]="*‘otiṇṇomhi jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;**‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[2728]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethā’ti.**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2729]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati.**When they’ve gone forth, they robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter a village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties.*";
P_HTM[2730]="*Arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi so tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā.**There they see a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes.*";
P_HTM[2731]="*Tassa mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti.**Lust infects their mind,*";
P_HTM[2732]="*So rāgānuddhaṃsena cittena sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**so they reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[2733]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, susukābhayassa bhīto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto.**This is called one who rejects the training and returns to a lesser life because they’re afraid of the danger of sharks.*";
P_HTM[2734]="*‘Susukābhayan’ti kho, bhikkhave, mātugāmassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Danger of sharks’ is a term for females.*";
P_HTM[2735]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri bhayāni, idhekacce puggale imasmiṃ dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajite pāṭikaṅkhitabbānī”ti.**These are the four dangers that a gentleman who goes forth from the lay life to homelessness in this teaching and training should anticipate.”*";
P_HTM[2736]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2737]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2738]="*Cātumasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2739]="*68. Naḷakapānasutta**At Naḷakapāna*";
P_HTM[2740]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2741]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu viharati naḷakapāne palāsavane.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Kosalans near Naḷakapāna in the Parrot Tree grove.*";
P_HTM[2742]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā kulaputtā bhagavantaṃ uddissa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā honti—**Now at that time several very well-known gentlemen had gone forth from the lay life to homelessness out of faith in the Buddha—*";
P_HTM[2743]="*āyasmā ca anuruddho, āyasmā ca bhaddiyo, āyasmā ca kimilo, āyasmā ca bhagu, āyasmā ca koṇḍañño, āyasmā ca revato, āyasmā ca ānando, aññe ca abhiññātā abhiññātā kulaputtā.**The venerables Anuruddha, Bhaddiya, Kimbila, Bhagu, Koṇḍañña, Revata, Ānanda, and other very well-known gentlemen.*";
P_HTM[2744]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaparivuto abbhokāse nisinno hoti.**Now at that time the Buddha was sitting in the open, surrounded by the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[2745]="*Atha kho bhagavā te kulaputte ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about those gentlemen:*";
P_HTM[2746]="*“ye te, bhikkhave, kulaputtā mamaṃ uddissa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, kacci te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū abhiratā brahmacariye”ti?**“Mendicants, those gentlemen who have gone forth from the lay life to homelessness out of faith in me—I trust they’re satisfied with the spiritual life?”*";
P_HTM[2747]="*Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**When this was said, the mendicants kept silent.*";
P_HTM[2748]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā te kulaputte ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:**For a second and a third time the Buddha asked the same question.*";
P_HTM[2749]="*“ye te, bhikkhave, kulaputtā mamaṃ uddissa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, kacci te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū abhiratā brahmacariye”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2750]="*Dutiyampi kho te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2751]="*Tatiyampi kho bhagavā te kulaputte ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:* **";
P_HTM[2752]="*“ye te, bhikkhave, kulaputtā mamaṃ uddissa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, kacci te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū abhiratā brahmacariye”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2753]="*Tatiyampi kho te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**For a third time, the mendicants kept silent.*";
P_HTM[2754]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then it occurred to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[2755]="*“yannūnāhaṃ te kulaputte puccheyyan”ti.**“Why don’t I question just those gentlemen?”*";
P_HTM[2756]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to Venerable Anuruddha,*";
P_HTM[2757]="*“kacci tumhe, anuruddhā, abhiratā brahmacariye”ti?**“Anuruddha and friends, I hope you’re satisfied with the spiritual life?”*";
P_HTM[2758]="*“Taggha mayaṃ, bhante, abhiratā brahmacariye”ti.**“Indeed, sir, we are satisfied with the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[2759]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good, Anuruddha and friends!*";
P_HTM[2760]="*Etaṃ kho, anuruddhā, tumhākaṃ patirūpaṃ kulaputtānaṃ saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitānaṃ yaṃ tumhe abhirameyyātha brahmacariye.**It’s appropriate for gentlemen like yourselves, who have gone forth in faith from the lay life to homelessness, to be satisfied with the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[2761]="*Yena tumhe, anuruddhā, bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā susukāḷakesā kāme paribhuñjeyyātha tena tumhe, anuruddhā, bhadrenapi yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā susukāḷakesā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā.**Since you’re blessed with youth, in the prime of life, black-haired, you could have enjoyed sensual pleasures; yet you have gone forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[2762]="*Te ca kho pana tumhe, anuruddhā, neva rājābhinītā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, na corābhinītā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, na iṇaṭṭā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, na bhayaṭṭā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, nājīvikāpakatā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā.**But you didn’t go forth because you were forced to by kings or bandits, or because you’re in debt or threatened, or to earn a living.*";
P_HTM[2763]="*Api ca khomhi otiṇṇo jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, dukkhotiṇṇo dukkhapareto;**Rather, didn’t you go forth thinking: ‘I’m swamped by rebirth, old age, and death; by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. I’m swamped by suffering, mired in suffering.*";
P_HTM[2764]="*appeva nāma imassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa antakiriyā paññāyethāti—**Hopefully I can find an end to this entire mass of suffering’?”*";
P_HTM[2765]="*nanu tumhe, anuruddhā, evaṃ saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2766]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2767]="*“Evaṃ pabbajitena ca pana, anuruddhā, kulaputtena kimassa karaṇīyaṃ?**“But, Anuruddha and friends, when a gentleman has gone forth like this, what should they do?*";
P_HTM[2768]="*Vivekaṃ, anuruddhā, kāmehi vivekaṃ akusalehi dhammehi pītisukhaṃ nādhigacchati aññaṃ vā tato santataraṃ, tassa abhijjhāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, byāpādopi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, thinamiddhampi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati uddhaccakukkuccampi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, vicikicchāpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, aratīpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, tandīpi cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**Take someone who doesn’t achieve the rapture and bliss that are secluded from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities, or something even more peaceful than that. Their mind is still occupied by desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, doubt, discontent, and sloth.*";
P_HTM[2769]="*Vivekaṃ, anuruddhā, kāmehi vivekaṃ akusalehi dhammehi pītisukhaṃ nādhigacchati aññaṃ vā tato santataraṃ.**That’s someone who doesn’t achieve the rapture and bliss that are secluded from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities, or something even more peaceful than that.*";
P_HTM[2770]="*Vivekaṃ, anuruddhā, kāmehi vivekaṃ akusalehi dhammehi pītisukhaṃ adhigacchati aññaṃ vā tato santataraṃ, tassa abhijjhāpi cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, byāpādopi cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, thinamiddhampi cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, uddhaccakukkuccampi cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, vicikicchāpi cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, aratīpi cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati, tandīpi cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**Take someone who does achieve the rapture and bliss that are secluded from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities, or something even more peaceful than that. Their mind is not occupied by desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, doubt, discontent, and sloth.*";
P_HTM[2771]="*Vivekaṃ, anuruddhā, kāmehi vivekaṃ akusalehi dhammehi pītisukhaṃ adhigacchati aññaṃ vā tato santataraṃ.**That’s someone who does achieve the rapture and bliss that are secluded from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities, or something even more peaceful than that.*";
P_HTM[2772]="*Kinti vo, anuruddhā, mayi hoti:**Is this what you think of me?*";
P_HTM[2773]="*‘ye āsavā saṃkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā, appahīnā te tathāgatassa;**‘The Realized One has not given up the defilements, the corruptions that lead to future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[2774]="*tasmā tathāgato saṅkhāyekaṃ paṭisevati, saṅkhāyekaṃ adhivāseti, saṅkhāyekaṃ parivajjeti, saṅkhāyekaṃ vinodetī’”ti?**That’s why, after reflection, he uses some things, endures some things, avoids some things, and gets rid of some things.’”*";
P_HTM[2775]="*“Na kho no, bhante, bhagavati evaṃ hoti:**“No sir, we don’t think of you that way.*";
P_HTM[2776]="*‘ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā, appahīnā te tathāgatassa;* **";
P_HTM[2777]="*tasmā tathāgato saṅkhāyekaṃ paṭisevati, saṅkhāyekaṃ adhivāseti, saṅkhāyekaṃ parivajjeti, saṅkhāyekaṃ vinodetī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2778]="*Evaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavati hoti:**We think of you this way:*";
P_HTM[2779]="*‘ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā, pahīnā te tathāgatassa;**‘The Realized One has given up the defilements, the corruptions that lead to future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[2780]="*tasmā tathāgato saṅkhāyekaṃ paṭisevati, saṅkhāyekaṃ adhivāseti, saṅkhāyekaṃ parivajjeti, saṅkhāyekaṃ vinodetī’”ti.**That’s why, after reflection, he uses some things, endures some things, avoids some things, and gets rid of some things.’”*";
P_HTM[2781]="*“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddhā.**“Good, good, Anuruddha and friends!*";
P_HTM[2782]="*Tathāgatassa, anuruddhā, ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā, pahīnā te ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**The Realized One has given up the defilements, the corruptions that lead to future lives and are hurtful, resulting in suffering and future rebirth, old age, and death. He has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them so they are unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[2783]="*Seyyathāpi, anuruddhā, tālo matthakacchinno abhabbo punavirūḷhiyā;**Just as a palm tree with its crown cut off is incapable of further growth,*";
P_HTM[2784]="*evameva kho, anuruddhā, tathāgatassa ye āsavā saṅkilesikā ponobbhavikā sadarā dukkhavipākā āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇiyā, pahīnā te ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā;**in the same way, the Realized One has given up the defilements so they are unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[2785]="*tasmā tathāgato saṅkhāyekaṃ paṭisevati, saṅkhāyekaṃ adhivāseti, saṅkhāyekaṃ parivajjeti, saṅkhāyekaṃ vinodeti.**That’s why, after reflection, he uses some things, endures some things, avoids some things, and gets rid of some things.*";
P_HTM[2786]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anuruddhā,**What do you think, Anuruddha and friends?*";
P_HTM[2787]="*kaṃ atthavasaṃ sampassamāno tathāgato sāvake abbhatīte kālaṅkate upapattīsu byākaroti:**What advantage does the Realized One see in declaring the rebirth of his disciples who have passed away:*";
P_HTM[2788]="*‘asu amutra upapanno; asu amutra upapanno’”ti?**‘This one is reborn here, while that one is reborn there’?”*";
P_HTM[2789]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā bhagavaṃnettikā bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. Sādhu vata, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[2790]="*“Na kho, anuruddhā, tathāgato janakuhanatthaṃ na janalapanatthaṃ na lābhasakkārasilokānisaṃsatthaṃ na ‘iti maṃ jano jānātū’ti sāvake abbhatīte kālaṅkate upapattīsu byākaroti:**“The Realized One does not declare such things for the sake of deceiving people or flattering them, nor for the benefit of possessions, honor, or popularity, nor thinking, ‘So let people know about me!’*";
P_HTM[2791]="*‘asu amutra upapanno, asu amutra upapanno’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2792]="*Santi ca kho, anuruddhā, kulaputtā saddhā uḷāravedā uḷārapāmojjā.**Rather, there are gentlemen of faith who are full of sublime joy and gladness.*";
P_HTM[2793]="*Te taṃ sutvā tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharanti.**When they hear that, they apply their minds to that end.*";
P_HTM[2794]="*Tesaṃ taṃ, anuruddhā, hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**That is for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[2795]="*Idhānuruddhā, bhikkhu suṇāti:**Take a monk who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2796]="*‘itthannāmo bhikkhu kālaṅkato;**‘The monk named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2797]="*so bhagavatā byākato—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2798]="*aññāya saṇṭhahī’ti.**he was enlightened.’*";
P_HTM[2799]="*So kho panassa āyasmā sāmaṃ diṭṭho vā hoti anussavassuto vā:**And he’s either seen for himself, or heard from someone else, that that venerable*";
P_HTM[2800]="*‘evaṃsīlo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃpañño so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃvihārī so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃvimutto so āyasmā ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2801]="*So tassa saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussaranto tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that monk’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, he applies his mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2802]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, bhikkhuno phāsuvihāro hoti.**That’s how a monk lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2803]="*Idhānuruddhā, bhikkhu suṇāti:**Take a monk who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2804]="*‘itthannāmo bhikkhu kālaṅkato;**‘The monk named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2805]="*so bhagavatā byākato—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2806]="*pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā’ti.**with the ending of the five lower fetters, he’s been reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.’*";
P_HTM[2807]="*So kho panassa āyasmā sāmaṃ diṭṭho vā hoti anussavassuto vā:**And he’s either seen for himself, or heard from someone else, that that venerable*";
P_HTM[2808]="*‘evaṃsīlo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammo … pe … evaṃpañño … evaṃvihārī … evaṃvimutto so āyasmā ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2809]="*So tassa saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussaranto tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that monk’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, he applies his mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2810]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, bhikkhuno phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a monk lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2811]="*Idhānuruddhā, bhikkhu suṇāti:**Take a monk who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2812]="*‘itthannāmo bhikkhu kālaṅkato;**‘The monk named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2813]="*so bhagavatā byākato—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2814]="*tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissatī’ti.**with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, he’s a once-returner. He’ll come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2815]="*So kho panassa āyasmā sāmaṃ diṭṭho vā hoti anussavassuto vā:**And he’s either seen for himself, or heard from someone else, that that venerable*";
P_HTM[2816]="*‘evaṃsīlo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammo … pe … evaṃpañño … evaṃvihārī … evaṃvimutto so āyasmā ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2817]="*So tassa saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussaranto tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that monk’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, he applies his mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2818]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, bhikkhuno phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a monk lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2819]="*Idhānuruddhā, bhikkhu suṇāti:**Take a monk who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2820]="*‘itthannāmo bhikkhu kālaṅkato;**‘The monk named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2821]="*so bhagavatā byākato—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2822]="*tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti.**with the ending of three fetters he’s a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[2823]="*So kho panassa āyasmā sāmaṃ diṭṭho vā hoti anussavassuto vā:**And he’s either seen for himself, or heard from someone else, that that venerable*";
P_HTM[2824]="*‘evaṃsīlo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammo … pe … evaṃpañño … evaṃvihārī … evaṃvimutto so āyasmā ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2825]="*So tassa saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussaranto tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that monk’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, he applies his mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2826]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, bhikkhuno phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a monk lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2827]="*Idhānuruddhā, bhikkhunī suṇāti:**Take a nun who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2828]="*‘itthannāmā bhikkhunī kālaṅkatā;**‘The nun named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2829]="*sā bhagavatā byākatā—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2830]="*aññāya saṇṭhahī’ti.**she was enlightened.’*";
P_HTM[2831]="*Sā kho panassā bhaginī sāmaṃ diṭṭhā vā hoti anussavassutā vā:**And she’s either seen for herself, or heard from someone else, that that sister*";
P_HTM[2832]="*‘evaṃsīlā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃpaññā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃvihārinī sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃvimuttā sā bhaginī ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2833]="*Sā tassā saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarantī tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that nun’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, she applies her mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2834]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, bhikkhuniyā phāsuvihāro hoti.**That’s how a nun lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2835]="*Idhānuruddhā, bhikkhunī suṇāti:**Take a nun who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2836]="*‘itthannāmā bhikkhunī kālaṅkatā;**‘The nun named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2837]="*sā bhagavatā byākatā—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2838]="*pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyinī anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā’ti.**with the ending of the five lower fetters, she’s been reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.’*";
P_HTM[2839]="*Sā kho panassā bhaginī sāmaṃ diṭṭhā vā hoti anussavassutā vā:**And she’s either seen for herself, or heard from someone else, that that sister*";
P_HTM[2840]="*‘evaṃsīlā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammā … pe … evaṃpaññā … evaṃvihārinī … evaṃvimuttā sā bhaginī ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2841]="*Sā tassā saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarantī tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that nun’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, she applies her mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2842]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, bhikkhuniyā phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a nun lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2843]="*Idhānuruddhā, bhikkhunī suṇāti:**Take a nun who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2844]="*‘itthannāmā bhikkhunī kālaṅkatā;**‘The nun named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2845]="*sā bhagavatā byākatā—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2846]="*tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāminī sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissatī’ti.**with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, she’s a once-returner. She’ll come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2847]="*Sā kho panassā bhaginī sāmaṃ diṭṭhā vā hoti anussavassutā vā:**And she’s either seen for herself, or heard from someone else, that that sister*";
P_HTM[2848]="*‘evaṃsīlā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammā … pe … evaṃpaññā … evaṃvihārinī … evaṃvimuttā sā bhaginī ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2849]="*Sā tassā saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarantī tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that nun’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, she applies her mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2850]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, bhikkhuniyā phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a nun lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2851]="*Idhānuruddhā, bhikkhunī suṇāti:**Take a nun who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2852]="*‘itthannāmā bhikkhunī kālaṅkatā;**‘The nun named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2853]="*sā bhagavatā byākatā—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2854]="*tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā’ti.**with the ending of three fetters she’s a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[2855]="*Sā kho panassā bhaginī sāmaṃ diṭṭhā vā hoti anussavassutā vā:**And she’s either seen for herself, or heard from someone else, that that sister*";
P_HTM[2856]="*‘evaṃsīlā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammā … evaṃpaññā … evaṃvihārinī … evaṃvimuttā sā bhaginī ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2857]="*Sā tassā saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarantī tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that nun’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, she applies her mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2858]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, bhikkhuniyā phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a nun lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2859]="*Idhānuruddhā, upāsako suṇāti:**Take a layman who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2860]="*‘itthannāmo upāsako kālaṅkato;**‘The layman named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2861]="*so bhagavatā byākato—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2862]="*pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā’ti.**with the ending of the five lower fetters, he’s been reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.’*";
P_HTM[2863]="*So kho panassa āyasmā sāmaṃ diṭṭho vā hoti anussavassuto vā:**And he’s either seen for himself, or heard from someone else, that that venerable*";
P_HTM[2864]="*‘evaṃsīlo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃpañño so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃvihārī so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃvimutto so āyasmā ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2865]="*So tassa saddhañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussaranto tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that layman’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, he applies his mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2866]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, upāsakassa phāsuvihāro hoti.**That’s how a layman lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2867]="*Idhānuruddhā, upāsako suṇāti:**Take a layman who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2868]="*‘itthannāmo upāsako kālaṅkato;**‘The layman named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2869]="*so bhagavatā byākato—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2870]="*tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissatī’ti.**with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, he’s a once-returner. He’ll come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2871]="*So kho panassa āyasmā sāmaṃ diṭṭho vā hoti anussavassuto vā:**And he’s either seen for himself, or heard from someone else, that that venerable*";
P_HTM[2872]="*‘evaṃsīlo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammo … evaṃpañño … evaṃvihārī … evaṃvimutto so āyasmā ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2873]="*So tassa saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussaranto tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that layman’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, he applies his mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2874]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, upāsakassa phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a layman lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2875]="*Idhānuruddhā, upāsako suṇāti:**Take a layman who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2876]="*‘itthannāmo upāsako kālaṅkato;**‘The layman named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2877]="*so bhagavatā byākato—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2878]="*tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti.**with the ending of three fetters he’s a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[2879]="*So kho panassa āyasmā sāmaṃ diṭṭho vā hoti anussavassuto vā:**And he’s either seen for himself, or heard from someone else, that that venerable*";
P_HTM[2880]="*‘evaṃsīlo so āyasmā ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammo … evaṃpañño … evaṃvihārī … evaṃvimutto so āyasmā ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2881]="*So tassa saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussaranto tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that layman’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, he applies his mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2882]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā upāsakassa phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a layman lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2883]="*Idhānuruddhā, upāsikā suṇāti:**Take a laywoman who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2884]="*‘itthannāmā upāsikā kālaṅkatā;**‘The laywoman named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2885]="*sā bhagavatā byākatā—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2886]="*pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyinī anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā’ti.**with the ending of the five lower fetters, she’s been reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.’*";
P_HTM[2887]="*Sā kho panassā bhaginī sāmaṃ diṭṭhā vā hoti anussavassutā vā:**And she’s either seen for herself, or heard from someone else, that that sister*";
P_HTM[2888]="*‘evaṃsīlā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammā … evaṃpaññā … evaṃvihārinī … evaṃvimuttā sā bhaginī ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2889]="*Sā tassā saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarantī tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that laywoman’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, she applies her mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2890]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, upāsikāya phāsuvihāro hoti.**That’s how a laywoman lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2891]="*Idhānuruddhā, upāsikā suṇāti:**Take a laywoman who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2892]="*‘itthannāmā upāsikā kālaṅkatā;**‘The laywoman named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2893]="*sā bhagavatā byākatā—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2894]="*tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāminī sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissatī’ti.**with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, she’s a once-returner. She’ll come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[2895]="*Sā kho panassā bhaginī sāmaṃ diṭṭhā vā hoti anussavassutā vā:**And she’s either seen for herself, or heard from someone else, that that sister*";
P_HTM[2896]="*‘evaṃsīlā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammā … evaṃpaññā … evaṃvihārinī … evaṃvimuttā sā bhaginī ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2897]="*Sā tassā saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarantī tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that laywoman’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, she applies her mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2898]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, upāsikāya phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a laywoman lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2899]="*Idhānuruddhā, upāsikā suṇāti:**Take a laywoman who hears this:*";
P_HTM[2900]="*‘itthannāmā upāsikā kālaṅkatā;**‘The laywoman named so-and-so has passed away.*";
P_HTM[2901]="*sā bhagavatā byākatā—**The Buddha has declared that,*";
P_HTM[2902]="*tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā’ti.**with the ending of three fetters she’s a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[2903]="*Sā kho panassā bhaginī sāmaṃ diṭṭhā vā hoti anussavassutā vā:**And she’s either seen for herself, or heard from someone else, that that sister*";
P_HTM[2904]="*‘evaṃsīlā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃdhammā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃpaññā sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃvihārinī sā bhaginī ahosi itipi, evaṃvimuttā sā bhaginī ahosi itipī’ti.**had such ethics, such qualities, such wisdom, such meditation, or such freedom.*";
P_HTM[2905]="*Sā tassā saddhañca sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarantī tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati.**Recollecting that laywoman’s faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom, she applies her mind to that end.*";
P_HTM[2906]="*Evampi kho, anuruddhā, upāsikāya phāsuvihāro hoti.**That too is how a laywoman lives at ease.*";
P_HTM[2907]="*Iti kho, anuruddhā, tathāgato na janakuhanatthaṃ na janalapanatthaṃ na lābhasakkārasilokānisaṃsatthaṃ na ‘iti maṃ jano jānātū’ti sāvake abbhatīte kālaṅkate upapattīsu byākaroti:**So it’s not for the sake of deceiving people or flattering them, nor for the benefit of possessions, honor, or popularity, nor thinking, ‘So let people know about me!’ that the Realized One declares the rebirth of his disciples who have passed away:*";
P_HTM[2908]="*‘asu amutra upapanno, asu amutra upapanno’ti.**‘This one is reborn here, while that one is reborn there.’*";
P_HTM[2909]="*Santi ca kho, anuruddhā, kulaputtā saddhā uḷāravedā uḷārapāmojjā.**Rather, there are gentlemen of faith who are full of joy and gladness.*";
P_HTM[2910]="*Te taṃ sutvā tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharanti.**When they hear that, they apply their minds to that end.*";
P_HTM[2911]="*Tesaṃ taṃ, anuruddhā, hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**That is for their lasting welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[2912]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2913]="*Attamano āyasmā anuruddho bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Anuruddha and friends were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2914]="*Naḷakapānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2915]="*69. Goliyānisutta**With Gulissāni*";
P_HTM[2916]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2917]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[2918]="*Tena kho pana samayena goliyāni nāma bhikkhu āraññiko padasamācāro saṃghamajjhe osaṭo hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time a wilderness mendicant of lax behavior named Gulissāni had come down to the midst of the Saṅgha on some business.*";
P_HTM[2919]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto goliyāniṃ bhikkhuṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Venerable Sāriputta spoke to the mendicants about Gulissāni:*";
P_HTM[2920]="*“Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena sabrahmacārīsu sagāravena bhavitabbaṃ sappatissena.**“Reverends, a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha should have respect and reverence for his spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[2921]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu saṃghagato saṃghe viharanto sabrahmacārīsu agāravo hoti appatisso, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he doesn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2922]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena, yo ayamāyasmā sabrahmacārīsu agāravo hoti appatisso’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he has no respect and reverence for his spiritual companions?’*";
P_HTM[2923]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2924]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena sabrahmacārīsu sagāravena bhavitabbaṃ sappatissena. (1)**That’s why a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha should have respect and reverence for his spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[2925]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena āsanakusalena bhavitabbaṃ:**A wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha should be careful where he sits, thinking:*";
P_HTM[2926]="*‘iti there ca bhikkhū nānupakhajja nisīdissāmi nave ca bhikkhū na āsanena paṭibāhissāmī’ti.**‘I shall sit so that I don’t intrude on the senior monks and I don’t block the junior monks from a seat.’*";
P_HTM[2927]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu saṃghagato saṃghe viharanto na āsanakusalo hoti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he doesn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2928]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena, yo ayamāyasmā āsanakusalo na hotī’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he’s not careful where he sits?’*";
P_HTM[2929]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2930]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena āsanakusalena bhavitabbaṃ. (2)**That’s why a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha should be careful where he sits.*";
P_HTM[2931]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena ābhisamācārikopi dhammo jānitabbo.**A wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha should know even the supplementary regulations.*";
P_HTM[2932]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu saṃghagato saṃghe viharanto ābhisamācārikampi dhammaṃ na jānāti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he doesn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2933]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā ābhisamācārikampi dhammaṃ na jānātī’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he doesn’t even know the supplementary regulations?’*";
P_HTM[2934]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2935]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena ābhisamācārikopi dhammo jānitabbo. (3)**That’s why a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha should know even the supplementary regulations.*";
P_HTM[2936]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena nātikālena gāmo pavisitabbo nātidivā paṭikkamitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha shouldn’t enter the village too early or return too late in the day.*";
P_HTM[2937]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu saṃghagato saṃghe viharanto atikālena gāmaṃ pavisati atidivā paṭikkamati, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he does so, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2938]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā atikālena gāmaṃ pavisati atidivā paṭikkamatī’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he enters the village too early or returns too late in the day?’*";
P_HTM[2939]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2940]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena nātikālena gāmo pavisitabbo, nātidivā paṭikkamitabbaṃ. (4)**That’s why a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha shouldn’t enter the village too early or return too late in the day.*";
P_HTM[2941]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā saṅghagatena saṅghe viharantena na purebhattaṃ pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha shouldn’t socialize with families before or after the meal.*";
P_HTM[2942]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu saṅghagato saṅghe viharanto purebhattaṃ pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he does so, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2943]="*‘Ayaṃ nūnimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena viharato vikālacariyā bahulīkatā, tamenaṃ saṅghagatampi samudācaratī’ti—**‘This wilderness venerable, staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, must be used to wandering about at the wrong time, since he behaves like this when he’s come to the Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[2944]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2945]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā saṅghagatena saṅghe viharantena na purebhattaṃ pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjitabbaṃ. (5)**That’s why a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha shouldn’t socialize with families before or after the meal.*";
P_HTM[2946]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā saṅghagatena saṅghe viharantena anuddhatena bhavitabbaṃ acapalena.**A wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha shouldn’t be restless and fickle.*";
P_HTM[2947]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu saṅghagato saṅghe viharanto uddhato hoti capalo, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he is, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2948]="*‘Idaṃ nūnimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena viharato uddhaccaṃ cāpalyaṃ bahulīkataṃ, tamenaṃ saṅghagatampi samudācaratī’ti—**‘This wilderness venerable, staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, must be used to being restless and fickle, since he behaves like this when he’s come to the Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[2949]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2950]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā saṅghagatena saṅghe viharantena anuddhatena bhavitabbaṃ acapalena. (6)**That’s why a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha shouldn’t be restless and fickle.*";
P_HTM[2951]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā saṅghagatena saṅghe viharantena amukharena bhavitabbaṃ avikiṇṇavācena.**A wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha shouldn’t be gossipy and loose-tongued.*";
P_HTM[2952]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu saṅghagato saṅghe viharanto mukharo hoti vikiṇṇavāco, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he is, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2953]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā mukharo vikiṇṇavāco’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he’s gossipy and loose-tongued?’*";
P_HTM[2954]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2955]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā saṅghagatena saṅghe viharantena amukharena bhavitabbaṃ avikiṇṇavācena. (7)**That’s why a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha shouldn’t be gossipy and loose-tongued.*";
P_HTM[2956]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena suvacena bhavitabbaṃ kalyāṇamittena.**A wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha should be easy to admonish, with good friends.*";
P_HTM[2957]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu saṃghagato saṃghe viharanto dubbaco hoti pāpamitto, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he’s hard to admonish, with bad friends, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2958]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā dubbaco pāpamitto’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he’s hard to admonish, with bad friends?’*";
P_HTM[2959]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2960]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā saṃghagatena saṃghe viharantena suvacena bhavitabbaṃ kalyāṇamittena. (8)**That’s why a wilderness monk who has come to stay in the Saṅgha should be easy to admonish, with good friends.*";
P_HTM[2961]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā indriyesu guttadvārena bhavitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk should guard the sense doors.*";
P_HTM[2962]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu indriyesu aguttadvāro hoti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he doesn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2963]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā indriyesu aguttadvāro’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he doesn’t guard the sense doors?’*";
P_HTM[2964]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2965]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā indriyesu guttadvārena bhavitabbaṃ. (9)**That’s why a wilderness monk should guard the sense doors.*";
P_HTM[2966]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā bhojane mattaññunā bhavitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk should eat in moderation.*";
P_HTM[2967]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu bhojane amattaññū hoti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he doesn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2968]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā bhojane amattaññū’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he eats too much?’*";
P_HTM[2969]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2970]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā bhojane mattaññunā bhavitabbaṃ. (10)**That’s why a wilderness monk should eat in moderation.*";
P_HTM[2971]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā jāgariyaṃ anuyuttena bhavitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk should be committed to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[2972]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu jāgariyaṃ ananuyutto hoti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he isn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2973]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā jāgariyaṃ ananuyutto’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he’s not committed to wakefulness?’*";
P_HTM[2974]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2975]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā jāgariyaṃ anuyuttena bhavitabbaṃ. (11)**That’s why a wilderness monk should be committed to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[2976]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā āraddhavīriyena bhavitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk should be energetic.*";
P_HTM[2977]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu kusīto hoti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he isn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2978]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā kusīto’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he’s not energetic?’*";
P_HTM[2979]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2980]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā āraddhavīriyena bhavitabbaṃ. (12)**That’s why a wilderness monk should be energetic.*";
P_HTM[2981]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā upaṭṭhitassatinā bhavitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk should be mindful.*";
P_HTM[2982]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu muṭṭhassatī hoti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he isn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2983]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā muṭṭhassatī’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he’s not mindful?’*";
P_HTM[2984]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2985]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā upaṭṭhitassatinā bhavitabbaṃ. (13)**That’s why a wilderness monk should be mindful.*";
P_HTM[2986]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā samāhitena bhavitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk should have immersion.*";
P_HTM[2987]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu asamāhito hoti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he doesn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2988]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā asamāhito’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he doesn’t have immersion?’*";
P_HTM[2989]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2990]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā samāhitena bhavitabbaṃ. (14)**That’s why a wilderness monk should have immersion.*";
P_HTM[2991]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā paññavatā bhavitabbaṃ.**A wilderness monk should be wise.*";
P_HTM[2992]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu duppañño hoti, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he isn’t, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2993]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā duppañño’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he’s not wise?’*";
P_HTM[2994]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[2995]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā paññavatā bhavitabbaṃ. (15)**That’s why a wilderness monk should be wise.*";
P_HTM[2996]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā abhidhamme abhivinaye yogo karaṇīyo.**A wilderness monk should make an effort to learn the teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2997]="*Santāvuso, āraññikaṃ bhikkhuṃ abhidhamme abhivinaye pañhaṃ pucchitāro.**There are those who will question a wilderness monk about the teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2998]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu abhidhamme abhivinaye pañhaṃ puṭṭho na sampāyati, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he fails to answer, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[2999]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā abhidhamme abhivinaye pañhaṃ puṭṭho na sampāyatī’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he can’t answer a question about the teaching and training?’*";
P_HTM[3000]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[3001]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā abhidhamme abhivinaye yogo karaṇīyo. (16)**That’s why a wilderness monk should make an effort to learn the teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[3002]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā tattha yogo karaṇīyo.**A wilderness monk should practice meditation to realize the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form.*";
P_HTM[3003]="*Santāvuso, āraññikaṃ bhikkhuṃ ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā tattha pañhaṃ pucchitāro.**There are those who will question a wilderness monk regarding the formless liberations.*";
P_HTM[3004]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho na sampāyati, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he fails to answer, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[3005]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho na sampāyatī’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he can’t answer a question about the formless liberations?’*";
P_HTM[3006]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[3007]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā tattha yogo karaṇīyo. (17)**That’s why a wilderness monk should practice meditation to realize the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form.*";
P_HTM[3008]="*Āraññikenāvuso, bhikkhunā uttari manussadhamme yogo karaṇīyo.**A wilderness monk should practice meditation to realize the superhuman state.*";
P_HTM[3009]="*Santāvuso, āraññikaṃ bhikkhuṃ uttari manussadhamme pañhaṃ pucchitāro.**There are those who will question a wilderness monk about the superhuman state.*";
P_HTM[3010]="*Sace, āvuso, āraññiko bhikkhu uttari manussadhamme pañhaṃ puṭṭho na sampāyati, tassa bhavanti vattāro.**If he fails to answer, there’ll be some who say:*";
P_HTM[3011]="*‘Kiṃ panimassāyasmato āraññikassa ekassāraññe serivihārena yo ayamāyasmā yassatthāya pabbajito tamatthaṃ na jānātī’ti—**‘What’s the point of this wilderness venerable’s staying alone and autonomous in the wilderness, since he doesn’t know the goal for which he went forth?’*";
P_HTM[3012]="*tassa bhavanti vattāro.* **";
P_HTM[3013]="*Tasmā āraññikena bhikkhunā uttari manussadhamme yogo karaṇīyo”ti. (18)**That’s why a wilderness monk should practice meditation to realize the superhuman state.”*";
P_HTM[3014]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When Venerable Sāriputta said this, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said to him,*";
P_HTM[3015]="*“āraññikeneva nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhunā ime dhammā samādāya vattitabbā udāhu gāmantavihārināpī”ti?**“Reverend Sāriputta, should these things be undertaken and followed only by wilderness monks, or by those who live in the neighborhood of a village as well?”*";
P_HTM[3016]="*“Āraññikenāpi kho, āvuso moggallāna, bhikkhunā ime dhammā samādāya vattitabbā pageva gāmantavihārinā”ti.**“Reverend Moggallāna, these things should be undertaken and followed by wilderness monks, and still more by those who live in the neighborhood of a village.”*";
P_HTM[3017]="*Goliyānisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3018]="*70. Kīṭāgirisutta**At Kīṭāgiri*";
P_HTM[3019]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3020]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kāsīsu cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kāsīs together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[3021]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3022]="*“ahaṃ kho, bhikkhave, aññatreva rattibhojanā bhuñjāmi.**“Mendicants, I abstain from eating at night.*";
P_HTM[3023]="*Aññatra kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, rattibhojanā bhuñjamāno appābādhatañca sañjānāmi appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.**Doing so, I find that I’m healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[3024]="*Etha, tumhepi, bhikkhave, aññatreva rattibhojanā bhuñjatha.**You too should abstain from eating at night.*";
P_HTM[3025]="*Aññatra kho pana, bhikkhave, tumhepi rattibhojanā bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānissatha appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañcā”ti.**Doing so, you’ll find that you’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.”*";
P_HTM[3026]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3027]="*Atha kho bhagavā kāsīsu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena kīṭāgiri nāma kāsīnaṃ nigamo tadavasari.**Then the Buddha, traveling stage by stage in the land of the Kāsīs, arrived at a town of the Kāsīs named Kīṭāgiri,*";
P_HTM[3028]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā kīṭāgirismiṃ viharati kāsīnaṃ nigame.**and stayed there.*";
P_HTM[3029]="*Tena kho pana samayena assajipunabbasukā nāma bhikkhū kīṭāgirismiṃ āvāsikā honti.**Now at that time the mendicants who followed Assaji and Punabbasuka were residing at Kīṭāgiri.*";
P_HTM[3030]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to them and said,*";
P_HTM[3031]="*“bhagavā kho, āvuso, aññatreva rattibhojanā bhuñjati bhikkhusaṅgho ca.**“Reverends, the Buddha abstains from eating at night, and so does the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3032]="*Aññatra kho panāvuso, rattibhojanā bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānanti appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.**Doing so, they find that they’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[3033]="*Etha, tumhepi, āvuso, aññatreva rattibhojanā bhuñjatha.**You too should abstain from eating at night.*";
P_HTM[3034]="*Aññatra kho panāvuso, tumhepi rattibhojanā bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānissatha appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañcā”ti.**Doing so, you’ll find that you’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.”*";
P_HTM[3035]="*Evaṃ vutte, assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ:**When they said this, the mendicants who followed Assaji and Punabbasuka said to them,*";
P_HTM[3036]="*“mayaṃ kho, āvuso, sāyañceva bhuñjāma pāto ca divā ca vikāle.**“Reverends, we eat in the evening, the morning, and at the wrong time of day.*";
P_HTM[3037]="*Te mayaṃ sāyañceva bhuñjamānā pāto ca divā ca vikāle appābādhatañca sañjānāma appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.**Doing so, we find that we’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[3038]="*Te mayaṃ kiṃ sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvissāma?**Why should we give up what is visible in the present to chase after what takes effect over time?*";
P_HTM[3039]="*Sāyañceva mayaṃ bhuñjissāma pāto ca divā ca vikāle”ti.**We shall eat in the evening, the morning, and at the wrong time of day.”*";
P_HTM[3040]="*Yato kho te bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū saññāpetuṃ, atha yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Since those mendicants were unable to convince the mendicants who were followers of Assaji and Punabbasuka, they approached the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[3041]="*“idha mayaṃ, bhante, yena assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū etadavocumha:* **";
P_HTM[3042]="*‘bhagavā kho, āvuso, aññatreva rattibhojanā bhuñjati bhikkhusaṅgho ca;* **";
P_HTM[3043]="*aññatra kho panāvuso, rattibhojanā bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānanti appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.* **";
P_HTM[3044]="*Etha, tumhepi, āvuso, aññatreva rattibhojanā bhuñjatha.* **";
P_HTM[3045]="*Aññatra kho panāvuso, tumhepi rattibhojanā bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānissatha appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañcā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3046]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhante, assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū amhe etadavocuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[3047]="*‘mayaṃ kho, āvuso, sāyañceva bhuñjāma pāto ca divā ca vikāle.* **";
P_HTM[3048]="*Te mayaṃ sāyañceva bhuñjamānā pāto ca divā ca vikāle appābādhatañca sañjānāma appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.* **";
P_HTM[3049]="*Te mayaṃ kiṃ sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvissāma?* **";
P_HTM[3050]="*Sāyañceva mayaṃ bhuñjissāma pāto ca divā ca vikāle’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3051]="*Yato kho mayaṃ, bhante, nāsakkhimha assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū saññāpetuṃ, atha mayaṃ etamatthaṃ bhagavato ārocemā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3052]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:**So the Buddha said to a certain monk,*";
P_HTM[3053]="*“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū āmantehi:**“Please, monk, in my name tell the mendicants who follow Assaji and Punabbasuka that*";
P_HTM[3054]="*‘satthā āyasmante āmantetī’”ti.**the teacher summons them.”*";
P_HTM[3055]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yena assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to those mendicants and said,*";
P_HTM[3056]="*“satthā āyasmante āmantetī”ti.**“Venerables, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[3057]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho assajipunabbasukā bhikkhū tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho assajipunabbasuke bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” those mendicants replied. They went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[3058]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, sambahulā bhikkhū tumhe upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:**The Buddha said to them, “Is it really true, mendicants, that several mendicants went to you and said:*";
P_HTM[3059]="*‘bhagavā kho, āvuso, aññatreva rattibhojanā bhuñjati bhikkhusaṃgho ca.**‘Reverends, the Buddha abstains from eating at night, and so does the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3060]="*Aññatra kho panāvuso, rattibhojanā bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānanti appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.**Doing so, they find that they’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[3061]="*Etha, tumhepi, āvuso, aññatreva rattibhojanā bhuñjatha.**You too should abstain from eating at night.*";
P_HTM[3062]="*Aññatra kho panāvuso, tumhepi rattibhojanā bhuñjamānā appābādhatañca sañjānissatha appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañcā’ti.**Doing so, you’ll find that you’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.’*";
P_HTM[3063]="*Evaṃ vutte, kira, bhikkhave, tumhe te bhikkhū evaṃ avacuttha:**When they said this, did you really say to them:*";
P_HTM[3064]="*‘mayaṃ kho panāvuso, sāyañceva bhuñjāma pāto ca divā ca vikāle.**‘Reverends, we eat in the evening, the morning, and at the wrong time of day.*";
P_HTM[3065]="*Te mayaṃ sāyañceva bhuñjamānā pāto ca divā ca vikāle appābādhatañca sañjānāma appātaṅkatañca lahuṭṭhānañca balañca phāsuvihārañca.**Doing so, we find that we’re healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[3066]="*Te mayaṃ kiṃ sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvissāma?**Why should we give up what is visible in the present to chase after what takes effect over time?*";
P_HTM[3067]="*Sāyañceva mayaṃ bhuñjissāma pāto ca divā ca vikāle’”ti.**We shall eat in the evening, the morning, and at the wrong time of day.’”*";
P_HTM[3068]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3069]="*“Kiṃ nu me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha yaṃ kiñcāyaṃ purisapuggalo paṭisaṃvedeti sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tassa akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhantī”ti?**“Mendicants, have you ever known me to teach the Dhamma like this: no matter what this individual experiences—pleasurable, painful, or neutral—their unskillful qualities decline and their skillful qualities grow?”*";
P_HTM[3070]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3071]="*“Nanu me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha idhekaccassa yaṃ evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, idha panekaccassa evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, idha panekaccassa evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, idha panekaccassa evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhantī”ti?**“Haven’t you known me to teach the Dhamma like this: ‘When someone feels this kind of pleasant feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline. But when someone feels that kind of pleasant feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow. When someone feels this kind of painful feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline. But when someone feels that kind of painful feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow. When someone feels this kind of neutral feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline. But when someone feels that kind of neutral feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow’?”*";
P_HTM[3072]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3073]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[3074]="*Mayā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, aññātaṃ abhavissa adiṭṭhaṃ aviditaṃ asacchikataṃ aphassitaṃ paññāya:**Now, suppose I hadn’t known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3075]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyantī’ti,**‘When someone feels this kind of pleasant feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline.’*";
P_HTM[3076]="*evāhaṃ ajānanto ‘evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ pajahathā’ti vadeyyaṃ; api nu me etaṃ, bhikkhave, patirūpaṃ abhavissā”ti?**Not knowing this, would it be appropriate for me to say: ‘You should give up this kind of pleasant feeling’?”*";
P_HTM[3077]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3078]="*“Yasmā ca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā ñātaṃ diṭṭhaṃ viditaṃ sacchikataṃ phassitaṃ paññāya:**“But I have known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3079]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyantī’ti, tasmāhaṃ ‘evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ pajahathā’ti vadāmi.**‘When someone feels this kind of pleasant feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline.’ Since this is so, that’s why I say: ‘You should give up this kind of pleasant feeling.’*";
P_HTM[3080]="*Mayā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, aññātaṃ abhavissa adiṭṭhaṃ aviditaṃ asacchikataṃ aphassitaṃ paññāya:**Now, suppose I hadn’t known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3081]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhantī’ti, evāhaṃ ajānanto ‘evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti vadeyyaṃ;**‘When someone feels that kind of pleasant feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow.’*";
P_HTM[3082]="*api nu me etaṃ, bhikkhave, patirūpaṃ abhavissā”ti?**Not knowing this, would it be appropriate for me to say: ‘You should enter and remain in that kind of pleasant feeling’?”*";
P_HTM[3083]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3084]="*“Yasmā ca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā ñātaṃ diṭṭhaṃ viditaṃ sacchikataṃ phassitaṃ paññāya:**“But I have known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3085]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhantī’ti, tasmāhaṃ ‘evarūpaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti vadāmi.**‘When someone feels that kind of pleasant feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow.’ Since this is so, that’s why I say: ‘You should enter and remain in that kind of pleasant feeling.’*";
P_HTM[3086]="*Mayā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, aññātaṃ abhavissa adiṭṭhaṃ aviditaṃ asacchikataṃ aphassitaṃ paññāya:**Now, suppose I hadn’t known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3087]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyantī’ti, evāhaṃ ajānanto ‘evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ pajahathā’ti vadeyyaṃ;**‘When someone feels this kind of painful feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline.’*";
P_HTM[3088]="*api nu me etaṃ, bhikkhave, patirūpaṃ abhavissā”ti?**Not knowing this, would it be appropriate for me to say: ‘You should give up this kind of painful feeling’?”*";
P_HTM[3089]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3090]="*“Yasmā ca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā ñātaṃ diṭṭhaṃ viditaṃ sacchikataṃ phassitaṃ paññāya:**“But I have known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3091]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyantī’ti, tasmāhaṃ ‘evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ pajahathā’ti vadāmi.**‘When someone feels this kind of painful feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline.’ Since this is so, that’s why I say: ‘You should give up this kind of painful feeling.’*";
P_HTM[3092]="*Mayā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, aññātaṃ abhavissa adiṭṭhaṃ aviditaṃ asacchikataṃ aphassitaṃ paññāya:**Now, suppose I hadn’t known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3093]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhantī’ti, evāhaṃ ajānanto ‘evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti vadeyyaṃ;**‘When someone feels that kind of painful feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow.’*";
P_HTM[3094]="*api nu me etaṃ, bhikkhave, patirūpaṃ abhavissā”ti?**Not knowing this, would it be appropriate for me to say: ‘You should enter and remain in that kind of painful feeling’?”*";
P_HTM[3095]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3096]="*“Yasmā ca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā ñātaṃ diṭṭhaṃ viditaṃ sacchikataṃ phassitaṃ paññāya:**“But I have known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3097]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhantī’ti, tasmāhaṃ ‘evarūpaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti vadāmi.**‘When someone feels that kind of painful feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow.’ Since this is so, that’s why I say: ‘You should enter and remain in that kind of painful feeling.’*";
P_HTM[3098]="*Mayā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, aññātaṃ abhavissa adiṭṭhaṃ aviditaṃ asacchikataṃ aphassitaṃ paññāya:**Now, suppose I hadn’t known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3099]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyantī’ti, evāhaṃ ajānanto ‘evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ pajahathā’ti vadeyyaṃ;**‘When someone feels this kind of neutral feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline.’*";
P_HTM[3100]="*api nu me etaṃ, bhikkhave, patirūpaṃ abhavissā”ti?**Not knowing this, would it be appropriate for me to say: ‘You should give up this kind of neutral feeling’?”*";
P_HTM[3101]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3102]="*“Yasmā ca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā ñātaṃ diṭṭhaṃ viditaṃ sacchikataṃ phassitaṃ paññāya:**“But I have known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3103]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti kusalā dhammā parihāyantī’ti, tasmāhaṃ ‘evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ pajahathā’ti vadāmi.**‘When someone feels this kind of neutral feeling, unskillful qualities grow and skillful qualities decline.’ Since this is so, that’s why I say: ‘You should give up this kind of neutral feeling.’*";
P_HTM[3104]="*Mayā cetaṃ, bhikkhave, aññātaṃ abhavissa adiṭṭhaṃ aviditaṃ asacchikataṃ aphassitaṃ paññāya:**Now, suppose I hadn’t known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3105]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhantī’ti, evāhaṃ ajānanto ‘evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti vadeyyaṃ;**‘When someone feels that kind of neutral feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow.’*";
P_HTM[3106]="*api nu me etaṃ, bhikkhave, patirūpaṃ abhavissā”ti?**Not knowing this, would it be appropriate for me to say: ‘You should enter and remain in that kind of neutral feeling’?”*";
P_HTM[3107]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3108]="*“Yasmā ca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, mayā ñātaṃ diṭṭhaṃ viditaṃ sacchikataṃ phassitaṃ paññāya:**“But I have known, seen, understood, realized, and experienced this with wisdom:*";
P_HTM[3109]="*‘idhekaccassa evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhantī’ti, tasmāhaṃ ‘evarūpaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti vadāmi.**‘When someone feels that kind of neutral feeling, unskillful qualities decline and skillful qualities grow.’ Since this is so, that’s why I say: ‘You should enter and remain in that kind of neutral feeling.’*";
P_HTM[3110]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sabbesaṃyeva bhikkhūnaṃ ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi;**Mendicants, I don’t say that all these mendicants still have work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3111]="*na panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sabbesaṃyeva bhikkhūnaṃ ‘na appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**Nor do I say that all these mendicants have no work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3112]="*Ye te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, tathārūpānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ ‘na appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**I say that mendicants don’t have work to do with diligence if they are perfected, with defilements ended, having completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and become rightly freed through enlightenment.*";
P_HTM[3113]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3114]="*Kataṃ tesaṃ appamādena.**They’ve done their work with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3115]="*Abhabbā te pamajjituṃ.**They’re incapable of being negligent.*";
P_HTM[3116]="*Ye ca kho te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sekkhā appattamānasā anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamānā viharanti, tathārūpānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**I say that mendicants still have work to do with diligence if they are trainees, who haven’t achieved their heart’s desire, but live aspiring to the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[3117]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that? Thinking:*";
P_HTM[3118]="*Appeva nāmime āyasmanto anulomikāni senāsanāni paṭisevamānā kalyāṇamitte bhajamānā indriyāni samannānayamānā—**‘Hopefully this venerable will frequent appropriate lodgings, associate with good friends, and control their faculties.*";
P_HTM[3119]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyunti.**Then they might realize the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life, and live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[3120]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ appamādaphalaṃ sampassamāno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**Seeing this fruit of diligence for those mendicants, I say that they still have work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3121]="*Sattime, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**Mendicants, these seven people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3122]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[3123]="*Ubhatobhāgavimutto, paññāvimutto, kāyasakkhi, diṭṭhippatto, saddhāvimutto, dhammānusārī, saddhānusārī.**One freed both ways, one freed by wisdom, a personal witness, one attained to view, one freed by faith, a follower of the teachings, and a follower by faith.*";
P_HTM[3124]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo ubhatobhāgavimutto?**And what person is freed both ways?*";
P_HTM[3125]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā te kāyena phusitvā viharati paññāya cassa disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā honti.**It’s a person who has direct meditative experience of the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements have come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3126]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo ubhatobhāgavimutto**This person is called freed both ways.*";
P_HTM[3127]="*imassa kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ‘na appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**And I say that this mendicant has no work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3128]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3129]="*Kataṃ tassa appamādena.**They’ve done their work with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3130]="*Abhabbo so pamajjituṃ. (1)**They’re incapable of being negligent.*";
P_HTM[3131]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo paññāvimutto?**And what person is freed by wisdom?*";
P_HTM[3132]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā te na kāyena phusitvā viharati, paññāya cassa disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā honti.**It’s a person who does not have direct meditative experience of the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form. Nevertheless, having seen with wisdom, their defilements have come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3133]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo paññāvimutto.**This person is called freed by wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3134]="*Imassapi kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ‘na appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**I say that this mendicant has no work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3135]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3136]="*Kataṃ tassa appamādena.**They’ve done their work with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3137]="*Abhabbo so pamajjituṃ. (2)**They’re incapable of being negligent.*";
P_HTM[3138]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo kāyasakkhi?**And what person is a personal witness?*";
P_HTM[3139]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā te kāyena phusitvā viharati, paññāya cassa disvā ekacce āsavā parikkhīṇā honti.**It’s a person who has direct meditative experience of the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form. And, having seen with wisdom, some of their defilements have come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3140]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo kāyasakkhi.**This person is called a personal witness.*";
P_HTM[3141]="*Imassa kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**I say that this mendicant still has work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3142]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that? Thinking:*";
P_HTM[3143]="*Appeva nāma ayamāyasmā anulomikāni senāsanāni paṭisevamāno kalyāṇamitte bhajamāno indriyāni samannānayamāno—**‘Hopefully this venerable will frequent appropriate lodgings, associate with good friends, and control their faculties.*";
P_HTM[3144]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyāti.**Then they might realize the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life, and live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[3145]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa bhikkhuno appamādaphalaṃ sampassamāno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi. (3)**Seeing this fruit of diligence for this mendicant, I say that they still have work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3146]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo diṭṭhippatto?**And what person is attained to view?*";
P_HTM[3147]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā te na kāyena phusitvā viharati, paññāya cassa disvā ekacce āsavā parikkhīṇā honti, tathāgatappaveditā cassa dhammā paññāya vodiṭṭhā honti vocaritā.**It’s a person who doesn’t have direct meditative experience of the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form. Nevertheless, having seen with wisdom, some of their defilements have come to an end. And they have clearly seen and clearly contemplated with wisdom the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3148]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo diṭṭhippatto.**This person is called attained to view.*";
P_HTM[3149]="*Imassapi kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**I say that this mendicant also still has work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3150]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that? Thinking:*";
P_HTM[3151]="*Appeva nāma ayamāyasmā anulomikāni senāsanāni paṭisevamāno kalyāṇamitte bhajamāno indriyāni samannānayamāno—**‘Hopefully this venerable will frequent appropriate lodgings, associate with good friends, and control their faculties.*";
P_HTM[3152]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyāti.**Then they might realize the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life, and live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[3153]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa bhikkhuno appamādaphalaṃ sampassamāno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi. (4)**Seeing this fruit of diligence for this mendicant, I say that they still have work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3154]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo saddhāvimutto.**And what person is freed by faith?*";
P_HTM[3155]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā te na kāyena phusitvā viharati, paññāya cassa disvā ekacce āsavā parikkhīṇā honti, tathāgate cassa saddhā niviṭṭhā hoti mūlajātā patiṭṭhitā.**It’s a person who doesn’t have direct meditative experience of the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form. Nevertheless, having seen with wisdom, some of their defilements have come to an end. And their faith is settled, rooted, and planted in the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3156]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo saddhāvimutto.**This person is called freed by faith.*";
P_HTM[3157]="*Imassapi kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**I say that this mendicant also still has work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3158]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that? Thinking:*";
P_HTM[3159]="*Appeva nāma ayamāyasmā anulomikāni senāsanāni paṭisevamāno kalyāṇamitte bhajamāno indriyāni samannānayamāno—**‘Hopefully this venerable will frequent appropriate lodgings, associate with good friends, and control their faculties.*";
P_HTM[3160]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyāti.**Then they might realize the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life, and live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[3161]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa bhikkhuno appamādaphalaṃ sampassamāno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi. (5)**Seeing this fruit of diligence for this mendicant, I say that they still have work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3162]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo dhammānusārī?**And what person is a follower of the teachings?*";
P_HTM[3163]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā te na kāyena phusitvā viharati, paññāya cassa disvā ekacce āsavā parikkhīṇā honti, tathāgatappaveditā cassa dhammā paññāya mattaso nijjhānaṃ khamanti, api cassa ime dhammā honti, seyyathidaṃ—**It’s a person who doesn’t have direct meditative experience of the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form. Nevertheless, having seen with wisdom, some of their defilements have come to an end. And they accept the teachings proclaimed by the Realized One after considering them with a degree of wisdom. And they have the following qualities:*";
P_HTM[3164]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**the faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3165]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo dhammānusārī.**This person is called a follower of the teachings.*";
P_HTM[3166]="*Imassapi kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**I say that this mendicant also still has work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3167]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that? Thinking:*";
P_HTM[3168]="*Appeva nāma ayamāyasmā anulomikāni senāsanāni paṭisevamāno kalyāṇamitte bhajamāno indriyāni samannānayamāno—**‘Hopefully this venerable will frequent appropriate lodgings, associate with good friends, and control their faculties.*";
P_HTM[3169]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyāti.**Then they might realize the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life, and live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[3170]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa bhikkhuno appamādaphalaṃ sampassamāno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi. (6)**Seeing this fruit of diligence for this mendicant, I say that they still have work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3171]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo saddhānusārī?**And what person is a follower by faith?*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ye te santā vimokkhā atikkamma rūpe āruppā te na kāyena phusitvā viharati, paññāya cassa disvā ekacce āsavā parikkhīṇā honti, tathāgate cassa saddhāmattaṃ hoti pemamattaṃ, api cassa ime dhammā honti, seyyathidaṃ—**It’s a person who doesn’t have direct meditative experience of the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form. Nevertheless, having seen with wisdom, some of their defilements have come to an end. And they have a degree of faith and love for the Realized One. And they have the following qualities:*";
P_HTM[3173]="*saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ.**the faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo saddhānusārī.**This person is called a follower by faith.*";
P_HTM[3175]="*Imassapi kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi.**I say that this mendicant also still has work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3176]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that? Thinking:*";
P_HTM[3177]="*Appeva nāma ayamāyasmā anulomikāni senāsanāni paṭisevamāno kalyāṇamitte bhajamāno indriyāni samannānayamāno—**‘Hopefully this venerable will frequent appropriate lodgings, associate with good friends, and control their faculties.*";
P_HTM[3178]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyāti.**Then they might realize the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life, and live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[3179]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa bhikkhuno appamādaphalaṃ sampassamāno ‘appamādena karaṇīyan’ti vadāmi. (7)**Seeing this fruit of diligence for this mendicant, I say that they still have work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3180]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ādikeneva aññārādhanaṃ vadāmi;**Mendicants, I don’t say that enlightenment is achieved right away.*";
P_HTM[3181]="*api ca, bhikkhave, anupubbasikkhā anupubbakiriyā anupubbapaṭipadā aññārādhanā hoti.**Rather, enlightenment is achieved by gradual training, progress, and practice.*";
P_HTM[3182]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, anupubbasikkhā anupubbakiriyā anupubbapaṭipadā aññārādhanā hoti?**And how is enlightenment achieved by gradual training, progress, and practice?*";
P_HTM[3183]="*Idha, bhikkhave, saddhājāto upasaṅkamati, upasaṅkamanto payirupāsati, payirupāsanto sotaṃ odahati, ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti, sutvā dhammaṃ dhāreti, dhatānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkhati, atthaṃ upaparikkhato dhammā nijjhānaṃ khamanti, dhammanijjhānakkhantiyā sati chando jāyati, chandajāto ussahati, ussāhetvā tuleti, tulayitvā padahati, pahitatto samāno kāyena ceva paramasaccaṃ sacchikaroti, paññāya ca naṃ ativijjha passati.**It’s when someone in whom faith has arisen approaches a teacher. They pay homage, lend an ear, hear the teachings, remember the teachings, reflect on their meaning, and accept them after consideration. Then enthusiasm springs up; they make an effort, weigh up, and persevere. Persevering, they directly realize the ultimate truth, and see it with penetrating wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3184]="*Sāpi nāma, bhikkhave, saddhā nāhosi;**Mendicants, there has not been that faith,*";
P_HTM[3185]="*tampi nāma, bhikkhave, upasaṅkamanaṃ nāhosi;**that approaching,*";
P_HTM[3186]="*sāpi nāma, bhikkhave, payirupāsanā nāhosi;**that paying homage,*";
P_HTM[3187]="*tampi nāma, bhikkhave, sotāvadhānaṃ nāhosi;**that listening,*";
P_HTM[3188]="*tampi nāma, bhikkhave, dhammassavanaṃ nāhosi;**that hearing the teachings,*";
P_HTM[3189]="*sāpi nāma, bhikkhave, dhammadhāraṇā nāhosi;**that remembering the teachings,*";
P_HTM[3190]="*sāpi nāma, bhikkhave, atthūpaparikkhā nāhosi;**that reflecting on their meaning,*";
P_HTM[3191]="*sāpi nāma, bhikkhave, dhammanijjhānakkhanti nāhosi;**that acceptance after consideration,*";
P_HTM[3192]="*sopi nāma, bhikkhave, chando nāhosi;**that enthusiasm,*";
P_HTM[3193]="*sopi nāma, bhikkhave, ussāho nāhosi;**that making an effort,*";
P_HTM[3194]="*sāpi nāma, bhikkhave, tulanā nāhosi;**that weighing up,*";
P_HTM[3195]="*tampi nāma, bhikkhave, padhānaṃ nāhosi.**or that striving.*";
P_HTM[3196]="*Vippaṭipannāttha, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipannāttha, bhikkhave.**You’ve lost the way, mendicants! You’re practicing the wrong way!*";
P_HTM[3197]="*Kīva dūrevime, bhikkhave, moghapurisā apakkantā imamhā dhammavinayā.**Just how far have these foolish people strayed from this teaching and training!*";
P_HTM[3198]="*Atthi, bhikkhave, catuppadaṃ veyyākaraṇaṃ yassuddiṭṭhassa viññū puriso nacirasseva paññāyatthaṃ ājāneyya.**There is an exposition in four parts, which a sensible person would quickly understand when it is recited.*";
P_HTM[3199]="*Uddisissāmi vo, bhikkhave, ājānissatha me tan”ti?**I shall recite it for you, mendicants. Try to understand it.”*";
P_HTM[3200]="*“Ke ca mayaṃ, bhante, ke ca dhammassa aññātāro”ti?**“Sir, who are we to be counted alongside those who understand the teaching?”*";
P_HTM[3201]="*“Yopi so, bhikkhave, satthā āmisagaru āmisadāyādo āmisehi saṃsaṭṭho viharati tassa pāyaṃ evarūpī paṇopaṇaviyā na upeti:**“Even with a teacher who values material things, is an heir in material things, who lives caught up in material things, you wouldn’t get into such haggling:*";
P_HTM[3202]="*‘evañca no assa atha naṃ kareyyāma, na ca no evamassa na naṃ kareyyāmā’ti, kiṃ pana, bhikkhave, yaṃ tathāgato sabbaso āmisehi visaṃsaṭṭho viharati.**‘If we get this, we’ll do that. If we don’t get this, we won’t do it.’ What then of the Realized One, who lives utterly detached from material things?*";
P_HTM[3203]="*Saddhassa, bhikkhave, sāvakassa satthusāsane pariyogāhiya vattato ayamanudhammo hoti:**For a faithful disciple who is practicing to fathom the Teacher’s instructions, this is in line with the teaching:*";
P_HTM[3204]="*‘satthā bhagavā, sāvakohamasmi;**‘The Buddha is my Teacher, I am his disciple.*";
P_HTM[3205]="*jānāti bhagavā, nāhaṃ jānāmī’ti.**The Buddha knows, I do not know.’*";
P_HTM[3206]="*Saddhassa, bhikkhave, sāvakassa satthusāsane pariyogāhiya vattato ruḷhanīyaṃ satthusāsanaṃ hoti ojavantaṃ.**For a faithful disciple who is practicing to fathom the Teacher’s instructions, the Teacher’s instructions are nourishing and nutritious.*";
P_HTM[3207]="*Saddhassa, bhikkhave, sāvakassa satthusāsane pariyogāhiya vattato ayamanudhammo hoti:**For a faithful disciple who is practicing to fathom the Teacher’s instructions, this is in line with the teaching:*";
P_HTM[3208]="*‘kāmaṃ taco ca nhāru ca aṭṭhi ca avasissatu, sarīre upassussatu maṃsalohitaṃ, yaṃ taṃ purisathāmena purisavīriyena purisaparakkamena pattabbaṃ na taṃ apāpuṇitvā vīriyassa saṇṭhānaṃ bhavissatī’ti.**‘Gladly, let only skin, sinews, and bones remain! Let the flesh and blood waste away in my body! I will not relax my energy until I have achieved what is possible by manly strength, energy, and vigor.’*";
P_HTM[3209]="*Saddhassa, bhikkhave, sāvakassa satthusāsane pariyogāhiya vattato dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—**A faithful disciple who is practicing to fathom the Teacher’s instructions can expect one of two results:*";
P_HTM[3210]="*diṭṭheva dhamme aññā, sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā”ti.**enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-return.”*";
P_HTM[3211]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3212]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3213]="*Kīṭāgirisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3214]="*Bhikkhuvaggo niṭṭhito dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[3215]="*Kuñjara rāhula sassataloko,* **";
P_HTM[3216]="*Mālukyaputto ca bhaddāli nāmo;* **";
P_HTM[3217]="*Khudda dijātha sahampatiyācaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[3218]="*Nāḷaka raññikiṭāgirināmo.* **";
P_HTM[3219]="*71. Tevijjavacchasutta**To Vacchagotta on the Three Knowledges*";
P_HTM[3220]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3221]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[3222]="*Tena kho pana samayena vacchagotto paribbājako ekapuṇḍarīke paribbājakārāme paṭivasati.**Now at that time the wanderer Vacchagotta was residing in the Single Lotus Monastery of the wanderers.*";
P_HTM[3223]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Vesālī for alms.*";
P_HTM[3224]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[3225]="*“atippago kho tāva vesāliyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ;**“It’s too early to wander for alms in Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[3226]="*yannūnāhaṃ yena ekapuṇḍarīko paribbājakārāmo yena vacchagotto paribbājako tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti.**Why don’t I visit the wanderer Vacchagotta at the Single Lotus Monastery?”*";
P_HTM[3227]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena ekapuṇḍarīko paribbājakārāmo yena vacchagotto paribbājako tenupasaṅkami.**So that’s what he did.*";
P_HTM[3228]="*Addasā kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Vacchagotta saw the Buddha coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[3229]="*Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3230]="*“Etu kho, bhante, bhagavā.**“Come, Blessed One!*";
P_HTM[3231]="*Svāgataṃ, bhante, bhagavato.**Welcome, Blessed One!*";
P_HTM[3232]="*Cirassaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavā imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya.**It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here.*";
P_HTM[3233]="*Nisīdatu, bhante, bhagavā idamāsanaṃ paññattan”ti.**Please, sir, sit down, this seat is ready.”*";
P_HTM[3234]="*Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane.**The Buddha sat on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[3235]="*Vacchagottopi kho paribbājako aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**while Vacchagotta took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[3236]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Vacchagotta said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[3237]="*“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:**“Sir, I have heard this:*";
P_HTM[3238]="*‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī, aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti,**‘The ascetic Gotama claims to be all-knowing and all-seeing, to know and see everything without exception, thus:*";
P_HTM[3239]="*carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti.**“Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.”’*";
P_HTM[3240]="*Ye te, bhante, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī, aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti, carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti, kacci te, bhante, bhagavato vuttavādino, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti?**I trust that those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and do not misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”*";
P_HTM[3241]="*“Ye te, vaccha, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī, aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti, carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti, na me te vuttavādino, abbhācikkhanti ca pana maṃ asatā abhūtenā”ti.**“Vaccha, those who say this do not repeat what I have said. They misrepresent me with what is false and untrue.”*";
P_HTM[3242]="*“Kathaṃ byākaramānā pana mayaṃ, bhante, vuttavādino ceva bhagavato assāma, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyāma, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyyāma, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyyā”ti?**“So how should we answer so as to repeat what the Buddha has said, and not misrepresent him with an untruth? How should we explain in line with his teaching, with no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”*";
P_HTM[3243]="*“‘Tevijjo samaṇo gotamo’ti kho, vaccha, byākaramāno vuttavādī ceva me assa, na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyya.**“‘The ascetic Gotama has the three knowledges.’ Answering like this you would repeat what I have said, and not misrepresent me with an untruth. You would explain in line with my teaching, and there would be no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism.*";
P_HTM[3244]="*Ahañhi, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāmi anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi,**For, Vaccha, whenever I want, I recollect my many kinds of past lives.*";
P_HTM[3245]="*seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi.**That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. I remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ And so I recollect my many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[3246]="*Ahañhi, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāmi dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi.**And whenever I want, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[3247]="*Ahañhi, vaccha, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmi.**And I have realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. I live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[3248]="*‘Tevijjo samaṇo gotamo’ti kho, vaccha, byākaramāno vuttavādī ceva me assa, na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyyā”ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama has the three knowledges.’ Answering like this you would repeat what I have said, and not misrepresent me with an untruth. You would explain in line with my teaching, and there would be no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism.”*";
P_HTM[3249]="*Evaṃ vutte, vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the wanderer Vacchagotta said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3250]="*“atthi nu kho, bho gotama, koci gihī gihisaṃyojanaṃ appahāya kāyassa bhedā dukkhassantakaro”ti?**“Master Gotama, are there any laypeople who, without giving up the fetter of lay life, make an end of suffering when the body breaks up?”*";
P_HTM[3251]="*“Natthi kho, vaccha, koci gihī gihisaṃyojanaṃ appahāya kāyassa bhedā dukkhassantakaro”ti.**“No, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3252]="*“Atthi pana, bho gotama, koci gihī gihisaṃyojanaṃ appahāya kāyassa bhedā saggūpago”ti?**“But are there any laypeople who, without giving up the fetter of lay life, go to heaven when the body breaks up?”*";
P_HTM[3253]="*“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye gihī gihisaṃyojanaṃ appahāya kāyassa bhedā saggūpagā”ti.**“There’s not just one hundred laypeople, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that who, without giving up the fetter of lay life, go to heaven when the body breaks up.”*";
P_HTM[3254]="*“Atthi nu kho, bho gotama, koci ājīvako kāyassa bhedā dukkhassantakaro”ti?**“Master Gotama, are there any Ājīvaka ascetics who make an end of suffering when the body breaks up?”*";
P_HTM[3255]="*“Natthi kho, vaccha, koci ājīvako kāyassa bhedā dukkhassantakaro”ti.**“No, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3256]="*“Atthi pana, bho gotama, koci ājīvako kāyassa bhedā saggūpago”ti?**“But are there any Ājīvaka ascetics who go to heaven when the body breaks up?”*";
P_HTM[3257]="*“Ito kho so, vaccha, ekanavuto kappo yamahaṃ anussarāmi, nābhijānāmi kañci ājīvakaṃ saggūpagaṃ aññatra ekena;**“Vaccha, when I recollect the past ninety-one eons, I can’t find any Ājīvaka ascetics who have gone to heaven, except one;*";
P_HTM[3258]="*sopāsi kammavādī kiriyavādī”ti.**and he taught the efficacy of deeds and action.”*";
P_HTM[3259]="*“Evaṃ sante, bho gotama, suññaṃ aduṃ titthāyatanaṃ antamaso saggūpagenapī”ti?**“In that case, Master Gotama, the sectarian tenets are empty even of the chance to go to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[3260]="*“Evaṃ, vaccha, suññaṃ aduṃ titthāyatanaṃ antamaso saggūpagenapī”ti.**“Yes, Vaccha, the sectarian tenets are empty even of the chance to go to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[3261]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3262]="*Attamano vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, the wanderer Vacchagotta was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3263]="*Tevijjavacchasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3264]="*72. Aggivacchasutta**With Vacchagotta on Fire*";
P_HTM[3265]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3266]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3267]="*Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3268]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[3269]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, ‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Master Gotama, is this your view: ‘The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3270]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3271]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3272]="*‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3273]="*“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, ‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘The world is not eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3274]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3275]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3276]="*‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3277]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, ‘antavā loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘The world is finite. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3278]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3279]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3280]="*‘antavā loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3281]="*“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, ‘anantavā loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘The world is infinite. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3282]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3283]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3284]="*‘anantavā loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3285]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, ‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘The soul and the body are the same thing. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3286]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3287]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3288]="*‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3289]="*“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘The soul and the body are different things. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3290]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3291]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3292]="*‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3293]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, ‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘A Realized One exists after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3294]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3295]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3296]="*‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3297]="*“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3298]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3299]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3300]="*‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3301]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, ‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3302]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3303]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3304]="*‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3305]="*“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, ‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—**“Then is this your view: ‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3306]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3307]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3308]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3309]="*“‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—**“Master Gotama, when asked these ten questions, you say: ‘That’s not my view.’*";
P_HTM[3310]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3311]="*sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3312]="*‘Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3313]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3314]="*asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3315]="*‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, antavā loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3316]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3317]="*antavā loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3318]="*‘Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, anantavā loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3319]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3320]="*anantavā loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3321]="*‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3322]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3323]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3324]="*‘Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3325]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3326]="*aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3327]="*‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3328]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3329]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3330]="*‘Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3331]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3332]="*na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3333]="*‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3334]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3335]="*hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3336]="*‘Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3337]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavaṃ gotamo’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na kho ahaṃ, vaccha, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3338]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3339]="*Kiṃ pana bho gotamo ādīnavaṃ sampassamāno evaṃ imāni sabbaso diṭṭhigatāni anupagato”ti?**Seeing what drawback do you avoid all these convictions?”*";
P_HTM[3340]="*“‘Sassato loko’ti kho, vaccha, diṭṭhigatametaṃ diṭṭhigahanaṃ diṭṭhikantāro diṭṭhivisūkaṃ diṭṭhivipphanditaṃ diṭṭhisaṃyojanaṃ sadukkhaṃ savighātaṃ saupāyāsaṃ sapariḷāhaṃ, na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati.**“Each of these ten convictions is the thicket of views, the desert of views, the trick of views, the evasiveness of views, the fetter of views. They’re beset with anguish, distress, and fever. They don’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[3341]="*‘Asassato loko’ti kho, vaccha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3342]="*‘antavā loko’ti kho, vaccha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3343]="*‘anantavā loko’ti kho, vaccha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3344]="*‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti kho, vaccha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3345]="*‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti kho, vaccha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3346]="*‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti kho, vaccha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3347]="*‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti kho, vaccha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3348]="*‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti kho, vaccha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3349]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti kho, vaccha, diṭṭhigatametaṃ diṭṭhigahanaṃ diṭṭhikantāro diṭṭhivisūkaṃ diṭṭhivipphanditaṃ diṭṭhisaṃyojanaṃ sadukkhaṃ savighātaṃ saupāyāsaṃ sapariḷāhaṃ, na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati.* **";
P_HTM[3350]="*Imaṃ kho ahaṃ, vaccha, ādīnavaṃ sampassamāno evaṃ imāni sabbaso diṭṭhigatāni anupagato”ti.**Seeing this drawback I avoid all these convictions.”*";
P_HTM[3351]="*“Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa kiñci diṭṭhigatan”ti?**“But does Master Gotama have any convictions at all?”*";
P_HTM[3352]="*“Diṭṭhigatanti kho, vaccha, apanītametaṃ tathāgatassa.**“The Realized One has done away with convictions.*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Diṭṭhañhetaṃ, vaccha, tathāgatena:**For the Realized One has seen:*";
P_HTM[3354]="*‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;**‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form.*";
P_HTM[3355]="*iti vedanā, iti vedanāya samudayo, iti vedanāya atthaṅgamo;**Such is feeling, such is the origin of feeling, such is the ending of feeling.*";
P_HTM[3356]="*iti saññā, iti saññāya samudayo, iti saññāya atthaṅgamo;**Such is perception, such is the origin of perception, such is the ending of perception.*";
P_HTM[3357]="*iti saṅkhārā, iti saṅkhārānaṃ samudayo, iti saṅkhārānaṃ atthaṅgamo;**Such are choices, such is the origin of choices, such is the ending of choices.*";
P_HTM[3358]="*iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti.**Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the ending of consciousness.’*";
P_HTM[3359]="*Tasmā tathāgato sabbamaññitānaṃ sabbamathitānaṃ sabbaahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayānaṃ khayā virāgā nirodhā cāgā paṭinissaggā anupādā vimuttoti vadāmī”ti.**That’s why the Realized One is freed with the ending, fading away, cessation, giving up, and letting go of all identifying, all worries, and all ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit, I say.”*";
P_HTM[3360]="*“Evaṃ vimuttacitto pana, bho gotama, bhikkhu kuhiṃ upapajjatī”ti?**“But Master Gotama, when a mendicant’s mind is freed like this, where are they reborn?”*";
P_HTM[3361]="*“Upapajjatīti kho, vaccha, na upeti”.**“‘They’re reborn’ doesn’t apply, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3362]="*“Tena hi, bho gotama, na upapajjatī”ti?**“Well then, are they not reborn?”*";
P_HTM[3363]="*“Na upapajjatīti kho, vaccha, na upeti”.**“‘They’re not reborn’ doesn’t apply, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3364]="*“Tena hi, bho gotama, upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatī”ti?**“Well then, are they both reborn and not reborn?”*";
P_HTM[3365]="*“Upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatīti kho, vaccha, na upeti”.**“‘They’re both reborn and not reborn’ doesn’t apply, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3366]="*“Tena hi, bho gotama, neva upapajjati na na upapajjatī”ti?**“Well then, are they neither reborn nor not reborn?”*";
P_HTM[3367]="*“Neva upapajjati na na upapajjatīti kho, vaccha, na upeti”.**“‘They’re neither reborn nor not reborn’ doesn’t apply, Vaccha.”*";
P_HTM[3368]="*“‘Evaṃ vimuttacitto pana, bho gotama, bhikkhu kuhiṃ upapajjatī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘upapajjatīti kho, vaccha, na upetī’ti vadesi.**“Master Gotama, when asked all these questions, you say: ‘It doesn’t apply.’*";
P_HTM[3369]="*‘Tena hi, bho gotama, na upapajjatī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘na upapajjatīti kho, vaccha, na upetī’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3370]="*‘Tena hi, bho gotama, upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatīti kho, vaccha, na upetī’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3371]="*‘Tena hi, bho gotama, neva upapajjati na na upapajjatī’ti iti puṭṭho samāno ‘neva upapajjati na na upapajjatīti kho, vaccha, na upetī’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3372]="*Etthāhaṃ, bho gotama, aññāṇamāpādiṃ, ettha sammohamāpādiṃ.**I fail to understand this point, Master Gotama; I’ve fallen into confusion.*";
P_HTM[3373]="*Yāpi me esā bhoto gotamassa purimena kathāsallāpena ahu pasādamattā sāpi me etarahi antarahitā”ti.**And I’ve now lost even the degree of clarity I had from previous discussions with Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3374]="*“Alañhi te, vaccha, aññāṇāya, alaṃ sammohāya.**“No wonder you don’t understand, Vaccha, no wonder you’re confused.*";
P_HTM[3375]="*Gambhīro hāyaṃ, vaccha, dhammo duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo.**For this principle is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute.*";
P_HTM[3376]="*So tayā dujjāno aññadiṭṭhikena aññakhantikena aññarucikena aññatrayogena aññatrācariyakena.**It’s hard for you to understand, since you have a different view, creed, preference, practice, and tradition.*";
P_HTM[3377]="*Tena hi, vaccha, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi; yathā te khameyya tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi.**Well then, Vaccha, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as you like.*";
P_HTM[3378]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vaccha,**What do you think, Vaccha?*";
P_HTM[3379]="*sace te purato aggi jaleyya, jāneyyāsi tvaṃ:**Suppose a fire was burning in front of you. Would you know:*";
P_HTM[3380]="*‘ayaṃ me purato aggi jalatī’”ti?**‘This fire is burning in front of me’?”*";
P_HTM[3381]="*“Sace me, bho gotama, purato aggi jaleyya, jāneyyāhaṃ:**“Yes, I would, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3382]="*‘ayaṃ me purato aggi jalatī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3383]="*“Sace pana taṃ, vaccha, evaṃ puccheyya:**“But Vaccha, suppose they were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[3384]="*‘yo te ayaṃ purato aggi jalati ayaṃ aggi kiṃ paṭicca jalatī’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho tvaṃ, vaccha, kinti byākareyyāsī”ti?**‘This fire burning in front of you: what does it depend on to burn?’ How would you answer?”*";
P_HTM[3385]="*“Sace maṃ, bho gotama, evaṃ puccheyya:* **";
P_HTM[3386]="*‘yo te ayaṃ purato aggi jalati ayaṃ aggi kiṃ paṭicca jalatī’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bho gotama, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ:**“I would answer like this:*";
P_HTM[3387]="*‘yo me ayaṃ purato aggi jalati ayaṃ aggi tiṇakaṭṭhupādānaṃ paṭicca jalatī’”ti.**‘This fire burning in front of me burns in dependence on grass and logs as fuel.’”*";
P_HTM[3388]="*“Sace te, vaccha, purato so aggi nibbāyeyya, jāneyyāsi tvaṃ:**“Suppose that fire burning in front of you was extinguished. Would you know:*";
P_HTM[3389]="*‘ayaṃ me purato aggi nibbuto’”ti?**‘This fire in front of me is extinguished’?”*";
P_HTM[3390]="*“Sace me, bho gotama, purato so aggi nibbāyeyya, jāneyyāhaṃ:**“Yes, I would, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3391]="*‘ayaṃ me purato aggi nibbuto’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3392]="*“Sace pana taṃ, vaccha, evaṃ puccheyya:**“But Vaccha, suppose they were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[3393]="*‘yo te ayaṃ purato aggi nibbuto so aggi ito katamaṃ disaṃ gato—**‘This fire in front of you that is extinguished: in what direction did it go—*";
P_HTM[3394]="*puratthimaṃ vā dakkhiṇaṃ vā pacchimaṃ vā uttaraṃ vā’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho tvaṃ, vaccha, kinti byākareyyāsī”ti?**east, south, west, or north?’ How would you answer?”*";
P_HTM[3395]="*“Na upeti, bho gotama, yañhi so, bho gotama, aggi tiṇakaṭṭhupādānaṃ paṭicca ajali tassa ca pariyādānā aññassa ca anupahārā anāhāro nibbutotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti.**“It doesn’t apply, Master Gotama. The fire depended on grass and logs as fuel. When that runs out, and no more fuel is added, the fire is reckoned to have become extinguished due to lack of fuel.”*";
P_HTM[3396]="*“Evameva kho, vaccha, yena rūpena tathāgataṃ paññāpayamāno paññāpeyya taṃ rūpaṃ tathāgatassa pahīnaṃ ucchinnamūlaṃ tālāvatthukataṃ anabhāvaṃkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ.**“In the same way, Vaccha, any form by which a Realized One might be described has been cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[3397]="*Rūpasaṅkhayavimutto kho, vaccha, tathāgato gambhīro appameyyo duppariyogāḷho—**A Realized One is freed from reckoning in terms of form. They’re deep, immeasurable, and hard to fathom,*";
P_HTM[3398]="*seyyathāpi mahāsamuddo.**like the ocean.*";
P_HTM[3399]="*Upapajjatīti na upeti, na upapajjatīti na upeti, upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatīti na upeti, neva upapajjati na na upapajjatīti na upeti.**‘They’re reborn’, ‘they’re not reborn’, ‘they’re both reborn and not reborn’, ‘they’re neither reborn nor not reborn’—none of these apply.*";
P_HTM[3400]="*Yāya vedanāya tathāgataṃ paññāpayamāno paññāpeyya sā vedanā tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**Any feeling …*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Vedanāsaṅkhayavimutto kho, vaccha, tathāgato gambhīro appameyyo duppariyogāḷho—* **";
P_HTM[3402]="*seyyathāpi mahāsamuddo.* **";
P_HTM[3403]="*Upapajjatīti na upeti, na upapajjatīti na upeti, upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatīti na upeti, neva upapajjati na na upapajjatīti na upeti.* **";
P_HTM[3404]="*Yāya saññāya tathāgataṃ paññāpayamāno paññāpeyya sā saññā tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**perception …*";
P_HTM[3405]="*Saññāsaṅkhayavimutto kho, vaccha, tathāgato gambhīro appameyyo duppariyogāḷho—* **";
P_HTM[3406]="*seyyathāpi mahāsamuddo.* **";
P_HTM[3407]="*Upapajjatīti na upeti, na upapajjatīti na upeti, upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatīti na upeti, neva upapajjati na na upapajjatīti na upeti.* **";
P_HTM[3408]="*Yehi saṅkhārehi tathāgataṃ paññāpayamāno paññāpeyya te saṅkhārā tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā.**choices …*";
P_HTM[3409]="*Saṅkhārasaṅkhayavimutto kho, vaccha, tathāgato gambhīro appameyyo duppariyogāḷho—* **";
P_HTM[3410]="*seyyathāpi mahāsamuddo.* **";
P_HTM[3411]="*Upapajjatīti na upeti, na upapajjatīti na upeti, upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatīti na upeti, neva upapajjati na na upapajjatīti na upeti.* **";
P_HTM[3412]="*Yena viññāṇena tathāgataṃ paññāpayamāno paññāpeyya taṃ viññāṇaṃ tathāgatassa pahīnaṃ ucchinnamūlaṃ tālāvatthukataṃ anabhāvaṅkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ.**consciousness by which a Realized One might be described has been cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[3413]="*Viññāṇasaṅkhayavimutto kho, vaccha, tathāgato gambhīro appameyyo duppariyogāḷho—**A Realized One is freed from reckoning in terms of consciousness. They’re deep, immeasurable, and hard to fathom,*";
P_HTM[3414]="*seyyathāpi mahāsamuddo.**like the ocean.*";
P_HTM[3415]="*Upapajjatīti na upeti, na upapajjatīti na upeti, upapajjati ca na ca upapajjatīti na upeti, neva upapajjati na na upapajjatīti na upetī”ti.**‘They’re reborn’, ‘they’re not reborn’, ‘they’re both reborn and not reborn’, ‘they’re neither reborn nor not reborn’—none of these apply.”*";
P_HTM[3416]="*Evaṃ vutte, vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the wanderer Vacchagotta said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[3417]="*“seyyathāpi, bho gotama, gāmassa vā nigamassa vā avidūre mahāsālarukkho.**“Master Gotama, suppose there was a large sal tree not far from a town or village.*";
P_HTM[3418]="*Tassa aniccatā sākhāpalāsā palujjeyyuṃ, tacapapaṭikā palujjeyyuṃ, pheggū palujjeyyuṃ;**And because it’s impermanent, its branches and foliage, bark and shoots, and softwood would fall off.*";
P_HTM[3419]="*so aparena samayena apagatasākhāpalāso apagatatacapapaṭiko apagataphegguko suddho assa, sāre patiṭṭhito;**After some time it would be rid of branches and foliage, bark and shoots, and softwood, consisting purely of heartwood.*";
P_HTM[3420]="*evameva bhoto gotamassa pāvacanaṃ apagatasākhāpalāsaṃ apagatatacapapaṭikaṃ apagatapheggukaṃ suddhaṃ, sāre patiṭṭhitaṃ.**In the same way, Master Gotama’s dispensation is rid of branches and foliage, bark and shoots, and softwood, consisting purely of heartwood.*";
P_HTM[3421]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**Excellent, Master Gotama! …*";
P_HTM[3422]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[3423]="*Aggivacchasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3424]="*73. Mahāvacchasutta**The Longer Discourse With Vacchagotta*";
P_HTM[3425]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3426]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[3427]="*Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3428]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3429]="*“dīgharattāhaṃ bhotā gotamena sahakathī.**“For a long time I have had discussions with Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[3430]="*Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo saṃkhittena kusalākusalaṃ desetū”ti.**Please teach me in brief what is skillful and what is unskillful.”*";
P_HTM[3431]="*“Saṃkhittenapi kho te ahaṃ, vaccha, kusalākusalaṃ deseyyaṃ, vitthārenapi kho te ahaṃ, vaccha, kusalākusalaṃ deseyyaṃ;**“Vaccha, I can teach you what is skillful and what is unskillful in brief or in detail.*";
P_HTM[3432]="*api ca te ahaṃ, vaccha, saṃkhittena kusalākusalaṃ desessāmi.**Still, let me do so in brief.*";
P_HTM[3433]="*Taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[3434]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Vaccha replied.*";
P_HTM[3435]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3436]="*“Lobho kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, alobho kusalaṃ;**“Greed is unskillful, contentment is skillful.*";
P_HTM[3437]="*doso kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, adoso kusalaṃ;**Hate is unskillful, love is skillful.*";
P_HTM[3438]="*moho kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, amoho kusalaṃ.**Delusion is unskillful, understanding is skillful.*";
P_HTM[3439]="*Iti kho, vaccha, ime tayo dhammā akusalā, tayo dhammā kusalā.**So there are these three unskillful things and three that are skillful.*";
P_HTM[3440]="*Pāṇātipāto kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pāṇātipātā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;**Killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; covetousness, ill will, and wrong view: these things are unskillful.*";
P_HTM[3441]="*adinnādānaṃ kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, adinnādānā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;**Refraining from killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; refraining from speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; contentment, kind-heartedness, and right view: these things are skillful.*";
P_HTM[3442]="*kāmesumicchācāro kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3443]="*musāvādo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, musāvādā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3444]="*pisuṇā vācā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī kusalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3445]="*pharusā vācā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī kusalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3446]="*samphappalāpo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, samphappalāpā veramaṇī kusalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3447]="*abhijjhā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, anabhijjhā kusalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3448]="*byāpādo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, abyāpādo kusalaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3449]="*micchādiṭṭhi kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ sammādiṭṭhi kusalaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3450]="*Iti kho, vaccha, ime dasa dhammā akusalā, dasa dhammā kusalā.**So there are these ten unskillful things and ten that are skillful.*";
P_HTM[3451]="*Yato kho, vaccha, bhikkhuno taṇhā pahīnā hoti ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā, so hoti bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto”ti.**When a mendicant has given up craving so it is cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future, that mendicant is perfected. They’ve ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment.”*";
P_HTM[3452]="*“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo.**“Leaving aside Master Gotama,*";
P_HTM[3453]="*Atthi pana te bhoto gotamassa ekabhikkhupi sāvako yo āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti?**is there even a single monk disciple of Master Gotama who has realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements?”*";
P_HTM[3454]="*“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye bhikkhū mama sāvakā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.**“There are not just one hundred such monks who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”*";
P_HTM[3455]="*“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū.**“Leaving aside Master Gotama and the monks,*";
P_HTM[3456]="*Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekā bhikkhunīpi sāvikā yā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti?**is there even a single nun disciple of Master Gotama who has realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements?”*";
P_HTM[3457]="*“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā bhikkhuniyo mama sāvikā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.**“There are not just one hundred such nuns who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”*";
P_HTM[3458]="*“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo.**“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, and the nuns,*";
P_HTM[3459]="*Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsakopi sāvako gihī odātavasano brahmacārī yo pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā”ti?**is there even a single layman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed and celibate—who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, is reborn spontaneously, to be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world?”*";
P_HTM[3460]="*“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye upāsakā mama sāvakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti.**“There are not just one hundred such celibate laymen who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”*";
P_HTM[3461]="*“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino.**“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, and the celibate laymen,*";
P_HTM[3462]="*Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsakopi sāvako gihī odātavasano kāmabhogī sāsanakaro ovādappaṭikaro yo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane viharatī”ti?**is there even a single layman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed, enjoying sensual pleasures, following instructions, and responding to advice—who has gone beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and lives self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instruction?”*";
P_HTM[3463]="*“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye upāsakā mama sāvakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharantī”ti.**“There are not just one hundred such laymen enjoying sensual pleasures who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”*";
P_HTM[3464]="*“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino.**“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, the celibate laymen, and the laymen enjoying sensual pleasures,*";
P_HTM[3465]="*Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsikāpi sāvikā gihinī odātavasanā brahmacārinī yā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyinī anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti?**is there even a single laywoman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed and celibate—who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, is reborn spontaneously, to be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world?”*";
P_HTM[3466]="*“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā upāsikā mama sāvikā gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyiniyo anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti.**“There are not just one hundred such celibate laywomen who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”*";
P_HTM[3467]="*“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino, tiṭṭhantu upāsikā gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo.**“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, the celibate laymen, the laymen enjoying sensual pleasures, and the celibate laywomen,*";
P_HTM[3468]="*Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsikāpi sāvikā gihinī odātavasanā kāmabhoginī sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā yā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharatī”ti?**is there even a single laywoman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed, enjoying sensual pleasures, following instructions, and responding to advice—who has gone beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and lives self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instruction?”*";
P_HTM[3469]="*“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā upāsikā mama sāvikā gihiniyo odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharantī”ti.**“There are not just one hundred such laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.”*";
P_HTM[3470]="*“Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavaṃyeva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, no ca kho bhikkhū ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu;**“If Master Gotama was the only one to succeed in this teaching, not any monks,*";
P_HTM[3471]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena.**then this spiritual path would be incomplete in that respect.*";
P_HTM[3472]="*Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako bhikkhū ca ārādhakā;**But because both Master Gotama and monks have succeeded in this teaching,*";
P_HTM[3473]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena.**this spiritual path is complete in that respect.*";
P_HTM[3474]="*Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho bhikkhuniyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu;**If Master Gotama and the monks were the only ones to succeed in this teaching, not any nuns …*";
P_HTM[3475]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena.* **";
P_HTM[3476]="*Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā;* **";
P_HTM[3477]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena.* **";
P_HTM[3478]="*Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu;**celibate laymen …*";
P_HTM[3479]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena.* **";
P_HTM[3480]="*Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā;* **";
P_HTM[3481]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena.* **";
P_HTM[3482]="*Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu;**laymen enjoying sensual pleasures …*";
P_HTM[3483]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena.* **";
P_HTM[3484]="*Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā;* **";
P_HTM[3485]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena.* **";
P_HTM[3486]="*Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsikā gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu;**celibate laywomen …*";
P_HTM[3487]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena.* **";
P_HTM[3488]="*Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā, upāsikā ca gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā;* **";
P_HTM[3489]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena.* **";
P_HTM[3490]="*Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, upāsikā ca gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsikā gihiniyo odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu;**laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures,*";
P_HTM[3491]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena.**then this spiritual path would be incomplete in that respect.*";
P_HTM[3492]="*Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā, upāsikā ca gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā, upāsikā ca gihiniyo odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo ārādhikā;**But because Master Gotama, monks, nuns, celibate laymen, laymen enjoying sensual pleasures, celibate laywomen, and laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures have all succeeded in this teaching,*";
P_HTM[3493]="*evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena.**this spiritual path is complete in that respect.*";
P_HTM[3494]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, gaṅgā nadī samuddaninnā samuddapoṇā samuddapabbhārā samuddaṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati, evamevāyaṃ bhoto gotamassa parisā sagahaṭṭhapabbajitā nibbānaninnā nibbānapoṇā nibbānapabbhārā nibbānaṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati.**Just as the Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines towards the ocean, and keeps pushing into the ocean, in the same way Master Gotama’s assembly—with both laypeople and renunciates—slants, slopes, and inclines towards extinguishment, and keeps pushing into extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[3495]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**Excellent, Master Gotama! …*";
P_HTM[3496]="*esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3497]="*Labheyyāhaṃ bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti.**Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”*";
P_HTM[3498]="*“Yo kho, vaccha, aññatitthiyapubbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhati pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhati upasampadaṃ, so cattāro māse parivasati. Catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya;**“Vaccha, if someone formerly ordained in another sect wishes to take the going forth, the ordination in this teaching and training, they must spend four months on probation. When four months have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, they’ll give the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.*";
P_HTM[3499]="*api ca mettha puggalavemattatā viditā”ti.**However, I have recognized individual differences in this matter.”*";
P_HTM[3500]="*“Sace, bhante, aññatitthiyapubbā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhantā pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhantā upasampadaṃ cattāro māse parivasanti, catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya; ahaṃ cattāri vassāni parivasissāmi. Catunnaṃ vassānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājentu upasampādentu bhikkhubhāvāyā”ti.**“Sir, if four months probation are required in such a case, I’ll spend four years on probation. When four years have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, let them give me the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.”*";
P_HTM[3501]="*Alattha kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ alattha upasampadaṃ.**And the wanderer Vaccha received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence.*";
P_HTM[3502]="*Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā vacchagotto addhamāsūpasampanno yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā vacchagotto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Not long after his ordination, a fortnight later, Venerable Vacchagotta went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3503]="*“yāvatakaṃ, bhante, sekhena ñāṇena sekhāya vijjāya pattabbaṃ, anuppattaṃ taṃ mayā;**“Sir, I’ve reached as far as possible with the knowledge and understanding of a trainee.*";
P_HTM[3504]="*uttari ca me bhagavā dhammaṃ desetū”ti.**Please teach me further.”*";
P_HTM[3505]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, vaccha, dve dhamme uttari bhāvehi—samathañca vipassanañca.**“Well then, Vaccha, further develop two things: serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[3506]="*Ime kho te, vaccha, dve dhammā uttari bhāvitā—samatho ca vipassanā ca—anekadhātupaṭivedhāya saṃvattissanti.**When you have further developed these two things, they’ll lead to the penetration of many elements.*";
P_HTM[3507]="*So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:**Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case:*";
P_HTM[3508]="*‘anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhaveyyaṃ—ekopi hutvā bahudhā assaṃ, bahudhāpi hutvā eko assaṃ; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gaccheyyaṃ, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ kareyyaṃ, seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gaccheyyaṃ, seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kameyyaṃ, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimaseyyaṃ, parimajjeyyaṃ; yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteyyan’ti,**‘May I wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying myself and becoming one again; appearing and disappearing; going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with my hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful; controlling my body as far as the Brahmā realm.’*";
P_HTM[3509]="*tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (1)* **";
P_HTM[3510]="*So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:**Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case:*";
P_HTM[3511]="*‘dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇeyyaṃ—dibbe ca mānuse ca, ye dūre santike cā’ti, tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (2)**‘With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, may I hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.’*";
P_HTM[3512]="*So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:**Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case:*";
P_HTM[3513]="*‘parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajāneyyaṃ—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ sarāgaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ vītarāgaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ sadosaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ vītadosaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; samohaṃ vā cittaṃ samohaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ vītamohaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ saṅkhittaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ vikkhittaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ mahaggataṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ amahaggataṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ sauttaraṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ anuttaraṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ samāhitaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ asamāhitaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ avimuttaṃ cittanti pajāneyyan’ti,**‘May I understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with my mind. May I understand mind with greed as “mind with greed”, and mind without greed as “mind without greed”; mind with hate as “mind with hate”, and mind without hate as “mind without hate”; mind with delusion as “mind with delusion”, and mind without delusion as “mind without delusion”; constricted mind as “constricted mind”, and scattered mind as “scattered mind”; expansive mind as “expansive mind”, and unexpansive mind as “unexpansive mind”; mind that is not supreme as “mind that is not supreme”, and mind that is supreme as “mind that is supreme”; mind immersed in samādhi as “mind immersed in samādhi”, and mind not immersed in samādhi as “mind not immersed in samādhi”; freed mind as “freed mind”, and unfreed mind as “unfreed mind”.’*";
P_HTM[3514]="*tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (3)* **";
P_HTM[3515]="*So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:**Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case:*";
P_HTM[3516]="*‘anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi; anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe—amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapannoti; iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyyan’ti,**‘May I recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. May I remember: “There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.” May I recollect my many past lives, with features and details.’*";
P_HTM[3517]="*tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (4)* **";
P_HTM[3518]="*So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:**Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case:*";
P_HTM[3519]="*‘dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passeyyaṃ cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajāneyyaṃ—ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā; ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannāti; iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passeyyaṃ cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajāneyyan’ti,**‘With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, may I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place—and understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds: “These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.” And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, may I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. And may I understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.’*";
P_HTM[3520]="*tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (5)* **";
P_HTM[3521]="*So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi:**Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case:*";
P_HTM[3522]="*‘āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyan’ti,**‘May I realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.’*";
P_HTM[3523]="*tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane”ti. (6)* **";
P_HTM[3524]="*Atha kho āyasmā vacchagotto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**And then Venerable Vacchagotta approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[3525]="*Atha kho āyasmā vacchagotto eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**Then Vacchagotta, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[3526]="*“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi.**He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[3527]="*Aññataro kho panāyasmā vacchagotto arahataṃ ahosi.**And Venerable Vacchagotta became one of the perfected.*";
P_HTM[3528]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ dassanāya gacchanti.**Now at that time several mendicants were going to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3529]="*Addasā kho āyasmā vacchagotto te bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante.**Vacchagotta saw them coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[3530]="*Disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca:**went up to them, and said,*";
P_HTM[3531]="*“handa kahaṃ pana tumhe āyasmanto gacchathā”ti?**“Hello venerables, where are you going?”*";
P_HTM[3532]="*“Bhagavantaṃ kho mayaṃ, āvuso, dassanāya gacchāmā”ti.**“Reverend, we are going to see the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[3533]="*“Tenahāyasmanto mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatha, evañca vadetha:**“Well then, reverends, in my name please bow with your head to the Buddha’s feet and say:*";
P_HTM[3534]="*‘vacchagotto, bhante, bhikkhu bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti—**‘Sir, the mendicant Vacchagotta bows with his head to your feet and says,*";
P_HTM[3535]="*pariciṇṇo me bhagavā, pariciṇṇo me sugato’”ti.**“I have served the Blessed One! I have served the Holy One!”’”*";
P_HTM[3536]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato vacchagottassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3537]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then those mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3538]="*“āyasmā, bhante, vacchagotto bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti:**“Sir, the mendicant Vacchagotta bows with his head to your feet and says:*";
P_HTM[3539]="*‘pariciṇṇo me bhagavā, pariciṇṇo me sugato’”ti.**‘I have served the Blessed One! I have served the Holy One!’”*";
P_HTM[3540]="*“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, vacchagotto bhikkhu cetasā ceto paricca vidito:**“I’ve already comprehended Vacchagotta’s mind and understood that*";
P_HTM[3541]="*‘tevijjo vacchagotto bhikkhu mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo’ti.**he has the three knowledges, and is very mighty and powerful.*";
P_HTM[3542]="*Devatāpi me etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ:**And deities also told me about this.”*";
P_HTM[3543]="*‘tevijjo, bhante, vacchagotto bhikkhu mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3544]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3545]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3546]="*Mahāvacchasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3547]="*74. Dīghanakhasutta**With Dīghanakha*";
P_HTM[3548]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3549]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate sūkarakhatāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain in the Boar’s Cave.*";
P_HTM[3550]="*Atha kho dīghanakho paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Dīghanakha went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3551]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho dīghanakho paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side, and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3552]="*“ahañhi, bho gotama, evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“Master Gotama, this is my doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[3553]="*‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’”ti.**‘I believe in nothing.’”*";
P_HTM[3554]="*“Yāpi kho te esā, aggivessana, diṭṭhi:**“This view of yours, Aggivessana—*";
P_HTM[3555]="*‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti, esāpi te diṭṭhi nakkhamatī”ti?**do you believe in that?”*";
P_HTM[3556]="*“Esā ce me, bho gotama, diṭṭhi khameyya, taṃpassa tādisameva, taṃpassa tādisamevā”ti.**“If I believed in this view, Master Gotama, it wouldn’t make any difference, it wouldn’t make any difference!”*";
P_HTM[3557]="*“Ato kho te, aggivessana, bahū hi bahutarā lokasmiṃ ye evamāhaṃsu:**“Well, Aggivessana, there are many more in the world who say,*";
P_HTM[3558]="*‘taṃpassa tādisameva, taṃpassa tādisamevā’ti.**‘It wouldn’t make any difference! It wouldn’t make any difference!’*";
P_HTM[3559]="*Te tañceva diṭṭhiṃ nappajahanti aññañca diṭṭhiṃ upādiyanti.**But they don’t give up that view, and they grasp another view.*";
P_HTM[3560]="*Ato kho te, aggivessana, tanū hi tanutarā lokasmiṃ ye evamāhaṃsu:**And there are a scant few in the world who say,*";
P_HTM[3561]="*‘taṃpassa tādisameva, taṃpassa tādisamevā’ti.**‘It wouldn’t make any difference! It wouldn’t make any difference!’*";
P_HTM[3562]="*Te tañceva diṭṭhiṃ pajahanti aññañca diṭṭhiṃ na upādiyanti.**And they give up that view by not grasping another view.*";
P_HTM[3563]="*Santaggivessana, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[3564]="*‘sabbaṃ me khamatī’ti;**‘I believe in everything.’*";
P_HTM[3565]="*santaggivessana, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[3566]="*‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti;**‘I believe in nothing.’*";
P_HTM[3567]="*santaggivessana, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[3568]="*‘ekaccaṃ me khamati, ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti.**‘I believe in some things, and not in others.’*";
P_HTM[3569]="*Tatraggivessana, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: ‘sabbaṃ me khamatī’ti**Regarding this, the view of the ascetics and brahmins who believe in everything*";
P_HTM[3570]="*tesamayaṃ diṭṭhi sārāgāya santike, saññogāya santike, abhinandanāya santike, ajjhosānāya santike, upādānāya santike;**is close to greed, bondage, approving, attachment, and grasping.*";
P_HTM[3571]="*tatraggivessana ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino: ‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti**The view of the ascetics and brahmins who believe in nothing*";
P_HTM[3572]="*tesamayaṃ diṭṭhi asārāgāya santike, asaññogāya santike, anabhinandanāya santike, anajjhosānāya santike, anupādānāya santike”ti.**is far from greed, bondage, approving, attachment, and grasping.”*";
P_HTM[3573]="*Evaṃ vutte, dīghanakho paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the wanderer Dīghanakha said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3574]="*“ukkaṃseti me bhavaṃ gotamo diṭṭhigataṃ, samukkaṃseti me bhavaṃ gotamo diṭṭhigatan”ti.**“Master Gotama commends my conviction! He recommends my conviction!”*";
P_HTM[3575]="*“Tatraggivessana, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**“Now, regarding the ascetics and brahmins who*";
P_HTM[3576]="*‘ekaccaṃ me khamati, ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti.**believe in some things and not in others.*";
P_HTM[3577]="*Yā hi tesaṃ khamati sāyaṃ diṭṭhi sārāgāya santike, saññogāya santike, abhinandanāya santike, ajjhosānāya santike, upādānāya santike;**Their view of what they believe in is close to greed, bondage, approving, attachment, and grasping.*";
P_HTM[3578]="*yā hi tesaṃ nakkhamati sāyaṃ diṭṭhi asārāgāya santike, asaññogāya santike, anabhinandanāya santike, anajjhosānāya santike, anupādānāya santike.**Their view of what they don’t believe in is far from greed, bondage, approving, attachment, and grasping.*";
P_HTM[3579]="*Tatraggivessana, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**When it comes to the view of the ascetics and brahmins who*";
P_HTM[3580]="*‘sabbaṃ me khamatī’ti**believe in everything,*";
P_HTM[3581]="*tattha viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**a sensible person reflects like this:*";
P_HTM[3582]="*‘yā kho me ayaṃ diṭṭhi—**‘I have the view that*";
P_HTM[3583]="*sabbaṃ me khamatīti,**I believe in everything.*";
P_HTM[3584]="*imañce ahaṃ diṭṭhiṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa vohareyyaṃ—**Suppose I obstinately stick to this view and insist that,*";
P_HTM[3585]="*idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti;**“This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.”*";
P_HTM[3586]="*dvīhi me assa viggaho—**Then I’d argue with two people—*";
P_HTM[3587]="*yo cāyaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—sabbaṃ me nakkhamatīti,**an ascetic or brahmin who believes in nothing,*";
P_HTM[3588]="*yo cāyaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—ekaccaṃ me khamati, ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatīti—**and an ascetic or brahmin who believes in some things and not in others.*";
P_HTM[3589]="*imehi assa dvīhi viggaho.* **";
P_HTM[3590]="*Iti viggahe sati vivādo, vivāde sati vighāto, vighāte sati vihesā’.**And when there’s arguing, there’s quarreling; when there’s quarreling there’s anguish; and when there’s anguish there’s harm.’*";
P_HTM[3591]="*Iti so viggahañca vivādañca vighātañca vihesañca attani sampassamāno tañceva diṭṭhiṃ pajahati aññañca diṭṭhiṃ na upādiyati.**So, considering in themselves the potential for arguing, quarreling, anguish, and harm, they give up that view by not grasping another view.*";
P_HTM[3592]="*Evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ paṭinissaggo hoti.**That’s how those views are given up and let go.*";
P_HTM[3593]="*Tatraggivessana, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**When it comes to the view of the ascetics and brahmins who*";
P_HTM[3594]="*‘sabbaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti**believe in nothing,*";
P_HTM[3595]="*tattha viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**a sensible person reflects like this:*";
P_HTM[3596]="*‘yā kho me ayaṃ diṭṭhi—**‘I have the view that*";
P_HTM[3597]="*sabbaṃ me nakkhamatīti,**I believe in nothing.*";
P_HTM[3598]="*imañce ahaṃ diṭṭhiṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa vohareyyaṃ—**Suppose I obstinately stick to this view and insist that,*";
P_HTM[3599]="*idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti;**“This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.”*";
P_HTM[3600]="*dvīhi me assa viggaho—**Then I’d argue with two people—*";
P_HTM[3601]="*yo cāyaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—sabbaṃ me khamatīti,**an ascetic or brahmin who believes in everything,*";
P_HTM[3602]="*yo cāyaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—ekaccaṃ me khamati ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatīti—**and an ascetic or brahmin who believes in some things and not in others.*";
P_HTM[3603]="*imehi assa dvīhi viggaho.* **";
P_HTM[3604]="*Iti viggahe sati vivādo, vivāde sati vighāto, vighāte sati vihesā’.**And when there’s arguing, there’s quarreling; when there’s quarreling there’s anguish; and when there’s anguish there’s harm.’*";
P_HTM[3605]="*Iti so viggahañca vivādañca vighātañca vihesañca attani sampassamāno tañceva diṭṭhiṃ pajahati aññañca diṭṭhiṃ na upādiyati.**So, considering in themselves the potential for arguing, quarreling, anguish, and harm, they give up that view by not grasping another view.*";
P_HTM[3606]="*Evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ paṭinissaggo hoti.**That’s how those views are given up and let go.*";
P_HTM[3607]="*Tatraggivessana, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:**When it comes to the view of the ascetics and brahmins who*";
P_HTM[3608]="*‘ekaccaṃ me khamati, ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti**believe in some things and not in others,*";
P_HTM[3609]="*tattha viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**a sensible person reflects like this:*";
P_HTM[3610]="*‘yā kho me ayaṃ diṭṭhi—**‘I have the view that*";
P_HTM[3611]="*ekaccaṃ me khamati, ekaccaṃ me nakkhamatīti,**I believe in some things and not in others.*";
P_HTM[3612]="*imañce ahaṃ diṭṭhiṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa vohareyyaṃ—**Suppose I obstinately stick to this view and insist that,*";
P_HTM[3613]="*idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti;**“This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.”*";
P_HTM[3614]="*dvīhi me assa viggaho—**Then I’d argue with two people—*";
P_HTM[3615]="*yo cāyaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—sabbaṃ me khamatīti,**an ascetic or brahmin who believes in everything,*";
P_HTM[3616]="*yo cāyaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—sabbaṃ me nakkhamatīti—**and an ascetic or brahmin who believes in nothing.*";
P_HTM[3617]="*imehi assa dvīhi viggaho.* **";
P_HTM[3618]="*Iti viggahe sati vivādo, vivāde sati vighāto, vighāte sati vihesā’.**And when there’s arguing, there’s quarreling; when there’s quarreling there’s anguish; and when there’s anguish there’s harm.’*";
P_HTM[3619]="*Iti so viggahañca vivādañca vighātañca vihesañca attani sampassamāno tañceva diṭṭhiṃ pajahati aññañca diṭṭhiṃ na upādiyati.**So, considering in themselves the potential for arguing, quarreling, anguish, and harm, they give up that view by not grasping another view.*";
P_HTM[3620]="*Evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ pahānaṃ hoti, evametāsaṃ diṭṭhīnaṃ paṭinissaggo hoti.**That’s how those views are given up and let go.*";
P_HTM[3621]="*Ayaṃ kho panaggivessana, kāyo rūpī cātumahābhūtiko mātāpettikasambhavo odanakummāsūpacayo aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammo, aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassitabbo.**Aggivessana, this body is physical. It’s made up of the four primary elements, produced by mother and father, built up from rice and porridge, liable to impermanence, to wearing away and erosion, to breaking up and destruction. You should see it as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as not-self.*";
P_HTM[3622]="*Tassimaṃ kāyaṃ aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassato yo kāyasmiṃ kāyachando kāyasneho kāyanvayatā sā pahīyati.**Doing so, you’ll give up desire, affection, and subservience to the body.*";
P_HTM[3623]="*Tisso kho imā, aggivessana, vedanā—**There are these three feelings:*";
P_HTM[3624]="*sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā.**pleasant, painful, and neutral.*";
P_HTM[3625]="*Yasmiṃ, aggivessana, samaye sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti, neva tasmiṃ samaye dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti, na adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti;**At a time when you feel a pleasant feeling, you don’t feel a painful or neutral feeling;*";
P_HTM[3626]="*sukhaṃyeva tasmiṃ samaye vedanaṃ vedeti.**you only feel a pleasant feeling.*";
P_HTM[3627]="*Yasmiṃ, aggivessana, samaye dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti, neva tasmiṃ samaye sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti, na adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti;**At a time when you feel a painful feeling, you don’t feel a pleasant or neutral feeling;*";
P_HTM[3628]="*dukkhaṃyeva tasmiṃ samaye vedanaṃ vedeti.**you only feel a painful feeling.*";
P_HTM[3629]="*Yasmiṃ, aggivessana, samaye adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti, neva tasmiṃ samaye sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti, na dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedeti;**At a time when you feel a neutral feeling, you don’t feel a pleasant or painful feeling;*";
P_HTM[3630]="*adukkhamasukhaṃyeva tasmiṃ samaye vedanaṃ vedeti.**you only feel a neutral feeling.*";
P_HTM[3631]="*Sukhāpi kho, aggivessana, vedanā aniccā saṅkhatā paṭiccasamuppannā khayadhammā vayadhammā virāgadhammā nirodhadhammā;**Pleasant, painful, and neutral feelings are impermanent, conditioned, dependently originated, liable to end, vanish, fade away, and cease.*";
P_HTM[3632]="*dukkhāpi kho, aggivessana, vedanā aniccā saṅkhatā paṭiccasamuppannā khayadhammā vayadhammā virāgadhammā nirodhadhammā;* **";
P_HTM[3633]="*adukkhamasukhāpi kho, aggivessana, vedanā aniccā saṅkhatā paṭiccasamuppannā khayadhammā vayadhammā virāgadhammā nirodhadhammā.* **";
P_HTM[3634]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, aggivessana, sutavā ariyasāvako sukhāyapi vedanāya nibbindati, dukkhāyapi vedanāya nibbindati, adukkhamasukhāyapi vedanāya nibbindati;**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with pleasant, painful, and neutral feelings.*";
P_HTM[3635]="*nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ, vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[3636]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[3637]="*Evaṃ vimuttacitto kho, aggivessana, bhikkhu na kenaci saṃvadati, na kenaci vivadati, yañca loke vuttaṃ tena voharati, aparāmasan”ti.**A mendicant whose mind is freed like this doesn’t side with anyone or fight with anyone. They speak the language of the world without misapprehending it.”*";
P_HTM[3638]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato piṭṭhito ṭhito hoti bhagavantaṃ bījayamāno.**Now at that time Venerable Sāriputta was standing behind the Buddha fanning him.*";
P_HTM[3639]="*Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:**Then he thought,*";
P_HTM[3640]="*“tesaṃ tesaṃ kira no bhagavā dhammānaṃ abhiññā pahānamāha, tesaṃ tesaṃ kira no sugato dhammānaṃ abhiññā paṭinissaggamāhā”ti.**“It seems the Buddha speaks of giving up and letting go all these things through direct knowledge.”*";
P_HTM[3641]="*Iti hidaṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa paṭisañcikkhato anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimucci.**Reflecting like this, Venerable Sāriputta’s mind was freed from the defilements by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[3642]="*Dīghanakhassa pana paribbājakassa virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:**And the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in the wanderer Dīghanakha:*";
P_HTM[3643]="*“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti.**“Everything that has a beginning has an end.”*";
P_HTM[3644]="*Atha kho dīghanakho paribbājako diṭṭhadhammo pattadhammo viditadhammo pariyogāḷhadhammo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṃkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Dīghanakha saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. He went beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. He said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[3645]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[3646]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evameva kho bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[3647]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3648]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[3649]="*Dīghanakhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3650]="*75. Māgaṇḍiyasutta**With Māgaṇḍiya*";
P_HTM[3651]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3652]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kurūsu viharati kammāsadhammaṃ nāma kurūnaṃ nigamo, bhāradvājagottassa brāhmaṇassa agyāgāre tiṇasanthārake.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Kurus, near the Kuru town named Kammāsadamma, on a grass mat in the fire chamber of a brahmin of the Bhāradvāja clan.*";
P_HTM[3653]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya kammāsadhammaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Kammāsadamma for alms.*";
P_HTM[3654]="*Kammāsadhammaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena aññataro vanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**He wandered for alms in Kammāsadamma. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to a certain forest grove for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[3655]="*Taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**Having plunged deep into it, he sat at the root of a certain tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[3656]="*Atha kho māgaṇḍiyo paribbājako jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena bhāradvājagottassa brāhmaṇassa agyāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Then as the wanderer Māgaṇḍiya was going for a walk he approached that fire chamber.*";
P_HTM[3657]="*Addasā kho māgaṇḍiyo paribbājako bhāradvājagottassa brāhmaṇassa agyāgāre tiṇasanthārakaṃ paññattaṃ.**He saw the grass mat spread out there*";
P_HTM[3658]="*Disvāna bhāradvājagottaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**and asked the brahmin of the Bhāradvāja clan,*";
P_HTM[3659]="*“kassa nvayaṃ bhoto bhāradvājassa agyāgāre tiṇasanthārako paññatto, samaṇaseyyānurūpaṃ maññe”ti?**“Mister Bhāradvāja, who has this grass mat been spread out for? It looks like an ascetic’s bed.”*";
P_HTM[3660]="*“Atthi, bho māgaṇḍiya, samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito.**“There is the ascetic Gotama, a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family.*";
P_HTM[3661]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[3662]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[3663]="*Tassesā bhoto gotamassa seyyā paññattā”ti.**This bed has been spread for that Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3664]="*“Duddiṭṭhaṃ vata, bho bhāradvāja, addasāma;**“Well, it’s a sad sight, Mister Bhāradvāja,*";
P_HTM[3665]="*duddiṭṭhaṃ vata, bho bhāradvāja, addasāma.**a very sad sight indeed,*";
P_HTM[3666]="*Ye mayaṃ tassa bhoto gotamassa bhūnahuno seyyaṃ addasāmā”ti.**to see a bed for Master Gotama, that life-destroyer!”*";
P_HTM[3667]="*“Rakkhassetaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, vācaṃ;**“Be careful what you say, Māgaṇḍiya,*";
P_HTM[3668]="*rakkhassetaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, vācaṃ.**be careful what you say.*";
P_HTM[3669]="*Bahū hi tassa bhoto gotamassa khattiyapaṇḍitāpi brāhmaṇapaṇḍitāpi gahapatipaṇḍitāpi samaṇapaṇḍitāpi abhippasannā vinītā ariye ñāye dhamme kusale”ti.**Many astute aristocrats, brahmins, householders, and ascetics are devoted to Master Gotama. They’ve been guided by him in the noble method, the skillful teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3670]="*“Sammukhā cepi mayaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ passeyyāma, sammukhāpi naṃ vadeyyāma:**“Even if I was to see Master Gotama face to face, Mister Bhāradvāja, I would say to his face:*";
P_HTM[3671]="*‘bhūnahu samaṇo gotamo’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama is a life-destroyer.’*";
P_HTM[3672]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3673]="*Evañhi no sutte ocaratī”ti.**Because that’s what it implies in a discourse of ours.”*";
P_HTM[3674]="*“Sace taṃ bhoto māgaṇḍiyassa agaru āroceyyāmi taṃ samaṇassa gotamassā”ti.**“If you don’t mind, I’ll tell the ascetic Gotama about this.”*";
P_HTM[3675]="*“Appossukko bhavaṃ bhāradvājo vuttova naṃ vadeyyā”ti.**“Don’t worry, Mister Bharadvāja. You may tell him exactly what I’ve said.”*";
P_HTM[3676]="*Assosi kho bhagavā dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya bhāradvājagottassa brāhmaṇassa māgaṇḍiyena paribbājakena saddhiṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ.**With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, the Buddha heard this discussion between the brahmin of the Bhāradvāja clan and the wanderer Māgaṇḍiya.*";
P_HTM[3677]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhāradvājagottassa brāhmaṇassa agyāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nisīdi bhagavā paññatte tiṇasanthārake.**Coming out of retreat, he went to the brahmin’s fire chamber and sat on the grass mat.*";
P_HTM[3678]="*Atha kho bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the brahmin of the Bhāradvāja clan went to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3679]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho bhāradvājagottaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[3680]="*“ahu pana te, bhāradvāja, māgaṇḍiyena paribbājakena saddhiṃ imaṃyeva tiṇasanthārakaṃ ārabbha kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti?**“Bhāradvāja, did you have a discussion with the wanderer Māgaṇḍiya about this grass mat?”*";
P_HTM[3681]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo saṃviggo lomahaṭṭhajāto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the brahmin said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3682]="*“etadeva kho pana mayaṃ bhoto gotamassa ārocetukāmā.**“I wanted to mention this very thing to Master Gotama,*";
P_HTM[3683]="*Atha ca pana bhavaṃ gotamo anakkhātaṃyeva akkhāsī”ti.**but you brought it up before I had a chance.”*";
P_HTM[3684]="*Ayañca hi bhagavato bhāradvājagottena brāhmaṇena saddhiṃ antarākathā vippakatā hoti.**But this conversation between the Buddha and the brahmin was left unfinished.*";
P_HTM[3685]="*Atha kho māgaṇḍiyo paribbājako jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena bhāradvājagottassa brāhmaṇassa agyāgāraṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then as the wanderer Māgaṇḍiya was going for a walk he approached that fire chamber. He went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3686]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho māgaṇḍiyaṃ paribbājakaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and the Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[3687]="*“Cakkhuṃ kho, māgaṇḍiya, rūpārāmaṃ rūparataṃ rūpasammuditaṃ.**“Māgaṇḍiya, the eye likes sights, it loves them and enjoys them.*";
P_HTM[3688]="*Taṃ tathāgatassa dantaṃ guttaṃ rakkhitaṃ saṃvutaṃ, tassa ca saṃvarāya dhammaṃ deseti.**That’s been tamed, guarded, protected and restrained by the Realized One, and he teaches Dhamma for its restraint.*";
P_HTM[3689]="*Idaṃ nu te etaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**Is that what you were referring to when you called me*";
P_HTM[3690]="*‘bhūnahu samaṇo gotamo’”ti?**a life-destroyer?”*";
P_HTM[3691]="*“Etadeva kho pana me, bho gotama, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“That’s exactly what I was referring to.*";
P_HTM[3692]="*‘bhūnahu samaṇo gotamo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3693]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3694]="*Evañhi no sutte ocaratī”ti.**Because that’s what it implies in a discourse of ours.”*";
P_HTM[3695]="*“Sotaṃ kho, māgaṇḍiya, saddārāmaṃ … pe …**“The ear likes sounds …*";
P_HTM[3696]="*ghānaṃ kho, māgaṇḍiya gandhārāmaṃ …**The nose likes smells …*";
P_HTM[3697]="*jivhā kho, māgaṇḍiya, rasārāmā rasaratā rasasammuditā.**The tongue likes tastes …*";
P_HTM[3698]="*Sā tathāgatassa dantā guttā rakkhitā saṃvutā, tassā ca saṃvarāya dhammaṃ deseti.* **";
P_HTM[3699]="*Idaṃ nu te etaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[3700]="*‘bhūnahu samaṇo gotamo’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[3701]="*“Etadeva kho pana me, bho gotama, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[3702]="*‘bhūnahu samaṇo gotamo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3703]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?* **";
P_HTM[3704]="*Evañhi no sutte ocaratī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3705]="*“Kāyo kho, māgaṇḍiya, phoṭṭhabbārāmo phoṭṭhabbarato … pe …**The body likes touches …*";
P_HTM[3706]="*mano kho, māgaṇḍiya, dhammārāmo dhammarato dhammasammudito.**The mind likes thoughts, it loves them and enjoys them.*";
P_HTM[3707]="*So tathāgatassa danto gutto rakkhito saṃvuto, tassa ca saṃvarāya dhammaṃ deseti.**That’s been tamed, guarded, protected and restrained by the Realized One, and he teaches Dhamma for its restraint.*";
P_HTM[3708]="*Idaṃ nu te etaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**Is that what you were referring to when you called me*";
P_HTM[3709]="*‘bhūnahu samaṇo gotamo’”ti?**a life-destroyer?”*";
P_HTM[3710]="*“Etadeva kho pana me, bho gotama, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“That’s exactly what I was referring to.*";
P_HTM[3711]="*‘bhūnahu samaṇo gotamo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3712]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3713]="*Evañhi no sutte ocaratī”ti.**Because that’s what it implies in a discourse of ours.”*";
P_HTM[3714]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya:**“What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya?*";
P_HTM[3715]="*‘idhekacco cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi paricāritapubbo assa iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi, so aparena samayena rūpānaṃyeva samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā rūpataṇhaṃ pahāya rūpapariḷāhaṃ paṭivinodetvā vigatapipāso ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto vihareyya.**Take someone who used to amuse themselves with sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. Some time later—having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sights, and having given up craving and dispelled passion for sights—they would live rid of thirst, their mind peaceful inside.*";
P_HTM[3716]="*Imassa pana te, māgaṇḍiya, kimassa vacanīyan’”ti?**What would you have to say to them, Māgaṇḍiya?”*";
P_HTM[3717]="*“Na kiñci, bho gotama”.**“Nothing, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3718]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya:**“What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya?*";
P_HTM[3719]="*‘idhekacco sotaviññeyyehi saddehi … pe …**Take someone who used to amuse themselves with sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[3720]="*ghānaviññeyyehi gandhehi …**smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[3721]="*jivhāviññeyyehi rasehi …**tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[3722]="*kāyaviññeyyehi phoṭṭhabbehi paricāritapubbo assa iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi,**touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3723]="*so aparena samayena phoṭṭhabbānaṃyeva samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā phoṭṭhabbataṇhaṃ pahāya phoṭṭhabbapariḷāhaṃ paṭivinodetvā vigatapipāso ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto vihareyya.**Some time later—having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of touches, and having given up craving and dispelled passion for touches—they would live rid of thirst, their mind peaceful inside.*";
P_HTM[3724]="*Imassa pana te, māgaṇḍiya, kimassa vacanīyan’”ti?**What would you have to say to them, Māgaṇḍiya?”*";
P_HTM[3725]="*“Na kiñci, bho gotama”.**“Nothing, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3726]="*“Ahaṃ kho pana, māgaṇḍiya, pubbe agāriyabhūto samāno pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāresiṃ cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi, sotaviññeyyehi saddehi … pe …**“Well, when I was still a layperson I used to amuse myself, supplied and provided with sights known by the eye … sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[3727]="*ghānaviññeyyehi gandhehi …**smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[3728]="*jivhāviññeyyehi rasehi …**tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[3729]="*kāyaviññeyyehi phoṭṭhabbehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi.**touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3730]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, tayo pāsādā ahesuṃ—**I had three stilt longhouses—*";
P_HTM[3731]="*eko vassiko, eko hemantiko, eko gimhiko.**one for the rainy season, one for the winter, and one for the summer.*";
P_HTM[3732]="*So kho ahaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, vassike pāsāde vassike cattāro māse nippurisehi tūriyehi paricārayamāno na heṭṭhāpāsādaṃ orohāmi.**I stayed in a stilt longhouse without coming downstairs for the four months of the rainy season, where I was entertained by musicians—none of them men.*";
P_HTM[3733]="*So aparena samayena kāmānaṃyeva samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā kāmataṇhaṃ pahāya kāmapariḷāhaṃ paṭivinodetvā vigatapipāso ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto viharāmi.**Some time later—having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sensual pleasures, and having given up craving and dispelled passion for sensual pleasures—I live rid of thirst, my mind peaceful inside.*";
P_HTM[3734]="*So aññe satte passāmi kāmesu avītarāge kāmataṇhāhi khajjamāne kāmapariḷāhena pariḍayhamāne kāme paṭisevante.**I see other sentient beings who are not free from sensual pleasures being consumed by craving for sensual pleasures, burning with passion for sensual pleasures, indulging in sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[3735]="*So tesaṃ na pihemi, na tattha abhiramāmi.**I don’t envy them, nor do I hope to enjoy that.*";
P_HTM[3736]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3737]="*Yāhayaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, rati, aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi—**Because there is a satisfaction that is apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities,*";
P_HTM[3738]="*api dibbaṃ sukhaṃ samadhigayha tiṭṭhati—**which even achieves the level of heavenly pleasure.*";
P_HTM[3739]="*tāya ratiyā ramamāno hīnassa na pihemi, na tattha abhiramāmi.**Enjoying that satisfaction, I don’t envy what is inferior, nor do I hope to enjoy it.*";
P_HTM[3740]="*Seyyathāpi, māgaṇḍiya, gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreyya cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi …**Suppose there was a householder or a householder’s child who was rich, affluent, and wealthy. And they would amuse themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation. That is, sights known by the eye …*";
P_HTM[3741]="*pe …**sounds … smells … tastes …*";
P_HTM[3742]="*phoṭṭhabbehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi.**touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3743]="*So kāyena sucaritaṃ caritvā vācāya sucaritaṃ caritvā manasā sucaritaṃ caritvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ.**Having practiced good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, when their body breaks up, after death, they’d be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm, in the company of the gods of the Thirty-Three.*";
P_HTM[3744]="*So tattha nandane vane accharāsaṅghaparivuto dibbehi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreyya.**There they’d amuse themselves in the Garden of Delight, escorted by a band of nymphs, supplied and provided with the five kinds of heavenly sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3745]="*So passeyya gahapatiṃ vā gahapatiputtaṃ vā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitaṃ samaṅgībhūtaṃ paricārayamānaṃ.**Then they’d see a householder or a householder’s child amusing themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3746]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya, api nu so devaputto nandane vane accharāsaṅghaparivuto dibbehi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricārayamāno amussa gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā piheyya, mānusakānaṃ vā pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ mānusakehi vā kāmehi āvaṭṭeyyā”ti?**What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya? Would that god—amusing themselves in the Garden of Delight, escorted by a band of nymphs, supplied and provided with the five kinds of heavenly sensual stimulation—envy that householder or householder’s child their five kinds of human sensual stimulation, or return to human sensual pleasures?”*";
P_HTM[3747]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[3748]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3749]="*Mānusakehi, bho gotama, kāmehi dibbakāmā abhikkantatarā ca paṇītatarā cā”ti.**Because heavenly sensual pleasures are better than human sensual pleasures.”*";
P_HTM[3750]="*“Evameva kho ahaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, pubbe agāriyabhūto samāno pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāresiṃ cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi, sotaviññeyyehi saddehi … pe …**“In the same way, Māgaṇḍiya, when I was still a layperson I used to entertain myself with sights … sounds …*";
P_HTM[3751]="*ghānaviññeyyehi gandhehi …**smells …*";
P_HTM[3752]="*jivhāviññeyyehi rasehi …**tastes …*";
P_HTM[3753]="*kāyaviññeyyehi phoṭṭhabbehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi.**touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3754]="*So aparena samayena kāmānaṃyeva samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā kāmataṇhaṃ pahāya kāmapariḷāhaṃ paṭivinodetvā vigatapipāso ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto viharāmi.**Some time later—having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sensual pleasures, and having given up craving and dispelled passion for sensual pleasures—I live rid of thirst, my mind peaceful inside.*";
P_HTM[3755]="*So aññe satte passāmi kāmesu avītarāge kāmataṇhāhi khajjamāne kāmapariḷāhena pariḍayhamāne kāme paṭisevante, so tesaṃ na pihemi, na tattha abhiramāmi.**I see other sentient beings who are not free from sensual pleasures being consumed by craving for sensual pleasures, burning with passion for sensual pleasures, indulging in sensual pleasures. I don’t envy them, nor do I hope to enjoy that.*";
P_HTM[3756]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3757]="*Yāhayaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, rati aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi—**Because there is a satisfaction that is apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities,*";
P_HTM[3758]="*api dibbaṃ sukhaṃ samadhigayha tiṭṭhati—**which even achieves the level of heavenly pleasure.*";
P_HTM[3759]="*tāya ratiyā ramamāno hīnassa na pihemi, na tattha abhiramāmi.**Enjoying that satisfaction, I don’t envy what is inferior, nor do I hope to enjoy it.*";
P_HTM[3760]="*Seyyathāpi, māgaṇḍiya, kuṭṭhī puriso arugatto pakkagatto kimīhi khajjamāno nakhehi vaṇamukhāni vippatacchamāno aṅgārakāsuyā kāyaṃ paritāpeyya.**Suppose there was a person affected by leprosy, with sores and blisters on their limbs. Being devoured by worms, scratching with their nails at the opening of their wounds, they’d cauterize their body over a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[3761]="*Tassa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā bhisakkaṃ sallakattaṃ upaṭṭhāpeyyuṃ.**Their friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would get a field surgeon to treat them.*";
P_HTM[3762]="*Tassa so bhisakko sallakatto bhesajjaṃ kareyya.**The field surgeon would make medicine for them,*";
P_HTM[3763]="*So taṃ bhesajjaṃ āgamma kuṭṭhehi parimucceyya, arogo assa sukhī serī sayaṃvasī yena kāmaṃ gamo.**and by using that they’d be cured of leprosy. They’d be healthy, happy, autonomous, master of themselves, able to go where they wanted.*";
P_HTM[3764]="*So aññaṃ kuṭṭhiṃ purisaṃ passeyya arugattaṃ pakkagattaṃ kimīhi khajjamānaṃ nakhehi vaṇamukhāni vippatacchamānaṃ aṅgārakāsuyā kāyaṃ paritāpentaṃ.**Then they’d see another person affected by leprosy, with sores and blisters on their limbs, being devoured by worms, scratching with their nails at the opening of their wounds, cauterizing their body over a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[3765]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya,**What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya?*";
P_HTM[3766]="*api nu so puriso amussa kuṭṭhissa purisassa piheyya aṅgārakāsuyā vā bhesajjaṃ paṭisevanāya vā”ti?**Would that person envy that other person affected by leprosy for their pit of glowing coals or for taking medicine?”*";
P_HTM[3767]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[3768]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3769]="*Roge hi, bho gotama, sati bhesajjena karaṇīyaṃ hoti, roge asati na bhesajjena karaṇīyaṃ hotī”ti.**Because you need to take medicine only when there’s a disease. When there’s no disease, there’s no need for medicine.”*";
P_HTM[3770]="*“Evameva kho ahaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, pubbe agāriyabhūto samāno pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāresiṃ, cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi, sotaviññeyyehi saddehi … pe …**“In the same way, Māgaṇḍiya, when I was still a layperson I used to entertain myself with sights … sounds …*";
P_HTM[3771]="*ghānaviññeyyehi gandhehi …**smells …*";
P_HTM[3772]="*jivhāviññeyyehi rasehi …**tastes …*";
P_HTM[3773]="*kāyaviññeyyehi phoṭṭhabbehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi.**touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3774]="*So aparena samayena kāmānaṃyeva samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā kāmataṇhaṃ pahāya kāmapariḷāhaṃ paṭivinodetvā vigatapipāso ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto viharāmi.**Some time later—having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sensual pleasures, and having given up craving and dispelled passion for sensual pleasures—I live rid of thirst, my mind peaceful inside.*";
P_HTM[3775]="*So aññe satte passāmi kāmesu avītarāge kāmataṇhāhi khajjamāne kāmapariḷāhena pariḍayhamāne kāme paṭisevante.**I see other sentient beings who are not free from sensual pleasures being consumed by craving for sensual pleasures, burning with passion for sensual pleasures, indulging in sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[3776]="*So tesaṃ na pihemi, na tattha abhiramāmi.**I don’t envy them, nor do I hope to enjoy that.*";
P_HTM[3777]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3778]="*Yāhayaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, rati, aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi—**Because there is a satisfaction that is apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities,*";
P_HTM[3779]="*api dibbaṃ sukhaṃ samadhigayha tiṭṭhati—**which even achieves the level of heavenly pleasure.*";
P_HTM[3780]="*tāya ratiyā ramamāno hīnassa na pihemi, na tattha abhiramāmi.**Enjoying that satisfaction, I don’t envy what is inferior, nor do I hope to enjoy it.*";
P_HTM[3781]="*Seyyathāpi, māgaṇḍiya, kuṭṭhī puriso arugatto pakkagatto kimīhi khajjamāno nakhehi vaṇamukhāni vippatacchamāno aṅgārakāsuyā kāyaṃ paritāpeyya.**Suppose there was a person affected by leprosy, with sores and blisters on their limbs. Being devoured by worms, scratching with their nails at the opening of their wounds, they’d cauterize their body over a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[3782]="*Tassa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā bhisakkaṃ sallakattaṃ upaṭṭhāpeyyuṃ.**Their friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would get a field surgeon to treat them.*";
P_HTM[3783]="*Tassa so bhisakko sallakatto bhesajjaṃ kareyya.**The field surgeon would make medicine for them,*";
P_HTM[3784]="*So taṃ bhesajjaṃ āgamma kuṭṭhehi parimucceyya, arogo assa sukhī serī sayaṃvasī yena kāmaṃ gamo.**and by using that they’d be cured of leprosy. They’d be healthy, happy, autonomous, master of themselves, able to go where they wanted.*";
P_HTM[3785]="*Tamenaṃ dve balavanto purisā nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuṃ upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**Then two strong men would grab them by the arms and drag them towards the pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[3786]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya,**What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya?*";
P_HTM[3787]="*api nu so puriso iti citiceva kāyaṃ sannāmeyyā”ti?**Wouldn’t that person writhe and struggle to and fro?”*";
P_HTM[3788]="*“Evaṃ, bho gotama.**“Yes, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[3789]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3790]="*Asu hi, bho gotama, aggi dukkhasamphasso ceva mahābhitāpo ca mahāpariḷāho cā”ti.**Because that fire is really painful to touch, fiercely burning and scorching.”*";
P_HTM[3791]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya,**“What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya?*";
P_HTM[3792]="*idāneva nu kho so aggi dukkhasamphasso ceva mahābhitāpo ca mahāpariḷāho ca udāhu pubbepi so aggi dukkhasamphasso ceva mahābhitāpo ca mahāpariḷāho cā”ti?**Is it only now that the fire is really painful to touch, fiercely burning and scorching, or was it painful previously as well?”*";
P_HTM[3793]="*“Idāni ceva, bho gotama, so aggi dukkhasamphasso ceva mahābhitāpo ca mahāpariḷāho ca, pubbepi so aggi dukkhasamphasso ceva mahābhitāpo ca mahāpariḷāho ca.**“That fire is painful now and it was also painful previously.*";
P_HTM[3794]="*Asu ca, bho gotama, kuṭṭhī puriso arugatto pakkagatto kimīhi khajjamāno nakhehi vaṇamukhāni vippatacchamāno upahatindriyo dukkhasamphasseyeva aggismiṃ sukhamiti viparītasaññaṃ paccalatthā”ti.**That person was affected by leprosy, with sores and blisters on their limbs. Being devoured by worms, scratching with their nails at the opening of their wounds, their sense faculties were impaired. So even though the fire was actually painful to touch, they had a distorted perception that it was pleasant.”*";
P_HTM[3795]="*“Evameva kho, māgaṇḍiya, atītampi addhānaṃ kāmā dukkhasamphassā ceva mahābhitāpā ca mahāpariḷāhā ca, anāgatampi addhānaṃ kāmā dukkhasamphassā ceva mahābhitāpā ca mahāpariḷāhā ca, etarahipi paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ kāmā dukkhasamphassā ceva mahābhitāpā ca mahāpariḷāhā ca.**“In the same way, sensual pleasures of the past, future, and present are painful to touch, fiercely burning and scorching.*";
P_HTM[3796]="*Ime ca, māgaṇḍiya, sattā kāmesu avītarāgā kāmataṇhāhi khajjamānā kāmapariḷāhena pariḍayhamānā upahatindriyā dukkhasamphassesuyeva kāmesu sukhamiti viparītasaññaṃ paccalatthuṃ.**These sentient beings who are not free from sensual pleasures—being consumed by craving for sensual pleasures, burning with passion for sensual pleasures—have impaired sense faculties. So even though sensual pleasures are actually painful to touch, they have a distorted perception that they are pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3797]="*Seyyathāpi, māgaṇḍiya, kuṭṭhī puriso arugatto pakkagatto kimīhi khajjamāno nakhehi vaṇamukhāni vippatacchamāno aṅgārakāsuyā kāyaṃ paritāpeti.**Suppose there was a person affected by leprosy, with sores and blisters on their limbs. Being devoured by worms, scratching with their nails at the opening of their wounds, they’re cauterizing their body over a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[3798]="*Yathā yathā kho, māgaṇḍiya, asu kuṭṭhī puriso arugatto pakkagatto kimīhi khajjamāno nakhehi vaṇamukhāni vippatacchamāno aṅgārakāsuyā kāyaṃ paritāpeti tathā tathāssa tāni vaṇamukhāni asucitarāni ceva honti duggandhatarāni ca pūtikatarāni ca, hoti ceva kāci sātamattā assādamattā—yadidaṃ vaṇamukhānaṃ kaṇḍūvanahetu;**The more they scratch their wounds and cauterize their body, the more their wounds become foul, stinking, and infected. But still, they derive a degree of pleasure and gratification from the itchiness of their wounds.*";
P_HTM[3799]="*evameva kho, māgaṇḍiya, sattā kāmesu avītarāgā kāmataṇhāhi khajjamānā kāmapariḷāhena ca pariḍayhamānā kāme paṭisevanti.**In the same way, I see other sentient beings who are not free from sensual pleasures being consumed by craving for sensual pleasures, burning with passion for sensual pleasures, indulging in sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[3800]="*Yathā yathā kho, māgaṇḍiya, sattā kāmesu avītarāgā kāmataṇhāhi khajjamānā kāmapariḷāhena ca pariḍayhamānā kāme paṭisevanti tathā tathā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ kāmataṇhā ceva pavaḍḍhati, kāmapariḷāhena ca pariḍayhanti, hoti ceva sātamattā assādamattā—yadidaṃ pañcakāmaguṇe paṭicca.**The more they indulge in sensual pleasures, the more their craving for sensual pleasures grows, and the more they burn with passion for sensual pleasures. But still, they derive a degree of pleasure and gratification from the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3801]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya,**What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya?*";
P_HTM[3802]="*api nu te diṭṭho vā suto vā rājā vā rājamahāmatto vā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricārayamāno kāmataṇhaṃ appahāya kāmapariḷāhaṃ appaṭivinodetvā vigatapipāso ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto vihāsi vā viharati vā viharissati vā”ti?**Have you seen or heard of a king or a royal minister of the past, future, or present, amusing themselves supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation, who—without giving up craving for sensual pleasures and dispelling passion for sensual pleasures—lives rid of thirst, their mind peaceful inside?”*";
P_HTM[3803]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3804]="*“Sādhu, māgaṇḍiya.**“Good, Māgaṇḍiya.*";
P_HTM[3805]="*Mayāpi kho etaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, neva diṭṭhaṃ na sutaṃ rājā vā rājamahāmatto vā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricārayamāno kāmataṇhaṃ appahāya kāmapariḷāhaṃ appaṭivinodetvā vigatapipāso ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto vihāsi vā viharati vā viharissati vā.**Neither have I.*";
P_HTM[3806]="*Atha kho, māgaṇḍiya, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā vigatapipāsā ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacittā vihāsuṃ vā viharanti vā viharissanti vā sabbe te kāmānaṃyeva samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā kāmataṇhaṃ pahāya kāmapariḷāhaṃ paṭivinodetvā vigatapipāsā ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacittā vihāsuṃ vā viharanti vā viharissanti vā”ti.**On the contrary, all the ascetics or brahmins of the past, future, or present who live rid of thirst, their minds peaceful inside, do so after truly understanding the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sensual pleasures, and after giving up craving and dispelling passion for sensual pleasures.”*";
P_HTM[3807]="*Atha kho bhagavā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi:**Then on that occasion the Buddha was inspired to exclaim:*";
P_HTM[3808]="*“Ārogyaparamā lābhā,**“Health is the ultimate blessing;*";
P_HTM[3809]="*nibbānaṃ paramaṃ sukhaṃ;**extinguishment, the ultimate happiness.*";
P_HTM[3810]="*Aṭṭhaṅgiko ca maggānaṃ,**Of paths, the ultimate is eightfold—*";
P_HTM[3811]="*khemaṃ amatagāminan”ti.**it’s safe, and leads to the deathless.”*";
P_HTM[3812]="*Evaṃ vutte, māgaṇḍiyo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Māgaṇḍiya said to him,*";
P_HTM[3813]="*“acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama.**“It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[3814]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ bhotā gotamena:**How well said this was by Master Gotama!*";
P_HTM[3815]="*‘ārogyaparamā lābhā, nibbānaṃ paramaṃ sukhan’ti.**‘Health is the ultimate blessing; extinguishment, the ultimate happiness.’*";
P_HTM[3816]="*Mayāpi kho etaṃ, bho gotama, sutaṃ pubbakānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:**I’ve also heard that wanderers of the past, the teachers of teachers, said:*";
P_HTM[3817]="*‘ārogyaparamā lābhā, nibbānaṃ paramaṃ sukhan’ti;**‘Health is the ultimate blessing; extinguishment, the ultimate happiness.’*";
P_HTM[3818]="*tayidaṃ, bho gotama, sametī”ti.**And it agrees, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3819]="*“Yaṃ pana te etaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, sutaṃ pubbakānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:**“But Māgaṇḍiya, when you heard that wanderers of the past said this,*";
P_HTM[3820]="*‘ārogyaparamā lābhā, nibbānaṃ paramaṃ sukhan’ti, katamaṃ taṃ ārogyaṃ, katamaṃ taṃ nibbānan”ti?**what is that health? And what is that extinguishment?”*";
P_HTM[3821]="*Evaṃ vutte, māgaṇḍiyo paribbājako sakāneva sudaṃ gattāni pāṇinā anomajjati:**When he said this, Māgaṇḍiya stroked his own limbs with his hands, saying:*";
P_HTM[3822]="*“idantaṃ, bho gotama, ārogyaṃ, idantaṃ nibbānaṃ.**“This is that health, Master Gotama, this is that extinguishment!*";
P_HTM[3823]="*Ahañhi, bho gotama, etarahi arogo sukhī, na maṃ kiñci ābādhatī”ti.**For I am now healthy and happy, and have no afflictions.”*";
P_HTM[3824]="*“Seyyathāpi, māgaṇḍiya, jaccandho puriso;**“Māgaṇḍiya, suppose a person was born blind.*";
P_HTM[3825]="*so na passeyya kaṇhasukkāni rūpāni, na passeyya nīlakāni rūpāni, na passeyya pītakāni rūpāni, na passeyya lohitakāni rūpāni, na passeyya mañjiṭṭhakāni rūpāni, na passeyya samavisamaṃ, na passeyya tārakarūpāni, na passeyya candimasūriye.**They couldn’t see sights that are dark or bright, or blue, yellow, red, or magenta. They couldn’t see even and uneven ground, or the stars, or the moon and sun.*";
P_HTM[3826]="*So suṇeyya cakkhumato bhāsamānassa:**They might hear a sighted person saying:*";
P_HTM[3827]="*‘chekaṃ vata, bho, odātaṃ vatthaṃ abhirūpaṃ nimmalaṃ sucī’ti.**‘White cloth is really nice, it’s attractive, stainless, and clean.’*";
P_HTM[3828]="*So odātapariyesanaṃ careyya.**They’d go in search of white cloth.*";
P_HTM[3829]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro puriso telamalikatena sāhuḷicīrena vañceyya:**But someone would cheat them with a dirty, soiled garment, saying:*";
P_HTM[3830]="*‘idaṃ te, ambho purisa, odātaṃ vatthaṃ abhirūpaṃ nimmalaṃ sucī’ti.**‘Sir, here is a white cloth for you, it’s attractive, stainless, and clean.’*";
P_HTM[3831]="*So taṃ paṭiggaṇheyya, paṭiggahetvā pārupeyya, pārupetvā attamano attamanavācaṃ nicchāreyya:**They’d take it and put it on, expressing their gladness:*";
P_HTM[3832]="*‘chekaṃ vata, bho, odātaṃ vatthaṃ abhirūpaṃ nimmalaṃ sucī’ti.**‘White cloth is really nice, it’s attractive, stainless, and clean.’*";
P_HTM[3833]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya,**What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya?*";
P_HTM[3834]="*api nu so jaccandho puriso jānanto passanto amuṃ telamalikataṃ sāhuḷicīraṃ paṭiggaṇheyya, paṭiggahetvā pārupeyya, pārupetvā attamano attamanavācaṃ nicchāreyya:**Did that person blind from birth do this knowing and seeing,*";
P_HTM[3835]="*‘chekaṃ vata, bho, odātaṃ vatthaṃ abhirūpaṃ nimmalaṃ sucī’ti udāhu cakkhumato saddhāyā”ti?**or out of faith in the sighted person?”*";
P_HTM[3836]="*“Ajānanto hi, bho gotama, apassanto so jaccandho puriso amuṃ telamalikataṃ sāhuḷicīraṃ paṭiggaṇheyya, paṭiggahetvā pārupeyya, pārupetvā attamano attamanavācaṃ nicchāreyya:**“They did so not knowing or seeing,*";
P_HTM[3837]="*‘chekaṃ vata, bho, odātaṃ vatthaṃ abhirūpaṃ nimmalaṃ sucī’ti, cakkhumato saddhāyā”ti.**but out of faith in the sighted person.”*";
P_HTM[3838]="*“Evameva kho, māgaṇḍiya, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā andhā acakkhukā ajānantā ārogyaṃ, apassantā nibbānaṃ, atha ca panimaṃ gāthaṃ bhāsanti:**“In the same way, the wanderers who follow other paths are blind and sightless. Not knowing health and not seeing extinguishment, they still recite this verse:*";
P_HTM[3839]="*‘ārogyaparamā lābhā, nibbānaṃ paramaṃ sukhan’ti.**‘Health is the ultimate blessing; extinguishment, the ultimate happiness.’*";
P_HTM[3840]="*Pubbakehesā, māgaṇḍiya, arahantehi sammāsambuddhehi gāthā bhāsitā:**For this verse was recited by the perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas of the past:*";
P_HTM[3841]="*‘Ārogyaparamā lābhā,**‘Health is the ultimate blessing;*";
P_HTM[3842]="*nibbānaṃ paramaṃ sukhaṃ;**extinguishment, the ultimate happiness.*";
P_HTM[3843]="*Aṭṭhaṅgiko ca maggānaṃ,**Of paths, the ultimate is eightfold—*";
P_HTM[3844]="*khemaṃ amatagāminan’ti.**it’s safe, and leads to the deathless.'*";
P_HTM[3845]="*Sā etarahi anupubbena puthujjanagāthā.**These days it has gradually become a verse used by ordinary people.*";
P_HTM[3846]="*Ayaṃ kho pana, māgaṇḍiya, kāyo rogabhūto gaṇḍabhūto sallabhūto aghabhūto ābādhabhūto, so tvaṃ imaṃ kāyaṃ rogabhūtaṃ gaṇḍabhūtaṃ sallabhūtaṃ aghabhūtaṃ ābādhabhūtaṃ:**But Māgaṇḍiya, this body is a disease, an abscess, a dart, a misery, an affliction. Yet you say of this body:*";
P_HTM[3847]="*‘idantaṃ, bho gotama, ārogyaṃ, idantaṃ nibbānan’ti vadesi.**‘This is that health, this is that extinguishment!’*";
P_HTM[3848]="*Tañhi te, māgaṇḍiya, ariyaṃ cakkhuṃ natthi yena tvaṃ ariyena cakkhunā ārogyaṃ jāneyyāsi, nibbānaṃ passeyyāsī”ti.**Māgaṇḍiya, you don’t have the noble vision by which you might know health and see extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[3849]="*“Evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ bhoto gotamassa.**“I am quite confident that Master Gotama*";
P_HTM[3850]="*Pahoti me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetuṃ yathāhaṃ ārogyaṃ jāneyyaṃ, nibbānaṃ passeyyan”ti.**is capable of teaching me so that I can know health and see extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[3851]="*“Seyyathāpi, māgaṇḍiya, jaccandho puriso;**“Māgaṇḍiya, suppose a person was born blind.*";
P_HTM[3852]="*so na passeyya kaṇhasukkāni rūpāni, na passeyya nīlakāni rūpāni, na passeyya pītakāni rūpāni, na passeyya lohitakāni rūpāni, na passeyya mañjiṭṭhakāni rūpāni, na passeyya samavisamaṃ, na passeyya tārakarūpāni, na passeyya candimasūriye.**They couldn’t see sights that are dark or bright, or blue, yellow, red, or magenta. They couldn’t see even and uneven ground, or the stars, or the moon and sun.*";
P_HTM[3853]="*Tassa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā bhisakkaṃ sallakattaṃ upaṭṭhāpeyyuṃ.**Their friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would get a field surgeon to treat them.*";
P_HTM[3854]="*Tassa so bhisakko sallakatto bhesajjaṃ kareyya.**The field surgeon would make medicine for them,*";
P_HTM[3855]="*So taṃ bhesajjaṃ āgamma na cakkhūni uppādeyya, na cakkhūni visodheyya.**but when they used it their eyes were not cured and they still could not see clearly.*";
P_HTM[3856]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māgaṇḍiya,**What do you think, Māgaṇḍiya?*";
P_HTM[3857]="*nanu so vejjo yāvadeva kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti?**Wouldn’t that doctor just get weary and frustrated?”*";
P_HTM[3858]="*“Evaṃ, bho gotama”.**“Yes, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[3859]="*“Evameva kho, māgaṇḍiya, ahañce te dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ:**“In the same way, suppose I were to teach you the Dhamma, saying:*";
P_HTM[3860]="*‘idantaṃ ārogyaṃ, idantaṃ nibbānan’ti, so tvaṃ ārogyaṃ na jāneyyāsi, nibbānaṃ na passeyyāsi.**‘This is that health, this is that extinguishment.’ But you might not know health or see extinguishment,*";
P_HTM[3861]="*So mamassa kilamatho, sā mamassa vihesā”ti.**which would be wearying and troublesome for me.”*";
P_HTM[3862]="*“Evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ bhoto gotamassa.**“I am quite confident that Master Gotama*";
P_HTM[3863]="*Pahoti me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetuṃ yathāhaṃ ārogyaṃ jāneyyaṃ, nibbānaṃ passeyyan”ti.**is capable of teaching me so that I can know health and see extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[3864]="*“Seyyathāpi, māgaṇḍiya, jaccandho puriso;**“Māgaṇḍiya, suppose a person was born blind.*";
P_HTM[3865]="*so na passeyya kaṇhasukkāni rūpāni, na passeyya nīlakāni rūpāni, na passeyya pītakāni rūpāni, na passeyya lohitakāni rūpāni, na passeyya mañjiṭṭhakāni rūpāni, na passeyya samavisamaṃ, na passeyya tārakarūpāni, na passeyya candimasūriye.**They couldn’t see sights that are dark or bright, or blue, yellow, red, or magenta. They couldn’t see even and uneven ground, or the stars, or the moon and sun.*";
P_HTM[3866]="*So suṇeyya cakkhumato bhāsamānassa:**They might hear a sighted person saying:*";
P_HTM[3867]="*‘chekaṃ vata, bho, odātaṃ vatthaṃ abhirūpaṃ nimmalaṃ sucī’ti.**‘White cloth is really nice, it’s attractive, stainless, and clean.’*";
P_HTM[3868]="*So odātapariyesanaṃ careyya.**They’d go in search of white cloth.*";
P_HTM[3869]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro puriso telamalikatena sāhuḷicīrena vañceyya:**But someone would cheat them with a dirty, soiled garment, saying:*";
P_HTM[3870]="*‘idaṃ te, ambho purisa, odātaṃ vatthaṃ abhirūpaṃ nimmalaṃ sucī’ti.**‘Sir, here is a white cloth for you, it’s attractive, stainless, and clean.’*";
P_HTM[3871]="*So taṃ paṭiggaṇheyya, paṭiggahetvā pārupeyya.**They’d take it and put it on.*";
P_HTM[3872]="*Tassa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā bhisakkaṃ sallakattaṃ upaṭṭhāpeyyuṃ.**Their friends and colleagues, relatives and kin would get a field surgeon to treat them.*";
P_HTM[3873]="*Tassa so bhisakko sallakatto bhesajjaṃ kareyya—**The field surgeon would make medicine for them:*";
P_HTM[3874]="*uddhaṃvirecanaṃ adhovirecanaṃ añjanaṃ paccañjanaṃ natthukammaṃ.**emetics, purgatives, ointment, counter-ointment, or nasal treatment.*";
P_HTM[3875]="*So taṃ bhesajjaṃ āgamma cakkhūni uppādeyya, cakkhūni visodheyya.**And when they used it their eyes would be cured so that they could see clearly.*";
P_HTM[3876]="*Tassa saha cakkhuppādā yo amusmiṃ telamalikate sāhuḷicīre chandarāgo so pahīyetha.**As soon as their eyes were cured they’d lose all desire for that dirty, soiled garment.*";
P_HTM[3877]="*Tañca naṃ purisaṃ amittatopi daheyya, paccatthikatopi daheyya, api ca jīvitā voropetabbaṃ maññeyya:**Then they would consider that person to be no friend, but an enemy, and might even think of murdering them:*";
P_HTM[3878]="*‘dīgharattaṃ vata, bho, ahaṃ iminā purisena telamalikatena sāhuḷicīrena nikato vañcito paluddho—**‘For such a long time I’ve been cheated, tricked, and deceived by that person with this dirty, soiled garment when he said,*";
P_HTM[3879]="*idaṃ te, ambho purisa, odātaṃ vatthaṃ abhirūpaṃ nimmalaṃ sucī’ti.**“Sir, here is a white cloth for you, it’s attractive, stainless, and clean.”’*";
P_HTM[3880]="*Evameva kho, māgaṇḍiya, ahañce te dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ:**In the same way, Māgaṇḍiya, suppose I were to teach you the Dhamma, saying:*";
P_HTM[3881]="*‘idantaṃ ārogyaṃ, idantaṃ nibbānan’ti.**‘This is that health, this is that extinguishment.’*";
P_HTM[3882]="*So tvaṃ ārogyaṃ jāneyyāsi, nibbānaṃ passeyyāsi.**You might know health and see extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[3883]="*Tassa te saha cakkhuppādā yo pañcasupādānakkhandhesu chandarāgo so pahīyetha;**And as soon as your vision arises you might give up desire for the five grasping aggregates.*";
P_HTM[3884]="*api ca te evamassa:**And you might even think:*";
P_HTM[3885]="*‘dīgharattaṃ vata bho ahaṃ iminā cittena nikato vañcito paluddho.**‘For such a long time I’ve been cheated, tricked, and deceived by this mind.*";
P_HTM[3886]="*Ahañhi rūpaṃyeva upādiyamāno upādiyiṃ, vedanaṃyeva upādiyamāno upādiyiṃ, saññaṃyeva upādiyamāno upādiyiṃ, saṅkhāreyeva upādiyamāno upādiyiṃ, viññāṇaṃyeva upādiyamāno upādiyiṃ.**For what I have been grasping is only form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3887]="*Tassa me upādānapaccayā bhavo, bhavapaccayā jāti, jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti;**My grasping is a condition for continued existence. Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be.*";
P_HTM[3888]="*evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hotī’”ti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.’”*";
P_HTM[3889]="*“Evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ bhoto gotamassa.**“I am quite confident that Master Gotama*";
P_HTM[3890]="*Pahoti me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetuṃ yathāhaṃ imamhā āsanā anandho vuṭṭhaheyyan”ti.**is capable of teaching me so that I can rise from this seat cured of blindness.”*";
P_HTM[3891]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, sappurise bhajeyyāsi.**“Well then, Māgaṇḍiya, you should associate with good people.*";
P_HTM[3892]="*Yato kho tvaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, sappurise bhajissasi tato tvaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, saddhammaṃ sossasi;**When you associate with good people, you will hear the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3893]="*yato kho tvaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, saddhammaṃ sossasi tato tvaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, dhammānudhammaṃ paṭipajjissasi;**When you hear the true teaching, you’ll practice in line with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[3894]="*yato kho tvaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, dhammānudhammaṃ paṭipajjissasi tato tvaṃ, māgaṇḍiya, sāmaṃyeva ñassasi, sāmaṃ dakkhissasi—**When you practice in line with the teaching, you’ll know and see for yourself:*";
P_HTM[3895]="*ime rogā gaṇḍā sallā;**‘These are diseases, boils, and darts.*";
P_HTM[3896]="*idha rogā gaṇḍā sallā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And here is where diseases, boils, and darts cease without anything left over.’*";
P_HTM[3897]="*Tassa me upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho, bhavanirodhā jātinirodho, jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti;**When my grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease.*";
P_HTM[3898]="*evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.”*";
P_HTM[3899]="*Evaṃ vutte, māgaṇḍiyo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Māgaṇḍiya said to him,*";
P_HTM[3900]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[3901]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[3902]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3903]="*Labheyyāhaṃ bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti.**Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”*";
P_HTM[3904]="*“Yo kho, māgaṇḍiya, aññatitthiyapubbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhati pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhati upasampadaṃ, so cattāro māse parivasati; catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti, upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya.**“Māgaṇḍiya, if someone formerly ordained in another sect wishes to take the going forth, the ordination in this teaching and training, they must spend four months on probation. When four months have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, they’ll give the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.*";
P_HTM[3905]="*Api ca mettha puggalavemattatā viditā”ti.**However, I have recognized individual differences in this matter.”*";
P_HTM[3906]="*“Sace, bhante, aññatitthiyapubbā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhantā pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhantā upasampadaṃ cattāro māse parivasanti, catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya; ahaṃ cattāri vassāni parivasissāmi, catunnaṃ vassānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājentu, upasampādentu bhikkhubhāvāyā”ti.**“Sir, if four months probation are required in such a case, I’ll spend four years on probation. When four years have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, let them give me the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.”*";
P_HTM[3907]="*Alattha kho māgaṇḍiyo paribbājako bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ.**And the wanderer Māgaṇḍiya received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence.*";
P_HTM[3908]="*Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā māgaṇḍiyo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**Not long after his ordination, Venerable Māgaṇḍiya, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, realized the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[3909]="*“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi.**He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[3910]="*Aññataro kho panāyasmā māgaṇḍiyo arahataṃ ahosīti.**And Venerable Māgaṇḍiya became one of the perfected.*";
P_HTM[3911]="*Māgaṇḍiyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3912]="*76. Sandakasutta**With Sandaka*";
P_HTM[3913]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3914]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[3915]="*Tena kho pana samayena sandako paribbājako pilakkhaguhāyaṃ paṭivasati mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ pañcamattehi paribbājakasatehi.**Now at that time the wanderer Sandaka was residing at the cave of the wavy leaf fig tree together with a large assembly of around five hundred wanderers.*";
P_HTM[3916]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Ānanda came out of retreat and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3917]="*“āyāmāvuso, yena devakatasobbho tenupasaṅkamissāma guhādassanāyā”ti.**“Come, reverends, let’s go to the Devakata Pool to see the cave.”*";
P_HTM[3918]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3919]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena devakatasobbho tenupasaṅkami.**Then Ānanda together with several mendicants went to the Devakata Pool.*";
P_HTM[3920]="*Tena kho pana samayena sandako paribbājako mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ nisinno hoti unnādiniyā uccāsaddamahāsaddāya anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathentiyā, seyyathidaṃ—**Now at that time, Sandaka and the large assembly of wanderers were sitting together making an uproar, a dreadful racket. They engaged in all kinds of unworthy talk, such as*";
P_HTM[3921]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā.**talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence.*";
P_HTM[3922]="*Addasā kho sandako paribbājako āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Sandaka saw Ānanda coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[3923]="*Disvāna sakaṃ parisaṃ saṇṭhāpesi:**and hushed his own assembly,*";
P_HTM[3924]="*“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha;**“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.*";
P_HTM[3925]="*ayaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako āgacchati samaṇo ānando.**The ascetic Ānanda, a disciple of the ascetic Gotama, is coming.*";
P_HTM[3926]="*Yāvatā kho pana samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakā kosambiyaṃ paṭivasanti, ayaṃ tesaṃ aññataro samaṇo ānando.**He is included among the disciples of the ascetic Gotama, who is residing near Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[3927]="*Appasaddakāmā kho pana te āyasmanto appasaddavinītā appasaddassa vaṇṇavādino;**Such venerables like the quiet, are educated to be quiet, and praise the quiet.*";
P_HTM[3928]="*appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”*";
P_HTM[3929]="*Atha kho te paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**Then those wanderers fell silent.*";
P_HTM[3930]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena sandako paribbājako tenupasaṅkami.**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the wanderer Sandaka,*";
P_HTM[3931]="*Atha kho sandako paribbājako āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**who said to him,*";
P_HTM[3932]="*“etu kho bhavaṃ ānando, svāgataṃ bhoto ānandassa.**“Come, Master Ānanda! Welcome, Master Ānanda!*";
P_HTM[3933]="*Cirassaṃ kho bhavaṃ ānando imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya.**It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here.*";
P_HTM[3934]="*Nisīdatu bhavaṃ ānando, idamāsanaṃ paññattan”ti.**Please, sir, sit down, this seat is ready.”*";
P_HTM[3935]="*Nisīdi kho āyasmā ānando paññatte āsane.**Ānanda sat down on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[3936]="*Sandakopi kho paribbājako aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**while Sandaka took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[3937]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho sandakaṃ paribbājakaṃ āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Ānanda said to Sandaka,*";
P_HTM[3938]="*“kāya nuttha, sandaka, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?**“Sandaka, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was unfinished?”*";
P_HTM[3939]="*“Tiṭṭhatesā, bho ānanda, kathā yāya mayaṃ etarahi kathāya sannisinnā.**“Master Ānanda, leave aside what we were sitting talking about just now.*";
P_HTM[3940]="*Nesā bhoto ānandassa kathā dullabhā bhavissati pacchāpi savanāya.**It won’t be hard for you to hear about that later.*";
P_HTM[3941]="*Sādhu vata bhavantaṃyeva ānandaṃ paṭibhātu sake ācariyake dhammīkathā”ti.**It’d be great if Master Ānanda himself would give a Dhamma talk explaining his own tradition.”*";
P_HTM[3942]="*“Tena hi, sandaka, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, Sandaka, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[3943]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sandako paribbājako āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Sandaka.*";
P_HTM[3944]="*Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Venerable Ānanda said this:*";
P_HTM[3945]="*“cattārome, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena abrahmacariyavāsā akkhātā cattāri ca anassāsikāni brahmacariyāni akkhātāni, yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti.**“Sandaka, these things have been explained by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha: four ways that negate the spiritual life, and four kinds of unreliable spiritual life. A sensible person would, to the best of their ability, not practice such spiritual paths, and if they did practice them, they wouldn’t succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3946]="*“Katame pana te, bho ānanda, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāro abrahmacariyavāsā akkhātā, yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti?**“But Master Ānanda, what are the four ways that negate the spiritual life, and the four kinds of unreliable spiritual life?”*";
P_HTM[3947]="*“Idha, sandaka, ekacco satthā evaṃvādī hoti evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“Sandaka, take a certain teacher who has this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[3948]="*‘natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ, natthi hutaṃ, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko, natthi paroloko, natthi mātā, natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedenti.**‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no obligation to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.*";
P_HTM[3949]="*Cātumahābhūtiko ayaṃ puriso yadā kālaṃ karoti, pathavī pathavīkāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, āpo āpokāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, tejo tejokāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, vāyo vāyokāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, ākāsaṃ indriyāni saṅkamanti.**This person is made up of the four primary elements. When they die, the earth in their body merges and coalesces with the main mass of earth. The water in their body merges and coalesces with the main mass of water. The fire in their body merges and coalesces with the main mass of fire. The air in their body merges and coalesces with the main mass of air. The faculties are transferred to space.*";
P_HTM[3950]="*Āsandipañcamā purisā mataṃ ādāya gacchanti,**Four men with a bier carry away the corpse.*";
P_HTM[3951]="*yāvāḷāhanā padāni paññāyanti.**Their footprints show the way to the cemetery.*";
P_HTM[3952]="*Kāpotakāni aṭṭhīni bhavanti.**The bones become bleached.*";
P_HTM[3953]="*Bhassantā āhutiyo;**Offerings dedicated to the gods end in ashes.*";
P_HTM[3954]="*dattupaññattaṃ yadidaṃ dānaṃ.**Giving is a doctrine for morons.*";
P_HTM[3955]="*Tesaṃ tucchā musā vilāpo ye keci atthikavādaṃ vadanti.**When anyone affirms a positive teaching it’s just hollow, false nonsense.*";
P_HTM[3956]="*Bāle ca paṇḍite ca kāyassa bhedā ucchijjanti vinassanti na honti paraṃ maraṇā’ti.**Both the foolish and the astute are annihilated and destroyed when their body breaks up, and they don’t exist after death.’*";
P_HTM[3957]="*Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[3958]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—**‘This teacher has such a doctrine and view.*";
P_HTM[3959]="*natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ, natthi hutaṃ, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko, natthi paroloko, natthi mātā, natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedenti.* **";
P_HTM[3960]="*Cātumahābhūtiko ayaṃ puriso yadā kālaṃ karoti, pathavī pathavīkāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, āpo āpokāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, tejo tejokāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, vāyo vāyokāyaṃ anupeti anupagacchati, ākāsaṃ indriyāni saṅkamanti.* **";
P_HTM[3961]="*Āsandipañcamā purisā mataṃ ādāya gacchanti, yāvāḷāhanā padāni paññāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[3962]="*Kāpotakāni aṭṭhīni bhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[3963]="*Bhassantā āhutiyo;* **";
P_HTM[3964]="*dattupaññattaṃ yadidaṃ dānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3965]="*Tesaṃ tucchā musā vilāpo ye keci atthikavādaṃ vadanti.* **";
P_HTM[3966]="*Bāle ca paṇḍite ca kāyassa bhedā ucchijjanti vinassanti na honti paraṃ maraṇā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3967]="*Sace imassa bhoto satthuno saccaṃ vacanaṃ, akatena me ettha kataṃ, avusitena me ettha vusitaṃ.**If what that teacher says is true, both I who have not accomplished this and one who has accomplished it*";
P_HTM[3968]="*Ubhopi mayaṃ ettha samasamā sāmaññaṃ pattā, yo cāhaṃ na vadāmi ‘ubho kāyassa bhedā ucchijjissāma, vinassissāma, na bhavissāma paraṃ maraṇā’ti.**have attained exactly the same level. Yet I’m not one who says that both of us are annihilated and destroyed when our body breaks up, and we don’t exist after death.*";
P_HTM[3969]="*Atirekaṃ kho panimassa bhoto satthuno naggiyaṃ muṇḍiyaṃ ukkuṭikappadhānaṃ kesamassulocanaṃ, yohaṃ puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasanto kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhonto mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhārento jātarūparajataṃ sādiyanto iminā bhotā satthārā samasamagatiko bhavissāmi abhisamparāyaṃ.**But it’s superfluous for this teacher to go naked, shaven, persisting in squatting, tearing out their hair and beard. For I’m living at home with my children, using sandalwood imported from Kāsi, wearing garlands, perfumes, and makeup, and accepting gold and money. Yet I’ll have exactly the same destiny in the next life as this teacher.*";
P_HTM[3970]="*Sohaṃ kiṃ jānanto kiṃ passanto imasmiṃ satthari brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi?**What do I know or see that I should live the spiritual life under this teacher?*";
P_HTM[3971]="*‘So abrahmacariyavāso ayan’ti—**This negates the spiritual life.’*";
P_HTM[3972]="*iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati.**Realizing this, they leave disappointed.*";
P_HTM[3973]="*Ayaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena paṭhamo abrahmacariyavāso akkhāto yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**This is the first way that negates the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[3974]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā evaṃvādī hoti evaṃdiṭṭhi:**Furthermore, take a certain teacher who has this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[3975]="*‘karoto kārayato chindato chedāpayato pacato pācāpayato socayato socāpayato kilamato kilamāpayato phandato phandāpayato pāṇamatipātayato adinnaṃ ādiyato sandhiṃ chindato nillopaṃ harato ekāgārikaṃ karoto paripanthe tiṭṭhato paradāraṃ gacchato musā bhaṇato karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ.**‘Nothing bad is done by the doer when they punish, mutilate, torture, aggrieve, oppress, intimidate, or when they encourage others to do the same. Nothing bad is done when they kill, steal, break into houses, plunder wealth, steal from isolated buildings, commit highway robbery, commit adultery, and lie.*";
P_HTM[3976]="*Khurapariyantena cepi cakkena yo imissā pathaviyā pāṇe ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ kareyya, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo.**If you were to reduce all the living creatures of this earth to one heap and mass of flesh with a razor-edged chakram, no evil comes of that, and no outcome of evil.*";
P_HTM[3977]="*Dakkhiṇañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya hananto ghātento chindanto chedāpento pacanto pacāpento, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo.**If you were to go along the south bank of the Ganges killing, mutilating, and torturing, and encouraging others to do the same, no evil comes of that, and no outcome of evil.*";
P_HTM[3978]="*Uttarañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya dadanto dāpento yajanto yajāpento, natthi tatonidānaṃ puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo.**If you were to go along the north bank of the Ganges giving and sacrificing and encouraging others to do the same, no merit comes of that, and no outcome of merit.*";
P_HTM[3979]="*Dānena damena saṃyamena saccavajjena natthi puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo’ti.**In giving, self-control, restraint, and truthfulness there is no merit or outcome of merit.’*";
P_HTM[3980]="*Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[3981]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—**‘This teacher has such a doctrine and view.*";
P_HTM[3982]="*karoto kārayato chindato chedāpayato pacato pācāpayato socato socāpayato kilamato kilamāpayato phandato phandāpayato pāṇamatipātayato adinnaṃ ādiyato sandhiṃ chindato nillopaṃ harato ekāgārikaṃ karoto paripanthe tiṭṭhato paradāraṃ gacchato musā bhaṇato karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ khurapariyantena cepi cakkena yo imissā pathaviyā pāṇe ekaṃ maṃsakhalaṃ ekaṃ maṃsapuñjaṃ kareyya, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo.* **";
P_HTM[3983]="*Dakkhiṇañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya hananto ghātento chindanto chedāpento pacanto pacāpento, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo.* **";
P_HTM[3984]="*Uttarañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya dadanto dāpento yajanto yajāpento, natthi tatonidānaṃ puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo.* **";
P_HTM[3985]="*Dānena damena saṃyamena saccavajjena natthi puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3986]="*Sace imassa bhoto satthuno saccaṃ vacanaṃ, akatena me ettha kataṃ, avusitena me ettha vusitaṃ.**If what that teacher says is true, both I who have not accomplished this and one who has accomplished it*";
P_HTM[3987]="*Ubhopi mayaṃ ettha samasamā sāmaññaṃ pattā, yo cāhaṃ na vadāmi ‘ubhinnaṃ kurutaṃ na karīyati pāpan’ti.**have attained exactly the same level. Yet I’m not one who says that when both of us act, nothing wrong is done.*";
P_HTM[3988]="*Atirekaṃ kho panimassa bhoto satthuno naggiyaṃ muṇḍiyaṃ ukkuṭikappadhānaṃ kesamassulocanaṃ, yohaṃ puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasanto kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhonto mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhārento jātarūparajataṃ sādiyanto iminā bhotā satthārā samasamagatiko bhavissāmi abhisamparāyaṃ.**But it’s superfluous for this teacher to go naked, shaven, persisting in squatting, tearing out their hair and beard. For I’m living at home with my children, using sandalwood imported from Kāsi, wearing garlands, perfumes, and makeup, and accepting gold and money. Yet I’ll have exactly the same destiny in the next life as this teacher.*";
P_HTM[3989]="*Sohaṃ kiṃ jānanto kiṃ passanto imasmiṃ satthari brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi?**What do I know or see that I should live the spiritual life under this teacher?*";
P_HTM[3990]="*‘So abrahmacariyavāso ayan’ti**This negates the spiritual life.’*";
P_HTM[3991]="*iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati.**Realizing this, they leave disappointed.*";
P_HTM[3992]="*Ayaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dutiyo abrahmacariyavāso akkhāto yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**This is the second way that negates the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[3993]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā evaṃvādī hoti evaṃdiṭṭhi:**Furthermore, take a certain teacher who has this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[3994]="*‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya;**‘There is no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[3995]="*ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti;**Sentient beings are corrupted without cause or reason.*";
P_HTM[3996]="*natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;**There’s no cause or condition for the purification of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[3997]="*ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhanti;**Sentient beings are purified without cause or reason.*";
P_HTM[3998]="*natthi balaṃ, natthi vīriyaṃ, natthi purisathāmo, natthi purisaparakkamo;**There is no power, no energy, no manly strength or vigor.*";
P_HTM[3999]="*sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā niyatisaṅgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti.**All sentient beings, all living creatures, all beings, all souls lack control, power, and energy. Molded by destiny, circumstance, and nature, they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth.’*";
P_HTM[4000]="*Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[4001]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—**‘This teacher has such a doctrine and view.*";
P_HTM[4002]="*natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya, ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti.* **";
P_HTM[4003]="*Natthi hetu natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā, ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhanti.* **";
P_HTM[4004]="*Natthi balaṃ, natthi vīriyaṃ, natthi purisathāmo, natthi purisaparakkamo, sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā niyatisaṅgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4005]="*Sace imassa bhoto satthuno saccaṃ vacanaṃ, akatena me ettha kataṃ, avusitena me ettha vusitaṃ.**If what that teacher says is true, both I who have not accomplished this and one who has accomplished it*";
P_HTM[4006]="*Ubhopi mayaṃ ettha samasamā sāmaññaṃ pattā, yo cāhaṃ na vadāmi ‘ubho ahetū appaccayā visujjhissāmā’ti.**have attained exactly the same level. Yet I’m not one who says that both of us are purified without cause or reason.*";
P_HTM[4007]="*Atirekaṃ kho panimassa bhoto satthuno naggiyaṃ muṇḍiyaṃ ukkuṭikappadhānaṃ kesamassulocanaṃ, yohaṃ puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasanto kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhonto mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhārento jātarūparajataṃ sādiyanto iminā bhotā satthārā samasamagatiko bhavissāmi abhisamparāyaṃ.**But it’s superfluous for this teacher to go naked, shaven, persisting in squatting, tearing out their hair and beard. For I’m living at home with my children, using sandalwood imported from Kāsi, wearing garlands, perfumes, and makeup, and accepting gold and money. Yet I’ll have exactly the same destiny in the next life as this teacher.*";
P_HTM[4008]="*Sohaṃ kiṃ jānanto kiṃ passanto imasmiṃ satthari brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi?**What do I know or see that I should live the spiritual life under this teacher?*";
P_HTM[4009]="*‘So abrahmacariyavāso ayan’ti—**This negates the spiritual life.’*";
P_HTM[4010]="*iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati.**Realizing this, they leave disappointed.*";
P_HTM[4011]="*Ayaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena tatiyo abrahmacariyavāso akkhāto yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**This is the third way that negates the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[4012]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā evaṃvādī hoti evaṃdiṭṭhi:**Furthermore, take a certain teacher who has this doctrine and view:*";
P_HTM[4013]="*‘sattime kāyā akaṭā akaṭavidhā animmitā animmātā vañjhā kūṭaṭṭhā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā,**‘There are these seven substances that are not made, not derived, not created, without a creator, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar.*";
P_HTM[4014]="*te na iñjanti na vipariṇamanti na aññamaññaṃ byābādhenti nālaṃ aññamaññassa sukhāya vā dukkhāya vā sukhadukkhāya vā.**They don’t move or deteriorate or obstruct each other. They’re unable to cause pleasure, pain, or neutral feeling to each other.*";
P_HTM[4015]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[4016]="*Pathavīkāyo āpokāyo tejokāyo vāyokāyo sukhe dukkhe jīve sattame—**The substances of earth, water, fire, air; pleasure, pain, and the soul is the seventh.*";
P_HTM[4017]="*ime sattakāyā akaṭā akaṭavidhā animmitā animmātā vañjhā kūṭaṭṭhā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā.**These seven substances are not made, not derived, not created, without a creator, barren, steady as a mountain peak, standing firm like a pillar.*";
P_HTM[4018]="*Te na iñjanti na vipariṇamanti na aññamaññaṃ byābādhenti. Nālaṃ aññamaññassa sukhāya vā dukkhāya vā sukhadukkhāya vā.**They don’t move or deteriorate or obstruct each other. They’re unable to cause pleasure, pain, or neutral feeling to each other.*";
P_HTM[4019]="*Tattha natthi hantā vā ghātetā vā sotā vā sāvetā vā viññātā vā viññāpetā vā.**And here there is no-one who kills or who makes others kill; no-one who learns or who educates others; no-one who understands or who helps others understand.*";
P_HTM[4020]="*Yopi tiṇhena satthena sīsaṃ chindati, na koci kañci jīvitā voropeti.**If you chop off someone’s head with a sharp sword, you don’t take anyone’s life.*";
P_HTM[4021]="*Sattannaṃ tveva kāyānamantarena satthaṃ vivaramanupatati.**The sword simply passes through the gap between the seven substances.*";
P_HTM[4022]="*Cuddasa kho panimāni yonipamukhasatasahassāni saṭṭhi ca satāni cha ca satāni pañca ca kammuno satāni pañca ca kammāni tīṇi ca kammāni, kamme ca aḍḍhakamme ca, dvaṭṭhipaṭipadā, dvaṭṭhantarakappā, chaḷābhijātiyo, aṭṭha purisabhūmiyo, ekūnapaññāsa ājīvakasate, ekūnapaññāsa paribbājakasate, ekūnapaññāsa nāgāvāsasate, vīse indriyasate, tiṃse nirayasate, chattiṃsa rajodhātuyo, satta saññīgabbhā, satta asaññīgabbhā, satta nigaṇṭhigabbhā, satta devā, satta mānusā, satta pesācā, satta sarā, satta pavuṭā, satta papātā, satta papātasatāni, satta supinā, satta supinasatāni, cullāsīti mahākappino satasahassāni, yāni bāle ca paṇḍite ca sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ karissanti.**There are 1.4 million main wombs, and 6,000, and 600. There are 500 deeds, and five, and three. There are deeds and half-deeds. There are 62 paths, 62 sub-eons, six classes of rebirth, and eight stages in a person’s life. There are 4,900 Ājīvaka ascetics, 4,900 wanderers, and 4,900 naked ascetics. There are 2,000 faculties, 3,000 hells, and 36 realms of dust. There are seven percipient embryos, seven non-percipient embryos, and seven embryos without attachments. There are seven gods, seven humans, and seven goblins. There are seven lakes, seven winds, seven cliffs, and 700 cliffs. There are seven dreams and 700 dreams. There are 8.4 million great eons through which the foolish and the astute transmigrate before making an end of suffering.*";
P_HTM[4023]="*Tattha natthi imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā aparipakkaṃ vā kammaṃ paripācessāmi, paripakkaṃ vā kammaṃ phussa phussa byantiṃ karissāmīti.**And here there is no such thing as this: “By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life I shall force unripened deeds to bear their fruit, or eliminate old deeds by experiencing their results little by little”—for that cannot be.*";
P_HTM[4024]="*Hevaṃ natthi doṇamite sukhadukkhe pariyantakate saṃsāre, natthi hāyanavaḍḍhane, natthi ukkaṃsāvakaṃse.**Pleasure and pain are allotted. Transmigration lasts only for a limited period, so there’s no increase or decrease, no getting better or worse.*";
P_HTM[4025]="*Seyyathāpi nāma suttaguḷe khitte nibbeṭhiyamānameva paleti;**It’s like how, when you toss a ball of string, it rolls away unraveling.*";
P_HTM[4026]="*evameva bāle ca paṇḍite ca sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ karissantī’ti.**In the same way, after transmigrating the foolish and the astute will make an end of suffering.’*";
P_HTM[4027]="*Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[4028]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi—**‘This teacher has such a doctrine and view.*";
P_HTM[4029]="*sattime kāyā akaṭā akaṭavidhā animmitā animmātā vañjhā kūṭaṭṭhā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā.* **";
P_HTM[4030]="*Te na iñjanti na vipariṇamanti na aññamaññaṃ byābādhenti.* **";
P_HTM[4031]="*Nālaṃ aññamaññassa sukhāya vā dukkhāya vā sukhadukkhāya vā.* **";
P_HTM[4032]="*Katame satta?* **";
P_HTM[4033]="*Pathavīkāyo āpokāyo tejokāyo vāyokāyo sukhe dukkhe jīve sattame—* **";
P_HTM[4034]="*ime satta kāyā akaṭā akaṭavidhā animmitā animmātā vañjhā kūṭaṭṭhā esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā.* **";
P_HTM[4035]="*Te na iñjanti na vipariṇamanti na aññamaññaṃ byābādhenti.* **";
P_HTM[4036]="*Nālaṃ aññamaññassa sukhāya vā dukkhāya vā sukhadukkhāya vā.* **";
P_HTM[4037]="*Tattha natthi hantā vā ghātetā vā sotā vā sāvetā vā viññātā vā viññāpetā vā.* **";
P_HTM[4038]="*Yopi tiṇhena satthena sīsaṃ chindati, na koci kañci jīvitā voropeti.* **";
P_HTM[4039]="*Sattannaṃ tveva kāyānamantarena satthaṃ vivaramanupatati.* **";
P_HTM[4040]="*Cuddasa kho panimāni yonipamukhasatasahassāni saṭṭhi ca satāni cha ca satāni pañca ca kammuno satāni pañca ca kammāni tīṇi ca kammāni, kamme ca aḍḍhakamme ca, dvaṭṭhipaṭipadā, dvaṭṭhantarakappā, chaḷābhijātiyo, aṭṭha purisabhūmiyo, ekūnapaññāsa ājīvakasate, ekūnapaññāsa paribbājakasate, ekūnapaññāsa nāgāvāsasate, vīse indriyasate, tiṃse nirayasate, chattiṃsa rajodhātuyo, satta saññīgabbhā, satta asaññīgabbhā, satta nigaṇṭhigabbhā, satta devā, satta mānusā, satta pesācā, satta sarā, satta pavuṭā, satta papātā, satta papātasatāni, satta supinā, satta supinasatāni, cullāsīti mahākappino satasahassāni, yāni bāle ca paṇḍite ca sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ karissanti.* **";
P_HTM[4041]="*Tattha natthi imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā aparipakkaṃ vā kammaṃ paripācessāmi, paripakkaṃ vā kammaṃ phussa phussa byantiṃ karissāmīti, hevaṃ natthi doṇamite sukhadukkhe pariyantakate saṃsāre, natthi hāyanavaḍḍhane, natthi ukkaṃsāvakaṃse.* **";
P_HTM[4042]="*Seyyathāpi nāma suttaguḷe khitte nibbeṭhiyamānameva paleti;* **";
P_HTM[4043]="*evameva bāle ca paṇḍite ca sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ karissantī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4044]="*Sace pana imassa bhoto satthuno saccaṃ vacanaṃ, akatena me ettha kataṃ, avusitena me ettha vusitaṃ.**If what that teacher says is true, both I who have not accomplished this and one who has accomplished it*";
P_HTM[4045]="*Ubhopi mayaṃ ettha samasamā sāmaññaṃ pattā, yo cāhaṃ na vadāmi ‘ubho sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ karissāmā’ti.**have attained exactly the same level. Yet I’m not one who says that after transmigrating both of us will make an end of suffering.*";
P_HTM[4046]="*Atirekaṃ kho panimassa bhoto satthuno naggiyaṃ muṇḍiyaṃ ukkuṭikappadhānaṃ kesamassulocanaṃ, yohaṃ puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasanto kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhonto mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhārento jātarūparajataṃ sādiyanto iminā bhotā satthārā samasamagatiko bhavissāmi abhisamparāyaṃ.**But it’s superfluous for this teacher to go naked, shaven, persisting in squatting, tearing out their hair and beard. For I’m living at home with my children, using sandalwood imported from Kāsi, wearing garlands, perfumes, and makeup, and accepting gold and money. Yet I’ll have exactly the same destiny in the next life as this teacher.*";
P_HTM[4047]="*Sohaṃ kiṃ jānanto kiṃ passanto imasmiṃ satthari brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi?**What do I know or see that I should live the spiritual life under this teacher?*";
P_HTM[4048]="*‘So abrahmacariyavāso ayan’ti—**This negates the spiritual life.’*";
P_HTM[4049]="*iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati.**Realizing this, they leave disappointed.*";
P_HTM[4050]="*Ayaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena catuttho abrahmacariyavāso akkhāto yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**This is the fourth way that negates the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[4051]="*Ime kho te, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāro abrahmacariyavāsā akkhātā yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti.**These are the four ways that negate the spiritual life that have been explained by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. A sensible person would, to the best of their ability, not practice such spiritual paths, and if they did practice them, they wouldn’t succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.”*";
P_HTM[4052]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho ānanda, abbhutaṃ, bho ānanda.**“It’s incredible, Master Ānanda, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[4053]="*Yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāro abrahmacariyavāsāva samānā ‘abrahmacariyavāsā’ti akkhātā yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalanti.**how these four ways that negate the spiritual life have been explained by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4054]="*Katamāni pana tāni, bho ānanda, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāri anassāsikāni brahmacariyāni akkhātāni yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti?**But Master Ānanda, what are the four kinds of unreliable spiritual life?”*";
P_HTM[4055]="*“Idha, sandaka, ekacco satthā sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti:**“Sandaka, take a certain teacher who claims to be all-knowing and all-seeing, to know and see everything without exception, thus:*";
P_HTM[4056]="*‘carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti.**‘Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.’*";
P_HTM[4057]="*So suññampi agāraṃ pavisati, piṇḍampi na labhati, kukkuropi ḍaṃsati, caṇḍenapi hatthinā samāgacchati, caṇḍenapi assena samāgacchati, caṇḍenapi goṇena samāgacchati, itthiyāpi purisassapi nāmampi gottampi pucchati, gāmassapi nigamassapi nāmampi maggampi pucchati.**He enters an empty house; he gets no alms-food; a dog bites him; he encounters a wild elephant, a wild horse, and a wild cow; he asks the name and clan of a woman or man; he asks the name and path to a village or town.*";
P_HTM[4058]="*So ‘kimidan’ti puṭṭho samāno ‘suññaṃ me agāraṃ pavisitabbaṃ ahosi’, tena pāvisiṃ; ‘piṇḍampi aladdhabbaṃ ahosi’, tena nālatthaṃ; ‘kukkurena ḍaṃsitabbaṃ ahosi’, tenamhi daṭṭho; ‘caṇḍena hatthinā samāgantabbaṃ ahosi’, tena samāgamiṃ; ‘caṇḍena assena samāgantabbaṃ ahosi’, tena samāgamiṃ; ‘caṇḍena goṇena samāgantabbaṃ ahosi’, tena samāgamiṃ; ‘itthiyāpi purisassapi nāmampi gottampi pucchitabbaṃ ahosi’, tena pucchiṃ; ‘gāmassapi nigamassapi nāmampi maggampi pucchitabbaṃ ahosi’, tena pucchinti.**When asked, ‘Why is this?’ he answers: ‘I had to enter an empty house, that’s why I entered it. I had to get no alms-food, that’s why I got none. I had to get bitten by a dog, that’s why I was bitten. I had to encounter a wild elephant, a wild horse, and a wild cow, that’s why I encountered them. I had to ask the name and clan of a woman or man, that’s why I asked. I had to ask the name and path to a village or town, that’s why I asked.’*";
P_HTM[4059]="*Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[4060]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti … pe … ‘gāmassapi nigamassapi nāmampi maggampi pucchitabbaṃ ahosi, tena pucchin’ti.**‘This teacher makes such a claim, but he answers in such a way.*";
P_HTM[4061]="*So ‘anassāsikaṃ idaṃ brahmacariyan’ti—**This spiritual life is unreliable.’*";
P_HTM[4062]="*iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati.**Realizing this, they leave disappointed.*";
P_HTM[4063]="*Idaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena paṭhamaṃ anassāsikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ akkhātaṃ yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**This is the first kind of unreliable spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[4064]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā anussaviko hoti anussavasacco.**Furthermore, take another teacher who is an oral transmitter, who takes oral transmission to be the truth.*";
P_HTM[4065]="*So anussavena itihitihaparamparāya piṭakasampadāya dhammaṃ deseti.**He teaches by oral transmission, by the lineage of testament, by canonical authority.*";
P_HTM[4066]="*Anussavikassa kho pana, sandaka, satthuno anussavasaccassa sussutampi hoti dussutampi hoti tathāpi hoti aññathāpi hoti.**But when a teacher takes oral transmission to be the truth, some of that is well learned, some poorly learned, some true, and some otherwise.*";
P_HTM[4067]="*Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[4068]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā anussaviko anussavasacco so anussavena itihitihaparamparāya piṭakasampadāya dhammaṃ deseti.**‘This teacher takes oral transmission to be the truth. He teaches by oral transmission, by the lineage of testament, by canonical authority.*";
P_HTM[4069]="*Anussavikassa kho pana satthuno anussavasaccassa sussutampi hoti dussutampi hoti tathāpi hoti aññathāpi hoti’.**But when a teacher takes oral transmission to be the truth, some of that is well learned, some poorly learned, some true, and some otherwise.*";
P_HTM[4070]="*So ‘anassāsikaṃ idaṃ brahmacariyan’ti—**This spiritual life is unreliable.’*";
P_HTM[4071]="*iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati.**Realizing this, they leave disappointed.*";
P_HTM[4072]="*Idaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dutiyaṃ anassāsikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ akkhātaṃ yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**This is the second kind of unreliable spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[4073]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā takkī hoti vīmaṃsī.**Furthermore, take another teacher who relies on logic and inquiry.*";
P_HTM[4074]="*So takkapariyāhataṃ vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayampaṭibhānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.**He teaches what he has worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, expressing his own perspective.*";
P_HTM[4075]="*Takkissa kho pana, sandaka, satthuno vīmaṃsissa sutakkitampi hoti duttakkitampi hoti tathāpi hoti aññathāpi hoti.**But when a teacher relies on logic and inquiry, some of that is well reasoned, some poorly reasoned, some true, and some otherwise.*";
P_HTM[4076]="*Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[4077]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā takkī vīmaṃsī.**‘This teacher relies on logic and inquiry.*";
P_HTM[4078]="*So takkapariyāhataṃ vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayampaṭibhānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.**He teaches what he has worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, expressing his own perspective.*";
P_HTM[4079]="*Takkissa kho pana satthuno vīmaṃsissa sutakkitampi hoti duttakkitampi hoti tathāpi hoti aññathāpi hoti’.**But when a teacher relies on logic and inquiry, some of that is well reasoned, some poorly reasoned, some true, and some otherwise.*";
P_HTM[4080]="*So ‘anassāsikaṃ idaṃ brahmacariyan’ti—**This spiritual life is unreliable.’*";
P_HTM[4081]="*iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati.**Realizing this, they leave disappointed.*";
P_HTM[4082]="*Idaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena tatiyaṃ anassāsikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ akkhātaṃ yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**This is the third kind of unreliable spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[4083]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā mando hoti momūho.**Furthermore, take another teacher who is dull and stupid.*";
P_HTM[4084]="*So mandattā momūhattā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjati amarāvikkhepaṃ:**Because of that, whenever he’s asked a question, he resorts to evasiveness and equivocation:*";
P_HTM[4085]="*‘evantipi me no, tathātipi me no, aññathātipi me no, notipi me no, no notipi me no’ti.**‘I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t deny it’s not so.’*";
P_HTM[4086]="*Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:**A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:*";
P_HTM[4087]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā mando momūho.**‘This teacher is dull and stupid.*";
P_HTM[4088]="*So mandattā momūhattā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjati amarāvikkhepaṃ—**Because of that, whenever he’s asked a question, he resorts to evasiveness and equivocation:*";
P_HTM[4089]="*evantipi me no, tathātipi me no, aññathātipi me no, notipi me no, no notipi me no’ti.**“I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t deny it’s not so.”*";
P_HTM[4090]="*So ‘anassāsikaṃ idaṃ brahmacariyan’ti—**This spiritual life is unreliable.’*";
P_HTM[4091]="*iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati.**Realizing this, they leave disappointed.*";
P_HTM[4092]="*Idaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena catutthaṃ anassāsikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ akkhātaṃ yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**This is the fourth kind of unreliable spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[4093]="*Imāni kho tāni, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāri anassāsikāni brahmacariyāni akkhātāni yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti.**These are the four kinds of unreliable spiritual life that have been explained by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. A sensible person would, to the best of their ability, not practice such spiritual paths, and if they did practice them, they wouldn’t complete the procedure of the skillful teaching.”*";
P_HTM[4094]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho ānanda, abbhutaṃ, bho ānanda.**“It’s incredible, Master Ānanda, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[4095]="*Yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāri anassāsikāneva brahmacariyāni anassāsikāni brahmacariyānīti akkhātāni yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**how these four kinds of unreliable spiritual life have been explained by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4096]="*So pana, bho ānanda, satthā kiṃ vādī kiṃ akkhāyī yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti.**But, Master Ānanda, what would a teacher say and explain so that a sensible person would, to the best of their ability, practice such a spiritual path, and once practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching?”*";
P_HTM[4097]="*“Idha, sandaka, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā … pe …**“Sandaka, it’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed. …*";
P_HTM[4098]="*so ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe**He gives up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4099]="*vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, he enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4100]="*Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[4101]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant … enters and remains in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[4102]="*Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4103]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[4104]="*Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4105]="*Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[4106]="*Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[4107]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[4108]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. … They recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[4109]="*Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[4110]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[4111]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. … They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[4112]="*Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[4113]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4114]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti;**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[4115]="*‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[4116]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati.**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4117]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[4118]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[4119]="*Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti.**A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching.”*";
P_HTM[4120]="*“Yo pana so, bho ānanda, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññā vimutto paribhuñjeyya so kāme”ti?**“But Master Ānanda, when a mendicant is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment—could they still enjoy sensual pleasures?”*";
P_HTM[4121]="*“Yo so, sandaka, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, abhabbo so pañcaṭṭhānāni ajjhācarituṃ.**“Sandaka, a mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment—can’t transgress in five respects.*";
P_HTM[4122]="*Abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropetuṃ, abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātuṃ, abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevetuṃ, abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sampajānamusā bhāsituṃ, abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sannidhikārakaṃ kāme paribhuñjituṃ, seyyathāpi pubbe agāriyabhūto.**A mendicant with defilements ended can’t deliberately take the life of a living creature, take something with the intention to steal, have sex, tell a deliberate lie, or store up goods for their own enjoyment like they did as a lay person.*";
P_HTM[4123]="*Yo so, sandaka, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, abhabbo so imāni pañcaṭṭhānāni ajjhācaritun”ti.**A mendicant who is perfected can’t transgress in these five respects.”*";
P_HTM[4124]="*“Yo pana so, bho ānanda, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto tassa carato ceva tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ:**“But Master Ānanda, when a mendicant is perfected, would the knowledge and vision that their defilements are ended be constantly and continually present to them, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking?”*";
P_HTM[4125]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4126]="*“Tena hi, sandaka, upamaṃ te karissāmi;**“Well then, Sandaka, I shall give you a simile.*";
P_HTM[4127]="*upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti.**For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said.*";
P_HTM[4128]="*Seyyathāpi, sandaka, purisassa hatthapādā chinnā;**Suppose there was a person whose hands and feet had been amputated.*";
P_HTM[4129]="*tassa carato ceva tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ jānāti:**Would they be aware that their hands and feet had been amputated constantly and continually, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking?*";
P_HTM[4130]="*‘chinnā me hatthapādā’ti, udāhu paccavekkhamāno jānāti:**Or would they be aware of it only when they checked it?”*";
P_HTM[4131]="*‘chinnā me hatthapādā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4132]="*“Na kho, bho ānanda, so puriso satataṃ samitaṃ jānāti:**“They wouldn’t be aware of it constantly,*";
P_HTM[4133]="*‘chinnā me hatthapādā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4134]="*Api ca kho pana naṃ paccavekkhamāno jānāti:**only when they checked it.”*";
P_HTM[4135]="*‘chinnā me hatthapādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4136]="*“Evameva kho, sandaka, yo so bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto tassa carato ceva tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ na paccupaṭṭhitaṃ:**“In the same way, when a mendicant is perfected, the knowledge and vision that their defilements are ended is not constantly and continually present to them, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.*";
P_HTM[4137]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti;* **";
P_HTM[4138]="*api ca kho pana naṃ paccavekkhamāno jānāti:**Rather, they are aware of it only when they checked it.”*";
P_HTM[4139]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4140]="*“Kīvabahukā pana, bho ānanda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye niyyātāro”ti?**“But Reverend Ānanda, how many emancipators are there in this teaching and training?”*";
P_HTM[4141]="*“Na kho, sandaka, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye imasmiṃ dhammavinaye niyyātāro”ti.**“There are not just one hundred emancipators, Sandaka, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that in this teaching and training.”*";
P_HTM[4142]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho ānanda, abbhutaṃ, bho ānanda.**“It’s incredible, Master Ānanda, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[4143]="*Na ca nāma sadhammokkaṃsanā bhavissati, na paradhammavambhanā, āyatane ca dhammadesanā tāva bahukā ca niyyātāro paññāyissanti.**Namely, that there’s no glorifying one’s own teaching and putting down the teaching of others. The Dhamma is taught in its own field, and so many emancipators are recognized.*";
P_HTM[4144]="*Ime panājīvakā puttamatāya puttā attānañceva ukkaṃsenti, pare ca vambhenti tayo ceva niyyātāro paññapenti, seyyathidaṃ—**But these Ājīvakas, those sons of dead sons, glorify themselves and put others down. And they only recognize three emancipators:*";
P_HTM[4145]="*nandaṃ vacchaṃ, kisaṃ saṅkiccaṃ, makkhaliṃ gosālan”ti.**Nanda Vaccha, Kisa Saṅkicca, and Makkhali Gosāla.”*";
P_HTM[4146]="*Atha kho sandako paribbājako sakaṃ parisaṃ āmantesi:**Then the wanderer Sandaka addressed his own assembly,*";
P_HTM[4147]="*“carantu bhonto samaṇe gotame brahmacariyavāso.**“Go, good sirs. The spiritual life is lived under the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[4148]="*Na dāni sukaraṃ amhehi lābhasakkārasiloke pariccajitun”ti.**It’s not easy for me to give up possessions, honor, or popularity now.”*";
P_HTM[4149]="*Iti hidaṃ sandako paribbājako sakaṃ parisaṃ uyyojesi bhagavati brahmacariyeti.**And that’s how the wanderer Sandaka sent his own assembly to live the spiritual life under the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4150]="*Sandakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4151]="*77. Mahāsakuludāyisutta**The Longer Discourse with Sakuludāyī*";
P_HTM[4152]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4153]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4154]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā paribbājakā moranivāpe paribbājakārāme paṭivasanti, seyyathidaṃ—**Now at that time several very well-known wanderers were residing in the monastery of the wanderers in the peacocks’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4155]="*annabhāro varadharo sakuludāyī ca paribbājako aññe ca abhiññātā abhiññātā paribbājakā.**They included Annabhāra, Varadhara, Sakuludāyī, and other very well-known wanderers.*";
P_HTM[4156]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Rājagaha for alms.*";
P_HTM[4157]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[4158]="*“atippago kho tāva rājagahe piṇḍāya carituṃ.**“It’s too early to wander for alms in Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[4159]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yena moranivāpo paribbājakārāmo yena sakuludāyī paribbājako tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti.**Why don’t I visit the wanderer Sakuludāyī at the monastery of the wanderers in the peacocks’ feeding ground?”*";
P_HTM[4160]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena moranivāpo paribbājakārāmo tenupasaṅkami.**So the Buddha went to the monastery of the wanderers.*";
P_HTM[4161]="*Tena kho pana samayena sakuludāyī paribbājako mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ nisinno hoti unnādiniyā uccāsaddamahāsaddāya anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathentiyā, seyyathidaṃ—**Now at that time, Sakuludāyī was sitting together with a large assembly of wanderers making an uproar, a dreadful racket. They engaged in all kinds of unworthy talk, such as*";
P_HTM[4162]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā.**talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence.*";
P_HTM[4163]="*Addasā kho sakuludāyī paribbājako bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Sakuludāyī saw the Buddha coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[4164]="*Disvāna sakaṃ parisaṃ saṇṭhāpeti:**and hushed his own assembly,*";
P_HTM[4165]="*“appasaddā bhonto hontu;**“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.*";
P_HTM[4166]="*mā bhonto saddamakattha.* **";
P_HTM[4167]="*Ayaṃ samaṇo gotamo āgacchati;**Here comes the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[4168]="*appasaddakāmo kho pana so āyasmā appasaddassa vaṇṇavādī.**The venerable likes quiet and praises quiet.*";
P_HTM[4169]="*Appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”*";
P_HTM[4170]="*Atha kho te paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**Then those wanderers fell silent.*";
P_HTM[4171]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena sakuludāyī paribbājako tenupasaṅkami.**Then the Buddha approached Sakuludāyī,*";
P_HTM[4172]="*Atha kho sakuludāyī paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**who said to him,*";
P_HTM[4173]="*“etu kho, bhante, bhagavā.**“Come, Blessed One!*";
P_HTM[4174]="*Svāgataṃ, bhante, bhagavato.**Welcome, Blessed One!*";
P_HTM[4175]="*Cirassaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavā imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya.**It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here.*";
P_HTM[4176]="*Nisīdatu, bhante, bhagavā;**Please, sir, sit down, this seat is ready.”*";
P_HTM[4177]="*idamāsanaṃ paññattan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4178]="*Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane.**The Buddha sat on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[4179]="*Sakuludāyīpi kho paribbājako aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**while Sakuludāyī took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[4180]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho sakuludāyiṃ paribbājakaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[4181]="*“Kāya nuttha, udāyi, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?**“Udāyī, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was unfinished?”*";
P_HTM[4182]="*“Tiṭṭhatesā, bhante, kathā yāya mayaṃ etarahi kathāya sannisinnā.**“Sir, leave aside what we were sitting talking about just now.*";
P_HTM[4183]="*Nesā, bhante, kathā bhagavato dullabhā bhavissati pacchāpi savanāya.**It won’t be hard for you to hear about that later.*";
P_HTM[4184]="*Purimāni, bhante, divasāni purimatarāni nānātitthiyānaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ kutūhalasālāyaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:**Sir, a few days ago several ascetics and brahmins who follow various other paths were sitting together at the debating hall, and this discussion came up among them:*";
P_HTM[4185]="*‘lābhā vata, bho, aṅgamagadhānaṃ, suladdhalābhā vata, bho, aṅgamagadhānaṃ.**‘The people of Aṅga and Magadha are so fortunate, so very fortunate!*";
P_HTM[4186]="*Tatrime samaṇabrāhmaṇā saṃghino gaṇino gaṇācariyā ñātā yasassino titthakarā sādhusammatā bahujanassa rājagahaṃ vassāvāsaṃ osaṭā.**For there are these ascetics and brahmins who lead an order and a community, and teach a community. They’re well-known and famous religious founders, regarded as holy by many people. And they have come down for the rainy season residence at Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[4187]="*Ayampi kho pūraṇo kassapo saṃghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa;**They include Pūraṇa Kassapa,*";
P_HTM[4188]="*sopi rājagahaṃ vassāvāsaṃ osaṭo.* **";
P_HTM[4189]="*Ayampi kho makkhali gosālo … pe …**Makkhali Gosāla,*";
P_HTM[4190]="*ajito kesakambalo …**Ajita Kesakambala,*";
P_HTM[4191]="*pakudho kaccāyano …**Pakudha Kaccāyana,*";
P_HTM[4192]="*sañjayo belaṭṭhaputto …**Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta,*";
P_HTM[4193]="*nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto saṃghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa;**and Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta.*";
P_HTM[4194]="*sopi rājagahaṃ vassāvāsaṃ osaṭo.* **";
P_HTM[4195]="*Ayampi kho samaṇo gotamo saṃghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa;**This ascetic Gotama also leads an order and a community, and teaches a community. He’s a well-known and famous religious founder, regarded as holy by many people.*";
P_HTM[4196]="*sopi rājagahaṃ vassāvāsaṃ osaṭo.**And he too has come down for the rains residence at Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[4197]="*Ko nu kho imesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saṃghīnaṃ gaṇīnaṃ gaṇācariyānaṃ ñātānaṃ yasassinaṃ titthakarānaṃ sādhusammatānaṃ bahujanassa sāvakānaṃ sakkato garukato mānito pūjito, kañca pana sāvakā sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharantī’ti?**Which of these ascetics and brahmins is honored, respected, revered, and venerated by their disciples? And how do their disciples, after honoring and respecting them, remain loyal?’*";
P_HTM[4198]="*Tatrekacce evamāhaṃsu:**Some of them said:*";
P_HTM[4199]="*‘ayaṃ kho pūraṇo kassapo saṅghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa;**‘This Pūraṇa Kassapa leads an order and a community, and teaches a community. He’s a well-known and famous religious founder, regarded as holy by many people.*";
P_HTM[4200]="*so ca kho sāvakānaṃ na sakkato na garukato na mānito na pūjito, na ca pana pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ sāvakā sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**But he’s not honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by his disciples. And his disciples, not honoring and respecting him, don’t remain loyal to him.*";
P_HTM[4201]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ pūraṇo kassapo anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ deseti.**Once it so happened that he was teaching an assembly of many hundreds.*";
P_HTM[4202]="*Tatraññataro pūraṇassa kassapassa sāvako saddamakāsi:**Then one of his disciples made a noise,*";
P_HTM[4203]="*“mā bhonto pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ etamatthaṃ pucchittha;**“My good sirs, don’t ask Pūraṇa Kassapa about that.*";
P_HTM[4204]="*neso etaṃ jānāti;**He doesn’t know that.*";
P_HTM[4205]="*mayametaṃ jānāma, amhe etamatthaṃ pucchatha;**I know it. Ask me about it,*";
P_HTM[4206]="*mayametaṃ bhavantānaṃ byākarissāmā”ti.**and I’ll answer you.”*";
P_HTM[4207]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ pūraṇo kassapo bāhā paggayha kandanto na labhati:**It happened that Pūraṇa Kassapa didn’t get his way, though he called out with raised arms,*";
P_HTM[4208]="*“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha.**“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.*";
P_HTM[4209]="*Nete, bhavante, pucchanti, amhe ete pucchanti;**They’re not asking you, they’re asking me!*";
P_HTM[4210]="*mayametesaṃ byākarissāmā”ti.**I’ll answer you!”*";
P_HTM[4211]="*Bahū kho pana pūraṇassa kassapassa sāvakā vādaṃ āropetvā apakkantā:**Indeed, many of his disciples have left him after refuting his doctrine:*";
P_HTM[4212]="*“na tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāsi, ahaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāmi, kiṃ tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānissasi? Micchāpaṭipanno tvamasi, ahamasmi sammāpaṭipanno, sahitaṃ me, asahitaṃ te, purevacanīyaṃ pacchā avaca, pacchāvacanīyaṃ pure avaca, adhiciṇṇaṃ te viparāvattaṃ, āropito te vādo, niggahitosi, cara vādappamokkhāya, nibbeṭhehi vā sace pahosī”ti.**“You don’t understand this teaching and training. I understand this teaching and training. What, you understand this teaching and training? You’re practicing wrong. I’m practicing right. I stay on topic, you don’t. You said last what you should have said first. You said first what you should have said last. What you’ve thought so much about has been disproved. Your doctrine is refuted. Go on, save your doctrine! You’re trapped; get yourself out of this—if you can!”*";
P_HTM[4213]="*Iti pūraṇo kassapo sāvakānaṃ na sakkato na garukato na mānito na pūjito, na ca pana pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ sāvakā sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**That’s how Pūraṇa Kassapa is not honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by his disciples. On the contrary, his disciples, not honoring and respecting him, don’t remain loyal to him.*";
P_HTM[4214]="*Akkuṭṭho ca pana pūraṇo kassapo dhammakkosenā’ti.**Rather, he’s reviled, and rightly so.’*";
P_HTM[4215]="*Ekacce evamāhaṃsu:**Others said:*";
P_HTM[4216]="*‘ayampi kho makkhali gosālo … pe …**'This Makkhali Gosāla …*";
P_HTM[4217]="*ajito kesakambalo …**Ajita Kesakambala …*";
P_HTM[4218]="*pakudho kaccāyano …**Pakudha Kaccāyana …*";
P_HTM[4219]="*sañjayo belaṭṭhaputto …**Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta …*";
P_HTM[4220]="*nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto saṅghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa;**Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta leads an order and a community, and teaches a community. He’s a well-known and famous religious founder, regarded as holy by many people.*";
P_HTM[4221]="*so ca kho sāvakānaṃ na sakkato na garukato na mānito na pūjito, na ca pana nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ sāvakā sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**But he’s not honored, respected, revered, and venerated by his disciples. And his disciples, not honoring and respecting him, don’t remain loyal to him.*";
P_HTM[4222]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ deseti.**Once it so happened that he was teaching an assembly of many hundreds.*";
P_HTM[4223]="*Tatraññataro nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa sāvako saddamakāsi:**Then one of his disciples made a noise,*";
P_HTM[4224]="*“mā bhonto nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ etamatthaṃ pucchittha;**“My good sirs, don’t ask Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta about that.*";
P_HTM[4225]="*neso etaṃ jānāti;**He doesn’t know that.*";
P_HTM[4226]="*mayametaṃ jānāma, amhe etamatthaṃ pucchatha;**I know it. Ask me about it,*";
P_HTM[4227]="*mayametaṃ bhavantānaṃ byākarissāmā”ti.**and I’ll answer you.”*";
P_HTM[4228]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto bāhā paggayha kandanto na labhati:**It happened that Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta didn’t get his way, though he called out with raised arms,*";
P_HTM[4229]="*“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha.**“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.*";
P_HTM[4230]="*Nete bhavante pucchanti, amhe ete pucchanti;**They’re not asking you, they’re asking me!*";
P_HTM[4231]="*mayametesaṃ byākarissāmā”ti.**I’ll answer you!”*";
P_HTM[4232]="*Bahū kho pana nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa sāvakā vādaṃ āropetvā apakkantā:**Indeed, many of his disciples have left him after refuting his doctrine:*";
P_HTM[4233]="*“na tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāsi, ahaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāmi. Kiṃ tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānissasi? Micchāpaṭipanno tvamasi. Ahamasmi sammāpaṭipanno. Sahitaṃ me asahitaṃ te, purevacanīyaṃ pacchā avaca, pacchāvacanīyaṃ pure avaca, adhiciṇṇaṃ te viparāvattaṃ, āropito te vādo, niggahitosi, cara vādappamokkhāya, nibbeṭhehi vā sace pahosī”ti.**“You don’t understand this teaching and training. I understand this teaching and training. What, you understand this teaching and training? You’re practicing wrong. I’m practicing right. I stay on topic, you don’t. You said last what you should have said first. You said first what you should have said last. What you’ve thought so much about has been disproved. Your doctrine is refuted. Go on, save your doctrine! You’re trapped; get yourself out of this—if you can!”*";
P_HTM[4234]="*Iti nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto sāvakānaṃ na sakkato na garukato na mānito na pūjito, na ca pana nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ sāvakā sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**That’s how Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta is not honored, respected, revered, and venerated by his disciples. On the contrary, his disciples, not honoring and respecting him, don’t remain loyal to him.*";
P_HTM[4235]="*Akkuṭṭho ca pana nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto dhammakkosenā’ti.**Rather, he’s reviled, and rightly so.’*";
P_HTM[4236]="*Ekacce evamāhaṃsu:**Others said:*";
P_HTM[4237]="*‘ayampi kho samaṇo gotamo saṃghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa;**‘This ascetic Gotama leads an order and a community, and teaches a community. He’s a well-known and famous religious founder, regarded as holy by many people.*";
P_HTM[4238]="*so ca kho sāvakānaṃ sakkato garukato mānito pūjito, samaṇañca pana gotamaṃ sāvakā sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**He’s honored, respected, revered, and venerated by his disciples. And his disciples, honoring and respecting him, remain loyal to him.*";
P_HTM[4239]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ samaṇo gotamo anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ desesi.**Once it so happened that he was teaching an assembly of many hundreds.*";
P_HTM[4240]="*Tatraññataro samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako ukkāsi.**Then one of his disciples cleared their throat.*";
P_HTM[4241]="*Tamenāññataro sabrahmacārī jaṇṇukena ghaṭṭesi:**And one of their spiritual companions nudged them with their knee, to indicate,*";
P_HTM[4242]="*“appasaddo āyasmā hotu, māyasmā saddamakāsi, satthā no bhagavā dhammaṃ desesī”ti.**“Hush, venerable, don’t make sound! Our teacher, the Blessed One, is teaching!”*";
P_HTM[4243]="*Yasmiṃ samaye samaṇo gotamo anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ deseti, neva tasmiṃ samaye samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakānaṃ khipitasaddo vā hoti ukkāsitasaddo vā.**While the ascetic Gotama is teaching an assembly of many hundreds, there is no sound of his disciples coughing or clearing their throats.*";
P_HTM[4244]="*Tamenaṃ mahājanakāyo paccāsīsamānarūpo paccupaṭṭhito hoti:**That large crowd is poised on the edge of their seats, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4245]="*“yaṃ no bhagavā dhammaṃ bhāsissati taṃ no sossāmā”ti.**“Whatever the Buddha teaches, we shall listen to it.”*";
P_HTM[4246]="*Seyyathāpi nāma puriso cātummahāpathe khuddamadhuṃ anelakaṃ pīḷeyya.**It’s like when there’s a person at the crossroads pressing out pure manuka honey,*";
P_HTM[4247]="*Tamenaṃ mahājanakāyo paccāsīsamānarūpo paccupaṭṭhito assa.**and a large crowd is poised on the edge of their seats.*";
P_HTM[4248]="*Evameva yasmiṃ samaye samaṇo gotamo anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ deseti, neva tasmiṃ samaye samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakānaṃ khipitasaddo vā hoti ukkāsitasaddo vā.**In the same way, while the ascetic Gotama is teaching an assembly of many hundreds, there is no sound of his disciples coughing or clearing their throats.*";
P_HTM[4249]="*Tamenaṃ mahājanakāyo paccāsīsamānarūpo paccupaṭṭhito hoti:**That large crowd is poised on the edge of their seats, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4250]="*“yaṃ no bhagavā dhammaṃ bhāsissati taṃ no sossāmā”ti.**“Whatever the Buddha teaches, we shall listen to it.”*";
P_HTM[4251]="*Yepi samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakā sabrahmacārīhi sampayojetvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattanti tepi satthu ceva vaṇṇavādino honti, dhammassa ca vaṇṇavādino honti, saṃghassa ca vaṇṇavādino honti, attagarahinoyeva honti anaññagarahino, “mayamevamhā alakkhikā mayaṃ appapuññā te mayaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitvā nāsakkhimhā yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caritun”ti.**Even when a disciple of the ascetic Gotama rejects the training and returns to a lesser life, having been overly attached to their spiritual companions, they speak only praise of the teacher, the teaching, and the Saṅgha. They blame only themselves, not others: “We were unlucky, we had little merit. For even after going forth in such a well explained teaching and training we weren’t able to practice for life the perfectly full and pure spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[4252]="*Te ārāmikabhūtā vā upāsakabhūtā vā pañcasikkhāpade samādāya vattanti.**They become monastery workers or lay followers, and they proceed having undertaken the five precepts.*";
P_HTM[4253]="*Iti samaṇo gotamo sāvakānaṃ sakkato garukato mānito pūjito, samaṇañca pana gotamaṃ sāvakā sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharantī’”ti.**That’s how the ascetic Gotama is honored, respected, revered, and venerated by his disciples. And that’s how his disciples, honoring and respecting him, remain loyal to him.’”*";
P_HTM[4254]="*“Kati pana tvaṃ, udāyi, mayi dhamme samanupassasi, yehi mamaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharantī”ti?**“But Udāyī, how many qualities do you see in me, because of which my disciples honor, respect, revere, and venerate me; and after honoring and respecting me, they remain loyal to me?”*";
P_HTM[4255]="*“Pañca kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati dhamme samanupassāmi yehi bhagavantaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**“Sir, I see five such qualities in the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4256]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4257]="*Bhagavā hi, bhante, appāhāro, appāhāratāya ca vaṇṇavādī.**The Buddha eats little and praises eating little.*";
P_HTM[4258]="*Yampi, bhante, bhagavā appāhāro, appāhāratāya ca vaṇṇavādī imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ samanupassāmi yena bhagavantaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti. (1)**This is the first such quality I see in the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4259]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, bhagavā santuṭṭho itarītarena cīvarena, itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, the Buddha is content with any kind of robe, and praises such contentment.*";
P_HTM[4260]="*Yampi, bhante, bhagavā santuṭṭho itarītarena cīvarena, itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati dutiyaṃ dhammaṃ samanupassāmi yena bhagavantaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti. (2)**This is the second such quality I see in the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4261]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, bhagavā santuṭṭho itarītarena piṇḍapātena, itarītarapiṇḍapātasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, the Buddha is content with any kind of almsfood, and praises such contentment.*";
P_HTM[4262]="*Yampi, bhante, bhagavā santuṭṭho itarītarena piṇḍapātena, itarītarapiṇḍapātasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati tatiyaṃ dhammaṃ samanupassāmi yena bhagavantaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti. (3)**This is the third such quality I see in the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4263]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, bhagavā santuṭṭho itarītarena senāsanena, itarītarasenāsanasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, the Buddha is content with any kind of lodging, and praises such contentment.*";
P_HTM[4264]="*Yampi, bhante, bhagavā santuṭṭho itarītarena senāsanena, itarītarasenāsanasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati catutthaṃ dhammaṃ samanupassāmi yena bhagavantaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti. (4)**This is the fourth such quality I see in the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4265]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, bhagavā pavivitto, pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, the Buddha is secluded, and praises seclusion.*";
P_HTM[4266]="*Yampi, bhante, bhagavā pavivitto, pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādī, imaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati pañcamaṃ dhammaṃ samanupassāmi yena bhagavantaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti. (5)**This is the fifth such quality I see in the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4267]="*Ime kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati pañca dhamme samanupassāmi yehi bhagavantaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharantī”ti.**These are the five qualities I see in the Buddha, because of which his disciples honor, respect, revere, and venerate him; and after honoring and respecting him, they remain loyal to him.”*";
P_HTM[4268]="*“‘Appāhāro samaṇo gotamo, appāhāratāya ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, santi kho pana me, udāyi, sāvakā kosakāhārāpi aḍḍhakosakāhārāpi beluvāhārāpi aḍḍhabeluvāhārāpi.**“Suppose, Udāyī, my disciples were loyal to me because I eat little. Well, there are disciples of mine who eat a cupful of food, or half a cupful; they eat a wood apple, or half a wood apple.*";
P_HTM[4269]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, udāyi, appekadā iminā pattena samatittikampi bhuñjāmi bhiyyopi bhuñjāmi.**But sometimes I even eat this bowl full to the brim, or even more.*";
P_HTM[4270]="*‘Appāhāro samaṇo gotamo, appāhāratāya ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, ye te, udāyi, mama sāvakā kosakāhārāpi aḍḍhakosakāhārāpi beluvāhārāpi aḍḍhabeluvāhārāpi na maṃ te iminā dhammena sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ. (1)**So if it were the case that my disciples are loyal to me because I eat little, then those disciples who eat even less would not be loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4271]="*‘Santuṭṭho samaṇo gotamo itarītarena cīvarena, itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, santi kho pana me, udāyi, sāvakā paṃsukūlikā lūkhacīvaradharā te susānā vā saṅkārakūṭā vā pāpaṇikā vā nantakāni uccinitvā saṅghāṭiṃ karitvā dhārenti.**Suppose my disciples were loyal to me because I’m content with any kind of robe. Well, there are disciples of mine who have rag robes, wearing shabby robes. They gather scraps from charnel grounds, rubbish dumps, and shops, make them into a patchwork robe and wear it.*";
P_HTM[4272]="*Ahaṃ kho panudāyi, appekadā gahapaticīvarāni dhāremi daḷhāni satthalūkhāni alābulomasāni.**But sometimes I wear robes offered by householders that are strong, yet next to which bottle-gourd down is coarse.*";
P_HTM[4273]="*‘Santuṭṭho samaṇo gotamo itarītarena cīvarena, itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, ye te, udāyi, mama sāvakā paṃsukūlikā lūkhacīvaradharā te susānā vā saṅkārakūṭā vā pāpaṇikā vā nantakāni uccinitvā saṅghāṭiṃ karitvā dhārenti, na maṃ te iminā dhammena sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ. (2)**So if it were the case that my disciples are loyal to me because I’m content with any kind of robe, then those disciples who wear rag robes would not be loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4274]="*‘Santuṭṭho samaṇo gotamo itarītarena piṇḍapātena, itarītarapiṇḍapātasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, santi kho pana me, udāyi, sāvakā piṇḍapātikā sapadānacārino uñchāsake vate ratā, te antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhā samānā āsanenapi nimantiyamānā na sādiyanti.**Suppose my disciples were loyal to me because I’m content with any kind of alms-food. Well, there are disciples of mine who eat only alms-food, wander indiscriminately for alms-food, happy to eat whatever they glean. When they’ve entered an inhabited area, they don’t consent when invited to sit down.*";
P_HTM[4275]="*Ahaṃ kho panudāyi, appekadā nimantanepi bhuñjāmi sālīnaṃ odanaṃ vicitakāḷakaṃ anekasūpaṃ anekabyañjanaṃ.**But sometimes I even eat by invitation boiled fine rice with the dark grains picked out, served with many soups and sauces.*";
P_HTM[4276]="*‘Santuṭṭho samaṇo gotamo itarītarena piṇḍapātena, itarītarapiṇḍapātasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, ye te, udāyi, mama sāvakā piṇḍapātikā sapadānacārino uñchāsake vate ratā te antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhā samānā āsanenapi nimantiyamānā na sādiyanti, na maṃ te iminā dhammena sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ. (3)**So if it were the case that my disciples are loyal to me because I’m content with any kind of alms-food, then those disciples who eat only alms-food would not be loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4277]="*‘Santuṭṭho samaṇo gotamo itarītarena senāsanena, itarītarasenāsanasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, santi kho pana me, udāyi, sāvakā rukkhamūlikā abbhokāsikā, te aṭṭhamāse channaṃ na upenti.**Suppose my disciples were loyal to me because I’m content with any kind of lodging. Well, there are disciples of mine who stay at the root of a tree, in the open air. For eight months they don’t go under a roof.*";
P_HTM[4278]="*Ahaṃ kho panudāyi, appekadā kūṭāgāresupi viharāmi ullittāvalittesu nivātesu phusitaggaḷesu pihitavātapānesu.**But sometimes I even stay in bungalows, plastered inside and out, draft-free, with latches fastened and windows shuttered.*";
P_HTM[4279]="*‘Santuṭṭho samaṇo gotamo itarītarena senāsanena, itarītarasenāsanasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, ye te, udāyi, mama sāvakā rukkhamūlikā abbhokāsikā te aṭṭhamāse channaṃ na upenti, na maṃ te iminā dhammena sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ. (4)**So if it were the case that my disciples are loyal to me because I’m content with any kind of lodging, then those disciples who stay at the root of a tree would not be loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4280]="*‘Pavivitto samaṇo gotamo, pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ, santi kho pana me, udāyi, sāvakā āraññikā pantasenāsanā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni ajjhogāhetvā viharanti, te anvaddhamāsaṃ saṅghamajjhe osaranti pātimokkhuddesāya.**Suppose my disciples were loyal to me because I’m secluded and I praise seclusion. Well, there are disciples of mine who live in the wilderness, in remote lodgings. Having ventured deep into remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest, they live there, coming down to the midst of the Saṅgha each fortnight for the recitation of the monastic code.*";
P_HTM[4281]="*Ahaṃ kho panudāyi, appekadā ākiṇṇo viharāmi bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīhi upāsakehi upāsikāhi raññā rājamahāmattehi titthiyehi titthiyasāvakehi.**But sometimes I live crowded by monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen; by rulers and their ministers, and teachers of other paths and their disciples.*";
P_HTM[4282]="*‘Pavivitto samaṇo gotamo, pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādī’ti, iti ce maṃ, udāyi, sāvakā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ. Ye te, udāyi, mama sāvakā āraññakā pantasenāsanā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni ajjhogāhetvā viharanti te anvaddhamāsaṃ saṅghamajjhe osaranti pātimokkhuddesāya, na maṃ te iminā dhammena sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya vihareyyuṃ. (5)**So if it were the case that my disciples are loyal to me because I’m secluded and praise seclusion, then those disciples who live in the wilderness would not be loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4283]="*Iti kho, udāyi, na mamaṃ sāvakā imehi pañcahi dhammehi sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**So, Udāyī, it’s not because of these five qualities that my disciples honor, respect, revere, and venerate me; and after honoring and respecting me, they remain loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4284]="*Atthi kho, udāyi, aññe ca pañca dhammā yehi pañcahi dhammehi mamaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**There are five other qualities because of which my disciples honor, respect, revere, and venerate me; and after honoring and respecting me, they remain loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4285]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4286]="*Idhudāyi, mamaṃ sāvakā adhisīle sambhāventi:**Firstly, my disciples esteem me for the higher ethics:*";
P_HTM[4287]="*‘sīlavā samaṇo gotamo paramena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama is ethical. He possesses the entire spectrum of ethical conduct to the highest degree.’*";
P_HTM[4288]="*Yampudāyi, mamaṃ sāvakā adhisīle sambhāventi:**Since this is so,*";
P_HTM[4289]="*‘sīlavā samaṇo gotamo paramena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato’ti, ayaṃ kho, udāyi, paṭhamo dhammo yena mamaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**this is the first quality because of which my disciples are loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4290]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, mamaṃ sāvakā abhikkante ñāṇadassane sambhāventi:**Furthermore, my disciples esteem me for my excellent knowledge and vision:*";
P_HTM[4291]="*‘jānaṃyevāha samaṇo gotamo—jānāmīti,**‘The ascetic Gotama only claims to know when he does in fact know.*";
P_HTM[4292]="*passaṃyevāha samaṇo gotamo—passāmīti;**He only claims to see when he really does see.*";
P_HTM[4293]="*abhiññāya samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti no anabhiññāya;**He teaches based on direct knowledge, not without direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[4294]="*sanidānaṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti no anidānaṃ;**He teaches based on reason, not without reason.*";
P_HTM[4295]="*sappāṭihāriyaṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti no appāṭihāriyan’ti.**He teaches with a demonstrable basis, not without it.’*";
P_HTM[4296]="*Yampudāyi, mamaṃ sāvakā abhikkante ñāṇadassane sambhāventi:**Since this is so,*";
P_HTM[4297]="*‘jānaṃyevāha samaṇo gotamo—jānāmīti,* **";
P_HTM[4298]="*passaṃyevāha samaṇo gotamo—passāmīti;* **";
P_HTM[4299]="*abhiññāya samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti no anabhiññāya;* **";
P_HTM[4300]="*sanidānaṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti no anidānaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4301]="*sappāṭihāriyaṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti no appāṭihāriyan’ti, ayaṃ kho, udāyi, dutiyo dhammo yena mamaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**this is the second quality because of which my disciples are loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4302]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, mamaṃ sāvakā adhipaññāya sambhāventi:**Furthermore, my disciples esteem me for my higher wisdom:*";
P_HTM[4303]="*‘paññavā samaṇo gotamo paramena paññākkhandhena samannāgato;**‘The ascetic Gotama is wise. He possesses the entire spectrum of wisdom to the highest degree.*";
P_HTM[4304]="*taṃ vata anāgataṃ vādapathaṃ na dakkhati, uppannaṃ vā parappavādaṃ na sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggaṇhissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati’.**It’s not possible that he would fail to foresee grounds for future criticism, or to legitimately and completely refute the doctrines of others that come up.’*";
P_HTM[4305]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4306]="*api nu me sāvakā evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā antarantarā kathaṃ opāteyyun”ti?**Would my disciples, knowing and seeing this, break in and interrupt me?”*";
P_HTM[4307]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4308]="*“Na kho panāhaṃ, udāyi, sāvakesu anusāsaniṃ paccāsīsāmi;**“That’s because I don’t expect to be instructed by my disciples.*";
P_HTM[4309]="*aññadatthu mamayeva sāvakā anusāsaniṃ paccāsīsanti.**Invariably, my disciples expect instruction from me.*";
P_HTM[4310]="*Yampudāyi, mamaṃ sāvakā adhipaññāya sambhāventi:**Since this is so,*";
P_HTM[4311]="*‘paññavā samaṇo gotamo paramena paññākkhandhena samannāgato;* **";
P_HTM[4312]="*taṃ vata anāgataṃ vādapathaṃ na dakkhati, uppannaṃ vā parappavādaṃ na sahadhammena niggahitaṃ niggaṇhissatīti—* **";
P_HTM[4313]="*netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati’.* **";
P_HTM[4314]="*Ayaṃ kho, udāyi, tatiyo dhammo yena mamaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**this is the third quality because of which my disciples are loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4315]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, mama sāvakā yena dukkhena dukkhotiṇṇā dukkhaparetā te maṃ upasaṅkamitvā dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ pucchanti, tesāhaṃ dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ puṭṭho byākaromi, tesāhaṃ cittaṃ ārādhemi pañhassa veyyākaraṇena;**Furthermore, my disciples come to me and ask how the noble truth of suffering applies to the suffering in which they are swamped and mired. And I provide them with a satisfying answer to their question.*";
P_HTM[4316]="*te maṃ dukkhasamudayaṃ …**They ask how the noble truths of the origin of suffering,*";
P_HTM[4317]="*dukkhanirodhaṃ …**the cessation of suffering,*";
P_HTM[4318]="*dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ ariyasaccaṃ pucchanti, tesāhaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ ariyasaccaṃ puṭṭho byākaromi, tesāhaṃ cittaṃ ārādhemi pañhassa veyyākaraṇena.**and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering apply to the suffering that has overwhelmed them and brought them low. And I provide them with satisfying answers to their questions.*";
P_HTM[4319]="*Yampudāyi, mama sāvakā yena dukkhena dukkhotiṇṇā dukkhaparetā te maṃ upasaṅkamitvā dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ pucchanti, tesāhaṃ dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ puṭṭho byākaromi, tesāhaṃ cittaṃ ārādhemi pañhassa veyyākaraṇena.**Since this is so,*";
P_HTM[4320]="*Te maṃ dukkhasamudayaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[4321]="*dukkhanirodhaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[4322]="*dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ ariyasaccaṃ pucchanti.* **";
P_HTM[4323]="*Tesāhaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ ariyasaccaṃ puṭṭho byākaromi.* **";
P_HTM[4324]="*Tesāhaṃ cittaṃ ārādhemi pañhassa veyyākaraṇena.* **";
P_HTM[4325]="*Ayaṃ kho, udāyi, catuttho dhammo yena mamaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**this is the fourth quality because of which my disciples are loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4326]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā cattāro satipaṭṭhāne bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[4327]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;**It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[4328]="*vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati …**They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …*";
P_HTM[4329]="*citte cittānupassī viharati …**mind …*";
P_HTM[4330]="*dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ.**principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world.*";
P_HTM[4331]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4332]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā cattāro sammappadhāne bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the four right efforts.*";
P_HTM[4333]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, vīriyaṃ ārabhati, cittaṃ paggaṇhāti, padahati;**It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise.*";
P_HTM[4334]="*uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, vīriyaṃ ārabhati, cittaṃ paggaṇhāti, padahati;**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen are given up.*";
P_HTM[4335]="*anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, vīriyaṃ ārabhati, cittaṃ paggaṇhāti, padahati;**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities arise.*";
P_HTM[4336]="*uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti, vāyamati, vīriyaṃ ārabhati, cittaṃ paggaṇhāti, padahati.**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are fulfilled by development.*";
P_HTM[4337]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4338]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā cattāro iddhipāde bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the four bases of psychic power.*";
P_HTM[4339]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu chandasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[4340]="*vīriyasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[4341]="*cittasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti,**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to mental development, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[4342]="*vīmaṃsāsamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti.**They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to inquiry, and active effort.*";
P_HTM[4343]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4344]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā pañcindriyāni bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the five faculties.*";
P_HTM[4345]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu saddhindriyaṃ bhāveti upasamagāmiṃ sambodhagāmiṃ;**It’s when a mendicant develops the faculties of faith,*";
P_HTM[4346]="*vīriyindriyaṃ bhāveti … pe …**energy,*";
P_HTM[4347]="*satindriyaṃ bhāveti …**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[4348]="*samādhindriyaṃ bhāveti …**immersion,*";
P_HTM[4349]="*paññindriyaṃ bhāveti upasamagāmiṃ sambodhagāmiṃ.**and wisdom, which lead to peace and awakening.*";
P_HTM[4350]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4351]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā pañca balāni bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the five powers.*";
P_HTM[4352]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu saddhābalaṃ bhāveti upasamagāmiṃ sambodhagāmiṃ;**It’s when a mendicant develops the powers of faith,*";
P_HTM[4353]="*vīriyabalaṃ bhāveti … pe …**energy,*";
P_HTM[4354]="*satibalaṃ bhāveti …**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[4355]="*samādhibalaṃ bhāveti …**immersion,*";
P_HTM[4356]="*paññābalaṃ bhāveti upasamagāmiṃ sambodhagāmiṃ.**and wisdom, which lead to peace and awakening.*";
P_HTM[4357]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4358]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā sattabojjhaṅge bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the seven awakening factors.*";
P_HTM[4359]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ; dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe … vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ.**It’s when a mendicant develops the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go.*";
P_HTM[4360]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4361]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[4362]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti, sammāsaṅkappaṃ bhāveti, sammāvācaṃ bhāveti, sammākammantaṃ bhāveti, sammāājīvaṃ bhāveti, sammāvāyāmaṃ bhāveti, sammāsatiṃ bhāveti, sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti.**It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[4363]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4364]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā aṭṭha vimokkhe bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the eight liberations.*";
P_HTM[4365]="*Rūpī rūpāni passati,**Having physical form, they see visions.*";
P_HTM[4366]="*ayaṃ paṭhamo vimokkho;**This is the first liberation.*";
P_HTM[4367]="*ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī bahiddhā rūpāni passati,**Not perceiving form internally, they see visions externally.*";
P_HTM[4368]="*ayaṃ dutiyo vimokkho;**This is the second liberation.*";
P_HTM[4369]="*subhanteva adhimutto hoti,**They’re focused only on beauty.*";
P_HTM[4370]="*ayaṃ tatiyo vimokkho;**This is the third liberation.*";
P_HTM[4371]="*sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati,**Going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[4372]="*ayaṃ catuttho vimokkho;**This is the fourth liberation.*";
P_HTM[4373]="*sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati,**Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[4374]="*ayaṃ pañcamo vimokkho;**This is the fifth liberation.*";
P_HTM[4375]="*sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati,**Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[4376]="*ayaṃ chaṭṭho vimokkho;**This is the sixth liberation.*";
P_HTM[4377]="*sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati,**Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4378]="*ayaṃ sattamo vimokkho;**This is the seventh liberation.*";
P_HTM[4379]="*sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati,**Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[4380]="*ayaṃ aṭṭhamo vimokkho.**This is the eighth liberation.*";
P_HTM[4381]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4382]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā aṭṭha abhibhāyatanāni bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the eight dimensions of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4383]="*Ajjhattaṃ rūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati parittāni suvaṇṇadubbaṇṇāni.**Perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, limited, both pretty and ugly.*";
P_HTM[4384]="*‘Tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi, passāmī’ti evaṃ saññī hoti.**Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’*";
P_HTM[4385]="*Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ.**This is the first dimension of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4386]="*Ajjhattaṃ rūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati appamāṇāni suvaṇṇadubbaṇṇāni.**Perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, limitless, both pretty and ugly.*";
P_HTM[4387]="*‘Tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi, passāmī’ti evaṃ saññī hoti.**Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’*";
P_HTM[4388]="*Idaṃ dutiyaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ.**This is the second dimension of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4389]="*Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati parittāni suvaṇṇadubbaṇṇāni.**Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, limited, both pretty and ugly.*";
P_HTM[4390]="*‘Tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi, passāmī’ti evaṃ saññī hoti.**Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’*";
P_HTM[4391]="*Idaṃ tatiyaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ.**This is the third dimension of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4392]="*Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati appamāṇāni suvaṇṇadubbaṇṇāni.**Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, limitless, both pretty and ugly.*";
P_HTM[4393]="*‘Tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi, passāmī’ti evaṃ saññī hoti.**Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’*";
P_HTM[4394]="*Idaṃ catutthaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ.**This is the fourth dimension of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4395]="*Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati nīlāni nīlavaṇṇāni nīlanidassanāni nīlanibhāsāni.**Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, blue, with blue color, blue hue, and blue tint.*";
P_HTM[4396]="*Seyyathāpi nāma umāpupphaṃ nīlaṃ nīlavaṇṇaṃ nīlanidassanaṃ nīlanibhāsaṃ, seyyathā vā pana taṃ vatthaṃ bārāṇaseyyakaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhaṃ nīlaṃ nīlavaṇṇaṃ nīlanidassanaṃ nīlanibhāsaṃ;**They’re like a flax flower that’s blue, with blue color, blue hue, and blue tint. Or a cloth from Bāraṇasī that’s smoothed on both sides, blue, with blue color, blue hue, and blue tint.*";
P_HTM[4397]="*evameva ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati nīlāni nīlavaṇṇāni nīlanidassanāni nīlanibhāsāni.**In the same way, not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, blue, with blue color, blue hue, and blue tint.*";
P_HTM[4398]="*‘Tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi, passāmī’ti evaṃ saññī hoti.**Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’*";
P_HTM[4399]="*Idaṃ pañcamaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ.**This is the fifth dimension of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4400]="*Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati pītāni pītavaṇṇāni pītanidassanāni pītanibhāsāni.**Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are yellow, with yellow color, yellow hue, and yellow tint.*";
P_HTM[4401]="*Seyyathāpi nāma kaṇikārapupphaṃ pītaṃ pītavaṇṇaṃ pītanidassanaṃ pītanibhāsaṃ, seyyathā vā pana taṃ vatthaṃ bārāṇaseyyakaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhaṃ pītaṃ pītavaṇṇaṃ pītanidassanaṃ pītanibhāsaṃ;**They’re like a champak flower that’s yellow, with yellow color, yellow hue, and yellow tint. Or a cloth from Bāraṇasī that’s smoothed on both sides, yellow, with yellow color, yellow hue, and yellow tint.*";
P_HTM[4402]="*evameva ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati pītāni pītavaṇṇāni pītanidassanāni pītanibhāsāni.**In the same way, not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are yellow, with yellow color, yellow hue, and yellow tint.*";
P_HTM[4403]="*‘Tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi, passāmī’ti evaṃ saññī hoti.**Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’*";
P_HTM[4404]="*Idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ.**This is the sixth dimension of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4405]="*Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati lohitakāni lohitakavaṇṇāni lohitakanidassanāni lohitakanibhāsāni.**Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are red, with red color, red hue, and red tint.*";
P_HTM[4406]="*Seyyathāpi nāma bandhujīvakapupphaṃ lohitakaṃ lohitakavaṇṇaṃ lohitakanidassanaṃ lohitakanibhāsaṃ, seyyathā vā pana taṃ vatthaṃ bārāṇaseyyakaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhaṃ lohitakaṃ lohitakavaṇṇaṃ lohitakanidassanaṃ lohitakanibhāsaṃ;**They’re like a scarlet mallow flower that’s red, with red color, red hue, and red tint. Or a cloth from Bāraṇasī that’s smoothed on both sides, red, with red color, red hue, and red tint.*";
P_HTM[4407]="*evameva ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati lohitakāni lohitakavaṇṇāni lohitakanidassanāni lohitakanibhāsāni.**In the same way, not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are red, with red color, red hue, and red tint.*";
P_HTM[4408]="*‘Tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi, passāmī’ti evaṃ saññī hoti.**Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’*";
P_HTM[4409]="*Idaṃ sattamaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ.**This is the seventh dimension of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4410]="*Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati odātāni odātavaṇṇāni odātanidassanāni odātanibhāsāni.**Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are white, with white color, white hue, and white tint.*";
P_HTM[4411]="*Seyyathāpi nāma osadhitārakā odātā odātavaṇṇā odātanidassanā odātanibhāsā, seyyathā vā pana taṃ vatthaṃ bārāṇaseyyakaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhaṃ odātaṃ odātavaṇṇaṃ odātanidassanaṃ odātanibhāsaṃ;**They’re like the morning star that’s white, with white color, white hue, and white tint. Or a cloth from Bāraṇasī that’s smoothed on both sides, white, with white color, white hue, and white tint.*";
P_HTM[4412]="*evameva ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati odātāni odātavaṇṇāni odātanidassanāni odātanibhāsāni.**In the same way, not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are white, with white color, white hue, and white tint.*";
P_HTM[4413]="*‘Tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi, passāmī’ti evaṃsaññī hoti.**Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’*";
P_HTM[4414]="*Idaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ.**This is the eighth dimension of mastery.*";
P_HTM[4415]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4416]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā dasa kasiṇāyatanāni bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the ten universal dimensions of meditation.*";
P_HTM[4417]="*Pathavīkasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ advayaṃ appamāṇaṃ;**Someone perceives the meditation on universal earth above, below, across, non-dual and limitless.*";
P_HTM[4418]="*āpokasiṇameko sañjānāti … pe …**They perceive the meditation on universal water …*";
P_HTM[4419]="*tejokasiṇameko sañjānāti …**the meditation on universal fire …*";
P_HTM[4420]="*vāyokasiṇameko sañjānāti …**the meditation on universal air …*";
P_HTM[4421]="*nīlakasiṇameko sañjānāti …**the meditation on universal blue …*";
P_HTM[4422]="*pītakasiṇameko sañjānāti …**the meditation on universal yellow …*";
P_HTM[4423]="*lohitakasiṇameko sañjānāti …**the meditation on universal red …*";
P_HTM[4424]="*odātakasiṇameko sañjānāti …**the meditation on universal white …*";
P_HTM[4425]="*ākāsakasiṇameko sañjānāti …**the meditation on universal space …*";
P_HTM[4426]="*viññāṇakasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ advayaṃ appamāṇaṃ.**the meditation on universal consciousness above, below, across, non-dual and limitless.*";
P_HTM[4427]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4428]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā cattāri jhānāni bhāventi.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to develop the four absorptions.*";
P_HTM[4429]="*Idhudāyi, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4430]="*So imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with rapture and bliss born of seclusion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of seclusion.*";
P_HTM[4431]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, dakkho nhāpako vā nhāpakantevāsī vā kaṃsathāle nhānīyacuṇṇāni ākiritvā udakena paripphosakaṃ paripphosakaṃ sanneyya, sāyaṃ nhānīyapiṇḍi snehānugatā snehaparetā santarabāhirā phuṭā snehena na ca pagghariṇī;**It’s like when a deft bathroom attendant or their apprentice pours bath powder into a bronze dish, sprinkling it little by little with water. They knead it until the ball of bath powder is soaked and saturated with moisture, spread through inside and out; yet no moisture oozes out.*";
P_HTM[4432]="*evameva kho, udāyi, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ vivekajena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa vivekajena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body with rapture and bliss born of seclusion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of seclusion.*";
P_HTM[4433]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption. It has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4434]="*So imameva kāyaṃ samādhijena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa samādhijena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion.*";
P_HTM[4435]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, udakarahado gambhīro ubbhidodako. Tassa nevassa puratthimāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na pacchimāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na uttarāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, na dakkhiṇāya disāya udakassa āyamukhaṃ, devo ca na kālena kālaṃ sammā dhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya;**It’s like a deep lake fed by spring water. There’s no inlet to the east, west, north, or south, and no rainfall to replenish it from time to time.*";
P_HTM[4436]="*atha kho tamhāva udakarahadā sītā vāridhārā ubbhijjitvā tameva udakarahadaṃ sītena vārinā abhisandeyya parisandeyya paripūreyya paripphareyya, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato udakarahadassa sītena vārinā apphuṭaṃ assa.**But the stream of cool water welling up in the lake drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads throughout the lake. There’s no part of the lake that’s not spread through with cool water.*";
P_HTM[4437]="*Evameva kho, udāyi, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ samādhijena pītisukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa samādhijena pītisukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion.*";
P_HTM[4438]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption. They meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[4439]="*So imameva kāyaṃ nippītikena sukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa nippītikena sukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with bliss free of rapture. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with bliss free of rapture.*";
P_HTM[4440]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni anto nimuggaposīni, tāni yāva caggā yāva ca mūlā sītena vārinā abhisannāni parisannāni paripūrāni paripphuṭāni, nāssa kiñci sabbāvataṃ, uppalānaṃ vā padumānaṃ vā puṇḍarīkānaṃ vā sītena vārinā apphuṭaṃ assa;**It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving underwater. From the tip to the root they’re drenched, steeped, filled, and soaked with cool water. There’s no part of them that’s not soaked with cool water.*";
P_HTM[4441]="*evameva kho, udāyi, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ nippītikena sukhena abhisandeti parisandeti paripūreti parippharati, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa nippītikena sukhena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body with bliss free of rapture. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with bliss free of rapture.*";
P_HTM[4442]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption. It is without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[4443]="*So imameva kāyaṃ parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena pharitvā nisinno hoti, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**They sit spreading their body through with pure bright mind. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with pure bright mind.*";
P_HTM[4444]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, puriso odātena vatthena sasīsaṃ pārupitvā nisinno assa, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa odātena vatthena apphuṭaṃ assa;**It’s like someone sitting wrapped from head to foot with white cloth. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread over with white cloth.*";
P_HTM[4445]="*evameva kho, udāyi, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena pharitvā nisinno hoti, nāssa kiñci sabbāvato kāyassa parisuddhena cetasā pariyodātena apphuṭaṃ hoti.**In the same way, they sit spreading their body through with pure bright mind. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with pure bright mind.*";
P_HTM[4446]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4447]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā evaṃ pajānanti:**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to understand this:*";
P_HTM[4448]="*‘ayaṃ kho me kāyo rūpī cātumahābhūtiko mātāpettikasambhavo odanakummāsūpacayo aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammo;**‘This body of mine is physical. It’s made up of the four primary elements, produced by mother and father, built up from rice and porridge, liable to impermanence, to wearing away and erosion, to breaking up and destruction.*";
P_HTM[4449]="*idañca pana me viññāṇaṃ ettha sitaṃ ettha paṭibaddhaṃ’.**And this consciousness of mine is attached to it, tied to it.’*";
P_HTM[4450]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato accho vippasanno sabbākārasampanno;**Suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, well-worked, transparent and clear, endowed with all good qualities.*";
P_HTM[4451]="*tatridaṃ suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ vā.**And it was strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown.*";
P_HTM[4452]="*Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso hatthe karitvā paccavekkheyya:**And someone with good eyesight were to take it in their hand and check it:*";
P_HTM[4453]="*‘ayaṃ kho maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato accho vippasanno sabbākārasampanno;**‘This beryl gem is naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, well-worked, transparent and clear, endowed with all good qualities.*";
P_HTM[4454]="*tatridaṃ suttaṃ āvutaṃ nīlaṃ vā pītaṃ vā lohitaṃ vā odātaṃ vā paṇḍusuttaṃ vā’ti.**And it’s strung with a thread of blue, yellow, red, white, or golden brown.’*";
P_HTM[4455]="*Evameva kho, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā evaṃ pajānanti:**In the same way, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to understand this:*";
P_HTM[4456]="*‘ayaṃ kho me kāyo rūpī cātumahābhūtiko mātāpettikasambhavo odanakummāsūpacayo aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammo;**‘This body of mine is physical. It’s made up of the four primary elements, produced by mother and father, built up from rice and porridge, liable to impermanence, to wearing away and erosion, to breaking up and destruction.*";
P_HTM[4457]="*idañca pana me viññāṇaṃ ettha sitaṃ ettha paṭibaddhan’ti.**And this consciousness of mine is attached to it, tied to it.’*";
P_HTM[4458]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4459]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā imamhā kāyā aññaṃ kāyaṃ abhinimminanti rūpiṃ manomayaṃ sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ ahīnindriyaṃ.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to create from this body another body, consisting of form, mind-made, complete in all its various parts, not deficient in any faculty.*";
P_HTM[4460]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, puriso muñjamhā īsikaṃ pabbāheyya;**Suppose a person was to draw a reed out from its sheath.*";
P_HTM[4461]="*tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[4462]="*‘ayaṃ muñjo, ayaṃ īsikā; añño muñjo, aññā īsikā; muñjamhā tveva īsikā pabbāḷhā’ti.**‘This is the reed, this is the sheath. The reed and the sheath are different things. The reed has been drawn out from the sheath.’*";
P_HTM[4463]="*Seyyathā vā panudāyi, puriso asiṃ kosiyā pabbāheyya;**Or suppose a person was to draw a sword out from its scabbard.*";
P_HTM[4464]="*tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[4465]="*‘ayaṃ asi, ayaṃ kosi; añño asi aññā kosi; kosiyā tveva asi pabbāḷho’ti.**‘This is the sword, this is the scabbard. The sword and the scabbard are different things. The sword has been drawn out from the scabbard.’*";
P_HTM[4466]="*Seyyathā vā, panudāyi, puriso ahiṃ karaṇḍā uddhareyya;**Or suppose a person was to draw a snake out from its slough.*";
P_HTM[4467]="*tassa evamassa:**They’d think:*";
P_HTM[4468]="*‘ayaṃ ahi, ayaṃ karaṇḍo; añño ahi, añño karaṇḍo; karaṇḍā tveva ahi ubbhato’ti.**‘This is the snake, this is the slough. The snake and the slough are different things. The snake has been drawn out from the slough.’*";
P_HTM[4469]="*Evameva kho, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā imamhā kāyā aññaṃ kāyaṃ abhinimminanti rūpiṃ manomayaṃ sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ ahīnindriyaṃ.**In the same way, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to create from this body another body, consisting of form, mind-made, complete in all its various parts, not deficient in any faculty.*";
P_HTM[4470]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4471]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhonti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā honti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamānā gacchanti, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karonti, seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchanti, seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamanti, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimasanti parimajjanti, yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattenti.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying themselves and becoming one again; appearing and disappearing; going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful. They control the body as far as the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[4472]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, dakkho kumbhakāro vā kumbhakārantevāsī vā suparikammakatāya mattikāya yaṃ yadeva bhājanavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya taṃ tadeva kareyya abhinipphādeyya;**Suppose a deft potter or their apprentice had some well-prepared clay. They could produce any kind of pot that they like.*";
P_HTM[4473]="*seyyathā vā panudāyi, dakkho dantakāro vā dantakārantevāsī vā suparikammakatasmiṃ dantasmiṃ yaṃ yadeva dantavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya taṃ tadeva kareyya abhinipphādeyya;**Or suppose a deft ivory-carver or their apprentice had some well-prepared ivory. They could produce any kind of ivory item that they like.*";
P_HTM[4474]="*seyyathā vā panudāyi, dakkho suvaṇṇakāro vā suvaṇṇakārantevāsī vā suparikammakatasmiṃ suvaṇṇasmiṃ yaṃ yadeva suvaṇṇavikatiṃ ākaṅkheyya taṃ tadeva kareyya abhinipphādeyya.**Or suppose a deft goldsmith or their apprentice had some well-prepared gold. They could produce any kind of gold item that they like.*";
P_HTM[4475]="*Evameva kho, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhonti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā honti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamānā gacchanti, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karonti, seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchanti, seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamanti, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimasanti parimajjanti, yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattenti.**In the same way, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to wield the many kinds of psychic power …*";
P_HTM[4476]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4477]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇanti—dibbe ca mānuse ca, ye dūre santike ca.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use so that, with clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, they hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.*";
P_HTM[4478]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, balavā saṅkhadhamo appakasireneva cātuddisā viññāpeyya;**Suppose there was a powerful horn blower. They’d easily make themselves heard in the four directions.*";
P_HTM[4479]="*evameva kho, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇanti—dibbe ca mānuse ca, ye dūre santike ca.**In the same way, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use so that, with clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, they hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.*";
P_HTM[4480]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4481]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānanti—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti; sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sadosaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītadosaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti; samohaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘samohaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītamohaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti; saṃkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘saṃkhittaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vikkhittaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti; mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ ‘mahaggataṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ ‘amahaggataṃ cittan’ti pajānanti; sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sauttaraṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ ‘anuttaraṃ cittan’ti pajānanti; samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘samāhitaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘asamāhitaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti; vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘avimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with their own mind. They understand mind with greed as ‘mind with greed’, and mind without greed as ‘mind without greed’; mind with hate as ‘mind with hate’, and mind without hate as ‘mind without hate’; mind with delusion as ‘mind with delusion’, and mind without delusion as ‘mind without delusion’; constricted mind as ‘constricted mind’, and scattered mind as ‘scattered mind’; expansive mind as ‘expansive mind’, and unexpansive mind as ‘unexpansive mind’; mind that is not supreme as ‘mind that is not supreme’, and mind that is supreme as ‘mind that is supreme’; mind immersed in samādhi as ‘mind immersed in samādhi’, and mind not immersed in samādhi as ‘mind not immersed in samādhi’; freed mind as ‘freed mind’, and unfreed mind as ‘unfreed mind’.*";
P_HTM[4482]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanakajātiko ādāse vā parisuddhe pariyodāte acche vā udakapatte sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno sakaṇikaṃ vā ‘sakaṇikan’ti jāneyya, akaṇikaṃ vā ‘akaṇikan’ti jāneyya;**Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of adornments, and they check their own reflection in a clean bright mirror or a clear bowl of water. If they had a spot they’d know ‘I have a spot’, and if they had no spots they’d know ‘I have no spots’.*";
P_HTM[4483]="*evameva kho, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānanti—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti, vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ … pe … sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ … vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ … samohaṃ vā cittaṃ … vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ … saṃkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ … vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ … mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ … amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ … sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ … anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ … samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ … asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ … vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ … avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘avimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānanti.**In the same way, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with their own mind …*";
P_HTM[4484]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4485]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussaranti, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi, anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to recollect the many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[4486]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, puriso sakamhā gāmā aññaṃ gāmaṃ gaccheyya, tamhāpi gāmā aññaṃ gāmaṃ gaccheyya; so tamhā gāmā sakaṃyeva gāmaṃ paccāgaccheyya; tassa evamassa: ‘ahaṃ kho sakamhā gāmā aññaṃ gāmaṃ agacchiṃ, tatra evaṃ aṭṭhāsiṃ evaṃ nisīdiṃ evaṃ abhāsiṃ evaṃ tuṇhī ahosiṃ; tamhāpi gāmā amuṃ gāmaṃ agacchiṃ, tatrāpi evaṃ aṭṭhāsiṃ evaṃ nisīdiṃ evaṃ abhāsiṃ evaṃ tuṇhī ahosiṃ, somhi tamhā gāmā sakaṃyeva gāmaṃ paccāgato’ti.**Suppose a person was to leave their home village and go to another village. From that village they’d go to yet another village. And from that village they’d return to their home village. They’d think: ‘I went from my home village to another village. There I stood like this, sat like that, spoke like this, or kept silent like that. From that village I went to yet another village. There too I stood like this, sat like that, spoke like this, or kept silent like that. And from that village I returned to my home village.’*";
P_HTM[4487]="*Evameva kho, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussaranti, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussaranti.**In the same way, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to recollect the many kinds of past lives.*";
P_HTM[4488]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4489]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passanti cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānanti: ‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā; ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti. Iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passanti cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānanti.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use so that, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds: ‘These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[4490]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, dve agārā sadvārā. Tatra cakkhumā puriso majjhe ṭhito passeyya manusse gehaṃ pavisantepi nikkhamantepi anucaṅkamantepi anuvicarantepi;**Suppose there were two houses with doors. A person with good eyesight standing in between them would see people entering and leaving a house and wandering to and fro.*";
P_HTM[4491]="*evameva kho, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passanti cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānanti … pe …**In the same way, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use so that, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn …*";
P_HTM[4492]="*tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4493]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti.**Furthermore, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4494]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, pabbatasaṅkhepe udakarahado accho vippasanno anāvilo, tattha cakkhumā puriso tīre ṭhito passeyya sippisambukampi sakkharakaṭhalampi macchagumbampi carantampi tiṭṭhantampi. Tassa evamassa: ‘ayaṃ kho udakarahado accho vippasanno anāvilo, tatrime sippisambukāpi sakkharakaṭhalāpi macchagumbāpi carantipi tiṭṭhantipī’ti.**Suppose there was a lake that was transparent, clear, and unclouded. A person with good eyesight standing on the bank would see the mussel shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or staying still. They’d think: ‘This lake is transparent, clear, and unclouded. And here are the mussel shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or staying still.’*";
P_HTM[4495]="*Evameva kho, udāyi, akkhātā mayā sāvakānaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipannā me sāvakā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti.**In the same way, I have explained to my disciples a practice that they use to realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4496]="*Tatra ca pana me sāvakā bahū abhiññāvosānapāramippattā viharanti.**And many of my disciples meditate on that having attained perfection and consummation of insight.*";
P_HTM[4497]="*Ayaṃ kho, udāyi, pañcamo dhammo yena mama sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanti.**This is the fifth quality because of which my disciples are loyal to me.*";
P_HTM[4498]="*Ime kho, udāyi, pañca dhammā yehi mamaṃ sāvakā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharantī”ti.**These are the five qualities because of which my disciples honor, respect, revere, and venerate me; and after honoring and respecting me, they remain loyal to me.”*";
P_HTM[4499]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4500]="*Attamano sakuludāyī paribbājako bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, the wanderer Sakuludāyī was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4501]="*Mahāsakuludāyisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4502]="*78. Samaṇamuṇḍikasutta**With Uggāhamāna Samaṇamuṇḍika*";
P_HTM[4503]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4504]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4505]="*Tena kho pana samayena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto samayappavādake tindukācīre ekasālake mallikāya ārāme paṭivasati mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ pañcamattehi paribbājakasatehi.**Now at that time the wanderer Uggāhamāna Samaṇamuṇḍikāputta was residing together with around three hundred wanderers in Mallikā’s single-halled monastery for group debates, set among the flaking pale-moon ebony trees.*";
P_HTM[4506]="*Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati sāvatthiyā nikkhami divā divassa bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**Then the master builder Pañcakaṅga left Sāvatthī in the middle of the day to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4507]="*Atha kho pañcakaṅgassa thapatissa etadahosi:**It occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[4508]="*“akālo kho tāva bhagavantaṃ dassanāya;**“It’s the wrong time to see the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4509]="*paṭisallīno bhagavā.**as he’s in retreat.*";
P_HTM[4510]="*Manobhāvaniyānampi bhikkhūnaṃ asamayo dassanāya;**And it’s the wrong time to see the esteemed mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4511]="*paṭisallīnā manobhāvaniyā bhikkhū.**as they’re in retreat.*";
P_HTM[4512]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yena samayappavādako tindukācīro ekasālako mallikāya ārāmo yena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti.**Why don’t I go to Mallikā’s monastery to visit the wanderer Uggāhamāna?”*";
P_HTM[4513]="*Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yena samayappavādako tindukācīro ekasālako mallikāya ārāmo yena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto tenupasaṅkami.**So that’s what he did.*";
P_HTM[4514]="*Tena kho pana samayena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ nisinno hoti unnādiniyā uccāsaddamahāsaddāya anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathentiyā, seyyathidaṃ—**Now at that time, Uggāhamāna was sitting together with a large assembly of wanderers making an uproar, a dreadful racket. They engaged in all kinds of unworthy talk, such as*";
P_HTM[4515]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā.**talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence.*";
P_HTM[4516]="*Addasā kho uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Uggāhamāna saw Pañcakaṅga coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[4517]="*Disvāna sakaṃ parisaṃ saṇṭhāpesi:**and hushed his own assembly,*";
P_HTM[4518]="*“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha;**“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.*";
P_HTM[4519]="*ayaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako āgacchati pañcakaṅgo thapati.**Here comes Pañcakaṅga, a disciple of the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[4520]="*Yāvatā kho pana samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakā gihī odātavasanā sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasanti ayaṃ tesaṃ aññataro pañcakaṅgo thapati.**He is included among the white-clothed lay disciples of the ascetic Gotama, who is residing in Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4521]="*Appasaddakāmā kho pana te āyasmanto appasaddavinītā appasaddassa vaṇṇavādino;**Such venerables like the quiet, are educated to be quiet, and praise the quiet.*";
P_HTM[4522]="*appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”*";
P_HTM[4523]="*Atha kho te paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**Then those wanderers fell silent.*";
P_HTM[4524]="*Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yena uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā uggāhamānena paribbājakena samaṇamuṇḍikāputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Pañcakaṅga approached Uggāhamāna, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4525]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ uggāhamāno paribbājako samaṇamuṇḍikāputto etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. Uggāhamāna said to him:*";
P_HTM[4526]="*“catūhi kho ahaṃ, gahapati, dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi sampannakusalaṃ paramakusalaṃ uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ.**“Householder, when an individual has four qualities I describe them as an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment.*";
P_HTM[4527]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4528]="*Idha, gahapati, na kāyena pāpakammaṃ karoti, na pāpakaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati, na pāpakaṃ saṅkappaṃ saṅkappeti, na pāpakaṃ ājīvaṃ ājīvati—**It’s when they do no bad deeds with their body; speak no bad words; think no bad thoughts; and don’t earn a living by bad livelihood.*";
P_HTM[4529]="*imehi kho ahaṃ, gahapati, catūhi dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi sampannakusalaṃ paramakusalaṃ uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhan”ti.**When an individual has these four qualities I describe them as an invincible ascetic.”*";
P_HTM[4530]="*Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati uggāhamānassa paribbājakassa samaṇamuṇḍikāputtassa bhāsitaṃ neva abhinandi nappaṭikkosi.**Then Pañcakaṅga neither approved nor dismissed that mendicant’s statement.*";
P_HTM[4531]="*Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi:**He got up from his seat, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4532]="*“bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmī”ti.**“I will learn the meaning of this statement from the Buddha himself.”*";
P_HTM[4533]="*Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Then he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[4534]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yāvatako ahosi uggāhamānena paribbājakena samaṇamuṇḍikāputtena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi.**and informed the Buddha of all that had been discussed.*";
P_HTM[4535]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[4536]="*“evaṃ sante kho, thapati, daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako sampannakusalo bhavissati paramakusalo uttamapattipatto samaṇo ayojjho, yathā uggāhamānassa paribbājakassa samaṇamuṇḍikāputtassa vacanaṃ.**“Master builder, if what Uggāhamāna says is true, a little baby boy is an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment.*";
P_HTM[4537]="*Daharassa hi, thapati, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa kāyotipi na hoti, kuto pana kāyena pāpakammaṃ karissati, aññatra phanditamattā.**For a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘a body’, so how could they possibly do a bad deed with their body, apart from just wriggling?*";
P_HTM[4538]="*Daharassa hi, thapati, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa vācātipi na hoti, kuto pana pāpakaṃ vācaṃ bhāsissati, aññatra roditamattā.**And a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘speech’, so how could they possibly speak bad words, apart from just crying?*";
P_HTM[4539]="*Daharassa hi, thapati, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa saṅkappotipi na hoti, kuto pana pāpakaṃ saṅkappaṃ saṅkappissati, aññatra vikūjitamattā.**And a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘thought’, so how could they possibly think bad thoughts, apart from just whimpering?*";
P_HTM[4540]="*Daharassa hi, thapati, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa ājīvotipi na hoti, kuto pana pāpakaṃ ājīvaṃ ājīvissati, aññatra mātuthaññā.**And a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘livelihood’, so how could they possibly earn a living by bad livelihood, apart from their mother’s breast?*";
P_HTM[4541]="*Evaṃ sante kho, thapati, daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako sampannakusalo bhavissati paramakusalo uttamapattipatto samaṇo ayojjho, yathā uggāhamānassa paribbājakassa samaṇamuṇḍikāputtassa vacanaṃ.**If what Uggāhamāna says is true, a little baby boy is an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment.*";
P_HTM[4542]="*Catūhi kho ahaṃ, thapati, dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi na ceva sampannakusalaṃ na paramakusalaṃ na uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ, api cimaṃ daharaṃ kumāraṃ mandaṃ uttānaseyyakaṃ samadhigayha tiṭṭhati.**When an individual has four qualities I describe them, not as an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment—but as having achieved the same level as a little baby.*";
P_HTM[4543]="*Katamehi catūhi?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4544]="*Idha, thapati, na kāyena pāpakammaṃ karoti, na pāpakaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati, na pāpakaṃ saṅkappaṃ saṅkappeti, na pāpakaṃ ājīvaṃ ājīvati—**It’s when they do no bad deeds with their body; speak no bad words; think no bad thoughts; and don’t earn a living by bad livelihood.*";
P_HTM[4545]="*imehi kho ahaṃ, thapati, catūhi dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi na ceva sampannakusalaṃ na paramakusalaṃ na uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ, api cimaṃ daharaṃ kumāraṃ mandaṃ uttānaseyyakaṃ samadhigayha tiṭṭhati.**When an individual has these four qualities I describe them, not as an invincible ascetic, but as having achieved the same level as a little baby.*";
P_HTM[4546]="*Dasahi kho ahaṃ, thapati, dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi sampannakusalaṃ paramakusalaṃ uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ.**When an individual has ten qualities, master builder, I describe them as an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment.*";
P_HTM[4547]="*Ime akusalā sīlā;**But certain things must first be understood, I say. ‘These are unskillful behaviors.’*";
P_HTM[4548]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4549]="*Itosamuṭṭhānā akusalā sīlā;**‘Unskillful behaviors stem from this.’*";
P_HTM[4550]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4551]="*Idha akusalā sīlā aparisesā nirujjhanti;**‘Here unskillful behaviors cease without anything left over.’*";
P_HTM[4552]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4553]="*Evaṃ paṭipanno akusalānaṃ sīlānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti;**‘Someone practicing like this is practicing for the cessation of unskillful behaviors.’*";
P_HTM[4554]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4555]="*Ime kusalā sīlā;**‘These are skillful behaviors.’*";
P_HTM[4556]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4557]="*Itosamuṭṭhānā kusalā sīlā;**‘Skillful behaviors stem from this.’*";
P_HTM[4558]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4559]="*Idha kusalā sīlā aparisesā nirujjhanti;**‘Here skillful behaviors cease without anything left over.’*";
P_HTM[4560]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4561]="*Evaṃ paṭipanno kusalānaṃ sīlānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti;**‘Someone practicing like this is practicing for the cessation of skillful behaviors.’*";
P_HTM[4562]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4563]="*Ime akusalā saṅkappā;**‘These are unskillful thoughts.’*";
P_HTM[4564]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4565]="*Itosamuṭṭhānā akusalā saṅkappā;**‘Unskillful thoughts stem from this.’*";
P_HTM[4566]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4567]="*Idha akusalā saṅkappā aparisesā nirujjhanti;**‘Here unskillful thoughts cease without anything left over.’*";
P_HTM[4568]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4569]="*Evaṃ paṭipanno akusalānaṃ saṅkappānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti;**‘Someone practicing like this is practicing for the cessation of unskillful thoughts.’*";
P_HTM[4570]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4571]="*Ime kusalā saṅkappā;**‘These are skillful thoughts.’*";
P_HTM[4572]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4573]="*Itosamuṭṭhānā kusalā saṅkappā;**‘Skillful thoughts stem from this.’*";
P_HTM[4574]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4575]="*Idha kusalā saṅkappā aparisesā nirujjhanti;**‘Here skillful thoughts cease without anything left over.’*";
P_HTM[4576]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4577]="*Evaṃ paṭipanno kusalānaṃ saṅkappānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti;**‘Someone practicing like this is practicing for the cessation of skillful thoughts.’*";
P_HTM[4578]="*tamahaṃ, thapati, veditabbanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[4579]="*Katame ca, thapati, akusalā sīlā?**And what, master builder, are unskillful behaviors?*";
P_HTM[4580]="*Akusalaṃ kāyakammaṃ, akusalaṃ vacīkammaṃ, pāpako ājīvo—**Unskillful deeds by way of body and speech, and bad livelihood.*";
P_HTM[4581]="*ime vuccanti, thapati, akusalā sīlā.**These are called unskillful behaviors.*";
P_HTM[4582]="*Ime ca, thapati, akusalā sīlā kiṃsamuṭṭhānā?**And where do these unskillful behaviors stem from?*";
P_HTM[4583]="*Samuṭṭhānampi nesaṃ vuttaṃ.**Where they stem from has been stated.*";
P_HTM[4584]="*‘Cittasamuṭṭhānā’tissa vacanīyaṃ.**You should say that they stem from the mind.*";
P_HTM[4585]="*Katamaṃ cittaṃ?**What mind?*";
P_HTM[4586]="*Cittampi hi bahuṃ anekavidhaṃ nānappakārakaṃ.**The mind takes many and diverse forms.*";
P_HTM[4587]="*Yaṃ cittaṃ sarāgaṃ sadosaṃ samohaṃ, itosamuṭṭhānā akusalā sīlā.**But unskillful behaviors stem from a mind that has greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[4588]="*Ime ca, thapati, akusalā sīlā kuhiṃ aparisesā nirujjhanti?**And where do these unskillful behaviors cease without anything left over?*";
P_HTM[4589]="*Nirodhopi nesaṃ vutto.**Their cessation has also been stated.*";
P_HTM[4590]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveti, vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveti, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya manosucaritaṃ bhāveti, micchājīvaṃ pahāya sammājīvena jīvitaṃ kappeti—**It’s when a mendicant gives up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and develops good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind; they give up wrong livelihood and earn a living by right livelihood.*";
P_HTM[4591]="*etthete akusalā sīlā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**This is where these unskillful behaviors cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[4592]="*Kathaṃ paṭipanno, thapati, akusalānaṃ sīlānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti?**And how is someone practicing for the cessation of unskillful behaviors?*";
P_HTM[4593]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;**It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise.*";
P_HTM[4594]="*uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen are given up.*";
P_HTM[4595]="*anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities arise.*";
P_HTM[4596]="*uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are completed by development.*";
P_HTM[4597]="*Evaṃ paṭipanno kho, thapati, akusalānaṃ sīlānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti.**Someone practicing like this is practicing for the cessation of unskillful behaviors.*";
P_HTM[4598]="*Katame ca, thapati, kusalā sīlā?**And what are skillful behaviors?*";
P_HTM[4599]="*Kusalaṃ kāyakammaṃ, kusalaṃ vacīkammaṃ, ājīvaparisuddhampi kho ahaṃ, thapati, sīlasmiṃ vadāmi.**Skillful deeds by way of body and speech, and purified livelihood are included in behavior, I say.*";
P_HTM[4600]="*Ime vuccanti, thapati, kusalā sīlā.**These are called skillful behaviors.*";
P_HTM[4601]="*Ime ca, thapati, kusalā sīlā kiṃsamuṭṭhānā?**And where do these skillful behaviors stem from?*";
P_HTM[4602]="*Samuṭṭhānampi nesaṃ vuttaṃ.**Where they stem from has been stated.*";
P_HTM[4603]="*‘Cittasamuṭṭhānā’tissa vacanīyaṃ.**You should say that they stem from the mind.*";
P_HTM[4604]="*Katamaṃ cittaṃ?**What mind?*";
P_HTM[4605]="*Cittampi hi bahuṃ anekavidhaṃ nānappakārakaṃ.**The mind takes many and diverse forms.*";
P_HTM[4606]="*Yaṃ cittaṃ vītarāgaṃ vītadosaṃ vītamohaṃ, itosamuṭṭhānā kusalā sīlā.**But skillful behaviors stem from a mind that is free from greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[4607]="*Ime ca, thapati, kusalā sīlā kuhiṃ aparisesā nirujjhanti?**And where do these skillful behaviors cease without anything left over?*";
P_HTM[4608]="*Nirodhopi nesaṃ vutto.**Their cessation has also been stated.*";
P_HTM[4609]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti no ca sīlamayo,**It’s when a mendicant behaves ethically, but they don’t identify with their ethical behavior.*";
P_HTM[4610]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti; yatthassa te kusalā sīlā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where these skillful behaviors cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[4611]="*Kathaṃ paṭipanno ca, thapati, kusalānaṃ sīlānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti?**And how is someone practicing for the cessation of skillful behaviors?*";
P_HTM[4612]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;**It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise …*";
P_HTM[4613]="*uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya … pe …**so that unskillful qualities are given up …*";
P_HTM[4614]="*anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya … pe …**so that skillful qualities arise …*";
P_HTM[4615]="*uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are fulfilled by development.*";
P_HTM[4616]="*Evaṃ paṭipanno kho, thapati, kusalānaṃ sīlānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti.**Someone practicing like this is practicing for the cessation of skillful behaviors.*";
P_HTM[4617]="*Katame ca, thapati, akusalā saṅkappā?**And what are unskillful thoughts?*";
P_HTM[4618]="*Kāmasaṅkappo, byāpādasaṅkappo, vihiṃsāsaṅkappo—**Thoughts of sensuality, of malice, and of cruelty.*";
P_HTM[4619]="*ime vuccanti, thapati, akusalā saṅkappā.**These are called unskillful thoughts.*";
P_HTM[4620]="*Ime ca, thapati, akusalā saṅkappā kiṃsamuṭṭhānā?**And where do these unskillful thoughts stem from?*";
P_HTM[4621]="*Samuṭṭhānampi nesaṃ vuttaṃ.**Where they stem from has been stated.*";
P_HTM[4622]="*‘Saññāsamuṭṭhānā’tissa vacanīyaṃ.**You should say that they stem from perception.*";
P_HTM[4623]="*Katamā saññā?**What perception?*";
P_HTM[4624]="*Saññāpi hi bahū anekavidhā nānappakārakā.**Perception takes many and diverse forms.*";
P_HTM[4625]="*Kāmasaññā, byāpādasaññā, vihiṃsāsaññā—**Perceptions of sensuality, malice, and cruelty—*";
P_HTM[4626]="*itosamuṭṭhānā akusalā saṅkappā.**unskillful thoughts stem from this.*";
P_HTM[4627]="*Ime ca, thapati, akusalā saṅkappā kuhiṃ aparisesā nirujjhanti?**And where do these unskillful thoughts cease without anything left over?*";
P_HTM[4628]="*Nirodhopi nesaṃ vutto.**Their cessation has also been stated.*";
P_HTM[4629]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4630]="*etthete akusalā saṅkappā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**This is where these unskillful thoughts cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[4631]="*Kathaṃ paṭipanno ca, thapati, akusalānaṃ saṅkappānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti?**And how is someone practicing for the cessation of unskillful thoughts?*";
P_HTM[4632]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;**It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise …*";
P_HTM[4633]="*uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya … pe …**so that unskillful qualities are given up …*";
P_HTM[4634]="*anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya … pe …**so that skillful qualities arise …*";
P_HTM[4635]="*uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are fulfilled by development.*";
P_HTM[4636]="*Evaṃ paṭipanno kho, thapati, akusalānaṃ saṅkappānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti.**Someone practicing like this is practicing for the cessation of unskillful thoughts.*";
P_HTM[4637]="*Katame ca, thapati, kusalā saṅkappā?**And what are skillful thoughts?*";
P_HTM[4638]="*Nekkhammasaṅkappo, abyāpādasaṅkappo, avihiṃsāsaṅkappo—**Thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness.*";
P_HTM[4639]="*ime vuccanti, thapati, kusalā saṅkappā.**These are called skillful thoughts.*";
P_HTM[4640]="*Ime ca, thapati, kusalā saṅkappā kiṃsamuṭṭhānā?**And where do these skillful thoughts stem from?*";
P_HTM[4641]="*Samuṭṭhānampi nesaṃ vuttaṃ.**Where they stem from has been stated.*";
P_HTM[4642]="*‘Saññāsamuṭṭhānā’tissa vacanīyaṃ.**You should say that they stem from perception.*";
P_HTM[4643]="*Katamā saññā?**What perception?*";
P_HTM[4644]="*Saññāpi hi bahū anekavidhā nānappakārakā.**Perception takes many and diverse forms.*";
P_HTM[4645]="*Nekkhammasaññā, abyāpādasaññā, avihiṃsāsaññā—**Perceptions of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness—*";
P_HTM[4646]="*itosamuṭṭhānā kusalā saṅkappā.**skillful thoughts stem from this.*";
P_HTM[4647]="*Ime ca, thapati, kusalā saṅkappā kuhiṃ aparisesā nirujjhanti?**And where do these skillful thoughts cease without anything left over?*";
P_HTM[4648]="*Nirodhopi nesaṃ vutto.**Their cessation has also been stated.*";
P_HTM[4649]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**It’s when, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4650]="*etthete kusalā saṅkappā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**This is where these skillful thoughts cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[4651]="*Kathaṃ paṭipanno ca, thapati, kusalānaṃ saṅkappānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti?**And how is someone practicing for the cessation of skillful thoughts?*";
P_HTM[4652]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati;**It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise …*";
P_HTM[4653]="*uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya … pe …**so that unskillful qualities are given up …*";
P_HTM[4654]="*anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya … pe …**so that skillful qualities arise …*";
P_HTM[4655]="*uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati.**so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are fulfilled by development.*";
P_HTM[4656]="*Evaṃ paṭipanno kho, thapati, kusalānaṃ saṅkappānaṃ nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti.**Someone practicing like this is practicing for the cessation of skillful thoughts.*";
P_HTM[4657]="*Katamehi cāhaṃ, thapati, dasahi dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi sampannakusalaṃ paramakusalaṃ uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhaṃ?**Master builder, when an individual has what ten qualities do I describe them as an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment?*";
P_HTM[4658]="*Idha, thapati, bhikkhu asekhāya sammādiṭṭhiyā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāsaṅkappena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāvācāya samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammākammantena samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāājīvena samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāvāyāmena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāsatiyā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāsamādhinā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāñāṇena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāvimuttiyā samannāgato hoti—**It’s when a mendicant has an adept’s right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4659]="*imehi kho ahaṃ, thapati, dasahi dhammehi samannāgataṃ purisapuggalaṃ paññapemi sampannakusalaṃ paramakusalaṃ uttamapattipattaṃ samaṇaṃ ayojjhan”ti.**When an individual has these ten qualities, I describe them as an invincible ascetic—accomplished in the skillful, excelling in the skillful, attained to the highest attainment.”*";
P_HTM[4660]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4661]="*Attamano pañcakaṅgo thapati bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Pañcakaṅga the master builder was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4662]="*Samaṇamuṇḍikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4663]="*79. Cūḷasakuludāyisutta**The Shorter Discourse With Sakuludāyī*";
P_HTM[4664]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4665]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4666]="*Tena kho pana samayena sakuludāyī paribbājako moranivāpe paribbājakārāme paṭivasati mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ.**Now at that time the wanderer Sakuludāyī was residing together with a large assembly of wanderers in the monastery of the wanderers in the peacocks’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4667]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Rājagaha for alms.*";
P_HTM[4668]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[4669]="*“atippago kho tāva rājagahe piṇḍāya carituṃ.**“It’s too early to wander for alms in Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[4670]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yena moranivāpo paribbājakārāmo yena sakuludāyī paribbājako tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti.**Why don’t I visit the wanderer Sakuludāyī at the monastery of the wanderers in the peacocks’ feeding ground?”*";
P_HTM[4671]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena moranivāpo paribbājakārāmo tenupasaṅkami.**Then the Buddha went to the monastery of the wanderers.*";
P_HTM[4672]="*Tena kho pana samayena sakuludāyī paribbājako mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ nisinno hoti unnādiniyā uccāsaddamahāsaddāya anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathentiyā, seyyathidaṃ—**Now at that time, Sakuludāyī was sitting together with a large assembly of wanderers making an uproar, a dreadful racket. They engaged in all kinds of unworthy talk, such as*";
P_HTM[4673]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā.**talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence.*";
P_HTM[4674]="*Addasā kho sakuludāyī paribbājako bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Sakuludāyī saw the Buddha coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[4675]="*Disvāna sakaṃ parisaṃ saṇṭhāpesi:**and hushed his own assembly,*";
P_HTM[4676]="*“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha.**“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.*";
P_HTM[4677]="*Ayaṃ samaṇo gotamo āgacchati;**Here comes the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[4678]="*appasaddakāmo kho pana so āyasmā appasaddassa vaṇṇavādī.**The venerable likes quiet and praises quiet.*";
P_HTM[4679]="*Appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”*";
P_HTM[4680]="*Atha kho te paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**Then those wanderers fell silent.*";
P_HTM[4681]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena sakuludāyī paribbājako tenupasaṅkami.**Then the Buddha approached Sakuludāyī,*";
P_HTM[4682]="*Atha kho sakuludāyī paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**who said to him,*";
P_HTM[4683]="*“etu kho, bhante, bhagavā.**“Come, Blessed One!*";
P_HTM[4684]="*Svāgataṃ, bhante, bhagavato.**Welcome, Blessed One!*";
P_HTM[4685]="*Cirassaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavā imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya.**It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here.*";
P_HTM[4686]="*Nisīdatu, bhante, bhagavā;**Please, sir, sit down, this seat is ready.”*";
P_HTM[4687]="*idamāsanaṃ paññattan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4688]="*Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane.**The Buddha sat on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[4689]="*Sakuludāyīpi kho paribbājako aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**while Sakuludāyī took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[4690]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho sakuludāyiṃ paribbājakaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[4691]="*“kāya nuttha, udāyi, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?**“Udāyī, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was unfinished?”*";
P_HTM[4692]="*“Tiṭṭhatesā, bhante, kathā yāya mayaṃ etarahi kathāya sannisinnā.**“Sir, leave aside what we were sitting talking about just now.*";
P_HTM[4693]="*Nesā, bhante, kathā bhagavato dullabhā bhavissati pacchāpi savanāya.**It won’t be hard for you to hear about that later.*";
P_HTM[4694]="*Yadāhaṃ, bhante, imaṃ parisaṃ anupasaṅkanto homi athāyaṃ parisā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathentī nisinnā hoti;**When I don’t come to the assembly, they sit and engage in all kinds of unworthy talk.*";
P_HTM[4695]="*yadā ca kho ahaṃ, bhante, imaṃ parisaṃ upasaṅkanto homi athāyaṃ parisā mamaññeva mukhaṃ ullokentī nisinnā hoti:**But when I have come to the assembly, they sit gazing up at my face alone, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4696]="*‘yaṃ no samaṇo udāyī dhammaṃ bhāsissati taṃ sossāmā’ti;**‘Whatever the ascetic Udāyī teaches, we shall listen to it.’*";
P_HTM[4697]="*yadā pana, bhante, bhagavā imaṃ parisaṃ upasaṅkanto hoti athāhañceva ayañca parisā bhagavato mukhaṃ ullokentā nisinnā homa:**But when the Buddha has come to the assembly, both myself and the assembly sit gazing up at your face, thinking,*";
P_HTM[4698]="*‘yaṃ no bhagavā dhammaṃ bhāsissati taṃ sossāmā’”ti.**‘Whatever the Buddha teaches, we shall listen to it.’”*";
P_HTM[4699]="*“Tenahudāyi, taṃyevettha paṭibhātu yathā maṃ paṭibhāseyyā”ti.**“Well then, Udāyī, suggest something for me to talk about.”*";
P_HTM[4700]="*“Purimāni, bhante, divasāni purimatarāni sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānamāno ‘carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti.**“Master Gotama, a few days ago someone was claiming to be all-knowing and all-seeing, to know and see everything without exception, thus: ‘Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.’*";
P_HTM[4701]="*So mayā pubbantaṃ ārabbha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicari, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmesi, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātvākāsi.**When I asked them a question about the past, they dodged the issue, distracted the discussion with irrelevant points, and displayed annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[4702]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva ārabbha sati udapādi:**That reminded me of the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4703]="*‘aho nūna bhagavā, aho nūna sugato. Yo imesaṃ dhammānaṃ sukusalo’”ti.**‘Surely it must be the Blessed One, the Holy One who is so skilled in such matters.’”*";
P_HTM[4704]="*“Ko pana so, udāyi, sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānamāno ‘carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti, yo tayā pubbantaṃ ārabbha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicari, bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmesi kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātvākāsī”ti?**“But Udāyī, who was it that made such a claim and behaved in such a way?”*";
P_HTM[4705]="*“Nigaṇṭho, bhante, nāṭaputto”ti.**“It was Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4706]="*“Yo kho, udāyi, anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyya, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyya, so vā maṃ pubbantaṃ ārabbha pañhaṃ puccheyya, taṃ vāhaṃ pubbantaṃ ārabbha pañhaṃ puccheyyaṃ;**“Udāyī, someone who can recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details, might ask me a question about the past, or I might ask them a question about the past.*";
P_HTM[4707]="*so vā me pubbantaṃ ārabbha pañhassa veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheyya, tassa vāhaṃ pubbantaṃ ārabbha pañhassa veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheyyaṃ.**And they might satisfy me with their answer, or I might satisfy them with my answer.*";
P_HTM[4708]="*Yo kho, udāyi, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passeyya cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajāneyya, so vā maṃ aparantaṃ ārabbha pañhaṃ puccheyya, taṃ vāhaṃ aparantaṃ ārabbha pañhaṃ puccheyyaṃ;**Someone who, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, understands how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds might ask me a question about the future, or I might ask them a question about the future.*";
P_HTM[4709]="*so vā me aparantaṃ ārabbha pañhassa veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheyya, tassa vāhaṃ aparantaṃ ārabbha pañhassa veyyākaraṇena cittaṃ ārādheyyaṃ.**And they might satisfy me with their answer, or I might satisfy them with my answer.*";
P_HTM[4710]="*Api ca, udāyi, tiṭṭhatu pubbanto, tiṭṭhatu aparanto.**Nevertheless, Udāyī, leave aside the past and the future.*";
P_HTM[4711]="*Dhammaṃ te desessāmi—**I shall teach you the Dhamma:*";
P_HTM[4712]="*imasmiṃ sati idaṃ hoti, imassuppādā idaṃ uppajjati;**‘When this exists, that is; due to the arising of this, that arises.*";
P_HTM[4713]="*imasmiṃ asati idaṃ na hoti, imassa nirodhā idaṃ nirujjhatī”ti.**When this doesn’t exist, that is not; due to the cessation of this, that ceases.’”*";
P_HTM[4714]="*“Ahañhi, bhante, yāvatakampi me iminā attabhāvena paccanubhūtaṃ tampi nappahomi sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anussarituṃ,**“Well sir, I can’t even recall with features and details what I’ve undergone in this incarnation.*";
P_HTM[4715]="*kuto panāhaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarissāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarissāmi, seyyathāpi bhagavā?**How should I possibly recollect my many kinds of past lives with features and details, like the Buddha?*";
P_HTM[4716]="*Ahañhi, bhante, etarahi paṃsupisācakampi na passāmi,**And I can’t now see even a mud-goblin.*";
P_HTM[4717]="*kuto panāhaṃ dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passissāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānissāmi, seyyathāpi bhagavā?**How should I possibly, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, see sentient beings passing away and being reborn, like the Buddha?*";
P_HTM[4718]="*Yaṃ pana maṃ, bhante, bhagavā evamāha:**But then the Buddha told me,*";
P_HTM[4719]="*‘api ca, udāyi, tiṭṭhatu pubbanto, tiṭṭhatu aparanto;**‘Nevertheless, Udāyī, leave aside the past and the future.*";
P_HTM[4720]="*dhammaṃ te desessāmi—**I shall teach you the Dhamma:*";
P_HTM[4721]="*imasmiṃ sati idaṃ hoti, imassuppādā idaṃ uppajjati;**“When this exists, that is; due to the arising of this, that arises.*";
P_HTM[4722]="*imasmiṃ asati idaṃ na hoti, imassa nirodhā idaṃ nirujjhatī’ti tañca pana me bhiyyoso mattāya na pakkhāyati.**When this doesn’t exist, that is not; due to the cessation of this, that ceases.”’ But that is even more unclear to me.*";
P_HTM[4723]="*Appeva nāmāhaṃ, bhante, sake ācariyake bhagavato cittaṃ ārādheyyaṃ pañhassa veyyākaraṇenā”ti.**Perhaps I might satisfy the Buddha by answering a question about my own teacher’s doctrine.”*";
P_HTM[4724]="*“Kinti pana te, udāyi, sake ācariyake hotī”ti?**“But Udāyī, what is your own teacher’s doctrine?”*";
P_HTM[4725]="*“Amhākaṃ, bhante, sake ācariyake evaṃ hoti:**“Sir, it’s this:*";
P_HTM[4726]="*‘ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo, ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo’”ti.**‘This is the ultimate splendor, this is the ultimate splendor.’”*";
P_HTM[4727]="*“Yaṃ pana te etaṃ, udāyi, sake ācariyake evaṃ hoti:**“But what is that ultimate splendor?”*";
P_HTM[4728]="*‘ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo, ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo’ti, katamo so paramo vaṇṇo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4729]="*“Yasmā, bhante, vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthi so paramo vaṇṇo”ti.**“Sir, the ultimate splendor is the splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.”*";
P_HTM[4730]="*“Katamo pana so paramo vaṇṇo yasmā vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthī”ti?**“But what is that ultimate splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer?”*";
P_HTM[4731]="*“Yasmā, bhante, vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthi so paramo vaṇṇo”ti.**“Sir, the ultimate splendor is the splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.”*";
P_HTM[4732]="*“Dīghāpi kho te esā, udāyi, phareyya:**“Udāyī, you could draw this out for a long time.*";
P_HTM[4733]="*‘yasmā, bhante, vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthi so paramo vaṇṇo’ti vadesi, tañca vaṇṇaṃ na paññapesi.**You say, ‘The ultimate splendor is the splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.’ But you don’t describe that splendor.*";
P_HTM[4734]="*Seyyathāpi, udāyi, puriso evaṃ vadeyya:**Suppose a man was to say,*";
P_HTM[4735]="*‘ahaṃ yā imasmiṃ janapade janapadakalyāṇī taṃ icchāmi, taṃ kāmemī’ti.**‘Whoever the finest lady in the land is, it is her that I want, her I desire!’*";
P_HTM[4736]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him,*";
P_HTM[4737]="*‘ambho purisa, yaṃ tvaṃ janapadakalyāṇiṃ icchasi kāmesi, jānāsi taṃ janapadakalyāṇiṃ—khattiyī vā brāhmaṇī vā vessī vā suddī vā’ti?**‘Mister, that finest lady in the land who you desire—do you know whether she’s an aristocrat, a brahmin, a merchant, or a worker?’*";
P_HTM[4738]="*Iti puṭṭho ‘no’ti vadeyya.**Asked this, he’d say, ‘No.’*";
P_HTM[4739]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him,*";
P_HTM[4740]="*‘ambho purisa, yaṃ tvaṃ janapadakalyāṇiṃ icchasi kāmesi, jānāsi taṃ janapadakalyāṇiṃ—evaṃnāmā evaṅgottāti vāti … pe … dīghā vā rassā vā majjhimā vā kāḷī vā sāmā vā maṅguracchavī vāti … amukasmiṃ gāme vā nigame vā nagare vā’ti?**‘Mister, that finest lady in the land who you desire—do you know her name or clan? Whether she’s tall or short or medium? Whether her skin is black, brown, or tawny? What village, town, or city she comes from?’*";
P_HTM[4741]="*Iti puṭṭho ‘no’ti vadeyya.**Asked this, he’d say, ‘No.’*";
P_HTM[4742]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him,*";
P_HTM[4743]="*‘ambho purisa, yaṃ tvaṃ na jānāsi na passasi, taṃ tvaṃ icchasi kāmesī’ti?**‘Mister, do you desire someone who you’ve never even known or seen?’*";
P_HTM[4744]="*Iti puṭṭho ‘āmā’ti vadeyya.**Asked this, he’d say, ‘Yes.’*";
P_HTM[4745]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi—**What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4746]="*nanu evaṃ sante, tassa purisassa appāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti?**This being so, doesn’t that man’s statement turn out to have no demonstrable basis?”*";
P_HTM[4747]="*“Addhā kho, bhante, evaṃ sante tassa purisassa appāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti.**“Clearly that’s the case, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4748]="*“Evameva kho tvaṃ, udāyi, ‘yasmā, bhante, vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthi so paramo vaṇṇo’ti vadesi, tañca vaṇṇaṃ na paññapesī”ti.**“In the same way, you say, ‘The ultimate splendor is the splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.’ But you don’t describe that splendor.”*";
P_HTM[4749]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhante, maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato paṇḍukambale nikkhitto bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca, evaṃ vaṇṇo attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”ti.**“Sir, suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, well-worked. When placed on a cream rug it would shine and glow and radiate. Such is the splendor of the self that is sound after death.”*";
P_HTM[4750]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4751]="*yo vā maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato paṇḍukambale nikkhitto bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca, yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya kimi khajjopanako—imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: such a beryl gem, or a firefly in the dark of night?”*";
P_HTM[4752]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, rattandhakāratimisāya kimi khajjopanako—ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“A firefly in the dark of night, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4753]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4754]="*yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya kimi khajjopanako, yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya telappadīpo—imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: a firefly in the dark of night, or an oil lamp in the dark of night?”*";
P_HTM[4755]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, rattandhakāratimisāya telappadīpo—ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“An oil lamp in the dark of night, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4756]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4757]="*yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya telappadīpo, yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya mahāaggikkhandho—imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: an oil lamp in the dark of night, or a bonfire in the dark of night?”*";
P_HTM[4758]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, rattandhakāratimisāya mahāaggikkhandho—ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“A bonfire in the dark of night, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4759]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4760]="*yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya mahāaggikkhandho, yā vā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ viddhe vigatavalāhake deve osadhitārakā—imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: a bonfire in the dark of night, or the Morning Star in a clear and cloudless sky at the crack of dawn?”*";
P_HTM[4761]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ viddhe vigatavalāhake deve osadhitārakā—ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“The Morning Star in a clear and cloudless sky at the crack of dawn, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4762]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4763]="*yā vā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ viddhe vigatavalāhake deve osadhitārakā, yo vā tadahuposathe pannarase viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido aḍḍharattasamayaṃ cando—imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: the Morning Star in a clear and cloudless sky at the crack of dawn, or the full moon at midnight in a clear and cloudless sky on the fifteenth day sabbath?”*";
P_HTM[4764]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, tadahuposathe pannarase viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido aḍḍharattasamayaṃ cando—ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“The full moon at midnight in a clear and cloudless sky on the fifteenth day sabbath, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4765]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4766]="*yo vā tadahuposathe pannarase viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido aḍḍharattasamayaṃ cando, yo vā vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido majjhanhikasamayaṃ sūriyo—imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: the full moon at midnight in a clear and cloudless sky on the fifteenth day sabbath, or the sun at midday in a clear and cloudless sky in the last month of the rainy season?”*";
P_HTM[4767]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido majjhanhikasamayaṃ sūriyo—ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“The sun at midday in a clear and cloudless sky in the last month of the rainy season, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4768]="*“Ato kho te, udāyi, bahū hi bahutarā devā ye imesaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ ābhā nānubhonti, tyāhaṃ pajānāmi.**“Beyond this, Udāyī, I know very many gods on whom the light of the sun and moon make no impression.*";
P_HTM[4769]="*Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi:**Nevertheless, I do not say:*";
P_HTM[4770]="*‘yasmā vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthī’ti.**‘The splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.’*";
P_HTM[4771]="*Atha ca pana tvaṃ, udāyi, ‘yvāyaṃ vaṇṇo kiminā khajjopanakena nihīnataro ca patikiṭṭhataro ca so paramo vaṇṇo’ti vadesi, tañca vaṇṇaṃ na paññapesī”ti.**But of the splendor inferior to a firefly you say, ‘This is the ultimate splendor.’ And you don’t describe that splendor.”*";
P_HTM[4772]="*“Acchidaṃ bhagavā kathaṃ, acchidaṃ sugato kathan”ti.**“The Blessed One has cut short the discussion! The Holy One has cut short the discussion!”*";
P_HTM[4773]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, udāyi, evaṃ vadesi:**“But Udāyī, why do you say this?”*";
P_HTM[4774]="*‘acchidaṃ bhagavā kathaṃ, acchidaṃ sugato kathan’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4775]="*“Amhākaṃ, bhante, sake ācariyake evaṃ hoti:**“Sir, it says this in our own teacher’s doctrine:*";
P_HTM[4776]="*‘ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo, ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo’ti.**‘This is the ultimate splendor, this is the ultimate splendor.’*";
P_HTM[4777]="*Te mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā sake ācariyake samanuyuñjīyamānā samanuggāhīyamānā samanubhāsīyamānā rittā tucchā aparaddhā”ti.**But when pursued, pressed, and grilled on our own teacher’s doctrine, we turned out to be void, hollow, and mistaken.”*";
P_HTM[4778]="*“Kiṃ panudāyi, atthi ekantasukho loko, atthi ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti?**“But Udāyī, is there a world of perfect happiness? And is there a grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness?”*";
P_HTM[4779]="*“Amhākaṃ, bhante, sake ācariyake evaṃ hoti:**“Sir, it says this in our own teacher’s doctrine:*";
P_HTM[4780]="*‘atthi ekantasukho loko, atthi ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā’”ti.**‘There is a world of perfect happiness. And there is a grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness.’”*";
P_HTM[4781]="*“Katamā pana sā, udāyi, ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti?**“Well, what is that grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness?”*";
P_HTM[4782]="*“Idha, bhante, ekacco pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, aññataraṃ vā pana tapoguṇaṃ samādāya vattati.**“Sir, it’s when someone gives up killing living creatures, stealing, sexual misconduct, and lying. And they proceed having undertaken some kind of mortification.*";
P_HTM[4783]="*Ayaṃ kho sā, bhante, ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti.**This is the grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness.”*";
P_HTM[4784]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4785]="*yasmiṃ samaye pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, ekantasukhī vā tasmiṃ samaye attā hoti sukhadukkhī vā”ti?**On an occasion when someone refrains from killing living creatures, is their self perfectly happy at that time, or does it have both pleasure and pain?”*";
P_HTM[4786]="*“Sukhadukkhī, bhante”.**“It has both pleasure and pain.”*";
P_HTM[4787]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4788]="*yasmiṃ samaye adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, ekantasukhī vā tasmiṃ samaye attā hoti sukhadukkhī vā”ti?**On an occasion when someone refrains from stealing …*";
P_HTM[4789]="*“Sukhadukkhī, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[4790]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi, yasmiṃ samaye kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, ekantasukhī vā tasmiṃ samaye attā hoti sukhadukkhī vā”ti?**sexual misconduct …*";
P_HTM[4791]="*“Sukhadukkhī, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[4792]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi, yasmiṃ samaye musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, ekantasukhī vā tasmiṃ samaye attā hoti sukhadukkhī vā”ti?**lying, is their self perfectly happy at that time, or does it have both pleasure and pain?”*";
P_HTM[4793]="*“Sukhadukkhī, bhante”.**“It has both pleasure and pain.”*";
P_HTM[4794]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4795]="*yasmiṃ samaye aññataraṃ tapoguṇaṃ samādāya vattati, ekantasukhī vā tasmiṃ samaye attā hoti sukhadukkhī vā”ti?**On an occasion when someone undertakes and follows some kind of mortification, is their self perfectly happy at that time, or does it have both pleasure and pain?”*";
P_HTM[4796]="*“Sukhadukkhī, bhante”.**“It has both pleasure and pain.”*";
P_HTM[4797]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, udāyi,**“What do you think, Udāyī?*";
P_HTM[4798]="*api nu kho vokiṇṇasukhadukkhaṃ paṭipadaṃ āgamma ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyā hotī”ti?**Is a perfectly happy world realized by relying on a practice of mixed pleasure and pain?”*";
P_HTM[4799]="*“Acchidaṃ bhagavā kathaṃ, acchidaṃ sugato kathan”ti.**“The Blessed One has cut short the discussion! The Holy One has cut short the discussion!”*";
P_HTM[4800]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, udāyi, vadesi:**“But Udāyī, why do you say this?”*";
P_HTM[4801]="*‘acchidaṃ bhagavā kathaṃ, acchidaṃ sugato kathan’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4802]="*“Amhākaṃ, bhante, sake ācariyake evaṃ hoti:**“Sir, it says this in our own teacher’s doctrine:*";
P_HTM[4803]="*‘atthi ekantasukho loko, atthi ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā’ti.**‘There is a world of perfect happiness. And there is a grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness.’*";
P_HTM[4804]="*Te mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā sake ācariyake samanuyuñjiyamānā samanuggāhiyamānā samanubhāsiyamānā rittā tucchā aparaddhā”ti.**But when pursued, pressed, and grilled on our own teacher’s doctrine, we turned out to be void, hollow, and mistaken.*";
P_HTM[4805]="*“Kiṃ pana, bhante, atthi ekantasukho loko, atthi ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti?**But sir, is there a world of perfect happiness? And is there a grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness?”*";
P_HTM[4806]="*“Atthi kho, udāyi, ekantasukho loko, atthi ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti.**“There is a world of perfect happiness, Udāyī. And there is a grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness.”*";
P_HTM[4807]="*“Katamā pana sā, bhante, ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti?**“Well sir, what is that grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness?”*";
P_HTM[4808]="*“Idhudāyi, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**“It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[4809]="*vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption.*";
P_HTM[4810]="*pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati—**With the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption.*";
P_HTM[4811]="*ayaṃ kho sā, udāyi, ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti.**This is the grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness.”*";
P_HTM[4812]="*“Na kho sā, bhante, ākāravatī paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāya, sacchikato hissa, bhante, ettāvatā ekantasukho loko hotī”ti.**“Sir, that’s not the grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness. At that point a perfectly happy world has already been realized.”*";
P_HTM[4813]="*“Na khvāssa, udāyi, ettāvatā ekantasukho loko sacchikato hoti;**“No, Udāyī, at that point a perfectly happy world has not been realized.*";
P_HTM[4814]="*ākāravatī tveva sā paṭipadā ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti.**This is the grounded path for realizing a world of perfect happiness.”*";
P_HTM[4815]="*Evaṃ vutte, sakuludāyissa paribbājakassa parisā unnādinī uccāsaddamahāsaddā ahosi:**When he said this, Sakuludāyī’s assembly made an uproar, a dreadful racket,*";
P_HTM[4816]="*“ettha mayaṃ anassāma sācariyakā, ettha mayaṃ anassāma sācariyakā.**“In that case, we’re lost, and so are our teacher’s doctrines! We’re lost, and so are our teacher’s doctrines!*";
P_HTM[4817]="*Na mayaṃ ito bhiyyo uttaritaraṃ pajānāmā”ti.**We know nothing higher than this!”*";
P_HTM[4818]="*Atha kho sakuludāyī paribbājako te paribbājake appasadde katvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Sakuludāyī, having quieted those wanderers, said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4819]="*“kittāvatā panāssa, bhante, ekantasukho loko sacchikato hotī”ti?**“Well sir, at what point is a perfectly happy world realized?”*";
P_HTM[4820]="*“Idhudāyi, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ … upasampajja viharati.**“It’s when, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[4821]="*Yā tā devatā ekantasukhaṃ lokaṃ upapannā tāhi devatāhi saddhiṃ santiṭṭhati sallapati sākacchaṃ samāpajjati.**There are deities who have been reborn in a perfectly happy world. That mendicant associates with them, converses, and engages in discussion.*";
P_HTM[4822]="*Ettāvatā khvāssa, udāyi, ekantasukho loko sacchikato hotī”ti.**It’s at this point that a perfectly happy world has been realized.”*";
P_HTM[4823]="*“Etassa nūna, bhante, ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carantī”ti?**“Surely the mendicants must live the spiritual life under the Buddha for the sake of realizing this perfectly happy world?”*";
P_HTM[4824]="*“Na kho, udāyi, ekantasukhassa lokassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti.**“No, Udāyī, the mendicants don’t live the spiritual life under me for the sake of realizing this perfectly happy world.*";
P_HTM[4825]="*Atthi kho, udāyi, aññeva dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca, yesaṃ sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ carantī”ti.**There are other things that are finer, for the sake of which the mendicants live the spiritual life under me.”*";
P_HTM[4826]="*“Katame pana te, bhante, dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca yesaṃ sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū bhagavati brahmacariyaṃ carantī”ti?**“But what are those finer things?”*";
P_HTM[4827]="*“Idhudāyi, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā … pe …**“It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed. …*";
P_HTM[4828]="*so ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4829]="*vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[4830]="*Ayampi kho, udāyi, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti.**This is one of the finer things for the sake of which the mendicants live the spiritual life under me.*";
P_HTM[4831]="*Puna caparaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[4832]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[4833]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[4834]="*Ayampi kho, udāyi, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti.**This too is one of the finer things.*";
P_HTM[4835]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[4836]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. They recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[4837]="*Ayampi kho, udāyi, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti.**This too is one of the finer things.*";
P_HTM[4838]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[4839]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[4840]="*Ayampi kho, udāyi, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti.**This too is one of the finer things.*";
P_HTM[4841]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4842]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti,**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[4843]="*‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti … ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti … ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[4844]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati.**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[4845]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[4846]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[4847]="*Ayampi kho, udāyi, dhammo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca yassa sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ caranti.**This too is one of the finer things.*";
P_HTM[4848]="*Ime kho, udāyi, dhammā uttaritarā ca paṇītatarā ca yesaṃ sacchikiriyāhetu bhikkhū mayi brahmacariyaṃ carantī”ti.**These are the finer things for the sake of which the mendicants live the spiritual life under me.”*";
P_HTM[4849]="*Evaṃ vutte, sakuludāyī paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Sakuludāyī said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4850]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**“Excellent, sir! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[4851]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[4852]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[4853]="*Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti.**Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”*";
P_HTM[4854]="*Evaṃ vutte, sakuludāyissa paribbājakassa parisā sakuludāyiṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When he said this, Sakuludāyī’s assembly said to him,*";
P_HTM[4855]="*“mā bhavaṃ, udāyi, samaṇe gotame brahmacariyaṃ cari;**“Master Udāyī, don’t live the spiritual life under the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[4856]="*mā bhavaṃ, udāyi, ācariyo hutvā antevāsīvāsaṃ vasi.**You have been a teacher; don’t live as a student.*";
P_HTM[4857]="*Seyyathāpi nāma udakamaṇiko hutvā udañcaniko assa, evaṃ sampadamidaṃ bhoto udāyissa bhavissati.**The consequence for you will be as if a water jar were to become a water jug.*";
P_HTM[4858]="*Mā bhavaṃ, udāyi, samaṇe gotame brahmacariyaṃ cari;**Master Udāyī, don’t live the spiritual life under the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[4859]="*mā bhavaṃ, udāyi, ācariyo hutvā antevāsīvāsaṃ vasī”ti.**You have been a teacher; don’t live as a student.”*";
P_HTM[4860]="*Iti hidaṃ sakuludāyissa paribbājakassa parisā sakuludāyiṃ paribbājakaṃ antarāyamakāsi bhagavati brahmacariyeti.**And that’s how the wanderer Sakuludāyī’s own assembly prevented him from living the spiritual life under the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4861]="*Cūḷasakuludāyisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4862]="*80. Vekhanasasutta**With Vekhanasa*";
P_HTM[4863]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4864]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4865]="*Atha kho vekhanaso paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Vekhanasa went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4866]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side,*";
P_HTM[4867]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho vekhanaso paribbājako bhagavato santike udānaṃ udānesi:**and was inspired to exclaim:*";
P_HTM[4868]="*“ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo, ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo”ti.**“This is the ultimate splendor, this is the ultimate splendor.”*";
P_HTM[4869]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, kaccāna, evaṃ vadesi:**“But Kaccāna, why do you say:*";
P_HTM[4870]="*‘ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo, ayaṃ paramo vaṇṇo’ti?**‘This is the ultimate splendor, this is the ultimate splendor.’*";
P_HTM[4871]="*Katamo, kaccāna, so paramo vaṇṇo”ti?**What is that ultimate splendor?”*";
P_HTM[4872]="*“Yasmā, bho gotama, vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthi so paramo vaṇṇo”ti.**“Master Gotama, the ultimate splendor is the splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.”*";
P_HTM[4873]="*“Katamo pana so, kaccāna, vaṇṇo yasmā vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthī”ti?**“But what is that ultimate splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer?”*";
P_HTM[4874]="*“Yasmā, bho gotama, vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthi so paramo vaṇṇo”ti.**“Master Gotama, the ultimate splendor is the splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.”*";
P_HTM[4875]="*“Dīghāpi kho te esā, kaccāna, phareyya:**“Kaccāna, you could draw this out for a long time.*";
P_HTM[4876]="*‘yasmā, bho gotama, vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthi so paramo vaṇṇo’ti vadesi, tañca vaṇṇaṃ na paññapesi.**You say, ‘The ultimate splendor is the splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.’ But you don’t describe that splendor.*";
P_HTM[4877]="*Seyyathāpi, kaccāna, puriso evaṃ vadeyya:**Suppose a man was to say,*";
P_HTM[4878]="*‘ahaṃ yā imasmiṃ janapade janapadakalyāṇī, taṃ icchāmi taṃ kāmemī’ti.**‘Whoever the finest lady in the land is, it is her that I want, her I desire!’*";
P_HTM[4879]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him,*";
P_HTM[4880]="*‘ambho purisa, yaṃ tvaṃ janapadakalyāṇiṃ icchasi kāmesi, jānāsi taṃ janapadakalyāṇiṃ—khattiyī vā brāhmaṇī vā vessī vā suddī vā’ti?**‘Mister, that finest lady in the land who you desire—do you know whether she’s an aristocrat, a brahmin, a merchant, or a worker?’*";
P_HTM[4881]="*Iti puṭṭho ‘no’ti vadeyya.**Asked this, he’d say, ‘No.’*";
P_HTM[4882]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him,*";
P_HTM[4883]="*‘ambho purisa, yaṃ tvaṃ janapadakalyāṇiṃ icchasi kāmesi, jānāsi taṃ janapadakalyāṇiṃ evaṃnāmā evaṅgottāti vāti … pe … dīghā vā rassā vā majjhimā vā kāḷī vā sāmā vā maṅguracchavī vāti … amukasmiṃ gāme vā nigame vā nagare vā’ti?**‘Mister, that finest lady in the land who you desire—do you know her name or clan? Whether she’s tall or short or medium? Whether her skin is black, brown, or tawny? What village, town, or city she comes from?’*";
P_HTM[4884]="*Iti puṭṭho ‘no’ti vadeyya.**Asked this, he’d say, ‘No.’*";
P_HTM[4885]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:**They’d say to him,*";
P_HTM[4886]="*‘ambho purisa, yaṃ tvaṃ na jānāsi na passasi, taṃ tvaṃ icchasi kāmesī’ti?**‘Mister, do you desire someone who you’ve never even known or seen?’*";
P_HTM[4887]="*Iti puṭṭho ‘āmā’ti vadeyya.**Asked this, he’d say, ‘Yes.’*";
P_HTM[4888]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kaccāna,**What do you think, Kaccāna?*";
P_HTM[4889]="*nanu evaṃ sante tassa purisassa appāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti?**This being so, doesn’t that man’s statement turn out to have no demonstrable basis?”*";
P_HTM[4890]="*“Addhā kho, bho gotama, evaṃ sante tassa purisassa appāṭihīrakataṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjatī”ti.**“Clearly that’s the case, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4891]="*“Evameva kho tvaṃ, kaccāna, ‘yasmā, bho gotama, vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthi so paramo vaṇṇo’ti vadesi; tañca vaṇṇaṃ na paññapesī”ti.**“In the same way, you say, ‘The ultimate splendor is the splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.’ But you don’t describe that splendor.”*";
P_HTM[4892]="*“Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato paṇḍukambale nikkhitto bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca, evaṃ vaṇṇo attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”ti.**“Master Gotama, suppose there was a beryl gem that was naturally beautiful, eight-faceted, well-worked. When placed on a cream rug it would shine and glow and radiate. Such is the splendor of the self that is sound after death.”*";
P_HTM[4893]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kaccāna,**“What do you think, Kaccāna?*";
P_HTM[4894]="*yo vā maṇi veḷuriyo subho jātimā aṭṭhaṃso suparikammakato paṇḍukambale nikkhitto bhāsate ca tapate ca virocati ca, yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya kimi khajjopanako imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: such a beryl gem, or a firefly in the dark of night?”*";
P_HTM[4895]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho gotama, rattandhakāratimisāya kimi khajjopanako, ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“A firefly in the dark of night.”*";
P_HTM[4896]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kaccāna,**“What do you think, Kaccāna?*";
P_HTM[4897]="*yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya kimi khajjopanako, yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya telappadīpo, imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: a firefly in the dark of night, or an oil lamp in the dark of night?”*";
P_HTM[4898]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho gotama, rattandhakāratimisāya telappadīpo, ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“An oil lamp in the dark of night.”*";
P_HTM[4899]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kaccāna,**“What do you think, Kaccāna?*";
P_HTM[4900]="*yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya telappadīpo, yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya mahāaggikkhandho, imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: an oil lamp in the dark of night, or a bonfire in the dark of night?”*";
P_HTM[4901]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho gotama, rattandhakāratimisāya mahāaggikkhandho, ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“A bonfire in the dark of night.”*";
P_HTM[4902]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kaccāna,**“What do you think, Kaccāna?*";
P_HTM[4903]="*yo vā rattandhakāratimisāya mahāaggikkhandho, yā vā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ viddhe vigatavalāhake deve osadhitārakā, imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: a bonfire in the dark of night, or the Morning Star in a clear and cloudless sky at the crack of dawn?”*";
P_HTM[4904]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho gotama, rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ viddhe vigatavalāhake deve osadhitārakā, ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“The Morning Star in a clear and cloudless sky at the crack of dawn.”*";
P_HTM[4905]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kaccāna,**“What do you think, Kaccāna?*";
P_HTM[4906]="*yā vā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ viddhe vigatavalāhake deve osadhitārakā, yo vā tadahuposathe pannarase viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido aḍḍharattasamayaṃ cando, imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: the Morning Star in a clear and cloudless sky at the crack of dawn, or the full moon at midnight in a clear and cloudless sky on the fifteenth day sabbath?”*";
P_HTM[4907]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho gotama, tadahuposathe pannarase viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido aḍḍharattasamayaṃ cando, ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“The full moon at midnight in a clear and cloudless sky on the fifteenth day sabbath.”*";
P_HTM[4908]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, kaccāna,**“What do you think, Kaccāna?*";
P_HTM[4909]="*yo vā tadahuposathe pannarase viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido aḍḍharattasamayaṃ cando, yo vā vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido majjhanhikasamayaṃ sūriyo, imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ katamo vaṇṇo abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti?**Which of these two has a finer splendor: the full moon at midnight in a clear and cloudless sky on the fifteenth day sabbath, or the sun at midday in a clear and cloudless sky in the last month of the rainy season?”*";
P_HTM[4910]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho gotama, vassānaṃ pacchime māse saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve abhido majjhanhikasamayaṃ sūriyo—ayaṃ imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā”ti.**“The sun at midday in a clear and cloudless sky in the last month of the rainy season.”*";
P_HTM[4911]="*“Ato kho te, kaccāna, bahū hi bahutarā devā ye imesaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ ābhā nānubhonti, tyāhaṃ pajānāmi.**“Beyond this, Kaccāna, I know very many gods on whom the light of the sun and moon make no impression.*";
P_HTM[4912]="*Atha ca panāhaṃ na vadāmi:**Nevertheless, I do not say:*";
P_HTM[4913]="*‘yasmā vaṇṇā añño vaṇṇo uttaritaro ca paṇītataro ca natthī’ti.**‘The splendor compared to which no other splendor is finer.’*";
P_HTM[4914]="*Atha ca pana tvaṃ, kaccāna, ‘yvāyaṃ vaṇṇo kiminā khajjopanakena nihīnataro ca patikiṭṭhataro ca so paramo vaṇṇo’ti vadesi; tañca vaṇṇaṃ na paññapesi.**But of the splendor inferior to a firefly you say, ‘This is the ultimate splendor.’ And you don’t describe that splendor.*";
P_HTM[4915]="*Pañca kho ime, kaccāna, kāmaguṇā.**Kaccāna, there are these five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[4916]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4917]="*Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[4918]="*sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[4919]="*ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[4920]="*jivhāviññeyyā rasā …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[4921]="*kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[4922]="*ime kho, kaccāna, pañca kāmaguṇā.**These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[4923]="*Yaṃ kho, kaccāna, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati kāmasukhaṃ.**The pleasure and happiness that arises from these five kinds of sensual stimulation is called sensual pleasure.*";
P_HTM[4924]="*Iti kāmehi kāmasukhaṃ, kāmasukhā kāmaggasukhaṃ tattha aggamakkhāyatī”ti.**So there is the saying: ‘From the senses comes sensual pleasure. From sensual pleasure comes the best kind of sensual pleasure, which is said to be the best thing there.’”*";
P_HTM[4925]="*Evaṃ vutte, vekhanaso paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Vekhanasa said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4926]="*“acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama.**“It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[4927]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ bhotā gotamena:**How well said this was by Master Gotama!*";
P_HTM[4928]="*‘kāmehi kāmasukhaṃ, kāmasukhā kāmaggasukhaṃ tattha aggamakkhāyatī’ti.**‘From the senses comes sensual pleasure. From sensual pleasure comes the best kind of sensual pleasure, which is said to be the best thing there.’*";
P_HTM[4929]="*‘Kāmehi, bho gotama, kāmasukhaṃ, kāmasukhā kāmaggasukhaṃ, tattha aggamakkhāyatī’”ti**Master Gotama, from the senses comes sensual pleasure. From sensual pleasure comes the best kind of sensual pleasure, which is said to be the best thing there.”*";
P_HTM[4930]="*“dujjānaṃ kho etaṃ, kaccāna, tayā aññadiṭṭhikena aññakhantikena aññarucikena aññatrayogena aññatrācariyakena—**“Kaccāna, it’s hard for you, who has a different view, creed, preference, practice, and teacher’s doctrine, to understand*";
P_HTM[4931]="*kāmā vā kāmasukhaṃ vā kāmaggasukhaṃ vā.**the senses, sensual pleasure, and the best kind of sensual pleasure.*";
P_HTM[4932]="*Ye kho te, kaccāna, bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā te kho etaṃ jāneyyuṃ—**There are mendicants who are perfected, who have ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment. They can understand*";
P_HTM[4933]="*kāmā vā kāmasukhaṃ vā kāmaggasukhaṃ vā”ti.**the senses, sensual pleasure, and the best kind of sensual pleasure.”*";
P_HTM[4934]="*Evaṃ vutte, vekhanaso paribbājako kupito anattamano bhagavantaṃyeva khuṃsento bhagavantaṃyeva vambhento bhagavantaṃyeva vadamāno:**When he said this, Vekhanasa became angry and upset. He even attacked and badmouthed the Buddha himself, saying,*";
P_HTM[4935]="*“samaṇo gotamo pāpito bhavissatī”ti bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**“The ascetic Gotama will be worsted!” He said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4936]="*“evameva panidhekacce samaṇabrāhmaṇā ajānantā pubbantaṃ, apassantā aparantaṃ atha ca pana**“This is exactly what happens with some ascetics and brahmins. Not knowing the past or seeing the future, they nevertheless claim:*";
P_HTM[4937]="*‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti—pajānāmā’ti—paṭijānanti.**‘We understand: “Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[4938]="*Tesamidaṃ bhāsitaṃ hassakaṃyeva sampajjati, nāmakaṃyeva sampajjati, rittakaṃyeva sampajjati, tucchakaṃyeva sampajjatī”ti.**Their statement turns out to be a joke—mere words, void and hollow.”*";
P_HTM[4939]="*“Ye kho te, kaccāna, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ajānantā pubbantaṃ, apassantā aparantaṃ,**“Kaccāna, there are some ascetics and brahmins who, not knowing the past or seeing the future, nevertheless claim:*";
P_HTM[4940]="*‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti—pajānāmā’ti—paṭijānanti;**‘We understand: “Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[4941]="*tesaṃ soyeva sahadhammiko niggaho hoti.**There is a legitimate refutation of them.*";
P_HTM[4942]="*Api ca, kaccāna, tiṭṭhatu pubbanto, tiṭṭhatu aparanto.**Nevertheless, Kaccāna, leave aside the past and the future.*";
P_HTM[4943]="*Etu viññū puriso asaṭho amāyāvī ujujātiko, ahamanusāsāmi ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi.**Let a sensible person come—neither devious nor deceitful, a person of integrity. I teach and instruct them.*";
P_HTM[4944]="*Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno nacirasseva sāmaññeva ñassati sāmaṃ dakkhiti—**Practicing as instructed they will soon know and see for themselves,*";
P_HTM[4945]="*evaṃ kira sammā bandhanā vippamokkho hoti, yadidaṃ avijjā bandhanā.**‘So this is how to be rightly released from the bond, that is, the bond of ignorance.’*";
P_HTM[4946]="*Seyyathāpi, kaccāna, daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi baddho assa suttabandhanehi;**Suppose there was a little baby bound with swaddling up to the neck.*";
P_HTM[4947]="*tassa vuddhimanvāya indriyānaṃ paripākamanvāya tāni bandhanāni mucceyyuṃ;**As they grow up and their senses mature, they’re accordingly released from those bonds.*";
P_HTM[4948]="*so mokkhomhīti kho jāneyya no ca bandhanaṃ.**They’d know ‘I’m released,’ and there would be no more bonds.*";
P_HTM[4949]="*Evameva kho, kaccāna, etu viññū puriso asaṭho amāyāvī ujujātiko, ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi;**In the same way, let a sensible person come—neither devious nor deceitful, a person of integrity. I teach and instruct them.*";
P_HTM[4950]="*yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno nacirasseva sāmaññeva ñassati, sāmaṃ dakkhiti:**Practicing as instructed they will soon know and see for themselves,*";
P_HTM[4951]="*‘evaṃ kira sammā bandhanā vippamokkho hoti, yadidaṃ avijjā bandhanā’”ti.**‘So this is how to be rightly released from the bond, that is, the bond of ignorance.’”*";
P_HTM[4952]="*Evaṃ vutte, vekhanaso paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Vekhanasa said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4953]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! …*";
P_HTM[4954]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4955]="*Vekhanasasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4956]="*Paribbājakavaggo niṭṭhito tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[4957]="*Puṇḍarī aggisaha kathināmo,* **";
P_HTM[4958]="*Dīghanakho puna bhāradvājagotto;* **";
P_HTM[4959]="*Sandakaudāyimuṇḍikaputto,* **";
P_HTM[4960]="*Maṇiko tathākaccāno varavaggo.* **";
P_HTM[4961]="*81. Ghaṭikārasutta**With Ghaṭikāra*";
P_HTM[4962]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4963]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[4964]="*Atha kho bhagavā maggā okkamma aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi.**Then the Buddha left the road, and at a certain spot he smiled.*";
P_HTM[4965]="*Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:**Then Venerable Ānanda thought,*";
P_HTM[4966]="*“ko nu kho hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya?**“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled?*";
P_HTM[4967]="*Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti.**Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.”*";
P_HTM[4968]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**So Ānanda got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said,*";
P_HTM[4969]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya?**“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled?*";
P_HTM[4970]="*Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti.**Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.”*";
P_HTM[4971]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, imasmiṃ padese vegaḷiṅgaṃ nāma gāmanigamo ahosi iddho ceva phīto ca bahujano ākiṇṇamanusso.**“Once upon a time, Ānanda, there was a market town in this spot named Vebhaliṅga. It was successful and prosperous and full of people.*";
P_HTM[4972]="*Vegaḷiṅgaṃ kho, ānanda, gāmanigamaṃ kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho upanissāya vihāsi.**And Kassapa, a blessed one, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, lived supported by Vebhaliṅga.*";
P_HTM[4973]="*Idha sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ārāmo ahosi.**It was here, in fact, that he had his monastery,*";
P_HTM[4974]="*Idha sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho nisinnako bhikkhusaṃghaṃ ovadatī”ti.**where he sat and advised the mendicant Saṅgha.”*";
P_HTM[4975]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññapetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Ānanda spread out his outer robe folded in four and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4976]="*“tena hi, bhante, bhagavā nisīdatu ettha.**“Well then, sir, may the Blessed One sit here!*";
P_HTM[4977]="*Ayaṃ bhūmipadeso dvīhi arahantehi sammāsambuddhehi paribhutto bhavissatī”ti.**Then this piece of land will have been occupied by two perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas.”*";
P_HTM[4978]="*Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane.**The Buddha sat on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[4979]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**When he was seated he said to Venerable Ānanda:*";
P_HTM[4980]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, imasmiṃ padese vegaḷiṅgaṃ nāma gāmanigamo ahosi iddho ceva phīto ca bahujano ākiṇṇamanusso.**“Once upon a time, Ānanda, there was a market town in this spot named Vebhaliṅga. It was successful and prosperous and full of people.*";
P_HTM[4981]="*Vegaḷiṅgaṃ kho, ānanda, gāmanigamaṃ kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho upanissāya vihāsi.**And Kassapa, a blessed one, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, lived supported by Vebhaliṅga.*";
P_HTM[4982]="*Idha sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ārāmo ahosi.**It was here, in fact, that he had his monastery,*";
P_HTM[4983]="*Idha sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho nisinnako bhikkhusaṅghaṃ ovadati.**where he sat and advised the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[4984]="*Vegaḷiṅge kho, ānanda, gāmanigame ghaṭikāro nāma kumbhakāro kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko.**The Buddha Kassapa had as chief attendant in Vebhaliṅga a potter named Ghaṭīkāra.*";
P_HTM[4985]="*Ghaṭikārassa kho, ānanda, kumbhakārassa jotipālo nāma māṇavo sahāyo ahosi piyasahāyo.**Ghaṭīkāra had a dear friend named Jotipāla, a brahmin student.*";
P_HTM[4986]="*Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro jotipālaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi:**Then Ghaṭīkāra addressed Jotipāla,*";
P_HTM[4987]="*‘āyāma, samma jotipāla, kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāma.**‘Come, dear Jotipāla, let’s go to see the Blessed One Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4988]="*Sādhusammatañhi me tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti.**For I regard it as holy to see that Blessed One.’*";
P_HTM[4989]="*Evaṃ vutte, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Jotipāla said to him,*";
P_HTM[4990]="*‘alaṃ, samma ghaṭikāra.**‘Enough, dear Ghaṭīkāra.*";
P_HTM[4991]="*Kiṃ pana tena muṇḍakena samaṇakena diṭṭhenā’ti?**What’s the use of seeing that baldy, that fake ascetic?’*";
P_HTM[4992]="*Dutiyampi kho, ānanda … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[4993]="*tatiyampi kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro jotipālaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time, Ghaṭīkāra addressed Jotipāla,*";
P_HTM[4994]="*‘āyāma, samma jotipāla, kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāma.**‘Come, dear Jotipāla, let’s go to see the Blessed One Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4995]="*Sādhusammatañhi me tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti.**For I regard it as holy to see that Blessed One.’*";
P_HTM[4996]="*Tatiyampi kho, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca:**For a third time, Jotipāla said to him,*";
P_HTM[4997]="*‘alaṃ, samma ghaṭikāra.**‘Enough, dear Ghaṭīkāra.*";
P_HTM[4998]="*Kiṃ pana tena muṇḍakena samaṇakena diṭṭhenā’ti?**What’s the use of seeing that baldy, that fake ascetic?’*";
P_HTM[4999]="*‘Tena hi, samma jotipāla, sottisināniṃ ādāya nadiṃ gamissāma sināyitun’ti.**‘Well then, dear Jotipāla, let’s take some bathing paste of powdered shell and go to the river to bathe.’*";
P_HTM[5000]="*‘Evaṃ, sammā’ti kho, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa paccassosi.**‘Yes, dear,’ replied Jotipāla.*";
P_HTM[5001]="*Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro ca kumbhakāro jotipālo ca māṇavo sottisināniṃ ādāya nadiṃ agamaṃsu sināyituṃ.**So that’s what they did.*";
P_HTM[5002]="*Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro jotipālaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi:**Then Ghaṭīkāra addressed Jotipāla,*";
P_HTM[5003]="*‘ayaṃ, samma jotipāla, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa avidūre ārāmo.**‘Dear Jotipāla, the Buddha Kassapa’s monastery is not far away.*";
P_HTM[5004]="*Āyāma, samma jotipāla, kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāma.**Let’s go to see the Blessed One Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5005]="*Sādhusammatañhi me tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti.**For I regard it as holy to see that Blessed One.’*";
P_HTM[5006]="*Evaṃ vutte, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Jotipāla said to him,*";
P_HTM[5007]="*‘alaṃ, samma ghaṭikāra.**‘Enough, dear Ghaṭīkāra.*";
P_HTM[5008]="*Kiṃ pana tena muṇḍakena samaṇakena diṭṭhenā’ti?**What’s the use of seeing that baldy, that fake ascetic?’*";
P_HTM[5009]="*Dutiyampi kho, ānanda … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[5010]="*tatiyampi kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro jotipālaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time, Ghaṭīkāra addressed Jotipāla,*";
P_HTM[5011]="*‘ayaṃ, samma jotipāla, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa avidūre ārāmo.**‘Dear Jotipāla, the Buddha Kassapa’s monastery is not far away.*";
P_HTM[5012]="*Āyāma, samma jotipāla, kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāma.**Let’s go to see the Blessed One Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5013]="*Sādhusammatañhi me tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti.**For I regard it as holy to see that Blessed One.’*";
P_HTM[5014]="*Tatiyampi kho, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca:**For a third time, Jotipāla said to him,*";
P_HTM[5015]="*‘alaṃ, samma ghaṭikāra.**‘Enough, dear Ghaṭīkāra.*";
P_HTM[5016]="*Kiṃ pana tena muṇḍakena samaṇakena diṭṭhenā’ti?**What’s the use of seeing that baldy, that fake ascetic?’*";
P_HTM[5017]="*Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro jotipālaṃ māṇavaṃ ovaṭṭikāyaṃ parāmasitvā etadavoca:**Then Ghaṭīkāra grabbed Jotipāla by the belt and said,*";
P_HTM[5018]="*‘ayaṃ, samma jotipāla, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa avidūre ārāmo.**‘Dear Jotipāla, the Buddha Kassapa’s monastery is not far away.*";
P_HTM[5019]="*Āyāma, samma jotipāla, kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāma.**Let’s go to see the Blessed One Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5020]="*Sādhusammatañhi me tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti.**For I regard it as holy to see that Blessed One.’*";
P_HTM[5021]="*Atha kho, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ovaṭṭikaṃ vinivaṭṭetvā ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca:**So Jotipāla undid his belt and said to Ghaṭīkāra,*";
P_HTM[5022]="*‘alaṃ, samma ghaṭikāra.**‘Enough, dear Ghaṭīkāra.*";
P_HTM[5023]="*Kiṃ pana tena muṇḍakena samaṇakena diṭṭhenā’ti?**What’s the use of seeing that baldy, that fake ascetic?’*";
P_HTM[5024]="*Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro jotipālaṃ māṇavaṃ sīsaṃnhātaṃ kesesu parāmasitvā etadavoca:**Then Ghaṭīkāra grabbed Jotipāla by the hair of his freshly-washed head and said,*";
P_HTM[5025]="*‘ayaṃ, samma jotipāla, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa avidūre ārāmo.**‘Dear Jotipāla, the Buddha Kassapa’s monastery is not far away.*";
P_HTM[5026]="*Āyāma, samma jotipāla, kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāma.**Let’s go to see the Blessed One Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5027]="*Sādhusammatañhi me tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti.**For I regard it as holy to see that Blessed One.’*";
P_HTM[5028]="*Atha kho, ānanda, jotipālassa māṇavassa etadahosi:**Then Jotipāla thought,*";
P_HTM[5029]="*‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[5030]="*Yatra hi nāmāyaṃ ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro ittarajacco samāno amhākaṃ sīsaṃnhātānaṃ kesesu parāmasitabbaṃ maññissati;**how this potter Ghaṭikāra, though born in a lower caste, should presume to grab me by the hair of my freshly-washed head!*";
P_HTM[5031]="*na vatidaṃ kira orakaṃ maññe bhavissatī’ti;**This must be no ordinary matter.’*";
P_HTM[5032]="*ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca:**He said to Ghaṭīkāra,*";
P_HTM[5033]="*‘yāvatādohipi, samma ghaṭikārā’ti?**‘You’d even milk it to this extent, dear Ghaṭīkāra?’*";
P_HTM[5034]="*‘Yāvatādohipi, samma jotipāla.**‘I even milk it to this extent, dear Jotipāla.*";
P_HTM[5035]="*Tathā hi pana me sādhusammataṃ tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti.**For that is how holy I regard it to see that Blessed One.’*";
P_HTM[5036]="*‘Tena hi, samma ghaṭikāra, muñca; gamissāmā’ti.**‘Well then, dear Ghaṭīkāra, release me, we shall go.’*";
P_HTM[5037]="*Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro ca kumbhakāro jotipālo ca māṇavo yena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Jotipālo pana māṇavo kassapena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena saddhiṃ sammodi. Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Then Ghaṭīkāra the potter and Jotipāla the brahmin student went to the Buddha Kassapa. Ghaṭīkāra bowed and sat down to one side, but Jotipāla exchanged greetings with the Buddha and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[5038]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:**Ghaṭīkāra said to the Buddha Kassapa,*";
P_HTM[5039]="*‘ayaṃ me, bhante, jotipālo māṇavo sahāyo piyasahāyo.**‘Sir, this is my dear friend Jotipāla, a brahmin student.*";
P_HTM[5040]="*Imassa bhagavā dhammaṃ desetū’ti.**Please teach him the Dhamma.’*";
P_HTM[5041]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho ghaṭikārañca kumbhakāraṃ jotipālañca māṇavaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**Then the Buddha Kassapa educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired Ghaṭikāra and Jotipāla with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[5042]="*Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro ca kumbhakāro jotipālo ca māṇavo kassapena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu.**Then they got up from their seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha Kassapa, keeping him on their right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[5043]="*Atha kho, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca:**Then Jotipāla said to Ghatīkāra,*";
P_HTM[5044]="*‘imaṃ nu tvaṃ, samma ghaṭikāra, dhammaṃ suṇanto atha ca pana agārasmā anagāriyaṃ na pabbajissasī’ti?**‘Dear Ghaṭīkāra, you have heard this teaching, so why don’t you go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[5045]="*‘Nanu maṃ, samma jotipāla, jānāsi, andhe jiṇṇe mātāpitaro posemī’ti?**‘Don’t you know, dear Jotipāla, that I look after my blind old parents?’*";
P_HTM[5046]="*‘Tena hi, samma ghaṭikāra, ahaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmī’ti.**‘Well then, dear Ghaṭīkāra, I shall go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[5047]="*Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro ca kumbhakāro jotipālo ca māṇavo yena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:**Then Ghaṭīkāra and Jotipāla went to the Buddha Kassapa, bowed and sat down to one side. Ghaṭīkāra said to the Buddha Kassapa,*";
P_HTM[5048]="*‘ayaṃ me, bhante, jotipālo māṇavo sahāyo piyasahāyo.**‘Sir, this is my dear friend Jotipāla, a brahmin student.*";
P_HTM[5049]="*Imaṃ bhagavā pabbājetū’ti.**Please give him the going forth.’*";
P_HTM[5050]="*Alattha kho, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ.**And Jotipāla the brahmin student received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence.*";
P_HTM[5051]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho acirūpasampanne jotipāle māṇave aḍḍhamāsupasampanne vegaḷiṅge yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena bārāṇasī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**Not long after Jotipāla’s ordination, a fortnight later, the Buddha Kassapa—having stayed in Vebhaliṅga as long as he wished—set out for Benares.*";
P_HTM[5052]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bārāṇasī tadavasari.**Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Benares,*";
P_HTM[5053]="*Tatra sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye.**where he stayed near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana.*";
P_HTM[5054]="*Assosi kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā: ‘kassapo kira bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bārāṇasiṃ anuppatto bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye’ti.**King Kikī of Kāsi heard that he had arrived.*";
P_HTM[5055]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhadraṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi bārāṇasiyā niyyāsi mahaccarājānubhāvena kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya.**He had the finest carriages harnessed. He then mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out in full royal pomp from Benares to see the Buddha Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[5056]="*Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova yena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached the Buddha Kassapa on foot. He bowed and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[5057]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho, ānanda, kikiṃ kāsirājānaṃ kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**The Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[5058]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:**Then King Kikī said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5059]="*‘adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā’ti.**‘Sir, would the Buddha together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept tomorrow’s meal from me?’*";
P_HTM[5060]="*Adhivāsesi kho, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha Kassapa consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[5061]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapassa bhagavato sammāsambuddhassa adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, King Kikī got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[5062]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā paṇḍupuṭakassa sālino vigatakāḷakaṃ anekasūpaṃ anekabyañjanaṃ, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa kālaṃ ārocāpesi:**And when the night had passed, King Kikī had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home—soft saffron rice with the dark grains picked out, served with many soups and sauces. Then he had the Buddha informed of the time, saying,*";
P_HTM[5063]="*‘kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan’ti.**‘Sir, it’s time. The meal is ready.’*";
P_HTM[5064]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena kikissa kāsirañño nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**Then Kassapa Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of King Kikī, where he sat on the seat spread out, together with the Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[5065]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Then King Kikī served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[5066]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the Buddha Kassapa had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, King Kikī took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[5067]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:**There he said to the Buddha Kassapa,*";
P_HTM[5068]="*‘adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ vassāvāsaṃ;**‘Sir, may the Buddha please accept my invitation to reside in Benares for the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[5069]="*evarūpaṃ saṅghassa upaṭṭhānaṃ bhavissatī’ti.**The Saṅgha will be looked after in the same style.’*";
P_HTM[5070]="*‘Alaṃ, mahārāja.**‘Enough, great king.*";
P_HTM[5071]="*Adhivuttho me vassāvāso’ti.**I have already accepted an invitation for the rains residence.’*";
P_HTM[5072]="*Dutiyampi kho, ānanda …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[5073]="*tatiyampi kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time King Kikī said to the Buddha Kassapa,*";
P_HTM[5074]="*‘adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ vassāvāsaṃ;**‘Sir, may the Buddha please accept my invitation to reside in Benares for the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[5075]="*evarūpaṃ saṅghassa upaṭṭhānaṃ bhavissatī’ti.**The Saṅgha will be looked after in the same style.’*";
P_HTM[5076]="*‘Alaṃ, mahārāja.**‘Enough, Great King.*";
P_HTM[5077]="*Adhivuttho me vassāvāso’ti.**I have already accepted an invitation for the rains residence.’*";
P_HTM[5078]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikissa kāsirañño ‘na me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho adhivāseti bārāṇasiyaṃ vassāvāsan’ti ahudeva aññathattaṃ, ahu domanassaṃ.**Then King Kikī, thinking, ‘The Buddha does not accept my invitation to reside for the rains in Benares,’ became sad and upset.*";
P_HTM[5079]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:**Then King Kikī said to the Buddha Kassapa,*";
P_HTM[5080]="*‘atthi nu kho, bhante, añño koci mayā upaṭṭhākataro’ti?**‘Sir, do you have another attendant better than me?’*";
P_HTM[5081]="*‘Atthi, mahārāja, vegaḷiṅgaṃ nāma gāmanigamo.**‘Great king, there is a market town named Vebhaliṅga,*";
P_HTM[5082]="*Tattha ghaṭikāro nāma kumbhakāro;**where there’s a potter named Ghaṭīkāra.*";
P_HTM[5083]="*so me upaṭṭhāko aggupaṭṭhāko.**He is my chief attendant.*";
P_HTM[5084]="*Tuyhaṃ kho pana, mahārāja, na me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho adhivāseti bārāṇasiyaṃ vassāvāsanti attheva aññathattaṃ, atthi domanassaṃ.**Now, great king, you thought, “The Buddha does not accept my invitation to reside for the rains in Benares,” and you became sad and upset.*";
P_HTM[5085]="*Tayidaṃ ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa natthi ca na ca bhavissati.**But Ghaṭīkāra doesn’t get upset, nor will he.*";
P_HTM[5086]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato, dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato, saṃghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato.**Ghaṭīkāra has gone for refuge to the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[5087]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro pāṇātipātā paṭivirato, adinnādānā paṭivirato, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato, musāvādā paṭivirato, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato.**He doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or take alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5088]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, saṃghe aveccappasādena samannāgato, ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato.**He has experiential confidence in the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha, and has the ethics loved by the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[5089]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro dukkhe nikkaṅkho, dukkhasamudaye nikkaṅkho, dukkhanirodhe nikkaṅkho, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya nikkaṅkho.**He is free of doubt regarding suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation.*";
P_HTM[5090]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro ekabhattiko brahmacārī sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo.**He eats in one part of the day; he’s celibate, ethical, and of good character.*";
P_HTM[5091]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro nikkhittamaṇisuvaṇṇo apetajātarūparajato.**He has set aside gems and gold, and rejected gold and money.*";
P_HTM[5092]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro pannamusalo na sahatthā pathaviṃ khaṇati.**He’s put down the shovel and doesn’t dig the earth with his own hands.*";
P_HTM[5093]="*Yaṃ hoti kūlapaluggaṃ vā mūsikukkaro vā taṃ kājena āharitvā bhājanaṃ karitvā evamāha:**He takes what has crumbled off by a riverbank or been dug up by mice, and brings it back in a carrier. When he has made a pot, he says,*";
P_HTM[5094]="*“ettha yo icchati taṇḍulapaṭibhastāni vā muggapaṭibhastāni vā kaḷāyapaṭibhastāni vā nikkhipitvā yaṃ icchati taṃ haratū”ti.**“Anyone may leave bagged sesame, mung beans, or chickpeas here and take what they wish.”*";
P_HTM[5095]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro andhe jiṇṇe mātāpitaro poseti.**He looks after his blind old parents.*";
P_HTM[5096]="*Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā.**And since he has ended the five lower fetters, Ghaṭīkāra will be reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.*";
P_HTM[5097]="*Ekamidāhaṃ, mahārāja, samayaṃ vegaḷiṅge nāma gāmanigame viharāmi.**This one time, great king, I was staying near the market town of Vebhaliṅga.*";
P_HTM[5098]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro etadavocaṃ:**Then I robed up in the morning and, taking my bowl and robe, went to the home of Ghaṭīkāra’s parents, where I said to them,*";
P_HTM[5099]="*“handa ko nu kho ayaṃ bhaggavo gato”ti?**“Excuse me, where has Bhaggava gone?”*";
P_HTM[5100]="*“Nikkhanto kho te, bhante, upaṭṭhāko antokumbhiyā odanaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjā”ti.**“Your attendant has gone out, sir. But take rice from the pot and sauce from the pan and eat.”*";
P_HTM[5101]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, kumbhiyā odanaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ.**So that’s what I did. And after eating I got up from my seat and left.*";
P_HTM[5102]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro yena mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mātāpitaro etadavoca:**Then Ghaṭīkāra went up to his parents and said,*";
P_HTM[5103]="*“ko kumbhiyā odanaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti?**“Who took rice from the pot and sauce from the pan, ate it, and left?”*";
P_HTM[5104]="*“Kassapo, tāta, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kumbhiyā odanaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti?**“It was the Buddha Kassapa, my dear.”*";
P_HTM[5105]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa etadahosi:**Then Ghaṭīkāra thought,*";
P_HTM[5106]="*“lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me,**“I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[5107]="*yassa me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho evaṃ abhivissattho”ti.**in that the Buddha Kassapa trusts me so much!”*";
P_HTM[5108]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ aḍḍhamāsaṃ pītisukhaṃ na vijahati, sattāhaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ.**Then joy and happiness did not leave him for a fortnight, or his parents for a week.*";
P_HTM[5109]="*Ekamidāhaṃ, mahārāja, samayaṃ tattheva vegaḷiṅge nāma gāmanigame viharāmi.**Another time, great king, I was staying near that same market town of Vebhaliṅga.*";
P_HTM[5110]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro etadavocaṃ:**Then I robed up in the morning and, taking my bowl and robe, went to the home of Ghaṭīkāra’s parents, where I said to them,*";
P_HTM[5111]="*“handa ko nu kho ayaṃ bhaggavo gato”ti?**“Excuse me, where has Bhaggava gone?”*";
P_HTM[5112]="*“Nikkhanto kho te, bhante, upaṭṭhāko anto kaḷopiyā kummāsaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjā”ti.**“Your attendant has gone out, sir. But take porridge from the pot and sauce from the pan and eat.”*";
P_HTM[5113]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, kaḷopiyā kummāsaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ.**So that’s what I did. And after eating I got up from my seat and left.*";
P_HTM[5114]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro yena mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mātāpitaro etadavoca:**Then Ghaṭīkāra went up to his parents and said,*";
P_HTM[5115]="*“ko kaḷopiyā kummāsaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti?**“Who took porridge from the pot and sauce from the pan, ate it, and left?”*";
P_HTM[5116]="*“Kassapo, tāta, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kaḷopiyā kummāsaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti.**“It was the Buddha Kassapa, my dear.”*";
P_HTM[5117]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa etadahosi:**Then Ghaṭīkāra thought,*";
P_HTM[5118]="*“lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me,**“I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[5119]="*yassa me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho evaṃ abhivissattho”ti.**to be trusted so much by the Buddha Kassapa!”*";
P_HTM[5120]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ aḍḍhamāsaṃ pītisukhaṃ na vijahati, sattāhaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ.**Then joy and happiness did not leave him for a fortnight, or his parents for a week.*";
P_HTM[5121]="*Ekamidāhaṃ, mahārāja, samayaṃ tattheva vegaḷiṅge nāma gāmanigame viharāmi.**Another time, great king, I was staying near that same market town of Vebhaliṅga.*";
P_HTM[5122]="*Tena kho pana samayena kuṭi ovassati.**Now at that time my hut leaked.*";
P_HTM[5123]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, bhikkhū āmantesiṃ:**So I addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[5124]="*“gacchatha, bhikkhave, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa nivesane tiṇaṃ jānāthā”ti.**“Mendicants, go to Ghaṭikāra’s home and find some grass.”*";
P_HTM[5125]="*Evaṃ vutte, mahārāja, te bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ:**When I said this, those mendicants said to me,*";
P_HTM[5126]="*“natthi kho, bhante, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa nivesane tiṇaṃ, atthi ca khvāssa āvesane tiṇacchadanan”ti.**“Sir, there’s no grass there, but his workshop has a grass roof.”*";
P_HTM[5127]="*“Gacchatha, bhikkhave, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa āvesanaṃ uttiṇaṃ karothā”ti.**“Then go to the workshop and strip the grass.”*";
P_HTM[5128]="*Atha kho te, mahārāja, bhikkhū ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa āvesanaṃ uttiṇamakaṃsu.**So that’s what they did.*";
P_HTM[5129]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ:**Then Ghaṭīkāra’s parents said to those mendicants,*";
P_HTM[5130]="*“ke āvesanaṃ uttiṇaṃ karontī”ti?**“Who’s stripping the grass from the workshop?”*";
P_HTM[5131]="*“Bhikkhū, bhagini, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa kuṭi ovassatī”ti.**“It’s the mendicants, sister. The Buddha’s hut is leaking.”*";
P_HTM[5132]="*“Haratha, bhante, haratha, bhadramukhā”ti.**“Take it, sirs! Take it, my dears!”*";
P_HTM[5133]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro yena mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mātāpitaro etadavoca:**Then Ghaṭīkāra went up to his parents and said,*";
P_HTM[5134]="*“ke āvesanaṃ uttiṇamakaṃsū”ti?**“Who stripped the grass from the workshop?”*";
P_HTM[5135]="*“Bhikkhū, tāta, kassapassa kira bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa kuṭi ovassatī”ti.**“It was the mendicants, dear. It seems the Buddha’s hut is leaking.”*";
P_HTM[5136]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa etadahosi:**Then Ghaṭīkāra thought,*";
P_HTM[5137]="*“lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me,**“I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[5138]="*yassa me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho evaṃ abhivissattho”ti.**to be trusted so much by the Buddha Kassapa!”*";
P_HTM[5139]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ aḍḍhamāsaṃ pītisukhaṃ na vijahati, sattāhaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ.**Then joy and happiness did not leave him for a fortnight, or his parents for a week.*";
P_HTM[5140]="*Atha kho, mahārāja, āvesanaṃ sabbantaṃ temāsaṃ ākāsacchadanaṃ aṭṭhāsi, na devotivassi.**Then the workshop remained with the sky for a roof for the whole three months, but no rain fell on it.*";
P_HTM[5141]="*Evarūpo ca, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro’ti.**And that, great king, is what Ghaṭīkāra the potter is like.’*";
P_HTM[5142]="*‘Lābhā, bhante, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa, suladdhā, bhante, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa**‘Ghaṭīkāra the potter is fortunate, very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[5143]="*yassa bhagavā evaṃ abhivissattho’ti.**to be so trusted by the Buddha Kassapa.’*";
P_HTM[5144]="*Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa pañcamattāni taṇḍulavāhasatāni pāhesi paṇḍupuṭakassa sālino tadupiyañca sūpeyyaṃ.**Then King Kikī sent around five hundred cartloads of rice, soft saffron rice, and suitable sauce to Ghaṭīkāra.*";
P_HTM[5145]="*Atha kho te, ānanda, rājapurisā ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:**Then one of the king’s men approached Ghaṭīkāra and said,*";
P_HTM[5146]="*‘imāni kho, bhante, pañcamattāni taṇḍulavāhasatāni kikinā kāsirājena pahitāni paṇḍupuṭakassa sālino tadupiyañca sūpeyyaṃ.**‘Sir, these five hundred cartloads of rice, soft saffron rice, and suitable sauce have been sent to you by King Kikī of Kāsī.*";
P_HTM[5147]="*Tāni, bhante, paṭiggaṇhathā’ti.**Please accept them.’*";
P_HTM[5148]="*‘Rājā kho bahukicco bahukaraṇīyo.**‘The king has many duties, and much to do.*";
P_HTM[5149]="*Alaṃ me.**I have enough.*";
P_HTM[5150]="*Raññova hotū’ti.**Let this be for the king himself.’*";
P_HTM[5151]="*Siyā kho pana te, ānanda, evamassa:**Ānanda, you might think:*";
P_HTM[5152]="*‘añño nūna tena samayena jotipālo māṇavo ahosī’ti.**‘Surely the brahmin student Jotipāla must have been someone else at that time?’*";
P_HTM[5153]="*Na kho panetaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ.**But you should not see it like this.*";
P_HTM[5154]="*Ahaṃ tena samayena jotipālo māṇavo ahosin”ti.**I myself was the student Jotipāla at that time.”*";
P_HTM[5155]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5156]="*Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5157]="*Ghaṭikārasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5158]="*82. Raṭṭhapālasutta**With Raṭṭhapāla*";
P_HTM[5159]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5160]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kurūsu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena thullakoṭṭhikaṃ nāma kurūnaṃ nigamo tadavasari.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kurus together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a town of the Kurus named Thullakoṭṭhita.*";
P_HTM[5161]="*Assosuṃ kho thullakoṭṭhikā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:**The brahmins and householders of Thullakoṭṭhita heard:*";
P_HTM[5162]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kurūsu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ thullakoṭṭhikaṃ anuppatto.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has arrived at Thullakoṭṭhita, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[5163]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[5164]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[5165]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[5166]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[5167]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[5168]="*Atha kho thullakoṭṭhikā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Then the brahmins and householders of Thullakoṭṭhita went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent.*";
P_HTM[5169]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho thullakoṭṭhike brāhmaṇagahapatike bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**When they were seated, the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired them with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[5170]="*Tena kho pana samayena raṭṭhapālo nāma kulaputto tasmiṃyeva thullakoṭṭhike aggakulassa putto tissaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti.**Now at that time a gentleman named Raṭṭhapāla, the son of the leading clan in Thullakoṭṭhita, was sitting in the assembly.*";
P_HTM[5171]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa etadahosi:**He thought,*";
P_HTM[5172]="*“yathā yathā khvāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**“As I understand the Buddha’s teachings, it’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[5173]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan”ti.**Why don’t I cut off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from lay life to homelessness?”*";
P_HTM[5174]="*Atha kho thullakoṭṭhikā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu.**Then, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, the brahmins and householders of Thullakoṭṭhita got up from their seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[5175]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto acirapakkantesu thullakoṭṭhikesu brāhmaṇagahapatikesu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Soon after they left, Raṭṭhapāla went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5176]="*“yathā yathāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**“Sir, as I understand the Buddha’s teachings, it’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[5177]="*Icchāmahaṃ, bhante, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ.**I wish to cut off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5178]="*Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadaṃ.**Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?*";
P_HTM[5179]="*Pabbājetu maṃ bhagavā”ti.**May the Buddha please give me the going forth!”*";
P_HTM[5180]="*“Anuññātosi pana tvaṃ, raṭṭhapāla, mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?**“But, Raṭṭhapāla, do you have your parents’ permission?”*";
P_HTM[5181]="*“Na khohaṃ, bhante, anuññāto mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5182]="*“Na kho, raṭṭhapāla, tathāgatā ananuññātaṃ mātāpitūhi puttaṃ pabbājentī”ti.**“Raṭṭhapāla, Buddhas don’t give the going forth to the child of parents who haven’t given their permission.”*";
P_HTM[5183]="*“Svāhaṃ, bhante, tathā karissāmi yathā maṃ mātāpitaro anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti.**“I’ll make sure, sir, to get my parents’ permission.”*";
P_HTM[5184]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mātāpitaro etadavoca:**Then Raṭṭhapāla got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha. Then he went to his parents and said,*";
P_HTM[5185]="*“ammatātā, yathā yathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**“Mum and dad, as I understand the Buddha’s teachings, it’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[5186]="*Icchāmahaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ.**I wish to cut off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5187]="*Anujānātha maṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti.**Please give me permission to go forth.”*";
P_HTM[5188]="*Evaṃ vutte, raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa mātāpitaro raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When he said this, Raṭṭhapāla’s parents said to him,*";
P_HTM[5189]="*“tvaṃ khosi, tāta raṭṭhapāla, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparibhato.**“But, dear Raṭṭhapāla, you’re our only child. You’re dear to us and we love you. You’re dainty and raised in comfort.*";
P_HTM[5190]="*Na tvaṃ, tāta raṭṭhapāla, kassaci dukkhassa jānāsi.**You know nothing of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5191]="*() Maraṇenapi te mayaṃ akāmakā vinā bhavissāma.**When you die we will lose you against our wishes.*";
P_HTM[5192]="*Kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?**So how can we allow you to go forth while you’re still alive?”*";
P_HTM[5193]="*Dutiyampi kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto … pe …**For a second time,*";
P_HTM[5194]="*tatiyampi kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto mātāpitaro etadavoca:**and a third time, Raṭṭhapāla asked his parents for permission, but got the same reply.*";
P_HTM[5195]="*“ammatātā, yathā yathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5196]="*Icchāmahaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5197]="*Anujānātha maṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5198]="*Tatiyampi kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa mātāpitaro raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[5199]="*“tvaṃ khosi, tāta raṭṭhapāla, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparibhato.* **";
P_HTM[5200]="*Na tvaṃ, tāta raṭṭhapāla, kassaci dukkhassa jānāsi.* **";
P_HTM[5201]="*Maraṇenapi te mayaṃ akāmakā vinā bhavissāma.* **";
P_HTM[5202]="*Kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5203]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto:**Then Raṭṭhapāla thought,*";
P_HTM[5204]="*“na maṃ mātāpitaro anujānanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti tattheva anantarahitāya bhūmiyā nipajji:**“My parents don’t allow me to go forth.” He laid down there on the bare ground, saying,*";
P_HTM[5205]="*“idheva me maraṇaṃ bhavissati pabbajjā vā”ti.**“I’ll either die right here or go forth.”*";
P_HTM[5206]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto ekampi bhattaṃ na bhuñji, dvepi bhattāni na bhuñji, tīṇipi bhattāni na bhuñji, cattāripi bhattāni na bhuñji, pañcapi bhattāni na bhuñji, chapi bhattāni na bhuñji, sattapi bhattāni na bhuñji.**And he refused to eat, up to the seventh meal.*";
P_HTM[5207]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa mātāpitaro raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then Raṭṭhapāla’s parents said to him,*";
P_HTM[5208]="*“tvaṃ khosi, tāta raṭṭhapāla, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparibhato.**“Dear Raṭṭhapāla, you’re our only child. You’re dear to us and we love you. You’re dainty and raised in comfort.*";
P_HTM[5209]="*Na tvaṃ, tāta raṭṭhapāla, kassaci, dukkhassa jānāsi.**You know nothing of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5210]="*Maraṇenapi te mayaṃ akāmakā vinā bhavissāma.**When you die we will lose you against our wishes.*";
P_HTM[5211]="*Kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**So how can we allow you to go forth from lay life to homelessness while you’re still living?*";
P_HTM[5212]="*Uṭṭhehi, tāta raṭṭhapāla, bhuñja ca piva ca paricārehi ca;**Get up, Raṭṭhapāla! Eat, drink, and amuse yourself.*";
P_HTM[5213]="*bhuñjanto pivanto paricārento kāme paribhuñjanto puññāni karonto abhiramassu.**While enjoying sensual pleasures, delight in making merit.*";
P_HTM[5214]="*Na taṃ mayaṃ anujānāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**We don’t allow you to go forth.*";
P_HTM[5215]="*Maraṇenapi te mayaṃ akāmakā vinā bhavissāma.**When you die we will lose you against our wishes.*";
P_HTM[5216]="*Kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?**So how can we allow you to go forth while you’re still alive?”*";
P_HTM[5217]="*Evaṃ vutte, raṭṭhapālo kulaputto tuṇhī ahosi.**When they said this, Raṭṭhapāla kept silent.*";
P_HTM[5218]="*Dutiyampi kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa mātāpitaro raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ … pe …**For a second time,*";
P_HTM[5219]="*dutiyampi kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto tuṇhī ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[5220]="*Tatiyampi kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa mātāpitaro raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:**and a third time, Raṭṭhapāla’s parents made the same request.*";
P_HTM[5221]="*“tvaṃ khosi, tāta raṭṭhapāla, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparibhato.* **";
P_HTM[5222]="*Na tvaṃ, tāta raṭṭhapāla, kassaci dukkhassa jānāsi.* **";
P_HTM[5223]="*Maraṇenapi te mayaṃ akāmakā vinā bhavissāma, kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.* **";
P_HTM[5224]="*Uṭṭhehi, tāta raṭṭhapāla, bhuñja ca piva ca paricārehi ca;* **";
P_HTM[5225]="*bhuñjanto pivanto paricārento kāme paribhuñjanto puññāni karonto abhiramassu.* **";
P_HTM[5226]="*Na taṃ mayaṃ anujānāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.* **";
P_HTM[5227]="*Maraṇenapi te mayaṃ akāmakā vinā bhavissāma.* **";
P_HTM[5228]="*Kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5229]="*Tatiyampi kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto tuṇhī ahosi.**And for a third time, Raṭṭhapāla kept silent. Raṭṭhapāla’s parents then went to see his friends. They told them of the situation and asked for their help.*";
P_HTM[5230]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa sahāyakā yena raṭṭhapālo kulaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then Raṭṭhapāla’s friends went to him and said,*";
P_HTM[5231]="*“tvaṃ khosi, samma raṭṭhapāla, mātāpitūnaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparibhato.**“Our friend Raṭṭhapāla, you are your parents’ only child. You’re dear to them and they love you. You’re dainty and raised in comfort.*";
P_HTM[5232]="*Na tvaṃ, samma raṭṭhapāla, kassaci dukkhassa jānāsi.**You know nothing of suffering.*";
P_HTM[5233]="*Maraṇenapi te mātāpitaro akāmakā vinā bhavissanti.**When you die your parents will lose you against their wishes.*";
P_HTM[5234]="*Kiṃ pana te taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**So how can they allow you to go forth while you’re still alive?*";
P_HTM[5235]="*Uṭṭhehi, samma raṭṭhapāla, bhuñja ca piva ca paricārehi ca;**Get up, Raṭṭhapāla! Eat, drink, and amuse yourself.*";
P_HTM[5236]="*bhuñjanto pivanto paricārento kāme paribhuñjanto puññāni karonto abhiramassu.**While enjoying sensual pleasures, delight in making merit.*";
P_HTM[5237]="*Na taṃ mātāpitaro anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**Your parents will not allow you to go forth.*";
P_HTM[5238]="*Maraṇenapi te mātāpitaro akāmakā vinā bhavissanti.**When you die your parents will lose you against their wishes.*";
P_HTM[5239]="*Kiṃ pana te taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?**So how can they allow you to go forth while you’re still alive?”*";
P_HTM[5240]="*Evaṃ vutte, raṭṭhapālo kulaputto tuṇhī ahosi.**When they said this, Raṭṭhapāla kept silent.*";
P_HTM[5241]="*Dutiyampi kho …**For a second time,*";
P_HTM[5242]="*tatiyampi kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa sahāyakā raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:**and a third time, Raṭṭhapāla’s friends made the same request.*";
P_HTM[5243]="*“tvaṃ khosi, samma raṭṭhapāla, mātāpitūnaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparibhato, na tvaṃ, samma raṭṭhapāla, kassaci dukkhassa jānāsi, maraṇenapi te mātāpitaro akāmakā vinā bhavissanti.* **";
P_HTM[5244]="*Kiṃ pana te taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya?* **";
P_HTM[5245]="*Uṭṭhehi, samma raṭṭhapāla, bhuñja ca piva ca paricārehi ca, bhuñjanto pivanto paricārento kāme paribhuñjanto puññāni karonto abhiramassu.* **";
P_HTM[5246]="*Na taṃ mātāpitaro anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya, maraṇenapi te mātāpitaro akāmakā vinā bhavissanti.* **";
P_HTM[5247]="*Kiṃ pana te taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5248]="*Tatiyampi kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto tuṇhī ahosi.**And for a third time, Raṭṭhapāla kept silent.*";
P_HTM[5249]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa sahāyakā yena raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa mātāpitaro etadavocuṃ:**Then Raṭṭhapāla’s friends went to his parents and said,*";
P_HTM[5250]="*“ammatātā, eso raṭṭhapālo kulaputto tattheva anantarahitāya bhūmiyā nipanno:**“Mum and dad, Raṭṭhapāla is lying there on the bare ground saying:*";
P_HTM[5251]="*‘idheva me maraṇaṃ bhavissati pabbajjā vā’ti.**‘I’ll either die right here or go forth.’*";
P_HTM[5252]="*Sace tumhe raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ nānujānissatha agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya, tattheva maraṇaṃ āgamissati.**If you don’t allow him to go forth, he’ll die there.*";
P_HTM[5253]="*Sace pana tumhe raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ anujānissatha agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya, pabbajitampi naṃ dakkhissatha.**But if you do allow him to go forth, you’ll see him again afterwards.*";
P_HTM[5254]="*Sace raṭṭhapālo kulaputto nābhiramissati agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya, kā tassa aññā gati bhavissati? Idheva paccāgamissati.**And if he doesn’t enjoy the renunciate life, where else will he have to go? He’ll come right back here.*";
P_HTM[5255]="*Anujānātha raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti.**Please give Raṭṭhapāla permission to go forth.”*";
P_HTM[5256]="*“Anujānāma, tātā, raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**“Then, dears, we give Raṭṭhapāla permission to go forth.*";
P_HTM[5257]="*Pabbajitena ca pana mātāpitaro uddassetabbā”ti.**But once gone forth he must visit his parents.”*";
P_HTM[5258]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa sahāyakā yena raṭṭhapālo kulaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā raṭṭhapālaṃ kulaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then Raṭṭhapāla’s friends went to him and said,*";
P_HTM[5259]="*“uṭṭhehi, samma raṭṭhapāla, anuññātosi mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**“Get up, Raṭṭhapāla! Your parents have given you permission to go forth from lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5260]="*Pabbajitena ca pana te mātāpitaro uddassetabbā”ti.**But once gone forth you must visit your parents.”*";
P_HTM[5261]="*Atha kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto uṭṭhahitvā balaṃ gāhetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Raṭṭhapāla got up and regained his strength. He went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5262]="*“anuññāto ahaṃ, bhante, mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**“Sir, I have my parents’ permission to go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5263]="*Pabbājetu maṃ bhagavā”ti.**May the Buddha please give me the going forth.”*";
P_HTM[5264]="*Alattha kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ.**And Raṭṭhapāla received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence.*";
P_HTM[5265]="*Atha kho bhagavā acirūpasampanne āyasmante raṭṭhapāle aḍḍhamāsupasampanne thullakoṭṭhike yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**Not long after Venerable Raṭṭhapāla’s ordination, a fortnight later, the Buddha—having stayed in Thullakoṭṭhita as long as he wished—set out for Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5266]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi tadavasari.**Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[5267]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**where he stayed in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[5268]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**Then Venerable Raṭṭhapāla, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5269]="*“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi.**He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[5270]="*Aññataro kho panāyasmā raṭṭhapālo arahataṃ ahosi.**And Venerable Raṭṭhapāla became one of the perfected.*";
P_HTM[5271]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then he went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5272]="*“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, mātāpitaro uddassetuṃ, sace maṃ bhagavā anujānātī”ti.**“Sir, I’d like to visit my parents, if the Buddha allows it.”*";
P_HTM[5273]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa cetasā ceto paricca manasākāsi.**Then the Buddha focused on comprehending Raṭṭhapāla’s mind.*";
P_HTM[5274]="*Yathā bhagavā aññāsi:**When he knew that*";
P_HTM[5275]="*“abhabbo kho raṭṭhapālo kulaputto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattitun”ti, atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ etadavoca:**it was impossible for Raṭṭhapāla to reject the training and return to a lesser life, he said,*";
P_HTM[5276]="*“yassadāni tvaṃ, raṭṭhapāla, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, Raṭṭhapāla, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[5277]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena thullakoṭṭhikaṃ tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**And then Raṭṭhapāla got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. Then he set his lodgings in order and, taking his bowl and robe, set out for Thullakoṭṭhita.*";
P_HTM[5278]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena thullakoṭṭhiko tadavasari.**Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Thullakoṭṭhika,*";
P_HTM[5279]="*Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā raṭṭhapālo thullakoṭṭhike viharati rañño korabyassa migacīre.**where he stayed in King Koravya’s deer range.*";
P_HTM[5280]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya thullakoṭṭhikaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then Raṭṭhapāla robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Thullakoṭṭhita for alms.*";
P_HTM[5281]="*Thullakoṭṭhike sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena sakapitu nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Wandering indiscriminately for alms-food, he approached his own father’s house.*";
P_HTM[5282]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitā majjhimāya dvārasālāya ullikhāpeti.**Now at that time Raṭṭhapāla’s father was having his hair dressed in the hall of the middle gate.*";
P_HTM[5283]="*Addasā kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitā āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**He saw Raṭṭhapāla coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[5284]="*Disvāna etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[5285]="*“imehi muṇḍakehi samaṇakehi amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo pabbājito”ti.**“Our dear and beloved only son was made to go forth by these shavelings, these fake ascetics!”*";
P_HTM[5286]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo sakapitu nivesane neva dānaṃ alattha na paccakkhānaṃ;**And at his own father’s house Raṭṭhapāla received neither alms nor a polite refusal,*";
P_HTM[5287]="*aññadatthu akkosameva alattha.**but only abuse.*";
P_HTM[5288]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa ñātidāsī ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ chaḍḍetukāmā hoti.**Now at that time a family bondservant wanted to throw away the previous night’s porridge.*";
P_HTM[5289]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo taṃ ñātidāsiṃ etadavoca:**So Raṭṭhapāla said to her,*";
P_HTM[5290]="*“sacetaṃ, bhagini, chaḍḍanīyadhammaṃ, idha me patte ākirā”ti.**“If that’s to be thrown away, sister, pour it here in my bowl.”*";
P_HTM[5291]="*Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa ñātidāsī taṃ ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa patte ākirantī hatthānañca pādānañca sarassa ca nimittaṃ aggahesi.**As she was pouring the porridge into his bowl, she recognized the features of his hands, feet, and voice.*";
P_HTM[5292]="*Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa ñātidāsī yenāyasmato raṭṭhapālassa mātā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa mātaraṃ etadavoca:**She then went to his mother and said,*";
P_HTM[5293]="*“yaggheyye, jāneyyāsi:**“Please, madam, you should know this.*";
P_HTM[5294]="*‘ayyaputto raṭṭhapālo anuppatto’”ti.**My lord Raṭṭhapāla has arrived.”*";
P_HTM[5295]="*“Sace, je, saccaṃ bhaṇasi, adāsiṃ taṃ karomī”ti.**“Wow! If you speak the truth, I’ll make you a free woman!”*";
P_HTM[5296]="*Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa mātā yenāyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitaraṃ etadavoca:**Then Raṭṭhapāla’s mother went to his father and said,*";
P_HTM[5297]="*“yagghe, gahapati, jāneyyāsi:**“Please householder, you should know this.*";
P_HTM[5298]="*‘raṭṭhapālo kira kulaputto anuppatto’”ti?**It seems our son Raṭṭhapāla has arrived.”*";
P_HTM[5299]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā raṭṭhapālo taṃ ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ aññataraṃ kuṭṭamūlaṃ nissāya paribhuñjati.**Now at that time Raṭṭhapāla was eating last night’s porridge by a wall.*";
P_HTM[5300]="*Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitā yenāyasmā raṭṭhapālo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ etadavoca:**Then Raṭṭhapāla’s father went up to him and said,*";
P_HTM[5301]="*“atthi nāma, tāta raṭṭhapāla, ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ paribhuñjissasi?**“Dear Raṭṭhapāla! There’s … and you’ll be eating last night’s porridge!*";
P_HTM[5302]="*Nanu, tāta raṭṭhapāla, sakaṃ gehaṃ gantabban”ti?**Why not go to your own home?”*";
P_HTM[5303]="*“Kuto no, gahapati, amhākaṃ gehaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitānaṃ?**“Householder, how could those of us who have gone forth from the lay life to homelessness have a house?*";
P_HTM[5304]="*Anagārā mayaṃ, gahapati.**We’re homeless, householder.*";
P_HTM[5305]="*Agamamha kho te, gahapati, gehaṃ, tattha neva dānaṃ alatthamha na paccakkhānaṃ;**I came to your house, but there I received neither alms nor a polite refusal,*";
P_HTM[5306]="*aññadatthu akkosameva alatthamhā”ti.**but only abuse.”*";
P_HTM[5307]="*“Ehi, tāta raṭṭhapāla, gharaṃ gamissāmā”ti.**“Come, dear Raṭṭhapāla, let’s go to the house.”*";
P_HTM[5308]="*“Alaṃ, gahapati, kataṃ me ajja bhattakiccaṃ”.**“Enough, householder. My meal is finished for today.”*";
P_HTM[5309]="*“Tena hi, tāta raṭṭhapāla, adhivāsehi svātanāya bhattan”ti.**“Well then, dear Raṭṭhapāla, please accept tomorrow’s meal from me.”*";
P_HTM[5310]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo tuṇhībhāvena.**Raṭṭhapāla consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[5311]="*Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitā āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa adhivāsanaṃ viditvā yena sakaṃ nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mahantaṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇassa puñjaṃ kārāpetvā kilañjehi paṭicchādetvā āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa purāṇadutiyikā āmantesi:**Then, knowing that Raṭṭhapāla had consented, his father went back to his own house. He made a heap of gold coins and bullion and hid it under mats. Then he addressed Raṭṭhapāla’s former wives,*";
P_HTM[5312]="*“etha tumhe, vadhuyo, yena alaṅkārena alaṅkatā pubbe raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa piyā hotha manāpā tena alaṅkārena alaṅkarothā”ti.**“Please, daughters-in-law, adorn yourselves in the way that our son Raṭṭhapāla found you most adorable.”*";
P_HTM[5313]="*Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitā tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa kālaṃ ārocesi:**And when the night had passed Raṭṭhapāla’s father had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home, and announced the time to the Venerable Raṭṭhapāla, saying,*";
P_HTM[5314]="*“kālo, tāta raṭṭhapāla, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**“Sir, it’s time. The meal is ready.”*";
P_HTM[5315]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena sakapitu nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitā taṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇassa puñjaṃ vivarāpetvā āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ etadavoca:**Then Raṭṭhapāla robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to his father’s home, and sat down on the seat spread out. Raṭṭhapāla’s father, revealing the heap of gold coins and bullion, said to him,*";
P_HTM[5316]="*“idaṃ te, tāta raṭṭhapāla, mātu mattikaṃ dhanaṃ, aññaṃ pettikaṃ, aññaṃ pitāmahaṃ.**“Dear Raṭṭhapāla, this is your maternal fortune. There’s another paternal fortune, and an ancestral one.*";
P_HTM[5317]="*Sakkā, tāta raṭṭhapāla, bhoge ca bhuñjituṃ puññāni ca kātuṃ.**You can both enjoy your wealth and make merit.*";
P_HTM[5318]="*Ehi tvaṃ, tāta raṭṭhapāla, hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu puññāni ca karohī”ti.**Come, return to a lesser life, enjoy wealth, and make merit!”*";
P_HTM[5319]="*“Sace me tvaṃ, gahapati, vacanaṃ kareyyāsi, imaṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇassa puñjaṃ sakaṭe āropetvā nibbāhāpetvā majjhegaṅgāya nadiyā sote opilāpeyyāsi.**“If you’d follow my advice, householder, you’d have this heap of gold loaded on a cart and carried away to be dumped in the middle of the Ganges river.*";
P_HTM[5320]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5321]="*Ye uppajjissanti hi te, gahapati, tatonidānaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti.**Because this will bring you nothing but sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.”*";
P_HTM[5322]="*Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa purāṇadutiyikā paccekaṃ pādesu gahetvā āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then Raṭṭhapāla’s former wives each clasped his feet and said,*";
P_HTM[5323]="*“kīdisā nāma tā, ayyaputta, accharāyo yāsaṃ tvaṃ hetu brahmacariyaṃ carasī”ti?**“What are they like, lord, the nymphs for whom you lead the spiritual life?”*";
P_HTM[5324]="*“Na kho mayaṃ, bhaginī, accharānaṃ hetu brahmacariyaṃ carāmā”ti.**“Sisters, I don’t lead the spiritual life for the sake of nymphs.”*";
P_HTM[5325]="*“Bhaginivādena no ayyaputto raṭṭhapālo samudācaratī”ti tā tattheva mucchitā papatiṃsu.**Saying, “Our lord Raṭṭhapāla refers to us as sisters!” they fainted right away.*";
P_HTM[5326]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo pitaraṃ etadavoca:**Then Raṭṭhapāla said to his father,*";
P_HTM[5327]="*“sace, gahapati, bhojanaṃ dātabbaṃ, detha;**“If there is food to be given, householder, please give it.*";
P_HTM[5328]="*mā no viheṭhethā”ti.**But don’t harass me.”*";
P_HTM[5329]="*“Bhuñja, tāta raṭṭhapāla, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**“Eat, dear Raṭṭhapāla. The meal is ready.”*";
P_HTM[5330]="*Atha kho āyasmato raṭṭhapālassa pitā āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Then Raṭṭhapāla’s father served and satisfied Venerable Raṭṭhapāla with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[5331]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo bhuttāvī onītapattapāṇī ṭhitakova imā gāthā abhāsi:**When he had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, he recited these verses while standing right there:*";
P_HTM[5332]="*“Passa cittīkataṃ bimbaṃ,**“See this fancy puppet,*";
P_HTM[5333]="*arukāyaṃ samussitaṃ;**a body built of sores,*";
P_HTM[5334]="*Āturaṃ bahusaṅkappaṃ,**diseased, obsessed over,*";
P_HTM[5335]="*yassa natthi dhuvaṃ ṭhiti.**which doesn’t last at all.*";
P_HTM[5336]="*Passa cittīkataṃ rūpaṃ,**See this fancy figure,*";
P_HTM[5337]="*maṇinā kuṇḍalena ca;**with its gems and earrings;*";
P_HTM[5338]="*Aṭṭhi tacena onaddhaṃ,**it is bones wrapped in skin,*";
P_HTM[5339]="*saha vatthebhi sobhati.**made pretty by its clothes.*";
P_HTM[5340]="*Alattakakatā pādā,**Rouged feet*";
P_HTM[5341]="*mukhaṃ cuṇṇakamakkhitaṃ;**and powdered face*";
P_HTM[5342]="*Alaṃ bālassa mohāya,**may be enough to beguile a fool,*";
P_HTM[5343]="*no ca pāragavesino.**but not a seeker of the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5344]="*Aṭṭhāpadakatā kesā,**Hair in eight braids*";
P_HTM[5345]="*nettā añjanamakkhitā;**and eyeliner*";
P_HTM[5346]="*Alaṃ bālassa mohāya,**may be enough to beguile a fool,*";
P_HTM[5347]="*no ca pāragavesino.**but not a seeker of the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5348]="*Añjanīva navā cittā,**A rotting body all adorned*";
P_HTM[5349]="*pūtikāyo alaṅkato;**like a freshly painted makeup box*";
P_HTM[5350]="*Alaṃ bālassa mohāya,**may be enough to beguile a fool,*";
P_HTM[5351]="*no ca pāragavesino.**but not a seeker of the far shore.*";
P_HTM[5352]="*Odahi migavo pāsaṃ,**The hunter laid his snare,*";
P_HTM[5353]="*nāsadā vākaraṃ migo;**but the deer didn’t spring the trap.*";
P_HTM[5354]="*Bhutvā nivāpaṃ gacchāma,**I’ve eaten the bait and now I go,*";
P_HTM[5355]="*kandante migabandhake”ti.**leaving the trapper to lament.”*";
P_HTM[5356]="*Atha kho āyasmā raṭṭhapālo ṭhitakova imā gāthā bhāsitvā yena rañño korabyassa migacīraṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi.**Then Raṭṭhapāla, having recited this verse while standing, went to King Koravya’s deer range and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[5357]="*Atha kho rājā korabyo migavaṃ āmantesi:**Then King Koravya addressed his gamekeeper,*";
P_HTM[5358]="*“sodhehi, samma migava, migacīraṃ uyyānabhūmiṃ;**“My good gamekeeper, tidy up the park of the deer range.*";
P_HTM[5359]="*gacchāma subhūmiṃ dassanāyā”ti.**We will go to see the scenery.”*";
P_HTM[5360]="*“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho migavo rañño korabyassa paṭissutvā migacīraṃ sodhento addasa āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisinnaṃ.**“Yes, Your Majesty,” replied the gamekeeper. While tidying the deer range he saw Raṭṭhapāla sitting in meditation.*";
P_HTM[5361]="*Disvāna yena rājā korabyo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ korabyaṃ etadavoca:**Seeing this, he went to the king, and said,*";
P_HTM[5362]="*“suddhaṃ kho te, deva, migacīraṃ.**“The deer range is tidy, sire.*";
P_HTM[5363]="*Atthi cettha raṭṭhapālo nāma kulaputto imasmiṃyeva thullakoṭṭhike aggakulassa putto yassa tvaṃ abhiṇhaṃ kittayamāno ahosi, so aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisinno”ti.**And the gentleman named Raṭṭhapāla, the son of the leading clan in Thullakoṭṭhita, of whom you have often spoken highly, is meditating there at the root of a tree.”*";
P_HTM[5364]="*“Tena hi, samma migava, alaṃ dānajja uyyānabhūmiyā.**“Well then, my good gamekeeper, that’s enough of the park for today.*";
P_HTM[5365]="*Tameva dāni mayaṃ bhavantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ payirupāsissāmā”ti.**Now I shall pay homage to the Master Raṭṭhapāla.”*";
P_HTM[5366]="*Atha kho rājā korabyo “yaṃ tattha khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyattaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ vissajjethā”ti vatvā bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhadraṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi thullakoṭṭhikamhā niyyāsi mahaccarājānubhāvena āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ dassanāya.**And then King Koravya said, “Give away all the different foods that have been prepared there.” He had the finest carriages harnessed. Then he mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out in full royal pomp from Thullakoṭṭhita to see Raṭṭhapāla.*";
P_HTM[5367]="*Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova ussaṭāya ussaṭāya parisāya yenāyasmā raṭṭhapālo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā raṭṭhapālena saddhiṃ sammodi. Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho rājā korabyo āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ etadavoca:**He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached Raṭṭhapāla on foot, together with a group of eminent officials. They exchanged greetings, and, when the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side, and said to Raṭṭhapāla:*";
P_HTM[5368]="*“idha bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo hatthatthare nisīdatū”ti.**“Here, Master Raṭṭhapāla, sit on this elephant rug.”*";
P_HTM[5369]="*“Alaṃ, mahārāja, nisīda tvaṃ;**“Enough, great king, you sit on it.*";
P_HTM[5370]="*nisinno ahaṃ sake āsane”ti.**I’m sitting on my own seat.”*";
P_HTM[5371]="*Nisīdi rājā korabyo paññatte āsane. Nisajja kho rājā korabyo āyasmantaṃ raṭṭhapālaṃ etadavoca:**So the king sat down on the seat spread out, and said:*";
P_HTM[5372]="*“Cattārimāni, bho raṭṭhapāla, pārijuññāni yehi pārijuññehi samannāgatā idhekacce kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti.**“Master Raṭṭhapāla, there are these four kinds of decay. Because of these, some people shave off their hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5373]="*Katamāni cattāri?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5374]="*Jarāpārijuññaṃ, byādhipārijuññaṃ, bhogapārijuññaṃ, ñātipārijuññaṃ.**Decay due to old age, decay due to sickness, decay of wealth, and decay of relatives.*";
P_HTM[5375]="*Katamañca, bho raṭṭhapāla, jarāpārijuññaṃ?**And what is decay due to old age?*";
P_HTM[5376]="*Idha, bho raṭṭhapāla, ekacco jiṇṇo hoti vuḍḍho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto.**It’s when someone is old, elderly, and senior, advanced in years, and has reached the final stage of life.*";
P_HTM[5377]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:**They reflect:*";
P_HTM[5378]="*‘ahaṃ khomhi etarahi jiṇṇo vuḍḍho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto.**‘I’m now old, elderly, and senior. I’m advanced in years and have reached the final stage of life.*";
P_HTM[5379]="*Na kho pana mayā sukaraṃ anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigantuṃ adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ.**It’s not easy for me to acquire more wealth or to increase the wealth I’ve already acquired.*";
P_HTM[5380]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[5381]="*So tena jarāpārijuññena samannāgato kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**So because of that decay due to old age they go forth.*";
P_HTM[5382]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bho raṭṭhapāla, jarāpārijuññaṃ.**This is called decay due to old age.*";
P_HTM[5383]="*Bhavaṃ kho pana raṭṭhapālo etarahi daharo yuvā susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā.**But Master Raṭṭhapāla is now a youth, young, black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life.*";
P_HTM[5384]="*Taṃ bhoto raṭṭhapālassa jarāpārijuññaṃ natthi.**You have no decay due to old age.*";
P_HTM[5385]="*Kiṃ bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo ñatvā vā disvā vā sutvā vā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito? (1)**So what did you know or see or hear that made you go forth?*";
P_HTM[5386]="*Katamañca, bho raṭṭhapāla, byādhipārijuññaṃ?**And what is decay due to sickness?*";
P_HTM[5387]="*Idha, bho raṭṭhapāla, ekacco ābādhiko hoti dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**It’s when someone is sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[5388]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:**They reflect:*";
P_HTM[5389]="*‘ahaṃ khomhi etarahi ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**‘I’m now sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[5390]="*Na kho pana mayā sukaraṃ anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigantuṃ adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ.**It’s not easy for me to acquire more wealth or to increase the wealth I’ve already acquired.*";
P_HTM[5391]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[5392]="*So tena byādhipārijuññena samannāgato kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**So because of that decay due to sickness they go forth.*";
P_HTM[5393]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bho raṭṭhapāla, byādhipārijuññaṃ.**This is called decay due to sickness.*";
P_HTM[5394]="*Bhavaṃ kho pana raṭṭhapālo etarahi appābādho appātaṅko samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya nāccuṇhāya.**But Master Raṭṭhapāla is now rarely ill or unwell. Your stomach digests well, being neither too hot nor too cold.*";
P_HTM[5395]="*Taṃ bhoto raṭṭhapālassa byādhipārijuññaṃ natthi.**You have no decay due to sickness.*";
P_HTM[5396]="*Kiṃ bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo ñatvā vā disvā vā sutvā vā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito? (2)**So what did you know or see or hear that made you go forth?*";
P_HTM[5397]="*Katamañca, bho raṭṭhapāla, bhogapārijuññaṃ?**And what is decay of wealth?*";
P_HTM[5398]="*Idha, bho raṭṭhapāla, ekacco aḍḍho hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo.**It’s when someone is rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[5399]="*Tassa te bhogā anupubbena parikkhayaṃ gacchanti.**But gradually their wealth dwindles away.*";
P_HTM[5400]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:**They reflect:*";
P_HTM[5401]="*‘ahaṃ kho pubbe aḍḍho ahosiṃ mahaddhano mahābhogo.**‘I used to be rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[5402]="*Tassa me te bhogā anupubbena parikkhayaṃ gatā.**But gradually my wealth has dwindled away.*";
P_HTM[5403]="*Na kho pana mayā sukaraṃ anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigantuṃ adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ.**It’s not easy for me to acquire more wealth or to increase the wealth I’ve already acquired.*";
P_HTM[5404]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[5405]="*So tena bhogapārijuññena samannāgato kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**So because of that decay of wealth they go forth.*";
P_HTM[5406]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bho raṭṭhapāla, bhogapārijuññaṃ.**This is called decay of wealth.*";
P_HTM[5407]="*Bhavaṃ kho pana raṭṭhapālo imasmiṃyeva thullakoṭṭhike aggakulassa putto.**But Master Raṭṭhapāla is the son of the leading clan here in Thullakoṭṭhita.*";
P_HTM[5408]="*Taṃ bhoto raṭṭhapālassa bhogapārijuññaṃ natthi.**You have no decay of wealth.*";
P_HTM[5409]="*Kiṃ bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo ñatvā vā disvā vā sutvā vā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito? (3)**So what did you know or see or hear that made you go forth?*";
P_HTM[5410]="*Katamañca, bho raṭṭhapāla, ñātipārijuññaṃ?**And what is decay of relatives?*";
P_HTM[5411]="*Idha, bho raṭṭhapāla, ekaccassa bahū honti mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā.**It’s when someone has many friends and colleagues, relatives and kin.*";
P_HTM[5412]="*Tassa te ñātakā anupubbena parikkhayaṃ gacchanti.**But gradually their relatives dwindle away.*";
P_HTM[5413]="*So iti paṭisañcikkhati:**They reflect:*";
P_HTM[5414]="*‘mamaṃ kho pubbe bahū ahesuṃ mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā.**‘I used to have many friends and colleagues, relatives and kin.*";
P_HTM[5415]="*Tassa me te anupubbena parikkhayaṃ gatā.**But gradually they’ve dwindled away.*";
P_HTM[5416]="*Na kho pana mayā sukaraṃ anadhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ adhigantuṃ adhigataṃ vā bhogaṃ phātiṃ kātuṃ.**It’s not easy for me to acquire more wealth or to increase the wealth I’ve already acquired.*";
P_HTM[5417]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[5418]="*So tena ñātipārijuññena samannāgato kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**So because of that decay of relatives they go forth.*";
P_HTM[5419]="*Idaṃ vuccati, bho raṭṭhapāla, ñātipārijuññaṃ.**This is called decay of relatives.*";
P_HTM[5420]="*Bhoto kho pana raṭṭhapālassa imasmiṃyeva thullakoṭṭhike bahū mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā.**But Master Raṭṭhapāla has many friends and colleagues, relatives and kin right here in Thullakoṭṭhita.*";
P_HTM[5421]="*Taṃ bhoto raṭṭhapālassa ñātipārijuññaṃ natthi.**You have no decay of relatives.*";
P_HTM[5422]="*Kiṃ bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo ñatvā vā disvā vā sutvā vā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito? (4)**So what did you know or see or hear that made you go forth?*";
P_HTM[5423]="*Imāni kho, bho raṭṭhapāla, cattāri pārijuññāni, yehi pārijuññehi samannāgatā idhekacce kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti.**There are these four kinds of decay. Because of these, some people shave off their hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5424]="*Tāni bhoto raṭṭhapālassa natthi.**Master Raṭṭhapāla has none of these.*";
P_HTM[5425]="*Kiṃ bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo ñatvā vā disvā vā sutvā vā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti?**So what did you know or see or hear that made you go forth?”*";
P_HTM[5426]="*“Atthi kho, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāro dhammuddesā uddiṭṭhā, ye ahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.**“Great king, the Blessed One who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha has taught these four summaries of the teaching for recitation. It was after knowing and seeing and hearing these that I went forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5427]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[5428]="*Upaniyyati loko addhuvo’ti**‘The world is unstable and swept away.’*";
P_HTM[5429]="*kho, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena paṭhamo dhammuddeso uddiṭṭho, yamahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.**This is the first summary.*";
P_HTM[5430]="*‘Atāṇo loko anabhissaro’ti**‘The world has no shelter and no savior.’*";
P_HTM[5431]="*kho, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dutiyo dhammuddeso uddiṭṭho, yamahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.**This is the second summary.*";
P_HTM[5432]="*‘Assako loko, sabbaṃ pahāya gamanīyan’ti**‘The world has no owner—you must leave it all behind and pass on.’*";
P_HTM[5433]="*kho, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena tatiyo dhammuddeso uddiṭṭho, yamahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.**This is the third summary.*";
P_HTM[5434]="*‘Ūno loko atitto taṇhādāso’ti**‘The world is wanting, insatiable, the slave of craving.’*";
P_HTM[5435]="*kho, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena catuttho dhammuddeso uddiṭṭho, yamahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito.**This is the fourth summary.*";
P_HTM[5436]="*Ime kho, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāro dhammuddesā uddiṭṭhā, ye ahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti.**The Blessed One who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha taught these four summaries of the teaching. It was after knowing and seeing and hearing these that I went forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[5437]="*“‘Upaniyyati loko addhuvo’ti—**“‘The world is unstable and swept away.’*";
P_HTM[5438]="*bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo āha.**So Master Raṭṭhapāla said.*";
P_HTM[5439]="*Imassa, bho raṭṭhapāla, bhāsitassa kathaṃ attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**How should I see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[5440]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5441]="*tvaṃ vīsativassuddesikopi paṇṇavīsativassuddesikopi hatthismimpi katāvī assasmimpi katāvī rathasmimpi katāvī dhanusmimpi katāvī tharusmimpi katāvī ūrubalī bāhubalī alamatto saṅgāmāvacaro”ti?**When you were twenty or twenty-five years of age, were you proficient at riding elephants, horses, and chariots, and at archery? Were you strong in thigh and arm, capable, and battle-hardened?”*";
P_HTM[5442]="*“Ahosiṃ ahaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, vīsativassuddesikopi paṇṇavīsativassuddesikopi hatthismimpi katāvī assasmimpi katāvī rathasmimpi katāvī dhanusmimpi katāvī tharusmimpi katāvī ūrubalī bāhubalī alamatto saṅgāmāvacaro.**“I was, Master Raṭṭhapāla.*";
P_HTM[5443]="*Appekadāhaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, iddhimāva maññe na attano balena samasamaṃ samanupassāmī”ti.**Sometimes it seems as if I had superpowers then. I don’t see anyone who could have equalled me in strength.”*";
P_HTM[5444]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5445]="*evameva tvaṃ etarahi ūrubalī bāhubalī alamatto saṅgāmāvacaro”ti?**These days are you just as strong in thigh and arm, capable, and battle-hardened?”*";
P_HTM[5446]="*“No hidaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla.**“No, Master Raṭṭhapāla.*";
P_HTM[5447]="*Etarahi jiṇṇo vuḍḍho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto āsītiko me vayo vattati.**For now I am old, elderly, and senior, I’m advanced in years and have reached the final stage of life. I am eighty years old.*";
P_HTM[5448]="*Appekadāhaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, ‘idha pādaṃ karissāmī’ti aññeneva pādaṃ karomī”ti.**Sometimes I intend to step in one place, but my foot goes somewhere else.”*";
P_HTM[5449]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“This is what the Buddha was referring to when he said:*";
P_HTM[5450]="*‘upaniyyati loko addhuvo’ti,**‘The world is unstable and swept away.’”*";
P_HTM[5451]="*yamahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5452]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, abbhutaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla.**“It’s incredible, Master Raṭṭhapāla, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[5453]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena:**how well said this was by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5454]="*‘upaniyyati loko addhuvo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5455]="*Upaniyyati hi, bho raṭṭhapāla, loko addhuvo. (1)**For the world is indeed unstable and swept away.*";
P_HTM[5456]="*Saṃvijjante kho, bho raṭṭhapāla, imasmiṃ rājakule hatthikāyāpi assakāyāpi rathakāyāpi pattikāyāpi, amhākaṃ āpadāsu pariyodhāya vattissanti.**In this royal court you can find divisions of elephants, cavalry, chariots, and infantry. They will serve to defend us from any threats. Yet you said:*";
P_HTM[5457]="*‘Atāṇo loko anabhissaro’ti—**‘The world has no shelter and no savior.’*";
P_HTM[5458]="*bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo āha.* **";
P_HTM[5459]="*Imassa pana, bho raṭṭhapāla, bhāsitassa kathaṃ attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**How should I see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[5460]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5461]="*atthi te koci anusāyiko ābādho”ti?**Do you have any chronic ailments?”*";
P_HTM[5462]="*“Atthi me, bho raṭṭhapāla, anusāyiko ābādho.**“Yes, I do.*";
P_HTM[5463]="*Appekadā maṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā parivāretvā ṭhitā honti:**Sometimes my friends and colleagues, relatives and family members surround me, thinking:*";
P_HTM[5464]="*‘idāni rājā korabyo kālaṃ karissati, idāni rājā korabyo kālaṃ karissatī’”ti.**‘Now the king will die! Now the king will die!’”*";
P_HTM[5465]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5466]="*labhasi tvaṃ te mittāmacce ñātisālohite:**Can you get your friends and colleagues, relatives and family members to help:*";
P_HTM[5467]="*‘āyantu me bhonto mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā, sabbeva santā imaṃ vedanaṃ saṃvibhajatha, yathāhaṃ lahukatarikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyeyyan’ti—**‘Please, my dear friends and colleagues, relatives and family members, all of you here share my pain so that I may feel less pain.’*";
P_HTM[5468]="*udāhu tvaṃyeva taṃ vedanaṃ vediyasī”ti?**Or must you alone feel that pain?”*";
P_HTM[5469]="*“Nāhaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, labhāmi te mittāmacce ñātisālohite:**“I can’t get my friends to share my pain.*";
P_HTM[5470]="*‘āyantu me bhonto mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā, sabbeva santā imaṃ vedanaṃ saṃvibhajatha, yathāhaṃ lahukatarikaṃ vedanaṃ vediyeyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5471]="*Atha kho ahameva taṃ vedanaṃ vediyāmī”ti.**Rather, I alone must feel it.”*";
P_HTM[5472]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“This is what the Buddha was referring to when he said:*";
P_HTM[5473]="*‘atāṇo loko anabhissaro’ti,**‘The world has no shelter and no savior.’”*";
P_HTM[5474]="*yamahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5475]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, abbhutaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla.**“It’s incredible, Master Raṭṭhapāla, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[5476]="*Yāva subhāsitaṃ cidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena:**how well said this was by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5477]="*‘atāṇo loko anabhissaro’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5478]="*Atāṇo hi, bho raṭṭhapāla, loko anabhissaro. (2)**For the world indeed has no shelter and no savior.*";
P_HTM[5479]="*Saṃvijjati kho, bho raṭṭhapāla, imasmiṃ rājakule pahūtaṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇaṃ bhūmigatañca vehāsagatañca.**In this royal court you can find abundant gold coin and bullion stored in dungeons and towers. Yet you said:*";
P_HTM[5480]="*‘Assako loko, sabbaṃ pahāya gamanīyan’ti—**‘The world has no owner—you must leave it all behind and pass on.’*";
P_HTM[5481]="*bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo āha.* **";
P_HTM[5482]="*Imassa pana, bho raṭṭhapāla, bhāsitassa kathaṃ attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**How should I see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[5483]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**‘What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5484]="*yathā tvaṃ etarahi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāresi, lacchasi tvaṃ paratthāpi:**These days you amuse yourself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation. But is there any way to ensure that in the next life*";
P_HTM[5485]="*‘evamevāhaṃ imeheva pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāremī’ti, udāhu aññe imaṃ bhogaṃ paṭipajjissanti, tvaṃ pana yathākammaṃ gamissasī”ti?**you will continue to amuse yourself in the same way, supplied and provided with the same five kinds of sensual stimulation? Or will others make use of this property, while you pass on according to your deeds?”*";
P_HTM[5486]="*“Yathāhaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, etarahi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāremi, nāhaṃ lacchāmi paratthāpi:**“There’s no way to ensure that I will continue to amuse myself in the same way.*";
P_HTM[5487]="*‘evameva imeheva pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāremī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5488]="*Atha kho aññe imaṃ bhogaṃ paṭipajjissanti; ahaṃ pana yathākammaṃ gamissāmī”ti.**Rather, others will take over this property, while I pass on according to my deeds.”*";
P_HTM[5489]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“This is what the Buddha was referring to when he said:*";
P_HTM[5490]="*‘assako loko, sabbaṃ pahāya gamanīyan’ti,**‘The world has no owner—you must leave it all behind and pass on.’”*";
P_HTM[5491]="*yamahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5492]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, abbhutaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla.**“It’s incredible, Master Raṭṭhapāla, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[5493]="*Yāva subhāsitaṃ cidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena:**how well said this was by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5494]="*‘assako loko, sabbaṃ pahāya gamanīyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5495]="*Assako hi, bho raṭṭhapāla, loko sabbaṃ pahāya gamanīyaṃ. (3)**For the world indeed has no owner—you must leave it all behind and pass on.*";
P_HTM[5496]="*‘Ūno loko atitto taṇhādāso’ti—**You also said this: ‘The world is wanting, insatiable, the slave of craving.’*";
P_HTM[5497]="*bhavaṃ raṭṭhapālo āha.* **";
P_HTM[5498]="*Imassa, bho raṭṭhapāla, bhāsitassa kathaṃ attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**How should I see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[5499]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5500]="*phītaṃ kuruṃ ajjhāvasasī”ti?**Do you dwell in the prosperous land of Kuru?”*";
P_HTM[5501]="*“Evaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, phītaṃ kuruṃ ajjhāvasāmī”ti.**“Indeed I do.”*";
P_HTM[5502]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5503]="*idha puriso āgaccheyya puratthimāya disāya saddhāyiko paccayiko.**Suppose a trustworthy and reliable man were to come from the east.*";
P_HTM[5504]="*So taṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya:**He’d approach you and say:*";
P_HTM[5505]="*‘yagghe, mahārāja, jāneyyāsi, ahaṃ āgacchāmi puratthimāya disāya?**‘Please sir, you should know this. I come from the east.*";
P_HTM[5506]="*Tatthaddasaṃ mahantaṃ janapadaṃ iddhañceva phītañca bahujanaṃ ākiṇṇamanussaṃ.**There I saw a large country that is successful and prosperous and full of people.*";
P_HTM[5507]="*Bahū tattha hatthikāyā assakāyā rathakāyā pattikāyā;**They have many divisions of elephants, cavalry, chariots, and infantry.*";
P_HTM[5508]="*bahu tattha dhanadhaññaṃ;**And there’s plenty of money and grain,*";
P_HTM[5509]="*bahu tattha hiraññasuvaṇṇaṃ akatañceva katañca;**plenty of gold coins and bullion, both worked and unworked,*";
P_HTM[5510]="*bahu tattha itthipariggaho.**and plenty of women for the taking.*";
P_HTM[5511]="*Sakkā ca tāvatakeneva balamattena abhivijinituṃ.**With your current forces you can conquer it.*";
P_HTM[5512]="*Abhivijina, mahārājā’ti, kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti?**Conquer it, great king!’ What would you do?”*";
P_HTM[5513]="*“Tampi mayaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, abhivijiya ajjhāvaseyyāmā”ti.**“I would conquer it and dwell there.”*";
P_HTM[5514]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5515]="*idha puriso āgaccheyya pacchimāya disāya …**Suppose a trustworthy and reliable man were to come from the west,*";
P_HTM[5516]="*uttarāya disāya …**north,*";
P_HTM[5517]="*dakkhiṇāya disāya …**south,*";
P_HTM[5518]="*parasamuddato saddhāyiko paccayiko.**or from over the ocean.*";
P_HTM[5519]="*So taṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya:**He’d approach you and say the same thing.*";
P_HTM[5520]="*‘yagghe, mahārāja, jāneyyāsi, ahaṃ āgacchāmi parasamuddato?* **";
P_HTM[5521]="*Tatthaddasaṃ mahantaṃ janapadaṃ iddhañceva phītañca bahujanaṃ ākiṇṇamanussaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5522]="*Bahū tattha hatthikāyā assakāyā rathakāyā pattikāyā;* **";
P_HTM[5523]="*bahu tattha dhanadhaññaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5524]="*bahu tattha hiraññasuvaṇṇaṃ akatañceva katañca;* **";
P_HTM[5525]="*bahu tattha itthipariggaho.* **";
P_HTM[5526]="*Sakkā ca tāvatakeneva balamattena abhivijinituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5527]="*Abhivijina, mahārājā’ti, kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti?**What would you do?”*";
P_HTM[5528]="*“Tampi mayaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, abhivijiya ajjhāvaseyyāmā”ti.**“I would conquer it and dwell there.”*";
P_HTM[5529]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“This is what the Buddha was referring to when he said:*";
P_HTM[5530]="*‘ūno loko atitto taṇhādāso’ti,**‘The world is wanting, insatiable, the slave of craving.’*";
P_HTM[5531]="*yamahaṃ ñatvā ca disvā ca sutvā ca agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito”ti.**And it was after knowing and seeing and hearing this that I went forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[5532]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla, abbhutaṃ, bho raṭṭhapāla.**“It’s incredible, Master Raṭṭhapāla, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[5533]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena:**how well said this was by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5534]="*‘ūno loko atitto taṇhādāso’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5535]="*Ūno hi, bho raṭṭhapāla, loko atitto taṇhādāso”ti.**For the world is indeed wanting, insatiable, the slave of craving.”*";
P_HTM[5536]="*Idamavoca āyasmā raṭṭhapālo.**This is what Venerable Raṭṭhapāla said.*";
P_HTM[5537]="*Idaṃ vatvā athāparaṃ etadavoca:**Then he went on to say:*";
P_HTM[5538]="*“Passāmi loke sadhane manusse,**“I see rich people in the world who,*";
P_HTM[5539]="*Laddhāna vittaṃ na dadanti mohā;**because of delusion, give not the wealth they’ve earned.*";
P_HTM[5540]="*Luddhā dhanaṃ sannicayaṃ karonti,**Greedily, they hoard their riches,*";
P_HTM[5541]="*Bhiyyova kāme abhipatthayanti.**yearning for ever more sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[5542]="*Rājā pasayhā pathaviṃ vijitvā,**A king who conquered the earth by force,*";
P_HTM[5543]="*Sasāgarantaṃ mahimāvasanto;**ruling the land from sea to sea,*";
P_HTM[5544]="*Oraṃ samuddassa atittarūpo,**unsatisfied with the near shore of the ocean,*";
P_HTM[5545]="*Pāraṃ samuddassapi patthayetha.**would still yearn for the further shore.*";
P_HTM[5546]="*Rājā ca aññe ca bahū manussā,**Not just the king, but others too,*";
P_HTM[5547]="*Avītataṇhā maraṇaṃ upenti;**reach death not rid of craving.*";
P_HTM[5548]="*Ūnāva hutvāna jahanti dehaṃ,**They leave the body still wanting,*";
P_HTM[5549]="*Kāmehi lokamhi na hatthi titti.**for in this world sensual pleasures never satisfy.*";
P_HTM[5550]="*Kandanti naṃ ñātī pakiriya kese,**Relatives lament, their hair disheveled,*";
P_HTM[5551]="*Ahovatā no amarāti cāhu;**saying ‘Ah! Alas! They’re not immortal!’*";
P_HTM[5552]="*Vatthena naṃ pārutaṃ nīharitvā,**They take out the body wrapped in a shroud,*";
P_HTM[5553]="*Citaṃ samādāya tatoḍahanti.**heap up a pyre, and burn it there.*";
P_HTM[5554]="*So ḍayhati sūlehi tujjamāno,**It’s poked with stakes while being burnt,*";
P_HTM[5555]="*Ekena vatthena pahāya bhoge;**in just a single cloth, all wealth gone.*";
P_HTM[5556]="*Na mīyamānassa bhavanti tāṇā,**Relatives, friends, and companions*";
P_HTM[5557]="*Ñātīdha mittā atha vā sahāyā.**can’t help you when you’re dying.*";
P_HTM[5558]="*Dāyādakā tassa dhanaṃ haranti,**Heirs take your riches,*";
P_HTM[5559]="*Satto pana gacchati yena kammaṃ;**while beings fare on according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[5560]="*Na mīyamānaṃ dhanamanveti kiñci,**Riches don’t follow you when you die;*";
P_HTM[5561]="*Puttā ca dārā ca dhanañca raṭṭhaṃ.**nor do children, wife, wealth, nor kingdom.*";
P_HTM[5562]="*Na dīghamāyuṃ labhate dhanena,**Longevity isn’t gained by riches,*";
P_HTM[5563]="*Na cāpi vittena jaraṃ vihanti;**nor does wealth banish old age;*";
P_HTM[5564]="*Appaṃ hidaṃ jīvitamāhu dhīrā,**for the wise say this life is short,*";
P_HTM[5565]="*Asassataṃ vippariṇāmadhammaṃ.**it’s perishable and not eternal.*";
P_HTM[5566]="*Aḍḍhā daliddā ca phusanti phassaṃ,**The rich and the poor feel its touch;*";
P_HTM[5567]="*Bālo ca dhīro ca tatheva phuṭṭho;**the fool and the wise feel it too.*";
P_HTM[5568]="*Bālo ca bālyā vadhitova seti,**But the fool lies stricken by their own folly,*";
P_HTM[5569]="*Dhīro ca na vedhati phassaphuṭṭho.**while the wise don’t tremble at the touch.*";
P_HTM[5570]="*Tasmā hi paññāva dhanena seyyo,**Therefore wisdom’s much better than wealth,*";
P_HTM[5571]="*Yāya vosānamidhādhigacchati;**since by wisdom you reach consummation in this life.*";
P_HTM[5572]="*Abyositattā hi bhavābhavesu,**But if because of delusion you don’t reach consummation,*";
P_HTM[5573]="*Pāpāni kammāni karonti mohā.**you’ll do evil deeds in life after life.*";
P_HTM[5574]="*Upeti gabbhañca parañca lokaṃ,**One who enters a womb and the world beyond,*";
P_HTM[5575]="*Saṃsāramāpajja paramparāya;**will transmigrate from one life to the next.*";
P_HTM[5576]="*Tassappapañño abhisaddahanto,**While someone of little wisdom, placing faith in them,*";
P_HTM[5577]="*Upeti gabbhañca parañca lokaṃ.**also enters a womb and the world beyond.*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Coro yathā sandhimukhe gahito,**As a bandit caught in the door*";
P_HTM[5579]="*Sakammunā haññati pāpadhammo;**is punished for his own bad deeds;*";
P_HTM[5580]="*Evaṃ pajā pecca paramhi loke,**so after departing, in the world beyond,*";
P_HTM[5581]="*Sakammunā haññati pāpadhammo.**people are punished for their own bad deeds.*";
P_HTM[5582]="*Kāmāhi citrā madhurā manoramā,**Sensual pleasures are diverse, sweet, delightful;*";
P_HTM[5583]="*Virūparūpena mathenti cittaṃ;**appearing in disguise they disturb the mind.*";
P_HTM[5584]="*Ādīnavaṃ kāmaguṇesu disvā,**Seeing danger in the many kinds of sensual stimulation,*";
P_HTM[5585]="*Tasmā ahaṃ pabbajitomhi rāja.**I went forth, O King.*";
P_HTM[5586]="*Dumapphalāneva patanti māṇavā,**As fruit falls from a tree, so people fall,*";
P_HTM[5587]="*Daharā ca vuḍḍhā ca sarīrabhedā;**young and old, when the body breaks up.*";
P_HTM[5588]="*Etampi disvā pabbajitomhi rāja,**Seeing this, too, I went forth, O King;*";
P_HTM[5589]="*Apaṇṇakaṃ sāmaññameva seyyo”ti.**the ascetic life is guaranteed to be better.”*";
P_HTM[5590]="*Raṭṭhapālasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5591]="*83. Maghadevasutta**About King Makhādeva*";
P_HTM[5592]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5593]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā mithilāyaṃ viharati maghadevaambavane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Mithilā in the Makhādeva Mango Grove.*";
P_HTM[5594]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi.**Then the Buddha smiled at a certain spot.*";
P_HTM[5595]="*Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:**Then Venerable Ānanda thought,*";
P_HTM[5596]="*“ko nu kho hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya?**“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled?*";
P_HTM[5597]="*Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti.**Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.”*";
P_HTM[5598]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**So Ānanda got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said,*";
P_HTM[5599]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya?**“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled?*";
P_HTM[5600]="*Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti.**Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.”*";
P_HTM[5601]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, imissāyeva mithilāyaṃ rājā ahosi maghadevo nāma dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;**“Once upon a time, Ānanda, right here in Mithilā there was a just and principled king named Makhādeva, a great king who stood by his duty.*";
P_HTM[5602]="*dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;**He justly treated brahmins and householders, and people of town and country.*";
P_HTM[5603]="*uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassa.**And he observed the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of the fortnight.*";
P_HTM[5604]="*Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena kappakaṃ āmantesi:**Then, after many years, many hundred years, many thousand years had passed, King Makhādeva addressed his barber,*";
P_HTM[5605]="*‘yadā me, samma kappaka, passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha me āroceyyāsī’ti.**‘My dear barber, when you see grey hairs growing on my head, please tell me.’*";
P_HTM[5606]="*‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa paccassosi.**‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the barber.*";
P_HTM[5607]="*Addasā kho, ānanda, kappako bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena rañño maghadevassa sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni.**When many thousands of years had passed, the barber saw grey hairs growing on the king’s head.*";
P_HTM[5608]="*Disvāna rājānaṃ maghadevaṃ etadavoca:**He said to the king,*";
P_HTM[5609]="*‘pātubhūtā kho devassa devadūtā, dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātānī’ti.**‘The messengers of the gods have shown themselves to you. Grey hairs can be seen growing on your head.’*";
P_HTM[5610]="*‘Tena hi, samma kappaka, tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā mama añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpehī’ti.**‘Well then, my dear barber, carefully pull them out with tweezers and place them in my cupped hands.’*";
P_HTM[5611]="*‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa paṭissutvā tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā rañño maghadevassa añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpesi.**‘Yes, Your Majesty,’ replied the barber, and he did as the king said.*";
P_HTM[5612]="*Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca:**The king gave the barber a prize village, then summoned the crown prince and said,*";
P_HTM[5613]="*‘pātubhūtā kho me, tāta kumāra, devadūtā;**‘Dear prince, the messengers of the gods have shown themselves to me.*";
P_HTM[5614]="*dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni;**Grey hairs can be seen growing on my head.*";
P_HTM[5615]="*bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā;**I have enjoyed human pleasures.*";
P_HTM[5616]="*samayo dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ.**Now it is time to seek heavenly pleasures.*";
P_HTM[5617]="*Ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ rajjaṃ paṭipajja.**Come, dear prince, rule the realm.*";
P_HTM[5618]="*Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmi.**I shall shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5619]="*Tena hi, tāta kumāra, yadā tvampi passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyāsi.**For dear prince, you too will one day see grey hairs growing on your head. When this happens, after giving a prize village to the barber and carefully instructing the crown prince in kingship, you should shave off your hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5620]="*Yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ antimapuriso ahosi.**Keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my final man.*";
P_HTM[5621]="*Yasmiṃ kho, tāta kumāra, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti.**Whatever generation is current when such good practice is broken, he is their final man.*";
P_HTM[5622]="*Taṃ tāhaṃ, tāta kumāra, evaṃ vadāmi—**Therefore I say to you,*";
P_HTM[5623]="*yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ antimapuriso ahosī’ti.**“Keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my final man.”’*";
P_HTM[5624]="*Atha kho, ānanda, rājā maghadevo kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji.**And so, after giving a prize village to the barber and carefully instructing the crown prince in kingship, King Makhādeva shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness here in this mango grove.*";
P_HTM[5625]="*So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi.**He meditated spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, he spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[5626]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …**He meditated spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[5627]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā …**rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[5628]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi.**equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, he spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[5629]="*Rājā kho panānanda, maghadevo caturāsītivassasahassāni kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷi, caturāsītivassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito brahmacariyamacari.**For 84,000 years King Makhādeva played games as a child, for 84,000 years he acted as viceroy, for 84,000 years he ruled the realm, and for 84,000 years he led the spiritual life after going forth here in this mango grove.*";
P_HTM[5630]="*So cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpago ahosi.**Having developed these four Brahmā meditations, when his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[5631]="*Atha kho rañño, ānanda, maghadevassa putto bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena kappakaṃ āmantesi:**Then, after many years, many hundred years, many thousand years had passed, King Makhādeva’s son addressed his barber,*";
P_HTM[5632]="*‘yadā me, samma kappaka, passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha kho āroceyyāsī’ti.**‘My dear barber, when you see grey hairs growing on my head, please tell me.’*";
P_HTM[5633]="*‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa puttassa paccassosi.**And all unfolded as in the case of his father.*";
P_HTM[5634]="*Addasā kho, ānanda, kappako bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena rañño maghadevassa puttassa sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni.* **";
P_HTM[5635]="*Disvāna rañño maghadevassa puttaṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[5636]="*‘pātubhūtā kho devassa devadūtā;* **";
P_HTM[5637]="*dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātānī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5638]="*‘Tena hi, samma kappaka, tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā mama añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpehī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5639]="*‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako rañño maghadevassa puttassa paṭissutvā tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā rañño maghadevassa puttassa añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpesi.* **";
P_HTM[5640]="*Atha kho, ānanda, rañño maghadevassa putto kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[5641]="*‘pātubhūtā kho me, tāta kumāra, devadūtā;* **";
P_HTM[5642]="*dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni;* **";
P_HTM[5643]="*bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā;* **";
P_HTM[5644]="*samayo dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5645]="*Ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ rajjaṃ paṭipajja.* **";
P_HTM[5646]="*Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5647]="*Tena hi, tāta kumāra, yadā tvampi passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyāsi.* **";
P_HTM[5648]="*Yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ antimapuriso ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[5649]="*Yasmiṃ kho, tāta kumāra, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5650]="*Taṃ tāhaṃ, tāta kumāra, evaṃ vadāmi—* **";
P_HTM[5651]="*yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ antimapuriso ahosī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5652]="*Atha kho, ānanda, rañño maghadevassa putto kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji.* **";
P_HTM[5653]="*So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi.* **";
P_HTM[5654]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …* **";
P_HTM[5655]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā …* **";
P_HTM[5656]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi.* **";
P_HTM[5657]="*Rañño kho panānanda, maghadevassa putto caturāsītivassasahassāni kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷi, caturāsītivassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito brahmacariyamacari.* **";
P_HTM[5658]="*So cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpago ahosi.**And having developed the four Brahmā meditations, when his body broke up, after death, Makhādeva’s son was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[5659]="*Rañño kho panānanda, maghadevassa puttapaputtakā tassa paramparā caturāsītirājasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃsu.**And a lineage of 84,000 kings, sons of sons of King Makhādeva, shaved off their hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness here in this mango grove.*";
P_HTM[5660]="*Te mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihariṃsu, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihariṃsu.**They meditated spreading a heart full of love …*";
P_HTM[5661]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …**compassion …*";
P_HTM[5662]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā …**rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[5663]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihariṃsu, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihariṃsu.**equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[5664]="*Caturāsītivassasahassāni kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷiṃsu, caturāsītivassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresuṃ, caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ kāresuṃ, caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā brahmacariyamacariṃsu.**For 84,000 years they played games as a child, for 84,000 years they acted as viceroy, for 84,000 years they ruled the realm, and for 84,000 years they led the spiritual life after going forth here in this mango grove.*";
P_HTM[5665]="*Te cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpagā ahesuṃ.**And having developed the four Brahmā meditations, when their bodies broke up, after death, they were reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[5666]="*Nimi tesaṃ rājā pacchimako ahosi dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;**Nimi was the last of those kings, a just and principled king, a great king who stood by his duty.*";
P_HTM[5667]="*dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;**He justly treated brahmins and householders, and people of town and country.*";
P_HTM[5668]="*uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassa.**And he observed the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of the fortnight.*";
P_HTM[5669]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:**Once upon a time, Ānanda, while the gods of the Thirty-Three were sitting together in the Hall of Justice, this discussion came up among them:*";
P_HTM[5670]="*‘lābhā vata, bho, videhānaṃ, suladdhaṃ vata, bho, videhānaṃ,**‘The people of Videha are so fortunate, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[5671]="*yesaṃ nimi rājā dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;**to have Nimi as their king. He is a just and principled king, a great king who stands by his duty.*";
P_HTM[5672]="*dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;**He justly treats brahmins and householders, and people of town and country.*";
P_HTM[5673]="*uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassā’ti.**And he observes the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of the fortnight.’*";
P_HTM[5674]="*Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse āmantesi:**Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the gods of the Thirty-Three,*";
P_HTM[5675]="*‘iccheyyātha no tumhe, mārisā, nimiṃ rājānaṃ daṭṭhun’ti?**‘Good sirs, would you like to see King Nimi?’*";
P_HTM[5676]="*‘Icchāma mayaṃ, mārisa, nimiṃ rājānaṃ daṭṭhun’ti.**‘We would.’*";
P_HTM[5677]="*Tena kho pana, ānanda, samayena nimi rājā tadahuposathe pannarase sīsaṃnhāto uposathiko uparipāsādavaragato nisinno hoti.**Now at that time it was the fifteenth day sabbath, and King Nimi had bathed his head and was sitting upstairs in the stilt longhouse to observe the sabbath.*";
P_HTM[5678]="*Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—devesu tāvatiṃsesu antarahito nimissa rañño pamukhe pāturahosi.**Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, Sakka vanished from the Thirty-Three gods and reappeared in front of King Nimi.*";
P_HTM[5679]="*Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo nimiṃ rājānaṃ etadavoca:**He said to the king,*";
P_HTM[5680]="*‘lābhā te, mahārāja, suladdhaṃ te, mahārāja.**‘You’re fortunate, great king, so very fortunate.*";
P_HTM[5681]="*Devā, mahārāja, tāvatiṃsā sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ kittayamānarūpā sannisinnā:**The gods of the Thirty-Three were sitting together in the Hall of Justice, where they spoke very highly of you.*";
P_HTM[5682]="*“lābhā vata, bho, videhānaṃ, suladdhaṃ vata, bho, videhānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5683]="*yesaṃ nimi rājā dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;* **";
P_HTM[5684]="*dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;* **";
P_HTM[5685]="*uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5686]="*Devā te, mahārāja, tāvatiṃsā dassanakāmā.**They would like to see you.*";
P_HTM[5687]="*Tassa te ahaṃ, mahārāja, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ pahiṇissāmi;**I shall send a chariot harnessed with a thousand thoroughbreds for you, great king.*";
P_HTM[5688]="*abhiruheyyāsi, mahārāja, dibbaṃ yānaṃ avikampamāno’ti.**Mount the heavenly chariot, great king! Do not waver.’*";
P_HTM[5689]="*Adhivāsesi kho, ānanda, nimi rājā tuṇhībhāvena.**King Nimi consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[5690]="*Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo nimissa rañño adhivāsanaṃ viditvā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—nimissa rañño pamukhe antarahito devesu tāvatiṃsesu pāturahosi.**Then, knowing that the king had consented, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, Sakka vanished from King Nimi and reappeared among the Thirty-Three gods.*";
P_HTM[5691]="*Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo mātaliṃ saṅgāhakaṃ āmantesi:**Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his charioteer Mātali,*";
P_HTM[5692]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā nimiṃ rājānaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadehi—**‘Come, dear Mātali, harness the chariot with a thousand thoroughbreds. Then go to King Nimi and say,*";
P_HTM[5693]="*ayaṃ te, mahārāja, sahassayutto ājaññaratho sakkena devānamindena pesito;**“Great king, this chariot has been sent for you by Sakka, lord of gods.*";
P_HTM[5694]="*abhiruheyyāsi, mahārāja, dibbaṃ yānaṃ avikampamāno’ti.**Mount the heavenly chariot, great king! Do not waver.”’*";
P_HTM[5695]="*‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, ānanda, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā nimiṃ rājānaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca:**‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. He did as Sakka asked, and said to the king,*";
P_HTM[5696]="*‘ayaṃ te, mahārāja, sahassayutto ājaññaratho sakkena devānamindena pesito;**‘Great king, this chariot has been sent for you by Sakka, lord of gods.*";
P_HTM[5697]="*abhiruha, mahārāja, dibbaṃ yānaṃ avikampamāno.**Mount the heavenly chariot, great king! Do not waver.*";
P_HTM[5698]="*Api ca, mahārāja, katamena taṃ nemi, yena vā pāpakammā pāpakānaṃ kammānaṃ vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedenti, yena vā kalyāṇakammā kalyāṇakammānaṃ vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti?**But which way should we go—the way of those who experience the result of bad deeds, or the way of those who experience the result of good deeds?’*";
P_HTM[5699]="*‘Ubhayeneva maṃ, mātali, nehī’ti.**‘Take me both ways, Mātali.’*";
P_HTM[5700]="*Sampavesesi kho, ānanda, mātali, saṅgāhako nimiṃ rājānaṃ sudhammaṃ sabhaṃ.**Mātali brought King Nimi to the Hall of Justice.*";
P_HTM[5701]="*Addasā kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo nimiṃ rājānaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Sakka saw King Nimi coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[5702]="*Disvāna nimiṃ rājānaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him:*";
P_HTM[5703]="*‘ehi kho, mahārāja.**‘Come, great king!*";
P_HTM[5704]="*Svāgataṃ, mahārāja.**Welcome, great king!*";
P_HTM[5705]="*Devā te dassanakāmā, mahārāja, tāvatiṃsā sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ kittayamānarūpā sannisinnā:**The gods of the Thirty-Three who wanted to see you were sitting together in the Hall of Justice, where they spoke very highly of you.*";
P_HTM[5706]="*“lābhā vata, bho, videhānaṃ, suladdhaṃ vata, bho, videhānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5707]="*yesaṃ nimi rājā dhammiko dhammarājā dhamme ṭhito mahārājā;* **";
P_HTM[5708]="*dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;* **";
P_HTM[5709]="*uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5710]="*Devā te, mahārāja, tāvatiṃsā dassanakāmā.**The gods of the Thirty-Three would like to see you.*";
P_HTM[5711]="*Abhirama, mahārāja, devesu devānubhāvenā’ti.**Enjoy divine glory among the gods!’*";
P_HTM[5712]="*‘Alaṃ, mārisa, tattheva maṃ mithilaṃ paṭinetu.**‘Enough, good sir. Send me back to Mithila right away.*";
P_HTM[5713]="*Tathāhaṃ dhammaṃ carissāmi brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca;**That way I shall justly treat brahmins and householders, and people of town and country.*";
P_HTM[5714]="*uposathañca upavasāmi cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassā’ti.**And I shall observe the sabbath on the fourteenth, fifteenth, and eighth of the fortnight.’*";
P_HTM[5715]="*Atha kho, ānanda, sakko devānamindo mātaliṃ saṅgāhakaṃ āmantesi:**Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his charioteer Mātali,*";
P_HTM[5716]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā nimiṃ rājānaṃ tattheva mithilaṃ paṭinehī’ti.**‘Come, dear Mātali, harness the chariot with a thousand thoroughbreds and send King Nimi back to Mithila right away.’*";
P_HTM[5717]="*‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, ānanda, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā nimiṃ rājānaṃ tattheva mithilaṃ paṭinesi.**‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali, and did as Sakka asked.*";
P_HTM[5718]="*Tatra sudaṃ, ānanda, nimi rājā dhammaṃ carati brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamesu ceva jānapadesu ca, uposathañca upavasati cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ aṭṭhamiñca pakkhassāti.**And there King Nimi justly treated his people, and observed the sabbath.*";
P_HTM[5719]="*Atha kho, ānanda, nimi rājā bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena kappakaṃ āmantesi:**Then, after many years, many hundred years, many thousand years had passed, King Nimi addressed his barber,*";
P_HTM[5720]="*‘yadā me, samma kappaka, passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha me āroceyyāsī’ti.**‘My dear barber, when you see grey hairs growing on my head, please tell me.’*";
P_HTM[5721]="*‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako nimissa rañño paccassosi.**And all unfolded as before.*";
P_HTM[5722]="*Addasā kho, ānanda, kappako bahūnaṃ vassānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasatānaṃ bahūnaṃ vassasahassānaṃ accayena nimissa rañño sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni.* **";
P_HTM[5723]="*Disvāna nimiṃ rājānaṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[5724]="*‘pātubhūtā kho devassa devadūtā;* **";
P_HTM[5725]="*dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātānī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5726]="*‘Tena hi, samma kappaka, tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā mama añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpehī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5727]="*‘Evaṃ, devā’ti kho, ānanda, kappako nimissa rañño paṭissutvā tāni palitāni sādhukaṃ saṇḍāsena uddharitvā nimissa rañño añjalismiṃ patiṭṭhāpesi.* **";
P_HTM[5728]="*Atha kho, ānanda, nimi rājā kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[5729]="*‘pātubhūtā kho me, tāta kumāra, devadūtā;* **";
P_HTM[5730]="*dissanti sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni;* **";
P_HTM[5731]="*bhuttā kho pana me mānusakā kāmā;* **";
P_HTM[5732]="*samayo dibbe kāme pariyesituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5733]="*Ehi tvaṃ, tāta kumāra, imaṃ rajjaṃ paṭipajja.* **";
P_HTM[5734]="*Ahaṃ pana kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5735]="*Tena hi, tāta kumāra, yadā tvampi passeyyāsi sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni, atha kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyāsi.* **";
P_HTM[5736]="*Yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ antimapuriso ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[5737]="*Yasmiṃ kho, tāta kumāra, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5738]="*Taṃ tāhaṃ, tāta kumāra, evaṃ vadāmi:* **";
P_HTM[5739]="*“yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyāsi, mā kho me tvaṃ antimapuriso ahosī”’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5740]="*Atha kho, ānanda, nimi rājā kappakassa gāmavaraṃ datvā jeṭṭhaputtaṃ kumāraṃ sādhukaṃ rajje samanusāsitvā imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji.* **";
P_HTM[5741]="*So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi.* **";
P_HTM[5742]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …* **";
P_HTM[5743]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā …* **";
P_HTM[5744]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā vihāsi, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā vihāsi.* **";
P_HTM[5745]="*Nimi kho panānanda, rājā caturāsītivassasahassāni kumārakīḷitaṃ kīḷi, caturāsītivassasahassāni oparajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni rajjaṃ kāresi, caturāsītivassasahassāni imasmiṃyeva maghadevaambavane agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito brahmacariyamacari.* **";
P_HTM[5746]="*So cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmalokūpago ahosi.**And having developed the four Brahmā meditations, when his body broke up, after death, King Nimi was reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[5747]="*Nimissa kho panānanda, rañño kaḷārajanako nāma putto ahosi.**But King Nimi had a son named Kaḷārajanaka.*";
P_HTM[5748]="*Na so agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbaji.**He didn’t go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5749]="*So taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ samucchindi.**He broke that good practice.*";
P_HTM[5750]="*So tesaṃ antimapuriso ahosi.**He was their final man.*";
P_HTM[5751]="*Siyā kho pana te, ānanda, evamassa:**Ānanda, you might think,*";
P_HTM[5752]="*‘añño nūna tena samayena rājā maghadevo ahosi, yena taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitan’ti.**‘Surely King Makhādeva, by whom that good practice was founded, must have been someone else at that time?’*";
P_HTM[5753]="*Na kho panetaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ.**But you should not see it like this.*";
P_HTM[5754]="*Ahaṃ tena samayena rājā maghadevo ahosiṃ.**I myself was King Makhādeva at that time.*";
P_HTM[5755]="*Ahaṃ taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihiniṃ, mayā taṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ;**I was the one who founded that good practice,*";
P_HTM[5756]="*pacchimā janatā anuppavattesi.**which was kept up by those who came after.*";
P_HTM[5757]="*Taṃ kho panānanda, kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva brahmalokūpapattiyā.**But that good practice doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[5758]="*Idaṃ kho panānanda, etarahi mayā kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati.**But now I have founded a good practice that does lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[5759]="*Katamañcānanda, etarahi mayā kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati?**And what is that good practice?*";
P_HTM[5760]="*Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—**It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:*";
P_HTM[5761]="*sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi.**right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.*";
P_HTM[5762]="*Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etarahi mayā kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati.**This is the good practice I have now founded that leads to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[5763]="*Taṃ vo ahaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ vadāmi:**Ānanda, I say to you:*";
P_HTM[5764]="*‘yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyātha, mā kho me tumhe antimapurisā ahuvattha’.**‘You all should keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my final men.’*";
P_HTM[5765]="*Yasmiṃ kho, ānanda, purisayuge vattamāne evarūpassa kalyāṇassa vattassa samucchedo hoti so tesaṃ antimapuriso hoti.**Whatever generation is current when such good practice is broken, he is their final man.*";
P_HTM[5766]="*Taṃ vo ahaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ vadāmi:**Ānanda, I say to you:*";
P_HTM[5767]="*‘yena me idaṃ kalyāṇaṃ vattaṃ nihitaṃ anuppavatteyyātha, mā kho me tumhe antimapurisā ahuvatthā’”ti.**‘You all should keep up this good practice that I have founded. Do not be my final men.’”*";
P_HTM[5768]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5769]="*Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5770]="*Maghadevasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5771]="*84. Madhurasutta**At Madhurā*";
P_HTM[5772]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5773]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahākaccāno madhurāyaṃ viharati gundāvane.**At one time Venerable Mahākaccāna was staying near Madhurā, in Gunda’s Grove.*";
P_HTM[5774]="*Assosi kho rājā mādhuro avantiputto:**King Avantiputta of Madhurā heard,*";
P_HTM[5775]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, kaccāno madhurāyaṃ viharati gundāvane.**“It seems the ascetic Kaccāna is staying near Madhurā, in Gunda’s Grove.*";
P_HTM[5776]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ kaccānaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[5777]="*‘paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī bahussuto cittakathī kalyāṇapaṭibhāno vuddho ceva arahā ca’.**‘He is astute, competent, clever, learned, a brilliant speaker, eloquent, mature, a perfected one.’*";
P_HTM[5778]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[5779]="*Atha kho rājā mādhuro avantiputto bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhadraṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi madhurāya niyyāsi mahaccarājānubhāvena āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ dassanāya.**And then King Avantiputta had the finest carriages harnessed. He mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out in full royal pomp from Madhurā to see Mahākaccāna.*";
P_HTM[5780]="*Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahākaccānena saddhiṃ sammodi. Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā mādhuro avantiputto āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavoca:**He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached Mahākaccāna on foot. They exchanged greetings, and when the greetings and polite conversation were over, the king sat down to one side and said to Mahākaccāna:*";
P_HTM[5781]="*“brāhmaṇā, bho kaccāna, evamāhaṃsu:**“Master Kaccāna, the brahmins say:*";
P_HTM[5782]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo;**‘Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior.*";
P_HTM[5783]="*brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo;**Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark.*";
P_HTM[5784]="*brāhmaṇāva sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā;**Only brahmins are purified, not others.*";
P_HTM[5785]="*brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’ti.**Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.’*";
P_HTM[5786]="*Idha bhavaṃ kaccāno kimakkhāyī”ti?**What does Master Kaccāna have to say about this?”*";
P_HTM[5787]="*“Ghosoyeva kho eso, mahārāja, lokasmiṃ:**“Great king, that’s just propaganda.*";
P_HTM[5788]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo;* **";
P_HTM[5789]="*brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo;* **";
P_HTM[5790]="*brāhmaṇāva sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā;* **";
P_HTM[5791]="*brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5792]="*Tadamināpetaṃ, mahārāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā ghosoyeveso lokasmiṃ:**And here’s a way to understand that it’s just propaganda.*";
P_HTM[5793]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5794]="*brahmadāyādā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5795]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5796]="*khattiyassa cepi ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā khattiyopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī …**Suppose an aristocrat prospers in money, grain, silver, or gold. Wouldn’t there be aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers who would get up before him and go to bed after him, and be obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely?”*";
P_HTM[5797]="*brāhmaṇopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5798]="*vessopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5799]="*suddopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5800]="*“Khattiyassa cepi, bho kaccāna, ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā khattiyopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī …**“There would, Master Kaccāna.”*";
P_HTM[5801]="*brāhmaṇopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5802]="*vessopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5803]="*suddopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5804]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5805]="*brāhmaṇassa cepi ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā brāhmaṇopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī …**Suppose a brahmin …*";
P_HTM[5806]="*vessopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5807]="*suddopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5808]="*khattiyopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5809]="*“Brāhmaṇassa cepi, bho kaccāna, ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā brāhmaṇopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī …* **";
P_HTM[5810]="*vessopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5811]="*suddopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5812]="*khattiyopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5813]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, vessassa cepi ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā vessopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī …**a merchant …*";
P_HTM[5814]="*suddopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5815]="*khattiyopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5816]="*brāhmaṇopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5817]="*“Vessassa cepi, bho kaccāna, ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā vessopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī …* **";
P_HTM[5818]="*suddopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5819]="*khattiyopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5820]="*brāhmaṇopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5821]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, suddassa cepi ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā suddopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī …**a worker prospers in money, grain, silver, or gold. Wouldn’t there be workers, aristocrats, brahmins, and merchants who would get up before him and go to bed after him, and be obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely?”*";
P_HTM[5822]="*khattiyopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5823]="*brāhmaṇopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5824]="*vessopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5825]="*“Suddassa cepi, bho kaccāna, ijjheyya dhanena vā dhaññena vā rajatena vā jātarūpena vā suddopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādīti …**“There would, Master Kaccāna.”*";
P_HTM[5826]="*khattiyopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5827]="*brāhmaṇopissāssa …* **";
P_HTM[5828]="*vessopissāssa pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5829]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5830]="*yadi evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti no vā?**If this is so, are the four castes equal or not?*";
P_HTM[5831]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5832]="*“Addhā kho, bho kaccāna, evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti.**“Certainly, Master Kaccāna, in this case these four castes are equal.*";
P_HTM[5833]="*Nesaṃ ettha kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ samanupassāmī”ti.**I can’t see any difference between them.”*";
P_HTM[5834]="*“Imināpi kho etaṃ, mahārāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā ghosoyeveso lokasmiṃ:**“And here’s another way to understand that the claims of the brahmins are just propaganda.*";
P_HTM[5835]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5836]="*brahmadāyādā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5837]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5838]="*idhassa khattiyo pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya no vā?**Take an aristocrat who kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct; uses speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and is covetous, malicious, and has wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, would they be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell, or not?*";
P_HTM[5839]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5840]="*“Khattiyopi hi, bho kaccāna, pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya.**“Such an aristocrat would be reborn in a bad place.*";
P_HTM[5841]="*Evaṃ me ettha hoti, evañca pana me etaṃ arahataṃ sutan”ti.**That’s what I think, but I’ve also heard it from the perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[5842]="*“Sādhu sādhu, mahārāja.**“Good, good, great king!*";
P_HTM[5843]="*Sādhu kho te etaṃ, mahārāja, evaṃ hoti, sādhu ca pana te etaṃ arahataṃ sutaṃ.**It’s good that you think so, and it’s good that you’ve heard it from the perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[5844]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5845]="*idhassa brāhmaṇo … pe …**Take a brahmin …*";
P_HTM[5846]="*idhassa vesso … pe …**a merchant …*";
P_HTM[5847]="*idhassa suddo pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī … pe … micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya no vā?**a worker who kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct; uses speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and is covetous, malicious, and has wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, would they be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell, or not?*";
P_HTM[5848]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5849]="*“Suddopi hi, bho kaccāna, pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī … pe … micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya.**“Such a brahmin, merchant, or worker would be reborn in a bad place.*";
P_HTM[5850]="*Evaṃ me ettha hoti, evañca pana me etaṃ arahataṃ sutan”ti.**That’s what I think, but I’ve also heard it from the perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[5851]="*“Sādhu sādhu, mahārāja.**“Good, good, great king!*";
P_HTM[5852]="*Sādhu kho te etaṃ, mahārāja, evaṃ hoti, sādhu ca pana te etaṃ arahataṃ sutaṃ.**It’s good that you think so, and it’s good that you’ve heard it from the perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[5853]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5854]="*yadi evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti no vā?**If this is so, are the four castes equal or not?*";
P_HTM[5855]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5856]="*“Addhā kho, bho kaccāna, evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti.**“Certainly, Master Kaccāna, in this case these four castes are equal.*";
P_HTM[5857]="*Nesaṃ ettha kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ samanupassāmī”ti.**I can’t see any difference between them.”*";
P_HTM[5858]="*“Imināpi kho etaṃ, mahārāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā ghosoyeveso lokasmiṃ:**“And here’s another way to understand that the claims of the brahmins are just propaganda.*";
P_HTM[5859]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe … brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5860]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5861]="*idhassa khattiyo pāṇātipātā paṭivirato, adinnādānā paṭivirato, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato, musāvādā paṭivirato, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato, samphappalāpā paṭivirato, anabhijjhālu abyāpannacitto sammādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya no vā?**Take an aristocrat who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. When their body breaks up, after death, would they be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm, or not?*";
P_HTM[5862]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5863]="*“Khattiyopi hi, bho kaccāna, pāṇātipātā paṭivirato, adinnādānā paṭivirato, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato, musāvādā paṭivirato, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato, samphappalāpā paṭivirato, anabhijjhālu abyāpannacitto sammādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya.**“Such an aristocrat would be reborn in a good place.*";
P_HTM[5864]="*Evaṃ me ettha hoti, evañca pana me etaṃ arahataṃ sutan”ti.**That’s what I think, but I’ve also heard it from the perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[5865]="*“Sādhu sādhu, mahārāja.**“Good, good, great king!*";
P_HTM[5866]="*Sādhu kho te etaṃ, mahārāja, evaṃ hoti, sādhu ca pana te etaṃ arahataṃ sutaṃ.**It’s good that you think so, and it’s good that you’ve heard it from the perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[5867]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5868]="*idhassa brāhmaṇo, idhassa vesso, idhassa suddo pāṇātipātā paṭivirato adinnādānā paṭivirato … pe … sammādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya no vā?**Take a brahmin, merchant, or worker who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. When their body breaks up, after death, would they be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm, or not?*";
P_HTM[5869]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5870]="*“Suddopi hi, bho kaccāna, pāṇātipātā paṭivirato, adinnādānā paṭivirato … pe … sammādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya.**“Such a brahmin, merchant, or worker would be reborn in a good place.*";
P_HTM[5871]="*Evaṃ me ettha hoti, evañca pana me etaṃ arahataṃ sutan”ti.**That’s what I think, but I’ve also heard it from the perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[5872]="*“Sādhu sādhu, mahārāja.**“Good, good, great king!*";
P_HTM[5873]="*Sādhu kho te etaṃ, mahārāja, evaṃ hoti, sādhu ca pana te etaṃ arahataṃ sutaṃ.**It’s good that you think so, and it’s good that you’ve heard it from the perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[5874]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5875]="*yadi evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti no vā?**If this is so, are the four castes equal or not?*";
P_HTM[5876]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5877]="*“Addhā kho, bho kaccāna, evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti.**“Certainly, Master Kaccāna, in this case these four castes are equal.*";
P_HTM[5878]="*Nesaṃ ettha kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ samanupassāmī”ti.**I can’t see any difference between them.”*";
P_HTM[5879]="*“Imināpi kho etaṃ, mahārāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā ghosoyeveso lokasmiṃ:**“And here’s another way to understand that the claims of the brahmins are just propaganda.*";
P_HTM[5880]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe … brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5881]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5882]="*idha khattiyo sandhiṃ vā chindeyya, nillopaṃ vā hareyya, ekāgārikaṃ vā kareyya, paripanthe vā tiṭṭheyya, paradāraṃ vā gaccheyya, tañce te purisā gahetvā dasseyyuṃ:**Take an aristocrat who breaks into houses, plunders wealth, steals from isolated buildings, commits highway robbery, and commits adultery. Suppose your men arrest him and present him to you, saying:*";
P_HTM[5883]="*‘ayaṃ te, deva, coro āgucārī.**‘Your Majesty, this man is a bandit, a criminal.*";
P_HTM[5884]="*Imassa yaṃ icchasi taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti.**Punish him as you will.’*";
P_HTM[5885]="*Kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti?**What would you do to him?”*";
P_HTM[5886]="*“Ghāteyyāma vā, bho kaccāna, jāpeyyāma vā pabbājeyyāma vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kareyyāma.**“I would have him executed, fined, or banished, or dealt with as befits the crime.*";
P_HTM[5887]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5888]="*Yā hissa, bho kaccāna, pubbe ‘khattiyo’ti samaññā sāssa antarahitā; corotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti.**Because he’s lost his former status as an aristocrat, and is just reckoned as a bandit.”*";
P_HTM[5889]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5890]="*idha brāhmaṇo, idha vesso, idha suddo sandhiṃ vā chindeyya, nillopaṃ vā hareyya, ekāgārikaṃ vā kareyya, paripanthe vā tiṭṭheyya, paradāraṃ vā gaccheyya, tañce te purisā gahetvā dasseyyuṃ:**Take a brahmin, merchant, or worker who breaks into houses, plunders wealth, steals from isolated buildings, commits highway robbery, and commits adultery. Suppose your men arrest him and present him to you, saying:*";
P_HTM[5891]="*‘ayaṃ te, deva, coro āgucārī.**‘Your Majesty, this man is a bandit, a criminal.*";
P_HTM[5892]="*Imassa yaṃ icchasi taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti.**Punish him as you will.’*";
P_HTM[5893]="*Kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti?**What would you do to him?”*";
P_HTM[5894]="*“Ghāteyyāma vā, bho kaccāna, jāpeyyāma vā pabbājeyyāma vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kareyyāma.**“I would have him executed, fined, or banished, or dealt with as befits the crime.*";
P_HTM[5895]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5896]="*Yā hissa, bho kaccāna, pubbe ‘suddo’ti samaññā sāssa antarahitā; corotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti.**Because he’s lost his former status as a brahmin, merchant, or worker, and is just reckoned as a bandit.”*";
P_HTM[5897]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5898]="*yadi evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti no vā?**If this is so, are the four castes equal or not?*";
P_HTM[5899]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5900]="*“Addhā kho, bho kaccāna, evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti.**“Certainly, Master Kaccāna, in this case these four castes are equal.*";
P_HTM[5901]="*Nesaṃ ettha kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ samanupassāmī”ti.**I can’t see any difference between them.”*";
P_HTM[5902]="*“Imināpi kho etaṃ, mahārāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā ghosoyeveso lokasmiṃ:**“And here’s another way to understand that the claims of the brahmins are just propaganda.*";
P_HTM[5903]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe … brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5904]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5905]="*idha khattiyo kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito assa virato pāṇātipātā, virato adinnādānā, virato musāvādā, rattūparato, ekabhattiko, brahmacārī, sīlavā, kalyāṇadhammo.**Take an aristocrat who shaves off their hair and beard, dresses in ocher robes, and goes forth from the lay life to homelessness. They refrain from killing living creatures, stealing, and lying. They abstain from eating at night, eat in one part of the day, and are celibate, ethical, and of good character.*";
P_HTM[5906]="*Kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti?**How would you treat them?”*";
P_HTM[5907]="*“Abhivādeyyāma vā, bho kaccāna, paccuṭṭheyyāma vā āsanena vā nimanteyyāma abhinimanteyyāma vā naṃ cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi dhammikaṃ vā assa rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidaheyyāma.**“I would bow to them, rise in their presence, or offer them a seat. I’d invite them to accept robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. And I’d arrange for their lawful guarding and protection.*";
P_HTM[5908]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5909]="*Yā hissa, bho kaccāna, pubbe ‘khattiyo’ti samaññā sāssa antarahitā; samaṇotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti.**Because they’ve lost their former status as an aristocrat, and are just reckoned as an ascetic.”*";
P_HTM[5910]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5911]="*idha brāhmaṇo, idha vesso, idha suddo kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito assa virato pāṇātipātā, virato adinnādānā virato musāvādā, rattūparato, ekabhattiko, brahmacārī, sīlavā, kalyāṇadhammo.**Take a brahmin, merchant, or worker who shaves off their hair and beard, dresses in ocher robes, and goes forth from the lay life to homelessness. They refrain from killing living creatures, stealing, and lying. They abstain from eating at night, eat in one part of the day, and are celibate, ethical, and of good character.*";
P_HTM[5912]="*Kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti?**How would you treat them?”*";
P_HTM[5913]="*“Abhivādeyyāma vā, bho kaccāna, paccuṭṭheyyāma vā āsanena vā nimanteyyāma abhinimanteyyāma vā naṃ cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi dhammikaṃ vā assa rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidaheyyāma.**“I would bow to them, rise in their presence, or offer them a seat. I’d invite them to accept robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. And I’d arrange for their lawful guarding and protection.*";
P_HTM[5914]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5915]="*Yā hissa, bho kaccāna, pubbe ‘suddo’ti samaññā sāssa antarahitā; samaṇotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti.**Because they’ve lost their former status as a brahmin, merchant, or worker, and are just reckoned as an ascetic.”*";
P_HTM[5916]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[5917]="*yadi evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti no vā?**If this is so, are the four castes equal or not?*";
P_HTM[5918]="*Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?**Or how do you see this?”*";
P_HTM[5919]="*“Addhā kho, bho kaccāna, evaṃ sante, ime cattāro vaṇṇā samasamā honti.**“Certainly, Master Kaccāna, in this case these four castes are equal.*";
P_HTM[5920]="*Nesaṃ ettha kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ samanupassāmī”ti.**I can’t see any difference between them.”*";
P_HTM[5921]="*“Imināpi kho etaṃ, mahārāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā ghosoyeveso lokasmiṃ:**“This is another way to understand that this is just propaganda:*";
P_HTM[5922]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo;**‘Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior.*";
P_HTM[5923]="*brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo;**Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark.*";
P_HTM[5924]="*brāhmaṇāva sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā;**Only brahmins are purified, not others.*";
P_HTM[5925]="*brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’”ti.**Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.’”*";
P_HTM[5926]="*Evaṃ vutte, rājā mādhuro avantiputto āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, King Avantiputta of Madhurā said to Mahākaccāna,*";
P_HTM[5927]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho kaccāna, abhikkantaṃ, bho kaccāna.**“Excellent, Master Kaccāna! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[5928]="*Seyyathāpi, bho kaccāna, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā kaccānena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Kaccāna has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[5929]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ kaccānaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Kaccāna, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[5930]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ kaccāno dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Kaccāna remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[5931]="*“Mā kho maṃ tvaṃ, mahārāja, saraṇaṃ agamāsi.**“Great king, don’t go for refuge to me.*";
P_HTM[5932]="*Tameva tvaṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gaccha yamahaṃ saraṇaṃ gato”ti.**You should go for refuge to that same Blessed One to whom I have gone for refuge.”*";
P_HTM[5933]="*“Kahaṃ pana, bho kaccāna, etarahi so bhagavā viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti?**“But where is that Blessed One at present, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[5934]="*“Parinibbuto kho, mahārāja, etarahi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti.**“Great king, the Buddha has already become fully extinguished.”*";
P_HTM[5935]="*“Sacepi mayaṃ, bho kaccāna, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ dasasu yojanesu, dasapi mayaṃ yojanāni gaccheyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ.**“Master Kaccāna, if I heard that the Buddha was within ten leagues, or twenty, or even up to a hundred leagues away, I’d go a hundred leagues to see him.*";
P_HTM[5936]="*Sacepi mayaṃ, bho kaccāna, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ vīsatiyā yojanesu, tiṃsāya yojanesu, cattārīsāya yojanesu, paññāsāya yojanesu, paññāsampi mayaṃ yojanāni gaccheyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5937]="*Yojanasate cepi mayaṃ bho kaccāna, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ, yojanasatampi mayaṃ gaccheyyāma taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5938]="*Yato ca, bho kaccāna, parinibbuto so bhagavā, parinibbutampi mayaṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**But since the Buddha has become fully extinguished, I go for refuge to that fully extinguished Buddha, to the teaching, and to the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[5939]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ kaccāno dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Kaccāna remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[5940]="*Madhurasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5941]="*85. Bodhirājakumārasutta**With Prince Bodhi*";
P_HTM[5942]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5943]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood.*";
P_HTM[5944]="*Tena kho pana samayena bodhissa rājakumārassa kokanado nāma pāsādo acirakārito hoti anajjhāvuṭṭho samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā manussabhūtena.**Now at that time a new stilt longhouse named Pink Lotus had recently been constructed for Prince Bodhi. It had not yet been occupied by an ascetic or brahmin or any person at all.*";
P_HTM[5945]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro sañjikāputtaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi:**Then Prince Bodhi addressed the brahmin student Sañjikāputta,*";
P_HTM[5946]="*“ehi tvaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vanda, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha:**“Please, dear Sañjikāputta, go to the Buddha, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Ask him if he is healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[5947]="*‘bodhi, bhante, rājakumāro bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5948]="*Evañca vadehi:**And then ask him whether he*";
P_HTM[5949]="*‘adhivāsetu kira, bhante, bhagavā bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā’”ti.**might accept tomorrow’s meal from me together with the mendicant Saṅgha.”*";
P_HTM[5950]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sañjikāputto māṇavo bodhissa rājakumārassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**“Yes, sir,” Sañjikāputta replied. He did as Prince Bodhi asked, and*";
P_HTM[5951]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sañjikāputto māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[5952]="*“bodhi kho rājakumāro bhoto gotamassa pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati.* **";
P_HTM[5953]="*Evañca vadeti:* **";
P_HTM[5954]="*‘adhivāsetu kira bhavaṃ gotamo bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5955]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**the Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[5956]="*Atha kho sañjikāputto māṇavo bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bodhi rājakumāro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bodhiṃ rājakumāraṃ etadavoca:**Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, Sañjikāputta got up from his seat, went to Prince Bodhi, and said,*";
P_HTM[5957]="*“avocumha bhoto vacanena taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ:**“I gave the ascetic Gotama your message,*";
P_HTM[5958]="*‘bodhi kho rājakumāro bhoto gotamassa pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati.* **";
P_HTM[5959]="*Evañca vadeti—* **";
P_HTM[5960]="*adhivāsetu kira bhavaṃ gotamo bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5961]="*Adhivuṭṭhañca pana samaṇena gotamenā”ti.**and he accepted.”*";
P_HTM[5962]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā, kokanadañca pāsādaṃ odātehi dussehi santharāpetvā yāva pacchimasopānakaḷevarā, sañjikāputtaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi:**And when the night had passed Prince Bodhi had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home. He also had the Pink Lotus longhouse spread with white cloth down to the last step of the staircase. Then he said to Sañjikāputta,*";
P_HTM[5963]="*“ehi tvaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocehi:**“Please, dear Sañjikāputta, go to the Buddha, and announce the time, saying,*";
P_HTM[5964]="*‘kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan’”ti.**‘Sir, it’s time. The meal is ready.’”*";
P_HTM[5965]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sañjikāputto māṇavo bodhissa rājakumārassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocesi:**“Yes, sir,” Sañjikāputta replied, and he did as he was asked.*";
P_HTM[5966]="*“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5967]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena bodhissa rājakumārassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Prince Bodhi’s home.*";
P_HTM[5968]="*Tena kho pana samayena bodhi rājakumāro bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhito hoti bhagavantaṃ āgamayamāno.**Now at that time Prince Bodhi was standing outside the gates waiting for the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5969]="*Addasā kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Seeing the Buddha coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[5970]="*Disvāna paccuggantvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā purakkhatvā yena kokanado pāsādo tenupasaṅkami.**he went out to greet him. After bowing and inviting the Buddha to go first, he approached the Pink Lotus longhouse.*";
P_HTM[5971]="*Atha kho bhagavā pacchimaṃ sopānakaḷevaraṃ nissāya aṭṭhāsi.**But the Buddha stopped by the last step of the staircase.*";
P_HTM[5972]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Prince Bodhi said to him,*";
P_HTM[5973]="*“abhiruhatu, bhante, bhagavā dussāni, abhiruhatu sugato dussāni;**“Sir, let the Blessed One ascend on the cloth! Let the Holy One ascend on the cloth!*";
P_HTM[5974]="*yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**It will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[5975]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi.**But when he said this, the Buddha kept silent.*";
P_HTM[5976]="*Dutiyampi kho … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[5977]="*tatiyampi kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time, Prince Bodhi said to him,*";
P_HTM[5978]="*“abhiruhatu, bhante, bhagavā dussāni, abhiruhatu sugato dussāni;**“Sir, let the Blessed One ascend on the cloth! Let the Holy One ascend on the cloth!*";
P_HTM[5979]="*yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**It will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[5980]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ apalokesi.**Then the Buddha glanced at Venerable Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[5981]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bodhiṃ rājakumāraṃ etadavoca:**So Ānanda said to Prince Bodhi,*";
P_HTM[5982]="*“saṃharatu, rājakumāra, dussāni;**“Fold up the cloth, Prince.*";
P_HTM[5983]="*na bhagavā celapaṭikaṃ akkamissati.**The Buddha will not step upon white cloth.*";
P_HTM[5984]="*Pacchimaṃ janataṃ tathāgato anukampatī”ti.**The Realized One has compassion for future generations.”*";
P_HTM[5985]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro dussāni saṃharāpetvā uparikokanadapāsāde āsanāni paññapesi.**So Prince Bodhi had the cloth folded up and the seats spread out upstairs in the longhouse.*";
P_HTM[5986]="*Atha kho bhagavā kokanadaṃ pāsādaṃ abhiruhitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena.**Then the Buddha ascended the longhouse and sat on the seats spread out together with the Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[5987]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Then Prince Bodhi served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[5988]="*Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Prince Bodhi took a low seat, sat to one side,*";
P_HTM[5989]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5990]="*“mayhaṃ kho, bhante, evaṃ hoti:**“Sir, this is what I think:*";
P_HTM[5991]="*‘na kho sukhena sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ, dukkhena kho sukhaṃ adhigantabban’”ti.**‘Pleasure is not gained through pleasure; pleasure is gained through pain.’”*";
P_HTM[5992]="*“Mayhampi kho, rājakumāra, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi:**“Prince, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I too thought:*";
P_HTM[5993]="*‘na kho sukhena sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ, dukkhena kho sukhaṃ adhigantabban’ti.**‘Pleasure is not gained through pleasure; pleasure is gained through pain.’*";
P_HTM[5994]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, aparena samayena daharova samāno susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃ.**Some time later, while still black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life—though my mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful faces—I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[5995]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**Once I had gone forth I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5996]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso kālāma, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti.**‘Reverend Kālāma, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[5997]="*Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, āḷāro kālāmo maṃ etadavoca:**Āḷāra Kālāma replied,*";
P_HTM[5998]="*‘viharatāyasmā,**‘Stay, venerable.*";
P_HTM[5999]="*tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti.**This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own teacher’s doctrine with their own insight and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[6000]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ.**I quickly memorized that teaching.*";
P_HTM[6001]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi, theravādañca jānāmi passāmīti ca paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca.**So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others.*";
P_HTM[6002]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6003]="*‘na kho āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti;**‘It is not solely by mere faith that Āḷāra Kālāma declares: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”*";
P_HTM[6004]="*addhā āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharatī’ti.**Surely he meditates knowing and seeing this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[6005]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6006]="*‘kittāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend Kālāma, to what extent do you say you’ve realized this teaching with your own insight?’*";
P_HTM[6007]="*Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, āḷāro kālāmo ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi.**When I said this, he declared the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[6008]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6009]="*‘na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;**‘It’s not just Āḷāra Kālāma who has faith,*";
P_HTM[6010]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi vīriyaṃ … pe …**energy,*";
P_HTM[6011]="*sati …**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[6012]="*samādhi …**immersion,*";
P_HTM[6013]="*paññā, mayhampatthi paññā.**and wisdom; I too have these things.*";
P_HTM[6014]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ āḷāro kālāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Āḷāra Kālāma says he has realized with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[6015]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6016]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6017]="*‘ettāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend Kālāma, have you realized this teaching with your own insight up to this point, and declare having achieved it?’*";
P_HTM[6018]="*‘Ettāvatā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemī’ti.**‘I have, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[6019]="*‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti.**‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[6020]="*‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso,**‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[6021]="*ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma.**to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[6022]="*Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi, taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi.**So the teaching that I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it, you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6023]="*Yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi, tamahaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi.**The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6024]="*Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi tamahaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi.**So the teaching that I know, you know, and the teaching you know, I know.*";
P_HTM[6025]="*Iti yādiso ahaṃ, tādiso tuvaṃ; yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso ahaṃ.**I am like you and you are like me.*";
P_HTM[6026]="*Ehi dāni, āvuso, ubhova santā imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharāmā’ti.**Come now, reverend! We should both lead this community together.’*";
P_HTM[6027]="*Iti kho, rājakumāra, āḷāro kālāmo ācariyo me samāno attano antevāsiṃ maṃ samānaṃ attanā samasamaṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi.**And that is how my teacher Āḷāra Kālāma placed me, his student, on the same position as him, and honored me with lofty praise.*";
P_HTM[6028]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6029]="*‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva ākiñcaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti.**‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of nothingness.’*";
P_HTM[6030]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ.**Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed.*";
P_HTM[6031]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6032]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti.**‘Reverend, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[6033]="*Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, udako rāmaputto maṃ etadavoca:**Uddaka replied,*";
P_HTM[6034]="*‘viharatāyasmā,**‘Stay, venerable.*";
P_HTM[6035]="*tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti.**This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own teacher’s doctrine with their own insight and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[6036]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ.**I quickly memorized that teaching.*";
P_HTM[6037]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi, theravādañca jānāmi passāmīti ca paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca.**So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others.*";
P_HTM[6038]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6039]="*‘na kho rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi;**‘It is not solely by mere faith that Rāma declared: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”*";
P_HTM[6040]="*addhā rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ vihāsī’ti.**Surely he meditated knowing and seeing this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[6041]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6042]="*‘kittāvatā no, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend, to what extent did Rāma say he’d realized this teaching with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[6043]="*Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, udako rāmaputto nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi.**When I said this, Uddaka, son of Rāma, declared the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[6044]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6045]="*‘na kho rāmasseva ahosi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;**‘It’s not just Rāma who had faith,*";
P_HTM[6046]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi vīriyaṃ … pe …**energy,*";
P_HTM[6047]="*sati …**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[6048]="*samādhi …**immersion,*";
P_HTM[6049]="*paññā, mayhampatthi paññā.**and wisdom; I too have these things.*";
P_HTM[6050]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Rāma said he had realized with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[6051]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6052]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6053]="*‘ettāvatā no, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend, had Rāma realized this teaching with his own insight up to this point, and declared having achieved it?’*";
P_HTM[6054]="*‘Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti.**‘He had, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[6055]="*‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti.**‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[6056]="*‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso,**‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[6057]="*ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma.**to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[6058]="*Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi.**So the teaching that Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it, you've realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6059]="*Yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi.**The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[6060]="*Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi.**So the teaching that Rāma directly knew, you know, and the teaching you know, Rāma directly knew.*";
P_HTM[6061]="*Iti yādiso rāmo ahosi tādiso tuvaṃ, yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso rāmo ahosi.**Rāma was like you and you are like Rāma.*";
P_HTM[6062]="*Ehi dāni, āvuso, tuvaṃ imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharā’ti.**Come now, reverend! You should lead this community.’*";
P_HTM[6063]="*Iti kho, rājakumāra, udako rāmaputto sabrahmacārī me samāno ācariyaṭṭhāne maṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi.**And that is how my spiritual companion Uddaka, son of Rāma, placed me in the position of a teacher, and honored me with lofty praise.*";
P_HTM[6064]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6065]="*‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti.**‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’*";
P_HTM[6066]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ.**Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed.*";
P_HTM[6067]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno, magadhesu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno, yena uruvelā senānigamo tadavasariṃ.**I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. Traveling stage by stage in the Magadhan lands, I arrived at Senanigama near Uruvelā.*";
P_HTM[6068]="*Tatthaddasaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ bhūmibhāgaṃ, pāsādikañca vanasaṇḍaṃ, nadiñca sandantiṃ setakaṃ supatitthaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ samantā ca gocaragāmaṃ.**There I saw a delightful park, a lovely grove with a flowing river that was clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby was a village to go for alms.*";
P_HTM[6069]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6070]="*‘ramaṇīyo vata bho bhūmibhāgo, pāsādiko ca vanasaṇḍo, nadī ca sandati setakā supatitthā, ramaṇīyā samantā ca gocaragāmo.**‘This park is truly delightful, a lovely grove with a flowing river that’s clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby there’s a village to go for alms.*";
P_HTM[6071]="*Alaṃ vatidaṃ kulaputtassa padhānatthikassa padhānāyā’ti.**This is good enough for a gentleman who wishes to put forth effort in meditation.’*";
P_HTM[6072]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, tattheva nisīdiṃ:**So I sat down right there, thinking,*";
P_HTM[6073]="*‘alamidaṃ padhānāyā’ti.**‘This is good enough for meditation.’*";
P_HTM[6074]="*Apissu maṃ, rājakumāra, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**And then these three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6075]="*Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ udake nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a green, sappy log, and it was lying in water.*";
P_HTM[6076]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[6077]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[6078]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**What do you think, Prince?*";
P_HTM[6079]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ udake nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that green, sappy log lying in water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[6080]="*“No hidaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[6081]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6082]="*Aduñhi, bhante, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ tañca pana udake nikkhittaṃ,**Because it’s a green, sappy log, and it’s lying in the water.*";
P_HTM[6083]="*yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[6084]="*“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi avūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ na suppahīno hoti, na suppaṭippassaddho.**“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who don’t live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. They haven’t internally given up or stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings because of their efforts, they are incapable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[6085]="*Opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.* **";
P_HTM[6086]="*No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.* **";
P_HTM[6087]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, rājakumāra, paṭhamā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**This was the first example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6088]="*Aparāpi kho maṃ, rājakumāra, dutiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**Then a second example occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6089]="*Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a green, sappy log, and it was lying on dry land far from the water.*";
P_HTM[6090]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[6091]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[6092]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**What do you think, Prince?*";
P_HTM[6093]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that green, sappy log on dry land far from water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[6094]="*“No hidaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[6095]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6096]="*Aduñhi, bhante, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ kiñcāpi ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ,**Because it’s still a green, sappy log, despite the fact that it’s lying on dry land far from water.*";
P_HTM[6097]="*yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[6098]="*“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi vūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ na suppahīno hoti, na suppaṭippassaddho.**“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. But they haven’t internally given up or stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings because of their efforts, they are incapable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[6099]="*Opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.* **";
P_HTM[6100]="*No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.* **";
P_HTM[6101]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, rājakumāra, dutiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**This was the second example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6102]="*Aparāpi kho maṃ, rājakumāra, tatiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**Then a third example occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6103]="*Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a dried up, withered log, and it was lying on dry land far from the water.*";
P_HTM[6104]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[6105]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[6106]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**What do you think, Prince?*";
P_HTM[6107]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that dried up, withered log on dry land far from water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[6108]="*“Evaṃ, bhante.**“Yes, sir.*";
P_HTM[6109]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[6110]="*Aduñhi, bhante, sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ, tañca pana ārakā udakā thale nikkhittan”ti.**Because it’s a dried up, withered log, and it’s lying on dry land far from water.”*";
P_HTM[6111]="*“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi vūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ suppahīno hoti suppaṭippassaddho.**“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. And they have internally given up and stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings because of their efforts, they are capable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[6112]="*Opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, bhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.* **";
P_HTM[6113]="*No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, bhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.* **";
P_HTM[6114]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, rājakumāra, tatiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**This was the third example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6115]="*Imā kho maṃ, rājakumāra, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**These are the three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[6116]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6117]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇheyyaṃ abhinippīḷeyyaṃ abhisantāpeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I, with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of my mouth, squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind.’*";
P_HTM[6118]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhāmi abhinippīḷemi abhisantāpemi.**So that’s what I did,*";
P_HTM[6119]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato kacchehi sedā muccanti.**until sweat ran from my armpits.*";
P_HTM[6120]="*Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, balavā puriso dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ sīse vā gahetvā khandhe vā gahetvā abhiniggaṇheyya abhinippīḷeyya abhisantāpeyya;**It was like when a strong man grabs a weaker man by the head or throat or shoulder and squeezes, squashes, and tortures them.*";
P_HTM[6121]="*evameva kho me, rājakumāra, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato kacchehi sedā muccanti.**In the same way, with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of my mouth, I squeezed, squashed, and tortured mind with mind until sweat ran from my armpits.*";
P_HTM[6122]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, rājakumāra, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6123]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6124]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I practice the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6125]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose.*";
P_HTM[6126]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu kaṇṇasotehi vātānaṃ nikkhamantānaṃ adhimatto saddo hoti.**But then winds came out my ears making a loud noise,*";
P_HTM[6127]="*Seyyathāpi nāma kammāragaggariyā dhamamānāya adhimatto saddo hoti;**like the puffing of a blacksmith’s bellows.*";
P_HTM[6128]="*evameva kho me, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu kaṇṇasotehi vātānaṃ nikkhamantānaṃ adhimatto saddo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[6129]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, rājakumāra, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6130]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6131]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6132]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears.*";
P_HTM[6133]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā muddhani ūhananti.**But then strong winds ground my head,*";
P_HTM[6134]="*Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, balavā puriso tiṇhena sikharena muddhani abhimattheyya;**like a strong man was drilling into my head with a sharp point.*";
P_HTM[6135]="*evameva kho me, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā muddhani ūhananti.* **";
P_HTM[6136]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, rājakumāra, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6137]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6138]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6139]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears.*";
P_HTM[6140]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā honti.**But then I got a severe headache,*";
P_HTM[6141]="*Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, balavā puriso daḷhena varattakkhaṇḍena sīse sīsaveṭhaṃ dadeyya;**like a strong man was tightening a tough leather strap around my head.*";
P_HTM[6142]="*evameva kho me, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā honti.* **";
P_HTM[6143]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, rājakumāra, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6144]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6145]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6146]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears.*";
P_HTM[6147]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti.**But then strong winds carved up my belly,*";
P_HTM[6148]="*Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā tiṇhena govikantanena kucchiṃ parikanteyya;**like a deft butcher or their apprentice was slicing my belly open with a meat cleaver.*";
P_HTM[6149]="*evameva kho me, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā, vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti.* **";
P_HTM[6150]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, rājakumāra, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6151]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6152]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[6153]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose and ears.*";
P_HTM[6154]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho hoti.**But then there was an intense burning in my body,*";
P_HTM[6155]="*Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, dve balavanto purisā dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuyā santāpeyyuṃ samparitāpeyyuṃ;**like two strong men grabbing a weaker man by the arms to burn and scorch him on a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[6156]="*evameva kho me, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho hoti.* **";
P_HTM[6157]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, rājakumāra, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[6158]="*Apissu maṃ, rājakumāra, devatā disvā evamāhaṃsu:**Then some deities saw me and said,*";
P_HTM[6159]="*‘kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama is dead.’*";
P_HTM[6160]="*Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:**Others said,*";
P_HTM[6161]="*‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, api ca kālaṃ karotī’ti.**‘He’s not dead, but he’s dying.’*";
P_HTM[6162]="*Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:**Others said,*";
P_HTM[6163]="*‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, nāpi kālaṃ karoti. Arahaṃ samaṇo gotamo. Vihāro tveva so arahato evarūpo hotī’ti.**‘He’s not dead or dying. The ascetic Gotama is a perfected one, for that is how the perfected ones live.’*";
P_HTM[6164]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6165]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I practice completely cutting off food?’*";
P_HTM[6166]="*Atha kho maṃ, rājakumāra, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:**But deities came to me and said,*";
P_HTM[6167]="*‘mā kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajji.**‘Good sir, don’t practice totally cutting off food.*";
P_HTM[6168]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjissasi, tassa te mayaṃ dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāressāma, tāya tvaṃ yāpessasī’ti.**If you do, we’ll infuse divine nectar into your pores and you will live on that.’*";
P_HTM[6169]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6170]="*‘ahañceva kho pana sabbaso ajajjitaṃ paṭijāneyyaṃ. Imā ca me devatā dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāreyyuṃ, tāya cāhaṃ yāpeyyaṃ, taṃ mamassa musā’ti.**‘If I claim to be completely fasting while these deities are infusing divine nectar in my pores, that would be a lie on my part.’*";
P_HTM[6171]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, tā devatā paccācikkhāmi. ‘Halan’ti vadāmi.**So I dismissed those deities, saying, ‘There’s no need.’*";
P_HTM[6172]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6173]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ yadi vā hareṇukayūsan’ti.**‘Why don’t I just take a little bit of food each time, a cup of broth made from mung beans, lentils, chickpeas, or green gram.’*";
P_HTM[6174]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ yadi vā hareṇukayūsaṃ.**So that’s what I did,*";
P_HTM[6175]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ yadi vā hareṇukayūsaṃ, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.**until my body became extremely emaciated.*";
P_HTM[6176]="*Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, my limbs became like the joints of an eighty-year-old or a corpse,*";
P_HTM[6177]="*Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**my bottom became like a camel’s hoof,*";
P_HTM[6178]="*Seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako uṇṇatāvanato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**my vertebrae stuck out like beads on a string,*";
P_HTM[6179]="*Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**and my ribs were as gaunt as the broken-down rafters on an old barn.*";
P_HTM[6180]="*Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti; evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, the gleam of my eyes sank deep in their sockets, like the gleam of water sunk deep down a well.*";
P_HTM[6181]="*Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, my scalp shriveled and withered like a green bitter-gourd in the wind and sun.*";
P_HTM[6182]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, ‘udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmī’ti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, ‘piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmī’ti udaracchaviṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi. Yāvassu me, rājakumāra, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, the skin of my belly stuck to my backbone, so that when I tried to rub the skin of my belly I grabbed my backbone, and when I tried to rub my backbone I rubbed the skin of my belly.*";
P_HTM[6183]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, ‘vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmī’ti tattheva avakujjo papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to urinate or defecate I fell face down right there.*";
P_HTM[6184]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, imameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anumajjāmi. Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, pāṇinā gattāni anumajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni kāyasmā papatanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out.*";
P_HTM[6185]="*Apissu maṃ, rājakumāra, manussā disvā evamāhaṃsu: ‘kāḷo samaṇo gotamo’ti,**Then some people saw me and said, ‘The ascetic Gotama is black.’*";
P_HTM[6186]="*ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, sāmo samaṇo gotamo’ti.**Some said, ‘He’s not black, he’s brown.’*";
P_HTM[6187]="*Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, napi sāmo, maṅguracchavi samaṇo gotamo’ti.**Some said, ‘He’s neither black nor brown. The ascetic Gotama has tawny skin.’*";
P_HTM[6188]="*Yāvassu me, rājakumāra, tāva parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto upahato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**That’s how far the pure, bright complexion of my skin had been ruined by taking so little food.*";
P_HTM[6189]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6190]="*‘ye kho keci atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayiṃsu, etāvaparamaṃ nayito bhiyyo.**‘Whatever ascetics and brahmins have experienced painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion—whether in the past, future, or present—this is as far as it goes, no-one has done more than this.*";
P_HTM[6191]="*Yepi hi keci anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayissanti, etāvaparamaṃ nayito bhiyyo.* **";
P_HTM[6192]="*Yepi hi keci etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, etāvaparamaṃ nayito bhiyyo.* **";
P_HTM[6193]="*Na kho panāhaṃ imāya kaṭukāya dukkarakārikāya adhigacchāmi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ;**But I have not achieved any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones by this severe, gruelling work.*";
P_HTM[6194]="*siyā nu kho añño maggo bodhāyā’ti.**Could there be another path to awakening?’*";
P_HTM[6195]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6196]="*‘abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ pitu sakkassa kammante sītāya jambucchāyāya nisinno vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharitā;**‘I recall sitting in the cool shade of the rose-apple tree while my father the Sakyan was off working. Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6197]="*siyā nu kho eso maggo bodhāyā’ti.**Could that be the path to awakening?’*";
P_HTM[6198]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, satānusāri viññāṇaṃ ahosi:**Stemming from that memory came the realization:*";
P_HTM[6199]="*‘eseva maggo bodhāyā’ti.**‘That is the path to awakening!’*";
P_HTM[6200]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6201]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti?**‘Why am I afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual pleasures or unskillful qualities?’*";
P_HTM[6202]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6203]="*‘na kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti.**‘I’m not afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual pleasures or unskillful qualities.’*";
P_HTM[6204]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6205]="*‘na kho taṃ sukaraṃ sukhaṃ adhigantuṃ evaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyena. Yannūnāhaṃ oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ odanakummāsan’ti.**‘I can’t achieve that pleasure with a body so excessively emaciated. Why don’t I eat some solid food, some rice and porridge?’*";
P_HTM[6206]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ.**So I ate some solid food.*";
P_HTM[6207]="*Tena kho pana maṃ, rājakumāra, samayena pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū paccupaṭṭhitā honti:**Now at that time the five mendicants were attending on me, thinking,*";
P_HTM[6208]="*‘yaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ adhigamissati taṃ no ārocessatī’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama will tell us of any truth that he realizes.’*";
P_HTM[6209]="*Yato kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ, atha me te pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū nibbijja pakkamiṃsu:**But when I ate some solid food, they left disappointed in me, saying,*";
P_HTM[6210]="*‘bāhulliko samaṇo gotamo padhānavibbhanto, āvatto bāhullāyā’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama has become indulgent; he has strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence.’*";
P_HTM[6211]="*So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāretvā balaṃ gahetvā vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**After eating solid food and gathering my strength, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[6212]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**second absorption …*";
P_HTM[6213]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[6214]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[6215]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[6216]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi.**I recollected many past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. And so I recollected my many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[6217]="*Ayaṃ kho me, rājakumāra, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā**This was the first knowledge, which I achieved in the first watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[6218]="*vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[6219]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[6220]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi … pe …**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understood how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[6221]="*ayaṃ kho me, rājakumāra, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**This was the second knowledge, which I achieved in the middle watch of the night. Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[6222]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[6223]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;**I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[6224]="*‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ … pe … ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ.**I truly understood: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[6225]="*Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha.**Knowing and seeing like this, my mind was freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[6226]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ ahosi.**When it was freed, I knew it was freed.*";
P_HTM[6227]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti abbhaññāsiṃ.**I understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[6228]="*Ayaṃ kho me, rājakumāra, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā**This was the third knowledge, which I achieved in the last watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[6229]="*vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[6230]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6231]="*‘adhigato kho myāyaṃ dhammo gambhīro duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo.**‘This principle I have discovered is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute.*";
P_HTM[6232]="*Ālayarāmā kho panāyaṃ pajā ālayaratā ālayasammuditā.**But people like attachment, they love it and enjoy it.*";
P_HTM[6233]="*Ālayarāmāya kho pana pajāya ālayaratāya ālayasammuditāya duddasaṃ idaṃ ṭhānaṃ yadidaṃ—idappaccayatāpaṭiccasamuppādo.**It’s hard for them to see this thing; that is, specific conditionality, dependent origination.*";
P_HTM[6234]="*Idampi kho ṭhānaṃ duddasaṃ—yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ.**It’s also hard for them to see this thing; that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[6235]="*Ahañceva kho pana dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, pare ca me na ājāneyyuṃ, so mamassa kilamatho, sā mamassa vihesā’ti.**And if I were to teach the Dhamma, others might not understand me, which would be wearying and troublesome for me.’*";
P_HTM[6236]="*Apissu maṃ, rājakumāra, imā anacchariyā gāthāyo paṭibhaṃsu pubbe assutapubbā:**And then these verses, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[6237]="*‘Kicchena me adhigataṃ,**‘I’ve struggled hard to realize this,*";
P_HTM[6238]="*halaṃ dāni pakāsituṃ;**enough with trying to explain it!*";
P_HTM[6239]="*Rāgadosaparetehi,**This teaching is not easily understood*";
P_HTM[6240]="*nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho.**by those mired in greed and hate.*";
P_HTM[6241]="*Paṭisotagāmiṃ nipuṇaṃ,**Those caught up in greed can’t see*";
P_HTM[6242]="*gambhīraṃ duddasaṃ aṇuṃ;**what’s subtle, going against the stream,*";
P_HTM[6243]="*Rāgarattā na dakkhanti,**deep, hard to see, and very fine,*";
P_HTM[6244]="*tamokhandhena āvuṭā’ti.**for they’re shrouded in a mass of darkness.’*";
P_HTM[6245]="*Itiha me, rājakumāra, paṭisañcikkhato appossukkatāya cittaṃ namati no dhammadesanāya.**And as I reflected like this, my mind inclined to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[6246]="*Atha kho, rājakumāra, brahmuno sahampatissa mama cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya etadahosi:**Then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing what I was thinking, thought,*";
P_HTM[6247]="*‘nassati vata bho loko; vinassati vata bho loko. Yatra hi nāma tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa appossukkatāya cittaṃ namati no dhammadesanāyā’ti.**‘Oh my goodness! The world will be lost, the world will perish! For the mind of the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, inclines to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma.’*";
P_HTM[6248]="*Atha kho, rājakumāra, brahmā sahampati—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito mama purato pāturahosi.**Then Brahmā Sahampati, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6249]="*Atha kho, rājakumāra, brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yenāhaṃ tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā maṃ etadavoca:**He arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said,*";
P_HTM[6250]="*‘desetu, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ, desetu sugato dhammaṃ.**‘Sir, let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma! Let the Holy One teach the Dhamma!*";
P_HTM[6251]="*Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā assavanatāya dhammassa parihāyanti;**There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because they haven’t heard the teaching.*";
P_HTM[6252]="*bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro’ti.**There will be those who understand the teaching!’*";
P_HTM[6253]="*Idamavoca, rājakumāra, brahmā sahampati;**That’s what Brahmā Sahampati said.*";
P_HTM[6254]="*idaṃ vatvā athāparaṃ etadavoca:**Then he went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6255]="*‘Pāturahosi magadhesu pubbe,**‘Among the Magadhans there appeared in the past*";
P_HTM[6256]="*Dhammo asuddho samalehi cintito;**an impure teaching thought up by those still stained.*";
P_HTM[6257]="*Apāpuretaṃ amatassa dvāraṃ,**Fling open the door to the deathless!*";
P_HTM[6258]="*Suṇantu dhammaṃ vimalenānubuddhaṃ.**Let them hear the teaching the immaculate one discovered.*";
P_HTM[6259]="*Sele yathā pabbatamuddhaniṭṭhito,**Standing high on a rocky mountain,*";
P_HTM[6260]="*Yathāpi passe janataṃ samantato;**you can see the people all around.*";
P_HTM[6261]="*Tathūpamaṃ dhammamayaṃ sumedha,**In just the same way, all-seer, wise one,*";
P_HTM[6262]="*Pāsādamāruyha samantacakkhu.**ascend the palace built of Dhamma!*";
P_HTM[6263]="*Sokāvatiṇṇaṃ janatamapetasoko,**You’re free of sorrow; but look at these people*";
P_HTM[6264]="*Avekkhassu jātijarābhibhūtaṃ;**overwhelmed with sorrow, oppressed by rebirth and old age.*";
P_HTM[6265]="*Uṭṭhehi vīra vijitasaṅgāma,**Rise, hero! Victor in battle, leader of the caravan,*";
P_HTM[6266]="*Satthavāha aṇaṇa vicara loke;**wander the world without obligation.*";
P_HTM[6267]="*Desassu bhagavā dhammaṃ,**Let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma!*";
P_HTM[6268]="*Aññātāro bhavissantī’ti.**There will be those who understand!’*";
P_HTM[6269]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, brahmuno ca ajjhesanaṃ viditvā sattesu ca kāruññataṃ paṭicca buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokesiṃ.**Then, understanding Brahmā’s invitation, I surveyed the world with the eye of a Buddha, because of my compassion for sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[6270]="*Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokento satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe tikkhindriye mudindriye svākāre dvākāre suviññāpaye duviññāpaye appekacce paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante.**And I saw sentient beings with little dust in their eyes, and some with much dust in their eyes; with keen faculties and with weak faculties, with good qualities and with bad qualities, easy to teach and hard to teach. And some of them lived seeing the danger in the fault to do with the next world, while others did not.*";
P_HTM[6271]="*Seyyathāpi nāma uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni antonimuggaposīni, appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni samodakaṃ ṭhitāni, appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakā accuggamma ṭhitāni anupalittāni udakena;**It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving underwater. Some of them sprout and grow in the water reaching the water’s surface. And some of them sprout and grow in the water but rise up above the water and stand with no water clinging to them.*";
P_HTM[6272]="*evameva kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra; buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokento addasaṃ satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe tikkhindriye mudindriye svākāre dvākāre suviññāpaye duviññāpaye, appekacce paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante.* **";
P_HTM[6273]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, brahmānaṃ sahampatiṃ gāthāya paccabhāsiṃ:**Then I replied in verse to Brahmā Sahampati:*";
P_HTM[6274]="*‘Apārutā tesaṃ amatassa dvārā,**‘Flung open are the doors to the deathless!*";
P_HTM[6275]="*Ye sotavanto pamuñcantu saddhaṃ;**Let those with ears to hear decide their faith.*";
P_HTM[6276]="*Vihiṃsasaññī paguṇaṃ na bhāsiṃ,**Thinking it would be troublesome, Brahmā, I did not teach*";
P_HTM[6277]="*Dhammaṃ paṇītaṃ manujesu brahme’ti.**the sophisticated, sublime Dhamma among humans.’*";
P_HTM[6278]="*Atha kho, rājakumāra, brahmā sahampati ‘katāvakāso khomhi bhagavatā dhammadesanāyā’ti maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi.**Then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing that his request for me to teach the Dhamma had been granted, bowed and respectfully circled me, keeping me on his right, before vanishing right there.*";
P_HTM[6279]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6280]="*‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ?**‘Who should I teach first of all?*";
P_HTM[6281]="*Ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti?**Who will quickly understand the teaching?’*";
P_HTM[6282]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6283]="*‘ayaṃ kho āḷāro kālāmo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī dīgharattaṃ apparajakkhajātiko.**‘That Āḷāra Kālāma is astute, competent, clever, and has long had little dust in his eyes.*";
P_HTM[6284]="*Yannūnāhaṃ āḷārassa kālāmassa paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ;**Why don’t I teach him first of all?*";
P_HTM[6285]="*so imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti.**He’ll quickly understand the teaching.’*";
P_HTM[6286]="*Atha kho maṃ, rājakumāra, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca:**But a deity came to me and said,*";
P_HTM[6287]="*‘sattāhakālaṅkato, bhante, āḷāro kālāmo’ti.**‘Sir, Āḷāra Kālāma passed away seven days ago.’*";
P_HTM[6288]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**And knowledge and vision arose in me,*";
P_HTM[6289]="*‘sattāhakālaṅkato āḷāro kālāmo’ti.**‘Āḷāra Kālāma passed away seven days ago.’*";
P_HTM[6290]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6291]="*‘mahājāniyo kho āḷāro kālāmo.**‘This is a great loss for Āḷāra Kālāma.*";
P_HTM[6292]="*Sace hi so imaṃ dhammaṃ suṇeyya, khippameva ājāneyyā’ti.**If he had heard the teaching, he would have understood it quickly.’*";
P_HTM[6293]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6294]="*‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ?**‘Who should I teach first of all?*";
P_HTM[6295]="*Ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti?**Who will quickly understand the teaching?’*";
P_HTM[6296]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6297]="*‘ayaṃ kho udako rāmaputto paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī dīgharattaṃ apparajakkhajātiko.**‘That Uddaka, son of Rāma, is astute, competent, clever, and has long had little dust in his eyes.*";
P_HTM[6298]="*Yannūnāhaṃ udakassa rāmaputtassa paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ;**Why don’t I teach him first of all?*";
P_HTM[6299]="*so imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti.**He’ll quickly understand the teaching.’*";
P_HTM[6300]="*Atha kho maṃ, rājakumāra, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca:**But a deity came to me and said,*";
P_HTM[6301]="*‘abhidosakālaṅkato, bhante, udako rāmaputto’ti.**‘Sir, Uddaka, son of Rāma, passed away just last night.’*";
P_HTM[6302]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**And knowledge and vision arose in me,*";
P_HTM[6303]="*‘abhidosakālaṅkato udako rāmaputto’ti.**‘Uddaka, son of Rāma, passed away just last night.’*";
P_HTM[6304]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6305]="*‘mahājāniyo kho udako rāmaputto.**‘This is a great loss for Uddaka.*";
P_HTM[6306]="*Sace hi so imaṃ dhammaṃ suṇeyya, khippameva ājāneyyā’ti.**If he had heard the teaching, he would have understood it quickly.’*";
P_HTM[6307]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6308]="*‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ?**‘Who should I teach first of all?*";
P_HTM[6309]="*Ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti?**Who will quickly understand the teaching?’*";
P_HTM[6310]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6311]="*‘bahukārā kho me pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū ye maṃ padhānapahitattaṃ upaṭṭhahiṃsu.**‘The group of five mendicants were very helpful to me. They looked after me during my time of resolute striving.*";
P_HTM[6312]="*Yannūnāhaṃ pañcavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyan’ti.**Why don’t I teach them first of all?’*";
P_HTM[6313]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[6314]="*‘kahaṃ nu kho etarahi pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū viharantī’ti.**‘Where are the group of five mendicants staying these days?’*";
P_HTM[6315]="*Addasaṃ khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena pañcavaggiye bhikkhū bārāṇasiyaṃ viharante isipatane migadāye.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman I saw that the group of five mendicants were staying near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana.*";
P_HTM[6316]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, uruvelāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena bārāṇasī tena cārikaṃ pakkamiṃ.**So, when I had stayed in Uruvelā as long as I wished, I set out for Benares.*";
P_HTM[6317]="*Addasā kho maṃ, rājakumāra, upako ājīvako antarā ca gayaṃ antarā ca bodhiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannaṃ.**While I was traveling along the road between Gaya and Bodhgaya, the Ājīvaka ascetic Upaka saw me*";
P_HTM[6318]="*Disvāna maṃ etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[6319]="*‘vippasannāni kho te, āvuso, indriyāni, parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto.**‘Reverend, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[6320]="*Kaṃsi tvaṃ, āvuso, uddissa pabbajito? Ko vā te satthā? Kassa vā tvaṃ dhammaṃ rocesī’ti?**In whose name have you gone forth, reverend? Who is your Teacher? Whose teaching do you believe in?’*";
P_HTM[6321]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, rājakumāra, upakaṃ ājīvakaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsiṃ:**I replied to Upaka in verse:*";
P_HTM[6322]="*‘Sabbābhibhū sabbavidūhamasmi,**‘I am the champion, the knower of all,*";
P_HTM[6323]="*Sabbesu dhammesu anūpalitto;**unsullied in the midst of all things.*";
P_HTM[6324]="*Sabbañjaho taṇhākkhaye vimutto,**I’ve given up all, freed in the ending of craving.*";
P_HTM[6325]="*Sayaṃ abhiññāya kamuddiseyyaṃ.**When I know for myself, who should I follow?*";
P_HTM[6326]="*Na me ācariyo atthi,**I have no teacher.*";
P_HTM[6327]="*sadiso me na vijjati;**There is no-one like me.*";
P_HTM[6328]="*Sadevakasmiṃ lokasmiṃ,**In the world with its gods,*";
P_HTM[6329]="*natthi me paṭipuggalo.**I have no counterpart.*";
P_HTM[6330]="*Ahañhi arahā loke,**For in this world, I am the perfected one;*";
P_HTM[6331]="*ahaṃ satthā anuttaro;**I am the supreme Teacher.*";
P_HTM[6332]="*Ekomhi sammāsambuddho,**I alone am fully awakened,*";
P_HTM[6333]="*sītibhūtosmi nibbuto.**cooled, extinguished.*";
P_HTM[6334]="*Dhammacakkaṃ pavattetuṃ,**I am going to the city of Kāsi*";
P_HTM[6335]="*Gacchāmi kāsinaṃ puraṃ;**to roll forth the Wheel of Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[6336]="*Andhībhūtasmiṃ lokasmiṃ,**In this world that is so blind,*";
P_HTM[6337]="*Āhañchaṃ amatadundubhin’ti.**I’ll beat the deathless drum!’*";
P_HTM[6338]="*‘Yathā kho tvaṃ, āvuso, paṭijānāsi arahasi anantajino’ti.**‘According to what you claim, reverend, you ought to be the Infinite Victor.’*";
P_HTM[6339]="*‘Mādisā ve jinā honti,**‘The victors are those who, like me,*";
P_HTM[6340]="*ye pattā āsavakkhayaṃ;**have reached the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[6341]="*Jitā me pāpakā dhammā,**I have conquered bad qualities, Upaka—*";
P_HTM[6342]="*tasmāhamupaka jino’ti.**that’s why I’m a victor.’*";
P_HTM[6343]="*Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, upako ājīvako ‘hupeyyapāvuso’ti vatvā sīsaṃ okampetvā ummaggaṃ gahetvā pakkāmi.**When I had spoken, Upaka said: ‘If you say so, reverend.’ Shaking his head, he took a wrong turn and left.*";
P_HTM[6344]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bārāṇasī isipatanaṃ migadāyo yena pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃ.**Traveling stage by stage, I arrived at Benares, and went to see the group of five mendicants in the deer park at Isipatana.*";
P_HTM[6345]="*Addasaṃsu kho maṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The group of five mendicants saw me coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[6346]="*Disvāna aññamaññaṃ saṇṭhapesuṃ:**and stopped each other, saying,*";
P_HTM[6347]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, samaṇo gotamo āgacchati bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya.**‘Here comes the ascetic Gotama. He’s so indulgent; he strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence.*";
P_HTM[6348]="*So neva abhivādetabbo, na paccuṭṭhātabbo, nāssa pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ;**We shouldn’t bow to him or rise for him or receive his bowl and robe.*";
P_HTM[6349]="*api ca kho āsanaṃ ṭhapetabbaṃ—sace so ākaṅkhissati nisīdissatī’ti.**But we can set out a seat; he can sit if he likes.’*";
P_HTM[6350]="*Yathā yathā kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū upasaṅkamiṃ tathā tathā pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu sakāya katikāya saṇṭhātuṃ.**Yet as I drew closer, the group of five mendicants were unable to stop themselves as they had agreed.*";
P_HTM[6351]="*Appekacce maṃ paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahesuṃ. Appekacce āsanaṃ paññapesuṃ. Appekacce pādodakaṃ upaṭṭhapesuṃ.**Some came out to greet me and receive my bowl and robe, some spread out a seat, while others set out water for washing my feet.*";
P_HTM[6352]="*Api ca kho maṃ nāmena ca āvusovādena ca samudācaranti.**But they still addressed me by name and as ‘reverend’.*";
P_HTM[6353]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:**So I said to them,*";
P_HTM[6354]="*‘mā, bhikkhave, tathāgataṃ nāmena ca āvusovādena ca samudācaratha;**‘Mendicants, don’t address me by name and as “reverend”.*";
P_HTM[6355]="*arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho.**The Realized One is Perfected, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6356]="*Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ. Amatamadhigataṃ ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi.**Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[6357]="*Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti.**By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. You will live having achieved with your own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[6358]="*Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ:**But they said to me,*";
P_HTM[6359]="*‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ; kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti?**‘Reverend Gotama, even by that conduct, that practice, that grueling work you did not achieve any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones. How could you have achieved such a state now that you’ve become indulgent, strayed from the struggle and fallen into indulgence?’*";
P_HTM[6360]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:**So I said to them,*";
P_HTM[6361]="*‘na, bhikkhave, tathāgato bāhulliko na padhānavibbhanto na āvatto bāhullāya.**‘The Realized One has not become indulgent, strayed from the struggle and fallen into indulgence.*";
P_HTM[6362]="*Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho.**The Realized One is Perfected, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6363]="*Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ. Amatamadhigataṃ ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi.**Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[6364]="*Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti.**By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. You will live having achieved with your own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[6365]="*Dutiyampi kho, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ:**But for a second time they said to me,*";
P_HTM[6366]="*‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ; kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti?**‘Reverend Gotama … you’ve fallen into indulgence.’*";
P_HTM[6367]="*Dutiyampi kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:**So for a second time I said to them,*";
P_HTM[6368]="*‘na, bhikkhave, tathāgato bāhulliko na padhānavibbhanto na āvatto bāhullāya.**‘The Realized One has not become indulgent …’*";
P_HTM[6369]="*Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho.* **";
P_HTM[6370]="*Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ. Amatamadhigataṃ ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi.* **";
P_HTM[6371]="*Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6372]="*Tatiyampi kho, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ:**But for a third time they said to me,*";
P_HTM[6373]="*‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ; kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti?**‘Reverend Gotama … you’ve fallen into indulgence.’*";
P_HTM[6374]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ:**So I said to them,*";
P_HTM[6375]="*‘abhijānātha me no tumhe, bhikkhave, ito pubbe evarūpaṃ pabhāvitametan’ti?**‘Mendicants, have you ever known me to speak like this before?’*";
P_HTM[6376]="*‘No hetaṃ, bhante’.**‘No, sir.’*";
P_HTM[6377]="*‘Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho.**‘The Realized One is Perfected, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6378]="*Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ. Amatamadhigataṃ ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi.**Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma.*";
P_HTM[6379]="*Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti.**By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. You will live having achieved with your own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’*";
P_HTM[6380]="*Asakkhiṃ kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū saññāpetuṃ.**I was able to persuade the group of five mendicants.*";
P_HTM[6381]="*Dvepi sudaṃ, rājakumāra, bhikkhū ovadāmi. Tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caranti.**Then sometimes I advised two mendicants, while the other three went for alms.*";
P_HTM[6382]="*Yaṃ tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā āharanti, tena chabbaggiyā yāpema.**Then those three would feed all six of us with what they brought back.*";
P_HTM[6383]="*Tayopi sudaṃ, rājakumāra, bhikkhū ovadāmi, dve bhikkhū piṇḍāya caranti.**Sometimes I advised three mendicants, while the other two went for alms.*";
P_HTM[6384]="*Yaṃ dve bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā āharanti tena chabbaggiyā yāpema.**Then those two would feed all six of us with what they brought back.*";
P_HTM[6385]="*Atha kho, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū mayā evaṃ ovadiyamānā evaṃ anusāsiyamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihariṃsū”ti.**As the group of five mendicants were being advised and instructed by me like this, they soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. They lived having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[6386]="*Evaṃ vutte, bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Prince Bodhi said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6387]="*“kīva cirena nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā”ti?**“Sir, when a mendicant has the Realized One as trainer, how long would it take for them to realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life?”*";
P_HTM[6388]="*“Tena hi, rājakumāra, taṃyevettha paṭipucchissāmi. Yathā te khameyya, tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi.**“Well then, prince, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as you like.*";
P_HTM[6389]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**What do you think, prince?*";
P_HTM[6390]="*kusalo tvaṃ hatthārūḷhe aṅkusagayhe sippe”ti?**Are you skilled in the art of wielding a hooked goad while riding an elephant?”*";
P_HTM[6391]="*“Evaṃ, bhante, kusalo ahaṃ hatthārūḷhe aṅkusagayhe sippe”ti.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6392]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**“What do you think, prince?*";
P_HTM[6393]="*idha puriso āgaccheyya:**Suppose a man were to come along thinking,*";
P_HTM[6394]="*‘bodhi rājakumāro hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ jānāti;**‘Prince Bodhi knows the art of wielding a hooked goad while riding an elephant.*";
P_HTM[6395]="*tassāhaṃ santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkhissāmī’ti.**I’ll train in that art under him.’*";
P_HTM[6396]="*So cassa assaddho;**If he’s faithless,*";
P_HTM[6397]="*yāvatakaṃ saddhena pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya.**he wouldn’t achieve what he could with faith.*";
P_HTM[6398]="*So cassa bahvābādho;**If he’s unhealthy,*";
P_HTM[6399]="*yāvatakaṃ appābādhena pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya.**he wouldn’t achieve what he could with good health.*";
P_HTM[6400]="*So cassa saṭho māyāvī;**If he’s devious or deceitful,*";
P_HTM[6401]="*yāvatakaṃ asaṭhena amāyāvinā pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya.**he wouldn’t achieve what he could with honesty and integrity.*";
P_HTM[6402]="*So cassa kusīto;**If he’s lazy,*";
P_HTM[6403]="*yāvatakaṃ āraddhavīriyena pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya.**he wouldn’t achieve what he could with energy.*";
P_HTM[6404]="*So cassa duppañño;**If he’s stupid,*";
P_HTM[6405]="*yāvatakaṃ paññavatā pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya.**he wouldn’t achieve what he could with wisdom.*";
P_HTM[6406]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**What do you think, prince?*";
P_HTM[6407]="*api nu so puriso tava santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkheyyā”ti?**Could that man still train under you in the art of wielding a hooked goad while riding an elephant?”*";
P_HTM[6408]="*“Ekamekenāpi, bhante, aṅgena samannāgato so puriso na mama santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkheyya, ko pana vādo pañcahaṅgehī”ti.**“Sir, if he had even a single one of these factors he couldn’t train under me, let alone all five.”*";
P_HTM[6409]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**“What do you think, prince?*";
P_HTM[6410]="*idha puriso āgaccheyya:**Suppose a man were to come along thinking,*";
P_HTM[6411]="*‘bodhi rājakumāro hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ jānāti;**‘Prince Bodhi knows the art of wielding a hooked goad while riding an elephant.*";
P_HTM[6412]="*tassāhaṃ santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkhissāmī’ti.**I’ll train in that art under him.’*";
P_HTM[6413]="*So cassa saddho;**If he’s faithful,*";
P_HTM[6414]="*yāvatakaṃ saddhena pattabbaṃ taṃ sampāpuṇeyya.**he’d achieve what he could with faith.*";
P_HTM[6415]="*So cassa appābādho;**If he’s healthy,*";
P_HTM[6416]="*yāvatakaṃ appābādhena pattabbaṃ taṃ sampāpuṇeyya.**he’d achieve what he could with good health.*";
P_HTM[6417]="*So cassa asaṭho amāyāvī;**If he’s honest and has integrity,*";
P_HTM[6418]="*yāvatakaṃ asaṭhena amāyāvinā pattabbaṃ taṃ sampāpuṇeyya.**he’d achieve what he could with honesty and integrity.*";
P_HTM[6419]="*So cassa āraddhavīriyo;**If he’s energetic,*";
P_HTM[6420]="*yāvatakaṃ āraddhavīriyena pattabbaṃ taṃ sampāpuṇeyya.**he’d achieve what he could with energy.*";
P_HTM[6421]="*So cassa paññavā;**If he’s wise,*";
P_HTM[6422]="*yāvatakaṃ paññavatā pattabbaṃ taṃ sampāpuṇeyya.**he’d achieve what he could with wisdom.*";
P_HTM[6423]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra,**What do you think, prince?*";
P_HTM[6424]="*api nu so puriso tava santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkheyyā”ti?**Could that man still train under you in the art of wielding a hooked goad while riding an elephant?”*";
P_HTM[6425]="*“Ekamekenāpi, bhante, aṅgena samannāgato so puriso mama santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkheyya, ko pana vādo pañcahaṅgehī”ti.**“Sir, if he had even a single one of these factors he could train under me, let alone all five.”*";
P_HTM[6426]="*“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, pañcimāni padhāniyaṅgāni.**“In the same way, prince, there are these five factors that support meditation.*";
P_HTM[6427]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[6428]="*Idha, rājakumāra, bhikkhu saddho hoti; saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:**It’s when a noble disciple has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:*";
P_HTM[6429]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti;**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[6430]="*appābādho hoti appātaṅko samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya;**They are rarely ill or unwell. Their stomach digests well, being neither too hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation.*";
P_HTM[6431]="*asaṭho hoti amāyāvī yathābhūtaṃ attānaṃ āvikattā satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu;**They’re not devious or deceitful. They reveal themselves honestly to the Teacher or sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[6432]="*āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu;**They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[6433]="*paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammādukkhakkhayagāminiyā.**They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[6434]="*Imāni kho, rājakumāra, pañca padhāniyaṅgāni.**These are the five factors that support meditation.*";
P_HTM[6435]="*Imehi, rājakumāra, pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno—**When a mendicant with these five factors that support meditation has the Realized One as trainer, they could*";
P_HTM[6436]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya satta vassāni.**realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in seven years.*";
P_HTM[6437]="*Tiṭṭhantu, rājakumāra, satta vassāni.**Let alone seven years,*";
P_HTM[6438]="*Imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno—**they could*";
P_HTM[6439]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya chabbassāni …**realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in six years,*";
P_HTM[6440]="*pañca vassāni …* **";
P_HTM[6441]="*cattāri vassāni …* **";
P_HTM[6442]="*tīṇi vassāni …* **";
P_HTM[6443]="*dve vassāni …* **";
P_HTM[6444]="*ekaṃ vassaṃ.**or as little as one year.*";
P_HTM[6445]="*Tiṭṭhatu, rājakumāra, ekaṃ vassaṃ.**Let alone one year,*";
P_HTM[6446]="*Imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno—**when a mendicant with these five factors that support meditation has the Realized One as trainer, they could*";
P_HTM[6447]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya satta māsāni.**realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in seven months,*";
P_HTM[6448]="*Tiṭṭhantu, rājakumāra, satta māsāni.* **";
P_HTM[6449]="*Imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno—* **";
P_HTM[6450]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—* **";
P_HTM[6451]="*brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya cha māsāni …* **";
P_HTM[6452]="*pañca māsāni …* **";
P_HTM[6453]="*cattāri māsāni …* **";
P_HTM[6454]="*tīṇi māsāni …* **";
P_HTM[6455]="*dve māsāni …* **";
P_HTM[6456]="*ekaṃ māsaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[6457]="*aḍḍhamāsaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6458]="*Tiṭṭhatu, rājakumāra, aḍḍhamāso.* **";
P_HTM[6459]="*Imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno—* **";
P_HTM[6460]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—* **";
P_HTM[6461]="*brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya satta rattindivāni.* **";
P_HTM[6462]="*Tiṭṭhantu, rājakumāra, satta rattindivāni.* **";
P_HTM[6463]="*Imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno—* **";
P_HTM[6464]="*yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—* **";
P_HTM[6465]="*brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyya cha rattindivāni …* **";
P_HTM[6466]="*pañca rattindivāni …* **";
P_HTM[6467]="*cattāri rattindivāni …* **";
P_HTM[6468]="*tīṇi rattindivāni …* **";
P_HTM[6469]="*dve rattindivāni …* **";
P_HTM[6470]="*ekaṃ rattindivaṃ.**or as little as one day.*";
P_HTM[6471]="*Tiṭṭhatu, rājakumāra, eko rattindivo.**Let alone one day,*";
P_HTM[6472]="*Imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno sāyamanusiṭṭho pāto visesaṃ adhigamissati, pātamanusiṭṭho sāyaṃ visesaṃ adhigamissatī”ti.**when a mendicant with these five factors that support meditation has the Realized One as trainer, they could be instructed in the evening and achieve distinction in the morning, or be instructed in the morning and achieve distinction in the evening.”*";
P_HTM[6473]="*Evaṃ vutte, bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Prince Bodhi said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6474]="*“aho buddho, aho dhammo, aho dhammassa svākkhātatā.**“Oh, the Buddha! Oh, the teaching! Oh, how well explained is the teaching!*";
P_HTM[6475]="*Yatra hi nāma sāyamanusiṭṭho pāto visesaṃ adhigamissati, pātamanusiṭṭho sāyaṃ visesaṃ adhigamissatī”ti.**For someone could be instructed in the evening and achieve distinction in the morning, or be instructed in the morning and achieve distinction in the evening.”*";
P_HTM[6476]="*Evaṃ vutte, sañjikāputto māṇavo bodhiṃ rājakumāraṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Sañjikāputta said to Prince Bodhi,*";
P_HTM[6477]="*“evameva panāyaṃ bhavaṃ bodhi:**“Though Master Bodhi speaks like this,*";
P_HTM[6478]="*‘aho buddho, aho dhammo, aho dhammassa svākkhātatā’ti ca vadeti;* **";
P_HTM[6479]="*atha ca pana na taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchati dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañcā”ti.**you don’t go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.”*";
P_HTM[6480]="*“Mā hevaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, avaca; mā hevaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, avaca.**“Don’t say that, dear Sañjikāputta, don’t say that!*";
P_HTM[6481]="*Sammukhā metaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, ayyāya sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ”.**I have heard and learned this in the presence of the lady, my mother.*";
P_HTM[6482]="*“Ekamidaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**This one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6483]="*Atha kho me ayyā kucchimatī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho me ayyā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then my pregnant mother went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6484]="*‘yo me ayaṃ, bhante, kucchigato kumārako vā kumārikā vā so bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchati dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**‘Sir, the prince or princess in my womb goes for refuge to the Buddha, the teaching, and the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6485]="*Upāsakaṃ taṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan’ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember them as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.’*";
P_HTM[6486]="*Ekamidaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, samayaṃ bhagavā idheva bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**Another time the Buddha was staying here in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood.*";
P_HTM[6487]="*Atha kho maṃ dhāti aṅkena haritvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho maṃ dhāti bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then my nurse, carrying me on her hip, went to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6488]="*‘ayaṃ, bhante, bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchati dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**‘Sir, this Prince Bodhi goes for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6489]="*Upāsakaṃ taṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan’ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember him as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.’*";
P_HTM[6490]="*Esāhaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, tatiyakampi bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**Now for a third time I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[6491]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[6492]="*Bodhirājakumārasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6493]="*86. Aṅgulimālasutta**With Aṅgulimāla*";
P_HTM[6494]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6495]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6496]="*Tena kho pana samayena rañño pasenadissa kosalassa vijite coro aṅgulimālo nāma hoti luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu.**Now at that time in the realm of King Pasenadi of Kosala there was a bandit named Aṅgulimāla. He was violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings.*";
P_HTM[6497]="*Tena gāmāpi agāmā katā, nigamāpi anigamā katā, janapadāpi ajanapadā katā.**He laid waste to villages, towns, and countries.*";
P_HTM[6498]="*So manusse vadhitvā vadhitvā aṅgulīnaṃ mālaṃ dhāreti.**He was constantly murdering people, and he wore their fingers as a necklace.*";
P_HTM[6499]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[6500]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena coro aṅgulimālo tenaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajji.**Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, he set his lodgings in order and, taking his bowl and robe, he walked down the road that led to Aṅgulimāla.*";
P_HTM[6501]="*Addasāsuṃ kho gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino bhagavantaṃ yena coro aṅgulimālo tenaddhānamaggapaṭipannaṃ.**The cowherds, shepherds, farmers, and travelers saw him on the road,*";
P_HTM[6502]="*Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6503]="*“mā, samaṇa, etaṃ maggaṃ paṭipajji.**“Don’t take this road, ascetic.*";
P_HTM[6504]="*Etasmiṃ, samaṇa, magge coro aṅgulimālo nāma luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu.**On this road there is a bandit named Aṅgulimāla. He is violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings.*";
P_HTM[6505]="*Tena gāmāpi agāmā katā, nigamāpi anigamā katā, janapadāpi ajanapadā katā.**He has laid waste to villages, towns, and countries.*";
P_HTM[6506]="*So manusse vadhitvā vadhitvā aṅgulīnaṃ mālaṃ dhāreti.**He is constantly murdering people, and he wears their fingers as a necklace.*";
P_HTM[6507]="*Etañhi, samaṇa, maggaṃ dasapi purisā vīsampi purisā tiṃsampi purisā cattārīsampi purisā paññāsampi purisā saṅkaritvā saṅkaritvā paṭipajjanti.**People travel along this road only after banding closely together in groups of ten, twenty, thirty, forty, or fifty.*";
P_HTM[6508]="*Tepi corassa aṅgulimālassa hatthatthaṃ gacchantī”ti.**Still they meet their end by Aṅgulimāla’s hand.”*";
P_HTM[6509]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā tuṇhībhūto agamāsi.**But when they said this, the Buddha went on in silence.*";
P_HTM[6510]="*Dutiyampi kho gopālakā … pe …**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[6511]="*tatiyampi kho gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**and a third time, they urged the Buddha to turn back.*";
P_HTM[6512]="*“mā, samaṇa, etaṃ maggaṃ paṭipajji, etasmiṃ samaṇa magge coro aṅgulimālo nāma luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu, tena gāmāpi agāmā katā, nigamāpi anigamā katā, janapadāpi ajanapadā katā.* **";
P_HTM[6513]="*So manusse vadhitvā vadhitvā aṅgulīnaṃ mālaṃ dhāreti.* **";
P_HTM[6514]="*Etañhi samaṇa maggaṃ dasapi purisā vīsampi purisā tiṃsampi purisā cattārīsampi purisā paññāsampi purisā saṅkaritvā saṅkaritvā paṭipajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[6515]="*Tepi corassa aṅgulimālassa hatthatthaṃ gacchantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6516]="*Atha kho bhagavā tuṇhībhūto agamāsi.**But when they said this, the Buddha went on in silence.*";
P_HTM[6517]="*Addasā kho coro aṅgulimālo bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The bandit Aṅgulimāla saw the Buddha coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6518]="*Disvānassa etadahosi:**and thought,*";
P_HTM[6519]="*“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**“It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[6520]="*Imañhi maggaṃ dasapi purisā vīsampi purisā tiṃsampi purisā cattārīsampi purisā paññāsampi purisā saṅkaritvā saṅkaritvā paṭipajjanti.**People travel along this road only after banding closely together in groups of ten, twenty, thirty, forty, or fifty.*";
P_HTM[6521]="*Tepi mama hatthatthaṃ gacchanti.**Still they meet their end by my hand.*";
P_HTM[6522]="*Atha ca panāyaṃ samaṇo eko adutiyo pasayha maññe āgacchati.**But still this ascetic comes along alone and unaccompanied, like he had beaten me already.*";
P_HTM[6523]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ samaṇaṃ jīvitā voropeyyan”ti.**Why don’t I take his life?”*";
P_HTM[6524]="*Atha kho coro aṅgulimālo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi.**Then Aṅgulimāla donned his sword and shield, fastened his bow and arrows, and followed behind the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6525]="*Atha kho bhagavā tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsi yathā coro aṅgulimālo bhagavantaṃ pakatiyā gacchantaṃ sabbathāmena gacchanto na sakkoti sampāpuṇituṃ.**But the Buddha used his psychic power to will that Aṅgulimāla could not catch up with him no matter how hard he tried, even though the Buddha kept walking at a normal speed.*";
P_HTM[6526]="*Atha kho corassa aṅgulimālassa etadahosi:**Then Aṅgulimāla thought,*";
P_HTM[6527]="*“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**“It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[6528]="*Ahañhi pubbe hatthimpi dhāvantaṃ anupatitvā gaṇhāmi, assampi dhāvantaṃ anupatitvā gaṇhāmi, rathampi dhāvantaṃ anupatitvā gaṇhāmi, migampi dhāvantaṃ anupatitvā gaṇhāmi;**Previously, even when I’ve chased a speeding elephant, horse, chariot or deer, I’ve always caught up with them.*";
P_HTM[6529]="*atha ca panāhaṃ imaṃ samaṇaṃ pakatiyā gacchantaṃ sabbathāmena gacchanto na sakkomi sampāpuṇitun”ti.**But I can’t catch up with this ascetic no matter how hard I try, even though he’s walking at a normal speed.”*";
P_HTM[6530]="*Ṭhitova bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**He stood still and said,*";
P_HTM[6531]="*“tiṭṭha, tiṭṭha, samaṇā”ti.**“Stop, stop, ascetic!”*";
P_HTM[6532]="*“Ṭhito ahaṃ, aṅgulimāla, tvañca tiṭṭhā”ti.**“I’ve stopped, Aṅgulimāla—now you stop.”*";
P_HTM[6533]="*Atha kho corassa aṅgulimālassa etadahosi:**Then Aṅgulimāla thought,*";
P_HTM[6534]="*“ime kho samaṇā sakyaputtiyā saccavādino saccapaṭiññā.**“These Sakyan ascetics speak the truth.*";
P_HTM[6535]="*Atha panāyaṃ samaṇo gacchaṃ yevāha:**Yet while walking the ascetic Gotama says:*";
P_HTM[6536]="*‘ṭhito ahaṃ, aṅgulimāla, tvañca tiṭṭhā’ti.**‘I’ve stopped, Aṅgulimāla—now you stop.’*";
P_HTM[6537]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ samaṇaṃ puccheyyan”ti.**Why don’t I ask him about this?”*";
P_HTM[6538]="*Atha kho coro aṅgulimālo bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:**Then he addressed the Buddha in verse:*";
P_HTM[6539]="*“Gacchaṃ vadesi samaṇa ṭhitomhi,**“While walking, ascetic, you say ‘I’ve stopped.’*";
P_HTM[6540]="*Mamañca brūsi ṭhitamaṭṭhitoti;**And I have stopped, but you tell me I’ve not.*";
P_HTM[6541]="*Pucchāmi taṃ samaṇa etamatthaṃ,**I’m asking you this, ascetic:*";
P_HTM[6542]="*Kathaṃ ṭhito tvaṃ ahamaṭṭhitomhī”ti.**how is it you’ve stopped and I have not?”*";
P_HTM[6543]="*“Ṭhito ahaṃ aṅgulimāla sabbadā,**“Aṅgulimāla, I have forever stopped—*";
P_HTM[6544]="*Sabbesu bhūtesu nidhāya daṇḍaṃ;**I’ve cast off violence towards all creatures.*";
P_HTM[6545]="*Tuvañca pāṇesu asaññatosi,**But you can’t stop yourself from harming living creatures;*";
P_HTM[6546]="*Tasmā ṭhitohaṃ tuvamaṭṭhitosī”ti.**that’s why I’ve stopped, but you have not.”*";
P_HTM[6547]="*“Cirassaṃ vata me mahito mahesī,**“Oh, at long last a hermit,*";
P_HTM[6548]="*Mahāvanaṃ pāpuṇi saccavādī;**a great sage who I honor, has entered this great forest.*";
P_HTM[6549]="*Sohaṃ carissāmi pahāya pāpaṃ,**Now that I’ve heard your verse on Dhamma,*";
P_HTM[6550]="*Sutvāna gāthaṃ tava dhammayuttaṃ”.**I shall live without evil.”*";
P_HTM[6551]="*Itveva coro asimāvudhañca,**With these words, the bandit hurled his sword and weapons*";
P_HTM[6552]="*Sobbhe papāte narake akiri;**down a cliff into a chasm.*";
P_HTM[6553]="*Avandi coro sugatassa pāde,**He venerated the Holy One’s feet,*";
P_HTM[6554]="*Tattheva naṃ pabbajjaṃ ayāci.**and asked him for the going forth right away.*";
P_HTM[6555]="*Buddho ca kho kāruṇiko mahesi,**Then the Buddha, the compassionate great hermit,*";
P_HTM[6556]="*Yo satthā lokassa sadevakassa;**the teacher of the world with its gods,*";
P_HTM[6557]="*“Tamehi bhikkhū”ti tadā avoca,**said to him, “Come, monk!”*";
P_HTM[6558]="*Eseva tassa ahu bhikkhubhāvoti.**And with that he became a monk.*";
P_HTM[6559]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmatā aṅgulimālena pacchāsamaṇena yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**Then the Buddha set out for Sāvatthī with Venerable Aṅgulimāla as his second monk.*";
P_HTM[6560]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi tadavasari.**Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[6561]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**where he stayed in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6562]="*Tena kho pana samayena rañño pasenadissa kosalassa antepuradvāre mahājanakāyo sannipatitvā uccāsaddo mahāsaddo hoti:**Now at that time a crowd had gathered by the gate of King Pasenadi’s royal compound making a dreadful racket,*";
P_HTM[6563]="*“coro te, deva, vijite aṅgulimālo nāma luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu.**“In your realm, Your Majesty, there is a bandit named Aṅgulimāla. He is violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings.*";
P_HTM[6564]="*Tena gāmāpi agāmā katā, nigamāpi anigamā katā, janapadāpi ajanapadā katā.**He has laid waste to villages, towns, and countries.*";
P_HTM[6565]="*So manusse vadhitvā vadhitvā aṅgulīnaṃ mālaṃ dhāreti.**He is constantly murdering people, and he wears their fingers as a necklace.*";
P_HTM[6566]="*Taṃ devo paṭisedhetū”ti.**Your Majesty must put a stop to him!”*";
P_HTM[6567]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo pañcamattehi assasatehi sāvatthiyā nikkhami divā divassa.**Then King Pasenadi drove out from Sāvatthī in the middle of the day with around five hundred horses,*";
P_HTM[6568]="*Yena ārāmo tena pāvisi.**heading for the monastery.*";
P_HTM[6569]="*Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached the Buddha on foot. He bowed and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[6570]="*“kiṃ nu te, mahārāja, rājā vā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro kupito vesālikā vā licchavī aññe vā paṭirājāno”ti?**“What is it, great king? Is King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha angry with you, or the Licchavis of Vesālī, or some other opposing ruler?”*";
P_HTM[6571]="*“Na kho me, bhante, rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro kupito, nāpi vesālikā licchavī, nāpi aññe paṭirājāno.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[6572]="*Coro me, bhante, vijite aṅgulimālo nāma luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno pāṇabhūtesu.**In my realm there is a bandit named Aṅgulimāla. He is violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings. …*";
P_HTM[6573]="*Tena gāmāpi agāmā katā, nigamāpi anigamā katā, janapadāpi ajanapadā katā.* **";
P_HTM[6574]="*So manusse vadhitvā vadhitvā aṅgulīnaṃ mālaṃ dhāreti.* **";
P_HTM[6575]="*Tāhaṃ, bhante, paṭisedhissāmī”ti.**I shall put a stop to him.”*";
P_HTM[6576]="*“Sace pana tvaṃ, mahārāja, aṅgulimālaṃ passeyyāsi kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitaṃ, virataṃ pāṇātipātā, virataṃ adinnādānā, virataṃ musāvādā, ekabhattikaṃ, brahmacāriṃ, sīlavantaṃ, kalyāṇadhammaṃ, kinti naṃ kareyyāsī”ti?**“But great king, suppose you were to see that Aṅgulimāla had shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and gone forth from the lay life to homelessness. And that he was refraining from killing living creatures, stealing, and lying; that he was eating in one part of the day, and was celibate, ethical, and of good character. What would you do to him?”*";
P_HTM[6577]="*“Abhivādeyyāma vā, bhante, paccuṭṭheyyāma vā āsanena vā nimanteyyāma, abhinimanteyyāma vā naṃ cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi, dhammikaṃ vā assa rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidaheyyāma.**“I would bow to him, rise in his presence, or offer him a seat. I’d invite him to accept robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. And I’d arrange for his lawful guarding and protection.*";
P_HTM[6578]="*Kuto panassa, bhante, dussīlassa pāpadhammassa evarūpo sīlasaṃyamo bhavissatī”ti?**But sir, how could such an immoral, evil man ever have such virtue and restraint?”*";
P_HTM[6579]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā aṅgulimālo bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti.**Now, at that time Venerable Aṅgulimāla was sitting not far from the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6580]="*Atha kho bhagavā dakkhiṇaṃ bāhuṃ paggahetvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca:**Then the Buddha pointed with his right arm and said to the king,*";
P_HTM[6581]="*“eso, mahārāja, aṅgulimālo”ti.**“Great king, this is Aṅgulimāla.”*";
P_HTM[6582]="*Atha kho rañño pasenadissa kosalassa ahudeva bhayaṃ, ahu chambhitattaṃ, ahu lomahaṃso.**Then the king became frightened, scared, his hair standing on end.*";
P_HTM[6583]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ bhītaṃ saṃviggaṃ lomahaṭṭhajātaṃ viditvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca:**Knowing this, the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[6584]="*“mā bhāyi, mahārāja, natthi te ito bhayan”ti.**“Do not fear, great king. You have nothing to fear from him.”*";
P_HTM[6585]="*Atha kho rañño pasenadissa kosalassa yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ vā lomahaṃso vā so paṭippassambhi.**Then the king’s fear died down.*";
P_HTM[6586]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yenāyasmā aṅgulimālo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ aṅgulimālaṃ etadavoca:**Then the king went over to Aṅgulimāla and said,*";
P_HTM[6587]="*“ayyo no, bhante, aṅgulimālo”ti?**“Sir, is the venerable really Aṅgulimāla?”*";
P_HTM[6588]="*“Evaṃ, mahārājā”ti.**“Yes, great king.”*";
P_HTM[6589]="*“Kathaṅgotto ayyassa pitā, kathaṅgottā mātā”ti?**“What clans were your father and mother from?”*";
P_HTM[6590]="*“Gaggo kho, mahārāja, pitā, mantāṇī mātā”ti.**“My father was a Gagga, and my mother a Mantāṇī.”*";
P_HTM[6591]="*“Abhiramatu, bhante, ayyo gaggo mantāṇiputto.**“May the venerable Gagga Mantāṇīputta be happy.*";
P_HTM[6592]="*Ahamayyassa gaggassa mantāṇiputtassa ussukkaṃ karissāmi cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan”ti.**I’ll make sure that you’re provided with robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.”*";
P_HTM[6593]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā aṅgulimālo āraññiko hoti piṇḍapātiko paṃsukūliko tecīvariko.**But at that time Venerable Aṅgulimāla lived in the wilderness, ate only alms-food, and owned just three robes.*";
P_HTM[6594]="*Atha kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca:**So he said to the king,*";
P_HTM[6595]="*“alaṃ, mahārāja, paripuṇṇaṃ me cīvaran”ti.**“Enough, great king. My robes are complete.”*";
P_HTM[6596]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the king went back to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6597]="*“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[6598]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bhante, bhagavā adantānaṃ dametā, asantānaṃ sametā, aparinibbutānaṃ parinibbāpetā.**How the Buddha tames those who are wild, pacifies those who are violent, and extinguishes those who are unextinguished!*";
P_HTM[6599]="*Yañhi mayaṃ, bhante, nāsakkhimhā daṇḍenapi satthenapi dametuṃ so bhagavatā adaṇḍena asattheneva danto.**For I was not able to tame him with the rod and the sword, but the Buddha tamed him without rod or sword.*";
P_HTM[6600]="*Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante, gacchāma;**Well, now, sir, I must go.*";
P_HTM[6601]="*bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[6602]="*“Yassadāni, mahārāja, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, great king, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[6603]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Then King Pasenadi got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[6604]="*Atha kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then Venerable Aṅgulimāla robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[6605]="*Addasā kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo sāvatthiyaṃ sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno aññataraṃ itthiṃ mūḷhagabbhaṃ vighātagabbhaṃ.**Then as he was wandering indiscriminately for alms-food he saw a woman undergoing a painful obstructed labor.*";
P_HTM[6606]="*Disvānassa etadahosi:**Seeing this, it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[6607]="*“kilissanti vata, bho, sattā;**“Oh, beings suffer such filth!*";
P_HTM[6608]="*kilissanti vata, bho, sattā”ti.**Oh, beings suffer such filth!”*";
P_HTM[6609]="*Atha kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then after wandering for alms in Sāvatthī, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[6610]="*“idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6611]="*Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, sāvatthiyaṃ sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno aññataraṃ itthiṃ mūḷhagabbhaṃ vighātagabbhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6612]="*Disvāna mayhaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[6613]="*‘kilissanti vata bho sattā, kilissanti vata bho sattā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6614]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, aṅgulimāla, yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ itthiṃ evaṃ vadehi:**“Well then, Aṅgulimāla, go to that woman and say this:*";
P_HTM[6615]="*‘yatohaṃ, bhagini, jāto nābhijānāmi sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropetā, tena saccena sotthi te hotu, sotthi gabbhassā’”ti.**‘Ever since I was born, sister, I don’t recall having intentionally taken the life of a living creature. By this truth, may both you and your baby be safe.’”*";
P_HTM[6616]="*“So hi nūna me, bhante, sampajānamusāvādo bhavissati.**“But sir, wouldn’t that be telling a deliberate lie?*";
P_HTM[6617]="*Mayā hi, bhante, bahū sañcicca pāṇā jīvitā voropitā”ti.**For I have intentionally killed many living creatures.”*";
P_HTM[6618]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, aṅgulimāla, yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ itthiṃ evaṃ vadehi:**“In that case, Aṅgulimāla, go to that woman and say this:*";
P_HTM[6619]="*‘yatohaṃ, bhagini, ariyāya jātiyā jāto, nābhijānāmi sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropetā, tena saccena sotthi te hotu, sotthi gabbhassā’”ti.**‘Ever since I was born in the noble birth, sister, I don’t recall having intentionally taken the life of a living creature. By this truth, may both you and your baby be safe.’”*";
P_HTM[6620]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo bhagavato paṭissutvā yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ itthiṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” replied Aṅgulimāla. He went to that woman and said:*";
P_HTM[6621]="*“yatohaṃ, bhagini, ariyāya jātiyā jāto, nābhijānāmi sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropetā, tena saccena sotthi te hotu, sotthi gabbhassā”ti.**“Ever since I was born in the noble birth, sister, I don’t recall having intentionally taken the life of a living creature. By this truth, may both you and your baby be safe.”*";
P_HTM[6622]="*Atha khvāssā itthiyā sotthi ahosi, sotthi gabbhassa.**Then that woman was safe, and so was her baby.*";
P_HTM[6623]="*Atha kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**Then Aṅgulimāla, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[6624]="*“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi.**He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[6625]="*Aññataro kho panāyasmā aṅgulimālo arahataṃ ahosi.**And Venerable Aṅgulimāla became one of the perfected.*";
P_HTM[6626]="*Atha kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then Venerable Aṅgulimāla robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[6627]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññenapi leḍḍu khitto āyasmato aṅgulimālassa kāye nipatati, aññenapi daṇḍo khitto āyasmato aṅgulimālassa kāye nipatati, aññenapi sakkharā khittā āyasmato aṅgulimālassa kāye nipatati.**Now at that time someone threw a stone that hit Aṅgulimāla, someone else threw a stick, and someone else threw gravel.*";
P_HTM[6628]="*Atha kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo bhinnena sīsena, lohitena gaḷantena, bhinnena pattena, vipphālitāya saṅghāṭiyā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami.**Then Aṅgulimāla—with cracked head, bleeding, his bowl broken, and his outer robe torn—went to the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6629]="*Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ aṅgulimālaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The Buddha saw him coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6630]="*Disvāna āyasmantaṃ aṅgulimālaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6631]="*“adhivāsehi tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, adhivāsehi tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa.**“Endure it, brahmin! Endure it, brahmin!*";
P_HTM[6632]="*Yassa kho tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, kammassa vipākena bahūni vassāni bahūni vassasatāni bahūni vassasahassāni niraye pacceyyāsi tassa tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, kammassa vipākaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme paṭisaṃvedesī”ti.**You’re experiencing in this life the result of deeds that might have caused you to be tormented in hell for many years, many hundreds or thousands of years.”*";
P_HTM[6633]="*Atha kho āyasmā aṅgulimālo rahogato paṭisallīno vimuttisukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedi;**Later, Venerable Aṅgulimāla was experiencing the bliss of release while in private retreat.*";
P_HTM[6634]="*tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi:**On that occasion he was inspired to exclaim:*";
P_HTM[6635]="*“Yo pubbeva pamajjitvā,**“Someone who was heedless before,*";
P_HTM[6636]="*pacchā so nappamajjati;**and afterwards is not,*";
P_HTM[6637]="*Somaṃ lokaṃ pabhāseti,**lights up the world,*";
P_HTM[6638]="*abbhā muttova candimā.**like the moon freed from a cloud.*";
P_HTM[6639]="*Yassa pāpaṃ kataṃ kammaṃ,**Someone who, with skillful deeds,*";
P_HTM[6640]="*kusalena pidhīyati;**shuts the door on bad things they’ve done,*";
P_HTM[6641]="*Somaṃ lokaṃ pabhāseti,**lights up the world,*";
P_HTM[6642]="*abbhā muttova candimā.**like the moon freed from a cloud.*";
P_HTM[6643]="*Yo have daharo bhikkhu,**A young mendicant,*";
P_HTM[6644]="*yuñjati buddhasāsane;**devoted to the teaching of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6645]="*Somaṃ lokaṃ pabhāseti,**lights up the world,*";
P_HTM[6646]="*abbhā muttova candimā.**like the moon freed from a cloud.*";
P_HTM[6647]="*Disā hi me dhammakathaṃ suṇantu,**May even my enemies hear a Dhamma talk!*";
P_HTM[6648]="*Disā hi me yuñjantu buddhasāsane;**May even my enemies devote themselves to the Buddha’s teaching!*";
P_HTM[6649]="*Disā hi me te manujā bhajantu,**May even my enemies associate with those good people*";
P_HTM[6650]="*Ye dhammamevādapayanti santo.**who establish others in the Dhamma!*";
P_HTM[6651]="*Disā hi me khantivādānaṃ,**May even my enemies hear Dhamma at the right time,*";
P_HTM[6652]="*avirodhappasaṃsīnaṃ;**from those who speak on acceptance,*";
P_HTM[6653]="*Suṇantu dhammaṃ kālena,**praising acquiescence;*";
P_HTM[6654]="*tañca anuvidhīyantu.**and may they follow that path!*";
P_HTM[6655]="*Na hi jātu so mamaṃ hiṃse,**For then they’d surely wish no harm*";
P_HTM[6656]="*aññaṃ vā pana kiñci naṃ;**upon myself or others.*";
P_HTM[6657]="*Pappuyya paramaṃ santiṃ,**Having arrived at ultimate peace,*";
P_HTM[6658]="*rakkheyya tasathāvare.**they’d look after creatures firm and frail.*";
P_HTM[6659]="*Udakañhi nayanti nettikā,**For irrigators guide the water,*";
P_HTM[6660]="*Usukārā namayanti tejanaṃ;**and fletchers straighten arrows;*";
P_HTM[6661]="*Dāruṃ namayanti tacchakā,**carpenters carve timber—*";
P_HTM[6662]="*Attānaṃ damayanti paṇḍitā.**but the astute tame themselves.*";
P_HTM[6663]="*Daṇḍeneke damayanti,**Some tame by using the rod,*";
P_HTM[6664]="*aṅkusehi kasāhi ca;**some with goads, and some with whips.*";
P_HTM[6665]="*Adaṇḍena asatthena,**But the poised one tamed me*";
P_HTM[6666]="*ahaṃ dantomhi tādinā.**without rod or sword.*";
P_HTM[6667]="*Ahiṃsakoti me nāmaṃ,**My name is ‘Harmless’,*";
P_HTM[6668]="*hiṃsakassa pure sato;**though I used to be harmful.*";
P_HTM[6669]="*Ajjāhaṃ saccanāmomhi,**The name I bear today is true,*";
P_HTM[6670]="*na naṃ hiṃsāmi kiñci naṃ.**for I do no harm to anyone.*";
P_HTM[6671]="*Coro ahaṃ pure āsiṃ,**I used to be a bandit,*";
P_HTM[6672]="*aṅgulimāloti vissuto;**the notorious Aṅgulimāla.*";
P_HTM[6673]="*Vuyhamāno mahoghena,**Swept away in a great flood,*";
P_HTM[6674]="*buddhaṃ saraṇamāgamaṃ.**I went to the Buddha as a refuge.*";
P_HTM[6675]="*Lohitapāṇi pure āsiṃ,**I used to have blood on my hands,*";
P_HTM[6676]="*aṅgulimāloti vissuto;**the notorious Aṅgulimāla.*";
P_HTM[6677]="*Saraṇagamanaṃ passa,**See the refuge I’ve found—*";
P_HTM[6678]="*bhavanetti samūhatā.**the attachment to rebirth is eradicated.*";
P_HTM[6679]="*Tādisaṃ kammaṃ katvāna,**I’ve done many of the sort of deeds*";
P_HTM[6680]="*bahuṃ duggatigāminaṃ;**that lead to a bad destination.*";
P_HTM[6681]="*Phuṭṭho kammavipākena,**The result of my deeds has already hit me,*";
P_HTM[6682]="*aṇaṇo bhuñjāmi bhojanaṃ.**so I enjoy my food free of debt.*";
P_HTM[6683]="*Pamādamanuyuñjanti,**Fools and unintelligent people*";
P_HTM[6684]="*bālā dummedhino janā;**devote themselves to negligence.*";
P_HTM[6685]="*Appamādañca medhāvī,**But the intelligent protect diligence*";
P_HTM[6686]="*dhanaṃ seṭṭhaṃva rakkhati.**as their best treasure.*";
P_HTM[6687]="*Mā pamādamanuyuñjetha,**Don’t devote yourself to negligence,*";
P_HTM[6688]="*mā kāmarati santhavaṃ;**or delight in sexual intimacy.*";
P_HTM[6689]="*Appamatto hi jhāyanto,**For if you’re diligent and practice absorption,*";
P_HTM[6690]="*pappoti vipulaṃ sukhaṃ.**you’ll attain abundant happiness.*";
P_HTM[6691]="*Svāgataṃ nāpagataṃ,**It was welcome, not unwelcome,*";
P_HTM[6692]="*nayidaṃ dummantitaṃ mama;**the advice I got was good.*";
P_HTM[6693]="*Saṃvibhattesu dhammesu,**Of teachings that are shared,*";
P_HTM[6694]="*yaṃ seṭṭhaṃ tadupāgamaṃ.**I encountered the best.*";
P_HTM[6695]="*Svāgataṃ nāpagataṃ,**It was welcome, not unwelcome,*";
P_HTM[6696]="*nayidaṃ dummantitaṃ mama;**the advice I got was good.*";
P_HTM[6697]="*Tisso vijjā anuppattā,**I’ve attained the three knowledges*";
P_HTM[6698]="*kataṃ buddhassa sāsanan”ti.**and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”*";
P_HTM[6699]="*Aṅgulimālasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6700]="*87. Piyajātikasutta**Born From the Beloved*";
P_HTM[6701]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6702]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6703]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa gahapatissa ekaputtako piyo manāpo kālaṅkato hoti.**Now at that time a certain householder’s dear and beloved only child passed away.*";
P_HTM[6704]="*Tassa kālaṃkiriyāya neva kammantā paṭibhanti na bhattaṃ paṭibhāti.**After their death he didn’t feel like working or eating.*";
P_HTM[6705]="*So āḷāhanaṃ gantvā kandati:**He would go to the cemetery and wail,*";
P_HTM[6706]="*“kahaṃ, ekaputtaka, kahaṃ, ekaputtakā”ti.**“Where are you, my only child? Where are you, my only child?”*";
P_HTM[6707]="*Atha kho so gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then he went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[6708]="*“na kho te, gahapati, sake citte ṭhitassa indriyāni, atthi te indriyānaṃ aññathattan”ti.**“Householder, you look like someone who’s not in their right mind; your faculties have deteriorated.”*";
P_HTM[6709]="*“Kiñhi me, bhante, indriyānaṃ nāññathattaṃ bhavissati;**“And how, sir, could my faculties not have deteriorated?*";
P_HTM[6710]="*mayhañhi, bhante, ekaputto piyo manāpo kālaṅkato.**For my dear and beloved only child has passed away.*";
P_HTM[6711]="*Tassa kālaṃkiriyāya neva kammantā paṭibhanti, na bhattaṃ paṭibhāti.**Since their death I haven’t felt like working or eating.*";
P_HTM[6712]="*Sohaṃ āḷāhanaṃ gantvā kandāmi:**I go to the cemetery and wail:*";
P_HTM[6713]="*‘kahaṃ, ekaputtaka, kahaṃ, ekaputtakā’”ti.**‘Where are you, my only child? Where are you, my only child?’”*";
P_HTM[6714]="*“Evametaṃ, gahapati, evametaṃ, gahapati.**“That’s so true, householder! That’s so true, householder!*";
P_HTM[6715]="*Piyajātikā hi, gahapati, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā”ti.**For our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.”*";
P_HTM[6716]="*“Kassa kho nāmetaṃ, bhante, evaṃ bhavissati:**“Sir, who on earth could ever think such a thing!*";
P_HTM[6717]="*‘piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[6718]="*Piyajātikā hi kho, bhante, ānandasomanassā piyappabhavikā”ti.**For our loved ones are a source of joy and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[6719]="*Atha kho so gahapati bhagavato bhāsitaṃ anabhinanditvā paṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**Disagreeing with the Buddha’s statement, rejecting it, he got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[6720]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā akkhadhuttā bhagavato avidūre akkhehi dibbanti.**Now at that time several gamblers were playing dice not far from the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6721]="*Atha kho so gahapati yena te akkhadhuttā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā akkhadhutte etadavoca:**That householder approached them and told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[6722]="*“idhāhaṃ, bhonto, yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho maṃ, bhonto, samaṇo gotamo etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[6723]="*‘na kho te, gahapati, sake citte ṭhitassa indriyāni, atthi te indriyānaṃ aññathattan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6724]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhonto, samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ etadavocaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[6725]="*‘kiñhi me, bhante, indriyānaṃ nāññathattaṃ bhavissati;* **";
P_HTM[6726]="*mayhañhi, bhante, ekaputtako piyo manāpo kālaṅkato.* **";
P_HTM[6727]="*Tassa kālaṅkiriyāya neva kammantā paṭibhanti, na bhattaṃ paṭibhāti.* **";
P_HTM[6728]="*Sohaṃ āḷāhanaṃ gantvā kandāmi—* **";
P_HTM[6729]="*kahaṃ, ekaputtaka, kahaṃ, ekaputtakā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6730]="*‘Evametaṃ, gahapati, evametaṃ, gahapati.* **";
P_HTM[6731]="*Piyajātikā hi, gahapati, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6732]="*‘Kassa kho nāmetaṃ, bhante, evaṃ bhavissati—* **";
P_HTM[6733]="*piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā?* **";
P_HTM[6734]="*Piyajātikā hi kho, bhante, ānandasomanassā piyappabhavikā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6735]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhonto, samaṇassa gotamassa bhāsitaṃ anabhinanditvā paṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamin”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6736]="*“Evametaṃ, gahapati, evametaṃ, gahapati.**“That’s so true, householder! That’s so true, householder!*";
P_HTM[6737]="*Piyajātikā hi, gahapati, ānandasomanassā piyappabhavikā”ti.**For our loved ones are a source of joy and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[6738]="*Atha kho so gahapati “sameti me akkhadhuttehī”ti pakkāmi.**Thinking, “The gamblers and I are in agreement,” the householder left.*";
P_HTM[6739]="*Atha kho idaṃ kathāvatthu anupubbena rājantepuraṃ pāvisi.**Eventually that topic of discussion reached the royal compound.*";
P_HTM[6740]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo mallikaṃ deviṃ āmantesi:**Then King Pasenadi addressed Queen Mallikā,*";
P_HTM[6741]="*“idaṃ te, mallike, samaṇena gotamena bhāsitaṃ:**“Mallika, your ascetic Gotama said this:*";
P_HTM[6742]="*‘piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’”ti.**‘Our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.’”*";
P_HTM[6743]="*“Sacetaṃ, mahārāja, bhagavatā bhāsitaṃ, evametan”ti.**“If that’s what the Buddha said, great king, then that’s how it is.”*";
P_HTM[6744]="*“Evameva panāyaṃ mallikā yaññadeva samaṇo gotamo bhāsati taṃ tadevassa abbhanumodati:**“No matter what the ascetic Gotama says, Mallikā agrees with him:*";
P_HTM[6745]="*‘Sacetaṃ, mahārāja, bhagavatā bhāsitaṃ evametan’ti.**‘If that’s what the Buddha said, great king, then that’s how it is.’*";
P_HTM[6746]="*Seyyathāpi nāma, yaññadeva ācariyo antevāsissa bhāsati taṃ tadevassa antevāsī abbhanumodati:**You’re just like a student who agrees with everything their teacher says.*";
P_HTM[6747]="*‘evametaṃ, ācariya, evametaṃ, ācariyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6748]="*Evameva kho tvaṃ, mallike, yaññadeva samaṇo gotamo bhāsati taṃ tadevassa abbhanumodasi:* **";
P_HTM[6749]="*‘Sacetaṃ, mahārāja, bhagavatā bhāsitaṃ evametan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6750]="*Cara pire, mallike, vinassā”ti.**Go away, Mallikā, get out of here!”*";
P_HTM[6751]="*Atha kho mallikā devī nāḷijaṅghaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ āmantesi:**Then Queen Mallikā addressed the brahmin Nāḷijaṅgha,*";
P_HTM[6752]="*“ehi tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha:**“Please, brahmin, go to the Buddha, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Ask him if he is healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[6753]="*‘mallikā, bhante, devī bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’ti;* **";
P_HTM[6754]="*evañca vadehi:**And then say:*";
P_HTM[6755]="*‘bhāsitā nu kho, bhante, bhagavatā esā vācā—**‘Sir, did the Buddha make this statement:*";
P_HTM[6756]="*piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’ti.**“Our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress”?’*";
P_HTM[6757]="*Yathā te bhagavā byākaroti taṃ sādhukaṃ uggahetvā mama āroceyyāsi.**Remember well how the Buddha answers and tell it to me.*";
P_HTM[6758]="*Na hi tathāgatā vitathaṃ bhaṇantī”ti.**For Realized Ones say nothing that is not so.”*";
P_HTM[6759]="*“Evaṃ, bhotī”ti kho nāḷijaṅgho brāhmaṇo mallikāya deviyā paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**“Yes, ma’am,” he replied. He went to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[6760]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho nāḷijaṅgho brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6761]="*“mallikā, bho gotama, devī bhoto gotamassa pāde sirasā vandati; appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati;**“Master Gotama, Queen Mallikā bows with her head to your feet. She asks if you are healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[6762]="*evañca vadeti:**And she asks whether*";
P_HTM[6763]="*‘bhāsitā nu kho, bhante, bhagavatā esā vācā—**the Buddha made this statement:*";
P_HTM[6764]="*piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’”ti.**‘Our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.’”*";
P_HTM[6765]="*“Evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa, evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa.**“That’s right, brahmin, that’s right!*";
P_HTM[6766]="*Piyajātikā hi, brāhmaṇa, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikāti.**For our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[6767]="*Tadamināpetaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā.**And here’s a way to understand how our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[6768]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imissāyeva sāvatthiyā aññatarissā itthiyā mātā kālamakāsi.**Once upon a time right here in Sāvatthī a certain woman’s mother passed away.*";
P_HTM[6769]="*Sā tassā kālakiriyāya ummattikā khittacittā rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamāha:**And because of that she went mad and lost her mind. She went from street to street and from square to square saying,*";
P_HTM[6770]="*‘api me mātaraṃ addassatha, api me mātaraṃ addassathā’ti?**‘Has anyone seen my mother? Has anyone seen my mother?’*";
P_HTM[6771]="*Imināpi kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikāti.**And here’s another way to understand how our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[6772]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imissāyeva sāvatthiyā aññatarissā itthiyā pitā kālamakāsi …**Once upon a time right here in Sāvatthī a certain woman’s father …*";
P_HTM[6773]="*bhātā kālamakāsi …**brother …*";
P_HTM[6774]="*bhaginī kālamakāsi …**sister …*";
P_HTM[6775]="*putto kālamakāsi …**son …*";
P_HTM[6776]="*dhītā kālamakāsi …**daughter …*";
P_HTM[6777]="*sāmiko kālamakāsi.**husband passed away.*";
P_HTM[6778]="*Sā tassa kālakiriyāya ummattikā khittacittā rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamāha:**And because of that she went mad and lost her mind. She went from street to street and from square to square saying,*";
P_HTM[6779]="*‘api me sāmikaṃ addassatha, api me sāmikaṃ addassathā’ti?**‘Has anyone seen my husband? Has anyone seen my husband?’*";
P_HTM[6780]="*Imināpi kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikāti.**And here’s another way to understand how our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[6781]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imissāyeva sāvatthiyā aññatarassa purisassa mātā kālamakāsi.**Once upon a time right here in Sāvatthī a certain man’s mother …*";
P_HTM[6782]="*So tassā kālakiriyāya ummattako khittacitto rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamāha:* **";
P_HTM[6783]="*‘api me mātaraṃ addassatha, api me mātaraṃ addassathā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[6784]="*Imināpi kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikāti.* **";
P_HTM[6785]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imissāyeva sāvatthiyā aññatarassa purisassa pitā kālamakāsi …**father …*";
P_HTM[6786]="*bhātā kālamakāsi …**brother …*";
P_HTM[6787]="*bhaginī kālamakāsi …**sister …*";
P_HTM[6788]="*putto kālamakāsi …**son …*";
P_HTM[6789]="*dhītā kālamakāsi …**daughter …*";
P_HTM[6790]="*pajāpati kālamakāsi.**wife passed away.*";
P_HTM[6791]="*So tassā kālakiriyāya ummattako khittacitto rathikāya rathikaṃ siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evamāha:**And because of that he went mad and lost his mind. He went from street to street and from square to square saying,*";
P_HTM[6792]="*‘api me pajāpatiṃ addassatha, api me pajāpatiṃ addassathā’ti?**‘Has anyone seen my wife? Has anyone seen my wife?’*";
P_HTM[6793]="*Imināpi kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikāti.**And here’s another way to understand how our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[6794]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, brāhmaṇa, imissāyeva sāvatthiyā aññatarā itthī ñātikulaṃ agamāsi.**Once upon a time right here in Sāvatthī a certain woman went to live with her relative’s family.*";
P_HTM[6795]="*Tassā te ñātakā sāmikaṃ acchinditvā aññassa dātukāmā.**But her relatives wanted to divorce her from her husband and give her to another,*";
P_HTM[6796]="*Sā ca taṃ na icchati.**who she didn’t want.*";
P_HTM[6797]="*Atha kho sā itthī sāmikaṃ etadavoca:**So she told her husband about this.*";
P_HTM[6798]="*‘ime, maṃ, ayyaputta, ñātakā tvaṃ acchinditvā aññassa dātukāmā.* **";
P_HTM[6799]="*Ahañca taṃ na icchāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6800]="*Atha kho so puriso taṃ itthiṃ dvidhā chetvā attānaṃ upphālesi:**But he cut her in two and disemboweled himself, thinking,*";
P_HTM[6801]="*‘ubho pecca bhavissāmā’ti.**‘We shall be together after death.’*";
P_HTM[6802]="*Imināpi kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā”ti.**That’s another way to understand how our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.”*";
P_HTM[6803]="*Atha kho nāḷijaṅgho brāhmaṇo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena mallikā devī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā yāvatako ahosi bhagavatā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ mallikāya deviyā ārocesi. Atha kho mallikā devī yena rājā pasenadi kosalo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca:**Then Nāḷijaṅgha the brahmin, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha said, got up from his seat, went to Queen Mallikā, and told her of all they had discussed. Then Queen Mallikā approached King Pasenadi and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6804]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[6805]="*piyā te vajirī kumārī”ti?**Do you love Princess Vajirī?”*";
P_HTM[6806]="*“Evaṃ, mallike, piyā me vajirī kumārī”ti.**“Indeed I do, Mallikā.”*";
P_HTM[6807]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[6808]="*vajiriyā te kumāriyā vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**If she were to decay and perish, would sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress arise in you?”*";
P_HTM[6809]="*“Vajiriyā me, mallike, kumāriyā vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā jīvitassapi siyā aññathattaṃ, kiṃ pana me na uppajjissanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**“If she were to decay and perish, my life would fall apart. How could sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress not arise in me?”*";
P_HTM[6810]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“This is what the Buddha was referring to when he said:*";
P_HTM[6811]="*‘piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’ti.**‘Our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.’*";
P_HTM[6812]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[6813]="*piyā te vāsabhā khattiyā”ti?**Do you love Lady Vāsabhā? …*";
P_HTM[6814]="*“Evaṃ, mallike, piyā me vāsabhā khattiyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6815]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, vāsabhāya te khattiyāya vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6816]="*“Vāsabhāya me, mallike, khattiyāya vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā jīvitassapi siyā aññathattaṃ, kiṃ pana me na uppajjissanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6817]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[6818]="*‘piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6819]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, piyo te viṭaṭūbho senāpatī”ti?**Do you love your son, General Viḍūḍabha? …*";
P_HTM[6820]="*“Evaṃ, mallike, piyo me viṭaṭūbho senāpatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6821]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, viṭaṭūbhassa te senāpatissa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6822]="*“Viṭaṭūbhassa me, mallike, senāpatissa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā jīvitassapi siyā aññathattaṃ, kiṃ pana me na uppajjissanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6823]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[6824]="*‘piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[6825]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, piyā te ahan”ti?**Do you love me?”*";
P_HTM[6826]="*“Evaṃ, mallike, piyā mesi tvan”ti.**“Indeed I do love you, Mallikā.”*";
P_HTM[6827]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[6828]="*mayhaṃ te vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**If I were to decay and perish, would sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress arise in you?”*";
P_HTM[6829]="*“Tuyhañhi me, mallike, vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā jīvitassapi siyā aññathattaṃ, kiṃ pana me na uppajjissanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**“If you were to decay and perish, my life would fall apart. How could sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress not arise in me?”*";
P_HTM[6830]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“This is what the Buddha was referring to when he said:*";
P_HTM[6831]="*‘piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’ti.**‘Our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.’*";
P_HTM[6832]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[6833]="*piyā te kāsikosalā”ti?**Do you love the realms of Kāsi and Kosala?”*";
P_HTM[6834]="*“Evaṃ, mallike, piyā me kāsikosalā.**“Indeed I do, Mallikā.*";
P_HTM[6835]="*Kāsikosalānaṃ, mallike, ānubhāvena kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhoma, mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhāremā”ti.**It’s due to the bounty of Kāsi and Kosala that we use sandalwood imported from Kāsi and wear garlands, perfumes, and makeup.”*";
P_HTM[6836]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**“What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[6837]="*kāsikosalānaṃ te vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**If these realms were to decay and perish, would sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress arise in you?”*";
P_HTM[6838]="*“Kāsikosalānañhi, mallike, vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā jīvitassapi siyā aññathattaṃ, kiṃ pana me na uppajjissanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**“If they were to decay and perish, my life would fall apart. How could sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress not arise in me?”*";
P_HTM[6839]="*“Idaṃ kho taṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**“This is what the Buddha was referring to when he said:*";
P_HTM[6840]="*‘piyajātikā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā piyappabhavikā’”ti.**‘Our loved ones are a source of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.’”*";
P_HTM[6841]="*“Acchariyaṃ, mallike, abbhutaṃ, mallike.**“It’s incredible, Mallikā, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[6842]="*Yāvañca so bhagavā paññāya ativijjha maññe passati.**how far the Buddha sees with penetrating wisdom, it seems to me.*";
P_HTM[6843]="*Ehi, mallike, ācamehī”ti.**Come, Mallikā, rinse my hands.”*";
P_HTM[6844]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā tikkhattuṃ udānaṃ udānesi:**Then King Pasenadi got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and was inspired to exclaim three times:*";
P_HTM[6845]="*“Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**“Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[6846]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[6847]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassā”ti.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!”*";
P_HTM[6848]="*Piyajātikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6849]="*88. Bāhitikasutta**The Imported Cloth*";
P_HTM[6850]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6851]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6852]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms.*";
P_HTM[6853]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena pubbārāmo migāramātupāsādo tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya.**He wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he went to the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother, for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[6854]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo ekapuṇḍarīkaṃ nāgaṃ abhiruhitvā sāvatthiyā niyyāti divā divassa.**Now at that time King Pasenadi of Kosala mounted the Single Lotus Elephant and drove out from Sāvatthī in the middle of the day.*";
P_HTM[6855]="*Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**He saw Ānanda coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[6856]="*Disvāna sirivaḍḍhaṃ mahāmattaṃ āmantesi:**and said to the minister Sirivaḍḍha,*";
P_HTM[6857]="*“āyasmā no eso, samma sirivaḍḍha, ānando”ti.**“My dear Sirivaḍḍha, isn’t that Venerable Ānanda?”*";
P_HTM[6858]="*“Evaṃ, mahārāja, āyasmā eso ānando”ti.**“Indeed it is, great king.”*";
P_HTM[6859]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi:**Then King Pasenadi addressed a man,*";
P_HTM[6860]="*“ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena āyasmato ānandassa pāde sirasā vandāhi:**“Please, mister, go to Venerable Ānanda, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him:*";
P_HTM[6861]="*‘rājā, bhante, pasenadi kosalo āyasmato ānandassa pāde sirasā vandatī’ti;**‘Sir, King Pasenadi of Kosala bows with his head at your feet.’*";
P_HTM[6862]="*evañca vadehi:**And then say:*";
P_HTM[6863]="*‘sace kira, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa na kiñci accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ, āgametu kira, bhante, āyasmā ānando muhuttaṃ anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti.**‘Sir, if you have no urgent business, please wait a moment out of compassion.’”*";
P_HTM[6864]="*“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho so puriso rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭissutvā yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, Your Majesty,” that man replied. He did as the king asked.*";
P_HTM[6865]="*“rājā, bhante, pasenadi kosalo āyasmato ānandassa pāde sirasā vandati;* **";
P_HTM[6866]="*evañca vadeti:* **";
P_HTM[6867]="*‘sace kira, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa na kiñci accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ, āgametu kira, bhante, āyasmā ānando muhuttaṃ anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6868]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā ānando tuṇhībhāvena.**Ānanda consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[6869]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yāvatikā nāgassa bhūmi nāgena gantvā nāgā paccorohitvā pattikova yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**Then King Pasenadi rode on the elephant as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached Ānanda on foot. He bowed, stood to one side, and said to Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[6870]="*“sace, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa na kiñci accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ, sādhu, bhante, āyasmā ānando yena aciravatiyā nadiyā tīraṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti.**“Sir, if you have no urgent business, it would be nice of you to go to the bank of the Aciravatī river out of compassion.”*";
P_HTM[6871]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā ānando tuṇhībhāvena.**Ānanda consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[6872]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena aciravatiyā nadiyā tīraṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle paññatte āsane nisīdi.**He went to the river bank and sat at the root of a certain tree on a seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[6873]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yāvatikā nāgassa bhūmi nāgena gantvā nāgā paccorohitvā pattikova yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**Then King Pasenadi rode on the elephant as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached Ānanda on foot. He bowed, stood to one side, and said to Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[6874]="*“idha, bhante, āyasmā ānando hatthatthare nisīdatū”ti.**“Here, Venerable Ānanda, sit on this elephant rug.”*";
P_HTM[6875]="*“Alaṃ, mahārāja.**“Enough, great king,*";
P_HTM[6876]="*Nisīda tvaṃ;**you sit on it.*";
P_HTM[6877]="*nisinno ahaṃ sake āsane”ti.**I’m sitting on my own seat.”*";
P_HTM[6878]="*Nisīdi kho rājā pasenadi kosalo paññatte āsane.**So the king sat down on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[6879]="*Nisajja kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[6880]="*“kiṃ nu kho, bhante ānanda, so bhagavā tathārūpaṃ kāyasamācāraṃ samācareyya, yvāssa kāyasamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehī”ti?**“Sir, might the Buddha engage in the sort of behavior—by way of body, speech, or mind—that is faulted by ascetics and brahmins?”*";
P_HTM[6881]="*“Na kho, mahārāja, so bhagavā tathārūpaṃ kāyasamācāraṃ samācareyya, yvāssa kāyasamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti.**“No, great king, the Buddha would not engage in the sort of behavior that is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.”*";
P_HTM[6882]="*“Kiṃ pana, bhante ānanda, so bhagavā tathārūpaṃ vacīsamācāraṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6883]="*manosamācāraṃ samācareyya, yvāssa manosamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6884]="*“Na kho, mahārāja, so bhagavā tathārūpaṃ manosamācāraṃ samācareyya, yvāssa manosamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6885]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[6886]="*Yañhi mayaṃ, bhante, nāsakkhimhā pañhena paripūretuṃ taṃ, bhante, āyasmatā ānandena pañhassa veyyākaraṇena paripūritaṃ.**For I couldn’t fully express the question, but Ānanda’s answer completed it for me.*";
P_HTM[6887]="*Ye te, bhante, bālā abyattā ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā paresaṃ vaṇṇaṃ vā avaṇṇaṃ vā bhāsanti, na mayaṃ taṃ sārato paccāgacchāma;**I don’t believe that praise or criticism of others spoken by incompetent fools, without examining or scrutinizing, is the most important thing.*";
P_HTM[6888]="*ye pana te, bhante, paṇḍitā viyattā medhāvino anuvicca pariyogāhetvā paresaṃ vaṇṇaṃ vā avaṇṇaṃ vā bhāsanti, mayaṃ taṃ sārato paccāgacchāma.**Rather, I believe that praise or criticism of others spoken by competent and intelligent people after examining and scrutinizing is the most important thing.*";
P_HTM[6889]="*Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, kāyasamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti?**But sir, what kind of bodily behavior is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins?”*";
P_HTM[6890]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro akusalo”.**“Unskillful behavior.”*";
P_HTM[6891]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro akusalo”?**“But what kind of bodily behavior is unskillful?”*";
P_HTM[6892]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro sāvajjo”.**“Blameworthy behavior.”*";
P_HTM[6893]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro sāvajjo”?**“But what kind of bodily behavior is blameworthy?”*";
P_HTM[6894]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro sabyābajjho”.**“Hurtful behavior.”*";
P_HTM[6895]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro sabyābajjho”?**“But what kind of bodily behavior is hurtful?”*";
P_HTM[6896]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro dukkhavipāko”.**“Behavior that results in suffering.”*";
P_HTM[6897]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro dukkhavipāko”?**“But what kind of bodily behavior results in suffering?”*";
P_HTM[6898]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati.**“Bodily behavior that leads to hurting yourself, hurting others, and hurting both,*";
P_HTM[6899]="*Tassa akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti;**and which makes unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline.*";
P_HTM[6900]="*evarūpo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti.**That kind of bodily behavior is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.”*";
P_HTM[6901]="*“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, vacīsamācāro … pe …**“But what kind of verbal behavior …*";
P_HTM[6902]="*manosamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti?**mental behavior is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins?” …*";
P_HTM[6903]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro akusalo”.* **";
P_HTM[6904]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro akusalo”?* **";
P_HTM[6905]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro sāvajjo”.* **";
P_HTM[6906]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro sāvajjo”?* **";
P_HTM[6907]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro sabyābajjho”.* **";
P_HTM[6908]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro sabyābajjho”?* **";
P_HTM[6909]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro dukkhavipāko”.* **";
P_HTM[6910]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro dukkhavipāko”?* **";
P_HTM[6911]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro attabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati.**“Mental behavior that leads to hurting yourself, hurting others, and hurting both,*";
P_HTM[6912]="*Tassa akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti;**and which makes unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline.*";
P_HTM[6913]="*evarūpo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro opārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti.**That kind of mental behavior is faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.”*";
P_HTM[6914]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bhante ānanda, so bhagavā sabbesaṃyeva akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti?**“Sir, does the Buddha praise giving up all these unskillful things?”*";
P_HTM[6915]="*“Sabbākusaladhammapahīno kho, mahārāja, tathāgato kusaladhammasamannāgato”ti.**“Great king, the Realized One has given up all unskillful things and possesses skillful things.”*";
P_HTM[6916]="*“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, kāyasamācāro anopārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti?**“But sir, what kind of bodily behavior is not faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins?”*";
P_HTM[6917]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro kusalo”.**“Skillful behavior.”*";
P_HTM[6918]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro kusalo”?**“But what kind of bodily behavior is skillful?”*";
P_HTM[6919]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro anavajjo”.**“Blameless behavior.”*";
P_HTM[6920]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro anavajjo”?**“But what kind of bodily behavior is blameless?”*";
P_HTM[6921]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro abyābajjho”.**“Pleasing behavior.”*";
P_HTM[6922]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro abyābajjho”?**“But what kind of bodily behavior is pleasing?”*";
P_HTM[6923]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro sukhavipāko”.**“Behavior that results in happiness.”*";
P_HTM[6924]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, kāyasamācāro sukhavipāko”?**“But what kind of bodily behavior results in happiness?”*";
P_HTM[6925]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati.**“Bodily behavior that leads to pleasing yourself, pleasing others, and pleasing both,*";
P_HTM[6926]="*Tassa akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti.**and which makes unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow.*";
P_HTM[6927]="*Evarūpo kho, mahārāja, kāyasamācāro anopārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti.**That kind of bodily behavior is not faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.”*";
P_HTM[6928]="*“Katamo pana, bhante ānanda, vacīsamācāro … pe …**“But what kind of verbal behavior …*";
P_HTM[6929]="*manosamācāro anopārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti?**mental behavior is not faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins?” …*";
P_HTM[6930]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro kusalo”.* **";
P_HTM[6931]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro kusalo”?* **";
P_HTM[6932]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro anavajjo”.* **";
P_HTM[6933]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro anavajjo”?* **";
P_HTM[6934]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro abyābajjho”.* **";
P_HTM[6935]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro abyābajjho”?* **";
P_HTM[6936]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro sukhavipāko”.* **";
P_HTM[6937]="*“Katamo pana, bhante, manosamācāro sukhavipāko”?* **";
P_HTM[6938]="*“Yo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro nevattabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na parabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi saṃvattati.**“Mental behavior that leads to pleasing yourself, pleasing others, and pleasing both,*";
P_HTM[6939]="*Tassa akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti.**and which makes unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow.*";
P_HTM[6940]="*Evarūpo kho, mahārāja, manosamācāro anopārambho samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhī”ti.**That kind of mental behavior is not faulted by sensible ascetics and brahmins.”*";
P_HTM[6941]="*“Kiṃ pana, bhante ānanda, so bhagavā sabbesaṃyeva kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti?**“Sir, does the Buddha praise embracing all these skillful things?”*";
P_HTM[6942]="*“Sabbākusaladhammapahīno kho, mahārāja, tathāgato kusaladhammasamannāgato”ti.**“Great king, the Realized One has given up all unskillful things and possesses skillful things.”*";
P_HTM[6943]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[6944]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ, bhante, āyasmatā ānandena.**How well this was said by Venerable Ānanda!*";
P_HTM[6945]="*Iminā ca mayaṃ, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa subhāsitena attamanābhiraddhā.**I’m delighted and satisfied with what you’ve expressed so well.*";
P_HTM[6946]="*Evaṃ attamanābhiraddhā ca mayaṃ, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa subhāsitena.**So much so that*";
P_HTM[6947]="*Sace, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa hatthiratanaṃ kappeyya, hatthiratanampi mayaṃ āyasmato ānandassa dadeyyāma.**if an elephant treasure was suitable for you, I would give you one.*";
P_HTM[6948]="*Sace, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa assaratanaṃ kappeyya, assaratanampi mayaṃ āyasmato ānandassa dadeyyāma.**If a horse treasure was suitable for you, I would give you one.*";
P_HTM[6949]="*Sace, bhante, āyasmato ānandassa gāmavaraṃ kappeyya, gāmavarampi mayaṃ āyasmato ānandassa dadeyyāma.**If a prize village was suitable for you, I would give you one.*";
P_HTM[6950]="*Api ca, bhante, mayampetaṃ jānāma:**But, sir, I know that*";
P_HTM[6951]="*‘netaṃ āyasmato ānandassa kappatī’ti.**these things are not suitable for you.*";
P_HTM[6952]="*Ayaṃ me, bhante, bāhitikā raññā māgadhena ajātasattunā vedehiputtena vatthanāḷiyā pakkhipitvā pahitā soḷasasamā āyāmena, aṭṭhasamā vitthārena.**This imported cloth was sent to me by King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha packed in a parasol case. It’s exactly sixteen measures long and eight wide.*";
P_HTM[6953]="*Taṃ, bhante, āyasmā ānando paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti.**May Venerable Ānanda please accept it out of compassion.”*";
P_HTM[6954]="*“Alaṃ, mahārāja, paripuṇṇaṃ me ticīvaran”ti.**“Enough, great king. My three robes are complete.”*";
P_HTM[6955]="*“Ayaṃ, bhante, aciravatī nadī diṭṭhā āyasmatā ceva ānandena amhehi ca.**“Sir, we have both seen this river Aciravatī*";
P_HTM[6956]="*Yadā uparipabbate mahāmegho abhippavuṭṭho hoti, athāyaṃ aciravatī nadī ubhato kūlāni saṃvissandantī gacchati;**when it has rained heavily in the mountains, and the river overflows both its banks.*";
P_HTM[6957]="*evameva kho, bhante, āyasmā ānando imāya bāhitikāya attano ticīvaraṃ karissati.**In the same way, Venerable Ānanda can make a set of three robes for himself from this imported cloak.*";
P_HTM[6958]="*Yaṃ panāyasmato ānandassa purāṇaṃ ticīvaraṃ taṃ sabrahmacārīhi saṃvibhajissati.**And you can share your old robes with your fellow monks.*";
P_HTM[6959]="*Evāyaṃ amhākaṃ dakkhiṇā saṃvissandantī maññe gamissati.**In this way my religious donation will come to overflow, it seems to me.*";
P_HTM[6960]="*Paṭiggaṇhātu, bhante, āyasmā ānando bāhitikan”ti.**Please accept the imported cloth.”*";
P_HTM[6961]="*Paṭiggahesi kho āyasmā ānando bāhitikaṃ.**So Ānanda accepted it.*";
P_HTM[6962]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**Then King Pasenadi said to him,*";
P_HTM[6963]="*“handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante ānanda, gacchāma;**“Well, now, sir, I must go.*";
P_HTM[6964]="*bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[6965]="*“Yassadāni tvaṃ, mahārāja, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, great king, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[6966]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo āyasmato ānandassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Then King Pasenadi approved and agreed with what Ānanda said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled Ānanda, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[6967]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando acirapakkantassa rañño pasenadissa kosalassa yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Soon after he left, Ānanda went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[6968]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako ahosi raññā pasenadinā kosalena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi.**and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[6969]="*Tañca bāhitikaṃ bhagavato pādāsi.**He presented the cloth to the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6970]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[6971]="*“lābhā, bhikkhave, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa, suladdhalābhā, bhikkhave, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa;**“Mendicants, King Pasenadi is lucky, so very lucky,*";
P_HTM[6972]="*yaṃ rājā pasenadi kosalo labhati ānandaṃ dassanāya, labhati payirupāsanāyā”ti.**to get to see Ānanda and pay homage to him.”*";
P_HTM[6973]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6974]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6975]="*Bāhitikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6976]="*89. Dhammacetiyasutta**Shrines to the Teaching*";
P_HTM[6977]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6978]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati medāḷupaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near the Sakyan town named Medeḷumpa.*";
P_HTM[6979]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo nagarakaṃ anuppatto hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time King Pasenadi of Kosala had arrived at Nagaraka on some business.*";
P_HTM[6980]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo dīghaṃ kārāyanaṃ āmantesi:**Then he addressed Dīgha Kārāyana,*";
P_HTM[6981]="*“yojehi, samma kārāyana, bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni, uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma subhūmiṃ dassanāyā”ti.**“My good Kārāyana, harness the finest chariots. We will go to a park and see the scenery.”*";
P_HTM[6982]="*“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho dīgho kārāyano rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭissutvā bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni yojāpetvā rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭivedesi:**“Yes, Your Majesty,” replied Dīgha Kārāyana. He harnessed the chariots and informed the king,*";
P_HTM[6983]="*“yuttāni kho te, deva, bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni.**“Sire, the finest chariots are harnessed.*";
P_HTM[6984]="*Yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**Please go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[6985]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhadraṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi nagarakamhā niyyāsi mahaccā rājānubhāvena.**Then King Pasenadi mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out in full royal pomp from Nagaraka,*";
P_HTM[6986]="*Yena ārāmo tena pāyāsi.**heading for the park grounds.*";
P_HTM[6987]="*Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova ārāmaṃ pāvisi.**He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and entered the park on foot.*";
P_HTM[6988]="*Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo ārāme jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno rukkhamūlāni pāsādikāni pasādanīyāni appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni paṭisallānasāruppāni.**As he was going for a walk in the park he saw roots of trees that were impressive and inspiring, quiet and still, far from the madding crowd, remote from human settlements, and fit for retreat.*";
P_HTM[6989]="*Disvāna bhagavantaṃyeva ārabbha sati udapādi:**The sight reminded him right away of the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6990]="*“imāni kho tāni rukkhamūlāni pāsādikāni pasādanīyāni appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni paṭisallānasāruppāni, yattha sudaṃ mayaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ payirupāsāma arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti.**“These roots of trees, so impressive and inspiring, are like those where we used to pay homage to the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[6991]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo dīghaṃ kārāyanaṃ āmantesi:**He addressed Dīgha Kārāyana,*";
P_HTM[6992]="*“imāni kho, samma kārāyana, tāni rukkhamūlāni pāsādikāni pasādanīyāni appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni paṭisallānasāruppāni, yattha sudaṃ mayaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ payirupāsāma arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ.**“These roots of trees, so impressive and inspiring, are like those where we used to pay homage to the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6993]="*Kahaṃ nu kho, samma kārāyana, etarahi so bhagavā viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti?**My good Kārāyana, where is that Buddha at present?”*";
P_HTM[6994]="*“Atthi, mahārāja, medāḷupaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ nigamo.**“Great king, there is a Sakyan town named Medaḷumpa.*";
P_HTM[6995]="*Tattha so bhagavā etarahi viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti.**That’s where the Buddha is now staying.”*";
P_HTM[6996]="*“Kīvadūre pana, samma kārāyana, nagarakamhā medāḷupaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ nigamo hotī”ti?**“But how far away is that town?”*";
P_HTM[6997]="*“Na dūre, mahārāja;**“Not far, great king,*";
P_HTM[6998]="*tīṇi yojanāni;**it’s three leagues.*";
P_HTM[6999]="*sakkā divasāvasesena gantun”ti.**We can get there while it’s still light.”*";
P_HTM[7000]="*“Tena hi, samma kārāyana, yojehi bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni, gamissāma mayaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti.**“Well then, harness the chariots, and we shall go to see the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[7001]="*“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho dīgho kārāyano rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭissutvā bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni yojāpetvā rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭivedesi:**“Yes, Your Majesty,” replied Dīgha Kārāyana. He harnessed the chariots and informed the king,*";
P_HTM[7002]="*“yuttāni kho te, deva, bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni.**“Sire, the finest chariots are harnessed.*";
P_HTM[7003]="*Yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**Please go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[7004]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhadraṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi nagarakamhā yena medāḷupaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ nigamo tena pāyāsi.**Then King Pasenadi mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out from Nagaraka to Medaḷumpa.*";
P_HTM[7005]="*Teneva divasāvasesena medāḷupaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ nigamaṃ sampāpuṇi.**He reached the town while it was still light*";
P_HTM[7006]="*Yena ārāmo tena pāyāsi.**and headed for the park grounds.*";
P_HTM[7007]="*Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova ārāmaṃ pāvisi.**He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and entered the monastery on foot.*";
P_HTM[7008]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū abbhokāse caṅkamanti.**At that time several mendicants were walking meditation in the open air.*";
P_HTM[7009]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca:**King Pasenadi of Kosala went up to them and said,*";
P_HTM[7010]="*“kahaṃ nu kho, bhante, etarahi so bhagavā viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho?**“Sirs, where is the Blessed One at present, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha?*";
P_HTM[7011]="*Dassanakāmā hi mayaṃ taṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhan”ti.**For I want to see him.”*";
P_HTM[7012]="*“Eso, mahārāja, vihāro saṃvutadvāro. Tena appasaddo upasaṅkamitvā ataramāno āḷindaṃ pavisitvā ukkāsitvā aggaḷaṃ ākoṭehi. Vivarissati bhagavā te dvāran”ti.**“Great king, that’s his dwelling, with the door closed. Approach it quietly, without hurrying; go onto the porch, clear your throat, and knock with the latch. The Buddha will open the door.”*";
P_HTM[7013]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo tattheva khaggañca uṇhīsañca dīghassa kārāyanassa pādāsi.**The king right away presented his sword and turban to Dīgha Kārāyana,*";
P_HTM[7014]="*Atha kho dīghassa kārāyanassa etadahosi:**who thought,*";
P_HTM[7015]="*“rahāyati kho dāni rājā, idheva dāni mayā ṭhātabban”ti.**“Now the king seeks privacy. I should wait here.”*";
P_HTM[7016]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yena so vihāro saṃvutadvāro tena appasaddo upasaṅkamitvā ataramāno āḷindaṃ pavisitvā ukkāsitvā aggaḷaṃ ākoṭesi. Vivari bhagavā dvāraṃ.**Then the king approached the Buddha’s dwelling and knocked, and the Buddha opened the door.*";
P_HTM[7017]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo vihāraṃ pavisitvā bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavato pādāni mukhena ca paricumbati, pāṇīhi ca parisambāhati, nāmañca sāveti:**King Pasenadi entered the dwelling, and bowed with his head to the Buddha’s feet, caressing them and covering them with kisses, and pronounced his name:*";
P_HTM[7018]="*“rājāhaṃ, bhante, pasenadi kosalo;**“Sir, I am Pasenadi, king of Kosala!*";
P_HTM[7019]="*rājāhaṃ, bhante, pasenadi kosalo”ti.**I am Pasenadi, king of Kosala!”*";
P_HTM[7020]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, mahārāja, atthavasaṃ sampassamāno imasmiṃ sarīre evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karosi, mittūpahāraṃ upadaṃsesī”ti?**“But great king, for what reason do you demonstrate such utmost devotion for this body, conveying your manifest love?”*";
P_HTM[7021]="*“Atthi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti:**“Sir, I infer about the Buddha from the teaching:*";
P_HTM[7022]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[7023]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhante, passāmi eke samaṇabrāhmaṇe pariyantakataṃ brahmacariyaṃ carante dasapi vassāni, vīsampi vassāni, tiṃsampi vassāni, cattārīsampi vassāni.**It happens, sir, that I see some ascetics and brahmins leading the spiritual life only for a limited period: ten, twenty, thirty, or forty years.*";
P_HTM[7024]="*Te aparena samayena sunhātā suvilittā kappitakesamassū pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā paricārenti.**Some time later—nicely bathed and anointed, with hair and beard dressed—they amuse themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[7025]="*Idha panāhaṃ, bhante, bhikkhū passāmi yāvajīvaṃ āpāṇakoṭikaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carante.**But here I see the mendicants leading the spiritual life entirely full and pure as long as they live, to their last breath.*";
P_HTM[7026]="*Na kho panāhaṃ, bhante, ito bahiddhā aññaṃ evaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ samanupassāmi.**I don’t see any other spiritual life elsewhere so full and pure.*";
P_HTM[7027]="*Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti:**That’s why I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching:*";
P_HTM[7028]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[7029]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, rājānopi rājūhi vivadanti, khattiyāpi khattiyehi vivadanti, brāhmaṇāpi brāhmaṇehi vivadanti, gahapatayopi gahapatīhi vivadanti, mātāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi mātarā vivadati, pitāpi puttena vivadati, puttopi pitarā vivadati, bhātāpi bhaginiyā vivadati, bhaginīpi bhātarā vivadati, sahāyopi sahāyena vivadati.**Furthermore, kings fight with kings, aristocrats fight with aristocrats, brahmins fight with brahmins, householders fight with householders. A mother fights with her child, child with mother, father with child, and child with father. Brother fights with brother, brother with sister, sister with brother, and friend fights with friend.*";
P_HTM[7030]="*Idha panāhaṃ, bhante, bhikkhū passāmi samagge sammodamāne avivadamāne khīrodakībhūte aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassante viharante.**But here I see the mendicants living in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each other with kindly eyes.*";
P_HTM[7031]="*Na kho panāhaṃ, bhante, ito bahiddhā aññaṃ evaṃ samaggaṃ parisaṃ samanupassāmi.**I don’t see any other assembly elsewhere so harmonious.*";
P_HTM[7032]="*Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti:**So I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching:*";
P_HTM[7033]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[7034]="*Puna caparāhaṃ, bhante, ārāmena ārāmaṃ, uyyānena uyyānaṃ anucaṅkamāmi anuvicarāmi.**Furthermore, I have walked and wandered from monastery to monastery and from park to park.*";
P_HTM[7035]="*Sohaṃ tattha passāmi eke samaṇabrāhmaṇe kise lūkhe dubbaṇṇe uppaṇḍuppaṇḍukajāte dhamanisanthatagatte, na viya maññe cakkhuṃ bandhante janassa dassanāya.**There I’ve seen some ascetics and brahmins who are thin, haggard, pale, and veiny—hardly a captivating sight, you’d think.*";
P_HTM[7036]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:**It occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[7037]="*‘addhā ime āyasmanto anabhiratā vā brahmacariyaṃ caranti, atthi vā tesaṃ kiñci pāpaṃ kammaṃ kataṃ paṭicchannaṃ;**‘Clearly these venerables lead the spiritual life dissatisfied, or they’re hiding some bad deed they’ve done.*";
P_HTM[7038]="*tathā hi ime āyasmanto kisā lūkhā dubbaṇṇā uppaṇḍuppaṇḍukajātā dhamanisanthatagattā, na viya maññe cakkhuṃ bandhanti janassa dassanāyā’ti.**That’s why they’re thin, haggard, pale, and veiny—hardly a captivating sight, you’d think.’*";
P_HTM[7039]="*Tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi:**I went up to them and said:*";
P_HTM[7040]="*‘kiṃ nu kho tumhe āyasmanto kisā lūkhā dubbaṇṇā uppaṇḍuppaṇḍukajātā dhamanisanthatagattā, na viya maññe cakkhuṃ bandhatha janassa dassanāyā’ti?**‘Venerables, why are you so thin, haggard, pale, and veiny—hardly a captivating sight, you’d think?’*";
P_HTM[7041]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say:*";
P_HTM[7042]="*‘bandhukarogo no, mahārājā’ti.**‘We have jaundice, great king.’*";
P_HTM[7043]="*Idha panāhaṃ, bhante, bhikkhū passāmi haṭṭhapahaṭṭhe udaggudagge abhiratarūpe pīṇindriye appossukke pannalome paradattavutte migabhūtena cetasā viharante.**But here I see mendicants always smiling and joyful, obviously happy, with cheerful faces, living relaxed, unruffled, surviving on charity, their hearts free as a wild deer.*";
P_HTM[7044]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:**It occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[7045]="*‘addhā ime āyasmanto tassa bhagavato sāsane uḷāraṃ pubbenāparaṃ visesaṃ jānanti;**‘Clearly these venerables have realized a higher distinction in the Buddha’s instructions than they had before.*";
P_HTM[7046]="*tathā hi ime āyasmanto haṭṭhapahaṭṭhā udaggudaggā abhiratarūpā pīṇindriyā appossukkā pannalomā paradattavuttā migabhūtena cetasā viharantī’ti.**That’s why these venerables are always smiling and joyful, obviously happy, with cheerful faces, living relaxed, unruffled, surviving on charity, their hearts free as a wild deer.’*";
P_HTM[7047]="*Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti:**So I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching:*";
P_HTM[7048]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[7049]="*Puna caparāhaṃ, bhante, rājā khattiyo muddhāvasitto;**Furthermore, as an anointed king*";
P_HTM[7050]="*pahomi ghātetāyaṃ vā ghātetuṃ, jāpetāyaṃ vā jāpetuṃ, pabbājetāyaṃ vā pabbājetuṃ.**I am able to execute, fine, or banish those who are guilty.*";
P_HTM[7051]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, aḍḍakaraṇe nisinnassa antarantarā kathaṃ opātenti.**Yet when I’m sitting in judgment they interrupt me.*";
P_HTM[7052]="*Sohaṃ na labhāmi:**And I can’t get them*";
P_HTM[7053]="*‘mā me bhonto aḍḍakaraṇe nisinnassa antarantarā kathaṃ opātetha, kathāpariyosānaṃ me bhonto āgamentū’ti.**to stop interrupting me and wait until I’ve finished speaking.*";
P_HTM[7054]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, antarantarā kathaṃ opātenti.* **";
P_HTM[7055]="*Idha panāhaṃ, bhante, bhikkhū passāmi;**But here I’ve seen the mendicants*";
P_HTM[7056]="*yasmiṃ samaye bhagavā anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ deseti, neva tasmiṃ samaye bhagavato sāvakānaṃ khipitasaddo vā hoti ukkāsitasaddo vā.**while the Buddha is teaching an assembly of many hundreds, and there is no sound of his disciples coughing or clearing their throats.*";
P_HTM[7057]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhante, bhagavā anekasatāya parisāya dhammaṃ deseti.**Once it so happened that the Buddha was teaching an assembly of many hundreds.*";
P_HTM[7058]="*Tatraññataro bhagavato sāvako ukkāsi.**Then one of his disciples cleared their throat.*";
P_HTM[7059]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro sabrahmacārī jaṇṇukena ghaṭṭesi:**And one of their spiritual companions nudged them with their knee, to indicate:*";
P_HTM[7060]="*‘appasaddo āyasmā hotu, māyasmā saddamakāsi; satthā no bhagavā dhammaṃ desetī’ti.**‘Hush, venerable, don’t make a sound! Our teacher, the Blessed One, is teaching!’*";
P_HTM[7061]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:**It occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[7062]="*‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[7063]="*Adaṇḍena vata kira, bho, asatthena evaṃ suvinītā parisā bhavissatī’ti.**how an assembly can be so well trained without rod or sword!’*";
P_HTM[7064]="*Na kho panāhaṃ, bhante, ito bahiddhā aññaṃ evaṃ suvinītaṃ parisaṃ samanupassāmi.**I don’t see any other assembly elsewhere so well trained.*";
P_HTM[7065]="*Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti:**So I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching:*";
P_HTM[7066]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[7067]="*Puna caparāhaṃ, bhante, passāmi idhekacce khattiyapaṇḍite nipuṇe kataparappavāde vālavedhirūpe. Te bhindantā maññe caranti paññāgatena diṭṭhigatāni.**Furthermore, I’ve seen some clever aristocrats who are subtle, accomplished in the doctrines of others, hair-splitters. You’d think they live to demolish convictions with their intellect.*";
P_HTM[7068]="*Te suṇanti:**They hear:*";
P_HTM[7069]="*‘samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osarissatī’ti.**‘So, gentlemen, that ascetic Gotama will come down to such and such village or town.’*";
P_HTM[7070]="*Te pañhaṃ abhisaṅkharonti:**They formulate a question, thinking:*";
P_HTM[7071]="*‘imaṃ mayaṃ pañhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā pucchissāma.**‘We’ll approach the ascetic Gotama and ask him this question.*";
P_HTM[7072]="*Evañce no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evamassa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāma;**If he answers like this, we’ll refute him like that;*";
P_HTM[7073]="*evañcepi no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evampissa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāmā’ti.**and if he answers like that, we’ll refute him like this.’*";
P_HTM[7074]="*Te suṇanti:**When they hear that*";
P_HTM[7075]="*‘samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osaṭo’ti.**he has come down*";
P_HTM[7076]="*Te yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamanti.**they approach him.*";
P_HTM[7077]="*Te bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti.**The Buddha educates, encourages, fires up, and inspires them with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[7078]="*Te bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā na ceva bhagavantaṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti, kuto vādaṃ āropessanti?**They don’t even get around to asking their question to the Buddha, so how could they refute his answer?*";
P_HTM[7079]="*Aññadatthu bhagavato sāvakā sampajjanti.**Invariably, they become his disciples.*";
P_HTM[7080]="*Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti:**So I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching:*";
P_HTM[7081]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[7082]="*Puna caparāhaṃ, bhante, passāmi idhekacce brāhmaṇapaṇḍite … pe …**Furthermore, I see some clever brahmins …*";
P_HTM[7083]="*gahapatipaṇḍite … pe …**some clever householders …*";
P_HTM[7084]="*samaṇapaṇḍite nipuṇe kataparappavāde vālavedhirūpe. Te bhindantā maññe caranti paññāgatena diṭṭhigatāni.**some clever ascetics who are subtle, accomplished in the doctrines of others, hair-splitters. …*";
P_HTM[7085]="*Te suṇanti:* **";
P_HTM[7086]="*‘samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osarissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7087]="*Te pañhaṃ abhisaṅkharonti:* **";
P_HTM[7088]="*‘imaṃ mayaṃ pañhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ upasaṅkamitvā pucchissāma.* **";
P_HTM[7089]="*Evañce no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evamassa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāma;* **";
P_HTM[7090]="*evañcepi no puṭṭho evaṃ byākarissati, evampissa mayaṃ vādaṃ āropessāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7091]="*Te suṇanti:* **";
P_HTM[7092]="*‘samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo amukaṃ nāma gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā osaṭo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7093]="*Te yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamanti.* **";
P_HTM[7094]="*Te bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti.* **";
P_HTM[7095]="*Te bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā na ceva bhagavantaṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti, kuto vādaṃ āropessanti?**They don’t even get around to asking their question to the Buddha, so how could they refute his answer?*";
P_HTM[7096]="*Aññadatthu bhagavantaṃyeva okāsaṃ yācanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya.**Invariably, they ask the ascetic Gotama for the chance to go forth.*";
P_HTM[7097]="*Te bhagavā pabbājeti.**And he gives them the going-forth.*";
P_HTM[7098]="*Te tathāpabbajitā samānā ekā vūpakaṭṭhā appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharantā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti.**Soon after going forth, living withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, they realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. They live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[7099]="*Te evamāhaṃsu:**They say:*";
P_HTM[7100]="*‘manaṃ vata, bho, anassāma; manaṃ vata, bho, panassāma’.**‘We were almost lost! We almost perished!*";
P_HTM[7101]="*Mayañhi pubbe assamaṇāva samānā samaṇāmhāti paṭijānimhā, abrāhmaṇāva samānā brāhmaṇāmhāti paṭijānimhā, anarahantova samānā arahantāmhāti paṭijānimhā.**For we used to claim that we were ascetics, brahmins, and perfected ones, but we were none of these things.*";
P_HTM[7102]="*‘Idāni khomha samaṇā, idāni khomha brāhmaṇā, idāni khomha arahanto’ti.**But now we really are ascetics, brahmins, and perfected ones!’*";
P_HTM[7103]="*Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti:**So I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching:*";
P_HTM[7104]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[7105]="*Puna caparāhaṃ, bhante, ime isidattapurāṇā thapatayo mamabhattā mamayānā, ahaṃ nesaṃ jīvikāya dātā, yasassa āhattā;**Furthermore, these chamberlains Isidatta and Purāṇa share my meals and my carriages. I give them a livelihood and bring them renown.*";
P_HTM[7106]="*atha ca pana no tathā mayi nipaccakāraṃ karonti yathā bhagavati.**And yet they don’t show me the same level of devotion that they show to the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7107]="*Bhūtapubbāhaṃ, bhante, senaṃ abbhuyyāto samāno ime ca isidattapurāṇā thapatayo vīmaṃsamāno aññatarasmiṃ sambādhe āvasathe vāsaṃ upagacchiṃ.**Once it so happened that while I was leading a military campaign and testing Isidatta and Purāṇa I took up residence in a cramped house.*";
P_HTM[7108]="*Atha kho, bhante, ime isidattapurāṇā thapatayo bahudeva rattiṃ dhammiyā kathāya vītināmetvā, yato ahosi bhagavā tato sīsaṃ katvā maṃ pādato karitvā nipajjiṃsu.**They spent most of the night discussing the teaching, then they lay down with their heads towards where the Buddha was and their feet towards me.*";
P_HTM[7109]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:**It occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[7110]="*‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[7111]="*Ime isidattapurāṇā thapatayo mamabhattā mamayānā, ahaṃ nesaṃ jīvikāya dātā, yasassa āhattā;**These chamberlains Isidatta and Purāṇa share my meals and my carriages. I give them a livelihood and bring them renown.*";
P_HTM[7112]="*atha ca pana no tathā mayi nipaccakāraṃ karonti yathā bhagavati.**And yet they don’t show me the same level of devotion that they show to the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7113]="*Addhā ime āyasmanto tassa bhagavato sāsane uḷāraṃ pubbenāparaṃ visesaṃ jānantī’ti.**Clearly these venerables have realized a higher distinction in the Buddha’s instructions than they had before.’*";
P_HTM[7114]="*Ayampi kho me, bhante, bhagavati dhammanvayo hoti:**So I infer this about the Buddha from the teaching:*";
P_HTM[7115]="*‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho’ti.**‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained. The Saṅgha is practicing well.’*";
P_HTM[7116]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, bhagavāpi khattiyo, ahampi khattiyo;**Furthermore, the Buddha is an aristocrat, and so am I.*";
P_HTM[7117]="*bhagavāpi kosalo, ahampi kosalo;**The Buddha is Kosalan, and so am I.*";
P_HTM[7118]="*bhagavāpi āsītiko, ahampi āsītiko.**The Buddha is eighty years old, and so am I.*";
P_HTM[7119]="*Yampi, bhante, bhagavāpi khattiyo ahampi khattiyo, bhagavāpi kosalo ahampi kosalo, bhagavāpi āsītiko ahampi āsītiko;**Since this is so,*";
P_HTM[7120]="*imināvārahāmevāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavati paramanipaccakāraṃ kātuṃ, mittūpahāraṃ upadaṃsetuṃ.**it’s proper for me to show the Buddha such utmost devotion and demonstrate such friendship.*";
P_HTM[7121]="*Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante, gacchāma;**Well, now, sir, I must go.*";
P_HTM[7122]="*bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[7123]="*“Yassadāni tvaṃ, mahārāja, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, great king, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[7124]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Then King Pasenadi got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[7125]="*Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkantassa rañño pasenadissa kosalassa bhikkhū āmantesi:**Soon after the king had left, the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[7126]="*“eso, bhikkhave, rājā pasenadi kosalo dhammacetiyāni bhāsitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto.**“Mendicants, before he got up and left, King Pasenadi spoke shrines to the teaching.*";
P_HTM[7127]="*Uggaṇhatha, bhikkhave, dhammacetiyāni;**Learn these shrines to the teaching!*";
P_HTM[7128]="*pariyāpuṇātha, bhikkhave, dhammacetiyāni;**Memorize these shrines to the teaching!*";
P_HTM[7129]="*dhāretha, bhikkhave, dhammacetiyāni.**Remember these shrines to the teaching!*";
P_HTM[7130]="*Atthasaṃhitāni, bhikkhave, dhammacetiyāni ādibrahmacariyakānī”ti.**These shrines to the teaching are beneficial and relate to the fundamentals of the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[7131]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7132]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7133]="*Dhammacetiyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7134]="*90. Kaṇṇakatthalasutta**At Kaṇṇakatthala*";
P_HTM[7135]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7136]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruññāyaṃ viharati kaṇṇakatthale migadāye.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Ujuñña, in the deer park at Kaṇṇakatthala.*";
P_HTM[7137]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo uruññaṃ anuppatto hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time King Pasenadi of Kosala had arrived at Ujuñña on some business.*";
P_HTM[7138]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi:**Then he addressed a man,*";
P_HTM[7139]="*“ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha:**“Please, mister, go to the Buddha, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Ask him if he is healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[7140]="*‘rājā, bhante, pasenadi kosalo bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’ti;* **";
P_HTM[7141]="*evañca vadehi:**And then say:*";
P_HTM[7142]="*‘ajja kira, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo pacchābhattaṃ bhuttapātarāso bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī’”ti.**‘Sir, King Pasenadi of Kosala will come to see you today when he has finished breakfast.’”*";
P_HTM[7143]="*“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho so puriso rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, Your Majesty,” that man replied. He did as the king asked.*";
P_HTM[7144]="*“rājā, bhante, pasenadi kosalo bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati;* **";
P_HTM[7145]="*evañca vadeti:* **";
P_HTM[7146]="*‘ajja kira, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo pacchābhattaṃ bhuttapātarāso bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7147]="*Assosuṃ kho somā ca bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī:**The sisters Somā and Sakulā heard this.*";
P_HTM[7148]="*“ajja kira rājā pasenadi kosalo pacchābhattaṃ bhuttapātarāso bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7149]="*Atha kho somā ca bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ bhattābhihāre upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:**While the meal was being served, they approached the king and said,*";
P_HTM[7150]="*“tena hi, mahārāja, amhākampi vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha:**“Great king, since you are going to the Buddha, please bow in our name with your head to his feet. Ask him if he is healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.”*";
P_HTM[7151]="*‘somā ca, bhante, bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7152]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo pacchābhattaṃ bhuttapātarāso yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had finished breakfast, King Pasenadi went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[7153]="*“somā ca, bhante, bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī”ti.**“Sir, the sisters Somā and Sakulā bow with their heads to your feet. They ask if you are healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.”*";
P_HTM[7154]="*“Kiṃ pana, mahārāja, somā ca bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī aññaṃ dūtaṃ nālatthun”ti?**“But, great king, couldn’t they get any other messenger?”*";
P_HTM[7155]="*“Assosuṃ kho, bhante, somā ca bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī:**So Pasenadi explained the circumstances of the message.*";
P_HTM[7156]="*‘ajja kira rājā pasenadi kosalo pacchābhattaṃ bhuttapātarāso bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7157]="*Atha kho, bhante, somā ca bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī maṃ bhattābhihāre upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[7158]="*‘tena hi, mahārāja, amhākampi vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha—* **";
P_HTM[7159]="*somā ca bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7160]="*“Sukhiniyo hontu tā, mahārāja, somā ca bhaginī sakulā ca bhaginī”ti.**The Buddha said, “May the sisters Somā and Sakulā be happy, great king.”*";
P_HTM[7161]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the king said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7162]="*“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, samaṇo gotamo evamāha:**“I have heard, sir, that the ascetic Gotama says this:*";
P_HTM[7163]="*‘natthi so samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā yo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānissati, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’ti.**‘There is no ascetic or brahmin who will claim to be all-knowing and all-seeing, to know and see everything without exception: that is not possible.’*";
P_HTM[7164]="*Ye te, bhante, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo evamāha—natthi so samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā yo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānissati, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’ti; kacci te, bhante, bhagavato vuttavādino, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti?**Do those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and not misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”*";
P_HTM[7165]="*“Ye te, mahārāja, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo evamāha—natthi so samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā yo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānissati, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’ti; na me te vuttavādino, abbhācikkhanti ca pana maṃ te asatā abhūtenā”ti.**“Great king, those who say this do not repeat what I have said. They misrepresent me with what is false and untrue.”*";
P_HTM[7166]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo viṭaṭūbhaṃ senāpatiṃ āmantesi:**Then King Pasenadi addressed General Viḍūḍabha,*";
P_HTM[7167]="*“ko nu kho, senāpati, imaṃ kathāvatthuṃ rājantepure abbhudāhāsī”ti?**“General, who introduced this topic of discussion to the royal compound?”*";
P_HTM[7168]="*“Sañjayo, mahārāja, brāhmaṇo ākāsagotto”ti.**“It was Sañjaya, great king, the brahmin of the Ākāsa clan.”*";
P_HTM[7169]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi:**Then the king addressed a man,*";
P_HTM[7170]="*“ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, mama vacanena sañjayaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ ākāsagottaṃ āmantehi:**“Please, mister, in my name tell Sañjaya that*";
P_HTM[7171]="*‘rājā taṃ, bhante, pasenadi kosalo āmantetī’”ti.**King Pasenadi summons him.”*";
P_HTM[7172]="*“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho so puriso rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭissutvā yena sañjayo brāhmaṇo ākāsagotto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā sañjayaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ ākāsagottaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, Your Majesty,” that man replied. He did as the king asked.*";
P_HTM[7173]="*“rājā taṃ, bhante, pasenadi kosalo āmantetī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7174]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the king said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7175]="*“siyā nu kho, bhante, bhagavatā aññadeva kiñci sandhāya bhāsitaṃ, tañca jano aññathāpi paccāgaccheyya.**“Sir, might the Buddha have spoken in reference to one thing, but that person believed it was something else?*";
P_HTM[7176]="*Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, bhagavā abhijānāti vācaṃ bhāsitā”ti?**How then do you recall making this statement?”*";
P_HTM[7177]="*“Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, mahārāja, abhijānāmi vācaṃ bhāsitā:**“Great king, I recall making this statement:*";
P_HTM[7178]="*‘natthi so samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā yo sakideva sabbaṃ ñassati, sabbaṃ dakkhiti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’”ti.**‘There is no ascetic or brahmin who knows all and sees all simultaneously: that is not possible.’”*";
P_HTM[7179]="*“Heturūpaṃ, bhante, bhagavā āha; saheturūpaṃ, bhante, bhagavā āha:**“What the Buddha says appears reasonable.*";
P_HTM[7180]="*‘natthi so samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā yo sakideva sabbaṃ ñassati, sabbaṃ dakkhiti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7181]="*Cattārome, bhante, vaṇṇā—**Sir, there are these four classes:*";
P_HTM[7182]="*khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā.**aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers.*";
P_HTM[7183]="*Imesaṃ nu kho, bhante, catunnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ siyā viseso siyā nānākaraṇan”ti?**Is there any difference between them?”*";
P_HTM[7184]="*“Cattārome, mahārāja, vaṇṇā—* **";
P_HTM[7185]="*khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā.* **";
P_HTM[7186]="*Imesaṃ kho, mahārāja, catunnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ dve vaṇṇā aggamakkhāyanti—**“Of the four classes, two are said to be preeminent—*";
P_HTM[7187]="*khattiyā ca brāhmaṇā ca—**the aristocrats and the brahmins.*";
P_HTM[7188]="*yadidaṃ abhivādanapaccuṭṭhānaañjalikammasāmīcikammānī”ti.**That is, when it comes to bowing down, rising up, greeting with joined palms, and observing proper etiquette.”*";
P_HTM[7189]="*“Nāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ diṭṭhadhammikaṃ pucchāmi;**“Sir, I am not asking you about the present life,*";
P_HTM[7190]="*samparāyikāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ pucchāmi.**but about the life to come.”*";
P_HTM[7191]="*Cattārome, bhante, vaṇṇā—* **";
P_HTM[7192]="*khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā.* **";
P_HTM[7193]="*Imesaṃ nu kho, bhante, catunnaṃ vaṇṇānaṃ siyā viseso siyā nānākaraṇan”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7194]="*“Pañcimāni, mahārāja, padhāniyaṅgāni.**“Great king, there are these five factors that support meditation.*";
P_HTM[7195]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[7196]="*Idha, mahārāja, bhikkhu saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:**It’s when a mendicant has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:*";
P_HTM[7197]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti;**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[7198]="*appābādho hoti appātaṅko samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya;**They are rarely ill or unwell. Their stomach digests well, being neither too hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation.*";
P_HTM[7199]="*asaṭho hoti amāyāvī yathābhūtaṃ attānaṃ āvikattā satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu;**They’re not devious or deceitful. They reveal themselves honestly to the Teacher or sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[7200]="*āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu;**They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[7201]="*paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammādukkhakkhayagāminiyā—**They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[7202]="*imāni kho, mahārāja, pañca padhāniyaṅgāni.**These are the five factors that support meditation.*";
P_HTM[7203]="*Cattārome, mahārāja, vaṇṇā—**There are these four classes:*";
P_HTM[7204]="*khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā.**aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers.*";
P_HTM[7205]="*Te cassu imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgatā;**If they had these five factors that support meditation,*";
P_HTM[7206]="*ettha pana nesaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**that would be for their lasting welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[7207]="*“Cattārome, bhante, vaṇṇā—**“Sir, there are these four classes:*";
P_HTM[7208]="*khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā.**aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers.*";
P_HTM[7209]="*Te cassu imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgatā;**If they had these five factors that support meditation,*";
P_HTM[7210]="*ettha pana nesaṃ, bhante, siyā viseso siyā nānākaraṇan”ti?**would there be any difference between them?”*";
P_HTM[7211]="*“Ettha kho nesāhaṃ, mahārāja, padhānavemattataṃ vadāmi.**“In that case, I say it is the diversity of their efforts in meditation.*";
P_HTM[7212]="*Seyyathāpissu, mahārāja, dve hatthidammā vā assadammā vā godammā vā sudantā suvinītā, dve hatthidammā vā assadammā vā godammā vā adantā avinītā.**Suppose there was a pair of elephants or horses or oxen in training who were well tamed and well trained. And there was a pair who were not tamed or trained.*";
P_HTM[7213]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[7214]="*ye te dve hatthidammā vā assadammā vā godammā vā sudantā suvinītā, api nu te dantāva dantakāraṇaṃ gaccheyyuṃ, dantāva dantabhūmiṃ sampāpuṇeyyun”ti?**Wouldn’t the pair that was well tamed and well trained perform the tasks of the tamed, and reach the level of the tamed?”*";
P_HTM[7215]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7216]="*“Ye pana te dve hatthidammā vā assadammā vā godammā vā adantā avinītā, api nu te adantāva dantakāraṇaṃ gaccheyyuṃ, adantāva dantabhūmiṃ sampāpuṇeyyuṃ, seyyathāpi te dve hatthidammā vā assadammā vā godammā vā sudantā suvinītā”ti?**“But would the pair that was not tamed and trained perform the tasks of the tamed and reach the level of the tamed, just like the tamed pair?”*";
P_HTM[7217]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7218]="*“Evameva kho, mahārāja, yaṃ taṃ saddhena pattabbaṃ appābādhena asaṭhena amāyāvinā āraddhavīriyena paññavatā, taṃ vata assaddho bahvābādho saṭho māyāvī kusīto duppañño pāpuṇissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti.**“In the same way, there are things that must be attained by someone with faith, health, integrity, energy, and wisdom. It’s not possible for a faithless, unhealthy, deceitful, lazy, witless person to attain them.”*";
P_HTM[7219]="*“Heturūpaṃ, bhante, bhagavā āha; saheturūpaṃ, bhante, bhagavā āha.**“What the Buddha says appears reasonable.*";
P_HTM[7220]="*Cattārome, bhante, vaṇṇā—**Sir, there are these four classes:*";
P_HTM[7221]="*khattiyā, brāhmaṇā, vessā, suddā.**aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers.*";
P_HTM[7222]="*Te cassu imehi pañcahi padhāniyaṅgehi samannāgatā te cassu sammappadhānā;**If they had these five factors that support meditation, and if they practiced rightly,*";
P_HTM[7223]="*ettha pana nesaṃ, bhante, siyā viseso siyā nānākaraṇan”ti?**would there be any difference between them?”*";
P_HTM[7224]="*“Ettha kho nesāhaṃ, mahārāja, na kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ vadāmi—yadidaṃ vimuttiyā vimuttiṃ.**“In that case, I say that there is no difference between the freedom of one and the freedom of the other.*";
P_HTM[7225]="*Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso sukkhaṃ sākakaṭṭhaṃ ādāya aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyya;**Suppose a person took dry teak wood and lit a fire and produced heat.*";
P_HTM[7226]="*athāparo puriso sukkhaṃ sālakaṭṭhaṃ ādāya aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyya;**Then another person did the same using sāl wood,*";
P_HTM[7227]="*athāparo puriso sukkhaṃ ambakaṭṭhaṃ ādāya aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyya;**another used mango wood,*";
P_HTM[7228]="*athāparo puriso sukkhaṃ udumbarakaṭṭhaṃ ādāya aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyya.**while another used wood of the cluster fig.*";
P_HTM[7229]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja,**What do you think, great king?*";
P_HTM[7230]="*siyā nu kho tesaṃ aggīnaṃ nānādāruto abhinibbattānaṃ kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ acciyā vā acciṃ, vaṇṇena vā vaṇṇaṃ, ābhāya vā ābhan”ti?**Would there be any difference between the fires produced by these different kinds of wood, that is, in the flame, color, or light?”*";
P_HTM[7231]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7232]="*“Evameva kho, mahārāja, yaṃ taṃ tejaṃ vīriyā nimmathitaṃ padhānābhinibbattaṃ, nāhaṃ tattha kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ vadāmi—yadidaṃ vimuttiyā vimuttin”ti.**“In the same way, when fire has been kindled by energy and produced by effort, I say that there is no difference between the freedom of one and the freedom of the other.”*";
P_HTM[7233]="*“Heturūpaṃ, bhante, bhagavā āha; saheturūpaṃ, bhante, bhagavā āha.**“What the Buddha says appears reasonable.*";
P_HTM[7234]="*Kiṃ pana, bhante, atthi devā”ti?**But sir, do gods absolutely exist?”*";
P_HTM[7235]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, mahārāja, evaṃ vadesi:**“But what exactly are you asking?”*";
P_HTM[7236]="*‘kiṃ pana, bhante, atthi devā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7237]="*“Yadi vā te, bhante, devā āgantāro itthattaṃ yadi vā anāgantāro itthattaṃ”?**“Whether those gods come back to this state of existence or not.”*";
P_HTM[7238]="*“Ye te, mahārāja, devā sabyābajjhā te devā āgantāro itthattaṃ, ye te devā abyābajjhā te devā anāgantāro itthattan”ti.**“Those gods who are subject to affliction come back to this state of existence, but those free of affliction do not come back.”*";
P_HTM[7239]="*Evaṃ vutte, viṭaṭūbho senāpati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, General Viḍūḍabha said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7240]="*“ye te, bhante, devā sabyābajjhā āgantāro itthattaṃ te devā, ye te devā abyābajjhā anāgantāro itthattaṃ te deve tamhā ṭhānā cāvessanti vā pabbājessanti vā”ti?**“Sir, will the gods subject to affliction topple or expel from their place the gods who are free of affliction?”*";
P_HTM[7241]="*Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:**Then Venerable Ānanda thought,*";
P_HTM[7242]="*“ayaṃ kho viṭaṭūbho senāpati rañño pasenadissa kosalassa putto;**“This General Viḍūḍabha is King Pasenadi’s son,*";
P_HTM[7243]="*ahaṃ bhagavato putto.**and I am the Buddha’s son.*";
P_HTM[7244]="*Ayaṃ kho kālo yaṃ putto puttena manteyyā”ti.**Now is the time for one son to confer with another.”*";
P_HTM[7245]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando viṭaṭūbhaṃ senāpatiṃ āmantesi:**So Ānanda addressed General Viḍūḍabha,*";
P_HTM[7246]="*“tena hi, senāpati, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi; yathā te khameyya tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi.**“Well then, general, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as you like.*";
P_HTM[7247]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, senāpati,**What do you think, general?*";
P_HTM[7248]="*yāvatā rañño pasenadissa kosalassa vijitaṃ yattha ca rājā pasenadi kosalo issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kāreti, pahoti tattha rājā pasenadi kosalo samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā puññavantaṃ vā apuññavantaṃ vā brahmacariyavantaṃ vā abrahmacariyavantaṃ vā tamhā ṭhānā cāvetuṃ vā pabbājetuṃ vā”ti?**As far as the dominion of King Pasenadi of Kosala extends, where he rules as sovereign lord, can he topple or expel from that place any ascetic or brahmin, regardless of whether they are good or bad, or whether or not they are genuine spiritual practitioners?”*";
P_HTM[7249]="*“Yāvatā, bho, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa vijitaṃ yattha ca rājā pasenadi kosalo issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kāreti, pahoti tattha rājā pasenadi kosalo samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā puññavantaṃ vā apuññavantaṃ vā brahmacariyavantaṃ vā abrahmacariyavantaṃ vā tamhā ṭhānā cāvetuṃ vā pabbājetuṃ vā”ti.**“He can, mister.”*";
P_HTM[7250]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, senāpati,**“What do you think, general?*";
P_HTM[7251]="*yāvatā rañño pasenadissa kosalassa avijitaṃ yattha ca rājā pasenadi kosalo na issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kāreti, tattha pahoti rājā pasenadi kosalo samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā puññavantaṃ vā apuññavantaṃ vā brahmacariyavantaṃ vā abrahmacariyavantaṃ vā tamhā ṭhānā cāvetuṃ vā pabbājetuṃ vā”ti?**As far as the dominion of King Pasenadi does not extend, where he does not rule as sovereign lord, can he topple or expel from that place any ascetic or brahmin, regardless of whether they are good or bad, or whether or not they are genuine spiritual practitioners?”*";
P_HTM[7252]="*“Yāvatā, bho, rañño pasenadissa kosalassa avijitaṃ yattha ca rājā pasenadi kosalo na issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kāreti, na tattha pahoti rājā pasenadi kosalo samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā puññavantaṃ vā apuññavantaṃ vā brahmacariyavantaṃ vā abrahmacariyavantaṃ vā tamhā ṭhānā cāvetuṃ vā pabbājetuṃ vā”ti.**“He cannot, mister.”*";
P_HTM[7253]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, senāpati,**“What do you think, general?*";
P_HTM[7254]="*sutā te devā tāvatiṃsā”ti?**Have you heard of the gods of the Thirty-Three?”*";
P_HTM[7255]="*“Evaṃ, bho.**“Yes, mister,*";
P_HTM[7256]="*Sutā me devā tāvatiṃsā.**I’ve heard of them,*";
P_HTM[7257]="*Idhāpi bhotā raññā pasenadinā kosalena sutā devā tāvatiṃsā”ti.**and so has the good King Pasenadi.”*";
P_HTM[7258]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, senāpati,**“What do you think, general?*";
P_HTM[7259]="*pahoti rājā pasenadi kosalo deve tāvatiṃse tamhā ṭhānā cāvetuṃ vā pabbājetuṃ vā”ti?**Can King Pasenadi topple or expel from their place the gods of the Thirty-Three?”*";
P_HTM[7260]="*“Dassanampi, bho, rājā pasenadi kosalo deve tāvatiṃse nappahoti, kuto pana tamhā ṭhānā cāvessati vā pabbājessati vā”ti?**“King Pasenadi can’t even see the gods of the Thirty-Three, so how could he possibly topple or expel them from their place?”*";
P_HTM[7261]="*“Evameva kho, senāpati, ye te devā sabyābajjhā āgantāro itthattaṃ te devā, ye te devā abyābajjhā anāgantāro itthattaṃ te deve dassanāyapi nappahonti; kuto pana tamhā ṭhānā cāvessanti vā pabbājessanti vā”ti?**“In the same way, general, the gods subject to affliction can’t even see the gods who are free of affliction, so how could they possibly topple or expel them from their place?”*";
P_HTM[7262]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the king said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7263]="*“konāmo ayaṃ, bhante, bhikkhū”ti?**“Sir, what is this mendicant’s name?”*";
P_HTM[7264]="*“Ānando nāma, mahārājā”ti.**“Ānanda, great king.”*";
P_HTM[7265]="*“Ānando vata bho, ānandarūpo vata bho.**“A joy he is, and a joy he seems!*";
P_HTM[7266]="*Heturūpaṃ, bhante, āyasmā ānando āha; saheturūpaṃ, bhante, āyasmā ānando āha.**What Venerable Ānanda says seems reasonable.*";
P_HTM[7267]="*Kiṃ pana, bhante, atthi brahmā”ti?**But sir, does Brahmā absolutely exist?”*";
P_HTM[7268]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, mahārāja, evaṃ vadesi:**“But what exactly are you asking?”*";
P_HTM[7269]="*‘kiṃ pana, bhante, atthi brahmā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7270]="*“Yadi vā so, bhante, brahmā āgantā itthattaṃ, yadi vā anāgantā itthattan”ti?**“Whether that Brahmā comes back to this state of existence or not.”*";
P_HTM[7271]="*“Yo so, mahārāja, brahmā sabyābajjho so brahmā āgantā itthattaṃ, yo so brahmā abyābajjho so brahmā anāgantā itthattan”ti.**“Any Brahmā who is subject to affliction comes back to this state of existence, but those free of affliction do not come back.”*";
P_HTM[7272]="*Atha kho aññataro puriso rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca:**Then a certain man said to the king,*";
P_HTM[7273]="*“sañjayo, mahārāja, brāhmaṇo ākāsagotto āgato”ti.**“Great king, Sañjaya, the brahmin of the Ākāsa clan, has come.”*";
P_HTM[7274]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo sañjayaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ ākāsagottaṃ etadavoca:**Then King Pasenadi asked Sañjaya,*";
P_HTM[7275]="*“ko nu kho, brāhmaṇa, imaṃ kathāvatthuṃ rājantepure abbhudāhāsī”ti?**“Brahmin, who introduced this topic of discussion to the royal compound?”*";
P_HTM[7276]="*“Viṭaṭūbho, mahārāja, senāpatī”ti.**“It was General Viḍūḍabha, great king.”*";
P_HTM[7277]="*Viṭaṭūbho senāpati evamāha:**But Viḍūḍabha said,*";
P_HTM[7278]="*“sañjayo, mahārāja, brāhmaṇo ākāsagotto”ti.**“It was Sañjaya, great king, the brahmin of the Ākāsa clan.”*";
P_HTM[7279]="*Atha kho aññataro puriso rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca:**Then a certain man said to the king,*";
P_HTM[7280]="*“yānakālo, mahārājā”ti.**“It’s time to depart, great king.”*";
P_HTM[7281]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**So the king said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7282]="*“sabbaññutaṃ mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ apucchimhā, sabbaññutaṃ bhagavā byākāsi;**“Sir, I asked you about omniscience, and you answered.*";
P_HTM[7283]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca, tena camhā attamanā.**I like and accept this, and am satisfied with it.*";
P_HTM[7284]="*Cātuvaṇṇisuddhiṃ mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ apucchimhā, cātuvaṇṇisuddhiṃ bhagavā byākāsi;**I asked you about the four classes,*";
P_HTM[7285]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca, tena camhā attamanā.* **";
P_HTM[7286]="*Adhideve mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ apucchimhā, adhideve bhagavā byākāsi;**about the gods,*";
P_HTM[7287]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca, tena camhā attamanā.* **";
P_HTM[7288]="*Adhibrahmānaṃ mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ apucchimhā, adhibrahmānaṃ bhagavā byākāsi;**and about Brahmā, and you answered in each case.*";
P_HTM[7289]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca, tena camhā attamanā.* **";
P_HTM[7290]="*Yaṃ yadeva ca mayaṃ bhagavantaṃ apucchimhā taṃ tadeva bhagavā byākāsi;**Whatever I asked the Buddha about, he answered.*";
P_HTM[7291]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca, tena camhā attamanā.**I like and accept this, and am satisfied with it.*";
P_HTM[7292]="*Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bhante, gacchāma;**Well, now, sir, I must go.*";
P_HTM[7293]="*bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[7294]="*“Yassadāni tvaṃ, mahārāja, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, great king, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[7295]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmīti.**Then King Pasenadi approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. Then he got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[7296]="*Kaṇṇakatthalasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7297]="*Rājavaggo niṭṭhito catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[7298]="*Ghaṭikāro raṭṭhapālo,* **";
P_HTM[7299]="*maghadevo madhuriyaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7300]="*Bodhi aṅgulimālo ca,* **";
P_HTM[7301]="*piyajātaṃ bāhitikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[7302]="*Dhammacetiyasuttañca,* **";
P_HTM[7303]="*dasamaṃ kaṇṇakatthalaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7304]="*91. Brahmāyusutta**With Brahmāyu*";
P_HTM[7305]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7306]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā videhesu cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Videhans together with a large Saṅgha of five hundred mendicants.*";
P_HTM[7307]="*Tena kho pana samayena brahmāyu brāhmaṇo mithilāyaṃ paṭivasati jiṇṇo vuḍḍho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto, vīsavassasatiko jātiyā, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo.**Now at that time the brahmin Brahmāyu was residing in Mithilā. He was old, elderly, and senior, advanced in years, having reached the final stage of life; he was a hundred and twenty years old. He had mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. He knew philology and grammar, and was well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[7308]="*Assosi kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo:**He heard:*";
P_HTM[7309]="*“samaṇo khalu bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito videhesu cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—is wandering in the land of the Videhans, together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred mendicants.*";
P_HTM[7310]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[7311]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[7312]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[7313]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He explains a teaching that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[7314]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[7315]="*Tena kho pana samayena brahmāyussa brāhmaṇassa uttaro nāma māṇavo antevāsī hoti tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo.**Now at that time the brahmin Brahmāyu had a student named Uttara. He too had mastered the Vedic curriculum*";
P_HTM[7316]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo uttaraṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi:**Brahmāyu told Uttara of the Buddha’s presence in the land of the Videhans, and added:*";
P_HTM[7317]="*“ayaṃ, tāta uttara, samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito videhesu cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi.* **";
P_HTM[7318]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:* **";
P_HTM[7319]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7320]="*sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7321]="*Ehi tvaṃ, tāta uttara, yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ jānāhi, yadi vā taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ tathā santaṃyeva saddo abbhuggato, yadi vā no tathā;**“Please, dear Uttara, go to the ascetic Gotama and find out whether or not he lives up to his reputation.*";
P_HTM[7322]="*yadi vā so bhavaṃ gotamo tādiso, yadi vā na tādiso.* **";
P_HTM[7323]="*Tathā mayaṃ taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ vedissāmā”ti.**Through you I shall learn about Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[7324]="*“Yathā kathaṃ panāhaṃ, bho, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ jānissāmi yadi vā taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ tathā santaṃyeva saddo abbhuggato, yadi vā no tathā;**“But sir, how shall I find out whether or not the ascetic Gotama lives up to his reputation?”*";
P_HTM[7325]="*yadi vā so bhavaṃ gotamo tādiso, yadi vā na tādiso”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7326]="*“Āgatāni kho, tāta uttara, amhākaṃ mantesu dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni, yehi samannāgatassa mahāpurisassa dveyeva gatiyo bhavanti anaññā.**“Dear Uttara, the thirty-two marks of a great man have been handed down in our hymns. A great man who possesses these has only two possible destinies, no other.*";
P_HTM[7327]="*Sace agāraṃ ajjhāvasati, rājā hoti cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato.**If he stays at home he becomes a king, a wheel-turning monarch, a just and principled king. His dominion extends to all four sides, he achieves stability in the country, and he possesses the seven treasures.*";
P_HTM[7328]="*Tassimāni satta ratanāni bhavanti, seyyathidaṃ—**He has the following seven treasures:*";
P_HTM[7329]="*cakkaratanaṃ, hatthiratanaṃ, assaratanaṃ, maṇiratanaṃ, itthiratanaṃ, gahapatiratanaṃ, pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ.**the wheel, the elephant, the horse, the jewel, the woman, the treasurer, and the counselor as the seventh treasure.*";
P_HTM[7330]="*Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā bhavanti sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā.**He has over a thousand sons who are valiant and heroic, crushing the armies of his enemies.*";
P_HTM[7331]="*So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya ajjhāvasati.**After conquering this land girt by sea, he reigns by principle, without rod or sword.*";
P_HTM[7332]="*Sace kho pana agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati, arahaṃ hoti sammāsambuddho loke vivaṭṭacchado.**But if he goes forth from the lay life to homelessness, he becomes a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, who draws back the veil from the world.*";
P_HTM[7333]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, tāta uttara, mantānaṃ dātā;**But, dear Uttara, I am the one who gives the hymns,*";
P_HTM[7334]="*tvaṃ mantānaṃ paṭiggahetā”ti.**and you are the one who receives them.”*";
P_HTM[7335]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho uttaro māṇavo brahmāyussa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā brahmāyuṃ brāhmaṇaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā videhesu yena bhagavā tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Uttara. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled Brahmāyu before setting out for the land of the Videhans where the Buddha was wandering.*";
P_HTM[7336]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Traveling stage by stage, he came to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7337]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[7338]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho uttaro māṇavo bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni samannesi.**and scrutinized his body for the thirty-two marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[7339]="*Addasā kho uttaro māṇavo bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni, yebhuyyena thapetvā dve.**He saw all of them except for two,*";
P_HTM[7340]="*Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—**which he had doubts about:*";
P_HTM[7341]="*kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya ca.**whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue.*";
P_HTM[7342]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then it occurred to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7343]="*“passati kho me ayaṃ uttaro māṇavo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni, yebhuyyena thapetvā dve.**“This brahmin student Uttara sees all the marks except for two,*";
P_HTM[7344]="*Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—**which he has doubts about:*";
P_HTM[7345]="*kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya cā”ti.**whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue.”*";
P_HTM[7346]="*Atha kho bhagavā tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsi yathā addasa uttaro māṇavo bhagavato kosohitaṃ vatthaguyhaṃ.**So the Buddha used his psychic power to will that Uttara would see his retracted private parts.*";
P_HTM[7347]="*Atha kho bhagavā jivhaṃ ninnāmetvā ubhopi kaṇṇasotāni anumasi paṭimasi; ubhopi nāsikasotāni anumasi paṭimasi; kevalampi nalāṭamaṇḍalaṃ jivhāya chādesi.**And he stuck out his tongue and stroked back and forth on his ear holes and nostrils, and covered his entire forehead with his tongue.*";
P_HTM[7348]="*Atha kho uttarassa māṇavassa etadahosi:**Then Uttara thought,*";
P_HTM[7349]="*“samannāgato kho samaṇo gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi.**“The ascetic Gotama possesses the thirty-two marks.*";
P_HTM[7350]="*Yannūnāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ anubandheyyaṃ, iriyāpathamassa passeyyan”ti.**Why don’t I follow him and observe his deportment?”*";
P_HTM[7351]="*Atha kho uttaro māṇavo sattamāsāni bhagavantaṃ anubandhi chāyāva anapāyinī.**So Uttara followed the Buddha like a shadow for seven months.*";
P_HTM[7352]="*Atha kho uttaro māṇavo sattannaṃ māsānaṃ accayena videhesu yena mithilā tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When seven months had passed he set out wandering towards Mithilā.*";
P_HTM[7353]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena mithilā yena brahmāyu brāhmaṇo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā brahmāyuṃ brāhmaṇaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho uttaraṃ māṇavaṃ brahmāyu brāhmaṇo etadavoca:**There he approached the brahmin Brahmāyu, bowed, and sat down to one side. Brahmāyu said to him,*";
P_HTM[7354]="*“kacci, tāta uttara, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ tathā santaṃyeva saddo abbhuggato, no aññathā?**“Well, dear Uttara, does Master Gotama live up to his reputation or not?”*";
P_HTM[7355]="*Kacci pana so bhavaṃ gotamo tādiso, no aññādiso”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7356]="*“Tathā santaṃyeva, bho, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saddo abbhuggato, no aññathā;**“He does, sir.*";
P_HTM[7357]="*tādisova so bhavaṃ gotamo, no aññādiso.* **";
P_HTM[7358]="*Samannāgato ca so bhavaṃ gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi.**Master Gotama possesses the thirty-two marks.*";
P_HTM[7359]="*Suppatiṭṭhitapādo kho pana bho bhavaṃ gotamo;**He has well-planted feet.*";
P_HTM[7360]="*idampi tassa bhoto gotamassa mahāpurisassa mahāpurisalakkhaṇaṃ bhavati. (1)* **";
P_HTM[7361]="*Heṭṭhā kho pana tassa bhoto gotamassa pādatalesu cakkāni jātāni sahassārāni sanemikāni sanābhikāni sabbākāraparipūrāni … (2)**On the soles of his feet there are thousand-spoked wheels, with rims and hubs, complete in every detail.*";
P_HTM[7362]="*Āyatapaṇhi kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (3)**He has projecting heels.*";
P_HTM[7363]="*Dīghaṅguli kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (4)**He has long fingers.*";
P_HTM[7364]="*Mudutalunahatthapādo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (5)**His hands and feet are tender.*";
P_HTM[7365]="*Jālahatthapādo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (6)**His hands and feet cling gracefully.*";
P_HTM[7366]="*Ussaṅkhapādo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (7)**His feet are arched.*";
P_HTM[7367]="*Eṇijaṅgho kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (8)**His calves are like those of an antelope.*";
P_HTM[7368]="*Ṭhitako kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo anonamanto ubhohi pāṇitalehi jaṇṇukāni parimasati parimajjati … (9)**When standing upright and not bending over, the palms of both hands touch the knees.*";
P_HTM[7369]="*Kosohitavatthaguyho kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (10)**His private parts are retracted.*";
P_HTM[7370]="*Suvaṇṇavaṇṇo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo kañcanasannibhattaco … (11)**He is gold colored; his skin has a golden sheen.*";
P_HTM[7371]="*Sukhumacchavi kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo. Sukhumattā chaviyā rajojallaṃ kāye na upalimpati … (12)**He has delicate skin, so delicate that dust and dirt don’t stick to his body.*";
P_HTM[7372]="*Ekekalomo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo; ekekāni lomāni lomakūpesu jātāni … (13)**His hairs grow one per pore.*";
P_HTM[7373]="*Uddhaggalomo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo; uddhaggāni lomāni jātāni nīlāni añjanavaṇṇāni kuṇḍalāvaṭṭāni dakkhiṇāvaṭṭakajātāni … (14)**His hairs stand up; they’re blue-black and curl clockwise.*";
P_HTM[7374]="*Brahmujugatto kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (15)**His body is as straight as Brahmā’s.*";
P_HTM[7375]="*Sattussado kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (16)**He has bulging muscles in seven places.*";
P_HTM[7376]="*Sīhapubbaddhakāyo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (17)**His chest is like that of a lion.*";
P_HTM[7377]="*Citantaraṃso kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (18)**The gap between the shoulder-blades is filled in.*";
P_HTM[7378]="*Nigrodhaparimaṇḍalo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo; yāvatakvassa kāyo tāvatakvassa byāmo, yāvatakvassa byāmo tāvatakvassa kāyo … (19)**He has the proportional circumference of a banyan tree: the span of his arms equals the height of his body.*";
P_HTM[7379]="*Samavaṭṭakkhandho kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (20)**His torso is cylindrical.*";
P_HTM[7380]="*Rasaggasaggī kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (21)**He has an excellent sense of taste.*";
P_HTM[7381]="*Sīhahanu kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (22)**His jaw is like that of a lion.*";
P_HTM[7382]="*Cattālīsadanto kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (23)**He has forty teeth.*";
P_HTM[7383]="*Samadanto kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (24)**His teeth are even.*";
P_HTM[7384]="*Aviraḷadanto kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (25)**His teeth have no gaps.*";
P_HTM[7385]="*Susukkadāṭho kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (26)**His teeth are perfectly white.*";
P_HTM[7386]="*Pahūtajivho kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (27)**He has a large tongue.*";
P_HTM[7387]="*Brahmassaro kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo karavikabhāṇī … (28)**He has the voice of Brahmā, like a cuckoo’s call.*";
P_HTM[7388]="*Abhinīlanetto kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (29)**His eyes are deep blue.*";
P_HTM[7389]="*Gopakhumo kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo … (30)**He has eyelashes like a cow’s.*";
P_HTM[7390]="*Uṇṇā kho panassa bhoto gotamassa bhamukantare jātā odātā mudutūlasannibhā … (31)**Between his eyebrows there grows a tuft, soft and white like cotton-wool.*";
P_HTM[7391]="*Uṇhīsasīso kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo; idampi tassa bhoto gotamassa mahāpurisassa mahāpurisalakkhaṇaṃ bhavati. (32)**His head is shaped like a turban.*";
P_HTM[7392]="*Imehi kho, bho, so bhavaṃ gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi samannāgato.**These are the thirty-two marks of a great man possessed by Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[7393]="*Gacchanto kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo dakkhiṇeneva pādena paṭhamaṃ pakkamati.**When he’s walking he takes the first step with the right foot.*";
P_HTM[7394]="*So nātidūre pādaṃ uddharati, nāccāsanne pādaṃ nikkhipati;**He doesn’t lift his foot too far or place it too near.*";
P_HTM[7395]="*so nātisīghaṃ gacchati, nātisaṇikaṃ gacchati;**He doesn’t walk too slow or too fast.*";
P_HTM[7396]="*na ca adduvena adduvaṃ saṅghaṭṭento gacchati, na ca gopphakena gopphakaṃ saṅghaṭṭento gacchati.**He walks without knocking his knees or ankles together.*";
P_HTM[7397]="*So gacchanto na satthiṃ unnāmeti, na satthiṃ onāmeti; na satthiṃ sannāmeti, na satthiṃ vināmeti.**When he’s walking he keeps his thighs neither too straight nor too bent, neither too tight nor too loose.*";
P_HTM[7398]="*Gacchato kho pana tassa bhoto gotamassa adharakāyova iñjati, na ca kāyabalena gacchati.**When he walks, only the lower half of his body moves, and he walks effortlessly.*";
P_HTM[7399]="*Apalokento kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo sabbakāyeneva apaloketi;**When he turns to look he does so with the whole body.*";
P_HTM[7400]="*so na uddhaṃ ulloketi, na adho oloketi;**He doesn’t look directly up or down.*";
P_HTM[7401]="*na ca vipekkhamāno gacchati, yugamattañca pekkhati; tato cassa uttari anāvaṭaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ bhavati.**He doesn’t look all around while walking, but focuses a plough’s length in front. Beyond that he has unhindered knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[7402]="*So antaragharaṃ pavisanto na kāyaṃ unnāmeti, na kāyaṃ onāmeti; na kāyaṃ sannāmeti, na kāyaṃ vināmeti.**When entering an inhabited area he keeps his body neither too straight nor too bent, neither too tight nor too loose.*";
P_HTM[7403]="*So nātidūre nāccāsanne āsanassa parivattati, na ca pāṇinā ālambitvā āsane nisīdati, na ca āsanasmiṃ kāyaṃ pakkhipati.**He turns around neither too far nor too close to the seat. He doesn’t lean on his hand when sitting down. And he doesn’t just plonk his body down on the seat.*";
P_HTM[7404]="*So antaraghare nisinno samāno na hatthakukkuccaṃ āpajjati, na pādakukkuccaṃ āpajjati;**When sitting in inhabited areas he doesn’t fidget with his hands or feet.*";
P_HTM[7405]="*na adduvena adduvaṃ āropetvā nisīdati; na ca gopphakena gopphakaṃ āropetvā nisīdati;**He doesn’t sit with his knees or ankles crossed.*";
P_HTM[7406]="*na ca pāṇinā hanukaṃ upadahitvā nisīdati.**He doesn’t sit with his hand holding his chin.*";
P_HTM[7407]="*So antaraghare nisinno samāno na chambhati na kampati na vedhati na paritassati. So achambhī akampī avedhī aparitassī vigatalomahaṃso.**When sitting in inhabited areas he doesn’t cower or shake or tremble or get anxious, and so he is not nervous at all.*";
P_HTM[7408]="*Vivekavatto ca so bhavaṃ gotamo antaraghare nisinno hoti.**When sitting in inhabited areas he still practices seclusion.*";
P_HTM[7409]="*So pattodakaṃ paṭiggaṇhanto na pattaṃ unnāmeti, na pattaṃ onāmeti; na pattaṃ sannāmeti, na pattaṃ vināmeti.**When receiving water for rinsing the bowl, he holds the bowl neither too straight nor too bent, neither too tight nor too loose.*";
P_HTM[7410]="*So pattodakaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti nātithokaṃ nātibahuṃ.**He receives neither too little nor too much water.*";
P_HTM[7411]="*So na khulukhulukārakaṃ pattaṃ dhovati, na samparivattakaṃ pattaṃ dhovati, na pattaṃ bhūmiyaṃ nikkhipitvā hatthe dhovati; hatthesu dhotesu patto dhoto hoti, patte dhote hatthā dhotā honti.**He rinses the bowl without making a sloshing noise, or spinning it around. He doesn’t put the bowl on the ground to rinse his hands; his hands and bowl are rinsed at the same time.*";
P_HTM[7412]="*So pattodakaṃ chaḍḍeti nātidūre nāccāsanne, na ca vicchaḍḍayamāno.**He doesn’t throw the bowl rinsing water away too far or too near, or splash it about.*";
P_HTM[7413]="*So odanaṃ paṭiggaṇhanto na pattaṃ unnāmeti, na pattaṃ onāmeti; na pattaṃ sannāmeti, na pattaṃ vināmeti.**When receiving rice, he holds the bowl neither too straight nor too bent, neither too close nor too loose.*";
P_HTM[7414]="*So odanaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti nātithokaṃ nātibahuṃ.**He receives neither too little nor too much rice.*";
P_HTM[7415]="*Byañjanaṃ kho pana bhavaṃ gotamo byañjanamattāya āhāreti, na ca byañjanena ālopaṃ atināmeti.**He eats sauce in a moderate proportion, and doesn’t spend too much time saucing his portions.*";
P_HTM[7416]="*Dvattikkhattuṃ kho bhavaṃ gotamo mukhe ālopaṃ samparivattetvā ajjhoharati;**He chews over each portion two or three times before swallowing.*";
P_HTM[7417]="*na cassa kāci odanamiñjā asambhinnā kāyaṃ pavisati, na cassa kāci odanamiñjā mukhe avasiṭṭhā hoti;**But no grain of rice enters his body unchewed, and none remain in his mouth.*";
P_HTM[7418]="*athāparaṃ ālopaṃ upanāmeti.**Only then does he raise another portion to his lips.*";
P_HTM[7419]="*Rasapaṭisaṃvedī kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo āhāraṃ āhāreti, no ca rasarāgapaṭisaṃvedī.**He eats experiencing the taste, but without experiencing greed for the taste.*";
P_HTM[7420]="*Aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgataṃ kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo āhāraṃ āhāreti—**He eats food thinking of eight reasons:*";
P_HTM[7421]="*neva davāya, na madāya na maṇḍanāya na vibhūsanāya, yāvadeva imassa kāyassa ṭhitiyā yāpanāya, vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya: ‘iti purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me bhavissati anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti.**‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to sustain this body, to avoid harm, and to support spiritual practice. In this way, I shall put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and I will live blamelessly and at ease.’*";
P_HTM[7422]="*So bhuttāvī pattodakaṃ paṭiggaṇhanto na pattaṃ unnāmeti, na pattaṃ onāmeti; na pattaṃ sannāmeti, na pattaṃ vināmeti.**After eating, when receiving water for washing the bowl, he holds the bowl neither too straight nor too bent, neither too tight nor too loose.*";
P_HTM[7423]="*So pattodakaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti nātithokaṃ nātibahuṃ.**He receives neither too little nor too much water.*";
P_HTM[7424]="*So na khulukhulukārakaṃ pattaṃ dhovati, na samparivattakaṃ pattaṃ dhovati, na pattaṃ bhūmiyaṃ nikkhipitvā hatthe dhovati; hatthesu dhotesu patto dhoto hoti, patte dhote hatthā dhotā honti.**He washes the bowl without making a sloshing noise, or spinning it around. He doesn’t put the bowl on the ground to wash his hands; his hands and bowl are washed at the same time.*";
P_HTM[7425]="*So pattodakaṃ chaḍḍeti nātidūre nāccāsanne, na ca vicchaḍḍayamāno.**He doesn’t throw the bowl washing water away too far or too near, or splash it about.*";
P_HTM[7426]="*So bhuttāvī na pattaṃ bhūmiyaṃ nikkhipati nātidūre nāccāsanne, na ca anatthiko pattena hoti, na ca ativelānurakkhī pattasmiṃ.**After eating he doesn’t put the bowl on the ground too far away or too close. He’s not careless with his bowl, nor does he spend too much time on it.*";
P_HTM[7427]="*So bhuttāvī muhuttaṃ tuṇhī nisīdati, na ca anumodanassa kālamatināmeti.**After eating he sits for a while in silence, but doesn’t wait too long to give the verses of appreciation.*";
P_HTM[7428]="*So bhuttāvī anumodati, na taṃ bhattaṃ garahati, na aññaṃ bhattaṃ paṭikaṅkhati;**After eating he expresses appreciation without criticizing the meal or expecting another one.*";
P_HTM[7429]="*aññadatthu dhammiyā kathāya taṃ parisaṃ sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti.**Invariably, he educates, encourages, fires up, and inspires that assembly with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[7430]="*So taṃ parisaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamati.**Then he gets up from his seat and leaves.*";
P_HTM[7431]="*So nātisīghaṃ gacchati, nātisaṇikaṃ gacchati, na ca muccitukāmo gacchati;**He walks neither too fast nor too slow, without wanting to get out of there.*";
P_HTM[7432]="*na ca tassa bhoto gotamassa kāye cīvaraṃ accukkaṭṭhaṃ hoti na ca accokkaṭṭhaṃ, na ca kāyasmiṃ allīnaṃ na ca kāyasmā apakaṭṭhaṃ;**He wears his robe on his body neither too high nor too low, neither too tight nor too loose.*";
P_HTM[7433]="*na ca tassa bhoto gotamassa kāyamhā vāto cīvaraṃ apavahati;**The wind doesn’t blow his robe off his body.*";
P_HTM[7434]="*na ca tassa bhoto gotamassa kāye rajojallaṃ upalimpati.**And dust and dirt don’t stick to his body.*";
P_HTM[7435]="*So ārāmagato nisīdati paññatte āsane. Nisajja pāde pakkhāleti;**When he has gone to the monastery he sits on a seat spread out and washes his feet.*";
P_HTM[7436]="*na ca so bhavaṃ gotamo pādamaṇḍanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**But he doesn’t waste time with pedicures.*";
P_HTM[7437]="*So pāde pakkhāletvā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**When he has washed his feet, he sits down cross-legged, with his body straight, and establishes mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[7438]="*So neva attabyābādhāya ceteti, na parabyābādhāya ceteti, na ubhayabyābādhāya ceteti;**He has no intention to hurt himself, hurt others, or hurt both.*";
P_HTM[7439]="*attahitaparahitaubhayahitasabbalokahitameva so bhavaṃ gotamo cintento nisinno hoti.**He only wishes for the welfare of himself, of others, of both, and of the whole world.*";
P_HTM[7440]="*So ārāmagato parisati dhammaṃ deseti, na taṃ parisaṃ ussādeti, na taṃ parisaṃ apasādeti;**In the monastery when he teaches Dhamma to an assembly, he neither flatters them nor rebukes them.*";
P_HTM[7441]="*aññadatthu dhammiyā kathāya taṃ parisaṃ sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti.**Invariably, he educates, encourages, fires up, and inspires that assembly with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[7442]="*Aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgato kho panassa bhoto gotamassa mukhato ghoso niccharati—**His voice has eight qualities:*";
P_HTM[7443]="*vissaṭṭho ca, viññeyyo ca, mañju ca, savanīyo ca, bindu ca, avisārī ca, gambhīro ca, ninnādī ca.**it is clear, comprehensible, charming, audible, rounded, undistorted, deep, and resonant.*";
P_HTM[7444]="*Yathāparisaṃ kho pana so bhavaṃ gotamo sarena viññāpeti, na cassa bahiddhā parisāya ghoso niccharati.**He makes sure his voice is intelligible as far as the assembly goes, but it doesn’t extend outside the assembly.*";
P_HTM[7445]="*Te tena bhotā gotamena dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamanti avalokayamānāyeva avijahitattā.**And when they’ve been inspired with a Dhamma talk by Master Gotama they get up from their seats and leave looking back at him alone, and not forgetting their lesson.*";
P_HTM[7446]="*Addasāma kho mayaṃ, bho, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ gacchantaṃ, addasāma ṭhitaṃ, addasāma antaragharaṃ pavisantaṃ, addasāma antaraghare nisinnaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ, addasāma antaraghare bhuñjantaṃ, addasāma bhuttāviṃ nisinnaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ, addasāma bhuttāviṃ anumodantaṃ, addasāma ārāmaṃ gacchantaṃ, addasāma ārāmagataṃ nisinnaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ, addasāma ārāmagataṃ parisati dhammaṃ desentaṃ.**I have seen Master Gotama walking and standing; entering inhabited areas, and sitting and eating there; sitting silently after eating, and expressing appreciation; going to the monastery, sitting silently there, and teaching Dhamma to an assembly there.*";
P_HTM[7447]="*Ediso ca ediso ca so bhavaṃ gotamo, tato ca bhiyyo”ti.**Such is Master Gotama; such he is and more than that.”*";
P_HTM[7448]="*Evaṃ vutte, brahmāyu brāhmaṇo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā tikkhattuṃ udānaṃ udāneti:**When he had spoken, the brahmin Brahmāyu got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and uttered this aphorism three times:*";
P_HTM[7449]="*“Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**“Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[7450]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[7451]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassāti.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[7452]="*Appeva nāma mayaṃ kadāci karahaci tena bhotā gotamena samāgaccheyyāma? Appeva nāma siyā kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti.**Hopefully, some time or other I’ll get to meet him, and we can have a discussion.”*";
P_HTM[7453]="*Atha kho bhagavā videhesu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena mithilā tadavasari.**And then the Buddha, traveling stage by stage in the Videhan lands, arrived at Mithilā,*";
P_HTM[7454]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā mithilāyaṃ viharati maghadevaambavane.**where he stayed in the Makhādeva Mango Grove.*";
P_HTM[7455]="*Assosuṃ kho mithileyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:**The brahmins and householders of Mithilā heard:*";
P_HTM[7456]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito videhesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi mithilaṃ anuppatto, mithilāyaṃ viharati maghadevaambavane.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has arrived at Mithilā, where he is staying in the Makhādeva Mango Grove.*";
P_HTM[7457]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[7458]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[7459]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[7460]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[7461]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[7462]="*Atha kho mithileyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu; appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Then the brahmins and householders of Mithilā went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent.*";
P_HTM[7463]="*Assosi kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo: “samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito mithilaṃ anuppatto, mithilāyaṃ viharati maghadevaambavane”ti.**The brahmin Brahmāyu also heard that the Buddha had arrived.*";
P_HTM[7464]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo sambahulehi sāvakehi saddhiṃ yena maghadevaambavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**So he went to the Makhādeva Mango Grove together with several disciples.*";
P_HTM[7465]="*Atha kho brahmāyuno brāhmaṇassa avidūre ambavanassa etadahosi:**Not far from the grove he thought,*";
P_HTM[7466]="*“na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ yohaṃ pubbe appaṭisaṃvidito samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkameyyan”ti.**“It wouldn’t be appropriate for me to go to see the ascetic Gotama without first letting him know.”*";
P_HTM[7467]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo aññataraṃ māṇavakaṃ āmantesi:**So he addressed one of his students:*";
P_HTM[7468]="*“ehi tvaṃ, māṇavaka, yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha:**“Here, student, go to the ascetic Gotama and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Ask him if he is healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[7469]="*‘brahmāyu, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7470]="*Evañca vadehi:**And then say:*";
P_HTM[7471]="*‘brahmāyu, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo jiṇṇo vuḍḍho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto, vīsavassasatiko jātiyā, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo.**‘Master Gotama, the brahmin Brahmāyu is old, elderly, and senior, advanced in years, having reached the final stage of life; he is a hundred and twenty years old. He has mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. He knows philology and grammar, and is well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[7472]="*Yāvatā, bho, brāhmaṇagahapatikā mithilāyaṃ paṭivasanti, brahmāyu tesaṃ brāhmaṇo aggamakkhāyati—**Of all the brahmins and householders residing in Mithilā, Brahmāyu is said to be the foremost in*";
P_HTM[7473]="*yadidaṃ bhogehi;**wealth,*";
P_HTM[7474]="*brahmāyu tesaṃ brāhmaṇo aggamakkhāyati—* **";
P_HTM[7475]="*yadidaṃ mantehi;**hymns,*";
P_HTM[7476]="*brahmāyu tesaṃ brāhmaṇo aggamakkhāyati—* **";
P_HTM[7477]="*yadidaṃ āyunā ceva yasasā ca.**lifespan, and fame.*";
P_HTM[7478]="*So bhoto gotamassa dassanakāmo’”ti.**He wants to see Master Gotama.’”*";
P_HTM[7479]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho so māṇavako brahmāyussa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**“Yes, sir,” that student replied. He did as he was asked, and the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[7480]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho so māṇavako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[7481]="*“brahmāyu, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati;* **";
P_HTM[7482]="*evañca vadeti:* **";
P_HTM[7483]="*‘brahmāyu, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo jiṇṇo vuḍḍho mahallako addhagato vayoanuppatto, vīsavassasatiko jātiyā, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo.* **";
P_HTM[7484]="*Yāvatā, bho, brāhmaṇagahapatikā mithilāyaṃ paṭivasanti, brahmāyu tesaṃ brāhmaṇo aggamakkhāyati—* **";
P_HTM[7485]="*yadidaṃ bhogehi;* **";
P_HTM[7486]="*brahmāyu tesaṃ brāhmaṇo aggamakkhāyati—* **";
P_HTM[7487]="*yadidaṃ mantehi;* **";
P_HTM[7488]="*brahmāyu tesaṃ brāhmaṇo aggamakkhāyati—* **";
P_HTM[7489]="*yadidaṃ āyunā ceva yasasā ca.* **";
P_HTM[7490]="*So bhoto gotamassa dassanakāmo’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7491]="*“Yassadāni, māṇava, brahmāyu brāhmaṇo kālaṃ maññatī”ti.**“Please, student, let Brahmāyu come when he’s ready.”*";
P_HTM[7492]="*Atha kho so māṇavako yena brahmāyu brāhmaṇo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā brahmāyuṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**The student went back to Brahmāyu and said to him,*";
P_HTM[7493]="*“katāvakāso khomhi bhavatā samaṇena gotamena.**“Your request for an audience with the ascetic Gotama has been granted.*";
P_HTM[7494]="*Yassadāni bhavaṃ kālaṃ maññatī”ti.**Please go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[7495]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami.**Then the brahmin Brahmāyu went up to the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7496]="*Addasā kho sā parisā brahmāyuṃ brāhmaṇaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The assembly saw him coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[7497]="*Disvāna oramiya okāsamakāsi yathā taṃ ñātassa yasassino.**and made way for him, as he was well-known and famous.*";
P_HTM[7498]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo taṃ parisaṃ etadavoca:**Brahmāyu said to that retinue,*";
P_HTM[7499]="*“alaṃ, bho.**“Enough, gentlemen.*";
P_HTM[7500]="*Nisīdatha tumhe sake āsane.**Please sit on your own seats.*";
P_HTM[7501]="*Idhāhaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa santike nisīdissāmī”ti.**I shall sit here by the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[7502]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the brahmin Brahmāyu went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7503]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[7504]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni samannesi.**and scrutinized the Buddha’s body for the thirty-two marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[7505]="*Addasā kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni, yebhuyyena ṭhapetvā dve.**He saw all of them except for two,*";
P_HTM[7506]="*Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—**which he had doubts about:*";
P_HTM[7507]="*kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya ca.**whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue.*";
P_HTM[7508]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:**Then Brahmāyu addressed the Buddha in verse:*";
P_HTM[7509]="*“Ye me dvattiṃsāti sutā,**“I have learned of the thirty-two*";
P_HTM[7510]="*mahāpurisalakkhaṇā;**marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[7511]="*Duve tesaṃ na passāmi,**There are two that I don’t see*";
P_HTM[7512]="*bhoto kāyasmiṃ gotama.**on the body of the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[7513]="*Kacci kosohitaṃ bhoto,**Are the private parts retracted,*";
P_HTM[7514]="*vatthaguyhaṃ naruttama;**O supreme person?*";
P_HTM[7515]="*Nārīsamānasavhayā,**Though called by a word of the feminine gender,*";
P_HTM[7516]="*kacci jivhā na dassakā.**perhaps your tongue is a manly one?*";
P_HTM[7517]="*Kacci pahūtajivhosi,**Perhaps your tongue is large,*";
P_HTM[7518]="*yathā taṃ jāniyāmase;**as we have been informed.*";
P_HTM[7519]="*Ninnāmayetaṃ pahūtaṃ,**Please stick it out in its full extent,*";
P_HTM[7520]="*kaṅkhaṃ vinaya no ise.**and so, O hermit, dispel my doubt.*";
P_HTM[7521]="*Diṭṭhadhammahitatthāya,**For my welfare and benefit in this life,*";
P_HTM[7522]="*samparāyasukhāya ca;**and happiness in the next.*";
P_HTM[7523]="*Katāvakāsā pucchāma,**And I ask you to grant the opportunity*";
P_HTM[7524]="*yaṃ kiñci abhipatthitan”ti.**to ask whatever I desire.”*";
P_HTM[7525]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then the Buddha thought,*";
P_HTM[7526]="*“passati kho me ayaṃ brahmāyu brāhmaṇo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni, yebhuyyena ṭhapetvā dve.**“Brahmāyu sees all the marks except for two,*";
P_HTM[7527]="*Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—**which he has doubts about:*";
P_HTM[7528]="*kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya cā”ti.**whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue.”*";
P_HTM[7529]="*Atha kho bhagavā tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsi yathā addasa brahmāyu brāhmaṇo bhagavato kosohitaṃ vatthaguyhaṃ.**So the Buddha used his psychic power to will that Brahmāyu would see his retracted private parts.*";
P_HTM[7530]="*Atha kho bhagavā jivhaṃ ninnāmetvā ubhopi kaṇṇasotāni anumasi paṭimasi; ubhopi nāsikasotāni anumasi paṭimasi; kevalampi nalāṭamaṇḍalaṃ jivhāya chādesi.**And he stuck out his tongue and stroked back and forth on his ear holes and nostrils, and covered his entire forehead with his tongue.*";
P_HTM[7531]="*Atha kho bhagavā brahmāyuṃ brāhmaṇaṃ gāthāhi paccabhāsi:**Then the Buddha replied to Brahmāyu in verse:*";
P_HTM[7532]="*“Ye te dvattiṃsāti sutā,**“The thirty-two marks of a great man*";
P_HTM[7533]="*mahāpurisalakkhaṇā;**that you have learned*";
P_HTM[7534]="*Sabbe te mama kāyasmiṃ,**are all found on my body:*";
P_HTM[7535]="*mā te kaṅkhāhu brāhmaṇa.**so do not doubt, brahmin.*";
P_HTM[7536]="*Abhiññeyyaṃ abhiññātaṃ,**I have known what should be known,*";
P_HTM[7537]="*bhāvetabbañca bhāvitaṃ;**and developed what should be developed,*";
P_HTM[7538]="*Pahātabbaṃ pahīnaṃ me,**and given up what should be given up:*";
P_HTM[7539]="*tasmā buddhosmi brāhmaṇa.**and so, brahmin, I am a Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7540]="*Diṭṭhadhammahitatthāya,**For your welfare and benefit in this life,*";
P_HTM[7541]="*samparāyasukhāya ca;**and happiness in the next:*";
P_HTM[7542]="*Katāvakāso pucchassu,**I grant you the opportunity*";
P_HTM[7543]="*yaṃ kiñci abhipatthitan”ti.**to ask whatever you desire.”*";
P_HTM[7544]="*Atha kho brahmāyussa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi:**Then Brahmāyu thought:*";
P_HTM[7545]="*“katāvakāso khomhi samaṇena gotamena.**“My request has been granted.*";
P_HTM[7546]="*Kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ puccheyyaṃ:**Should I ask him about*";
P_HTM[7547]="*‘diṭṭhadhammikaṃ vā atthaṃ samparāyikaṃ vā’”ti.**what is beneficial in this life or the next?”*";
P_HTM[7548]="*Atha kho brahmāyussa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi:**Then he thought,*";
P_HTM[7549]="*“kusalo kho ahaṃ diṭṭhadhammikānaṃ atthānaṃ.**“I’m well versed in the benefits that apply to this life,*";
P_HTM[7550]="*Aññepi maṃ diṭṭhadhammikaṃ atthaṃ pucchanti.**and others ask me about this.*";
P_HTM[7551]="*Yannūnāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ samparāyikaṃyeva atthaṃ puccheyyan”ti.**Why don’t I ask the ascetic Gotama about the benefit that specifically applies to lives to come?”*";
P_HTM[7552]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:**So Brahmāyu addressed the Buddha in verse:*";
P_HTM[7553]="*“Kathaṃ kho brāhmaṇo hoti,**“How do you become a brahmin?*";
P_HTM[7554]="*kathaṃ bhavati vedagū;**And how do you become a knowledge master?*";
P_HTM[7555]="*Tevijjo bho kathaṃ hoti,**How a master of the three knowledges?*";
P_HTM[7556]="*sotthiyo kinti vuccati.**And how is one called a scholar?*";
P_HTM[7557]="*Arahaṃ bho kathaṃ hoti,**How do you become a perfected one?*";
P_HTM[7558]="*kathaṃ bhavati kevalī;**And how a consummate one?*";
P_HTM[7559]="*Muni ca bho kathaṃ hoti,**How do you become a sage?*";
P_HTM[7560]="*buddho kinti pavuccatī”ti.**And how is one declared to be awakened?”*";
P_HTM[7561]="*Atha kho bhagavā brahmāyuṃ brāhmaṇaṃ gāthāhi paccabhāsi:**Then the Buddha replied to Brahmāyu in verse:*";
P_HTM[7562]="*“Pubbenivāsaṃ yo vedi,**“One who knows their past lives,*";
P_HTM[7563]="*saggāpāyañca passati;**and sees heaven and places of loss,*";
P_HTM[7564]="*Atho jātikkhayaṃ patto,**and has attained the end of rebirth:*";
P_HTM[7565]="*abhiññā vosito muni.**that sage has perfect insight.*";
P_HTM[7566]="*Cittaṃ visuddhaṃ jānāti,**They know their mind is pure,*";
P_HTM[7567]="*muttaṃ rāgehi sabbaso;**completely freed from greed;*";
P_HTM[7568]="*Pahīnajātimaraṇo,**they’ve given up birth and death,*";
P_HTM[7569]="*brahmacariyassa kevalī;**and have completed the spiritual journey.*";
P_HTM[7570]="*Pāragū sabbadhammānaṃ,**Gone beyond all things,*";
P_HTM[7571]="*buddho tādī pavuccatī”ti.**such a one is declared to be awakened.”*";
P_HTM[7572]="*Evaṃ vutte, brahmāyu brāhmaṇo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavato pādāni mukhena ca paricumbati, pāṇīhi ca parisambāhati, nāmañca sāveti:**When he said this, Brahmāyu got up from his seat and arranged his robe on one shoulder. He bowed with his head to the Buddha’s feet, caressing them and covering them with kisses, and pronounced his name:*";
P_HTM[7573]="*“brahmāyu ahaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo;**“I am the brahmin Brahmāyu, Master Gotama!*";
P_HTM[7574]="*brahmāyu ahaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo”ti.**I am the brahmin Brahmāyu!”*";
P_HTM[7575]="*Atha kho sā parisā acchariyabbhutacittajātā ahosi:**Then that assembly, their minds full of wonder and amazement, thought,*";
P_HTM[7576]="*“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**“It’s incredible, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[7577]="*Yatra hi nāmāyaṃ brahmāyu brāhmaṇo ñāto yasassī evarūpaṃ paramanipaccakāraṃ karissatī”ti.**that Brahmāyu, who is so well-known and famous, should show the Buddha such utmost devotion.”*";
P_HTM[7578]="*Atha kho bhagavā brahmāyuṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**Then the Buddha said to Brahmāyu,*";
P_HTM[7579]="*“alaṃ, brāhmaṇa, uṭṭhaha nisīda tvaṃ sake āsane yato te mayi cittaṃ pasannan”ti.**“Enough, brahmin. Get up, and sit in your own seat, since your mind has such confidence in me.”*";
P_HTM[7580]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo uṭṭhahitvā sake āsane nisīdi.**So Brahmāyu got up and sat in his own seat.*";
P_HTM[7581]="*Atha kho bhagavā brahmāyussa brāhmaṇassa anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, seyyathidaṃ—**Then the Buddha taught him step by step, with*";
P_HTM[7582]="*dānakathaṃ, sīlakathaṃ, saggakathaṃ;**a talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven.*";
P_HTM[7583]="*kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi.**He explained the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[7584]="*Yadā bhagavā aññāsi brahmāyuṃ brāhmaṇaṃ kallacittaṃ muducittaṃ vinīvaraṇacittaṃ udaggacittaṃ pasannacittaṃ, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā taṃ pakāsesi—**And when the Buddha knew that Brahmāyu’s mind was ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas:*";
P_HTM[7585]="*dukkhaṃ, samudayaṃ, nirodhaṃ, maggaṃ.**suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path.*";
P_HTM[7586]="*Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya;**Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye,*";
P_HTM[7587]="*evameva brahmāyussa brāhmaṇassa tasmiṃyeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:**in that very seat the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in the brahmin Brahmāyu:*";
P_HTM[7588]="*“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti.**“Everything that has a beginning has an end.”*";
P_HTM[7589]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo diṭṭhadhammo pattadhammo viditadhammo pariyogāḷhadhammo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Brahmāyu saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. He went beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. He said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7590]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[7591]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[7592]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[7593]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.*";
P_HTM[7594]="*Adhivāsetu ca me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**Would you and the mendicant Saṅgha please accept a meal from me tomorrow?”*";
P_HTM[7595]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[7596]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, Brahmāyu got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[7597]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi:**And when the night had passed Brahmāyu had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home. Then he had the Buddha informed of the time, saying,*";
P_HTM[7598]="*“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**“It’s time, Master Gotama, the meal is ready.”*";
P_HTM[7599]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena brahmāyussa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of the brahmin Brahmāyu, where he sat on the seat spread out, together with the Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[7600]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo sattāhaṃ buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Brahmāyu served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[7601]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassa sattāhassa accayena videhesu cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**A week later, the Buddha departed to wander in the Videhan lands.*";
P_HTM[7602]="*Atha kho brahmāyu brāhmaṇo acirapakkantassa bhagavato kālamakāsi.**Not long after the Buddha left, Brahmāyu passed away.*";
P_HTM[7603]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[7604]="*“brahmāyu, bhante, brāhmaṇo kālaṅkato.**“Sir, Brahmāyu has passed away.*";
P_HTM[7605]="*Tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo”ti?**Where has he been reborn in his next life?”*";
P_HTM[7606]="*“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, brahmāyu brāhmaṇo paccapādi dhammassānudhammaṃ, na ca maṃ dhammādhikaraṇaṃ vihesesi.**“Mendicants, the brahmin Brahmāyu was astute. He practiced in line with the teachings, and did not trouble me about the teachings.*";
P_HTM[7607]="*Brahmāyu, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇo pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti, tattha parinibbāyī, anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā”ti.**With the ending of the five lower fetters, he’s been reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.”*";
P_HTM[7608]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7609]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7610]="*Brahmāyusuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7611]="*92. Selasutta**With Sela*";
P_HTM[7612]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7613]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā aṅguttarāpesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ aḍḍhateḷasehi bhikkhusatehi yena āpaṇaṃ nāma aṅguttarāpānaṃ nigamo tadavasari.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Northern Āpaṇas together with a large Saṅgha of 1,250 mendicants when he arrived at a town of the Northern Āpaṇas named Āpaṇa.*";
P_HTM[7614]="*Assosi kho keṇiyo jaṭilo:**The matted-hair ascetic Keṇiya heard:*";
P_HTM[7615]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito aṅguttarāpesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ aḍḍhateḷasehi bhikkhusatehi āpaṇaṃ anuppatto.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has arrived at Āpaṇa, together with a large Saṅgha of 1,250 mendicants.*";
P_HTM[7616]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[7617]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[7618]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[7619]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[7620]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[7621]="*Atha kho keṇiyo jaṭilo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**So Keṇiya approached the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7622]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[7623]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho keṇiyaṃ jaṭilaṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**The Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[7624]="*Atha kho keṇiyo jaṭilo bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then he said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7625]="*“adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**“Would Master Gotama together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept tomorrow’s meal from me?”*";
P_HTM[7626]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā keṇiyaṃ jaṭilaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[7627]="*“mahā kho, keṇiya, bhikkhusaṅgho aḍḍhateḷasāni bhikkhusatāni, tvañca brāhmaṇesu abhippasanno”ti.**“The Saṅgha is large, Keṇiya; there are 1,250 mendicants. And you are devoted to the brahmins.”*";
P_HTM[7628]="*Dutiyampi kho keṇiyo jaṭilo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**For a second time …*";
P_HTM[7629]="*“kiñcāpi kho, bho gotama, mahā bhikkhusaṅgho aḍḍhateḷasāni bhikkhusatāni, ahañca brāhmaṇesu abhippasanno;* **";
P_HTM[7630]="*adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7631]="*Dutiyampi kho bhagavā keṇiyaṃ jaṭilaṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[7632]="*“mahā kho, keṇiya, bhikkhusaṅgho aḍḍhateḷasāni bhikkhusatāni, tvañca brāhmaṇesu abhippasanno”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7633]="*Tatiyampi kho keṇiyo jaṭilo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**and a third time Keṇiya asked the Buddha to accept a meal offering.*";
P_HTM[7634]="*“kiñcāpi kho, bho gotama, mahā bhikkhusaṅgho aḍḍhateḷasāni bhikkhusatāni, ahañca brāhmaṇesu abhippasanno;* **";
P_HTM[7635]="*adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7636]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**Finally, the Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[7637]="*Atha kho keṇiyo jaṭilo bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena sako assamo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mittāmacce ñātisālohite āmantesi:**Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, Keṇiya got up from his seat and went to his own hermitage. There he addressed his friends and colleagues, relatives and family members,*";
P_HTM[7638]="*“suṇantu me bhonto, mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā;**“Gentlemen, please listen.*";
P_HTM[7639]="*samaṇo me gotamo nimantito svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena.**The ascetic Gotama together with the mendicant Saṅgha has been invited by me for tomorrow’s meal.*";
P_HTM[7640]="*Yena me kāyaveyyāvaṭikaṃ kareyyāthā”ti.**Please help me with the preparations.”*";
P_HTM[7641]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho keṇiyassa jaṭilassa mittāmaccā ñātisālohitā keṇiyassa jaṭilassa paṭissutvā appekacce uddhanāni khaṇanti, appekacce kaṭṭhāni phālenti, appekacce bhājanāni dhovanti, appekacce udakamaṇikaṃ patiṭṭhāpenti, appekacce āsanāni paññapenti.**“Yes, sir,” they replied. Some dug ovens, some chopped wood, some washed dishes, some set out a water jar, and some spread out seats.*";
P_HTM[7642]="*Keṇiyo pana jaṭilo sāmaṃyeva maṇḍalamālaṃ paṭiyādeti.**Meanwhile, Keṇiya set up the pavilion himself.*";
P_HTM[7643]="*Tena kho pana samayena selo brāhmaṇo āpaṇe paṭivasati tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo, tīṇi ca māṇavakasatāni mante vāceti.**Now at that time the brahmin Sela was residing in Āpaṇa. He had mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. He knew philology and grammar, and was well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man. And he was teaching three hundred students to recite the hymns.*";
P_HTM[7644]="*Tena kho pana samayena keṇiyo jaṭilo sele brāhmaṇe abhippasanno hoti.**Now at that time Keṇiya was devoted to Sela.*";
P_HTM[7645]="*Atha kho selo brāhmaṇo tīhi māṇavakasatehi parivuto jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena keṇiyassa jaṭilassa assamo tenupasaṅkami.**Then Sela, while going for a walk escorted by the three hundred students, approached Keṇiya’s hermitage.*";
P_HTM[7646]="*Addasā kho selo brāhmaṇo keṇiyassa jaṭilassa assame appekacce uddhanāni khaṇante, appekacce kaṭṭhāni phālente, appekacce bhājanāni dhovante, appekacce udakamaṇikaṃ patiṭṭhāpente, appekacce āsanāni paññapente, keṇiyaṃ pana jaṭilaṃ sāmaṃyeva maṇḍalamālaṃ paṭiyādentaṃ.**He saw the preparations going on,*";
P_HTM[7647]="*Disvāna keṇiyaṃ jaṭilaṃ etadavoca:**and said to Keṇiya,*";
P_HTM[7648]="*“kiṃ nu bhoto keṇiyassa āvāho vā bhavissati vivāho vā bhavissati mahāyañño vā paccupaṭṭhito, rājā vā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro nimantito svātanāya saddhiṃ balakāyenā”ti?**“Keṇiya, is your son or daughter being married? Or are you setting up a big sacrifice? Or has King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha been invited for tomorrow’s meal?”*";
P_HTM[7649]="*“Na me, bho sela, āvāho bhavissati napi vivāho bhavissati napi rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro nimantito svātanāya saddhiṃ balakāyena;**“There is no marriage, Sela, and the king is not coming.*";
P_HTM[7650]="*api ca kho me mahāyañño paccupaṭṭhito.**Rather, I am setting up a big sacrifice.*";
P_HTM[7651]="*Atthi, bho, samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito aṅguttarāpesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ aḍḍhateḷasehi bhikkhusatehi āpaṇaṃ anuppatto.**The ascetic Gotama has arrived at Āpaṇa, together with a large Saṅgha of 1,250 mendicants.*";
P_HTM[7652]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[7653]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[7654]="*So me nimantito svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**He has been invited by me for tomorrow’s meal together with the mendicant Saṅgha.”*";
P_HTM[7655]="*“Buddhoti—bho keṇiya, vadesi”?**“Mister Keṇiya, did you say ‘the awakened one’?”*";
P_HTM[7656]="*“Buddhoti—bho sela, vadāmi”.**“I said ‘the awakened one’.”*";
P_HTM[7657]="*“Buddhoti—bho keṇiya, vadesi”?**“Did you say ‘the awakened one’?”*";
P_HTM[7658]="*“Buddhoti—bho sela, vadāmī”ti.**“I said ‘the awakened one’.”*";
P_HTM[7659]="*Atha kho selassa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi:**Then Sela thought,*";
P_HTM[7660]="*“ghosopi kho eso dullabho lokasmiṃ—yadidaṃ ‘buddho’ti.**“It’s hard to even find the word ‘awakened one’ in the world.*";
P_HTM[7661]="*Āgatāni kho panamhākaṃ mantesu dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni, yehi samannāgatassa mahāpurisassa dveyeva gatiyo bhavanti anaññā.**The thirty-two marks of a great man have been handed down in our hymns. A great man who possesses these has only two possible destinies, no other.*";
P_HTM[7662]="*Sace agāraṃ ajjhāvasati, rājā hoti cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato.**If he stays at home he becomes a king, a wheel-turning monarch, a just and principled king. His dominion extends to all four sides, he achieves stability in the country, and he possesses the seven treasures.*";
P_HTM[7663]="*Tassimāni satta ratanāni bhavanti, seyyathidaṃ—**He has the following seven treasures:*";
P_HTM[7664]="*cakkaratanaṃ, hatthiratanaṃ, assaratanaṃ, maṇiratanaṃ, itthiratanaṃ, gahapatiratanaṃ, pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ.**the wheel, the elephant, the horse, the jewel, the woman, the treasurer, and the counselor as the seventh treasure.*";
P_HTM[7665]="*Parosahassaṃ kho panassa puttā bhavanti sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā.**He has over a thousand sons who are valiant and heroic, crushing the armies of his enemies.*";
P_HTM[7666]="*So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya ajjhāvasati.**After conquering this land girt by sea, he reigns by principle, without rod or sword.*";
P_HTM[7667]="*Sace pana agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati, arahaṃ hoti sammāsambuddho loke vivaṭṭacchado”.**But if he goes forth from the lay life to homelessness, he becomes a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, who draws back the veil from the world.”*";
P_HTM[7668]="*“Kahaṃ pana, bho keṇiya, etarahi so bhavaṃ gotamo viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti?**“But Keṇiya, where is the Blessed One at present, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[7669]="*Evaṃ vutte, keṇiyo jaṭilo dakkhiṇaṃ bāhuṃ paggahetvā selaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Keṇiya pointed with his right arm and said,*";
P_HTM[7670]="*“yenesā, bho sela, nīlavanarājī”ti.**“There, Mister Sela, at that line of blue forest.”*";
P_HTM[7671]="*Atha kho selo brāhmaṇo tīhi māṇavakasatehi saddhiṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami.**Then Sela, together with his students, approached the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7672]="*Atha kho selo brāhmaṇo te māṇavake āmantesi:**He said to his students,*";
P_HTM[7673]="*“appasaddā bhonto āgacchantu pade padaṃ nikkhipantā;**“Come quietly, gentlemen, tread gently.*";
P_HTM[7674]="*durāsadā hi te bhagavanto sīhāva ekacarā.**For the Buddhas are intimidating, like a lion living alone.*";
P_HTM[7675]="*Yadā cāhaṃ, bho, samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ manteyyaṃ, mā me bhonto antarantarā kathaṃ opātetha.**When I’m consulting with the ascetic Gotama, don’t interrupt.*";
P_HTM[7676]="*Kathāpariyosānaṃ me bhavanto āgamentū”ti.**Wait until I’ve finished speaking.”*";
P_HTM[7677]="*Atha kho selo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Sela went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7678]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[7679]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho selo brāhmaṇo bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni samannesi.**and scrutinized the Buddha’s body for the thirty-two marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[7680]="*Addasā kho selo brāhmaṇo bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni, yebhuyyena ṭhapetvā dve.**He saw all of them except for two,*";
P_HTM[7681]="*Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—**which he had doubts about:*";
P_HTM[7682]="*kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya ca.**whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue.*";
P_HTM[7683]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then it occurred to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7684]="*“passati kho me ayaṃ selo brāhmaṇo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni, yebhuyyena ṭhapetvā dve.**“Sela sees all the marks except for two,*";
P_HTM[7685]="*Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—**which he has doubts about:*";
P_HTM[7686]="*kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya cā”ti.**whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue.”*";
P_HTM[7687]="*Atha kho bhagavā tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsi, yathā addasa selo brāhmaṇo bhagavato kosohitaṃ vatthaguyhaṃ.**The Buddha used his psychic power to will that Sela would see his retracted private parts.*";
P_HTM[7688]="*Atha kho bhagavā jivhaṃ ninnāmetvā ubhopi kaṇṇasotāni anumasi paṭimasi; ubhopi nāsikasotāni anumasi paṭimasi; kevalampi nalāṭamaṇḍalaṃ jivhāya chādesi.**And he stuck out his tongue and stroked back and forth on his ear holes and nostrils, and covered his entire forehead with his tongue.*";
P_HTM[7689]="*Atha kho selassa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi:**Then Sela thought,*";
P_HTM[7690]="*“samannāgato kho samaṇo gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi paripuṇṇehi, no aparipuṇṇehi;**“The ascetic Gotama possesses the thirty-two marks completely, lacking none.*";
P_HTM[7691]="*no ca kho naṃ jānāmi buddho vā no vā.**But I don’t know whether or not he is an awakened one.*";
P_HTM[7692]="*Sutaṃ kho pana metaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ vuddhānaṃ mahallakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:**I have heard that brahmins of the past who were elderly and senior, the teachers of teachers, said,*";
P_HTM[7693]="*‘ye te bhavanti arahanto sammāsambuddhā te sake vaṇṇe bhaññamāne attānaṃ pātukarontī’ti.**‘Those who are perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas reveal themselves when praised.’*";
P_HTM[7694]="*Yannūnāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ sammukhā sāruppāhi gāthāhi abhitthaveyyan”ti.**Why don’t I extoll him in his presence with fitting verses?”*";
P_HTM[7695]="*Atha kho selo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ sammukhā sāruppāhi gāthāhi abhitthavi:**Then Sela extolled the Buddha in his presence with fitting verses:*";
P_HTM[7696]="*“Paripuṇṇakāyo suruci,**“O Blessed One, your body’s perfect,*";
P_HTM[7697]="*Sujāto cārudassano;**you’re radiant, handsome, lovely to behold;*";
P_HTM[7698]="*Suvaṇṇavaṇṇosi bhagavā,**golden colored,*";
P_HTM[7699]="*Susukkadāṭhosi vīriyavā.**with teeth so white; you’re strong.*";
P_HTM[7700]="*Narassa hi sujātassa,**The characteristics*";
P_HTM[7701]="*ye bhavanti viyañjanā;**of a handsome man,*";
P_HTM[7702]="*Sabbe te tava kāyasmiṃ,**the marks of a great man,*";
P_HTM[7703]="*mahāpurisalakkhaṇā.**are all in your body.*";
P_HTM[7704]="*Pasannanetto sumukho,**Your eyes are clear, your face is fair,*";
P_HTM[7705]="*brahā uju patāpavā;**you’re formidable, upright, majestic.*";
P_HTM[7706]="*Majjhe samaṇasaṃghassa,**In the midst of the Saṅgha of ascetics,*";
P_HTM[7707]="*ādiccova virocasi.**you shine like the sun.*";
P_HTM[7708]="*Kalyāṇadassano bhikkhu,**You’re a mendicant fine to see,*";
P_HTM[7709]="*kañcanasannibhattaco;**with skin of golden sheen.*";
P_HTM[7710]="*Kiṃ te samaṇabhāvena,**But with such excellent appearance,*";
P_HTM[7711]="*evaṃ uttamavaṇṇino.**what do you want with the ascetic life?*";
P_HTM[7712]="*Rājā arahasi bhavituṃ,**You’re fit to be a king,*";
P_HTM[7713]="*cakkavattī rathesabho;**a wheel-turning monarch, chief of charioteers,*";
P_HTM[7714]="*Cāturanto vijitāvī,**victorious in the four directions,*";
P_HTM[7715]="*jambusaṇḍassa issaro.**lord of all India.*";
P_HTM[7716]="*Khattiyā bhogirājāno,**Aristocrats, nobles, and kings*";
P_HTM[7717]="*anuyantā bhavantu te;**follow your rule.*";
P_HTM[7718]="*Rājābhirājā manujindo,**Gotama, you should reign*";
P_HTM[7719]="*rajjaṃ kārehi gotama”.**as king of kings, lord of men!”*";
P_HTM[7720]="*“Rājāhamasmi selāti,**“I am a king, Sela—*";
P_HTM[7721]="*dhammarājā anuttaro;**the supreme king of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[7722]="*Dhammena cakkaṃ vattemi,**By the teaching I roll forth the wheel*";
P_HTM[7723]="*cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ”.**which cannot be rolled back.”*";
P_HTM[7724]="*“Sambuddho paṭijānāsi,**“You claim to be awakened,*";
P_HTM[7725]="*dhammarājā anuttaro;**the supreme king of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[7726]="*‘Dhammena cakkaṃ vattemi’,**‘I roll forth the teaching’:*";
P_HTM[7727]="*iti bhāsasi gotama.**so you say, Gotama.*";
P_HTM[7728]="*Ko nu senāpati bhoto,**Then who is your general,*";
P_HTM[7729]="*sāvako satthuranvayo;**the disciple who follows the Teacher’s way?*";
P_HTM[7730]="*Ko tetamanuvatteti,**Who keeps rolling the wheel*";
P_HTM[7731]="*dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ”.**of teaching you rolled forth?”*";
P_HTM[7732]="*“Mayā pavattitaṃ cakkaṃ,**“By me the wheel was rolled forth,”*";
P_HTM[7733]="*(selāti bhagavā)**said the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7734]="*Dhammacakkaṃ anuttaraṃ;**“the supreme wheel of teaching.*";
P_HTM[7735]="*Sāriputto anuvatteti,**Sāriputta, taking after the Realized One,*";
P_HTM[7736]="*Anujāto tathāgataṃ.**keeps it rolling on.*";
P_HTM[7737]="*Abhiññeyyaṃ abhiññātaṃ,**I have known what should be known,*";
P_HTM[7738]="*bhāvetabbañca bhāvitaṃ;**and developed what should be developed,*";
P_HTM[7739]="*Pahātabbaṃ pahīnaṃ me,**and given up what should be given up:*";
P_HTM[7740]="*tasmā buddhosmi brāhmaṇa.**and so, brahmin, I am a Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7741]="*Vinayassu mayi kaṅkhaṃ,**Dispel your doubt in me—*";
P_HTM[7742]="*adhimuccassu brāhmaṇa;**make up your mind, brahmin!*";
P_HTM[7743]="*Dullabhaṃ dassanaṃ hoti,**The sight of a Buddha*";
P_HTM[7744]="*sambuddhānaṃ abhiṇhaso.**is hard to find again.*";
P_HTM[7745]="*Yesaṃ ve dullabho loke,**I am a Buddha, brahmin,*";
P_HTM[7746]="*pātubhāvo abhiṇhaso;**the supreme surgeon,*";
P_HTM[7747]="*Sohaṃ brāhmaṇa sambuddho,**one of those whose appearance in the world*";
P_HTM[7748]="*sallakatto anuttaro.**is hard to find again.*";
P_HTM[7749]="*Brahmabhūto atitulo,**Holy, unequalled,*";
P_HTM[7750]="*mārasenappamaddano;**crusher of Māra’s army;*";
P_HTM[7751]="*Sabbāmitte vasī katvā,**having subdued all my opponents,*";
P_HTM[7752]="*modāmi akutobhayo”.**I rejoice, fearing nothing from any quarter.”*";
P_HTM[7753]="*“Imaṃ bhonto nisāmetha,**“Pay heed, sirs, to what*";
P_HTM[7754]="*yathā bhāsati cakkhumā;**is spoken by the seer.*";
P_HTM[7755]="*Sallakatto mahāvīro,**The surgeon, the great hero,*";
P_HTM[7756]="*sīhova nadatī vane.**roars like a lion in the jungle.*";
P_HTM[7757]="*Brahmabhūtaṃ atitulaṃ,**Holy, unequalled,*";
P_HTM[7758]="*mārasenappamaddanaṃ;**crusher of Māra’s army;*";
P_HTM[7759]="*Ko disvā nappasīdeyya,**who would not be inspired by him,*";
P_HTM[7760]="*api kaṇhābhijātiko.**even one whose nature is dark?*";
P_HTM[7761]="*Yo maṃ icchati anvetu,**Those who wish may follow me;*";
P_HTM[7762]="*yo vā nicchati gacchatu;**those who don’t may go.*";
P_HTM[7763]="*Idhāhaṃ pabbajissāmi,**Right here, I’ll go forth in the presence of him,*";
P_HTM[7764]="*varapaññassa santike”.**this man of such splendid wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[7765]="*“Etañce ruccati bhoto,**“Sir, if you like*";
P_HTM[7766]="*sammāsambuddhasāsanaṃ;**the teaching of the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7767]="*Mayampi pabbajissāma,**we’ll also go forth in the presence of him,*";
P_HTM[7768]="*varapaññassa santike”.**this man of such splendid wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[7769]="*Brāhmaṇā tisatā ime,**“These three hundred brahmins*";
P_HTM[7770]="*yācanti pañjalīkatā;**with joined palms held up, ask:*";
P_HTM[7771]="*“Brahmacariyaṃ carissāma,**‘May we lead the spiritual life*";
P_HTM[7772]="*bhagavā tava santike”.**in your presence, Blessed One?’”*";
P_HTM[7773]="*“Svākkhātaṃ brahmacariyaṃ,**“The spiritual life is well explained,”*";
P_HTM[7774]="*(selāti bhagavā)**said the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[7775]="*Sandiṭṭhikamakālikaṃ;**“visible in this very life, immediately effective.*";
P_HTM[7776]="*Yattha amoghā pabbajjā,**Here the going forth isn’t in vain*";
P_HTM[7777]="*Appamattassa sikkhato”ti.**for one who trains with diligence.”*";
P_HTM[7778]="*Alattha kho selo brāhmaṇo sapariso bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ.**And the brahmin Sela together with his assembly received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence.*";
P_HTM[7779]="*Atha kho keṇiyo jaṭilo tassā rattiyā accayena sake assame paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi:**And when the night had passed Keṇiya had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home. Then he had the Buddha informed of the time, saying,*";
P_HTM[7780]="*“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**“It’s time, Master Gotama, the meal is ready.”*";
P_HTM[7781]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena keṇiyassa jaṭilassa assamo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Keṇiya’s hermitage, where he sat on the seat spread out, together with the Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[7782]="*Atha kho keṇiyo jaṭilo buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi, sampavāresi.**Then Keṇiya served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[7783]="*Atha kho keṇiyo jaṭilo bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Keṇiya took a low seat and sat to one side.*";
P_HTM[7784]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho keṇiyaṃ jaṭilaṃ bhagavā imāhi gāthāhi anumodi:**The Buddha expressed his appreciation with these verses:*";
P_HTM[7785]="*“Aggihuttamukhā yaññā,**“The foremost of sacrifices is offering to the sacred flame;*";
P_HTM[7786]="*sāvittī chandaso mukhaṃ;**the Sāvittī is the foremost of poetic meters;*";
P_HTM[7787]="*Rājā mukhaṃ manussānaṃ,**of humans, the king is the foremost;*";
P_HTM[7788]="*nadīnaṃ sāgaro mukhaṃ.**the ocean’s the foremost of rivers;*";
P_HTM[7789]="*Nakkhattānaṃ mukhaṃ cando,**the foremost of stars is the moon;*";
P_HTM[7790]="*ādicco tapataṃ mukhaṃ;**the sun is the foremost of lights;*";
P_HTM[7791]="*Puññaṃ ākaṅkhamānānaṃ,**for those who sacrifice seeking merit,*";
P_HTM[7792]="*saṅgho ve yajataṃ mukhan”ti.**the Saṅgha is the foremost.”*";
P_HTM[7793]="*Atha kho bhagavā keṇiyaṃ jaṭilaṃ imāhi gāthāhi anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**When the Buddha had expressed his appreciation to Keṇiya the matted-hair ascetic with these verses, he got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[7794]="*Atha kho āyasmā selo sapariso eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**Then Venerable Sela and his assembly, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. They lived having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[7795]="*“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi.**They understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[7796]="*Aññataro kho panāyasmā selo sapariso arahataṃ ahosi.**And Venerable Sela together with his assembly became perfected.*";
P_HTM[7797]="*Atha kho āyasmā selo sapariso yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:**Then Sela with his assembly went to see the Buddha. He arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said:*";
P_HTM[7798]="*“Yaṃ taṃ saraṇamāgamma,**“This is the eighth day since*";
P_HTM[7799]="*ito aṭṭhami cakkhumā;**we went for refuge, O seer.*";
P_HTM[7800]="*Sattarattena bhagavā,**In these seven days, Blessed One,*";
P_HTM[7801]="*dantamha tava sāsane.**we’ve become tamed in your teaching.*";
P_HTM[7802]="*Tuvaṃ buddho tuvaṃ satthā,**You are the Buddha, you are the Teacher,*";
P_HTM[7803]="*tuvaṃ mārābhibhū muni;**you are the sage who has overcome Māra;*";
P_HTM[7804]="*Tuvaṃ anusaye chetvā,**you have cut off the underlying tendencies,*";
P_HTM[7805]="*tiṇṇo tāresimaṃ pajaṃ.**you’ve crossed over, and you bring humanity across.*";
P_HTM[7806]="*Upadhī te samatikkantā,**You have transcended attachments,*";
P_HTM[7807]="*āsavā te padālitā;**your defilements are shattered;*";
P_HTM[7808]="*Sīhova anupādāno,**by not grasping, like a lion,*";
P_HTM[7809]="*pahīnabhayabheravo.**you’ve given up fear and dread.*";
P_HTM[7810]="*Bhikkhavo tisatā ime,**These three hundred mendicants*";
P_HTM[7811]="*tiṭṭhanti pañjalīkatā;**stand with joined palms raised.*";
P_HTM[7812]="*Pāde vīra pasārehi,**Stretch out your feet, great hero:*";
P_HTM[7813]="*nāgā vandantu satthuno”ti.**let these giants worship the Teacher.”*";
P_HTM[7814]="*Selasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7815]="*93. Assalāyanasutta**With Assalāyana*";
P_HTM[7816]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7817]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7818]="*Tena kho pana samayena nānāverajjakānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ pañcamattāni brāhmaṇasatāni sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasanti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time around five hundred brahmins from abroad were residing in Sāvatthī on some business.*";
P_HTM[7819]="*Atha kho tesaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ etadahosi:**Then those brahmins thought,*";
P_HTM[7820]="*“ayaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paññapeti.**“This ascetic Gotama advocates purification for all four classes.*";
P_HTM[7821]="*Ko nu kho pahoti samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti?**Who is capable of having a dialogue with him about this?”*";
P_HTM[7822]="*Tena kho pana samayena assalāyano nāma māṇavo sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati daharo, vuttasiro, soḷasavassuddesiko jātiyā, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo.**Now at that time the brahmin student Assalāyana was residing in Sāvatthī. He was young, newly tonsured; he was sixteen years old. He had mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. He knew philology and grammar, and was well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[7823]="*Atha kho tesaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ etadahosi:**Then those brahmins thought,*";
P_HTM[7824]="*“ayaṃ kho assalāyano māṇavo sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati daharo, vuttasiro, soḷasavassuddesiko jātiyā, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū … pe … anavayo.* **";
P_HTM[7825]="*So kho pahoti samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti.**“This Assalāyana is capable of having a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.”*";
P_HTM[7826]="*Atha kho te brāhmaṇā yena assalāyano māṇavo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā assalāyanaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavocuṃ:**So they approached Assalāyana and said to him,*";
P_HTM[7827]="*“ayaṃ, bho assalāyana, samaṇo gotamo cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paññapeti.**“This ascetic Gotama advocates purification for all four classes.*";
P_HTM[7828]="*Etu bhavaṃ assalāyano samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetū”ti.**Please, Mister Assalāyana, have a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.”*";
P_HTM[7829]="*Evaṃ vutte, assalāyano māṇavo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca:**When they said this, Assalāyana said to them,*";
P_HTM[7830]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dhammavādī;**“They say that the ascetic Gotama is a speaker of principle.*";
P_HTM[7831]="*dhammavādino ca pana duppaṭimantiyā bhavanti.**But speakers of principle are hard to have a dialogue with.*";
P_HTM[7832]="*Nāhaṃ sakkomi samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti.**I’m not capable of having a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.”*";
P_HTM[7833]="*Dutiyampi kho te brāhmaṇā assalāyanaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavocuṃ:**For a second time, those brahmins said to him*";
P_HTM[7834]="*“ayaṃ, bho assalāyana, samaṇo gotamo cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paññapeti.**“This ascetic Gotama advocates purification for all four classes.*";
P_HTM[7835]="*Etu bhavaṃ assalāyano samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetu.**Please, Mister Assalāyana, have a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.*";
P_HTM[7836]="*Caritaṃ kho pana bhotā assalāyanena paribbājakan”ti.**For you have lived as a wanderer.”*";
P_HTM[7837]="*Dutiyampi kho assalāyano māṇavo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca:**And for a second time, Assalāyana refused.*";
P_HTM[7838]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dhammavādī;* **";
P_HTM[7839]="*dhammavādino ca pana duppaṭimantiyā bhavanti.* **";
P_HTM[7840]="*Nāhaṃ sakkomi samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7841]="*Tatiyampi kho te brāhmaṇā assalāyanaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavocuṃ:**For a third time, those brahmins said to him,*";
P_HTM[7842]="*“ayaṃ, bho assalāyana, samaṇo gotamo cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paññapeti.**“This ascetic Gotama advocates purification for all four classes.*";
P_HTM[7843]="*Etu bhavaṃ assalāyano samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetu.**Please, Mister Assalāyana, have a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.*";
P_HTM[7844]="*Caritaṃ kho pana bhotā assalāyanena paribbājakaṃ.**For you have lived as a wanderer.*";
P_HTM[7845]="*Mā bhavaṃ assalāyano ayuddhaparājitaṃ parājayī”ti.**Don’t admit defeat before going into battle!”*";
P_HTM[7846]="*Evaṃ vutte, assalāyano māṇavo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca:**When they said this, Assalāyana said to them,*";
P_HTM[7847]="*“addhā kho ahaṃ bhavanto na labhāmi.**“Clearly, gentlemen, I’m not getting through to you when I say:*";
P_HTM[7848]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dhammavādī;**‘They say that the ascetic Gotama is a speaker of principle.*";
P_HTM[7849]="*dhammavādino ca pana duppaṭimantiyā bhavanti.**But speakers of principle are hard to have a dialogue with.*";
P_HTM[7850]="*Nāhaṃ sakkomi samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetunti.**I’m not capable of having a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.’*";
P_HTM[7851]="*Api cāhaṃ bhavantānaṃ vacanena gamissāmī”ti.**Nevertheless, I shall go at your bidding.”*";
P_HTM[7852]="*Atha kho assalāyano māṇavo mahatā brāhmaṇagaṇena saddhiṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Assalāyana together with a large group of brahmins went to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[7853]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho assalāyano māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[7854]="*“brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, evamāhaṃsu:**“Master Gotama, the brahmins say:*";
P_HTM[7855]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo;**‘Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior.*";
P_HTM[7856]="*brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo;**Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark.*";
P_HTM[7857]="*brāhmaṇova sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā;**Only brahmins are purified, not others.*";
P_HTM[7858]="*brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’ti.**Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.’*";
P_HTM[7859]="*Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti?**What do you say about this?”*";
P_HTM[7860]="*“Dissanti kho pana, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ brāhmaṇiyo utuniyopi gabbhiniyopi vijāyamānāpi pāyamānāpi.**“But Assalāyana, brahmin women are seen menstruating, being pregnant, giving birth, and breastfeeding.*";
P_HTM[7861]="*Te ca brāhmaṇiyonijāva samānā evamāhaṃsu:**Yet even though they’re born from a brahmin womb they say:*";
P_HTM[7862]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo;**‘Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior.*";
P_HTM[7863]="*brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo;**Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark.*";
P_HTM[7864]="*brāhmaṇāva sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā;**Only brahmins are purified, not others.*";
P_HTM[7865]="*brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’”ti.**Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.’”*";
P_HTM[7866]="*“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti:**“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.”*";
P_HTM[7867]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7868]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7869]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7870]="*sutaṃ te: ‘yonakambojesu aññesu ca paccantimesu janapadesu dveva vaṇṇā—ayyo ceva dāso ca; ayyo hutvā dāso hoti, dāso hutvā ayyo hotī’”ti?**Have you heard that in Greece and Persia and other foreign lands there are only two classes, masters and bonded servants; and that masters may become servants, and servants masters?”*";
P_HTM[7871]="*“Evaṃ, bho, sutaṃ taṃ me: ‘yonakambojesu aññesu ca paccantimesu janapadesu dveva vaṇṇā—ayyo ceva dāso ca; ayyo hutvā dāso hoti, dāso hutvā ayyo hotī’”ti.**“Yes, I have heard that.”*";
P_HTM[7872]="*“Ettha, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ kiṃ balaṃ, ko assāso yadettha brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:**“Then what is the source of the brahmins’ self-confidence and forcefulness in this matter that they make this claim?”*";
P_HTM[7873]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7874]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7875]="*“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti:**“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.”*";
P_HTM[7876]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7877]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7878]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7879]="*khattiyova nu kho pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya, no brāhmaṇo?**Suppose an aristocrat were to kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct; to use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and to be covetous, malicious, with wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’d be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. Would this happen only to an aristocrat, and not to a brahmin?*";
P_HTM[7880]="*Vessova nu kho … pe …**Or suppose a merchant,*";
P_HTM[7881]="*suddova nu kho pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya, no brāhmaṇo”ti?**or a worker were to act in the same way. Would that result befall only a merchant or a worker, and not to a brahmin?”*";
P_HTM[7882]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[7883]="*Khattiyopi hi, bho gotama, pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya.**If they acted the same way, the same result would befall an aristocrat, a brahmin, a merchant, or a worker.*";
P_HTM[7884]="*Brāhmaṇopi hi, bho gotama … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7885]="*vessopi hi, bho gotama … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7886]="*suddopi hi, bho gotama … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7887]="*sabbepi hi, bho gotama, cattāro vaṇṇā pāṇātipātino adinnādāyino kāmesumicchācārino musāvādino pisuṇavācā pharusavācā samphappalāpino abhijjhālū byāpannacittā micchādiṭṭhī kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyyun”ti.**For if any of the four classes were to kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct; to use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and to be covetous, malicious, with wrong view, then, when their body breaks up, after death, they’d be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.”*";
P_HTM[7888]="*“Ettha, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ kiṃ balaṃ, ko assāso yadettha brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:**“Then what is the source of the brahmins’ self-confidence and forcefulness in this matter that they make this claim?”*";
P_HTM[7889]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7890]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7891]="*“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti:**“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.”*";
P_HTM[7892]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7893]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7894]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7895]="*brāhmaṇova nu kho pāṇātipātā paṭivirato adinnādānā paṭivirato kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato musāvādā paṭivirato pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato samphappalāpā paṭivirato anabhijjhālu abyāpannacitto sammādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya, no khattiyo, no vesso, no suddo”ti?**Suppose a brahmin were to refrain from killing living creatures, stealing, and committing sexual misconduct; from using speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and from covetousness, malice, and wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’d be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. Would this happen only to an brahmin, and not to an aristocrat, a merchant, or a worker?”*";
P_HTM[7896]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[7897]="*Khattiyopi hi, bho gotama, pāṇātipātā paṭivirato adinnādānā paṭivirato kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato musāvādā paṭivirato pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato samphappalāpā paṭivirato anabhijjhālu abyāpannacitto sammādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyya.**If they acted the same way, the same result would befall an aristocrat, a brahmin, a merchant, or a worker.*";
P_HTM[7898]="*Brāhmaṇopi hi, bho gotama … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7899]="*vessopi hi, bho gotama … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7900]="*suddopi hi, bho gotama … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7901]="*sabbepi hi, bho gotama, cattāro vaṇṇā pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā adinnādānā paṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratā musāvādā paṭiviratā pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratā pharusāya vācāya paṭiviratā samphappalāpā paṭiviratā anabhijjhālū abyāpannacittā sammādiṭṭhī kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyun”ti.**For if any of the four classes were to refrain from killing living creatures, stealing, and committing sexual misconduct; from using speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and from covetousness, malice, and wrong view, then, when their body breaks up, after death, they’d be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.”*";
P_HTM[7902]="*“Ettha, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ kiṃ balaṃ, ko assāso yadettha brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:**“Then what is the source of the brahmins’ self-confidence and forcefulness in this matter that they make this claim?”*";
P_HTM[7903]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7904]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7905]="*“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti:**“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.”*";
P_HTM[7906]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7907]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7908]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7909]="*brāhmaṇova nu kho pahoti asmiṃ padese averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāvetuṃ, no khattiyo, no vesso, no suddo”ti?**Is only a brahmin capable of developing a heart of love, free of enmity and ill will for this region, and not an aristocrat, merchant, or worker?”*";
P_HTM[7910]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[7911]="*Khattiyopi hi, bho gotama, pahoti asmiṃ padese averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāvetuṃ;**Aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers can all do so.*";
P_HTM[7912]="*brāhmaṇopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[7913]="*vessopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[7914]="*suddopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[7915]="*sabbepi hi, bho gotama, cattāro vaṇṇā pahonti asmiṃ padese averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāvetun”ti.**For all four classes are capable of developing a heart of love, free of enmity and ill will for this region.”*";
P_HTM[7916]="*“Ettha, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ kiṃ balaṃ, ko assāso yadettha brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:**“Then what is the source of the brahmins’ self-confidence and forcefulness in this matter that they make this claim?”*";
P_HTM[7917]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7918]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7919]="*“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti:**“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.”*";
P_HTM[7920]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7921]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7922]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7923]="*brāhmaṇova nu kho pahoti sottisināniṃ ādāya nadiṃ gantvā rajojallaṃ pavāhetuṃ, no khattiyo, no vesso, no suddo”ti?**Is only a brahmin capable of taking some bathing paste of powdered shell, going to the river, and washing off dust and dirt, and not an aristocrat, merchant, or worker?”*";
P_HTM[7924]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[7925]="*Khattiyopi hi, bho gotama, pahoti sottisināniṃ ādāya nadiṃ gantvā rajojallaṃ pavāhetuṃ, brāhmaṇopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[7926]="*vessopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[7927]="*suddopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[7928]="*sabbepi hi, bho gotama, cattāro vaṇṇā pahonti sottisināniṃ ādāya nadiṃ gantvā rajojallaṃ pavāhetun”ti.**All four classes are capable of doing this.”*";
P_HTM[7929]="*“Ettha, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ kiṃ balaṃ, ko assāso yadettha brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:**“Then what is the source of the brahmins’ self-confidence and forcefulness in this matter that they make this claim?”*";
P_HTM[7930]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7931]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7932]="*“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti:**“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.”*";
P_HTM[7933]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7934]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7935]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7936]="*idha rājā khattiyo muddhāvasitto nānājaccānaṃ purisānaṃ purisasataṃ sannipāteyya:**Suppose an anointed aristocratic king were to gather a hundred people born in different castes and say to them:*";
P_HTM[7937]="*‘āyantu bhonto ye tattha khattiyakulā brāhmaṇakulā rājaññakulā uppannā, sākassa vā sālassa vā salaḷassa vā candanassa vā padumakassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya, aggiṃ abhinibbattentu, tejo pātukarontu.**‘Please gentlemen, let anyone here who was born in a family of aristocrats, brahmins, or chieftains take a drill-stick made of teak, sal, frankincense wood, sandalwood, or cherry wood, light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[7938]="*Āyantu pana bhonto ye tattha caṇḍālakulā nesādakulā venakulā rathakārakulā pukkusakulā uppannā, sāpānadoṇiyā vā sūkaradoṇiyā vā rajakadoṇiyā vā eraṇḍakaṭṭhassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya, aggiṃ abhinibbattentu, tejo pātukarontū’ti.**And let anyone here who was born in a family of outcastes, hunters, bamboo-workers, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors take a drill-stick made from a dog’s drinking trough, a pig’s trough, a dustbin, or castor-oil wood, light a fire and produce heat.’*";
P_HTM[7939]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7940]="*yo evaṃ nu kho so khattiyakulā brāhmaṇakulā rājaññakulā uppannehi sākassa vā sālassa vā salaḷassa vā candanassa vā padumakassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggi abhinibbatto, tejo pātukato, so eva nu khvāssa aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro ca, tena ca sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ;**Would only the fire produced by the high class people with good quality wood have flames, color, and radiance, and be usable as fire,*";
P_HTM[7941]="*yo pana so caṇḍālakulā nesādakulā venakulā rathakārakulā pukkusakulā uppannehi sāpānadoṇiyā vā sūkaradoṇiyā vā rajakadoṇiyā vā eraṇḍakaṭṭhassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggi abhinibbatto, tejo pātukato svāssa aggi na ceva accimā na ca vaṇṇavā na ca pabhassaro, na ca tena sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātun”ti?**and not the fire produced by the low class people with poor quality wood?”*";
P_HTM[7942]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[7943]="*Yopi hi so, bho gotama, khattiyakulā brāhmaṇakulā rājaññakulā uppannehi sākassa vā sālassa vā salaḷassa vā candanassa vā padumakassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggi abhinibbatto, tejo pātukato svāssa aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro ca, tena ca sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ;**The fire produced by the high class people with good quality wood would have flames, color, and radiance, and be usable as fire,*";
P_HTM[7944]="*yopi so caṇḍālakulā nesādakulā venakulā rathakārakulā pukkusakulā uppannehi sāpānadoṇiyā vā sūkaradoṇiyā vā rajakadoṇiyā vā eraṇḍakaṭṭhassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggi abhinibbatto, tejo pātukato, svāssa aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro ca, tena ca sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ.**and so would the fire produced by the low class people with poor quality wood.*";
P_HTM[7945]="*Sabbopi hi, bho gotama, aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro ca, sabbenapi sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātun”ti.**For all fire has flames, color, and radiance, and is usable as fire.”*";
P_HTM[7946]="*“Ettha, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ kiṃ balaṃ, ko assāso yadettha brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:**“Then what is the source of the brahmins’ self-confidence and forcefulness in this matter that they make this claim?”*";
P_HTM[7947]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo;* **";
P_HTM[7948]="*brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo;* **";
P_HTM[7949]="*brāhmaṇāva sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā;* **";
P_HTM[7950]="*brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[7951]="*“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti:**“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.”*";
P_HTM[7952]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7953]="*brahmadāyādā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[7954]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7955]="*idha khattiyakumāro brāhmaṇakaññāya saddhiṃ saṃvāsaṃ kappeyya, tesaṃ saṃvāsamanvāya putto jāyetha;**Suppose an aristocrat boy was to sleep with a brahmin girl, and they had a child.*";
P_HTM[7956]="*yo so khattiyakumārena brāhmaṇakaññāya putto uppanno, siyā so mātupi sadiso pitupi sadiso, ‘khattiyo’tipi vattabbo ‘brāhmaṇo’tipi vattabbo”ti?**Would that child be called an aristocrat after the father or a brahmin after the mother?”*";
P_HTM[7957]="*“Yo so, bho gotama, khattiyakumārena brāhmaṇakaññāya putto uppanno, siyā so mātupi sadiso pitupi sadiso, ‘khattiyo’tipi vattabbo ‘brāhmaṇo’tipi vattabbo”ti.**“They could be called either.”*";
P_HTM[7958]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7959]="*idha brāhmaṇakumāro khattiyakaññāya saddhiṃ saṃvāsaṃ kappeyya, tesaṃ saṃvāsamanvāya putto jāyetha;**Suppose a brahmin boy was to sleep with an aristocrat girl, and they had a child.*";
P_HTM[7960]="*yo so brāhmaṇakumārena khattiyakaññāya putto uppanno, siyā so mātupi sadiso pitupi sadiso, ‘khattiyo’tipi vattabbo ‘brāhmaṇo’tipi vattabbo”ti?**Would that child be called an aristocrat after the mother or a brahmin after the father?”*";
P_HTM[7961]="*“Yo so, bho gotama, brāhmaṇakumārena khattiyakaññāya putto uppanno, siyā so mātupi sadiso pitupi sadiso, ‘khattiyo’tipi vattabbo ‘brāhmaṇo’tipi vattabbo”ti.**“They could be called either.”*";
P_HTM[7962]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7963]="*idha vaḷavaṃ gadrabhena sampayojeyyuṃ, tesaṃ sampayogamanvāya kisoro jāyetha;**Suppose a mare were to mate with a donkey, and she gave birth to a mule.*";
P_HTM[7964]="*yo so vaḷavāya gadrabhena kisoro uppanno, siyā so mātupi sadiso pitupi sadiso, ‘asso’tipi vattabbo ‘gadrabho’tipi vattabbo”ti?**Would that mule be called a horse after the mother or a donkey after the father?”*";
P_HTM[7965]="*“Kuṇḍañhi so, bho gotama, assataro hoti.**“It’s a mule, as it is a crossbreed.*";
P_HTM[7966]="*Idaṃ hissa, bho gotama, nānākaraṇaṃ passāmi;**I see the difference in this case,*";
P_HTM[7967]="*amutra ca panesānaṃ na kiñci nānākaraṇaṃ passāmī”ti.**but not in the previous cases.”*";
P_HTM[7968]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7969]="*idhāssu dve māṇavakā bhātaro sodariyā, eko ajjhāyako upanīto eko anajjhāyako anupanīto.**Suppose there were two brahmin students who were brothers who had shared a womb. One was educated, a reciter, while the other was uneducated and not a reciter.*";
P_HTM[7970]="*Kamettha brāhmaṇā paṭhamaṃ bhojeyyuṃ saddhe vā thālipāke vā yaññe vā pāhune vā”ti?**Who would the brahmins feed first at an offering of food for ancestors, an offering of a dish of milk-rice, a sacrifice, or a feast for guests?”*";
P_HTM[7971]="*“Yo so, bho gotama, māṇavako ajjhāyako upanīto tamettha brāhmaṇā paṭhamaṃ bhojeyyuṃ saddhe vā thālipāke vā yaññe vā pāhune vā.**“They’d first feed the student who was educated, a reciter.*";
P_HTM[7972]="*Kiñhi, bho gotama, anajjhāyake anupanīte dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ bhavissatī”ti?**For how could an offering to someone who is uneducated and not a reciter be very fruitful?”*";
P_HTM[7973]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana,**“What do you think, Assalāyana?*";
P_HTM[7974]="*idhāssu dve māṇavakā bhātaro sodariyā, eko ajjhāyako upanīto dussīlo pāpadhammo, eko anajjhāyako anupanīto sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo.**Suppose there were two brahmin students who were brothers who had shared a womb. One was educated, a reciter, but was unethical, of bad character, while the other was uneducated and not a reciter, but was ethical and of good character.*";
P_HTM[7975]="*Kamettha brāhmaṇā paṭhamaṃ bhojeyyuṃ saddhe vā thālipāke vā yaññe vā pāhune vā”ti?**Who would the brahmins feed first?”*";
P_HTM[7976]="*“Yo so, bho gotama, māṇavako anajjhāyako anupanīto sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo tamettha brāhmaṇā paṭhamaṃ bhojeyyuṃ saddhe vā thālipāke vā yaññe vā pāhune vā.**“They’d first feed the student who was uneducated and not a reciter, but was ethical and of good character.*";
P_HTM[7977]="*Kiñhi, bho gotama, dussīle pāpadhamme dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ bhavissatī”ti?**For how could an offering to someone who is unethical and of bad character be very fruitful?”*";
P_HTM[7978]="*“Pubbe kho tvaṃ, assalāyana, jātiṃ agamāsi;**“Firstly you relied on birth, Assalāyana,*";
P_HTM[7979]="*jātiṃ gantvā mante agamāsi;**then you switched to education,*";
P_HTM[7980]="*mante gantvā tape agamāsi;**then you switched to abstemious behavior.*";
P_HTM[7981]="*tape gantvā cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paccāgato, yamahaṃ paññapemī”ti.**Now you’ve come around to believing in purification for the four classes, just as I advocate.”*";
P_HTM[7982]="*Evaṃ vutte, assalāyano māṇavo tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto pattakkhandho adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno nisīdi.**When he said this, Assalāyana sat silent, embarrassed, shoulders drooping, downcast, depressed, with nothing to say.*";
P_HTM[7983]="*Atha kho bhagavā assalāyanaṃ māṇavaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ maṅkubhūtaṃ pattakkhandhaṃ adhomukhaṃ pajjhāyantaṃ appaṭibhānaṃ viditvā assalāyanaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavoca:**Knowing this, the Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[7984]="*“bhūtapubbaṃ, assalāyana, sattannaṃ brāhmaṇisīnaṃ araññāyatane paṇṇakuṭīsu sammantānaṃ evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti:**“Once upon a time, Assalāyana, seven brahmin hermits settled in leaf huts in a wilderness region. They had the following harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[7985]="*‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo …**‘Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior.*";
P_HTM[7986]="*pe …**Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark. Only brahmins are purified, not others.*";
P_HTM[7987]="*brahmadāyādā’ti.**Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.’*";
P_HTM[7988]="*Assosi kho, assalāyana, asito devalo isi:**The hermit Devala the Dark heard about this.*";
P_HTM[7989]="*‘sattannaṃ kira brāhmaṇisīnaṃ araññāyatane paṇṇakuṭīsu sammantānaṃ evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[7990]="*brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[7991]="*brahmadāyādā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[7992]="*Atha kho, assalāyana, asito devalo isi kesamassuṃ kappetvā mañjiṭṭhavaṇṇāni dussāni nivāsetvā paṭaliyo upāhanā āruhitvā jātarūpamayaṃ daṇḍaṃ gahetvā sattannaṃ brāhmaṇisīnaṃ patthaṇḍile pāturahosi.**So he did up his hair and beard, dressed in magenta robes, put on his boots, grasped a golden staff, and appeared in the courtyard of the seven brahmin hermits.*";
P_HTM[7993]="*Atha kho, assalāyana, asito devalo isi sattannaṃ brāhmaṇisīnaṃ patthaṇḍile caṅkamamāno evamāha:**Then he wandered about the yard saying,*";
P_HTM[7994]="*‘handa ko nu kho ime bhavanto brāhmaṇisayo gatā;**‘Where, oh where have those brahmin hermits gone?*";
P_HTM[7995]="*handa ko nu kho ime bhavanto brāhmaṇisayo gatā’ti?**Where, oh where have those brahmin hermits gone?’*";
P_HTM[7996]="*Atha kho, assalāyana, sattannaṃ brāhmaṇisīnaṃ etadahosi:**Then those brahmin hermits said,*";
P_HTM[7997]="*‘ko nāyaṃ gāmaṇḍalarūpo viya sattannaṃ brāhmaṇisīnaṃ patthaṇḍile caṅkamamāno evamāha:**‘Who’s this wandering about our courtyard like a cowpoke?*";
P_HTM[7998]="*“handa ko nu kho ime bhavanto brāhmaṇisayo gatā;* **";
P_HTM[7999]="*handa ko nu kho ime bhavanto brāhmaṇisayo gatāti?* **";
P_HTM[8000]="*Handa naṃ abhisapāmā”’ti.**Let’s curse him!’*";
P_HTM[8001]="*Atha kho, assalāyana, satta brāhmaṇisayo asitaṃ devalaṃ isiṃ abhisapiṃsu:**So they cursed Devala the Dark,*";
P_HTM[8002]="*‘bhasmā, vasala, hohi;**‘Be ashes, wretch!*";
P_HTM[8003]="*bhasmā, vasala, hohī’ti.**Be ashes, wretch!’*";
P_HTM[8004]="*Yathā yathā kho, assalāyana, satta brāhmaṇisayo asitaṃ devalaṃ isiṃ abhisapiṃsu tathā tathā asito devalo isi abhirūpataro ceva hoti dassanīyataro ca pāsādikataro ca.**But the more the hermits cursed him, the more attractive, good-looking, and lovely Devala the Dark became.*";
P_HTM[8005]="*Atha kho, assalāyana, sattannaṃ brāhmaṇisīnaṃ etadahosi:**Then those brahmin hermits said,*";
P_HTM[8006]="*‘moghaṃ vata no tapo, aphalaṃ brahmacariyaṃ.**‘Our austerities are in vain! Our spiritual path is fruitless!*";
P_HTM[8007]="*Mayañhi pubbe yaṃ abhisapāma—**For when we used to curse someone*";
P_HTM[8008]="*bhasmā, vasala, hohi;**to become ashes,*";
P_HTM[8009]="*bhasmā, vasala, hohīti bhasmāva bhavati ekacco.**ashes they became.*";
P_HTM[8010]="*Imaṃ pana mayaṃ yathā yathā abhisapāma tathā tathā abhirūpataro ceva hoti dassanīyataro ca pāsādikataro cā’ti.**But the more we curse this one, the more attractive, good-looking, and lovely he becomes.’*";
P_HTM[8011]="*‘Na bhavantānaṃ moghaṃ tapo, nāphalaṃ brahmacariyaṃ.**‘Gentlemen, your austerities are not in vain; your spiritual path is not fruitless.*";
P_HTM[8012]="*Iṅgha bhavanto, yo mayi manopadoso taṃ pajahathā’ti.**Please let go of your malevolence towards me.’*";
P_HTM[8013]="*‘Yo bhavati manopadoso taṃ pajahāma.**‘We let go of our malevolence towards you.*";
P_HTM[8014]="*Ko nu bhavaṃ hotī’ti?**But who are you, sir?’*";
P_HTM[8015]="*‘Suto nu bhavataṃ—**‘Have you heard of*";
P_HTM[8016]="*asito devalo isī’ti?**the hermit Devala the Dark?’*";
P_HTM[8017]="*‘Evaṃ, bho’.**‘Yes, sir.’*";
P_HTM[8018]="*‘So khvāhaṃ, bho, homī’ti.**‘I am he, sirs.’*";
P_HTM[8019]="*Atha kho, assalāyana, satta brāhmaṇisayo asitaṃ devalaṃ isiṃ abhivādetuṃ upakkamiṃsu.**Then they approached Devala and bowed to him.*";
P_HTM[8020]="*Atha kho, assalāyana, asito devalo isi satta brāhmaṇisayo etadavoca:**Devala said to them,*";
P_HTM[8021]="*‘sutaṃ metaṃ, bho, sattannaṃ kira brāhmaṇisīnaṃ araññāyatane paṇṇakuṭīsu sammantānaṃ evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**‘I heard that when the seven brahmin hermits had settled in leaf huts in a wilderness region, they had the following harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[8022]="*brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo;**“Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior.*";
P_HTM[8023]="*brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo;**Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark.*";
P_HTM[8024]="*brāhmaṇāva sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā;**Only brahmins are purified, not others.*";
P_HTM[8025]="*brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’ti.**Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.”’*";
P_HTM[8026]="*‘Evaṃ, bho’.**‘That’s right, sir.’*";
P_HTM[8027]="*‘Jānanti pana bhonto—**‘But do you know*";
P_HTM[8028]="*yā janikā mātā brāhmaṇaṃyeva agamāsi, no abrāhmaṇan’ti?**whether your birth mother only had relations with a brahmin and not with a non-brahmin?’*";
P_HTM[8029]="*‘No hidaṃ, bho’.**‘We don’t know that.’*";
P_HTM[8030]="*‘Jānanti pana bhonto—**‘But do you know*";
P_HTM[8031]="*yā janikāmātu mātā yāva sattamā mātumātāmahayugā brāhmaṇaṃyeva agamāsi, no abrāhmaṇan’ti?**whether your birth mother’s mothers back to the seventh generation only had relations with brahmins and not with non-brahmins?’*";
P_HTM[8032]="*‘No hidaṃ, bho’.**‘We don’t know that.’*";
P_HTM[8033]="*‘Jānanti pana bhonto—**‘But do you know*";
P_HTM[8034]="*yo janako pitā brāhmaṇiṃyeva agamāsi, no abrāhmaṇin’ti?**whether your birth father only had relations with a brahmin woman and not with a non-brahmin?’*";
P_HTM[8035]="*‘No hidaṃ, bho’.**‘We don’t know that.’*";
P_HTM[8036]="*‘Jānanti pana bhonto—**‘But do you know*";
P_HTM[8037]="*yo janakapitu pitā yāva sattamā pitupitāmahayugā brāhmaṇiṃyeva agamāsi, no abrāhmaṇin’ti?**whether your birth father’s fathers back to the seventh generation only had relations with brahmins and not with non-brahmins?’*";
P_HTM[8038]="*‘No hidaṃ, bho’.**‘We don’t know that.’*";
P_HTM[8039]="*‘Jānanti pana bhonto—**‘But do you know*";
P_HTM[8040]="*yathā gabbhassa avakkanti hotī’ti?**how an embryo is conceived?’*";
P_HTM[8041]="*‘Jānāma mayaṃ, bho—**‘We do know that, sir.*";
P_HTM[8042]="*yathā gabbhassa avakkanti hoti.* **";
P_HTM[8043]="*Idha mātāpitaro ca sannipatitā honti, mātā ca utunī hoti, gandhabbo ca paccupaṭṭhito hoti; evaṃ tiṇṇaṃ sannipātā gabbhassa avakkanti hotī’ti.**An embryo is conceived when these three things come together—the mother and father come together, the mother is in the fertile part of her menstrual cycle, and the spirit being reborn is present.’*";
P_HTM[8044]="*‘Jānanti pana bhonto—**‘But do you know*";
P_HTM[8045]="*taggha, so gandhabbo khattiyo vā brāhmaṇo vā vesso vā suddo vā’ti?**for sure whether that spirit is an aristocrat, a brahmin, a merchant, or a worker?’*";
P_HTM[8046]="*‘Na mayaṃ, bho, jānāma—**‘We don’t know that.’*";
P_HTM[8047]="*taggha so gandhabbo khattiyo vā brāhmaṇo vā vesso vā suddo vā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[8048]="*‘Evaṃ sante, bho, jānātha—**‘In that case, sirs, don’t you know*";
P_HTM[8049]="*ke tumhe hothā’ti?**what you are?’*";
P_HTM[8050]="*‘Evaṃ sante, bho, na mayaṃ jānāma—**‘In that case, sir, we don’t know*";
P_HTM[8051]="*ke mayaṃ homā’ti.**what we are.’*";
P_HTM[8052]="*Te hi nāma, assalāyana, satta brāhmaṇisayo asitena devalena isinā sake jātivāde samanuyuñjīyamānā samanuggāhīyamānā samanubhāsīyamānā na sampāyissanti;**So even those seven brahmin hermits were stumped when pursued, pressed, and grilled by the seer Devala on their own doctrine of ancestry.*";
P_HTM[8053]="*kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi mayā sakasmiṃ jātivāde samanuyuñjīyamāno samanuggāhīyamāno samanubhāsīyamāno sampāyissasi, yesaṃ tvaṃ sācariyako na puṇṇo dabbigāho”ti.**So how could you succeed, being grilled by me now on your own doctrine of ancestry—you who have not even mastered your own teacher’s doctrine?”*";
P_HTM[8054]="*Evaṃ vutte, assalāyano māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Assalāyana said to him,*";
P_HTM[8055]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! …*";
P_HTM[8056]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[8057]="*Assalāyanasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8058]="*94. Ghoṭamukhasutta**With Ghoṭamukha*";
P_HTM[8059]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8060]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā udeno bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati khemiyambavane.**At one time Venerable Udena was staying near Benares in the Khemiya Mango Grove.*";
P_HTM[8061]="*Tena kho pana samayena ghoṭamukho brāhmaṇo bārāṇasiṃ anuppatto hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time the brahmin Ghoṭamukha had arrived at Benares on some business.*";
P_HTM[8062]="*Atha kho ghoṭamukho brāhmaṇo jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno yena khemiyambavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Then as he was going for a walk he went to the Khemiya Mango Grove.*";
P_HTM[8063]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udeno abbhokāse caṅkamati.**At that time Venerable Udena was walking meditation in the open air.*";
P_HTM[8064]="*Atha kho ghoṭamukho brāhmaṇo yenāyasmā udeno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā udenena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Ghoṭamukha approached and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[8065]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā āyasmantaṃ udenaṃ caṅkamantaṃ anucaṅkamamāno evamāha:**Walking alongside Udena, he said,*";
P_HTM[8066]="*“ambho samaṇa, ‘natthi dhammiko paribbajo’—**“Mister ascetic, there is no such thing as a principled renunciate life;*";
P_HTM[8067]="*evaṃ me ettha hoti.**that’s what I think.*";
P_HTM[8068]="*Tañca kho bhavantarūpānaṃ vā adassanā, yo vā panettha dhammo”ti.**And that’s without seeing gentlemen such as yourself, or a relevant teaching.”*";
P_HTM[8069]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udeno caṅkamā orohitvā vihāraṃ pavisitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**When he said this, Udena stepped down from the walking path, entered his dwelling, and sat down on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[8070]="*Ghoṭamukhopi kho brāhmaṇo caṅkamā orohitvā vihāraṃ pavisitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**Ghoṭamukha also stepped down from the walking path and entered the dwelling, where he stood to one side.*";
P_HTM[8071]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho ghoṭamukhaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ āyasmā udeno etadavoca:**Udena said to him,*";
P_HTM[8072]="*“saṃvijjanti kho, brāhmaṇa, āsanāni.**“There are seats, brahmin.*";
P_HTM[8073]="*Sace ākaṅkhasi, nisīdā”ti.**Please sit if you wish.”*";
P_HTM[8074]="*“Etadeva kho pana mayaṃ bhoto udenassa āgamayamānā nisīdāma.**“I was just waiting for you to sit down.*";
P_HTM[8075]="*Kathañhi nāma mādiso pubbe animantito āsane nisīditabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti?**For how could one such as I presume to sit first without being invited?”*";
P_HTM[8076]="*Atha kho ghoṭamukho brāhmaṇo aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Then he took a low seat and sat to one side,*";
P_HTM[8077]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho ghoṭamukho brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ udenaṃ etadavoca:**where he said,*";
P_HTM[8078]="*“ambho samaṇa, ‘natthi dhammiko paribbajo’—**“Mister ascetic, there is no such thing as a principled renunciate life;*";
P_HTM[8079]="*evaṃ me ettha hoti.**that’s what I think.*";
P_HTM[8080]="*Tañca kho bhavantarūpānaṃ vā adassanā, yo vā panettha dhammo”ti.**And that’s without seeing gentlemen such as yourself, or a relevant teaching.”*";
P_HTM[8081]="*“Sace kho pana me tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anuññeyyaṃ anujāneyyāsi, paṭikkositabbañca paṭikkoseyyāsi; yassa ca pana me bhāsitassa atthaṃ na jāneyyāsi, mamaṃyeva tattha uttari paṭipuccheyyāsi:**“Brahmin, we can discuss this. But only if you allow what should be allowed, and reject what should be rejected. And if you ask me the meaning of anything you don’t understand, saying:*";
P_HTM[8082]="*‘idaṃ, bho udena, kathaṃ, imassa kvattho’ti? Evaṃ katvā siyā no ettha kathāsallāpo”ti.**‘Sir, why is this? What does that mean?’”*";
P_HTM[8083]="*“Anuññeyyaṃ khvāhaṃ bhoto udenassa anujānissāmi, paṭikkositabbañca paṭikkosissāmi; yassa ca panāhaṃ bhoto udenassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ na jānissāmi, bhavantaṃyeva tattha udenaṃ uttari paṭipucchissāmi: ‘idaṃ, bho udena, kathaṃ, imassa kvattho’ti? Evaṃ katvā hotu no ettha kathāsallāpo”ti.**“Let us discuss this. I will do as you say.”*";
P_HTM[8084]="*“Cattārome, brāhmaṇa, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Brahmin, these four people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[8085]="*Katame cattāro?**What four?*";
P_HTM[8086]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo attantapo hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies themselves, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves.*";
P_HTM[8087]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo parantapo hoti paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies others, committed to the practice of mortifying others.*";
P_HTM[8088]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo attantapo ca hoti attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person mortifies themselves and others, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[8089]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo nevattantapo hoti nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**One person doesn’t mortify either themselves or others, committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others.*";
P_HTM[8090]="*So anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati.**They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.*";
P_HTM[8091]="*Imesaṃ, brāhmaṇa, catunnaṃ puggalānaṃ katamo te puggalo cittaṃ ārādhetī”ti?**Which one of these four people do you like the sound of?”*";
P_HTM[8092]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho udena, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto ayaṃ me puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti;**“Sir, I don’t like the sound of the first three people.*";
P_HTM[8093]="*yopāyaṃ, bho udena, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto ayampi me puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti;* **";
P_HTM[8094]="*yopāyaṃ, bho udena, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto ayampi me puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti;* **";
P_HTM[8095]="*yo ca kho ayaṃ, bho udena, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati.* **";
P_HTM[8096]="*Ayameva me puggalo cittaṃ ārādhetī”ti.**I only like the sound of the last person, who doesn’t mortify either themselves or others.”*";
P_HTM[8097]="*“Kasmā pana te, brāhmaṇa, ime tayo puggalā cittaṃ nārādhentī”ti?**“But why don’t you like the sound of those three people?”*";
P_HTM[8098]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho udena, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so attānaṃ sukhakāmaṃ dukkhapaṭikkūlaṃ ātāpeti paritāpeti;**“Sir, the person who mortifies themselves does so even though they want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[8099]="*iminā me ayaṃ puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.**That’s why I don’t like the sound of that person.*";
P_HTM[8100]="*Yopāyaṃ, bho udena, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so paraṃ sukhakāmaṃ dukkhapaṭikkūlaṃ ātāpeti paritāpeti;**The person who mortifies others does so even though others want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[8101]="*iminā me ayaṃ puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.**That’s why I don’t like the sound of that person.*";
P_HTM[8102]="*Yopāyaṃ, bho udena, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so attānañca parañca sukhakāmaṃ dukkhapaṭikkūlaṃ ātāpeti paritāpeti;**The person who mortifies themselves and others does so even though both themselves and others want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[8103]="*iminā me ayaṃ puggalo cittaṃ nārādheti.**That’s why I don’t like the sound of that person.*";
P_HTM[8104]="*Yo ca kho ayaṃ, bho udena, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati, so attānañca parañca sukhakāmaṃ dukkhapaṭikkūlaṃ neva ātāpeti na paritāpeti;**The person who doesn’t mortify either themselves or others—living without wishes, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves—does not torment themselves or others, both of whom want to be happy and recoil from pain.*";
P_HTM[8105]="*iminā me ayaṃ puggalo cittaṃ ārādhetī”ti.**That’s why I like the sound of that person.”*";
P_HTM[8106]="*“Dvemā, brāhmaṇa, parisā.**“There are, brahmin, these two groups of people.*";
P_HTM[8107]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[8108]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekaccā parisā sārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu puttabhariyaṃ pariyesati, dāsidāsaṃ pariyesati, khettavatthuṃ pariyesati, jātarūparajataṃ pariyesati.**There’s one group of people who, being infatuated with jewels and earrings, seeks partners and children, male and female bondservants, fields and lands, and gold and money.*";
P_HTM[8109]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekaccā parisā asārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu puttabhariyaṃ pahāya, dāsidāsaṃ pahāya, khettavatthuṃ pahāya, jātarūparajataṃ pahāya, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā.**And there’s another group of people who, not being infatuated with jewels and earrings, has given up partner and children, male and female bondservants, fields and lands, and gold and money, and goes forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[8110]="*Svāyaṃ, brāhmaṇa, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**Now, brahmin, that person who doesn’t mortify either themselves or others—*";
P_HTM[8111]="*So anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati.* **";
P_HTM[8112]="*Idha katamaṃ tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, puggalaṃ katamāya parisāya bahulaṃ samanupassasi—**in which of these two groups of people do you usually find such a person?”*";
P_HTM[8113]="*yā cāyaṃ parisā sārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu puttabhariyaṃ pariyesati dāsidāsaṃ pariyesati khettavatthuṃ pariyesati jātarūparajataṃ pariyesati, yā cāyaṃ parisā asārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu puttabhariyaṃ pahāya dāsidāsaṃ pahāya khettavatthuṃ pahāya jātarūparajataṃ pahāya agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8114]="*“Yvāyaṃ, bho udena, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati;**“I usually find such a person in*";
P_HTM[8115]="*imāhaṃ puggalaṃ yāyaṃ parisā asārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu puttabhariyaṃ pahāya dāsidāsaṃ pahāya khettavatthuṃ pahāya jātarūparajataṃ pahāya agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā imissaṃ parisāyaṃ bahulaṃ samanupassāmī”ti.**the group that has gone forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[8116]="*“Idāneva kho pana te, brāhmaṇa, bhāsitaṃ: ‘mayaṃ evaṃ ājānāma—**“Just now I understood you to say:*";
P_HTM[8117]="*ambho samaṇa, natthi dhammiko paribbajo,**‘Mister ascetic, there is no such thing as a principled renunciate life;*";
P_HTM[8118]="*evaṃ me ettha hoti.**that’s what I think.*";
P_HTM[8119]="*Tañca kho bhavantarūpānaṃ vā adassanā, yo vā panettha dhammo’”ti.**And that’s without seeing gentlemen such as yourself, nor a relevant teaching.’”*";
P_HTM[8120]="*“Addhā mesā, bho udena, sānuggahā vācā bhāsitā.**“Well, I obviously had my reasons for saying that, master Udena.*";
P_HTM[8121]="*‘Atthi dhammiko paribbajo’—**But there is such a thing as a principled renunciate life;*";
P_HTM[8122]="*evaṃ me ettha hoti.**that’s what I think.*";
P_HTM[8123]="*Evañca pana maṃ bhavaṃ udeno dhāretu.**Please remember me as saying this.*";
P_HTM[8124]="*Ye ca me bhotā udenena cattāro puggalā saṅkhittena vuttā vitthārena avibhattā, sādhu me bhavaṃ, udeno ime cattāro puggale vitthārena vibhajatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti.**Now, these four kinds of people that you’ve spoken of in a brief summary: please explain them to me in detail, out of compassion.”*";
P_HTM[8125]="*“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[8126]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho ghoṭamukho brāhmaṇo āyasmato udenassa paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Ghoṭamukha.*";
P_HTM[8127]="*Āyasmā udeno etadavoca:**Udena said this:*";
P_HTM[8128]="*“Katamo ca, brāhmaṇa, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**“What person mortifies themselves, committed to the practice of mortifying themselves?*";
P_HTM[8129]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo acelako hoti muttācāro hatthāpalekhano naehibhaddantiko natiṭṭhabhaddantiko, nābhihaṭaṃ na uddissakataṃ na nimantanaṃ sādiyati.**It’s when someone goes naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal.*";
P_HTM[8130]="*So na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na eḷakamantaraṃ, na daṇḍamantaraṃ, na musalamantaraṃ, na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ, na gabbhiniyā, na pāyamānāya, na purisantaragatāya, na saṅkittīsu, na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti, na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī, na macchaṃ na maṃsaṃ, na suraṃ na merayaṃ na thusodakaṃ pivati.**They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer.*";
P_HTM[8131]="*So ekāgāriko vā hoti ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā hoti dvālopiko … pe … sattāgāriko vā hoti sattālopiko;**They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls.*";
P_HTM[8132]="*ekissāpi dattiyā yāpeti, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpeti … pe … sattahipi dattīhi yāpeti;**They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day.*";
P_HTM[8133]="*ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti … pe … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti—iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikaṃ pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even up to once a fortnight. They live committed to the practice of eating food at set intervals.*";
P_HTM[8134]="*So sākabhakkho vā hoti, sāmākabhakkho vā hoti, nīvārabhakkho vā hoti, daddulabhakkho vā hoti, haṭabhakkho vā hoti, kaṇabhakkho vā hoti, ācāmabhakkho vā hoti, piññākabhakkho vā hoti, tiṇabhakkho vā hoti, gomayabhakkho vā hoti, vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī.**They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit.*";
P_HTM[8135]="*So sāṇānipi dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti, chavadussānipi dhāreti, paṃsukūlānipi dhāreti, tirīṭānipi dhāreti, ajinampi dhāreti, ajinakkhipampi dhāreti, kusacīrampi dhāreti, vākacīrampi dhāreti, phalakacīrampi dhāreti, kesakambalampi dhāreti, vāḷakambalampi dhāreti, ulūkapakkhampi dhāreti;**They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings.*";
P_HTM[8136]="*kesamassulocakopi hoti kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto,**They tear out their hair and beard, committed to this practice.*";
P_HTM[8137]="*ubbhaṭṭhakopi hoti āsanapaṭikkhitto,**They constantly stand, refusing seats.*";
P_HTM[8138]="*ukkuṭikopi hoti ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto,**They squat, committed to persisting in the squatting position.*";
P_HTM[8139]="*kaṇṭakāpassayikopi hoti kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappeti;**They lie on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns their bed.*";
P_HTM[8140]="*sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati—**They’re committed to the practice of immersion in water three times a day, including the evening.*";
P_HTM[8141]="*iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharati.**And so they live committed to practicing these various ways of mortifying and tormenting the body.*";
P_HTM[8142]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies themselves, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves.*";
P_HTM[8143]="*Katamo ca, brāhmaṇa, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And what person mortifies others, committed to the practice of mortifying others?*";
P_HTM[8144]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo orabbhiko hoti sūkariko sākuṇiko māgaviko luddo macchaghātako coro coraghātako goghātako bandhanāgāriko—ye vā panaññepi keci kurūrakammantā.**It’s when a person is a slaughterer of sheep, pigs, poultry, or deer, a hunter or fisher, a bandit, an executioner, a butcher of cattle, a jailer, or has some other cruel livelihood.*";
P_HTM[8145]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies others, being committed to the practice of mortifying others.*";
P_HTM[8146]="*Katamo ca, brāhmaṇa, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?**And what person mortifies themselves and others, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others?*";
P_HTM[8147]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco puggalo rājā vā hoti khattiyo muddhāvasitto, brāhmaṇo vā mahāsālo.**It’s when a person is an anointed king or a well-to-do brahmin.*";
P_HTM[8148]="*So puratthimena nagarassa navaṃ santhāgāraṃ kārāpetvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kharājinaṃ nivāsetvā sappitelena kāyaṃ abbhañjitvā magavisāṇena piṭṭhiṃ kaṇḍuvamāno navaṃ santhāgāraṃ pavisati saddhiṃ mahesiyā brāhmaṇena ca purohitena.**He has a new temple built to the east of the city. He shaves off his hair and beard, dresses in a rough antelope hide, and smears his body with ghee and oil. Scratching his back with antlers, he enters the temple with his chief queen and the brahmin high priest.*";
P_HTM[8149]="*So tattha anantarahitāya bhūmiyā haritupalittāya seyyaṃ kappeti.**There he lies on the bare ground strewn with grass.*";
P_HTM[8150]="*Ekissāya gāviyā sarūpavacchāya yaṃ ekasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena rājā yāpeti, yaṃ dutiyasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena mahesī yāpeti, yaṃ tatiyasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena brāhmaṇo purohito yāpeti, yaṃ catutthasmiṃ thane khīraṃ hoti tena aggiṃ juhati, avasesena vacchako yāpeti.**The king feeds on the milk from one teat of a cow that has a calf of the same color. The chief queen feeds on the milk from the second teat. The brahmin high priest feeds on the milk from the third teat. The milk from the fourth teat is offered to the flames. The calf feeds on the remainder.*";
P_HTM[8151]="*So evamāha:**He says:*";
P_HTM[8152]="*‘ettakā usabhā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā vacchatarā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā vacchatariyo haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā ajā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā urabbhā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā assā haññantu yaññatthāya, ettakā rukkhā chijjantu yūpatthāya, ettakā dabbhā lūyantu barihisatthāyā’ti.**‘Slaughter this many bulls, bullocks, heifers, goats, rams, and horses for the sacrifice! Fell this many trees and reap this much grass for the sacrificial equipment!’*";
P_HTM[8153]="*Yepissa te honti ‘dāsā’ti vā ‘pessā’ti vā ‘kammakarā’ti vā tepi daṇḍatajjitā bhayatajjitā assumukhā rudamānā parikammāni karonti.**His bondservants, employees, and workers do their jobs under threat of punishment and danger, weeping with tearful faces.*";
P_HTM[8154]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who mortifies themselves and others, being committed to the practice of mortifying themselves and others.*";
P_HTM[8155]="*Katamo ca, brāhmaṇa, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;**And what person doesn’t mortify either themselves or others, committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others,*";
P_HTM[8156]="*so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati?**living without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves?*";
P_HTM[8157]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā.**It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.*";
P_HTM[8158]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[8159]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[8160]="*Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule paccājāto.**A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some clan.*";
P_HTM[8161]="*So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati.**They gain faith in the Realized One,*";
P_HTM[8162]="*So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati:**and reflect:*";
P_HTM[8163]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajopatho abbhokāso pabbajjā.**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[8164]="*Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[8165]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[8166]="*So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya, appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[8167]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāsājīvasamāpanno pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.**Once they’ve gone forth, they take up the training and livelihood of the mendicants. They give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[8168]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī. Athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharati.**They give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. They keep themselves clean by not thieving.*";
P_HTM[8169]="*Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī hoti ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.**They give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.*";
P_HTM[8170]="*Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa.**They give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words.*";
P_HTM[8171]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti; ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā, samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[8172]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti. Yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[8173]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ.**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[8174]="*So bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti.**They avoid injuring plants and seeds.*";
P_HTM[8175]="*Ekabhattiko hoti rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā.**They eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[8176]="*Naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti.**They avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows.*";
P_HTM[8177]="*Mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**They avoid beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, perfumes, and makeup.*";
P_HTM[8178]="*Uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato hoti.**They avoid high and luxurious beds.*";
P_HTM[8179]="*Jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**They avoid receiving gold and money,*";
P_HTM[8180]="*Āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**raw grains,*";
P_HTM[8181]="*Āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**raw meat,*";
P_HTM[8182]="*Itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**women and girls,*";
P_HTM[8183]="*Dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**male and female bondservants,*";
P_HTM[8184]="*Ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**goats and sheep,*";
P_HTM[8185]="*Kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**chickens and pigs,*";
P_HTM[8186]="*Hatthigavassavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**elephants, cows, horses, and mares,*";
P_HTM[8187]="*Khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti.**and fields and land.*";
P_HTM[8188]="*Dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti.**They avoid running errands and messages;*";
P_HTM[8189]="*Kayavikkayā paṭivirato hoti.**buying and selling;*";
P_HTM[8190]="*Tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato hoti.**falsifying weights, metals, or measures;*";
P_HTM[8191]="*Ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato hoti.**bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity;*";
P_HTM[8192]="*Chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato hoti.**mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence.*";
P_HTM[8193]="*So santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena, kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati.**They’re content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[8194]="*Seyyathāpi nāma pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti sapattabhārova ḍeti;**They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden.*";
P_HTM[8195]="*evameva bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena, kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. So yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati.**In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[8196]="*So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a blameless happiness inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[8197]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they see a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[8198]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[8199]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[8200]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[8201]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[8202]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[8203]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[8204]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[8205]="*So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied bliss inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[8206]="*So abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti.**They act with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent.*";
P_HTM[8207]="*So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, imāya ca ariyāya santuṭṭhiyā samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato**When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble sense restraint, and this noble mindfulness and situational awareness,*";
P_HTM[8208]="*vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[8209]="*So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā, ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya, parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down cross-legged with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[8210]="*So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, cleansing the mind of desire.*";
P_HTM[8211]="*byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill will.*";
P_HTM[8212]="*thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[8213]="*uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti;**Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse.*";
P_HTM[8214]="*vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṃkathī kusalesu dhammesu, vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt.*";
P_HTM[8215]="*So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8216]="*vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[8217]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[8218]="*Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[8219]="*Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[8220]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[8221]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi, anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto; so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto; so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. They remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. Passing away from there, I was reborn here.’ And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[8222]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[8223]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti: ‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā … pe … ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā. Ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā … pe … ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti. Iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds: ‘These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[8224]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[8225]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti;**They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[8226]="*‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[8227]="*Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati.**Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[8228]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[8229]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[8230]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto, na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto.**This is called a person who neither mortifies themselves or others, being committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others.*";
P_HTM[8231]="*So anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharatī”ti.**They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.”*";
P_HTM[8232]="*Evaṃ vutte, ghoṭamukho brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ udenaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Ghoṭamukha said to him,*";
P_HTM[8233]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho udena, abhikkantaṃ, bho udena.**“Excellent, Master Udena! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[8234]="*Seyyathāpi, bho udena, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā udenena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Udena has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[8235]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ udenaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Udena, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[8236]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ udeno dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Udena remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[8237]="*“Mā kho maṃ tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, saraṇaṃ agamāsi.**“Brahmin, don’t go for refuge to me.*";
P_HTM[8238]="*Tameva bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāhi yamahaṃ saraṇaṃ gato”ti.**You should go for refuge to that same Blessed One to whom I have gone for refuge.”*";
P_HTM[8239]="*“Kahaṃ pana, bho udena, etarahi so bhavaṃ gotamo viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti?**“But Master Udena, where is the Blessed One at present, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[8240]="*“Parinibbuto kho, brāhmaṇa, etarahi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti.**“Brahmin, the Buddha has already become fully extinguished.”*";
P_HTM[8241]="*“Sacepi mayaṃ, bho udena, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dasasu yojanesu, dasapi mayaṃ yojanāni gaccheyyāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ.**“Master Udena, if I heard that the Buddha was within ten leagues, or twenty, or even up to a hundred leagues away, I’d go a hundred leagues to see him.*";
P_HTM[8242]="*Sacepi mayaṃ, bho udena, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ vīsatiyā yojanesu …* **";
P_HTM[8243]="*tiṃsāya yojanesu …* **";
P_HTM[8244]="*cattārīsāya yojanesu …* **";
P_HTM[8245]="*paññāsāya yojanesu, paññāsampi mayaṃ yojanāni gaccheyyāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8246]="*Yojanasate cepi mayaṃ, bho udena, suṇeyyāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ, yojanasatampi mayaṃ gaccheyyāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8247]="*Yato ca kho, bho udena, parinibbuto so bhavaṃ gotamo, parinibbutampi mayaṃ taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**But since the Buddha has become fully extinguished, I go for refuge to that fully extinguished Buddha, to the teaching, and to the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[8248]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ udeno dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ.**From this day forth, may Master Udena remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.*";
P_HTM[8249]="*Atthi ca me, bho udena, aṅgarājā devasikaṃ niccabhikkhaṃ dadāti, tato ahaṃ bhoto udenassa ekaṃ niccabhikkhaṃ dadāmī”ti.**Master Udena, the king of Aṅga gives me a regular daily allowance. I will give you one portion of that.”*";
P_HTM[8250]="*“Kiṃ pana te, brāhmaṇa, aṅgarājā devasikaṃ niccabhikkhaṃ dadātī”ti?**“But brahmin, what does the king of Aṅga give you as a regular daily allowance?”*";
P_HTM[8251]="*“Pañca, bho udena, kahāpaṇasatānī”ti.**“Five hundred dollars.”*";
P_HTM[8252]="*“Na kho no, brāhmaṇa, kappati jātarūparajataṃ paṭiggahetun”ti.**“It’s not proper for us to receive gold and money.”*";
P_HTM[8253]="*“Sace taṃ bhoto udenassa na kappati vihāraṃ bhoto udenassa kārāpessāmī”ti.**“If that’s not proper, I will have a dwelling built for Master Udena.”*";
P_HTM[8254]="*“Sace kho me tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vihāraṃ, kārāpetukāmo, pāṭaliputte saṅghassa upaṭṭhānasālaṃ kārāpehī”ti.**“If you want to build me a dwelling, then build an assembly hall for the Saṅgha at Pāṭaliputta.”*";
P_HTM[8255]="*“Imināpāhaṃ bhoto udenassa bhiyyoso mattāya attamano abhiraddho yaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ udeno saṅghe dāne samādapeti.**“Now I’m even more delighted and satisfied with Master Udena, since he encourages me to give to the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[8256]="*Esāhaṃ, bho udena, etissā ca niccabhikkhāya aparāya ca niccabhikkhāya pāṭaliputte saṅghassa upaṭṭhānasālaṃ kārāpessāmī”ti.**So with this allowance and another one I will have an assembly hall built for the Saṅgha at Pāṭaliputta.”*";
P_HTM[8257]="*Atha kho ghoṭamukho brāhmaṇo etissā ca niccabhikkhāya aparāya ca niccabhikkhāya pāṭaliputte saṅghassa upaṭṭhānasālaṃ kārāpesi.**And so he had that hall built.*";
P_HTM[8258]="*Sā etarahi “ghoṭamukhī”ti vuccatīti.**And these days it’s called the “Ghoṭamukhī”.*";
P_HTM[8259]="*Ghoṭamukhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8260]="*95. Caṅkīsutta**With Caṅkī*";
P_HTM[8261]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8262]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena opāsādaṃ nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇagāmo tadavasari.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Kosalan brahmins named Opāsāda.*";
P_HTM[8263]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā opāsāde viharati uttarena opāsādaṃ devavane sālavane.**He stayed in a sal grove to the north of Opāsāda called the “Gods’ Grove”.*";
P_HTM[8264]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṅkī brāhmaṇo opāsādaṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ raññā pasenadinā kosalena dinnaṃ rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ.**Now at that time the brahmin Caṅkī was living in Opāsāda. It was a crown property given by King Pasenadi of Kosala, teeming with living creatures, full of hay, wood, water, and grain, a royal endowment of the highest quality.*";
P_HTM[8265]="*Assosuṃ kho opāsādakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:**The brahmins and householders of Opāsāda heard:*";
P_HTM[8266]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ opāsādaṃ anuppatto, opāsāde viharati uttarena opāsādaṃ devavane sālavane.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has arrived at Opāsāda together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants. He is staying in the God’s Grove to the north.*";
P_HTM[8267]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[8268]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[8269]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[8270]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[8271]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[8272]="*Atha kho opāsādakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā opāsādā nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūtā uttarenamukhā gacchanti yena devavanaṃ sālavanaṃ.**Then, having departed Opāsāda, they formed into companies and headed north to the God’s Grove.*";
P_HTM[8273]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṅkī brāhmaṇo uparipāsāde divāseyyaṃ upagato.**Now at that time the brahmin Caṅkī had retired to the upper floor of his stilt longhouse for his midday nap.*";
P_HTM[8274]="*Addasā kho caṅkī brāhmaṇo opāsādake brāhmaṇagahapatike opāsādā nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūte uttarenamukhaṃ yena devavanaṃ sālavanaṃ tenupasaṅkamante.**He saw the brahmins and householders heading for the God’s Grove,*";
P_HTM[8275]="*Disvā khattaṃ āmantesi:**and addressed his steward,*";
P_HTM[8276]="*“kiṃ nu kho, bho khatte, opāsādakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā opāsādā nikkhamitvā saṅghasaṅghī gaṇībhūtā uttarenamukhā gacchanti yena devavanaṃ sālavanan”ti?**“My steward, why are the brahmins and householders heading north for the God’s Grove?”*";
P_HTM[8277]="*“Atthi, bho caṅkī, samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ opāsādaṃ anuppatto, opāsāde viharati uttarena opāsādaṃ devavane sālavane.**“The ascetic Gotama has arrived at Opāsāda together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants. He is staying in the God’s Grove to the north.*";
P_HTM[8278]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[8279]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[8280]="*Tamete bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya gacchantī”ti.**They’re going to see that Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8281]="*“Tena hi, bho khatte, yena opāsādakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā opāsādake brāhmaṇagahapatike evaṃ vadehi:**“Well then, go to the brahmins and householders and say to them:*";
P_HTM[8282]="*‘caṅkī, bho, brāhmaṇo evamāha—**“Sirs, the brahmin Caṅkī asks*";
P_HTM[8283]="*āgamentu kira bhonto, caṅkīpi brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī’”ti.**you to wait, as he will also go to see the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8284]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho so khatto caṅkissa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā yena opāsādakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā opāsādake brāhmaṇagahapatike etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” replied the steward, and did as he was asked.*";
P_HTM[8285]="*“caṅkī, bho, brāhmaṇo evamāha:* **";
P_HTM[8286]="*‘āgamentu kira bhonto, caṅkīpi brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8287]="*Tena kho pana samayena nānāverajjakānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ pañcamattāni brāhmaṇasatāni opāsāde paṭivasanti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time around five hundred brahmins from abroad were residing in Opāsāda on some business.*";
P_HTM[8288]="*Assosuṃ kho te brāhmaṇā:**They heard that*";
P_HTM[8289]="*“caṅkī kira brāhmaṇo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti.**the brahmin Caṅkī was going to see the ascetic Gotama.*";
P_HTM[8290]="*Atha kho te brāhmaṇā yena caṅkī brāhmaṇo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā caṅkiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocuṃ:**They approached Caṅkī and said to him,*";
P_HTM[8291]="*“saccaṃ kira bhavaṃ caṅkī samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti?**“Is it really true that you are going to see the ascetic Gotama?”*";
P_HTM[8292]="*“Evaṃ kho me, bho, hoti:**“Yes, gentlemen, it is true.”*";
P_HTM[8293]="*‘ahaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāmī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8294]="*“Mā bhavaṃ caṅkī samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkami.**“Please don’t!*";
P_HTM[8295]="*Na arahati bhavaṃ caṅkī samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;**It’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama;*";
P_HTM[8296]="*samaṇotveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ caṅkiṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ.**it’s appropriate that he comes to see you.*";
P_HTM[8297]="*Bhavañhi caṅkī ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.**You are well born on both your mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation.*";
P_HTM[8298]="*Yampi bhavaṃ caṅkī ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena, imināpaṅgena na arahati bhavaṃ caṅkī samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;**For this reason it’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama;*";
P_HTM[8299]="*samaṇotveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ caṅkiṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ.**it’s appropriate that he comes to see you.*";
P_HTM[8300]="*Bhavañhi caṅkī aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo … pe …**You’re rich, affluent, and wealthy. …*";
P_HTM[8301]="*bhavañhi caṅkī tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo … pe …**You recite and remember the hymns, and have mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. You know philology and grammar, and are well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man. …*";
P_HTM[8302]="*bhavañhi caṅkī abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato brahmavaṇṇī brahmavacchasī akhuddāvakāso dassanāya … pe …**You are attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. You are magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold. …*";
P_HTM[8303]="*bhavañhi caṅkī sīlavā vuddhasīlī vuddhasīlena samannāgato … pe …**You are ethical, mature in ethical conduct. …*";
P_HTM[8304]="*bhavañhi caṅkī kalyāṇavāco kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā … pe …**You’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that expresses the meaning. …*";
P_HTM[8305]="*bhavañhi caṅkī bahūnaṃ ācariyapācariyo, tīṇi māṇavakasatāni mante vāceti … pe …**You teach the teachers of many, and teach three hundred students to recite the hymns. …*";
P_HTM[8306]="*bhavañhi caṅkī rañño pasenadissa kosalassa sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe …**You’re honored, respected, revered, venerated, and esteemed by King Pasenadi of Kosala*";
P_HTM[8307]="*bhavañhi caṅkī brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa sakkato garukato mānito pūjito apacito … pe …**and the brahmin Pokkharasāti. …*";
P_HTM[8308]="*bhavañhi caṅkī opāsādaṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ raññā pasenadinā kosalena dinnaṃ rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ.**You live in Opāsāda, a crown property given by King Pasenadi of Kosala, teeming with living creatures, full of hay, wood, water, and grain, a royal endowment of the highest quality.*";
P_HTM[8309]="*Yampi bhavaṃ caṅkī opāsādaṃ ajjhāvasati sattussadaṃ satiṇakaṭṭhodakaṃ sadhaññaṃ rājabhoggaṃ raññā pasenadinā kosalena dinnaṃ rājadāyaṃ brahmadeyyaṃ, imināpaṅgena na arahati bhavaṃ caṅkī samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;**For all these reasons it’s not appropriate for you to go to see the ascetic Gotama;*";
P_HTM[8310]="*samaṇotveva gotamo arahati bhavantaṃ caṅkiṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitun”ti.**it’s appropriate that he comes to see you.”*";
P_HTM[8311]="*Evaṃ vutte, caṅkī brāhmaṇo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca:**When they had spoken, Caṅkī said to those brahmins:*";
P_HTM[8312]="*“tena hi, bho, mamapi suṇātha, yathā mayameva arahāma taṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;**“Well then, gentlemen, listen to why it’s appropriate for me to go to see the ascetic Gotama,*";
P_HTM[8313]="*na tveva arahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ.**and it’s not appropriate for him to come to see me.*";
P_HTM[8314]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.**He is well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation.*";
P_HTM[8315]="*Yampi, bho, samaṇo gotamo ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena, imināpaṅgena na arahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;**For this reason it’s not appropriate for the ascetic Gotama to come to see me;*";
P_HTM[8316]="*atha kho mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ.**rather, it’s appropriate for me to go to see him.*";
P_HTM[8317]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo pahūtaṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇaṃ ohāya pabbajito bhūmigatañca vehāsaṭṭhañca … pe …**When he went forth he abandoned abundant gold coin and bullion stored in dungeons and towers. …*";
P_HTM[8318]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo daharova samāno yuvā susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito … pe …**He went forth from the lay life to homelessness while still a youth, young, black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life. …*";
P_HTM[8319]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito … pe …**Though his mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful faces, he shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness. …*";
P_HTM[8320]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato brahmavaṇṇī brahmavacchasī akhuddāvakāso dassanāya … pe …**He is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. He is magnificent, splendid, remarkable to behold. …*";
P_HTM[8321]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sīlavā ariyasīlī kusalasīlī kusalena sīlena samannāgato … pe …**He is ethical, possessing ethical conduct that is noble and skillful. …*";
P_HTM[8322]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo kalyāṇavāco kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā … pe …**He’s a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that expresses the meaning. …*";
P_HTM[8323]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo bahūnaṃ ācariyapācariyo … pe …**He’s a teacher of teachers. …*";
P_HTM[8324]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo khīṇakāmarāgo vigatacāpallo … pe …**He has ended sensual desire, and is rid of caprice. …*";
P_HTM[8325]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo kammavādī kiriyavādī apāpapurekkhāro brahmaññāya pajāya … pe …**He teaches the efficacy of deeds and action. He doesn’t wish any harm upon the community of brahmins. …*";
P_HTM[8326]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo uccā kulā pabbajito asambhinnā khattiyakulā … pe …**He went forth from an eminent family of unbroken aristocratic lineage. …*";
P_HTM[8327]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo aḍḍhā kulā pabbajito mahaddhanā mahābhogā … pe …**He went forth from a rich, affluent, and wealthy family. …*";
P_HTM[8328]="*Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ tiroraṭṭhā tirojanapadā saṃpucchituṃ āgacchanti … pe …**People come from distant lands and distant countries to question him. …*";
P_HTM[8329]="*Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ anekāni devatāsahassāni pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gatāni … pe …**Many thousands of deities have gone for refuge for life to him. …*";
P_HTM[8330]="*Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[8331]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti … pe …**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ …*";
P_HTM[8332]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi samannāgato … pe …**He has the thirty-two marks of a great man. …*";
P_HTM[8333]="*Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro saputtadāro pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe …**King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha and his wives and children have gone for refuge for life to the ascetic Gotama. …*";
P_HTM[8334]="*Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ rājā pasenadi kosalo saputtadāro pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe …**King Pasenadi of Kosala and his wives and children have gone for refuge for life to the ascetic Gotama. …*";
P_HTM[8335]="*Samaṇaṃ khalu, bho, gotamaṃ brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti saputtadāro pāṇehi saraṇaṃ gato … pe …**The brahmin Pokkharasāti and his wives and children have gone for refuge for life to the ascetic Gotama. …*";
P_HTM[8336]="*Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo opāsādaṃ anuppatto opāsāde viharati uttarena opāsādaṃ devavane sālavane.**The ascetic Gotama has arrived to stay in the God’s Grove to the north of Opāsāda.*";
P_HTM[8337]="*Ye kho te samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā amhākaṃ gāmakkhettaṃ āgacchanti, atithī no te honti.**Any ascetic or brahmin who comes to stay in our village district is our guest,*";
P_HTM[8338]="*Atithī kho panamhehi sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā.**and should be honored and respected as such.*";
P_HTM[8339]="*Yampi samaṇo gotamo opāsādaṃ anuppatto opāsāde viharati uttarena opāsādaṃ devavane sālavane, atithimhākaṃ samaṇo gotamo.* **";
P_HTM[8340]="*Atithi kho panamhehi sakkātabbo garukātabbo mānetabbo pūjetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[8341]="*Imināpaṅgena na arahati so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;**For this reason, too, it’s not appropriate for Master Gotama to come to see me,*";
P_HTM[8342]="*atha kho mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ.**rather, it’s appropriate for me to go to see him.*";
P_HTM[8343]="*Ettake kho ahaṃ, bho, tassa bhoto gotamassa vaṇṇe pariyāpuṇāmi, no ca kho so bhavaṃ gotamo ettakavaṇṇo;**This is the extent of Master Gotama’s praise that I have learned. But his praises are not confined to this,*";
P_HTM[8344]="*aparimāṇavaṇṇo hi so bhavaṃ gotamo.**for the praise of Master Gotama is limitless.*";
P_HTM[8345]="*Ekamekenapi tena aṅgena samannāgato na arahati, so bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ;**The possession of even a single one of these factors makes it inappropriate for Master Gotama to come to see me,*";
P_HTM[8346]="*atha kho mayameva arahāma taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitunti.**rather, it’s appropriate for me to go to see him.*";
P_HTM[8347]="*Tena hi, bho, sabbeva mayaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāmā”ti.**Well then, gentlemen, let’s all go to see the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8348]="*Atha kho caṅkī brāhmaṇo mahatā brāhmaṇagaṇena saddhiṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Caṅkī together with a large group of brahmins went to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[8349]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[8350]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā vuddhehi vuddhehi brāhmaṇehi saddhiṃ kiñci kiñci kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā nisinno hoti.**Now at that time the Buddha was sitting engaged in some polite conversation together with some very senior brahmins.*";
P_HTM[8351]="*Tena kho pana samayena kāpaṭiko nāma māṇavo daharo vuttasiro soḷasavassuddesiko jātiyā, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo tassaṃ parisāyaṃ nisinno hoti.**And the brahmin student Kāpaṭika was sitting in that assembly. He was young, newly tonsured; he was sixteen years old. He had mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. He knew philology and grammar, and was well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[8352]="*So vuddhānaṃ vuddhānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ bhagavatā saddhiṃ mantayamānānaṃ antarantarā kathaṃ opāteti.**While the senior brahmins were conversing together with the Buddha, he interrupted.*";
P_HTM[8353]="*Atha kho bhagavā kāpaṭikaṃ māṇavaṃ apasādeti:**Then the Buddha rebuked Kāpaṭika,*";
P_HTM[8354]="*“māyasmā bhāradvājo vuddhānaṃ vuddhānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mantayamānānaṃ antarantarā kathaṃ opātetu.**“Venerable Bhāradvāja, don’t interrupt the senior brahmins.*";
P_HTM[8355]="*Kathāpariyosānaṃ āyasmā bhāradvājo āgametū”ti.**Wait until they’ve finished speaking.”*";
P_HTM[8356]="*Evaṃ vutte, caṅkī brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Caṅkī said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8357]="*“mā bhavaṃ gotamo kāpaṭikaṃ māṇavaṃ apasādesi.**“Master Gotama, don’t rebuke the student Kāpaṭika.*";
P_HTM[8358]="*kulaputto ca kāpaṭiko māṇavo, bahussuto ca kāpaṭiko māṇavo, paṇḍito ca kāpaṭiko māṇavo, kalyāṇavākkaraṇo ca kāpaṭiko māṇavo, pahoti ca kāpaṭiko māṇavo bhotā gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti.**He’s a gentleman, learned, astute, a good speaker. He’s capable of having a dialogue with Master Gotama about this.”*";
P_HTM[8359]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then it occurred to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8360]="*“addhā kho kāpaṭikassa māṇavassa tevijjake pāvacane kathā bhavissati.**“Clearly the student Kāpaṭika will talk about the scriptural heritage of the three Vedas.*";
P_HTM[8361]="*Tathā hi naṃ brāhmaṇā sampurekkharontī”ti.**That’s why they put him at the front.”*";
P_HTM[8362]="*Atha kho kāpaṭikassa māṇavassa etadahosi:**Then Kāpaṭika thought,*";
P_HTM[8363]="*“yadā me samaṇo gotamo cakkhuṃ upasaṃharissati, athāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pañhaṃ pucchissāmī”ti.**“When the ascetic Gotama looks at me, I’ll ask him a question.”*";
P_HTM[8364]="*Atha kho bhagavā kāpaṭikassa māṇavassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya yena kāpaṭiko māṇavo tena cakkhūni upasaṃhāsi.**Then the Buddha, knowing what Kāpaṭika was thinking, looked at him.*";
P_HTM[8365]="*Atha kho kāpaṭikassa māṇavassa etadahosi:**Then Kāpaṭika thought,*";
P_HTM[8366]="*“samannāharati kho maṃ samaṇo gotamo.**“The ascetic Gotama is engaging with me.*";
P_HTM[8367]="*Yannūnāhaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pañhaṃ puccheyyan”ti.**Why don’t I ask him a question?”*";
P_HTM[8368]="*Atha kho kāpaṭiko māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then he said,*";
P_HTM[8369]="*“yadidaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇānaṃ porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ itihitihaparamparāya piṭakasampadāya, tattha ca brāhmaṇā ekaṃsena niṭṭhaṃ gacchanti:**“Master Gotama, regarding that which by the lineage of testament and by canonical authority is the traditional hymnal of the brahmins, the brahmins come to the definite conclusion:*";
P_HTM[8370]="*‘idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’ti.**‘This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’*";
P_HTM[8371]="*Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti?**What do you say about this?”*";
P_HTM[8372]="*“Kiṃ pana, bhāradvāja, atthi koci brāhmaṇānaṃ ekabrāhmaṇopi yo evamāha:**“Well, Bhāradvāja, is there even a single one of the brahmins who says this:*";
P_HTM[8373]="*‘ahametaṃ jānāmi, ahametaṃ passāmi.**‘I know this, I see this:*";
P_HTM[8374]="*Idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’”ti?**this is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[8375]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8376]="*“Kiṃ pana, bhāradvāja, atthi koci brāhmaṇānaṃ ekācariyopi, ekācariyapācariyopi, yāva sattamā ācariyamahayugāpi, yo evamāha:**“Well, is there even a single teacher of the brahmins, or a teacher’s teacher, or anyone back to the seventh generation of teachers, who says this:*";
P_HTM[8377]="*‘ahametaṃ jānāmi, ahametaṃ passāmi.**‘I know this, I see this:*";
P_HTM[8378]="*Idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’”ti?**this is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[8379]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8380]="*“Kiṃ pana, bhāradvāja, yepi te brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samihitaṃ tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti vācitamanuvācenti seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako vāmako vāmadevo vessāmitto yamataggi aṅgīraso bhāradvājo vāseṭṭho kassapo bhagu,**“Well, what of the ancient hermits of the brahmins, namely Aṭṭhaka, Vāmaka, Vāmadeva, Vessāmitta, Yamadaggi, Aṅgīrasa, Bhāradvāja, Vāseṭṭha, Kassapa, and Bhagu? They were the authors and propagators of the hymns. Their hymnal was sung and propagated and compiled in ancient times; and these days, brahmins continue to sing and chant it, chanting what was chanted and teaching what was taught.*";
P_HTM[8381]="*tepi evamāhaṃsu:**Did even they say:*";
P_HTM[8382]="*‘mayametaṃ jānāma, mayametaṃ passāma.**‘We know this, we see this:*";
P_HTM[8383]="*Idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’”ti?**this is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[8384]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8385]="*“Iti kira, bhāradvāja, natthi koci brāhmaṇānaṃ ekabrāhmaṇopi yo evamāha:**“So, Bhāradvāja, it seems that there is not a single one of the brahmins,*";
P_HTM[8386]="*‘ahametaṃ jānāmi, ahametaṃ passāmi.* **";
P_HTM[8387]="*Idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[8388]="*natthi koci brāhmaṇānaṃ ekācariyopi ekācariyapācariyopi, yāva sattamā ācariyamahayugāpi, yo evamāha:**not even anyone back to the seventh generation of teachers,*";
P_HTM[8389]="*‘ahametaṃ jānāmi, ahametaṃ passāmi.* **";
P_HTM[8390]="*Idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’ti;* **";
P_HTM[8391]="*yepi te brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samihitaṃ tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti vācitamanuvācenti seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako vāmako vāmadevo vessāmitto yamataggi aṅgīraso bhāradvājo vāseṭṭho kassapo bhagu, tepi na evamāhaṃsu:**nor even the ancient hermits of the brahmins who say:*";
P_HTM[8392]="*‘mayametaṃ jānāma, mayametaṃ passāma.**‘We know this, we see this:*";
P_HTM[8393]="*Idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’ti.**this is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’*";
P_HTM[8394]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, andhaveṇi paramparāsaṃsattā purimopi na passati majjhimopi na passati pacchimopi na passati;**Suppose there was a queue of blind men, each holding the one in front: the first one does not see, the middle one does not see, and the last one does not see.*";
P_HTM[8395]="*evameva kho, bhāradvāja, andhaveṇūpamaṃ maññe brāhmaṇānaṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjati—purimopi na passati majjhimopi na passati pacchimopi na passati.**In the same way, it seems to me that the brahmins’ statement turns out to be like a queue of blind men: the first one does not see, the middle one does not see, and the last one does not see.*";
P_HTM[8396]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhāradvāja,**What do you think, Bhāradvāja?*";
P_HTM[8397]="*nanu evaṃ sante brāhmaṇānaṃ amūlikā saddhā sampajjatī”ti?**This being so, doesn’t the brahmins’ faith turn out to be baseless?”*";
P_HTM[8398]="*“Na khvettha, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā saddhāyeva payirupāsanti, anussavāpettha brāhmaṇā payirupāsantī”ti.**“The brahmins don’t just honor this because of faith, but also because of oral transmission.”*";
P_HTM[8399]="*“Pubbeva kho tvaṃ, bhāradvāja, saddhaṃ agamāsi, anussavaṃ idāni vadesi.**“First you relied on faith, now you speak of oral tradition.*";
P_HTM[8400]="*Pañca kho ime, bhāradvāja, dhammā diṭṭheva dhamme dvedhā vipākā.**These five things can be seen to turn out in two different ways.*";
P_HTM[8401]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[8402]="*Saddhā, ruci, anussavo, ākāraparivitakko, diṭṭhinijjhānakkhanti—**Faith, preference, oral tradition, reasoned contemplation, and acceptance of a view after consideration.*";
P_HTM[8403]="*ime kho, bhāradvāja, pañca dhammā diṭṭheva dhamme dvedhā vipākā.* **";
P_HTM[8404]="*Api ca, bhāradvāja, susaddahitaṃyeva hoti, tañca hoti rittaṃ tucchaṃ musā;**Even though you have full faith in something, it may be void, hollow, and false.*";
P_HTM[8405]="*no cepi susaddahitaṃ hoti, tañca hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anaññathā.**And even if you don’t have full faith in something, it may be true and real, not otherwise.*";
P_HTM[8406]="*Api ca, bhāradvāja, surucitaṃyeva hoti … pe …**Even though you have a strong preference for something …*";
P_HTM[8407]="*svānussutaṃyeva hoti … pe …**something may be accurately transmitted …*";
P_HTM[8408]="*suparivitakkitaṃyeva hoti … pe …**something may be well contemplated …*";
P_HTM[8409]="*sunijjhāyitaṃyeva hoti, tañca hoti rittaṃ tucchaṃ musā;**something may be well considered, it may be void, hollow, and false.*";
P_HTM[8410]="*no cepi sunijjhāyitaṃ hoti, tañca hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anaññathā.**And even if something is not well considered, it may be true and real, not otherwise.*";
P_HTM[8411]="*Saccamanurakkhatā, bhāradvāja, viññunā purisena nālamettha ekaṃsena niṭṭhaṃ gantuṃ:**For a sensible person who is preserving truth this is not sufficient to come to the definite conclusion:*";
P_HTM[8412]="*‘idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’”ti.**‘This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’”*";
P_HTM[8413]="*“Kittāvatā pana, bho gotama, saccānurakkhaṇā hoti, kittāvatā saccamanurakkhati?**“But Master Gotama, how do you define the preservation of truth?”*";
P_HTM[8414]="*Saccānurakkhaṇaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8415]="*“Saddhā cepi, bhāradvāja, purisassa hoti;**“If a person has faith,*";
P_HTM[8416]="*‘evaṃ me saddhā’ti—**they preserve truth by saying, ‘Such is my faith.’*";
P_HTM[8417]="*iti vadaṃ saccamanurakkhati, na tveva tāva ekaṃsena niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:**But they don’t yet come to the definite conclusion:*";
P_HTM[8418]="*‘idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’ti ().**‘This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’*";
P_HTM[8419]="*Ruci cepi, bhāradvāja, purisassa hoti … pe …**If a person has a preference …*";
P_HTM[8420]="*anussavo cepi, bhāradvāja, purisassa hoti … pe …**or has received an oral transmission …*";
P_HTM[8421]="*ākāraparivitakko cepi, bhāradvāja, purisassa hoti … pe …**or has a reasoned reflection about something …*";
P_HTM[8422]="*diṭṭhinijjhānakkhanti cepi, bhāradvāja, purisassa hoti;**or has accepted a view after contemplation,*";
P_HTM[8423]="*‘evaṃ me diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantī’ti—**they preserve truth by saying, ‘Such is the view I have accepted after contemplation.’*";
P_HTM[8424]="*iti vadaṃ saccamanurakkhati, na tveva tāva ekaṃsena niṭṭhaṃ gacchati:**But they don’t yet come to the definite conclusion:*";
P_HTM[8425]="*‘idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’ti.**‘This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.’*";
P_HTM[8426]="*Ettāvatā kho, bhāradvāja, saccānurakkhaṇā hoti, ettāvatā saccamanurakkhati, ettāvatā ca mayaṃ saccānurakkhaṇaṃ paññapema;**That’s how the preservation of truth is defined, Bhāradvāja. I describe the preservation of truth as defined in this way.*";
P_HTM[8427]="*na tveva tāva saccānubodho hotī”ti.**But this is not yet the awakening to the truth.”*";
P_HTM[8428]="*“Ettāvatā, bho gotama, saccānurakkhaṇā hoti, ettāvatā saccamanurakkhati, ettāvatā ca mayaṃ saccānurakkhaṇaṃ pekkhāma.**“That’s how the preservation of truth is defined, Master Gotama. We regard the preservation of truth as defined in this way.*";
P_HTM[8429]="*Kittāvatā pana, bho gotama, saccānubodho hoti, kittāvatā saccamanubujjhati?**But Master Gotama, how do you define awakening to the truth?”*";
P_HTM[8430]="*Saccānubodhaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8431]="*“Idha, bhāradvāja, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati.**“Bhāradvāja, take the case of a mendicant living supported by a town or village.*";
P_HTM[8432]="*Tamenaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā upasaṅkamitvā tīsu dhammesu samannesati—**A householder or their child approaches and scrutinizes them for three kinds of things:*";
P_HTM[8433]="*lobhanīyesu dhammesu, dosanīyesu dhammesu, mohanīyesu dhammesu.**things that arouse greed, things that provoke hate, and things that promote delusion.*";
P_HTM[8434]="*Atthi nu kho imassāyasmato tathārūpā lobhanīyā dhammā yathārūpehi lobhanīyehi dhammehi pariyādinnacitto ajānaṃ vā vadeyya—**‘Does this venerable have any qualities that arouse greed? Such qualities that, were their mind to be overwhelmed by them, they might say*";
P_HTM[8435]="*jānāmīti, apassaṃ vā vadeyya—**that they know, even though they don’t know, or that they see, even though they don’t see;*";
P_HTM[8436]="*passāmīti, paraṃ vā tadatthāya samādapeyya yaṃ paresaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyāti?**or that they might encourage others to do what is for their lasting harm and suffering?’*";
P_HTM[8437]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing them they find:*";
P_HTM[8438]="*‘natthi kho imassāyasmato tathārūpā lobhanīyā dhammā yathārūpehi lobhanīyehi dhammehi pariyādinnacitto ajānaṃ vā vadeyya—**‘This venerable has no such qualities that arouse greed.*";
P_HTM[8439]="*jānāmīti, apassaṃ vā vadeyya—* **";
P_HTM[8440]="*passāmīti, paraṃ vā tadatthāya samādapeyya yaṃ paresaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.* **";
P_HTM[8441]="*Tathārūpo kho panimassāyasmato kāyasamācāro tathārūpo vacīsamācāro yathā taṃ aluddhassa.**Rather, that venerable has bodily and verbal behavior like that of someone without greed.*";
P_HTM[8442]="*Yaṃ kho pana ayamāyasmā dhammaṃ deseti, gambhīro so dhammo duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo;**And the principle that they teach is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute.*";
P_HTM[8443]="*na so dhammo sudesiyo luddhenā’ti.**It’s not easy for someone with greed to teach this.’*";
P_HTM[8444]="*Yato naṃ samannesamāno visuddhaṃ lobhanīyehi dhammehi samanupassati tato naṃ uttari samannesati dosanīyesu dhammesu.**Scrutinizing them in this way they see that they are purified of qualities that arouse greed. Next, they search them for qualities that provoke hate.*";
P_HTM[8445]="*Atthi nu kho imassāyasmato tathārūpā dosanīyā dhammā yathārūpehi dosanīyehi dhammehi pariyādinnacitto ajānaṃ vā vadeyya—**‘Does this venerable have any qualities that provoke hate? Such qualities that, were their mind to be overwhelmed by them, they might say*";
P_HTM[8446]="*jānāmīti, apassaṃ vā vadeyya—**that they know, even though they don’t know, or that they see, even though they don’t see;*";
P_HTM[8447]="*passāmīti, paraṃ vā tadatthāya samādapeyya yaṃ paresaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyāti?**or that they might encourage others to do what is for their lasting harm and suffering?’*";
P_HTM[8448]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing them they find:*";
P_HTM[8449]="*‘natthi kho imassāyasmato tathārūpā dosanīyā dhammā yathārūpehi dosanīyehi dhammehi pariyādinnacitto ajānaṃ vā vadeyya—**‘This venerable has no such qualities that provoke hate.*";
P_HTM[8450]="*jānāmīti, apassaṃ vā vadeyya—* **";
P_HTM[8451]="*passāmīti, paraṃ vā tadatthāya samādapeyya yaṃ paresaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.* **";
P_HTM[8452]="*Tathārūpo kho panimassāyasmato kāyasamācāro tathārūpo vacīsamācāro yathā taṃ aduṭṭhassa.**Rather, that venerable has bodily and verbal behavior like that of someone without hate.*";
P_HTM[8453]="*Yaṃ kho pana ayamāyasmā dhammaṃ deseti, gambhīro so dhammo duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo;**And the principle that they teach is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute.*";
P_HTM[8454]="*na so dhammo sudesiyo duṭṭhenā’ti.**It’s not easy for someone with hate to teach this.’*";
P_HTM[8455]="*Yato naṃ samannesamāno visuddhaṃ dosanīyehi dhammehi samanupassati, tato naṃ uttari samannesati mohanīyesu dhammesu.**Scrutinizing them in this way they see that they are purified of qualities that provoke hate. Next, they scrutinize them for qualities that promote delusion.*";
P_HTM[8456]="*Atthi nu kho imassāyasmato tathārūpā mohanīyā dhammā yathārūpehi mohanīyehi dhammehi pariyādinnacitto ajānaṃ vā vadeyya—**‘Does this venerable have any qualities that promote delusion? Such qualities that, were their mind to be overwhelmed by them, they might say*";
P_HTM[8457]="*jānāmīti, apassaṃ vā vadeyya—**that they know, even though they don’t know, or that they see, even though they don’t see;*";
P_HTM[8458]="*passāmīti, paraṃ vā tadatthāya samādapeyya yaṃ paresaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyāti?**or that they might encourage others to do what is for their lasting harm and suffering?’*";
P_HTM[8459]="*Tamenaṃ samannesamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Scrutinizing them they find:*";
P_HTM[8460]="*‘natthi kho imassāyasmato tathārūpā mohanīyā dhammā yathārūpehi mohanīyehi dhammehi pariyādinnacitto ajānaṃ vā vadeyya—**‘This venerable has no such qualities that promote delusion.*";
P_HTM[8461]="*jānāmīti, apassaṃ vā vadeyya—* **";
P_HTM[8462]="*passāmīti, paraṃ vā tadatthāya samādapeyya yaṃ paresaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.* **";
P_HTM[8463]="*Tathārūpo kho panimassāyasmato kāyasamācāro tathārūpo vacīsamācāro yathā taṃ amūḷhassa.**Rather, that venerable has bodily and verbal behavior like that of someone without delusion.*";
P_HTM[8464]="*Yaṃ kho pana ayamāyasmā dhammaṃ deseti, gambhīro so dhammo duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo;**And the principle that they teach is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute.*";
P_HTM[8465]="*na so dhammo sudesiyo mūḷhenā’ti.**It’s not easy for someone with delusion to teach this.’*";
P_HTM[8466]="*Yato naṃ samannesamāno visuddhaṃ mohanīyehi dhammehi samanupassati;**Scrutinizing them in this way they see that they are purified of qualities that promote delusion.*";
P_HTM[8467]="*atha tamhi saddhaṃ niveseti, saddhājāto upasaṅkamati, upasaṅkamanto payirupāsati, payirupāsanto sotaṃ odahati, ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti, sutvā dhammaṃ dhāreti, dhatānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkhati, atthaṃ upaparikkhato dhammā nijjhānaṃ khamanti, dhammanijjhānakkhantiyā sati chando jāyati, chandajāto ussahati, ussahitvā tuleti, tulayitvā padahati, pahitatto samāno kāyena ceva paramasaccaṃ sacchikaroti paññāya ca naṃ ativijjha passati.**Next, they place faith in them. When faith has arisen they approach the teacher. They pay homage, lend an ear, hear the teachings, remember the teachings, reflect on their meaning, and accept them after consideration. Then enthusiasm springs up; they make an effort, weigh up, and persevere. Persevering, they directly realize the ultimate truth, and see it with penetrating wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8468]="*Ettāvatā kho, bhāradvāja, saccānubodho hoti, ettāvatā saccamanubujjhati, ettāvatā ca mayaṃ saccānubodhaṃ paññapema;**That’s how the awakening to truth is defined, Bhāradvāja. I describe the awakening to truth as defined in this way.*";
P_HTM[8469]="*na tveva tāva saccānuppatti hotī”ti.**But this is not yet the arrival at the truth.”*";
P_HTM[8470]="*“Ettāvatā, bho gotama, saccānubodho hoti, ettāvatā saccamanubujjhati, ettāvatā ca mayaṃ saccānubodhaṃ pekkhāma.**“That’s how the awakening to truth is defined, Master Gotama. I regard the awakening to truth as defined in this way.*";
P_HTM[8471]="*Kittāvatā pana, bho gotama, saccānuppatti hoti, kittāvatā saccamanupāpuṇāti?**But Master Gotama, how do you define the arrival at the truth?”*";
P_HTM[8472]="*Saccānuppattiṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8473]="*“Tesaṃyeva, bhāradvāja, dhammānaṃ āsevanā bhāvanā bahulīkammaṃ saccānuppatti hoti.**“By the cultivation, development, and making much of these very same things there is the arrival at the truth.*";
P_HTM[8474]="*Ettāvatā kho, bhāradvāja, saccānuppatti hoti, ettāvatā saccamanupāpuṇāti, ettāvatā ca mayaṃ saccānuppattiṃ paññapemā”ti.**That’s how the arrival at the truth is defined, Bhāradvāja. I describe the arrival at the truth as defined in this way.”*";
P_HTM[8475]="*“Ettāvatā, bho gotama, saccānuppatti hoti, ettāvatā saccamanupāpuṇāti, ettāvatā ca mayaṃ saccānuppattiṃ pekkhāma.**“That’s how the arrival at the truth is defined, Master Gotama. I regard the arrival at the truth as defined in this way.*";
P_HTM[8476]="*Saccānuppattiyā pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?**But what quality is helpful for arriving at the truth?”*";
P_HTM[8477]="*Saccānuppattiyā bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8478]="*“Saccānuppattiyā kho, bhāradvāja, padhānaṃ bahukāraṃ.**“Striving is helpful for arriving at the truth.*";
P_HTM[8479]="*No cetaṃ padaheyya, nayidaṃ saccamanupāpuṇeyya.**If you don’t strive, you won’t arrive at the truth.*";
P_HTM[8480]="*Yasmā ca kho padahati tasmā saccamanupāpuṇāti.**You arrive at the truth because you strive.*";
P_HTM[8481]="*Tasmā saccānuppattiyā padhānaṃ bahukāran”ti.**That’s why striving is helpful for arriving at the truth.”*";
P_HTM[8482]="*“Padhānassa pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?**“But what quality is helpful for striving?”*";
P_HTM[8483]="*Padhānassa bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8484]="*“Padhānassa kho, bhāradvāja, tulanā bahukārā.**“Weighing up the teachings is helpful for striving …*";
P_HTM[8485]="*No cetaṃ tuleyya, nayidaṃ padaheyya.* **";
P_HTM[8486]="*Yasmā ca kho tuleti tasmā padahati.* **";
P_HTM[8487]="*Tasmā padhānassa tulanā bahukārā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8488]="*“Tulanāya pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8489]="*Tulanāya bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8490]="*“Tulanāya kho, bhāradvāja, ussāho bahukāro.**Making an effort is helpful for weighing up the teachings …*";
P_HTM[8491]="*No cetaṃ ussaheyya, nayidaṃ tuleyya.* **";
P_HTM[8492]="*Yasmā ca kho ussahati tasmā tuleti.* **";
P_HTM[8493]="*Tasmā tulanāya ussāho bahukāro”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8494]="*“Ussāhassa pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8495]="*Ussāhassa bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8496]="*“Ussāhassa kho, bhāradvāja, chando bahukāro.**Enthusiasm is helpful for making an effort …*";
P_HTM[8497]="*No cetaṃ chando jāyetha, nayidaṃ ussaheyya.* **";
P_HTM[8498]="*Yasmā ca kho chando jāyati tasmā ussahati.* **";
P_HTM[8499]="*Tasmā ussāhassa chando bahukāro”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8500]="*“Chandassa pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8501]="*Chandassa bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8502]="*“Chandassa kho, bhāradvāja, dhammanijjhānakkhanti bahukārā.**Acceptance of the teachings after consideration is helpful for enthusiasm …*";
P_HTM[8503]="*No cete dhammā nijjhānaṃ khameyyuṃ, nayidaṃ chando jāyetha.* **";
P_HTM[8504]="*Yasmā ca kho dhammā nijjhānaṃ khamanti tasmā chando jāyati.* **";
P_HTM[8505]="*Tasmā chandassa dhammanijjhānakkhanti bahukārā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8506]="*“Dhammanijjhānakkhantiyā pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8507]="*Dhammanijjhānakkhantiyā bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8508]="*“Dhammanijjhānakkhantiyā kho, bhāradvāja, atthūpaparikkhā bahukārā.**Reflecting on the meaning of the teachings is helpful for accepting them after consideration …*";
P_HTM[8509]="*No cetaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkheyya, nayidaṃ dhammā nijjhānaṃ khameyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8510]="*Yasmā ca kho atthaṃ upaparikkhati tasmā dhammā nijjhānaṃ khamanti.* **";
P_HTM[8511]="*Tasmā dhammanijjhānakkhantiyā atthūpaparikkhā bahukārā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8512]="*“Atthūpaparikkhāya pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8513]="*Atthūpaparikkhāya bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8514]="*“Atthūpaparikkhāya kho, bhāradvāja, dhammadhāraṇā bahukārā.**Remembering the teachings is helpful for reflecting on their meaning …*";
P_HTM[8515]="*No cetaṃ dhammaṃ dhāreyya, nayidaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkheyya.* **";
P_HTM[8516]="*Yasmā ca kho dhammaṃ dhāreti tasmā atthaṃ upaparikkhati.* **";
P_HTM[8517]="*Tasmā atthūpaparikkhāya dhammadhāraṇā bahukārā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8518]="*“Dhammadhāraṇāya pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8519]="*Dhammadhāraṇāya bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8520]="*“Dhammadhāraṇāya kho, bhāradvāja, dhammassavanaṃ bahukāraṃ.**Hearing the teachings is helpful for remembering the teachings …*";
P_HTM[8521]="*No cetaṃ dhammaṃ suṇeyya, nayidaṃ dhammaṃ dhāreyya.* **";
P_HTM[8522]="*Yasmā ca kho dhammaṃ suṇāti tasmā dhammaṃ dhāreti.* **";
P_HTM[8523]="*Tasmā dhammadhāraṇāya dhammassavanaṃ bahukāran”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8524]="*“Dhammassavanassa pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8525]="*Dhammassavanassa bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8526]="*“Dhammassavanassa kho, bhāradvāja, sotāvadhānaṃ bahukāraṃ.**Listening is helpful for hearing the teachings …*";
P_HTM[8527]="*No cetaṃ sotaṃ odaheyya, nayidaṃ dhammaṃ suṇeyya.* **";
P_HTM[8528]="*Yasmā ca kho sotaṃ odahati tasmā dhammaṃ suṇāti.* **";
P_HTM[8529]="*Tasmā dhammassavanassa sotāvadhānaṃ bahukāran”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8530]="*“Sotāvadhānassa pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8531]="*Sotāvadhānassa bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8532]="*“Sotāvadhānassa kho, bhāradvāja, payirupāsanā bahukārā.**Paying homage is helpful for listening …*";
P_HTM[8533]="*No cetaṃ payirupāseyya, nayidaṃ sotaṃ odaheyya.* **";
P_HTM[8534]="*Yasmā ca kho payirupāsati tasmā sotaṃ odahati.* **";
P_HTM[8535]="*Tasmā sotāvadhānassa payirupāsanā bahukārā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8536]="*“Payirupāsanāya pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8537]="*Payirupāsanāya bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8538]="*“Payirupāsanāya kho, bhāradvāja, upasaṅkamanaṃ bahukāraṃ.**Approaching is helpful for paying homage …*";
P_HTM[8539]="*No cetaṃ upasaṅkameyya, nayidaṃ payirupāseyya.* **";
P_HTM[8540]="*Yasmā ca kho upasaṅkamati tasmā payirupāsati.* **";
P_HTM[8541]="*Tasmā payirupāsanāya upasaṅkamanaṃ bahukāran”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8542]="*“Upasaṅkamanassa pana, bho gotama, katamo dhammo bahukāro?* **";
P_HTM[8543]="*Upasaṅkamanassa bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ pucchāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8544]="*“Upasaṅkamanassa kho, bhāradvāja, saddhā bahukārā.**Faith is helpful for approaching a teacher.*";
P_HTM[8545]="*No cetaṃ saddhā jāyetha, nayidaṃ upasaṅkameyya.**If you don’t give rise to faith, you won’t approach a teacher.*";
P_HTM[8546]="*Yasmā ca kho saddhā jāyati tasmā upasaṅkamati.**You approach a teacher because you have faith.*";
P_HTM[8547]="*Tasmā upasaṅkamanassa saddhā bahukārā”ti.**That’s why faith is helpful for approaching a teacher.”*";
P_HTM[8548]="*“Saccānurakkhaṇaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ apucchimha, saccānurakkhaṇaṃ bhavaṃ gotamo byākāsi;**“I’ve asked Master Gotama about the preservation of truth, and he has answered me.*";
P_HTM[8549]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca tena camha attamanā.**I like and accept this, and am satisfied with it.*";
P_HTM[8550]="*Saccānubodhaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ apucchimha, saccānubodhaṃ bhavaṃ gotamo byākāsi;**I’ve asked Master Gotama about awakening to the truth, and he has answered me.*";
P_HTM[8551]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca tena camha attamanā.**I like and accept this, and am satisfied with it.*";
P_HTM[8552]="*Saccānuppattiṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ apucchimha, saccānuppattiṃ bhavaṃ gotamo byākāsi;**I’ve asked Master Gotama about the arrival at the truth, and he has answered me.*";
P_HTM[8553]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca tena camha attamanā.**I like and accept this, and am satisfied with it.*";
P_HTM[8554]="*Saccānuppattiyā bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ apucchimha, saccānuppattiyā bahukāraṃ dhammaṃ bhavaṃ gotamo byākāsi;**I’ve asked Master Gotama about the things that are helpful for the arrival at the truth, and he has answered me.*";
P_HTM[8555]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca tena camha attamanā.**I like and accept this, and am satisfied with it.*";
P_HTM[8556]="*Yaṃyadeva ca mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ apucchimha taṃtadeva bhavaṃ gotamo byākāsi;**Whatever I have asked Master Gotama about he has answered me.*";
P_HTM[8557]="*tañca panamhākaṃ ruccati ceva khamati ca tena camha attamanā.**I like and accept this, and am satisfied with it.*";
P_HTM[8558]="*Mayañhi, bho gotama, pubbe evaṃ jānāma:**Master Gotama, I used to think this:*";
P_HTM[8559]="*‘ke ca muṇḍakā samaṇakā ibbhā kaṇhā bandhupādāpaccā, ke ca dhammassa aññātāro’ti?**‘Who are these shavelings, fake ascetics, riffraff, black spawn from the feet of our Kinsman to be counted alongside those who understand the teaching?’*";
P_HTM[8560]="*Ajanesi vata me bhavaṃ gotamo samaṇesu samaṇapemaṃ, samaṇesu samaṇapasādaṃ, samaṇesu samaṇagāravaṃ.**The Buddha has inspired me to have love, confidence, and respect for ascetics!*";
P_HTM[8561]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**Excellent, Master Gotama! …*";
P_HTM[8562]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[8563]="*Caṅkīsuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8564]="*96. Esukārīsutta**With Esukārī*";
P_HTM[8565]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8566]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[8567]="*Atha kho esukārī brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Esukārī the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[8568]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho esukārī brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[8569]="*“brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, catasso pāricariyā paññapenti—**“Master Gotama, the brahmins prescribe four kinds of service:*";
P_HTM[8570]="*brāhmaṇassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti, khattiyassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti, vessassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti, suddassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti.**for a brahmin, an aristocrat, a merchant, and a worker.*";
P_HTM[8571]="*Tatridaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti:**This is the service they prescribe for a brahmin:*";
P_HTM[8572]="*‘brāhmaṇo vā brāhmaṇaṃ paricareyya, khattiyo vā brāhmaṇaṃ paricareyya, vesso vā brāhmaṇaṃ paricareyya, suddo vā brāhmaṇaṃ paricareyyā’ti.**‘A brahmin, an aristocrat, a merchant, and a worker may all serve a brahmin.’*";
P_HTM[8573]="*Idaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[8574]="*Tatridaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā khattiyassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti:**This is the service they prescribe for an aristocrat:*";
P_HTM[8575]="*‘khattiyo vā khattiyaṃ paricareyya, vesso vā khattiyaṃ paricareyya, suddo vā khattiyaṃ paricareyyā’ti.**‘An aristocrat, a merchant, and a worker may all serve an aristocrat.’*";
P_HTM[8576]="*Idaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā khattiyassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[8577]="*Tatridaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā vessassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti:**This is the service they prescribe for a merchant:*";
P_HTM[8578]="*‘vesso vā vessaṃ paricareyya, suddo vā vessaṃ paricareyyā’ti.**‘A merchant or a worker may serve a merchant.’*";
P_HTM[8579]="*Idaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā vessassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[8580]="*Tatridaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā suddassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti:**This is the service they prescribe for a worker:*";
P_HTM[8581]="*‘suddova suddaṃ paricareyya.**‘Only a worker may serve a worker.*";
P_HTM[8582]="*Ko panañño suddaṃ paricarissatī’ti?**For who else will serve a worker?’*";
P_HTM[8583]="*Idaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā suddassa pāricariyaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[8584]="*Brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, imā catasso pāricariyā paññapenti.**These are the four kinds of service that the brahmins prescribe.*";
P_HTM[8585]="*Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti?**What do you say about this?”*";
P_HTM[8586]="*“Kiṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, sabbo loko brāhmaṇānaṃ etadabbhanujānāti: ‘imā catasso pāricariyā paññapentū’”ti?**“But brahmin, did the whole world authorize the brahmins to prescribe these four kinds of service?”*";
P_HTM[8587]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8588]="*“Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, puriso daliddo assako anāḷhiyo. Tassa akāmassa bilaṃ olaggeyyuṃ: ‘idaṃ te, ambho purisa, maṃsaṃ khāditabbaṃ, mūlañca anuppadātabban’ti.**“It’s as if they were to force a steak on a poor, penniless person, telling them they must eat it and then pay for it.*";
P_HTM[8589]="*Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, brāhmaṇā appaṭiññāya tesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ, atha ca panimā catasso pāricariyā paññapenti.**In the same way, the brahmins have prescribed these four kinds of service without the consent of these ascetics and brahmins.*";
P_HTM[8590]="*Nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘sabbaṃ paricaritabban’ti vadāmi; nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘sabbaṃ na paricaritabban’ti vadāmi.**Brahmin, I don’t say that you should serve everyone, nor do I say that you shouldn’t serve anyone.*";
P_HTM[8591]="*Yaṃ hissa, brāhmaṇa, paricarato pāricariyāhetu pāpiyo assa na seyyo, nāhaṃ taṃ ‘paricaritabban’ti vadāmi;**I say that you shouldn’t serve someone if serving them makes you worse, not better.*";
P_HTM[8592]="*yañca khvāssa, brāhmaṇa, paricarato pāricariyāhetu seyyo assa na pāpiyo tamahaṃ ‘paricaritabban’ti vadāmi.**And I say that you should serve someone if serving them makes you better, not worse.*";
P_HTM[8593]="*Khattiyañcepi, brāhmaṇa, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**If they were to ask an aristocrat this,*";
P_HTM[8594]="*‘yaṃ vā te paricarato pāricariyāhetu pāpiyo assa na seyyo, yaṃ vā te paricarato pāricariyāhetu seyyo assa na pāpiyo;**‘Who should you serve? Someone in whose service you get worse, or someone in whose service you get better?’*";
P_HTM[8595]="*kamettha paricareyyāsī’ti, khattiyopi hi, brāhmaṇa, sammā byākaramāno evaṃ byākareyya:**Answering rightly, an aristocrat would say,*";
P_HTM[8596]="*‘yañhi me paricarato pāricariyāhetu pāpiyo assa na seyyo, nāhaṃ taṃ paricareyyaṃ; yañca kho me paricarato pāricariyāhetu seyyo assa na pāpiyo tamahaṃ paricareyyan’ti.**‘Someone in whose service I get better.’*";
P_HTM[8597]="*Brāhmaṇañcepi, brāhmaṇa … pe …**If they were to ask a brahmin …*";
P_HTM[8598]="*vessañcepi, brāhmaṇa … pe …**a merchant …*";
P_HTM[8599]="*suddañcepi, brāhmaṇa, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**or a worker this,*";
P_HTM[8600]="*‘yaṃ vā te paricarato pāricariyāhetu pāpiyo assa na seyyo, yaṃ vā te paricarato pāricariyāhetu seyyo assa na pāpiyo;**‘Who should you serve? Someone in whose service you get worse, or someone in whose service you get better?’*";
P_HTM[8601]="*kamettha paricareyyāsī’ti, suddopi hi, brāhmaṇa, sammā byākaramāno evaṃ byākareyya:**Answering rightly, a worker would say,*";
P_HTM[8602]="*‘yañhi me paricarato pāricariyāhetu pāpiyo assa na seyyo, nāhaṃ taṃ paricareyyaṃ; yañca kho me paricarato pāricariyāhetu seyyo assa na pāpiyo tamahaṃ paricareyyan’ti.**‘Someone in whose service I get better.’*";
P_HTM[8603]="*Nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘uccākulīnatā seyyaṃso’ti vadāmi, na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘uccākulīnatā pāpiyaṃso’ti vadāmi;**Brahmin, I don’t say that coming from an eminent family makes you a better or worse person.*";
P_HTM[8604]="*nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘uḷāravaṇṇatā seyyaṃso’ti vadāmi, na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘uḷāravaṇṇatā pāpiyaṃso’ti vadāmi;**I don’t say that being very beautiful makes you a better or worse person.*";
P_HTM[8605]="*nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘uḷārabhogatā seyyaṃso’ti vadāmi, na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘uḷārabhogatā pāpiyaṃso’ti vadāmi.**I don’t say that being very wealthy makes you a better or worse person.*";
P_HTM[8606]="*Uccākulīnopi hi, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇāvāco hoti, pharusāvāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti, abhijjhālu hoti, byāpannacitto hoti, micchādiṭṭhi hoti.**For some people from eminent families kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view.*";
P_HTM[8607]="*Tasmā ‘na uccākulīnatā seyyaṃso’ti vadāmi.**That’s why I don’t say that coming from an eminent family makes you a better person.*";
P_HTM[8608]="*Uccākulīnopi hi, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhi hoti.**But some people from eminent families also refrain from killing living creatures, stealing, and committing sexual misconduct. They refrain from using speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re not covetous or malicious, and they have right view.*";
P_HTM[8609]="*Tasmā ‘na uccākulīnatā pāpiyaṃso’ti vadāmi.**That’s why I don’t say that coming from an eminent family makes you a worse person.*";
P_HTM[8610]="*Uḷāravaṇṇopi hi, brāhmaṇa …**People who are very beautiful,*";
P_HTM[8611]="*pe …**or not very beautiful,*";
P_HTM[8612]="*uḷārabhogopi hi, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco pāṇātipātī hoti …**who are very wealthy,*";
P_HTM[8613]="*pe …**or not very wealthy,*";
P_HTM[8614]="*micchādiṭṭhi hoti.**may also behave in the same ways.*";
P_HTM[8615]="*Tasmā ‘na uḷārabhogatā seyyaṃso’ti vadāmi.**That’s why I don’t say that any of these things makes you a better or worse person.*";
P_HTM[8616]="*Uḷārabhogopi hi, brāhmaṇa, idhekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti.* **";
P_HTM[8617]="*Tasmā ‘na uḷārabhogatā pāpiyaṃso’ti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[8618]="*Nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘sabbaṃ paricaritabban’ti vadāmi, na panāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ‘sabbaṃ na paricaritabban’ti vadāmi.**Brahmin, I don’t say that you should serve everyone, nor do I say that you shouldn’t serve anyone.*";
P_HTM[8619]="*Yaṃ hissa, brāhmaṇa, paricarato pāricariyāhetu saddhā vaḍḍhati, sīlaṃ vaḍḍhati, sutaṃ vaḍḍhati, cāgo vaḍḍhati, paññā vaḍḍhati, tamahaṃ ‘paricaritabban’ti vadāmi.**And I say that you should serve someone if serving them makes you grow in faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[8620]="*Yaṃ hissa, brāhmaṇa, paricarato pāricariyāhetu na saddhā vaḍḍhati, na sīlaṃ vaḍḍhati, na sutaṃ vaḍḍhati, na cāgo vaḍḍhati, na paññā vaḍḍhati, nāhaṃ taṃ ‘paricaritabban’ti vadāmī”ti.**I say that you shouldn’t serve someone if serving them doesn’t make you grow in faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[8621]="*Evaṃ vutte, esukārī brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Esukārī said to him:*";
P_HTM[8622]="*“brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, cattāri dhanāni paññapenti—**“Master Gotama, the brahmins prescribe four kinds of wealth:*";
P_HTM[8623]="*brāhmaṇassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti, khattiyassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti, vessassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti, suddassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti.**for a brahmin, an aristocrat, a merchant, and a worker.*";
P_HTM[8624]="*Tatridaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti bhikkhācariyaṃ;**The wealth they prescribe for a brahmin is living on alms.*";
P_HTM[8625]="*bhikkhācariyañca pana brāhmaṇo sandhanaṃ atimaññamāno akiccakārī hoti gopova adinnaṃ ādiyamānoti.**A brahmin who scorns his own wealth, living on alms, fails in his duty like a guard who steals.*";
P_HTM[8626]="*Idaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[8627]="*Tatridaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā khattiyassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti dhanukalāpaṃ;**The wealth they prescribe for an aristocrat is the bow and quiver.*";
P_HTM[8628]="*dhanukalāpañca pana khattiyo sandhanaṃ atimaññamāno akiccakārī hoti gopova adinnaṃ ādiyamānoti.**An aristocrat who scorns his own wealth, the bow and quiver, fails in his duty like a guard who steals.*";
P_HTM[8629]="*Idaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā khattiyassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[8630]="*Tatridaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā vessassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti kasigorakkhaṃ;**The wealth they prescribe for a merchant is farming and animal husbandry.*";
P_HTM[8631]="*kasigorakkhañca pana vesso sandhanaṃ atimaññamāno akiccakārī hoti gopova adinnaṃ ādiyamānoti.**A merchant who scorns his own wealth, farming and animal husbandry, fails in his duty like a guard who steals.*";
P_HTM[8632]="*Idaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā vessassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[8633]="*Tatridaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā suddassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti asitabyābhaṅgiṃ;**The wealth they prescribe for a worker is the scythe and flail.*";
P_HTM[8634]="*asitabyābhaṅgiñca pana suddo sandhanaṃ atimaññamāno akiccakārī hoti gopova adinnaṃ ādiyamānoti.**A worker who scorns his own wealth, the scythe and flail, fails in his duty like a guard who steals.*";
P_HTM[8635]="*Idaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā suddassa sandhanaṃ paññapenti.* **";
P_HTM[8636]="*Brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, imāni cattāri dhanāni paññapenti.**These are the four kinds of wealth that the brahmins prescribe.*";
P_HTM[8637]="*Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti?**What do you say about this?”*";
P_HTM[8638]="*“Kiṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, sabbo loko brāhmaṇānaṃ etadabbhanujānāti: ‘imāni cattāri dhanāni paññapentū’”ti?**“But brahmin, did the whole world authorize the brahmins to prescribe these four kinds of wealth?”*";
P_HTM[8639]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8640]="*“Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, puriso daliddo assako anāḷhiyo. Tassa akāmassa bilaṃ olaggeyyuṃ: ‘idaṃ te, ambho purisa, maṃsaṃ khāditabbaṃ, mūlañca anuppadātabban’ti.**“It’s as if they were to force a steak on a poor, penniless person, telling them they must eat it and then pay for it.*";
P_HTM[8641]="*Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, brāhmaṇā appaṭiññāya tesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ, atha ca panimāni cattāri dhanāni paññapenti.**In the same way, the brahmins have prescribed these four kinds of wealth without the consent of these ascetics and brahmins.*";
P_HTM[8642]="*Ariyaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, lokuttaraṃ dhammaṃ purisassa sandhanaṃ paññapemi.**I declare that a person’s own wealth is the noble, transcendent teaching.*";
P_HTM[8643]="*Porāṇaṃ kho panassa mātāpettikaṃ kulavaṃsaṃ anussarato yattha yattheva attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti tena teneva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**But they are reckoned by recollecting the traditional family lineage of their mother and father wherever they are incarnated.*";
P_HTM[8644]="*Khattiyakule ce attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti ‘khattiyo’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**If they incarnate in a family of aristocrats they are reckoned as an aristocrat.*";
P_HTM[8645]="*brāhmaṇakule ce attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti ‘brāhmaṇo’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**If they incarnate in a family of brahmins they are reckoned as a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[8646]="*vessakule ce attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti ‘vesso’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**If they incarnate in a family of merchants they are reckoned as a merchant.*";
P_HTM[8647]="*suddakule ce attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti ‘suddo’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**If they incarnate in a family of workers they are reckoned as a worker.*";
P_HTM[8648]="*Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, yaṃyadeva paccayaṃ paṭicca aggi jalati tena teneva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**It’s like fire, which is reckoned according to the specific conditions dependent upon which it burns.*";
P_HTM[8649]="*Kaṭṭhañce paṭicca aggi jalati ‘kaṭṭhaggi’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**A fire that burns dependent on logs is reckoned as a log fire.*";
P_HTM[8650]="*sakalikañce paṭicca aggi jalati ‘sakalikaggi’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**A fire that burns dependent on twigs is reckoned as a twig fire.*";
P_HTM[8651]="*tiṇañce paṭicca aggi jalati ‘tiṇaggi’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;**A fire that burns dependent on grass is reckoned as a grass fire.*";
P_HTM[8652]="*gomayañce paṭicca aggi jalati ‘gomayaggi’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**A fire that burns dependent on cow-dung is reckoned as a cow-dung fire.*";
P_HTM[8653]="*Evameva kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, ariyaṃ lokuttaraṃ dhammaṃ purisassa sandhanaṃ paññapemi.**In the same way, I declare that a person’s own wealth is the noble, transcendent teaching.*";
P_HTM[8654]="*Porāṇaṃ kho panassa mātāpettikaṃ kulavaṃsaṃ anussarato yattha yattheva attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti tena teneva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.**But they are reckoned by recollecting the traditional family lineage of their mother and father wherever they are incarnated.*";
P_HTM[8655]="*Khattiyakule ce attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti ‘khattiyo’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;* **";
P_HTM[8656]="*brāhmaṇakule ce attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti ‘brāhmaṇo’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;* **";
P_HTM[8657]="*vessakule ce attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti ‘vesso’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati;* **";
P_HTM[8658]="*suddakule ce attabhāvassa abhinibbatti hoti ‘suddo’tveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[8659]="*Khattiyakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, abrahmacariyā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**Suppose someone from a family of aristocrats goes forth from the lay life to homelessness. Relying on the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One they refrain from killing living creatures, stealing, and sex. They refrain from using speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re not covetous or malicious, and they have right view. They succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[8660]="*Brāhmaṇakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**Suppose someone from a family of brahmins …*";
P_HTM[8661]="*Vessakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**merchants …*";
P_HTM[8662]="*Suddakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**workers goes forth from the lay life to homelessness. Relying on the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One … they succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[8663]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa,**What do you think, brahmin?*";
P_HTM[8664]="*brāhmaṇova nu kho pahoti asmiṃ padese averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāvetuṃ, no khattiyo no vesso no suddo”ti?**Is only a brahmin capable of developing a heart of love free of enmity and ill will for this region, and not an aristocrat, merchant, or worker?”*";
P_HTM[8665]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[8666]="*Khattiyopi hi, bho gotama, pahoti asmiṃ padese averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāvetuṃ;**Aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers can all do so.*";
P_HTM[8667]="*brāhmaṇopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[8668]="*vessopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[8669]="*suddopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[8670]="*sabbepi hi, bho gotama, cattāro vaṇṇā pahonti asmiṃ padese averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāvetun”ti.**For all four classes are capable of developing a heart of love free of enmity and ill will for this region.”*";
P_HTM[8671]="*“Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, khattiyakulā cepi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**“In the same way, suppose someone from a family of aristocrats,*";
P_HTM[8672]="*Brāhmaṇakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa …**brahmins,*";
P_HTM[8673]="*vessakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa …**merchants,*";
P_HTM[8674]="*suddakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**or workers goes forth from the lay life to homelessness. Relying on the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One … they succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[8675]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa,**What do you think, brahmin?*";
P_HTM[8676]="*brāhmaṇova nu kho pahoti sottisināniṃ ādāya nadiṃ gantvā rajojallaṃ pavāhetuṃ, no khattiyo no vesso no suddo”ti?**Is only a brahmin capable of taking some bathing paste of powdered shell, going to the river, and washing off dust and dirt, and not an aristocrat, merchant, or worker?”*";
P_HTM[8677]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[8678]="*Khattiyopi hi, bho gotama, pahoti sottisināniṃ ādāya nadiṃ gantvā rajojallaṃ pavāhetuṃ;* **";
P_HTM[8679]="*brāhmaṇopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[8680]="*vessopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[8681]="*suddopi hi, bho gotama …* **";
P_HTM[8682]="*sabbepi hi, bho gotama, cattāro vaṇṇā pahonti sottisināniṃ ādāya nadiṃ gantvā rajojallaṃ pavāhetun”ti.**All four classes are capable of doing this.”*";
P_HTM[8683]="*“Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, khattiyakulā cepi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**“In the same way, suppose someone from a family of aristocrats,*";
P_HTM[8684]="*Brāhmaṇakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa …**brahmins,*";
P_HTM[8685]="*vessakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa …**merchants,*";
P_HTM[8686]="*suddakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**or workers goes forth from the lay life to homelessness. Relying on the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One … they succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[8687]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa,**What do you think, brahmin?*";
P_HTM[8688]="*idha rājā khattiyo muddhāvasitto nānājaccānaṃ purisānaṃ purisasataṃ sannipāteyya:**Suppose an anointed aristocratic king were to gather a hundred people born in different castes and say to them:*";
P_HTM[8689]="*‘āyantu bhonto ye tattha khattiyakulā brāhmaṇakulā rājaññakulā uppannā sākassa vā sālassa vā salaḷassa vā candanassa vā padumakassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggiṃ abhinibbattentu, tejo pātukarontu;**‘Please gentlemen, let anyone here who was born in a family of aristocrats, brahmins, or chieftains take a drill-stick made of teak, sal, frankincense wood, sandalwood, or cherry wood, light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[8690]="*āyantu pana bhonto ye tattha caṇḍālakulā nesādakulā venakulā rathakārakulā pukkusakulā uppannā sāpānadoṇiyā vā sūkaradoṇiyā vā rajakadoṇiyā vā eraṇḍakaṭṭhassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggiṃ abhinibbattentu, tejo pātukarontū’”ti?**And let anyone here who was born in a family of outcastes, hunters, bamboo-workers, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors take a drill-stick made from a dog’s drinking trough, a pig’s trough, a dustbin, or castor-oil wood, light a fire and produce heat.’*";
P_HTM[8691]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa,**What do you think, brahmin?*";
P_HTM[8692]="*yo evaṃ nu kho so khattiyakulā brāhmaṇakulā rājaññakulā uppannehi sākassa vā sālassa vā salaḷassa vā candanassa vā padumakassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggi abhinibbatto tejo pātukato so eva nu khvāssa aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro ca tena ca sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ;**Would only the fire produced by the high class people with good quality wood have flames, color, and radiance, and be usable as fire,*";
P_HTM[8693]="*yo pana so caṇḍālakulā nesādakulā venakulā rathakārakulā pukkusakulā uppannehi sāpānadoṇiyā vā sūkaradoṇiyā vā rajakadoṇiyā vā eraṇḍakaṭṭhassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggi abhinibbatto tejo pātukato svāssa aggi na ceva accimā na ca vaṇṇavā na ca pabhassaro na ca tena sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātun”ti?**and not the fire produced by the low class people with poor quality wood?”*";
P_HTM[8694]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[8695]="*Yopi hi so, bho gotama, khattiyakulā brāhmaṇakulā rājaññakulā uppannehi sākassa vā sālassa vā salaḷassa vā candanassa vā padumakassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggi abhinibbatto tejo pātukato svāssa aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro ca tena ca sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ;**The fire produced by the high class people with good quality wood would have flames, color, and radiance, and be usable as fire,*";
P_HTM[8696]="*yopi so caṇḍālakulā nesādakulā venakulā rathakārakulā pukkusakulā uppannehi sāpānadoṇiyā vā sūkaradoṇiyā vā rajakadoṇiyā vā eraṇḍakaṭṭhassa vā uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya aggi abhinibbatto tejo pātukato svāssa aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro ca tena ca sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ.**and so would the fire produced by the low class people with poor quality wood.*";
P_HTM[8697]="*Sabbopi hi, bho gotama, aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro ca sabbenapi sakkā agginā aggikaraṇīyaṃ kātun”ti.**For all fire has flames, color, and radiance, and is usable as fire.”*";
P_HTM[8698]="*“Evameva kho, brāhmaṇa, khattiyakulā cepi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**“In the same way, suppose someone from a family of aristocrats,*";
P_HTM[8699]="*Brāhmaṇakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa …**brahmins,*";
P_HTM[8700]="*vessakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa …**merchants,*";
P_HTM[8701]="*suddakulā cepi, brāhmaṇa, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so ca tathāgatappaveditaṃ dhammavinayaṃ āgamma pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, abrahmacariyā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhi hoti, ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti.**or workers goes forth from the lay life to homelessness. Relying on the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One they refrain from killing living creatures, stealing, and sex. They refrain from using speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re not covetous or malicious, and they have right view. They succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.”*";
P_HTM[8702]="*Evaṃ vutte, esukārī brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Esukārī said to him,*";
P_HTM[8703]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[8704]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[8705]="*Esukārīsuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8706]="*97. Dhanañjānisutta**With Dhanañjāni*";
P_HTM[8707]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8708]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[8709]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto dakkhiṇāgirismiṃ cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ.**Now at that time Venerable Sāriputta was wandering in the Southern Hills together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[8710]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu rājagahe vassaṃvuṭṭho yena dakkhiṇāgiri yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then a certain mendicant who had completed the rainy season residence in Rājagaha went to the Southern Hills, where he approached Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[8711]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ bhikkhuṃ āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. Sāriputta said to him,*";
P_HTM[8712]="*“kaccāvuso, bhagavā arogo ca balavā cā”ti?**“Reverend, I hope the Buddha is healthy and well?”*";
P_HTM[8713]="*“Arogo cāvuso, bhagavā balavā cā”ti.**“He is, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[8714]="*“Kacci panāvuso, bhikkhusaṃgho arogo ca balavā cā”ti?**“And I hope that the mendicant Saṅgha is healthy and well.”*";
P_HTM[8715]="*“Bhikkhusaṃghopi kho, āvuso, arogo ca balavā cā”ti.**“It is.”*";
P_HTM[8716]="*“Ettha, āvuso, taṇḍulapālidvārāya dhanañjāni nāma brāhmaṇo atthi.**“Reverend, at the rice checkpoint there is a brahmin named Dhanañjāni.*";
P_HTM[8717]="*Kaccāvuso, dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo arogo ca balavā cā”ti?**I hope that he is healthy and well?”*";
P_HTM[8718]="*“Dhanañjānipi kho, āvuso, brāhmaṇo arogo ca balavā cā”ti.**“He too is well.”*";
P_HTM[8719]="*“Kacci panāvuso, dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo appamatto”ti?**“But is he diligent?”*";
P_HTM[8720]="*“Kuto panāvuso, dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa appamādo?**“How could he possibly be diligent?*";
P_HTM[8721]="*Dhanañjāni, āvuso, brāhmaṇo rājānaṃ nissāya brāhmaṇagahapatike vilumpati, brāhmaṇagahapatike nissāya rājānaṃ vilumpati.**Dhanañjāni robs the brahmins and householders in the name of the king, and he robs the king in the name of the brahmins and householders.*";
P_HTM[8722]="*Yāpissa bhariyā saddhā saddhakulā ānītā sāpi kālaṅkatā;**His wife, a lady of faith who he married from a family of faith, has passed away.*";
P_HTM[8723]="*aññāssa bhariyā assaddhā assaddhakulā ānītā”ti.**And he has taken a new wife who has no faith.”*";
P_HTM[8724]="*“Dussutaṃ vatāvuso, assumha, dussutaṃ vatāvuso, assumha;**“Oh, it’s bad news*";
P_HTM[8725]="*ye mayaṃ dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ pamattaṃ assumha.**to hear that Dhanañjāni is negligent.*";
P_HTM[8726]="*Appeva ca nāma mayaṃ kadāci karahaci dhanañjāninā brāhmaṇena saddhiṃ samāgaccheyyāma, appeva nāma siyā kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti?**Hopefully, some time or other I’ll get to meet him, and we can have a discussion.”*";
P_HTM[8727]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto dakkhiṇāgirismiṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena rājagahaṃ tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**When Sāriputta had stayed in the Southern Hills as long as he wished, he set out for Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[8728]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena rājagahaṃ tadavasari.**Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Rājagaha,*";
P_HTM[8729]="*Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā sāriputto rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**where he stayed in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[8730]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then he robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Rājagaha for alms.*";
P_HTM[8731]="*Tena kho pana samayena dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo bahinagare gāvo goṭṭhe duhāpeti.**Now at that time Dhanañjāni was having his cows milked in a cow-shed outside the city.*";
P_HTM[8732]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto rājagahe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo tenupasaṅkami.**Then Sāriputta wandered for alms in Rājagaha. After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he approached Dhanañjāni.*";
P_HTM[8733]="*Addasā kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Seeing Sāriputta coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[8734]="*Disvāna yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**Dhanañjāni went to him and said,*";
P_HTM[8735]="*“ito, bho sāriputta, payo, pīyataṃ tāva bhattassa kālo bhavissatī”ti.**“Here, Master Sāriputta, drink some fresh milk before the meal time.”*";
P_HTM[8736]="*“Alaṃ, brāhmaṇa.**“Enough, brahmin,*";
P_HTM[8737]="*Kataṃ me ajja bhattakiccaṃ.**I’ve finished eating for today.*";
P_HTM[8738]="*Amukasmiṃ me rukkhamūle divāvihāro bhavissati.**I shall be at the root of that tree for the day’s meditation.*";
P_HTM[8739]="*Tattha āgaccheyyāsī”ti.**Come see me there.”*";
P_HTM[8740]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Dhanañjāni.*";
P_HTM[8741]="*Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo pacchābhattaṃ bhuttapātarāso yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**When Dhanañjāni had finished breakfast he went to Sāriputta and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[8742]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. Sāriputta said to him,*";
P_HTM[8743]="*“kaccāsi, dhanañjāni, appamatto”ti?**“I hope you’re diligent, Dhanañjāni?”*";
P_HTM[8744]="*“Kuto, bho sāriputta, amhākaṃ appamādo yesaṃ no mātāpitaro posetabbā, puttadāro posetabbo, dāsakammakarā posetabbā, mittāmaccānaṃ mittāmaccakaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, ñātisālohitānaṃ ñātisālohitakaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, atithīnaṃ atithikaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, pubbapetānaṃ pubbapetakaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, devatānaṃ devatākaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, rañño rājakaraṇīyaṃ kātabbaṃ, ayampi kāyo pīṇetabbo brūhetabbo”ti?**“How can I possibly be diligent, Master Sāriputta? I have to provide for my mother and father, my wives and children, and my bondservants and workers. And I have to make the proper offerings to friends and colleagues, relatives and kin, guests, ancestors, deities, and king. And then this body must also be fattened and built up.”*";
P_HTM[8745]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni,**“What do you think, Dhanañjāni?*";
P_HTM[8746]="*idhekacco mātāpitūnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**Suppose someone was to behave in an unprincipled and unjust way for the sake of their parents. Because of this the wardens of hell would drag them to hell.*";
P_HTM[8747]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho mātāpitūnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, mātāpitaro vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?**Could they get out of being dragged to hell by pleading that they had acted for the sake of their parents? Or could their parents save them by pleading that the acts had been done for their sake?”*";
P_HTM[8748]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.**“No, Master Sāriputta.*";
P_HTM[8749]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.**Rather, even as they were wailing the wardens of hell would cast them down into hell.”*";
P_HTM[8750]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni,**“What do you think, Dhanañjāni?*";
P_HTM[8751]="*idhekacco puttadārassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**Suppose someone was to behave in an unprincipled and unjust way for the sake of their wives and children …*";
P_HTM[8752]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho puttadārassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, puttadāro vā panassa labheyya ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8753]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.* **";
P_HTM[8754]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[8755]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco dāsakammakaraporisassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**bondservants and workers …*";
P_HTM[8756]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho dāsakammakaraporisassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, dāsakammakaraporisā vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8757]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.* **";
P_HTM[8758]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[8759]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco mittāmaccānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**friends and colleagues …*";
P_HTM[8760]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho mittāmaccānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, mittāmaccā vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8761]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.* **";
P_HTM[8762]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[8763]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco ñātisālohitānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**relatives and kin …*";
P_HTM[8764]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho ñātisālohitānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, ñātisālohitā vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8765]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.* **";
P_HTM[8766]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[8767]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco atithīnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**guests …*";
P_HTM[8768]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho atithīnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, atithī vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8769]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.* **";
P_HTM[8770]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[8771]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco pubbapetānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**ancestors …*";
P_HTM[8772]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho pubbapetānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, pubbapetā vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8773]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.* **";
P_HTM[8774]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[8775]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco devatānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**deities …*";
P_HTM[8776]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho devatānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, devatā vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8777]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.* **";
P_HTM[8778]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[8779]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco rañño hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**king …*";
P_HTM[8780]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho rañño hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, rājā vā panassa labheyya ‘eso kho amhākaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8781]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.* **";
P_HTM[8782]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.* **";
P_HTM[8783]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, idhekacco kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, tamenaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu nirayaṃ nirayapālā upakaḍḍheyyuṃ.**fattening and building up their body. Because of this the wardens of hell would drag them to hell.*";
P_HTM[8784]="*Labheyya nu kho so ‘ahaṃ kho kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosiṃ, mā maṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’ti, pare vā panassa labheyyuṃ ‘eso kho kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu adhammacārī visamacārī ahosi, mā naṃ nirayaṃ nirayapālā’”ti?**Could they get out of being dragged to hell by pleading that they had acted for the sake of fattening and building up their body? Or could anyone else save them by pleading that the acts had been done for that reason?”*";
P_HTM[8785]="*“No hidaṃ, bho sāriputta.**“No, Master Sāriputta.*";
P_HTM[8786]="*Atha kho naṃ vikkandantaṃyeva niraye nirayapālā pakkhipeyyuṃ”.**Rather, even as they were wailing the wardens of hell would cast them down into hell.”*";
P_HTM[8787]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā mātāpitūnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā mātāpitūnaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**“Who do you think is better, Dhanañjāni? Someone who, for the sake of their parents, behaves in an unprincipled and unjust manner, or someone who behaves in a principled and just manner?”*";
P_HTM[8788]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8789]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, mātāpitūnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;**“Someone who behaves in a principled and just manner for the sake of their parents.*";
P_HTM[8790]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, mātāpitūnaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8791]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.**For principled and moral conduct is better than unprincipled and immoral conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8792]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā mātāpitaro ceva posetuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.**“Dhanañjāni, there are other livelihoods that are both profitable and legitimate. By means of these it’s possible to provide for your parents, avoid bad deeds, and practice the path of goodness.*";
P_HTM[8793]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā puttadārassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā puttadārassa hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**Who do you think is better, Dhanañjāni? Someone who, for the sake of their wives and children …*";
P_HTM[8794]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8795]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, puttadārassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;* **";
P_HTM[8796]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, puttadārassa hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8797]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8798]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā yehi sakkā puttadārañceva posetuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8799]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā dāsakammakaraporisassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā dāsakammakaraporisassa hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**bondservants and workers …*";
P_HTM[8800]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8801]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, dāsakammakaraporisassa hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;* **";
P_HTM[8802]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, dāsakammakaraporisassa hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8803]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8804]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā dāsakammakaraporise ceva posetuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8805]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā mittāmaccānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā mittāmaccānaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**friends and colleagues …*";
P_HTM[8806]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8807]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, mittāmaccānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;* **";
P_HTM[8808]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, mittāmaccānaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8809]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8810]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā mittāmaccānañceva mittāmaccakaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8811]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā ñātisālohitānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā ñātisālohitānaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**relatives and kin …*";
P_HTM[8812]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8813]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, ñātisālohitānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;* **";
P_HTM[8814]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, ñātisālohitānaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8815]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8816]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā ñātisālohitānañceva ñātisālohitakaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8817]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā atithīnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā atithīnaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**guests …*";
P_HTM[8818]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8819]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, atithīnaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;* **";
P_HTM[8820]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, atithīnaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8821]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8822]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā atithīnañceva atithikaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8823]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā pubbapetānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā pubbapetānaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**ancestors …*";
P_HTM[8824]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8825]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, pubbapetānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;* **";
P_HTM[8826]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, pubbapetānaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8827]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8828]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā pubbapetānañceva pubbapetakaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8829]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā devatānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā devatānaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**deities …*";
P_HTM[8830]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8831]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, devatānaṃ hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;* **";
P_HTM[8832]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, devatānaṃ hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8833]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8834]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā devatānañceva devatākaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8835]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā rañño hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā rañño hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;* **";
P_HTM[8836]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8837]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, rañño hetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;**king …*";
P_HTM[8838]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, rañño hetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8839]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8840]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā rañño ceva rājakaraṇīyaṃ kātuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8841]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, yo vā kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, yo vā kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu dhammacārī samacārī assa;**fattening and building up their body, behaves in an unprincipled and unjust manner, or someone who behaves in a principled and just manner?”*";
P_HTM[8842]="*katamaṃ seyyo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[8843]="*“Yo hi, bho sāriputta, kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu adhammacārī visamacārī assa, na taṃ seyyo;**“Someone who behaves in a principled and just manner.*";
P_HTM[8844]="*yo ca kho, bho sāriputta, kāyassa pīṇanāhetu brūhanāhetu dhammacārī samacārī assa, tadevettha seyyo.* **";
P_HTM[8845]="*Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhi, bho sāriputta, dhammacariyāsamacariyā seyyo”ti.**For principled and moral conduct is better than unprincipled and immoral conduct.”*";
P_HTM[8846]="*“Atthi kho, dhanañjāni, aññesaṃ hetukā dhammikā kammantā, yehi sakkā kāyañceva pīṇetuṃ brūhetuṃ, na ca pāpakammaṃ kātuṃ, puññañca paṭipadaṃ paṭipajjitun”ti.**“Dhanañjāni, there are other livelihoods that are both profitable and legitimate. By means of these it’s possible to fatten and build up your body, avoid bad deeds, and practice the path of goodness.”*";
P_HTM[8847]="*Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**Then Dhanañjāni the brahmin, having approved and agreed with what Venerable Sāriputta said, got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[8848]="*Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo aparena samayena ābādhiko ahosi dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**Some time later Dhanañjāni became sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[8849]="*Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi:**Then he addressed a man,*";
P_HTM[8850]="*“ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi:**“Please, mister, go to the Buddha, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him:*";
P_HTM[8851]="*‘dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**‘Sir, the brahmin Dhanañjāni is sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[8852]="*So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī’ti.**He bows with his head to your feet.’*";
P_HTM[8853]="*Yena cāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena āyasmato sāriputtassa pāde sirasā vandāhi:**Then go to Venerable Sāriputta, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him:*";
P_HTM[8854]="*‘dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**‘Sir, the brahmin Dhanañjāni is sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[8855]="*So āyasmato sāriputtassa pāde sirasā vandatī’ti.**He bows with his head to your feet.’*";
P_HTM[8856]="*Evañca vadehi:**And then say:*";
P_HTM[8857]="*‘sādhu kira, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto yena dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti.**‘Sir, please visit Dhanañjāni at his home out of compassion.’”*";
P_HTM[8858]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so puriso dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that man replied. He did as Dhanañjāni asked.*";
P_HTM[8859]="*“dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.* **";
P_HTM[8860]="*So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8861]="*Yena cāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[8862]="*“dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.* **";
P_HTM[8863]="*So āyasmato sāriputtassa pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti:* **";
P_HTM[8864]="*‘sādhu kira, bhante, āyasmā sāriputto yena dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8865]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā sāriputto tuṇhībhāvena.**Sāriputta consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[8866]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho āyasmā sāriputto dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**He robed up, and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Dhanañjāni’s home, where he sat on the seat spread out and said to Dhanañjāni,*";
P_HTM[8867]="*“kacci te, dhanañjāni, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ? Kacci dukkhā vedanā paṭikkamanti, no abhikkamanti? Paṭikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no abhikkamo”ti?**“Dhanañjāni, I hope you’re keeping well; I hope you’re alright. And I hope the pain is fading, not growing, that its fading is evident, not its growing.”*";
P_HTM[8868]="*“Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo.**“I’m not keeping well, Master Sāriputta, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading.*";
P_HTM[8869]="*Seyyathāpi, bho sāriputta, balavā puriso tiṇhena sikharena muddhani abhimattheyya; evameva kho, bho sāriputta, adhimattā vātā muddhani ca ūhananti.**The winds piercing my head are so severe, it feels like a strong man drilling into my head with a sharp point.*";
P_HTM[8870]="*Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo.**I’m not keeping well.*";
P_HTM[8871]="*Seyyathāpi, bho sāriputta, balavā puriso daḷhena varattakkhaṇḍena sīse sīsaveṭhaṃ dadeyya; evameva kho, bho sāriputta, adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā.**The pain in my head is so severe, it feels like a strong man tightening a tough leather strap around my head.*";
P_HTM[8872]="*Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo.**I’m not keeping well.*";
P_HTM[8873]="*Seyyathāpi, bho sāriputta, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā tiṇhena govikantanena kucchiṃ parikanteyya; evameva kho, bho sāriputta, adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti.**The winds piercing my belly are so severe, it feels like a deft butcher or their apprentice is slicing my belly open with a meat cleaver.*";
P_HTM[8874]="*Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo.**I’m not keeping well.*";
P_HTM[8875]="*Seyyathāpi, bho sāriputta, dve balavanto purisā dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuyā santāpeyyuṃ samparitāpeyyuṃ; evameva kho, bho sāriputta, adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho.**The burning in my body is so severe, it feels like two strong men grabbing a weaker man by the arms to burn and scorch him on a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[8876]="*Na me, bho sāriputta, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ. Bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti. Abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo”ti.**I’m not keeping well, Master Sāriputta, I’m not alright. The pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is evident, not its fading.”*";
P_HTM[8877]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Dhanañjāni, which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8878]="*nirayo vā tiracchānayoni vā”ti?**hell or the animal realm?”*";
P_HTM[8879]="*“Nirayā, bho sāriputta, tiracchānayoni seyyo”ti.**“The animal realm is better.”*";
P_HTM[8880]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8881]="*tiracchānayoni vā pettivisayo vā”ti?**the animal realm or the ghost realm?”*";
P_HTM[8882]="*“Tiracchānayoniyā, bho sāriputta, pettivisayo seyyo”ti.**“The ghost realm is better.”*";
P_HTM[8883]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8884]="*pettivisayo vā manussā vā”ti?**the ghost realm or human life?”*";
P_HTM[8885]="*“Pettivisayā, bho sāriputta, manussā seyyo”ti.**“Human life is better.”*";
P_HTM[8886]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8887]="*manussā vā cātumahārājikā vā devā”ti?**human life or as one of the Gods of the Four Great Kings?”*";
P_HTM[8888]="*“Manussehi, bho sāriputta, cātumahārājikā devā seyyo”ti.**“The Gods of the Four Great Kings.”*";
P_HTM[8889]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8890]="*cātumahārājikā vā devā tāvatiṃsā vā devā”ti?**the Gods of the Four Great Kings or the Gods of the Thirty-Three?”*";
P_HTM[8891]="*“Cātumahārājikehi, bho sāriputta, devehi tāvatiṃsā devā seyyo”ti.**“The Gods of the Thirty-Three.”*";
P_HTM[8892]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8893]="*tāvatiṃsā vā devā yāmā vā devā”ti?**the Gods of the Thirty-Three or the Gods of Yama?”*";
P_HTM[8894]="*“Tāvatiṃsehi, bho sāriputta, devehi yāmā devā seyyo”ti.**“The Gods of Yama.”*";
P_HTM[8895]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8896]="*yāmā vā devā tusitā vā devā”ti?**the Gods of Yama or the Joyful Gods?”*";
P_HTM[8897]="*“Yāmehi, bho sāriputta, devehi tusitā devā seyyo”ti.**“The Joyful Gods.”*";
P_HTM[8898]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8899]="*tusitā vā devā nimmānaratī vā devā”ti?**the Joyful Gods or the Gods Who Love to Create?”*";
P_HTM[8900]="*“Tusitehi, bho sāriputta, devehi nimmānaratī devā seyyo”ti.**“The Gods Who Love to Create.”*";
P_HTM[8901]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo—**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8902]="*nimmānaratī vā devā paranimmitavasavattī vā devā”ti?**the Gods Who Love to Create or the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others?”*";
P_HTM[8903]="*“Nimmānaratīhi, bho sāriputta, devehi paranimmitavasavattī devā seyyo”ti.**“The Gods Who Control the Creations of Others.”*";
P_HTM[8904]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, dhanañjāni, katamaṃ seyyo**“Which do you think is better:*";
P_HTM[8905]="*paranimmitavasavattī vā devā brahmaloko vā”ti?**the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others or the Brahmā realm?”*";
P_HTM[8906]="*“‘Brahmaloko’ti—bhavaṃ sāriputto āha;**“Master Sāriputta speaks of the Brahmā realm!*";
P_HTM[8907]="*‘brahmaloko’ti—bhavaṃ sāriputto āhā”ti.**Master Sāriputta speaks of the Brahmā realm!”*";
P_HTM[8908]="*Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:**Then Sāriputta thought:*";
P_HTM[8909]="*“ime kho brāhmaṇā brahmalokādhimuttā.**“These brahmins are devoted to the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[8910]="*Yannūnāhaṃ dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggaṃ deseyyan”ti.**Why don’t I teach him a path to the company of Brahmā?”*";
P_HTM[8911]="*“Brahmānaṃ te, dhanañjāni, sahabyatāya maggaṃ desessāmi;**“Dhanañjāni, I shall teach you a path to the company of Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[8912]="*taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[8913]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Dhanañjāni.*";
P_HTM[8914]="*Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**Venerable Sāriputta said this:*";
P_HTM[8915]="*“katamo ca, dhanañjāni, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo?**“And what is a path to companionship with Brahmā?*";
P_HTM[8916]="*Idha, dhanañjāni, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**Firstly, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[8917]="*Ayaṃ kho, dhanañjāni, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo.**This is a path to companionship with Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[8918]="*Puna caparaṃ, dhanañjāni, bhikkhu karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[8919]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā …**They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[8920]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[8921]="*Ayaṃ kho, dhanañjāni, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo”ti.**This is a path to companionship with Brahmā.”*";
P_HTM[8922]="*“Tena hi, bho sāriputta, mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi:**“Well then, Master Sāriputta, in my name bow with your head to the Buddha’s feet. Say to him:*";
P_HTM[8923]="*‘dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**‘Sir, the brahmin Dhanañjāni is sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[8924]="*So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī’”ti.**He bows with his head to your feet.’”*";
P_HTM[8925]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sati uttarikaraṇīye hīne brahmaloke patiṭṭhāpetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**Then Sāriputta, after establishing Dhanañjāni in the inferior Brahmā realm, got up from his seat and left while there was still more left to do.*";
P_HTM[8926]="*Atha kho dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo acirapakkante āyasmante sāriputte kālamakāsi, brahmalokañca upapajji.**Not long after Sāriputta had departed, Dhanañjāni passed away and was reborn in the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[8927]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[8928]="*“eso, bhikkhave, sāriputto dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sati uttarikaraṇīye hīne brahmaloke patiṭṭhāpetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti.**“Mendicants, Sāriputta, after establishing Dhanañjāni in the inferior Brahmā realm, got up from his seat and left while there was still more left to do.”*";
P_HTM[8929]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi, ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Sāriputta went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said,*";
P_HTM[8930]="*“dhanañjāni, bhante, brāhmaṇo ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno,**“Sir, the brahmin Dhanañjāni is sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[8931]="*so bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī”ti.**He bows with his head to your feet.”*";
P_HTM[8932]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, sāriputta, dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ sati uttarikaraṇīye hīne brahmaloke patiṭṭhāpetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti?**“But Sāriputta, after establishing Dhanañjāni in the inferior Brahmā realm, why did you get up from your seat and leave while there was still more left to do?”*";
P_HTM[8933]="*“Mayhaṃ kho, bhante, evaṃ ahosi:**“Sir, I thought:*";
P_HTM[8934]="*‘ime kho brāhmaṇā brahmalokādhimuttā, yannūnāhaṃ dhanañjānissa brāhmaṇassa brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggaṃ deseyyan’”ti.**‘These brahmins are devoted to the Brahmā realm. Why don’t I teach him a path to the company of Brahmā?’”*";
P_HTM[8935]="*“Kālaṅkato ca, sāriputta, dhanañjāni brāhmaṇo, brahmalokañca upapanno”ti.**“And Sāriputta, the brahmin Dhanañjāni has passed away and been reborn in the Brahmā realm.”*";
P_HTM[8936]="*Dhanañjānisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8937]="*98. Vāseṭṭhasutta**With Vāseṭṭha*";
P_HTM[8938]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8939]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā icchānaṅgale viharati icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍe.**At one time the Buddha was staying in a forest near Icchānaṅgala.*";
P_HTM[8940]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā brāhmaṇamahāsālā icchānaṅgale paṭivasanti, seyyathidaṃ—**Now at that time several very well-known well-to-do brahmins were residing in Icchānaṅgala. They included*";
P_HTM[8941]="*caṅkī brāhmaṇo, tārukkho brāhmaṇo, pokkharasāti brāhmaṇo, jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo, todeyyo brāhmaṇo, aññe ca abhiññātā abhiññātā brāhmaṇamahāsālā.**the brahmins Caṅkī, Tārukkha, Pokkharasāti, Jāṇussoṇi, Todeyya, and others.*";
P_HTM[8942]="*Atha kho vāseṭṭhabhāradvājānaṃ māṇavānaṃ jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamantānaṃ anuvicarantānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:**Then as the brahmin students Vāseṭṭha and Bhāradvāja were going for a walk they began to discussion the question of*";
P_HTM[8943]="*“kathaṃ, bho, brāhmaṇo hotī”ti?**how one is a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[8944]="*Bhāradvājo māṇavo evamāha:**Bhāradvāja said this:*";
P_HTM[8945]="*“yato kho, bho, ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena—**“When you’re well born on both your mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation—*";
P_HTM[8946]="*ettāvatā kho, bho, brāhmaṇo hotī”ti.**then you’re a brahmin.”*";
P_HTM[8947]="*Vāseṭṭho māṇavo evamāha:**Vāseṭṭha said this:*";
P_HTM[8948]="*“yato kho, bho, sīlavā ca hoti vattasampanno ca—**“When you’re ethical and accomplished in doing your duties—*";
P_HTM[8949]="*ettāvatā kho, bho, brāhmaṇo hotī”ti.**then you’re a brahmin.”*";
P_HTM[8950]="*Neva kho asakkhi bhāradvājo māṇavo vāseṭṭhaṃ māṇavaṃ saññāpetuṃ, na pana asakkhi vāseṭṭho māṇavo bhāradvājaṃ māṇavaṃ saññāpetuṃ.**But neither was able to persuade the other.*";
P_HTM[8951]="*Atha kho vāseṭṭho māṇavo bhāradvājaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi:**So Vāseṭṭha said to Bhāradvāja,*";
P_HTM[8952]="*“ayaṃ kho, bho bhāradvāja, samaṇo gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito icchānaṅgale viharati icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍe.**“Master Bhāradvāja, the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—is staying in a forest near Icchānaṅgala.*";
P_HTM[8953]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[8954]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[8955]="*Āyāma, bho bhāradvāja, yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ etamatthaṃ pucchissāma.**Come, let’s go to see him and ask him about this matter.*";
P_HTM[8956]="*Yathā no samaṇo gotamo byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti.**As he answers, so we’ll remember it.”*";
P_HTM[8957]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho bhāradvājo māṇavo vāseṭṭhassa māṇavassa paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Bhāradvāja.*";
P_HTM[8958]="*Atha kho vāseṭṭhabhāradvājā māṇavā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu.**So they went to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[8959]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[8960]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vāseṭṭho māṇavo bhagavantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:**and Vāseṭṭha addressed the Buddha in verse:*";
P_HTM[8961]="*“Anuññātapaṭiññātā,**“We’re both authorized masters*";
P_HTM[8962]="*tevijjā mayamasmubho;**of the three Vedas.*";
P_HTM[8963]="*Ahaṃ pokkharasātissa,**I’m a student of Pokkharasāti,*";
P_HTM[8964]="*tārukkhassāyaṃ māṇavo.**and he of Tārukkha.*";
P_HTM[8965]="*Tevijjānaṃ yadakkhātaṃ,**We’re fully qualified*";
P_HTM[8966]="*tatra kevalinosmase;**in all the Vedic experts teach.*";
P_HTM[8967]="*Padakasmā veyyākaraṇā,**As philologists and grammarians,*";
P_HTM[8968]="*jappe ācariyasādisā;**we match our teachers in recitation.*";
P_HTM[8969]="*Tesaṃ no jātivādasmiṃ,**We have a dispute*";
P_HTM[8970]="*vivādo atthi gotama.**regarding the question of ancestry.*";
P_HTM[8971]="*Jātiyā brāhmaṇo hoti,**For Bhāradvāja says that*";
P_HTM[8972]="*bhāradvājo iti bhāsati;**one is a brahmin due to birth,*";
P_HTM[8973]="*Ahañca kammunā brūmi,**but I declare it’s because of one’s actions.*";
P_HTM[8974]="*evaṃ jānāhi cakkhuma.**Oh seer, know this as our debate.*";
P_HTM[8975]="*Te na sakkoma ñāpetuṃ,**Since neither of us was able*";
P_HTM[8976]="*aññamaññaṃ mayaṃ ubho;**to convince the other,*";
P_HTM[8977]="*Bhavantaṃ puṭṭhumāgamā,**we’ve come to ask you, sir,*";
P_HTM[8978]="*sambuddhaṃ iti vissutaṃ.**so renowned as the awakened one.*";
P_HTM[8979]="*Candaṃ yathā khayātītaṃ,**As people honor with joined palms*";
P_HTM[8980]="*pecca pañjalikā janā;**the moon on the cusp of waxing,*";
P_HTM[8981]="*Vandamānā namassanti,**bowing, they revere*";
P_HTM[8982]="*lokasmiṃ gotamaṃ.**Gotama in the world.*";
P_HTM[8983]="*Cakkhuṃ loke samuppannaṃ,**We ask this of Gotama,*";
P_HTM[8984]="*mayaṃ pucchāma gotamaṃ;**the eye arisen in the world:*";
P_HTM[8985]="*Jātiyā brāhmaṇo hoti,**is one a brahmin due to birth,*";
P_HTM[8986]="*udāhu bhavati kammunā;**or else because of actions?*";
P_HTM[8987]="*Ajānataṃ no pabrūhi,**We don’t know, please tell us,*";
P_HTM[8988]="*yathā jānemu brāhmaṇan”ti.**so that we can know a brahmin.”*";
P_HTM[8989]="*“Tesaṃ vo ahaṃ byakkhissaṃ, (vāseṭṭhāti bhagavā)**“I shall explain to you,” said the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8990]="*Anupubbaṃ yathātathaṃ;**“accurately and in sequence,*";
P_HTM[8991]="*Jātivibhaṅgaṃ pāṇānaṃ,**the taxonomy of living creatures,*";
P_HTM[8992]="*Aññamaññāhi jātiyo.**for species are indeed diverse.*";
P_HTM[8993]="*Tiṇarukkhepi jānātha,**Know the grass and trees,*";
P_HTM[8994]="*na cāpi paṭijānare;**though they lack self-awareness.*";
P_HTM[8995]="*Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ,**They’re defined by their birth,*";
P_HTM[8996]="*aññamaññā hi jātiyo.**for species are indeed diverse.*";
P_HTM[8997]="*Tato kīṭe paṭaṅge ca,**Next there are bugs and moths,*";
P_HTM[8998]="*yāva kunthakipillike;**and so on, to ants and termites.*";
P_HTM[8999]="*Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ,**They’re defined by their birth,*";
P_HTM[9000]="*aññamaññā hi jātiyo.**for species are indeed diverse.*";
P_HTM[9001]="*Catuppadepi jānātha,**Know the quadrupeds, too,*";
P_HTM[9002]="*khuddake ca mahallake;**both small and large.*";
P_HTM[9003]="*Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ,**They’re defined by their birth,*";
P_HTM[9004]="*aññamaññā hi jātiyo.**for species are indeed diverse.*";
P_HTM[9005]="*Pādudarepi jānātha,**Know, too, the long-backed snakes,*";
P_HTM[9006]="*urage dīghapiṭṭhike;**crawling on their bellies.*";
P_HTM[9007]="*Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ,**They’re defined by their birth,*";
P_HTM[9008]="*aññamaññā hi jātiyo.**for species are indeed diverse.*";
P_HTM[9009]="*Tato macchepi jānātha,**Next know the fish,*";
P_HTM[9010]="*udake vārigocare;**whose habitat is the water.*";
P_HTM[9011]="*Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ,**They’re defined by their birth,*";
P_HTM[9012]="*aññamaññā hi jātiyo.**for species are indeed diverse.*";
P_HTM[9013]="*Tato pakkhīpi jānātha,**Next know the birds,*";
P_HTM[9014]="*pattayāne vihaṅgame;**flying with wings as chariots.*";
P_HTM[9015]="*Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ tesaṃ,**They’re defined by their birth,*";
P_HTM[9016]="*aññamaññā hi jātiyo.**for species are indeed diverse.*";
P_HTM[9017]="*Yathā etāsu jātīsu,**While the differences between these species*";
P_HTM[9018]="*liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ puthu;**are defined by their birth,*";
P_HTM[9019]="*Evaṃ natthi manussesu,**the differences between humans*";
P_HTM[9020]="*liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ puthu.**are not defined by their birth.*";
P_HTM[9021]="*Na kesehi na sīsehi,**Not by hair nor by head,*";
P_HTM[9022]="*na kaṇṇehi na akkhīhi;**not by ear nor by eye,*";
P_HTM[9023]="*Na mukhena na nāsāya,**not by mouth nor by nose,*";
P_HTM[9024]="*na oṭṭhehi bhamūhi vā.**not by lips nor by eyebrow,*";
P_HTM[9025]="*Na gīvāya na aṃsehi,**not by shoulder nor by neck,*";
P_HTM[9026]="*na udarena na piṭṭhiyā;**not by belly nor by back,*";
P_HTM[9027]="*Na soṇiyā na urasā,**not by buttocks nor by breast,*";
P_HTM[9028]="*na sambādhe na methune.**not by genitals nor by groin,*";
P_HTM[9029]="*Na hatthehi na pādehi,**not by hands nor by feet,*";
P_HTM[9030]="*naṅgulīhi nakhehi vā;**not by fingers nor by nails,*";
P_HTM[9031]="*Na jaṅghāhi na ūrūhi,**not by knees nor by thighs,*";
P_HTM[9032]="*na vaṇṇena sarena vā;**not by color nor by voice:*";
P_HTM[9033]="*Liṅgaṃ jātimayaṃ neva,**none of these are defined by birth*";
P_HTM[9034]="*yathā aññāsu jātisu.**as it is for other species.*";
P_HTM[9035]="*Paccattañca sarīresu,**In individual human bodies*";
P_HTM[9036]="*manussesvetaṃ na vijjati;**you can’t find such distinctions.*";
P_HTM[9037]="*Vokārañca manussesu,**The distinctions among humans*";
P_HTM[9038]="*samaññāya pavuccati.**are spoken of by convention.*";
P_HTM[9039]="*Yo hi koci manussesu,**Anyone among humans*";
P_HTM[9040]="*gorakkhaṃ upajīvati;**who lives off keeping cattle:*";
P_HTM[9041]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9042]="*kassako so na brāhmaṇo.**as a farmer, not a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9043]="*Yo hi koci manussesu,**Anyone among humans*";
P_HTM[9044]="*puthusippena jīvati;**who lives off various professions:*";
P_HTM[9045]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9046]="*sippiko so na brāhmaṇo.**as a professional, not a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9047]="*Yo hi koci manussesu,**Anyone among humans*";
P_HTM[9048]="*vohāraṃ upajīvati;**who lives off trade:*";
P_HTM[9049]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9050]="*vāṇijo so na brāhmaṇo.**as a trader, not a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9051]="*Yo hi koci manussesu,**Anyone among humans*";
P_HTM[9052]="*parapessena jīvati;**who lives off serving others:*";
P_HTM[9053]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9054]="*pessako so na brāhmaṇo.**as an employee, not a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9055]="*Yo hi koci manussesu,**Anyone among humans*";
P_HTM[9056]="*adinnaṃ upajīvati;**who lives off stealing:*";
P_HTM[9057]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9058]="*coro eso na brāhmaṇo.**as a bandit, not a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9059]="*Yo hi koci manussesu,**Anyone among humans*";
P_HTM[9060]="*issatthaṃ upajīvati;**who lives off archery:*";
P_HTM[9061]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9062]="*yodhājīvo na brāhmaṇo.**as a soldier, not a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9063]="*Yo hi koci manussesu,**Anyone among humans*";
P_HTM[9064]="*porohiccena jīvati;**who lives off priesthood:*";
P_HTM[9065]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9066]="*yājako so na brāhmaṇo.**as a sacrificer, not a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9067]="*Yo hi koci manussesu,**Anyone among humans*";
P_HTM[9068]="*gāmaṃ raṭṭhañca bhuñjati;**who taxes village and nation,*";
P_HTM[9069]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9070]="*rājā eso na brāhmaṇo.**as a ruler, not a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9071]="*Na cāhaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ brūmi,**I don’t call someone a brahmin*";
P_HTM[9072]="*yonijaṃ mattisambhavaṃ;**after the mother or womb they came from.*";
P_HTM[9073]="*Bhovādi nāma so hoti,**If they still have attachments,*";
P_HTM[9074]="*sace hoti sakiñcano;**they’re just someone who says ‘sir’.*";
P_HTM[9075]="*Akiñcanaṃ anādānaṃ,**One with nothing, by not grasping:*";
P_HTM[9076]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9077]="*Sabbasaṃyojanaṃ chetvā,**Having cut off all fetters*";
P_HTM[9078]="*yo ve na paritassati;**they have no anxiety.*";
P_HTM[9079]="*Saṅgātigaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ,**They’ve got over clinging, and are detached:*";
P_HTM[9080]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9081]="*Chetvā naddhiṃ varattañca,**They’ve cut the strap and harness,*";
P_HTM[9082]="*sandānaṃ sahanukkamaṃ;**the reins and bridle too,*";
P_HTM[9083]="*Ukkhittapalighaṃ buddhaṃ,**with cross-bar lifted, they’re awakened:*";
P_HTM[9084]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9085]="*Akkosaṃ vadhabandhañca,**Abuse, killing, caging:*";
P_HTM[9086]="*aduṭṭho yo titikkhati;**they endure these without anger.*";
P_HTM[9087]="*Khantībalaṃ balānīkaṃ,**Patience is their powerful army:*";
P_HTM[9088]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9089]="*Akkodhanaṃ vatavantaṃ,**Not irritable or stuck up,*";
P_HTM[9090]="*sīlavantaṃ anussadaṃ;**dutiful in precepts and observances,*";
P_HTM[9091]="*Dantaṃ antimasārīraṃ,**tamed, bearing their final body:*";
P_HTM[9092]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9093]="*Vāripokkharapatteva,**Like rain off a lotus leaf,*";
P_HTM[9094]="*āraggeriva sāsapo;**like a mustard seed off the point of a pin,*";
P_HTM[9095]="*Yo na limpati kāmesu,**sensual pleasures slide off them:*";
P_HTM[9096]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9097]="*Yo dukkhassa pajānāti,**They understand for themselves*";
P_HTM[9098]="*idheva khayamattano;**in this life the end of suffering;*";
P_HTM[9099]="*Pannabhāraṃ visaṃyuttaṃ,**with burden put down, detached:*";
P_HTM[9100]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9101]="*Gambhīrapaññaṃ medhāviṃ,**Deep in wisdom, intelligent,*";
P_HTM[9102]="*maggāmaggassa kovidaṃ;**expert in the variety of paths;*";
P_HTM[9103]="*Uttamatthamanuppattaṃ,**arrived at the highest goal:*";
P_HTM[9104]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9105]="*Asaṃsaṭṭhaṃ gahaṭṭhehi,**Socializing with neither*";
P_HTM[9106]="*anāgārehi cūbhayaṃ;**householders nor the homeless.*";
P_HTM[9107]="*Anokasārimappicchaṃ,**A migrant without a shelter, few in wishes:*";
P_HTM[9108]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9109]="*Nidhāya daṇḍaṃ bhūtesu,**They’ve laid down the rod*";
P_HTM[9110]="*tasesu thāvaresu ca;**against creatures firm and frail;*";
P_HTM[9111]="*Yo na hanti na ghāteti,**they don’t kill or cause to kill:*";
P_HTM[9112]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9113]="*Aviruddhaṃ viruddhesu,**Not fighting among those who fight,*";
P_HTM[9114]="*attadaṇḍesu nibbutaṃ;**they’re extinguished among those who’ve taken up arms.*";
P_HTM[9115]="*Sādānesu anādānaṃ,**Not grasping among those who grasp:*";
P_HTM[9116]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9117]="*Yassa rāgo ca doso ca,**They’ve discarded greed and hate,*";
P_HTM[9118]="*māno makkho ca ohito;**conceit and denigration,*";
P_HTM[9119]="*Sāsaporiva āraggā,**like a mustard seed off the point of a pin:*";
P_HTM[9120]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9121]="*Akakkasaṃ viññāpaniṃ,**The words they utter*";
P_HTM[9122]="*giraṃ saccaṃ udīraye;**are sweet, informative, and true,*";
P_HTM[9123]="*Yāya nābhisajje kiñci,**and don’t offend anyone:*";
P_HTM[9124]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9125]="*Yo ca dīghaṃ va rassaṃ vā,**They don’t steal anything in the world,*";
P_HTM[9126]="*aṇuṃ thūlaṃ subhāsubhaṃ;**long or short,*";
P_HTM[9127]="*Loke adinnaṃ nādeti,**fine or coarse, beautiful or ugly:*";
P_HTM[9128]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9129]="*Āsā yassa na vijjanti,**They have no hope*";
P_HTM[9130]="*asmiṃ loke paramhi ca;**for this world or the next;*";
P_HTM[9131]="*Nirāsāsaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ,**free of hope, detached:*";
P_HTM[9132]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9133]="*Yassālayā na vijjanti,**They have no clinging,*";
P_HTM[9134]="*aññāya akathaṅkathiṃ;**knowledge has freed them of indecision,*";
P_HTM[9135]="*Amatogadhaṃ anuppattaṃ,**they’ve arrived at the culmination of the deathless:*";
P_HTM[9136]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9137]="*Yodhapuññañca pāpañca,**They’ve escaped clinging*";
P_HTM[9138]="*ubho saṅgaṃ upaccagā;**to both good and bad deeds;*";
P_HTM[9139]="*Asokaṃ virajaṃ suddhaṃ,**sorrowless, stainless, pure:*";
P_HTM[9140]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9141]="*Candaṃ va vimalaṃ suddhaṃ,**Pure as the spotless moon,*";
P_HTM[9142]="*vippasannaṃ anāvilaṃ;**clear and undisturbed,*";
P_HTM[9143]="*Nandībhavaparikkhīṇaṃ,**they’ve ended desire to be reborn:*";
P_HTM[9144]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9145]="*Yo imaṃ palipathaṃ duggaṃ,**They’ve got past this grueling swamp*";
P_HTM[9146]="*saṃsāraṃ mohamaccagā;**of delusion, transmigration.*";
P_HTM[9147]="*Tiṇṇo pāraṅgato jhāyī,**They’ve crossed over to the far shore,*";
P_HTM[9148]="*anejo akathaṅkathī;**stilled and free of indecision.*";
P_HTM[9149]="*Anupādāya nibbuto,**They’re extinguished by not grasping:*";
P_HTM[9150]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9151]="*Yodhakāme pahantvāna,**They’ve given up sensual stimulations,*";
P_HTM[9152]="*anāgāro paribbaje;**and have gone forth from lay life;*";
P_HTM[9153]="*Kāmabhavaparikkhīṇaṃ,**they’ve ended rebirth in the sensual realm:*";
P_HTM[9154]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9155]="*Yodhataṇhaṃ pahantvāna,**They’ve given up craving,*";
P_HTM[9156]="*anāgāro paribbaje;**and have gone forth from lay life;*";
P_HTM[9157]="*Taṇhābhavaparikkhīṇaṃ,**they’ve ended craving to be reborn:*";
P_HTM[9158]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9159]="*Hitvā mānusakaṃ yogaṃ,**They’ve given up human bonds,*";
P_HTM[9160]="*dibbaṃ yogaṃ upaccagā;**and gone beyond heavenly bonds;*";
P_HTM[9161]="*Sabbayogavisaṃyuttaṃ,**detached from all attachments:*";
P_HTM[9162]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9163]="*Hitvā ratiñca aratiṃ,**They’ve given up liking and disliking,*";
P_HTM[9164]="*sītībhūtaṃ nirūpadhiṃ;**they’re cooled and free of attachments;*";
P_HTM[9165]="*Sabbalokābhibhuṃ vīraṃ,**a hero, master of the whole world:*";
P_HTM[9166]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9167]="*Cutiṃ yo vedi sattānaṃ,**They know the passing away*";
P_HTM[9168]="*upapattiñca sabbaso;**and rebirth of all beings;*";
P_HTM[9169]="*Asattaṃ sugataṃ buddhaṃ,**unattached, holy, awakened:*";
P_HTM[9170]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9171]="*Yassa gatiṃ na jānanti,**Gods, fairies, and humans*";
P_HTM[9172]="*devā gandhabbamānusā;**don’t know their destiny;*";
P_HTM[9173]="*Khīṇāsavaṃ arahantaṃ,**the perfected ones with defilements ended:*";
P_HTM[9174]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9175]="*Yassa pure ca pacchā ca,**They have nothing before or after,*";
P_HTM[9176]="*majjhe ca natthi kiñcanaṃ;**or even in between;*";
P_HTM[9177]="*Akiñcanaṃ anādānaṃ,**one with nothing, by not grasping:*";
P_HTM[9178]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9179]="*Usabhaṃ pavaraṃ vīraṃ,**Leader of the herd, excellent hero,*";
P_HTM[9180]="*mahesiṃ vijitāvinaṃ;**great hermit and victor;*";
P_HTM[9181]="*Anejaṃ nhātakaṃ buddhaṃ,**unstirred, washed, awakened:*";
P_HTM[9182]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9183]="*Pubbenivāsaṃ yo vedi,**They know their past lives,*";
P_HTM[9184]="*saggāpāyañca passati;**and see heaven and places of loss,*";
P_HTM[9185]="*Atho jātikkhayaṃ patto,**and have attained the end of rebirth:*";
P_HTM[9186]="*tamahaṃ brūmi brāhmaṇaṃ.**that’s who I call a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9187]="*Samaññā hesā lokasmiṃ,**For name and clan are assigned*";
P_HTM[9188]="*nāmagottaṃ pakappitaṃ;**as mere convention in the world.*";
P_HTM[9189]="*Sammuccā samudāgataṃ,**Arising by mutual agreement,*";
P_HTM[9190]="*tattha tattha pakappitaṃ.**they’re assigned to each individual.*";
P_HTM[9191]="*Dīgharattānusayitaṃ,**For a long time this misconception*";
P_HTM[9192]="*diṭṭhigatamajānataṃ;**has prejudiced those who don’t understand.*";
P_HTM[9193]="*Ajānantā no pabrunti,**Ignorant, they declare*";
P_HTM[9194]="*jātiyā hoti brāhmaṇo.**that one is a brahmin by birth.*";
P_HTM[9195]="*Na jaccā brāhmaṇo hoti,**You’re not a brahmin by birth,*";
P_HTM[9196]="*na jaccā hoti abrāhmaṇo;**nor by birth a non-brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9197]="*Kammunā brāhmaṇo hoti,**You’re a brahmin by your deeds,*";
P_HTM[9198]="*kammunā hoti abrāhmaṇo.**and by deeds a non-brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9199]="*Kassako kammunā hoti,**You’re a farmer by your deeds,*";
P_HTM[9200]="*sippiko hoti kammunā;**by deeds you’re a professional;*";
P_HTM[9201]="*Vāṇijo kammunā hoti,**you’re a trader by your deeds,*";
P_HTM[9202]="*pessako hoti kammunā.**by deeds are you an employee;*";
P_HTM[9203]="*Coropi kammunā hoti,**you’re a bandit by your deeds,*";
P_HTM[9204]="*yodhājīvopi kammunā;**by deeds you’re a soldier;*";
P_HTM[9205]="*Yājako kammunā hoti,**you’re a sacrificer by your deeds,*";
P_HTM[9206]="*rājāpi hoti kammunā.**by deeds you’re a ruler.*";
P_HTM[9207]="*Evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ,**In this way in accord with truth,*";
P_HTM[9208]="*kammaṃ passanti paṇḍitā;**the astute regard deeds.*";
P_HTM[9209]="*Paṭiccasamuppādadassā,**Seeing dependent origination,*";
P_HTM[9210]="*kammavipākakovidā.**they’re expert in deeds and their results.*";
P_HTM[9211]="*Kammunā vattati loko,**Deeds make the world go on,*";
P_HTM[9212]="*kammunā vattati pajā;**deeds make people go on;*";
P_HTM[9213]="*Kammanibandhanā sattā,**sentient beings are bound by deeds,*";
P_HTM[9214]="*rathassāṇīva yāyato.**like a moving chariot’s linchpin.*";
P_HTM[9215]="*Tapena brahmacariyena,**By austerity and spiritual practice,*";
P_HTM[9216]="*saṃyamena damena ca;**by restraint and by taming:*";
P_HTM[9217]="*Etena brāhmaṇo hoti,**that’s how to become a brahmin,*";
P_HTM[9218]="*etaṃ brāhmaṇamuttamaṃ.**this is the supreme brahmin.*";
P_HTM[9219]="*Tīhi vijjāhi sampanno,**Accomplished in the three knowledges,*";
P_HTM[9220]="*santo khīṇapunabbhavo;**peaceful, with rebirth ended,*";
P_HTM[9221]="*Evaṃ vāseṭṭha jānāhi,**know them, Vāseṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[9222]="*brahmā sakko vijānatan”ti.**as Brahmā and Sakka to the wise.”*";
P_HTM[9223]="*Evaṃ vutte, vāseṭṭhabhāradvājā māṇavā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When he had spoken, Vāseṭṭha and Bhāradvāja said to him,*";
P_HTM[9224]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[9225]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[9226]="*Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[9227]="*Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gate”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[9228]="*Vāseṭṭhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9229]="*99. Subhasutta**With Subha*";
P_HTM[9230]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[9231]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[9232]="*Tena kho pana samayena subho māṇavo todeyyaputto sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati aññatarassa gahapatissa nivesane kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Now at that time the brahmin student Subha, Todeyya’s son, was residing in Sāvatthī at a certain householder’s home on some business.*";
P_HTM[9233]="*Atha kho subho māṇavo todeyyaputto yassa gahapatissa nivesane paṭivasati taṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**Then Subha said to that householder,*";
P_HTM[9234]="*“sutaṃ metaṃ, gahapati:**“Householder, I’ve heard that*";
P_HTM[9235]="*‘avivittā sāvatthī arahantehī’ti.**Sāvatthī does not lack for perfected ones.*";
P_HTM[9236]="*Kaṃ nu khvajja samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā payirupāseyyāmā”ti?**What ascetic or brahmin might we pay homage to today?”*";
P_HTM[9237]="*“Ayaṃ, bhante, bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**“Sir, the Buddha is staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[9238]="*Taṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ payirupāsassū”ti.**You can pay homage to him.”*";
P_HTM[9239]="*Atha kho subho māṇavo todeyyaputto tassa gahapatissa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Acknowledging that householder, Subha went to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[9240]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[9241]="*“brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, evamāhaṃsu:**“Master Gotama, the brahmins say:*";
P_HTM[9242]="*‘gahaṭṭho ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ, na pabbajito ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan’ti.**‘Laypeople succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching, not renunciates.’*";
P_HTM[9243]="*Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti?**What do you say about this?”*";
P_HTM[9244]="*“Vibhajjavādo kho ahamettha, māṇava;**“On this point, student, I speak after analyzing the question,*";
P_HTM[9245]="*nāhamettha ekaṃsavādo.**without making generalizations.*";
P_HTM[9246]="*Gihissa vāhaṃ, māṇava, pabbajitassa vā micchāpaṭipattiṃ na vaṇṇemi.**I don’t praise wrong practice for either laypeople or renunciates.*";
P_HTM[9247]="*Gihī vā hi, māṇava, pabbajito vā micchāpaṭipanno micchāpaṭipattādhikaraṇahetu na ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ.**Because of wrong practice, neither laypeople nor renunciates succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.*";
P_HTM[9248]="*Gihissa vāhaṃ, māṇava, pabbajitassa vā sammāpaṭipattiṃ vaṇṇemi.**I praise right practice for both laypeople and renunciates.*";
P_HTM[9249]="*Gihī vā hi, māṇava, pabbajito vā sammāpaṭipanno sammāpaṭipattādhikaraṇahetu ārādhako hoti ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti.**Because of right practice, both laypeople and renunciates succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.”*";
P_HTM[9250]="*“Brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, evamāhaṃsu:**“Master Gotama, the brahmins say:*";
P_HTM[9251]="*‘mahaṭṭhamidaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ gharāvāsakammaṭṭhānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti;**‘Since the work of the lay life has many requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings it is very fruitful.*";
P_HTM[9252]="*appaṭṭhamidaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ pabbajjā kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaphalaṃ hotī’ti.**But since the work of the renunciate has few requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings it is not very fruitful.’*";
P_HTM[9253]="*Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti.**What do you say about this?”*";
P_HTM[9254]="*“Etthāpi kho ahaṃ, māṇava, vibhajjavādo;**“On this point, too, I speak after analyzing the question,*";
P_HTM[9255]="*nāhamettha ekaṃsavādo.**without making generalizations.*";
P_HTM[9256]="*Atthi, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ, vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti;**Some work has many requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and when it fails it’s not very fruitful.*";
P_HTM[9257]="*atthi, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ, sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti;**Some work has many requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and when it succeeds it is very fruitful.*";
P_HTM[9258]="*atthi, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ, vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti;**Some work has few requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and when it fails it’s not very fruitful.*";
P_HTM[9259]="*atthi, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti.**Some work has few requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and when it succeeds it is very fruitful.*";
P_HTM[9260]="*Katamañca, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti?**And what work has many requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and when it fails it’s not very fruitful?*";
P_HTM[9261]="*Kasi kho, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti.**Farming.*";
P_HTM[9262]="*Katamañca, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti?**And what work has many requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and when it succeeds it is very fruitful?*";
P_HTM[9263]="*Kasiyeva kho, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti.**Again, it is farming.*";
P_HTM[9264]="*Katamañca, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti?**And what work has few requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and when it fails it’s not very fruitful?*";
P_HTM[9265]="*Vaṇijjā kho, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti.**Trade.*";
P_HTM[9266]="*Katamañca, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti?**And what work has few requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and when it succeeds it is very fruitful?*";
P_HTM[9267]="*Vaṇijjāyeva kho, māṇava, kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti.**Again, it’s trade.*";
P_HTM[9268]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, kasi kammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti;**The lay life is like farming in that it’s work with many requirements and when it fails it’s not very fruitful;*";
P_HTM[9269]="*evameva kho, māṇava, gharāvāsakammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9270]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, kasiyeva kammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti;**but when it succeeds it is very fruitful.*";
P_HTM[9271]="*evameva kho, māṇava, gharāvāsakammaṭṭhānaṃ mahaṭṭhaṃ mahākiccaṃ mahādhikaraṇaṃ mahāsamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9272]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, vaṇijjā kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti;**The renunciate life is like trade in that it’s work with few requirements and when it fails it’s not very fruitful;*";
P_HTM[9273]="*evameva kho, māṇava, pabbajjā kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ vipajjamānaṃ appaphalaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9274]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, vaṇijjāyeva kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti;**but when it succeeds it is very fruitful.”*";
P_HTM[9275]="*evameva kho, māṇava, pabbajjā kammaṭṭhānaṃ appaṭṭhaṃ appakiccaṃ appādhikaraṇaṃ appasamārambhaṃ sampajjamānaṃ mahapphalaṃ hotī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9276]="*“Brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya, kusalassa ārādhanāyā”ti.**“Master Gotama, the brahmins prescribe five things for making merit and succeeding in the skillful.”*";
P_HTM[9277]="*“Ye te, māṇava, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya, kusalassa ārādhanāya—* **";
P_HTM[9278]="*sace te agaru—**“If you don’t mind,*";
P_HTM[9279]="*sādhu te pañca dhamme imasmiṃ parisati bhāsassū”ti.**please explain these in this assembly.”*";
P_HTM[9280]="*“Na kho me, bho gotama, garu yatthassu bhavanto vā nisinno bhavantarūpo vā”ti.**“It’s no trouble when gentlemen such as yourself are sitting here.”*";
P_HTM[9281]="*“Tena hi, māṇava, bhāsassū”ti.**“Well, speak then, student.”*";
P_HTM[9282]="*“Saccaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya, kusalassa ārādhanāya.**“Master Gotama, truth is the first thing.*";
P_HTM[9283]="*Tapaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā dutiyaṃ dhammaṃ paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya, kusalassa ārādhanāya.**Austerity is the second thing.*";
P_HTM[9284]="*Brahmacariyaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā tatiyaṃ dhammaṃ paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya, kusalassa ārādhanāya.**Celibacy is the third thing.*";
P_HTM[9285]="*Ajjhenaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā catutthaṃ dhammaṃ paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya, kusalassa ārādhanāya.**Recitation is the fourth thing.*";
P_HTM[9286]="*Cāgaṃ kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā pañcamaṃ dhammaṃ paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya, kusalassa ārādhanāya.**Generosity is the fifth thing.*";
P_HTM[9287]="*Brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, ime pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya, kusalassa ārādhanāyāti.**These are the five things that the brahmins prescribe for making merit and succeeding in the skillful.*";
P_HTM[9288]="*Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti?**What do you say about this?”*";
P_HTM[9289]="*“Kiṃ pana, māṇava, atthi koci brāhmaṇānaṃ ekabrāhmaṇopi yo evamāha:**“Well, student, is there even a single one of the brahmins who says this:*";
P_HTM[9290]="*‘ahaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ dhammānaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā vipākaṃ pavedemī’”ti?**‘I declare the result of these five things after realizing it with my own insight’?”*";
P_HTM[9291]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[9292]="*“Kiṃ pana, māṇava, atthi koci brāhmaṇānaṃ ekācariyopi ekācariyapācariyopi yāva sattamā ācariyamahayugāpi yo evamāha:**“Well, is there even a single teacher of the brahmins, or a teacher’s teacher, or anyone back to the seventh generation of teachers, who says this:*";
P_HTM[9293]="*‘ahaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ dhammānaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā vipākaṃ pavedemī’”ti?**‘I declare the result of these five things after realizing it with my own insight’?”*";
P_HTM[9294]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[9295]="*“Kiṃ pana, māṇava, yepi te brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samihitaṃ tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti vācitamanuvācenti, seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako vāmako vāmadevo vessāmitto yamataggi aṅgīraso bhāradvājo vāseṭṭho kassapo bhagu,**“Well, what of the ancient hermits of the brahmins, namely Aṭṭhaka, Vāmaka, Vāmadeva, Vessāmitta, Yamadaggi, Aṅgīrasa, Bhāradvāja, Vāseṭṭha, Kassapa, and Bhagu? They were the authors and propagators of the hymns. Their hymnal was sung and propagated and compiled in ancient times; and these days, brahmins continue to sing and chant it, chanting what was chanted and teaching what was taught.*";
P_HTM[9296]="*tepi evamāhaṃsu:**Did even they say:*";
P_HTM[9297]="*‘mayaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ dhammānaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā vipākaṃ pavedemā’”ti?**‘We declare the result of these five things after realizing it with our own insight’?”*";
P_HTM[9298]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[9299]="*“Iti kira, māṇava, natthi koci brāhmaṇānaṃ ekabrāhmaṇopi yo evamāha:**“So, student, it seems that there is not a single one of the brahmins,*";
P_HTM[9300]="*‘ahaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ dhammānaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā vipākaṃ pavedemī’ti;* **";
P_HTM[9301]="*natthi koci brāhmaṇānaṃ ekācariyopi ekācariyapācariyopi yāva sattamā ācariyamahayugāpi yo evamāha:**not even anyone back to the seventh generation of teachers,*";
P_HTM[9302]="*‘ahaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ dhammānaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā vipākaṃ pavedemī’ti;* **";
P_HTM[9303]="*yepi te brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro, yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samihitaṃ, tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti vācitamanuvācenti, seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako vāmako vāmadevo vessāmitto yamataggi aṅgīraso bhāradvājo vāseṭṭho kassapo bhagu.**nor even the ancient hermits of the brahmins*";
P_HTM[9304]="*Tepi na evamāhaṃsu:**who says:*";
P_HTM[9305]="*‘mayaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ dhammānaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā vipākaṃ pavedemā’ti.**‘We declare the result of these five things after realizing it with our own insight.’*";
P_HTM[9306]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, andhaveṇi paramparāsaṃsattā purimopi na passati majjhimopi na passati pacchimopi na passati;**Suppose there was a queue of blind men, each holding the one in front: the first one does not see, the middle one does not see, and the last one does not see.*";
P_HTM[9307]="*evameva kho, māṇava, andhaveṇūpamaṃ maññe brāhmaṇānaṃ bhāsitaṃ sampajjati—purimopi na passati majjhimopi na passati pacchimopi na passatī”ti.**In the same way, it seems to me that the brahmins’ statement turns out to be comparable to a queue of blind men: the first one does not see, the middle one does not see, and the last one does not see.”*";
P_HTM[9308]="*Evaṃ vutte, subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhagavatā andhaveṇūpamena vuccamāno kupito anattamano bhagavantaṃyeva khuṃsento bhagavantaṃyeva vambhento bhagavantaṃyeva vadamāno:**When he said this, Subha became angry and upset with the Buddha because of the simile of the queue of blind men. He even attacked and badmouthed the Buddha himself, saying,*";
P_HTM[9309]="*“samaṇo gotamo pāpito bhavissatī”ti bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**“The ascetic Gotama will be worsted!” He said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[9310]="*“brāhmaṇo, bho gotama, pokkharasāti opamañño subhagavaniko evamāha:**“Master Gotama, the brahmin Pokkharasāti Upamañña of the Subhaga Forest says:*";
P_HTM[9311]="*‘evameva panidhekacce samaṇabrāhmaṇā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ paṭijānanti.**‘This is exactly what happens with some ascetics and brahmins. They claim to have a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[9312]="*Tesamidaṃ bhāsitaṃ hassakaṃyeva sampajjati, nāmakaṃyeva sampajjati, rittakaṃyeva sampajjati, tucchakaṃyeva sampajjati.**But their statement turns out to be a joke—mere words, void and hollow.*";
P_HTM[9313]="*Kathañhi nāma manussabhūto uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ ñassati vā dakkhati vā sacchi vā karissatīti—**For how on earth can a human being know or see or realize a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones?*";
P_HTM[9314]="*netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’”ti?**That is not possible.’”*";
P_HTM[9315]="*“Kiṃ pana, māṇava, brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti opamañño subhagavaniko sabbesaṃyeva samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānātī”ti?**“But student, does Pokkharasāti understand the minds of all these ascetics and brahmins, having comprehended them with his mind?”*";
P_HTM[9316]="*“Sakāyapi hi, bho gotama, puṇṇikāya dāsiyā brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti opamañño subhagavaniko cetasā ceto paricca na pajānāti, kuto pana sabbesaṃyeva samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānissatī”ti?**“Master Gotama, Pokkharasāti doesn’t even know the mind of his own bonded maid Puṇṇikā, so how could he know all those ascetics and brahmins?”*";
P_HTM[9317]="*“Seyyathāpi, māṇava, jaccandho puriso na passeyya kaṇhasukkāni rūpāni, na passeyya nīlakāni rūpāni, na passeyya pītakāni rūpāni, na passeyya lohitakāni rūpāni, na passeyya mañjiṭṭhakāni rūpāni, na passeyya samavisamaṃ, na passeyya tārakarūpāni, na passeyya candimasūriye.**“Suppose there was a person blind from birth. They couldn’t see sights that are dark or bright, or blue, yellow, red, or magenta. They couldn’t see even and uneven ground, or the stars, or the moon and sun.*";
P_HTM[9318]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[9319]="*‘natthi kaṇhasukkāni rūpāni, natthi kaṇhasukkānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**‘There’s no such thing as dark and bright sights, and no-one who sees them.*";
P_HTM[9320]="*natthi nīlakāni rūpāni, natthi nīlakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**There’s no such thing as blue,*";
P_HTM[9321]="*natthi pītakāni rūpāni, natthi pītakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**yellow,*";
P_HTM[9322]="*natthi lohitakāni rūpāni, natthi lohitakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**red,*";
P_HTM[9323]="*natthi mañjiṭṭhakāni rūpāni, natthi mañjiṭṭhakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**magenta,*";
P_HTM[9324]="*natthi samavisamaṃ, natthi samavisamassa dassāvī;**even and uneven ground,*";
P_HTM[9325]="*natthi tārakarūpāni, natthi tārakarūpānaṃ dassāvī;**stars,*";
P_HTM[9326]="*natthi candimasūriyā, natthi candimasūriyānaṃ dassāvī.**moon and sun, and no-one who sees these things.*";
P_HTM[9327]="*Ahametaṃ na jānāmi, ahametaṃ na passāmi;**I don’t know it or see it,*";
P_HTM[9328]="*tasmā taṃ natthī’ti.**therefore it doesn’t exist.’*";
P_HTM[9329]="*Sammā nu kho so, māṇava, vadamāno vadeyyā”ti?**Would they be speaking rightly?”*";
P_HTM[9330]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[9331]="*Atthi kaṇhasukkāni rūpāni, atthi kaṇhasukkānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**There are such things as dark and bright sights, and one who sees them.*";
P_HTM[9332]="*atthi nīlakāni rūpāni, atthi nīlakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**There is blue,*";
P_HTM[9333]="*atthi pītakāni rūpāni, atthi pītakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**yellow,*";
P_HTM[9334]="*atthi lohitakāni rūpāni, atthi lohitakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**red,*";
P_HTM[9335]="*atthi mañjiṭṭhakāni rūpāni, atthi mañjiṭṭhakānaṃ rūpānaṃ dassāvī;**magenta,*";
P_HTM[9336]="*atthi samavisamaṃ, atthi samavisamassa dassāvī;**even and uneven ground,*";
P_HTM[9337]="*atthi tārakarūpāni, atthi tārakarūpānaṃ dassāvī;**stars,*";
P_HTM[9338]="*atthi candimasūriyā, atthi candimasūriyānaṃ dassāvī.**moon and sun, and one who sees these things.*";
P_HTM[9339]="*‘Ahametaṃ na jānāmi, ahametaṃ na passāmi;**So it’s not right to say this: ‘I don’t know it or see it,*";
P_HTM[9340]="*tasmā taṃ natthī’ti;**therefore it doesn’t exist.’”*";
P_HTM[9341]="*na hi so, bho gotama, sammā vadamāno vadeyyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9342]="*“Evameva kho, māṇava, brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti opamañño subhagavaniko andho acakkhuko.**“In the same way, Pokkharasāti is blind and sightless.*";
P_HTM[9343]="*So vata uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ ñassati vā dakkhati vā sacchi vā karissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s not possible for him to know or see or realize a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[9344]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māṇava,**What do you think, student?*";
P_HTM[9345]="*ye te kosalakā brāhmaṇamahāsālā, seyyathidaṃ—**There are well-to-do brahmins of Kosala such as*";
P_HTM[9346]="*caṅkī brāhmaṇo tārukkho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti brāhmaṇo jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo pitā ca te todeyyo, katamā nesaṃ seyyo, yaṃ vā te sammuccā vācaṃ bhāseyyuṃ yaṃ vā asammuccā”ti?**the brahmins Caṅkī, Tārukkha, Pokkharasāti, Jāṇussoṇi, and your father Todeyya. What’s better for them: that their speech agrees or disagrees with accepted usage?”*";
P_HTM[9347]="*“Sammuccā, bho gotama”.**“That it agrees, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[9348]="*“Katamā nesaṃ seyyo, yaṃ vā te mantā vācaṃ bhāseyyuṃ yaṃ vā amantā”ti?**“What’s better for them: that their speech is thoughtful or thoughtless?”*";
P_HTM[9349]="*“Mantā, bho gotama”.**“That it is thoughtful.”*";
P_HTM[9350]="*“Katamā nesaṃ seyyo, yaṃ vā te paṭisaṅkhāya vācaṃ bhāseyyuṃ yaṃ vā appaṭisaṅkhāyā”ti?**“What’s better for them: that their speech follows reflection or is unreflective?”*";
P_HTM[9351]="*“Paṭisaṅkhāya, bho gotama”.**“That it follows reflection.”*";
P_HTM[9352]="*“Katamā nesaṃ seyyo, yaṃ vā te atthasaṃhitaṃ vācaṃ bhāseyyuṃ yaṃ vā anatthasaṃhitan”ti?**“What’s better for them: that their speech is beneficial or worthless?”*";
P_HTM[9353]="*“Atthasaṃhitaṃ, bho gotama”.**“That it’s beneficial.”*";
P_HTM[9354]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māṇava,**“What do you think, student?*";
P_HTM[9355]="*yadi evaṃ sante, brāhmaṇena pokkharasātinā opamaññena subhagavanikena sammuccā vācā bhāsitā asammuccā”ti?**If this is so, does Pokkharasāti’s speech agree or disagree with accepted usage?”*";
P_HTM[9356]="*“Asammuccā, bho gotama”.**“It disagrees, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[9357]="*“Mantā vācā bhāsitā amantā vā”ti?**“Is it thoughtful or thoughtless?”*";
P_HTM[9358]="*“Amantā, bho gotama”.**“Thoughtless.”*";
P_HTM[9359]="*“Paṭisaṅkhāya vācā bhāsitā appaṭisaṅkhāyā”ti?**“Is it reflective or unreflective?”*";
P_HTM[9360]="*“Appaṭisaṅkhāya, bho gotama”.**“Unreflective.”*";
P_HTM[9361]="*“Atthasaṃhitā vācā bhāsitā anatthasaṃhitā”ti?**“Is it beneficial or worthless?”*";
P_HTM[9362]="*“Anatthasaṃhitā, bho gotama”.**“Worthless.”*";
P_HTM[9363]="*“Pañca kho ime, māṇava, nīvaraṇā.**“Student, there are these five hindrances.*";
P_HTM[9364]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[9365]="*Kāmacchandanīvaraṇaṃ, byāpādanīvaraṇaṃ, thinamiddhanīvaraṇaṃ uddhaccakukkuccanīvaraṇaṃ, vicikicchānīvaraṇaṃ—**The hindrances of sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, and doubt.*";
P_HTM[9366]="*ime kho, māṇava, pañca nīvaraṇā.**These are the five hindrances.*";
P_HTM[9367]="*Imehi kho, māṇava, pañcahi nīvaraṇehi brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti opamañño subhagavaniko āvuto nivuto ophuṭo pariyonaddho.**Pokkharasāti is caged, trapped, covered, and engulfed by these five hindrances.*";
P_HTM[9368]="*So vata uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ ñassati vā dakkhati vā sacchi vā karissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s not possible for him to know or see or realize a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[9369]="*Pañca kho ime, māṇava, kāmaguṇā.**There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[9370]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[9371]="*Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā;**There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[9372]="*sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …**There are sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[9373]="*ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …**smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[9374]="*jivhā viññeyyā rasā …**tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[9375]="*kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—**touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[9376]="*ime kho, māṇava, pañca kāmaguṇā.**These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[9377]="*Imehi kho, māṇava, pañcahi kāmaguṇehi brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti opamañño subhagavaniko gathito mucchito ajjhopanno anādīnavadassāvī anissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati.**Pokkharasāti enjoys himself with these five kinds of sensual stimulation, tied, infatuated, attached, blind to the drawbacks, and not understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[9378]="*So vata uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ ñassati vā dakkhati vā sacchi vā karissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s not possible for him to know or see or realize a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[9379]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māṇava,**What do you think, student?*";
P_HTM[9380]="*yaṃ vā tiṇakaṭṭhupādānaṃ paṭicca aggiṃ jāleyya yaṃ vā nissaṭṭhatiṇakaṭṭhupādānaṃ aggiṃ jāleyya, katamo nu khvāssa aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro cā”ti?**Which would have better flames, color, and radiance: a fire that depends on grass and logs as fuel, or one that does not?”*";
P_HTM[9381]="*“Sace taṃ, bho gotama, ṭhānaṃ nissaṭṭhatiṇakaṭṭhupādānaṃ aggiṃ jāletuṃ, svāssa aggi accimā ceva vaṇṇavā ca pabhassaro cā”ti.**“If it were possible for a fire to burn without depending on grass and logs as fuel, that would have better flames, color, and radiance.”*";
P_HTM[9382]="*“Aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, māṇava, anavakāso yaṃ nissaṭṭhatiṇakaṭṭhupādānaṃ aggiṃ jāleyya aññatra iddhimatā.**“But it isn’t possible, except by psychic power.*";
P_HTM[9383]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, tiṇakaṭṭhupādānaṃ paṭicca aggi jalati tathūpamāhaṃ, māṇava, imaṃ pītiṃ vadāmi yāyaṃ pīti pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca.**Rapture that depends on the five kinds of sensual stimulation is like a fire that depends on grass and logs as fuel.*";
P_HTM[9384]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, nissaṭṭhatiṇakaṭṭhupādāno aggi jalati tathūpamāhaṃ, māṇava, imaṃ pītiṃ vadāmi yāyaṃ pīti aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi.**Rapture that’s apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities is like a fire that doesn’t depend on grass and logs as fuel.*";
P_HTM[9385]="*Katamā ca, māṇava, pīti aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi?**And what is rapture that’s apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities?*";
P_HTM[9386]="*Idha, māṇava, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[9387]="*Ayampi kho, māṇava, pīti aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi.**This is rapture that’s apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[9388]="*Puna caparaṃ, māṇava, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[9389]="*Ayampi kho, māṇava, pīti aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehi.**This too is rapture that’s apart from sensual pleasures and unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[9390]="*Ye te, māṇava, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāya, katamettha brāhmaṇā dhammaṃ mahapphalataraṃ paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāyā”ti?**Of the five things that the brahmins prescribe for making merit and succeeding in the skillful, which do they say is the most fruitful?”*";
P_HTM[9391]="*“Yeme, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāya, cāgamettha brāhmaṇā dhammaṃ mahapphalataraṃ paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāyā”ti.**“Generosity.”*";
P_HTM[9392]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māṇava,**“What do you think, student?*";
P_HTM[9393]="*idha aññatarassa brāhmaṇassa mahāyañño paccupaṭṭhito assa.**Suppose a brahmin was setting up a big sacrifice.*";
P_HTM[9394]="*Atha dve brāhmaṇā āgaccheyyuṃ:**Then two brahmins came along,*";
P_HTM[9395]="*‘itthannāmassa brāhmaṇassa mahāyaññaṃ anubhavissāmā’ti.**thinking to participate.*";
P_HTM[9396]="*Tatrekassa brāhmaṇassa evamassa:**Then one of those brahmins thought:*";
P_HTM[9397]="*‘aho vata ahameva labheyyaṃ bhattagge aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍaṃ, na añño brāhmaṇo labheyya bhattagge aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan’ti.**‘Oh, I hope that I alone get the best seat, the best drink, and the best alms-food in the refectory, not some other brahmin.’*";
P_HTM[9398]="*Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, māṇava, vijjati yaṃ añño brāhmaṇo labheyya bhattagge aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍaṃ, na so brāhmaṇo labheyya bhattagge aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍaṃ.**But it’s possible that some other brahmin gets the best seat, the best drink, and the best alms-food in the refectory.*";
P_HTM[9399]="*‘Añño brāhmaṇo labhati bhattagge aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍaṃ, nāhaṃ labhāmi bhattagge aggāsanaṃ aggodakaṃ aggapiṇḍan’ti—**Thinking, ‘Some other brahmin has got the best seat, the best drink, the best alms-food,’*";
P_HTM[9400]="*iti so kupito hoti anattamano.**they get angry and bitter.*";
P_HTM[9401]="*Imassa pana, māṇava, brāhmaṇā kiṃ vipākaṃ paññapentī”ti?**What do the brahmins say is the result of this?”*";
P_HTM[9402]="*“Na khvettha, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā evaṃ dānaṃ denti:**“Master Gotama, brahmins don’t give gifts so that*";
P_HTM[9403]="*‘iminā paro kupito hotu anattamano’ti.**others will get angry and upset.*";
P_HTM[9404]="*Atha khvettha brāhmaṇā anukampājātikaṃyeva dānaṃ dentī”ti.**Rather, they give only out of compassion.”*";
P_HTM[9405]="*“Evaṃ sante kho, māṇava, brāhmaṇānaṃ idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ puññakiriyavatthu hoti—**“In that case, isn’t compassion a sixth ground for making merit?”*";
P_HTM[9406]="*yadidaṃ anukampājātikan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9407]="*“Evaṃ sante, bho gotama, brāhmaṇānaṃ idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ puññakiriyavatthu hoti—**“In that case, compassion is a sixth ground for making merit.”*";
P_HTM[9408]="*yadidaṃ anukampājātikan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9409]="*“Ye te, māṇava, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāya, ime tvaṃ pañca dhamme kattha bahulaṃ samanupassasi—**“Of the five things that the brahmins prescribe for making merit and succeeding in the skillful, where do you usually find them:*";
P_HTM[9410]="*gahaṭṭhesu vā pabbajitesu vā”ti?**among laypeople or renunciates?”*";
P_HTM[9411]="*“Yeme, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāya, imāhaṃ pañca dhamme pabbajitesu bahulaṃ samanupassāmi appaṃ gahaṭṭhesu.**“Mostly among renunciates, and less so among lay people.*";
P_HTM[9412]="*Gahaṭṭho hi, bho gotama, mahaṭṭho mahākicco mahādhikaraṇo mahāsamārambho, na satataṃ samitaṃ saccavādī hoti;**For a lay person has many requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and they can’t always tell the truth,*";
P_HTM[9413]="*pabbajito kho pana, bho gotama, appaṭṭho appakicco appādhikaraṇo appasamārambho, satataṃ samitaṃ saccavādī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9414]="*Gahaṭṭho hi, bho gotama, mahaṭṭho mahākicco mahādhikaraṇo mahāsamārambho na satataṃ samitaṃ tapassī hoti …**practice austerities,*";
P_HTM[9415]="*brahmacārī hoti …**be celibate,*";
P_HTM[9416]="*sajjhāyabahulo hoti …**do lots of recitation,*";
P_HTM[9417]="*cāgabahulo hoti;**or be very generous.*";
P_HTM[9418]="*pabbajito kho pana, bho gotama, appaṭṭho appakicco appādhikaraṇo appasamārambho satataṃ samitaṃ tapassī hoti …**But a renunciate has few requirements, duties, issues, and undertakings, and they can always tell the truth, practice austerities,*";
P_HTM[9419]="*brahmacārī hoti …**be celibate,*";
P_HTM[9420]="*sajjhāyabahulo hoti …**do lots of recitation,*";
P_HTM[9421]="*cāgabahulo hoti.**and be very generous.*";
P_HTM[9422]="*Yeme, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāya, imāhaṃ pañca dhamme pabbajitesu bahulaṃ samanupassāmi appaṃ gahaṭṭhesū”ti.**Of the five things that the brahmins prescribe for making merit and succeeding in the skillful, I usually find them among renunciates, and less so among laypeople.”*";
P_HTM[9423]="*“Ye te, māṇava, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāya cittassāhaṃ ete parikkhāre vadāmi—**“I say that the five things prescribed by the brahmins for making merit are prerequisites of the mind for*";
P_HTM[9424]="*yadidaṃ cittaṃ averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ tassa bhāvanāya.**developing a mind free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[9425]="*Idha, māṇava, bhikkhu saccavādī hoti.**Take a mendicant who speaks the truth.*";
P_HTM[9426]="*So ‘saccavādīmhī’ti labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ.**Thinking, ‘I’m truthful,’ they find joy in the meaning and the teaching, and find joy connected with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[9427]="*Yaṃ taṃ kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ, cittassāhaṃ etaṃ parikkhāraṃ vadāmi—**And I say that joy connected with the skillful is a prerequisite of the mind for*";
P_HTM[9428]="*yadidaṃ cittaṃ averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ tassa bhāvanāya.**developing a mind free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[9429]="*Idha, māṇava, bhikkhu tapassī hoti … pe …**Take a mendicant who practices austerities …*";
P_HTM[9430]="*brahmacārī hoti … pe …**is celibate …*";
P_HTM[9431]="*sajjhāyabahulo hoti … pe …**does lots of recitation …*";
P_HTM[9432]="*cāgabahulo hoti.**and is very generous.*";
P_HTM[9433]="*So ‘cāgabahulomhī’ti labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ.**Thinking, ‘I’m very generous,’ they find joy in the meaning and the teaching, and find joy connected with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[9434]="*Yaṃ taṃ kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ, cittassāhaṃ etaṃ parikkhāraṃ vadāmi—**And I say that joy connected with the skillful is a prerequisite of the mind for*";
P_HTM[9435]="*yadidaṃ cittaṃ averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ tassa bhāvanāya.**developing a mind free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[9436]="*Ye te, māṇava, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāya, cittassāhaṃ ete parikkhāre vadāmi—**I say that these five things prescribed by the brahmins for making merit are prerequisites of the mind for*";
P_HTM[9437]="*yadidaṃ cittaṃ averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ tassa bhāvanāyā”ti.**developing a mind free of enmity and ill will.”*";
P_HTM[9438]="*Evaṃ vutte, subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Subha said to him,*";
P_HTM[9439]="*“sutaṃ metaṃ, bho gotama:**“Master Gotama, I have heard that*";
P_HTM[9440]="*‘samaṇo gotamo brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggaṃ jānātī’”ti.**the ascetic Gotama knows a path to companionship with Brahmā.”*";
P_HTM[9441]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, māṇava,**“What do you think, student?*";
P_HTM[9442]="*āsanne ito naḷakāragāmo, na yito dūre naḷakāragāmo”ti?**Is the village of Naḷakāra nearby?”*";
P_HTM[9443]="*“Evaṃ, bho, āsanne ito naḷakāragāmo, na yito dūre naḷakāragāmo”ti.**“Yes it is, sir.”*";
P_HTM[9444]="*“Taṃ, kiṃ maññasi, māṇava, idhassa puriso naḷakāragāme jātavaddho;**“What do you think, student? Suppose a person was born and raised in Naḷakāra.*";
P_HTM[9445]="*tamenaṃ naḷakāragāmato tāvadeva avasaṭaṃ naḷakāragāmassa maggaṃ puccheyyuṃ;**And as soon as they left the town some people asked them for the road to Naḷakāra.*";
P_HTM[9446]="*siyā nu kho, māṇava, tassa purisassa naḷakāragāme jātavaddhassa naḷakāragāmassa maggaṃ puṭṭhassa dandhāyitattaṃ vā vitthāyitattaṃ vā”ti?**Would they be slow or hesitant to answer?”*";
P_HTM[9447]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[9448]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[9449]="*“Amu hi, bho gotama, puriso naḷakāragāme jātavaddho. Tassa sabbāneva naḷakāragāmassa maggāni suviditānī”ti.**Because they were born and raised in Naḷakāra. They’re well acquainted with all the roads to the village.”*";
P_HTM[9450]="*“Siyā nu kho, māṇava, tassa purisassa naḷakāragāme jātavaddhassa naḷakāragāmassa maggaṃ puṭṭhassa dandhāyitattaṃ vā vitthāyitattaṃ vāti, na tveva tathāgatassa brahmalokaṃ vā brahmalokagāminiṃ vā paṭipadaṃ puṭṭhassa dandhāyitattaṃ vā vitthāyitattaṃ vā.**“Still, it’s possible they might be slow or hesitant to answer. But the Realized One is never slow or hesitant when questioned about the Brahmā realm or the practice that leads to the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[9451]="*Brahmānañcāhaṃ, māṇava, pajānāmi brahmalokañca brahmalokagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ; yathāpaṭipanno ca brahmalokaṃ upapanno tañca pajānāmī”ti.**I understand Brahmā, the Brahmā realm, and the practice that leads to the Brahmā realm, practicing in accordance with which one is reborn in the Brahmā realm.”*";
P_HTM[9452]="*“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bho gotama:**“Master Gotama, I have heard that*";
P_HTM[9453]="*‘samaṇo gotamo brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggaṃ desetī’ti.**the ascetic Gotama teaches a path to companionship with Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[9454]="*Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggaṃ desetū”ti.**Please teach me that path.”*";
P_HTM[9455]="*“Tena hi, māṇava, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, student, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[9456]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Subha.*";
P_HTM[9457]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[9458]="*“Katamo ca, māṇava, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo?**“And what is a path to companionship with Brahmā?*";
P_HTM[9459]="*Idha, māṇava, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**Firstly, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[9460]="*Evaṃ bhāvitāya kho, māṇava, mettāya cetovimuttiyā yaṃ pamāṇakataṃ kammaṃ na taṃ tatrāvasissati, na taṃ tatrāvatiṭṭhati.**When the heart’s release by love has been developed and cultivated like this, any limited deeds they’ve done don’t remain or persist there.*";
P_HTM[9461]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, balavā saṅkhadhamo appakasireneva cātuddisā viññāpeyya;**Suppose there was a powerful horn blower. They’d easily make themselves heard in the four directions.*";
P_HTM[9462]="*evameva kho, māṇava … pe … evaṃ bhāvitāya kho, māṇava, mettāya cetovimuttiyā yaṃ pamāṇakataṃ kammaṃ na taṃ tatrāvasissati, na taṃ tatrāvatiṭṭhati.**In the same way, when the heart’s release by love has been developed and cultivated like this, any limited deeds they’ve done don’t remain or persist there.*";
P_HTM[9463]="*Ayampi kho, māṇava, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo.**This is a path to companionship with Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[9464]="*“Puna caparaṃ, māṇava, bhikkhu karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant meditates spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[9465]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe …**They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[9466]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ; iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyābajjhena pharitvā viharati.**They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[9467]="*Evaṃ bhāvitāya kho, māṇava, upekkhāya cetovimuttiyā yaṃ pamāṇakataṃ kammaṃ na taṃ tatrāvasissati, na taṃ tatrāvatiṭṭhati.**When the heart’s release by equanimity has been developed and cultivated like this, any limited deeds they’ve done don’t remain or persist there.*";
P_HTM[9468]="*Seyyathāpi, māṇava, balavā saṅkhadhamo appakasireneva cātuddisā viññāpeyya;**Suppose there was a powerful horn blower. They’d easily make themselves heard in the four directions.*";
P_HTM[9469]="*evameva kho, māṇava … pe … evaṃ bhāvitāya kho, māṇava, upekkhāya cetovimuttiyā yaṃ pamāṇakataṃ kammaṃ na taṃ tatrāvasissati, na taṃ tatrāvatiṭṭhati.**In the same way, when the heart’s release by equanimity has been developed and cultivated like this, any limited deeds they’ve done don’t remain or persist there.*";
P_HTM[9470]="*Ayampi kho, māṇava, brahmānaṃ sahabyatāya maggo”ti.**This too is a path to companionship with Brahmā.”*";
P_HTM[9471]="*Evaṃ vutte, subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Subha said to him,*";
P_HTM[9472]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[9473]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[9474]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[9475]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.*";
P_HTM[9476]="*Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bho gotama, gacchāma;**Well, now, Master Gotama, I must go.*";
P_HTM[9477]="*bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.**I have many duties, and much to do.”*";
P_HTM[9478]="*“Yassadāni tvaṃ, māṇava, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, student, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[9479]="*Atha kho subho māṇavo todeyyaputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**And then Subha approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[9480]="*Tena kho pana samayena jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo sabbasetena vaḷavābhirathena sāvatthiyā niyyāti divā divassa.**Now at that time the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi drove out from Sāvatthī in the middle of the day in an all-white chariot drawn by mares.*";
P_HTM[9481]="*Addasā kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo subhaṃ māṇavaṃ todeyyaputtaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**He saw the student Subha coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[9482]="*Disvāna subhaṃ māṇavaṃ todeyyaputtaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[9483]="*“handa kuto nu bhavaṃ bhāradvājo āgacchati divā divassā”ti?**“So, Master Bharadvāja, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?”*";
P_HTM[9484]="*“Ito hi kho ahaṃ, bho, āgacchāmi samaṇassa gotamassa santikā”ti.**“Just now, good sir, I’ve come from the presence of the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[9485]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhavaṃ bhāradvājo samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ paṇḍito maññeti”?**“What do you think of the ascetic Gotama’s lucidity of wisdom? Do you think he’s astute?”*";
P_HTM[9486]="*“Ko cāhaṃ, bho, ko ca samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ jānissāmi?**“My good man, who am I to judge the ascetic Gotama’s lucidity of wisdom?*";
P_HTM[9487]="*Sopi nūnassa tādisova yo samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ jāneyyā”ti.**You’d really have to be on the same level to judge his lucidity of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[9488]="*“Uḷārāya khalu bhavaṃ bhāradvājo samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pasaṃsāya pasaṃsatī”ti.**“Master Bharadvāja praises the ascetic Gotama with lofty praise indeed.”*";
P_HTM[9489]="*“Ko cāhaṃ, bho, ko ca samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pasaṃsissāmi?**“Who am I to praise the ascetic Gotama?*";
P_HTM[9490]="*Pasatthapasatthova so bhavaṃ gotamo seṭṭho devamanussānaṃ.**He is praised by the praised as the best of gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[9491]="*Ye cime, bho, brāhmaṇā pañca dhamme paññapenti puññassa kiriyāya kusalassa ārādhanāya;**The five things that the brahmins prescribe for making merit and succeeding in the skillful*";
P_HTM[9492]="*cittassete samaṇo gotamo parikkhāre vadeti—**he says are prerequisites of the mind for*";
P_HTM[9493]="*yadidaṃ cittaṃ averaṃ abyābajjhaṃ tassa bhāvanāyā”ti.**developing a mind free of enmity and ill will.”*";
P_HTM[9494]="*Evaṃ vutte, jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo sabbasetā vaḷavābhirathā orohitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā udānaṃ udānesi:**When he had spoken, Jāṇussoṇi got down from his chariot, arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and was inspired to exclaim three times,*";
P_HTM[9495]="*“lābhā rañño pasenadissa kosalassa, suladdhalābhā rañño pasenadissa kosalassa**“King Pasenadi of Kosala is lucky, so very lucky*";
P_HTM[9496]="*yassa vijite tathāgato viharati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho”ti.**that the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha is living in his realm!”*";
P_HTM[9497]="*Subhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9498]="*100. Saṅgāravasutta**With Saṅgārava*";
P_HTM[9499]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[9500]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[9501]="*Tena kho pana samayena dhanañjānī nāma brāhmaṇī cañcalikappe paṭivasati abhippasannā buddhe ca dhamme ca saṃghe ca.**Now at that time a brahmin lady named Dhanañjānī was residing at Caṇḍalakappa. She was devoted to the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[9502]="*Atha kho dhanañjānī brāhmaṇī upakkhalitvā tikkhattuṃ udānaṃ udānesi:**Once, she tripped and was inspired to exclaim three times:*";
P_HTM[9503]="*“Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**“Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[9504]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[9505]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassā”ti.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!”*";
P_HTM[9506]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅgāravo nāma māṇavo cañcalikappe paṭivasati tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo.**Now at that time the brahmin student Saṅgārava was residing in Caṇḍalakappa. He was young, newly tonsured; he was sixteen years old. He had mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. He knew philology and grammar, and was well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man.*";
P_HTM[9507]="*Assosi kho saṅgāravo māṇavo dhanañjāniyā brāhmaṇiyā evaṃ vācaṃ bhāsamānāya.**Hearing Dhanañjānī’s exclamation,*";
P_HTM[9508]="*Sutvā dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇiṃ etadavoca:**he said to her,*";
P_HTM[9509]="*“avabhūtāva ayaṃ dhanañjānī brāhmaṇī, parabhūtāva ayaṃ dhanañjānī brāhmaṇī, vijjamānānaṃ tevijjānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ, atha ca pana tassa muṇḍakassa samaṇakassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissatī”ti.**“The brahmin lady named Dhanañjānī is a disgrace! Though brahmins who are proficient in the three Vedas are found, she praises that shaveling, that fake ascetic.”*";
P_HTM[9510]="*“Na hi pana tvaṃ, tāta bhadramukha, tassa bhagavato sīlapaññāṇaṃ jānāsi.**“But my little dear, you don’t understand the Buddha’s ethics and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[9511]="*Sace tvaṃ, tāta bhadramukha, tassa bhagavato sīlapaññāṇaṃ jāneyyāsi, na tvaṃ, tāta bhadramukha, taṃ bhagavantaṃ akkositabbaṃ paribhāsitabbaṃ maññeyyāsī”ti.**If you did, you’d never think of abusing or insulting him.”*";
P_HTM[9512]="*“Tena hi, bhoti, yadā samaṇo gotamo cañcalikappaṃ anuppatto hoti atha me āroceyyāsī”ti.**“Well then, ma’am, let me know when the Buddha arrives in Caṇḍalakappa.”*";
P_HTM[9513]="*“Evaṃ, bhadramukhā”ti kho dhanañjānī brāhmaṇī saṅgāravassa māṇavassa paccassosi.**“I will, dear,” she replied.*";
P_HTM[9514]="*Atha kho bhagavā kosalesu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena cañcalikappaṃ tadavasari.**And then the Buddha, traveling stage by stage in the Kosalan lands, arrived at Caṇḍalakappa,*";
P_HTM[9515]="*Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā cañcalikappe viharati todeyyānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ ambavane.**where he stayed in the mango grove of the Todeyya brahmins.*";
P_HTM[9516]="*Assosi kho dhanañjānī brāhmaṇī: “bhagavā kira cañcalikappaṃ anuppatto, cañcalikappe viharati todeyyānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ ambavane”ti.**Dhanañjānī heard that he had arrived.*";
P_HTM[9517]="*Atha kho dhanañjānī brāhmaṇī yena saṅgāravo māṇavo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā saṅgāravaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavoca:**So she went to Saṅgārava and told him, adding,*";
P_HTM[9518]="*“ayaṃ, tāta bhadramukha, so bhagavā cañcalikappaṃ anuppatto, cañcalikappe viharati todeyyānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ ambavane.* **";
P_HTM[9519]="*Yassadāni, tāta bhadramukha, kālaṃ maññasī”ti.**“Please, my little dear, go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[9520]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho saṅgāravo māṇavo dhanañjāniyā brāhmaṇiyā paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**“Yes, ma’am,” replied Saṅgārava. He went to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[9521]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saṅgāravo māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[9522]="*“Santi kho, bho gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammābhiññāvosānapāramippattā, ādibrahmacariyaṃ paṭijānanti.**“Master Gotama, there are some ascetics and brahmins who claim to have mastered the fundamentals of the spiritual life having attained perfection and consummation of insight in the present life.*";
P_HTM[9523]="*Tatra, bho gotama, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammābhiññāvosānapāramippattā, ādibrahmacariyaṃ paṭijānanti, tesaṃ bhavaṃ gotamo katamo”ti?**Where do you stand regarding these?”*";
P_HTM[9524]="*“Diṭṭhadhammābhiññāvosānapāramippattānaṃ, ādibrahmacariyaṃ paṭijānantānampi kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, vemattaṃ vadāmi.**“I say there is a diversity among those who claim to have mastered the fundamentals of the spiritual life having attained perfection and consummation of insight in the present life.*";
P_HTM[9525]="*Santi, bhāradvāja, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā anussavikā.**There are some ascetics and brahmins who are oral transmitters.*";
P_HTM[9526]="*Te anussavena diṭṭhadhammābhiññāvosānapāramippattā, ādibrahmacariyaṃ paṭijānanti;**Through oral transmission they claim to have mastered the fundamentals of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[9527]="*seyyathāpi brāhmaṇā tevijjā.**For example, the brahmins who are proficient in the three Vedas.*";
P_HTM[9528]="*Santi pana, bhāradvāja, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena diṭṭhadhammābhiññāvosānapāramippattā, ādibrahmacariyaṃ paṭijānanti;**There are some ascetics and brahmins who solely by mere faith claim to have mastered the fundamentals of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[9529]="*seyyathāpi takkī vīmaṃsī.**For example, those who rely on logic and inquiry.*";
P_HTM[9530]="*Santi, bhāradvāja, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbe ananussutesu dhammesu sāmaṃyeva dhammaṃ abhiññāya diṭṭhadhammābhiññāvosānapāramippattā, ādibrahmacariyaṃ paṭijānanti.**There are some ascetics and brahmins who, having directly known for themselves the principle regarding teachings not learned before from another, claim to have mastered the fundamentals of the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[9531]="*Tatra, bhāradvāja, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbe ananussutesu dhammesu sāmaṃyeva dhammaṃ abhiññāya diṭṭhadhammābhiññāvosānapāramippattā, ādibrahmacariyaṃ paṭijānanti, tesāhamasmi.**I am one of those.*";
P_HTM[9532]="*Tadamināpetaṃ, bhāradvāja, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ, yathā ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbe ananussutesu dhammesu sāmaṃyeva dhammaṃ abhiññāya diṭṭhadhammābhiññāvosānapāramippattā, ādibrahmacariyaṃ paṭijānanti, tesāhamasmi.**And here’s a way to understand that I am one of them.*";
P_HTM[9533]="*Idha me, bhāradvāja, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi:**Before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought:*";
P_HTM[9534]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[9535]="*Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[9536]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[9537]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, aparena samayena daharova samāno susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃ.**Some time later, while still black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life—though my mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful faces—I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[9538]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kiṅkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**Once I had gone forth I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[9539]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso kālāma, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti.**‘Reverend Kālāma, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[9540]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhāradvāja, āḷāro kālāmo maṃ etadavoca:**Āḷāra Kālāma replied,*";
P_HTM[9541]="*‘viharatāyasmā.**‘Stay, venerable.*";
P_HTM[9542]="*Tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti.**This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own teacher’s doctrine with their own insight and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[9543]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ.**I quickly memorized that teaching.*";
P_HTM[9544]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ‘ñāṇavādañca vadāmi, theravādañca jānāmi, passāmī’ti ca paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca.**So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others.*";
P_HTM[9545]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9546]="*‘na kho āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti;**‘It is not solely by mere faith that Āḷāra Kālāma declares: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”*";
P_HTM[9547]="*addhā āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharatī’ti.**Surely he meditates knowing and seeing this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[9548]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhāradvāja, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him:*";
P_HTM[9549]="*‘kittāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend Kālāma, to what extent do you say you’ve realized this teaching with your own insight?’*";
P_HTM[9550]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhāradvāja, āḷāro kālāmo ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi.**When I said this, he declared the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[9551]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9552]="*‘na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;**‘It’s not just Āḷāra Kālāma who has faith,*";
P_HTM[9553]="*na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi vīriyaṃ … pe …**energy,*";
P_HTM[9554]="*sati …**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[9555]="*samādhi …**immersion,*";
P_HTM[9556]="*paññā, mayhampatthi paññā.**and wisdom; I too have these things.*";
P_HTM[9557]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ āḷāro kālāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Āḷāra Kālāma says he has realized with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[9558]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[9559]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhāradvāja, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him,*";
P_HTM[9560]="*‘ettāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend Kālāma, have you realized this teaching with your own insight up to this point, and declare having achieved it?’*";
P_HTM[9561]="*‘Ettāvatā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemī’ti.**‘I have, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[9562]="*‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti.**‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[9563]="*‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso,**‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[9564]="*ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma.**to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[9565]="*Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi;**So the teaching that I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it, you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[9566]="*yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi tamahaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi.**The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[9567]="*Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi, yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi tamahaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi.**So the teaching that I know, you know, and the teaching you know, I know.*";
P_HTM[9568]="*Iti yādiso ahaṃ tādiso tuvaṃ, yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso ahaṃ.**I am like you and you are like me.*";
P_HTM[9569]="*Ehi dāni, āvuso, ubhova santā imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharāmā’ti.**Come now, reverend! We should both lead this community together.’*";
P_HTM[9570]="*Iti kho, bhāradvāja, āḷāro kālāmo ācariyo me samāno attano antevāsiṃ maṃ samānaṃ attanā samasamaṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi.**And that is how my teacher Āḷāra Kālāma placed me, his student, on the same position as him, and honored me with lofty praise.*";
P_HTM[9571]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9572]="*‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva ākiñcaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti.**‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of nothingness.’*";
P_HTM[9573]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ.**Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed.*";
P_HTM[9574]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[9575]="*‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti.**‘Reverend, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’*";
P_HTM[9576]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhāradvāja, udako rāmaputto maṃ etadavoca:**Uddaka replied,*";
P_HTM[9577]="*‘viharatāyasmā.**‘Stay, venerable.*";
P_HTM[9578]="*Tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti.**This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own teacher’s doctrine with their own insight and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[9579]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ.**I quickly memorized that teaching.*";
P_HTM[9580]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ‘ñāṇavādañca vadāmi, theravādañca jānāmi, passāmī’ti ca paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca.**So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others.*";
P_HTM[9581]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9582]="*‘na kho rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi;**‘It is not solely by mere faith that Rāma declared: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.”*";
P_HTM[9583]="*addhā rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ vihāsī’ti.**Surely he meditated knowing and seeing this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[9584]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhāradvāja, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[9585]="*‘kittāvatā no, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend, to what extent did Rāma say he’d realized this teaching with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[9586]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhāradvāja, udako rāmaputto nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi.**When I said this, Uddaka, son of Rāma, declared the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[9587]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9588]="*‘na kho rāmasseva ahosi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā;**‘It’s not just Rāma who had faith,*";
P_HTM[9589]="*na kho rāmasseva ahosi vīriyaṃ … pe …**energy,*";
P_HTM[9590]="*sati …**mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[9591]="*samādhi …**immersion,*";
P_HTM[9592]="*paññā, mayhampatthi paññā.**and wisdom; I too have these things.*";
P_HTM[9593]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti.**Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Rāma said he had realized with his own insight?’*";
P_HTM[9594]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[9595]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, bhāradvāja, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[9596]="*‘ettāvatā no, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti?**‘Reverend, had Rāma realized this teaching with his own insight up to this point, and declared having achieved it?’*";
P_HTM[9597]="*‘Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti.**‘He had, reverend.’*";
P_HTM[9598]="*‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti.**‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’*";
P_HTM[9599]="*‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso,**‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate*";
P_HTM[9600]="*ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma.**to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[9601]="*Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi;**So the teaching that Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it, you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[9602]="*yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi.**The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it.*";
P_HTM[9603]="*Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi, yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi.**So the teaching that Rāma directly knew, you know, and the teaching you know, Rāma directly knew.*";
P_HTM[9604]="*Iti yādiso rāmo ahosi tādiso tuvaṃ, yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso rāmo ahosi.**Rāma was like you and you are like Rāma.*";
P_HTM[9605]="*Ehi dāni, āvuso, tuvaṃ imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharā’ti.**Come now, reverend! You should lead this community.’*";
P_HTM[9606]="*Iti kho, bhāradvāja, udako rāmaputto sabrahmacārī me samāno ācariyaṭṭhāne maṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi.**And that is how my spiritual companion Uddaka, son of Rāma, placed me in the position of a teacher, and honored me with lofty praise.*";
P_HTM[9607]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9608]="*‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti.**‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’*";
P_HTM[9609]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ.**Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed.*";
P_HTM[9610]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, kiṅkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno magadhesu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena uruvelā senānigamo tadavasariṃ.**I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. Traveling stage by stage in the Magadhan lands, I arrived at Senanigama near Uruvelā.*";
P_HTM[9611]="*Tatthaddasaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ bhūmibhāgaṃ, pāsādikañca vanasaṇḍaṃ, nadiñca sandantiṃ setakaṃ supatitthaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ, samantā ca gocaragāmaṃ.**There I saw a delightful park, a lovely grove with a flowing river that was clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby was a village to go for alms.*";
P_HTM[9612]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9613]="*‘ramaṇīyo vata bho bhūmibhāgo, pāsādiko ca vanasaṇḍo, nadī ca sandati setakā supatitthā ramaṇīyā, samantā ca gocaragāmo.**‘This park is truly delightful, a lovely grove with a flowing river that’s clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby there’s a village to go for alms.*";
P_HTM[9614]="*Alaṃ vatidaṃ kulaputtassa padhānatthikassa padhānāyā’ti.**This is good enough for a gentleman who wishes to put forth effort in meditation.’*";
P_HTM[9615]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, tattheva nisīdiṃ:**So I sat down right there, thinking:*";
P_HTM[9616]="*‘alamidaṃ padhānāyā’ti.**‘This is good enough for meditation.’*";
P_HTM[9617]="*Apissu maṃ, bhāradvāja, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**And then these three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[9618]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ udake nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a green, sappy log, and it was lying in water.*";
P_HTM[9619]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[9620]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[9621]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhāradvāja,**What do you think, Bhāradvāja?*";
P_HTM[9622]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ udake nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that green, sappy log lying in water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[9623]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[9624]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[9625]="*Aduñhi, bho gotama, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ, tañca pana udake nikkhittaṃ;**Because it’s a green, sappy log, and it’s lying in the water.*";
P_HTM[9626]="*yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[9627]="*“Evameva kho, bhāradvāja, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi avūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ na suppahīno hoti na suppaṭippassaddho, opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who don’t live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. They haven’t internally given up or stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion, they are incapable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[9628]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, bhāradvāja, paṭhamā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**This was the first example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[9629]="*Aparāpi kho maṃ, bhāradvāja, dutiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**Then a second example occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[9630]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a green, sappy log, and it was lying on dry land far from the water.*";
P_HTM[9631]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[9632]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[9633]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhāradvāja,**What do you think, Bhāradvāja?*";
P_HTM[9634]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that green, sappy log on dry land far from water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[9635]="*“No hidaṃ, bho gotama.**“No, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[9636]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[9637]="*Aduñhi, bho gotama, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ, kiñcāpi ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ;**Because it’s still a green, sappy log, despite the fact that it’s lying on dry land far from water.*";
P_HTM[9638]="*yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti. “Evameva kho, bhāradvāja, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi vūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ na suppahīno hoti na suppaṭippassaddho, opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.” “In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. But they haven’t internally given up or stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion, they are incapable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[9639]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, bhāradvāja, dutiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**This was the second example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[9640]="*Aparāpi kho maṃ, bhāradvāja, tatiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**Then a third example occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[9641]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ.**Suppose there was a dried up, withered log, and it was lying on dry land far from the water.*";
P_HTM[9642]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya:**Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking*";
P_HTM[9643]="*‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti.**to light a fire and produce heat.*";
P_HTM[9644]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhāradvāja,**What do you think, Bhāradvāja?*";
P_HTM[9645]="*api nu so puriso amuṃ sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti?**By drilling the stick against that dried up, withered log on dry land far from water, could they light a fire and produce heat?”*";
P_HTM[9646]="*“Evaṃ, bho gotama.**“Yes, Master Gotama.*";
P_HTM[9647]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[9648]="*Aduñhi, bho gotama, sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ, tañca pana ārakā udakā thale nikkhittan”ti.**Because it’s a dried up, withered log, and it’s lying on dry land far from water.”*";
P_HTM[9649]="*“Evameva kho, bhāradvāja, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi vūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ suppahīno hoti suppaṭippassaddho, opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, bhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, bhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya.**“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. And they have internally given up and stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion, they are capable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening.*";
P_HTM[9650]="*Ayaṃ kho maṃ, bhāradvāja, tatiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**This was the third example that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[9651]="*Imā kho maṃ, bhāradvāja, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā.**These are the three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, that occurred to me.*";
P_HTM[9652]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9653]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇheyyaṃ abhinippīḷeyyaṃ abhisantāpeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I, with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of my mouth, squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind.’*";
P_HTM[9654]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhāmi abhinippīḷemi abhisantāpemi.**So that’s what I did,*";
P_HTM[9655]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato kacchehi sedā muccanti.**until sweat ran from my armpits.*";
P_HTM[9656]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, balavā puriso dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ sīse vā gahetvā khandhe vā gahetvā abhiniggaṇheyya abhinippīḷeyya abhisantāpeyya;**It was like when a strong man grabs a weaker man by the head or throat or shoulder and squeezes, squashes, and tortures them.*";
P_HTM[9657]="*evameva kho me, bhāradvāja, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato kacchehi sedā muccanti.**In the same way, with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of my mouth, I squeezed, squashed, and tortured mind with mind until sweat ran from my armpits.*";
P_HTM[9658]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, bhāradvāja, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā; sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[9659]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9660]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I practice the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[9661]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose.*";
P_HTM[9662]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu kaṇṇasotehi vātānaṃ nikkhamantānaṃ adhimatto saddo hoti.**But then winds came out my ears making a loud noise,*";
P_HTM[9663]="*Seyyathāpi nāma kammāragaggariyā dhamamānāya adhimatto saddo hoti;**like the puffing of a blacksmith’s bellows.*";
P_HTM[9664]="*evameva kho me, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu kaṇṇasotehi vātānaṃ nikkhamantānaṃ adhimatto saddo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9665]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, bhāradvāja, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā; sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[9666]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9667]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[9668]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose.*";
P_HTM[9669]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā muddhani ūhananti.**But then strong winds ground my head,*";
P_HTM[9670]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, balavā puriso, tiṇhena sikharena muddhani abhimattheyya;**like a strong man was drilling into my head with a sharp point.*";
P_HTM[9671]="*evameva kho me, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā muddhani ūhananti.* **";
P_HTM[9672]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, bhāradvāja, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā; sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[9673]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9674]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[9675]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose.*";
P_HTM[9676]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā honti.**But then I got a severe headache,*";
P_HTM[9677]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, balavā puriso daḷhena varattakkhaṇḍena sīse sīsaveṭhaṃ dadeyya;**like a strong man was tightening a tough leather strap around my head.*";
P_HTM[9678]="*evameva kho, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā sīse sīsavedanā honti.* **";
P_HTM[9679]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, bhāradvāja, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā; sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[9680]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9681]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[9682]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose.*";
P_HTM[9683]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti.**But then strong winds carved up my belly,*";
P_HTM[9684]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā tiṇhena govikantanena kucchiṃ parikanteyya;**like a deft butcher or their apprentice was slicing my belly open with a meat cleaver.*";
P_HTM[9685]="*evameva kho me, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimattā vātā kucchiṃ parikantanti.* **";
P_HTM[9686]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, bhāradvāja, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā; sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[9687]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9688]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I keep practicing the breathless absorption?’*";
P_HTM[9689]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ.**So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose.*";
P_HTM[9690]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho hoti.**But then there was an intense burning in my body,*";
P_HTM[9691]="*Seyyathāpi, bhāradvāja, dve balavanto purisā dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ nānābāhāsu gahetvā aṅgārakāsuyā santāpeyyuṃ samparitāpeyyuṃ;**like two strong men grabbing a weaker man by the arms to burn and scorch him on a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[9692]="*evameva kho me, bhāradvāja, mukhato ca nāsato ca kaṇṇato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu adhimatto kāyasmiṃ ḍāho hoti.* **";
P_HTM[9693]="*Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, bhāradvāja, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato.**My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving.*";
P_HTM[9694]="*Apissu maṃ, bhāradvāja, devatā disvā evamāhaṃsu:**Then some deities saw me and said,*";
P_HTM[9695]="*‘kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama is dead.’*";
P_HTM[9696]="*Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:**Others said,*";
P_HTM[9697]="*‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, api ca kālaṃ karotī’ti.**‘He’s not dead, but he’s dying.’*";
P_HTM[9698]="*Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:**Others said,*";
P_HTM[9699]="*‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, nāpi kālaṃ karoti;**‘He’s not dead or dying. The ascetic Gotama is a perfected one, for that is how the perfected ones live.’*";
P_HTM[9700]="*arahaṃ samaṇo gotamo, vihāro tveva so arahato evarūpo hotī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9701]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9702]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjeyyan’ti.**‘Why don’t I practice completely cutting off food?’*";
P_HTM[9703]="*Atha kho maṃ, bhāradvāja, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:**But deities came to me and said,*";
P_HTM[9704]="*‘mā kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajji.**‘Good sir, don’t practice totally cutting off food.*";
P_HTM[9705]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjissasi, tassa te mayaṃ dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāressāma.**If you do, we’ll infuse divine nectar into your pores and you will live on that.’*";
P_HTM[9706]="*Tāya tvaṃ yāpessasī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9707]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9708]="*‘ahañceva kho pana sabbaso ajajjitaṃ paṭijāneyyaṃ, imā ca me devatā dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāreyyuṃ, tāya cāhaṃ yāpeyyaṃ.**‘If I claim to be completely fasting while these deities are infusing divine nectar in my pores, that would be a lie on my part.’*";
P_HTM[9709]="*Taṃ mamassa musā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9710]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, tā devatā paccācikkhāmi, ‘halan’ti vadāmi.**So I dismissed those deities, saying, ‘There’s no need.’*";
P_HTM[9711]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9712]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā hareṇukayūsan’ti.**‘Why don’t I just take a little bit of food each time, a cup of broth made from mung beans, lentils, chickpeas, or green gram.’*";
P_HTM[9713]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā hareṇukayūsaṃ.**So that’s what I did,*";
P_HTM[9714]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā hareṇukayūsaṃ, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti.**until my body became extremely emaciated.*";
P_HTM[9715]="*Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, my limbs became like the joints of an eighty-year-old or a corpse,*";
P_HTM[9716]="*Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya;**my bottom became like a camel’s hoof,*";
P_HTM[9717]="*seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako uṇṇatāvanato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**my vertebrae stuck out like beads on a string,*";
P_HTM[9718]="*Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**and my ribs were as gaunt as the broken-down rafters on an old barn.*";
P_HTM[9719]="*Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti; evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, the gleam of my eyes sank deep in their sockets, like the gleam of water sunk deep down a well.*";
P_HTM[9720]="*Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, my scalp shriveled and withered like a green bitter-gourd in the wind and sun.*";
P_HTM[9721]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, ‘udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmī’ti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, ‘piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmī’ti udaracchaviṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi; yāvassu me, bhāradvāja, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, the skin of my belly stuck to my backbone, so that when I tried to rub the skin of my belly I grabbed my backbone, and when I tried to rub my backbone I rubbed the skin of my belly.*";
P_HTM[9722]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, ‘vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmī’ti tattheva avakujjo papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to urinate or defecate I fell face down right there.*";
P_HTM[9723]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, imameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anumajjāmi. Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, pāṇinā gattāni anumajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni kāyasmā papatanti tāyevappāhāratāya.**Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out.*";
P_HTM[9724]="*Apissu maṃ, bhāradvāja, manussā disvā evamāhaṃsu: ‘kāḷo samaṇo gotamo’ti.**Then some people saw me and said: ‘The ascetic Gotama is black.’*";
P_HTM[9725]="*Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, sāmo samaṇo gotamo’ti.**Some said: ‘He’s not black, he’s brown.’*";
P_HTM[9726]="*Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo napi sāmo, maṅguracchavi samaṇo gotamo’ti;**Some said: ‘He’s neither black nor brown. The ascetic Gotama has tawny skin.’*";
P_HTM[9727]="*yāvassu me, bhāradvāja, tāva parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto upahato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya.**That’s how far the pure, bright complexion of my skin had been ruined by taking so little food.*";
P_HTM[9728]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9729]="*‘ye kho keci atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayiṃsu, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo;**‘Whatever ascetics and brahmins have experienced painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion—whether in the past, future, or present—this is as far as it goes, no-one has done more than this.*";
P_HTM[9730]="*yepi hi keci anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayissanti, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo;* **";
P_HTM[9731]="*yepi hi keci etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo.* **";
P_HTM[9732]="*Na kho panāhaṃ imāya kaṭukāya dukkarakārikāya adhigacchāmi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ.**But I have not achieved any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones by this severe, grueling work.*";
P_HTM[9733]="*Siyā nu kho añño maggo bodhāyā’ti?**Could there be another path to awakening?’*";
P_HTM[9734]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9735]="*‘abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ pitu sakkassa kammante sītāya jambucchāyāya nisinno vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharitā.**‘I recall sitting in the cool shade of the rose-apple tree while my father the Sakyan was off working. Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[9736]="*Siyā nu kho eso maggo bodhāyā’ti?**Could that be the path to awakening?’*";
P_HTM[9737]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, satānusāri viññāṇaṃ ahosi:**Stemming from that memory came the realization:*";
P_HTM[9738]="*‘eseva maggo bodhāyā’ti.**‘That is the path to awakening!’*";
P_HTM[9739]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9740]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti?**‘Why am I afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual pleasures or unskillful qualities?’*";
P_HTM[9741]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**I thought,*";
P_HTM[9742]="*‘na kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti.**‘I’m not afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual pleasures or unskillful qualities.’*";
P_HTM[9743]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me,*";
P_HTM[9744]="*‘na kho taṃ sukaraṃ sukhaṃ adhigantuṃ evaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyena.**‘I can’t achieve that pleasure with a body so excessively emaciated. Why don’t I eat some solid food, some rice and porridge?’*";
P_HTM[9745]="*Yannūnāhaṃ oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ odanakummāsan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9746]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ.**So I ate some solid food.*";
P_HTM[9747]="*Tena kho pana maṃ, bhāradvāja, samayena pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū paccupaṭṭhitā honti:**Now at that time the five mendicants were attending on me, thinking,*";
P_HTM[9748]="*‘yaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ adhigamissati taṃ no ārocessatī’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama will tell us of any truth that he realizes.’*";
P_HTM[9749]="*Yato kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ, atha me te pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū nibbijja pakkamiṃsu:**But when I ate some solid food, they left disappointed in me, saying,*";
P_HTM[9750]="*‘bāhulliko samaṇo gotamo padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāyā’ti.**‘The ascetic Gotama has become indulgent; he has strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence.’*";
P_HTM[9751]="*So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāretvā balaṃ gahetvā vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**After eating solid food and gathering my strength, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[9752]="*Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I entered and remained in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[9753]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**third absorption …*";
P_HTM[9754]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ.**fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[9755]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward recollection of past lives.*";
P_HTM[9756]="*So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi.**I recollected many past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. And so I recollected my many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[9757]="*Ayaṃ kho me, bhāradvāja, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā vijjā adhigatā,**This was the first knowledge, which I achieved in the first watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[9758]="*avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[9759]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings.*";
P_HTM[9760]="*So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi … pe …**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understood how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds …*";
P_HTM[9761]="*ayaṃ kho me, bhāradvāja, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā**This was the second knowledge, which I achieved in the middle watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[9762]="*vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[9763]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ.**When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[9764]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;**I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’.*";
P_HTM[9765]="*‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ.**I truly understood: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’.*";
P_HTM[9766]="*Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha.**Knowing and seeing like this, my mind was freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.*";
P_HTM[9767]="*Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ ahosi.**When it was freed, I knew it was freed.*";
P_HTM[9768]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti abbhaññāsiṃ.**I understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[9769]="*Ayaṃ kho me, bhāradvāja, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā**This was the third knowledge, which I achieved in the last watch of the night.*";
P_HTM[9770]="*vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato”ti.**Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.”*";
P_HTM[9771]="*Evaṃ vutte, saṅgāravo māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Saṅgārava said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[9772]="*“aṭṭhitavataṃ bhoto gotamassa padhānaṃ ahosi, sappurisavataṃ bhoto gotamassa padhānaṃ ahosi;**“Master Gotama’s effort was steadfast and appropriate for a good person,*";
P_HTM[9773]="*yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**since he is a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[9774]="*Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, atthi devā”ti?**But Master Gotama, do gods absolutely exist?”*";
P_HTM[9775]="*“Ṭhānaso metaṃ, bhāradvāja, viditaṃ yadidaṃ—**“I’ve understood the existence of gods in terms of causes.”*";
P_HTM[9776]="*adhidevā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9777]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, ‘atthi devā’ti puṭṭho samāno ‘ṭhānaso metaṃ, bhāradvāja, viditaṃ yadidaṃ adhidevā’ti vadesi.**“But Master Gotama, when asked ‘Do gods exist?’ why did you say that you have understood the existence of gods in terms of causes?*";
P_HTM[9778]="*Nanu, bho gotama, evaṃ sante tucchā musā hotī”ti?**If that’s the case, isn’t it a hollow lie?”*";
P_HTM[9779]="*“‘Atthi devā’ti, bhāradvāja, puṭṭho samāno ‘atthi devā’ti yo vadeyya, ‘ṭhānaso me viditā’ti yo vadeyya;**“When asked ‘Do gods exist’, whether you reply ‘Gods exist’ or ‘I’ve understood it in terms of causes’*";
P_HTM[9780]="*atha khvettha viññunā purisena ekaṃsena niṭṭhaṃ gantabbaṃ yadidaṃ:**a sensible person would come to the definite conclusion that*";
P_HTM[9781]="*‘atthi devā’”ti.**gods exist.”*";
P_HTM[9782]="*“Kissa pana me bhavaṃ gotamo ādikeneva na byākāsī”ti?**“But why didn’t you say that in the first place?”*";
P_HTM[9783]="*“Uccena sammataṃ kho etaṃ, bhāradvāja, lokasmiṃ yadidaṃ:**“It’s widely agreed in the world that*";
P_HTM[9784]="*‘atthi devā’”ti.**gods exist.”*";
P_HTM[9785]="*Evaṃ vutte, saṅgāravo māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he had spoken, Saṅgārava said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[9786]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[9787]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the Teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[9788]="*Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[9789]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[9790]="*Saṅgāravasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[9791]="*Brāhmaṇavaggo niṭṭhito pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[9792]="*Brahmāyu selassalāyano,* **";
P_HTM[9793]="*ghoṭamukho ca brāhmaṇo;* **";
P_HTM[9794]="*Caṅkī esu dhanañjāni,* **";
P_HTM[9795]="*vāseṭṭho subhagāravoti.* **";
P_HTM[9796]="*Vaggo gahapati bhikkhu,* **";
P_HTM[9797]="*paribbājakanāmako;* **";
P_HTM[9798]="*Rājavaggo brāhmaṇoti,* **";
P_HTM[9799]="*pañca majjhimaāgame.* **";
P_HTM[9800]="*Majjhimapaṇṇāsakaṃ samattaṃ.* **";
